{"id":1,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/1/","title":"Booked Up 2010","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30370/takeshita-demons-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30370","title":"Takeshita Demons","author":"by Cristy Burne","description":"When Miku moved to England from Japan, she never imagined that evil spirits would follow her. But one day an unusual looking supply teacher appears at school, and Miku suspects she may be a demon in disguise.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30372/z-rex-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30372","title":"Z.Rex","author":"by Steve Cole","description":"A novel that combines dinosaurs and fantasy, and has deeper and darker undertones for those who read it more closely.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30316/the-dying-photo-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30316","title":"The Dying Photo","author":"by Alan Gibbons","description":"Jimmy is Christmas shopping with his parents, when a mysterious stranger offers to take their photograph. In a flash, his Mum and Dad have disappeared and all that is left is a photo of them screaming."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30375/invisiblecity.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30375","title":"The Joshua Files: Invisible City","author":"by M G Harris","description":"Josh Garcia is an ordinary teenager living in Oxford, until his archaeologist father's plane disappears in Mexico.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30374/at-the-sign-of-the-sugared-plum-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30374","title":"At the Sign of the Sugared Plum","author":"by Mary Hooper","description":"It is 1665 and Hannah, the spirited heroine, is thrilled at the chance to visit London to help her sister in her sweetmeats shop, The Sugared Plum.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30376/love-aubrey-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30376","title":"Love, Aubrey","author":"by Suzanne LaFleur","description":"At the outset we meet 11-year-old Aubrey… living alone. Aubrey is the survivor of a car crash that has killed her sister and father – and now her mother has abandoned her."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30377/talesofterror.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30377","title":"Uncle Montague's Tales of Terror","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"These spine-tingling stories-within-a-story are the stuff of childhood nightmares, with a good smattering of ghosts, demons, blood and gore.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30378/fever-crumb-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30378","title":"Fever Crumb","author":"by Philip Reeve","description":"In a teasingly recognisable London threatened by northern invaders, orphan Engineer, Fever Crumb, is assigned to help renegade archaeologist Kit Solent.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30379/michael-rosen-s-a-z-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30379","title":"Michael Rosen's A to Z","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":"Former Children’s Laureate, Michael Rosen, gathers together the best children’s poetry from Agard to Zephaniah in this collection. From Grace Nichol's poem about her Caribbean Gran visiting England to Rosen's own hilarious account of his Dad's intolerance to 'The Noise',...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30380/wombats-bum-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30380","title":"How to Avoid a Wombat's Bum","author":"by Mitchell Symons","description":"Have you ever wondered how long it would take to walk to the sun (about 2,000 years, if you didn’t burn to a crisp!)? And did you know that a snail has 25,000 teeth?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30381/the-lost-thing-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30381","title":"The Lost Thing","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"A version of this unique book was the winner of Best Animated Short Film at the 2011 Oscars. A boy is out walking on the beach, when he spots a weird looking thing - it looks lost. The boy asks..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30382/crowfield-curse-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30382","title":"The Crowfield Curse","author":"by Pat Walsh","description":"Will finds a small creature caught in a trap in the woods; a hob. The discovery of this magical creature signals the beginning of an incredible adventure for Will. A more challenging read that really fires the imagination."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30384/me-and-my-cat-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30384","title":"Me and My Cat?","author":"by Satoshi Kitamura","description":"A witch casts a spell on Nicholas and he wakes up to discover he has turned into Leonardo, his pet cat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30387/calmdownboris.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30387","title":"Calm Down, Boris!","author":"by Sam Lloyd","description":"This interactive book comes complete with a Boris puppet making it perfect for sharing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30383/boffin-boy-ninja-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30383","title":"Boffin Boy and the Forest of the Ninja","author":"by David Orme","description":"This graphic novel style book is a quick read and perfect for those who don’t like too much text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30386/stone-soup-new.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30386","title":"Stone Soup","author":"by Jess Stockham","description":"This beautiful picture book retells the traditional story, complete with ‘flip-up’ flaps which encourage prediction, involvement and discussion.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"}]}
{"id":4,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/4/","title":"Booked Up 2009","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29280/desirable.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29280","title":"Desirable","author":"by Frank Cottrell Boyce","description":"George is a self-confessed social reject who spends more time with his Warhammer figures than actual people - but when he's given a bottle of aftershave called 'Desirable', women can't resist him!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29282/flood-child.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29282","title":"Flood Child","author":"by Emily Diamand","description":"Lilly Melkun, an English fisher-girl, is out sailing with her sea-cat when the bloodthirsty Reavers come raiding - and kidnap the Prime Minister's daughter.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29290/joeypigza.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29290","title":"Joey Pigza Swallowed The Key","author":"by Jack Gantos","description":"This is a sensitive portrayal of a young ADHD sufferer, but is also a thoroughly entertaining insight into the life of the immensely likeable Joey Pigza, whose escapades are certain to amuse any reader.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25454/once.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25454","title":"Once","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"Morris Gleitzman brings heart and humour to the difficult subject of the Holocaust in this ground-breaking children's book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29291/diary-of-a-wimpy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29291","title":"Diary of a Wimpy Kid","author":"by Jeff Kinney","description":"Greg Heffley is a normal American kid, albeit one with a habit of getting into (and out of) trouble.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29293/how-loud-can-you-burp.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29293","title":"How Loud Can You Burp?","author":"by Glenn Murphy","description":"This is a wonderfully funny and informative book, which helps us take a fresh look at the world (and universe) we live in, with no boring bits and an abundance of fascinating facts!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29281/lightingthief.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29281","title":"Percy Jackson and the Lightning Thief","author":"by Rick Riordan","description":"In this leftfield comic fantasy novel, 12-year-old Percy Jackson discovers that the Greek gods of Olympus are alive and living in modern-day New York.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29289/blood-hunters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29289","title":"Blood Hunters","author":"by Steve Voake","description":"They know where you are... In the middle of the Mexican jungle a small scientific team prepares to embark on an exploration of the world's deepest sinkhole; a naturally-formed underwater shaft that no one has ever reached the bottom of.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29371.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29371","title":"The Clumsy Crocodile","author":"by Felicity Everett","description":"Cassy finds that working in a department store when you are a big clumsy crocodile with a rather long tail can be quite a challenge.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29081/manfred_bad_pb.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29081","title":"Manfred The Baddie","author":"by John Fardell","description":"In this comic-style book Manfred is the baddest baddie of all, robbing people, kidnapping inventors and planning evil ways to rule the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29295/dereksheep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29295","title":"Derek the Sheep","author":"by Gary Northfield","description":"A collection of hilarious Derek the Sheep adventures, each having featured as a comic strip in The Beano since 2003.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29369/boffin-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29369","title":"Boffin Boy and the Deadly Swarm","author":"by David Orme","description":"Can Boffin Boy find the source of the insect menace and put an end to it once and for all?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":5,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/5/","title":"Booked Up 2008","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25630/scralett-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25630","title":"Scarlett","author":"by Cathy Cassidy","description":"Twelve-year-old Scarlett is a rebel: outrageous clothes, tongue stud, total contempt for authority and thinks she is totally cool.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24811/heartbeat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24811","title":"Heartbeat","author":"by Sharon Creech","description":"Annie loves drawing, running barefoot, her family, and possibly Max, her running partner. It’s an eventful time for the 12-year-old: as her mother is about to give birth, her beloved grandfather is sliding slowly into dementia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25929/the-london-eye-mystery.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25929","title":"The London Eye Mystery","author":"by Siobhan Dowd","description":"Ted likes the weather, he also likes statistics and routine but his life is thrown into disarray when his Aunt Gloria and cousin Salim arrive, like a hurricane, to stay in London en-route to a new life in New York.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25474/blackbookosecrets.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25474","title":"The Black Book of Secrets","author":"by F E Higgins","description":"An original and fascinating book by a talented new writer, which explores themes of trust, redemption, forgiveness and natural justice in the context of a dark and gripping mystery.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28785/arctic-hero.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28785","title":"Arctic Hero","author":"by Catherine Johnson","description":"American explorer Matthew Henson was one of the first men to reach the North Pole in 1909. But his place in history wasn’t formally acknowledged for many years, due to the colour of his skin."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24995/garbageking.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24995","title":"The Garbage King","author":"by Elizabeth Laird","description":"This pacy coming-of-age adventure concentrates on the private hopes, dreams and feelings that drive its characters along, but also keeps enough sense of the gritty realities of street life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25651/skullduggery-pleasant-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25651","title":"Skulduggery Pleasant","author":"by Derek Landy","description":"Meet Skulduggery Pleasant, skeleton detective, fighting to save the world from wizard-gone-to-the-dark-side, Nefarian Serpine.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28788/read-me-and-laugh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28788","title":"Read Me and Laugh","author":"by Gaby Morgan","description":"This is a collection of funny poems from a wide range of poets from Spike Milligan to Valarie Bloom, and Lewes Carroll to Michael Rosen.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28784/foulplay.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28784","title":"Foul Play","author":"by Tom Palmer","description":"Danny is obsessed with two things: football and investigating crimes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28783/kiss-of-death.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28783","title":"Kiss of Death","author":"by Malcolm Rose","description":"Twins Kim and Seth and their friend Wes visit the plague village of Eyam on a school trip and steal some cursed coins from an old well.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28786/why-eating-bogeys-is-good-for-you.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28786","title":"Why Eating Bogeys is Good For You","author":"by Mitchell Symons","description":"The facts in this book will make you laugh out loud and possibly answer some of life's great mysteries such as why eating bogeys is good for you.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28781/hive-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28781","title":"HIVE","author":"by Mark Walden","description":"H.I.V.E. (Higher Institute of Villainous Education) is a top secret school of villainy, where children with a talent for wrongdoing are sent to develop their talents to become criminal masterminds.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29981/giraffes-cant-dance.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29981","title":"Giraffes Can't Dance","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"Rhyming text and vibrant full-page illustrations make this marvellous picture book perfect for reading aloud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24856/9781862308077-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24856","title":"Mister Magnolia","author":"by Quentin Blake","description":"Mr Magnolia has many things - but only one boot.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30501/stories-of-dragons.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30501","title":"Stories of Dragons","author":"by Christopher Rawson","description":"A section ‘all about dragons' is followed by a series of dragon stories with multiple appeal.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24897/ottolineandtheyellowcat300dpi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24897","title":"Ottoline and the Yellow Cat","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Ottoline is good at solving mysteries, in part due to her eavesdropping habit and in part because of her qualification as a mistress of disguise.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25305/the-adventures-of-robin-hood.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25305","title":"The Adventures of Robin Hood","author":"by Marcia Williams","description":"A retelling of 11 Robin Hood stories, from his fight with Little John to the firing of his last arrow in humorous comic-strip format.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"}]}
{"id":6,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/6/","title":"Booked Up 2007","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30498/evilinventions.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30498","title":"Evil Inventions","author":"by Nick Arnold","description":"With fantastic fact files, quirky quizzes and crazy cartoons, Evil Inventions is buzzing with brilliant brainwaves.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24523/cloud-busting.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24523","title":"Cloud Busting","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Shortlisted for the 2004 Nestlé Smarties Book Prize (age 6-8 category), an exploration of an unlikely friendship between two very different boys.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25192/framed-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25192","title":"Framed","author":"by Frank Cottrell Boyce","description":"The story centres on Dylan Hughes, the only boy left in a small Welsh mountain town called Manod. This is an immensely entertaining book, about the power of art to bring about change and to redeem.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30504/ug.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30504","title":"Ug","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"Ug and his parents live in the Stone Age. This means stone blankets, stone-cold food, an even colder cave and, worst of all, hard stone trousers!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25667/a-dog-called-grk.jpg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25667","title":"A Dog Called Grk","author":"by Joshua Doder","description":"Returning a lost dog doesn't usually involve running away to obscure European countries, stealing helicopters, masterminding jail breaks and fleeing despotic generals.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25003/i-coriander.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25003","title":"I, Coriander","author":"by Sally Gardner","description":"Coriander Hobie's happy childhood in 17th-century London is brought to an abrupt end when her mother is murdered by an evil fairy queen from the land of her youth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24769/journey2-the-river-sea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24769","title":"Journey to the River Sea","author":"by Eva Ibbotson","description":"Orphan Maia is thrilled to learn she is to live with relatives in South America and cannot wait to experience the sights, sounds and smells of the Amazon.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30499/unbelievable-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30499","title":"Unbelievable!","author":"by Paul Jennings","description":"A brilliant collection of funny, weird and whacky short stories in which, believe it or not, a kid can grow younger; birds can bury you; ghosts have exams; there are eyes in the milk.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24766/saffysangel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24766","title":"Saffy's Angel","author":"by Hilary McKay","description":"This is an uplifting story about an eccentric family encased in chaos, but also full of intense warmth and loyalty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26113/freak-the-mighty.jpg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26113","title":"Freak the Mighty","author":"by Rodman Philbrick","description":"Kevin and Max are both accustomed to ridicule but when fate throws this seemingly mismatched pair together the result is awesome: Freak the Mighty. A tragic, suspenseful and touching story that is ultimately uplifting.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30497/dream-on.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30497","title":"Dream On","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"Much to the disapproval of his parents, Baljit is mad on football and when he is invited to trials at Leicester City, he has to lie about his whereabouts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24773/mortalengines-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24773","title":"Mortal Engines","author":"by Philip Reeve","description":"London is on the move again: the traction city trawls the world on wheels, capturing and eating smaller towns.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":9,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/9/","title":"Real life","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30828/artichoke-hearts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30828","title":"Artichoke Hearts","author":"by Sita Brahmachari","description":"This empathetic account of the process of bereavement, a month’s diary, reassures readers that we grow from our experiences, however painful they are.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25630/scralett-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25630","title":"Scarlett","author":"by Cathy Cassidy","description":"Twelve-year-old Scarlett is a rebel: outrageous clothes, tongue stud, total contempt for authority and thinks she is totally cool.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26090/sundaegirl...jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26090","title":"Sundae Girl","author":"by Cathy Cassidy","description":"All teenagers are embarrassed by their parents but Jude feels she has more reason than most to cringe when hers are around her in public.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30466/flyawayy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30466","title":"Flyaway","author":"by Lucy Christopher","description":"The possibility of losing loved ones is captured in heart-breaking detail in his touching teenage book which tackles first love, friendship and the challenge of overcoming fear.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24706/bindi-babes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24706","title":"Bindi Babes","author":"by Narinder Dhami","description":"Narinder Dhami has a light touch which girls in particular will enjoy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25929/the-london-eye-mystery.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25929","title":"The London Eye Mystery","author":"by Siobhan Dowd","description":"Ted likes the weather, he also likes statistics and routine but his life is thrown into disarray when his Aunt Gloria and cousin Salim arrive, like a hurricane, to stay in London en-route to a new life in New York.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29290/joeypigza.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29290","title":"Joey Pigza Swallowed The Key","author":"by Jack Gantos","description":"This is a sensitive portrayal of a young ADHD sufferer, but is also a thoroughly entertaining insight into the life of the immensely likeable Joey Pigza, whose escapades are certain to amuse any reader.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25454/once.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25454","title":"Once","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"Morris Gleitzman brings heart and humour to the difficult subject of the Holocaust in this ground-breaking children's book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30376/love-aubrey-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30376","title":"Love, Aubrey","author":"by Suzanne LaFleur","description":"At the outset we meet 11-year-old Aubrey… living alone. Aubrey is the survivor of a car crash that has killed her sister and father – and now her mother has abandoned her."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24995/garbageking.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24995","title":"The Garbage King","author":"by Elizabeth Laird","description":"This pacy coming-of-age adventure concentrates on the private hopes, dreams and feelings that drive its characters along, but also keeps enough sense of the gritty realities of street life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24766/saffysangel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24766","title":"Saffy's Angel","author":"by Hilary McKay","description":"This is an uplifting story about an eccentric family encased in chaos, but also full of intense warmth and loyalty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28507/ways-to-live-forever.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28507","title":"Ways to Live Forever","author":"by Sally Nicholls","description":"This debut novel from a very young and exceptionally talented new writer is striking in its simplicity, but tackles a traumatic and extraordinarily difficult subject with warmth, humour, sensitivity and brutal honesty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":25,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/25/","title":"Winter books","list_description":"Snuggle up with your little ones and share one of these wintery stories. What better way to explore the changing weather and seasons together?","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30559/skip-through-the-season.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30559","title":"Skip through the Seasons","author":"by Stella Blackstone","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30555/one-snowy-night.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30555","title":"One Snowy Night","author":"by Nick Butterworth","description":"This is a heartwarming story of animals in winter - the story teaches children to look and think about the world around them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34160/boy-who-lost-his-bumble.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34160","title":"The Boy who lost his Bumble","author":"by Trudi Esberger","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34370/surprise-for-tiny-mouse.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34370","title":"A Surprise for Tiny Mouse","author":"by Petr Horáček","description":"Expore different types of weather and turn the wheel for a surprise!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30643/9780230705418-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30643","title":"Jack Frost","author":"by Kazuno Kohara","description":"A little boy sits by the fire, miserable because it is winter and all his friends are hibernating.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30535/wind-or-rain.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30535","title":"Wind or Rain?","author":"by Anthony Lewis","description":"An interactive introduction to weather that encourages discussion about feelings and choices.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6 months+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29177/9780340950654-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29177","title":"Miki","author":"by Stephen Mackey","description":"Shimmering like the northern lights, the illustrations' luminous blues and greens glow out of the darkness in this chilly yet elegantly magical wintry tale","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30926/brrrr-a-book-of-winter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30926","title":"Brrrr: A Book of Winter","author":"by Il Sung Na","description":"When snow falls on the ground, and all the trees are bare, everything changes ... including the white rabbit!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31013/iris-and-isaac.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31013","title":"Iris and Isaac","author":"by Catherine Rayner","description":"This gorgeous story from an award-winning picture book- maker is a classic tale of friendship between two quarrelling polar bears. Rayner's illustrations are a delight and her animals are full of character.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33995/pip-posy-snowy-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33995","title":"Pip and Posy: The Snowy Day","author":"by Axel Scheffler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30564/foggyfoggyforest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30564","title":"The Foggy Foggy Forest","author":"by Nick Sharratt","description":"Who's lurking in the foggy forest? Look through the trees and guess the shapes to find out.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30474/9781407107912-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30474","title":"The Night Iceberg","author":"by Helen Stephens","description":"Tofta has found that sharing is really hard to get used to. But she discovers it can sometimes be fun – especially if it involves games and stories with an army of penguins.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":26,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/26/","title":"Dinosaur books","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30508/dinosnore-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30508","title":"Dinosnore!","author":"by John Bendall-Brunello","description":"This book of dinosaur fun shows the young dinos trying to wake mum."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33830/really-really-big-dinosaur.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33830","title":"The really, really, really big dinosaur","author":"by Richard Byrne","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33713/never-ask-a-dinosaur-to-dinner.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33713","title":"Never Ask a Dinosaur to Dinner","author":"by Gareth Edwards","description":"This fabulously daft tale around a child's evening routine is the perfect bedtime book to share.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30519/bumpusjumpus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30519","title":"Bumpus Jumpus Dinosaurumpus!","author":"by Tony Mitton","description":"Join in as the dinosaurs stir up a dinosaurumpus! Instantly appealing, with bright and lively illustrations, and Tony Mitton's fantastic poetry and rhyming words."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34133/dinosaurs-do-too.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34133","title":"Dinosaurs Do Too!","author":"by Katherine Redfern and Ali Pye","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33162/9781408836729.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33162","title":"Dino-Baby","author":"by Mark Sperring","description":"There’s a new baby in the Dinosaur household which is very exciting. But Dino Baby’s arrival means there are a lot of new rules, especially for big sisters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24830/dinosaurroar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24830","title":"Dinosaur Roar!","author":"by Henrietta Stickland","description":"This book is an absolute winner, which soon has toddlers joining in with the rhyming words - and admiring the fabulous dinosaur pictures.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30561/stomp-chomp.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30561","title":"Stomp, Chomp, Big Roars! Here Come the Dinosaurs!","author":"by Kaye Umansky","description":""}]}
{"id":27,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/27/","title":"Booktouch books","list_description":"Great books to share with blind or partially-sighted children. The Booktouch booklist aims to give you more book suggestions for children up to the age of five, based on ideas given to us by parents, teachers, the RNIB, ClearVision, children and other experts.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28657/the-patch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28657","title":"The Patch","author":"by Justina Chen Hedley","description":"Becca has amblyopia and needs to wear both glasses and an eye patch to strengthen her weak eye.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30548/twinkle-new.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30548","title":"Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"This book is all about signing and singing-along! The clear hand movements encourage signing as well as dancing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30635/there-was-an-old-lady-who-swallowed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30635","title":"There Was an Old Lady Who Swallowed a Fly","author":"by Pam Adams","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29872/the-very-busy-spider.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29872","title":"The Very Busy Spider","author":"by Eric Carle","description":"One morning in a farmyard a spider begins to spin a web. All the animals try to persuade her to stop but she doesn't answer any of them; she is too busy spinning her web.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30622/baby-shapes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30622","title":"Baby Shapes","author":"by Helen and Clive Dorman","description":"Four highly stimulating books featuring a range of shapes and facial expressions.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6months+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24916/bathtime-peekaboo-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24916","title":"Bathtime peekaboo!","author":"by Dorling Kindersley","description":"The Dorling Kindersley team have put together this colourful, waterproof, touch-and-feel, lift-the-flap, fun bathtime book to be shared with your baby.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 1+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30617/whats-the-time-mr-wolf.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30617","title":"What's the Time, Mr Wolf?","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"A captivating story of wolves with dinner on their minds. The wolf finger puppet attached to the book brings the story to life and is great fun for snapping at little fingers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30632/nursery-rhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30632","title":"Nursery Rhymes","author":"by Priddy Books","description":"A large board book of over 20 nursery rhymes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30633/10wrigglycaterpillars.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30633","title":"Ten Wriggly Wiggly Caterpillars","author":"by Debbie Tarbett","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30607/thats-not-my-kitten.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30607","title":"That's Not My Kitten...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"One of a growing series of touch and feel board books with interesting textures and shapes for inquisitive fingers to explore.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
