{"id":31,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/31/","title":"Books to suit different needs","list_description":"Sharing books together can have many benefits - helping concentration, coordination, language development, interaction and communication skills, for example. Best of all, it is great fun, and can be enjoyed by every parent and child! The books selected for the Bookstart packs are carefully chosen for their wide appeal. However, you may feel that your child has needs which might make other types of book particularly suitable in the early years. This booklist aims to give you a few ideas.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24855/wheresspot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24855","title":"Where's Spot?","author":"by Eric Hill","description":"This adorable picture book about Spot the dog is the first in the Spot series","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32256/9780552565783-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32256","title":"Sometimes I Feel Sunny","author":"by Gillian Shields","description":"An introduction for the youngest readers to the different feelings they experience, from sad to funny, angry to sunny, and even lost and small.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29965/hug.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29965","title":"Hug","author":"by Jez Alborough","description":"Bobo the chimp wanders sadly around the jungle looking for someone to hug, but all the animals are already cuddling someone else.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30645/maisy-s-panda.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30645","title":"Where is Maisy's Panda?","author":"by Lucy Cousins","description":"With bold, eye-catching primary colours (which are easy for the eye to focus on), simple rhymes and repetition, and a series of flaps to lift, this book should appeal to any or all of the senses."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24916/bathtime-peekaboo-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24916","title":"Bathtime peekaboo!","author":"by Dorling Kindersley","description":"The Dorling Kindersley team have put together this colourful, waterproof, touch-and-feel, lift-the-flap, fun bathtime book to be shared with your baby.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 1+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28690/the-mulberry-bush.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28690","title":"The Mulberry Bush","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"A large-format picture book with strong pages and peep-through holes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34221/what-can-i-feel-annie-kubler.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34221","title":"What Can I Feel?","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34176/baby-touch-flip-flap.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34176","title":"Baby Touch Flip-Flap book","author":"by Ladybird","description":"Touch-and-feel book with colourful pictures to explore with your baby","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30610/sign-about-meal-time.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30610","title":"Sign About: Meal Time","author":"by Anthony Lewis","description":"A great introduction to simple signs which can be used with children from a very early age.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34136/alphaprints-abc.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34136","title":"Alphaprints ABC","author":"by Sarah Powell","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30647/bearhuntcd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30647","title":"We're Going on a Bear Hunt (book and CD)","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24828/twinkly-night.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24828","title":"Twinkly Night","author":"by Helen Stephens","description":"'Night has fallen all around. Lights are shining in the sleepy town'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34180/thats-not-my-teddy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34180","title":"That's not my teddy...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"Touch-feely book with colourful illustrations and simply text","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30362/dart-and-dive.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30362","title":"Dart and Dive","author":"by Hannah Wood","description":"Babies will love blowing and watching the mobiles in these beautiful concertina books.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":32,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/32/","title":"Finding inclusive books","list_description":"Most children's books today suitably reflect our multicultural society. However, not so many reflect other forms of diversity, for example the fact that one in five school-age children has special educational needs. This is especially true of books for very young children. This list aims to help you to find early years books showing positive images of disability, as well as titles that may prove useful in discussing disability and diversity.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28664/my-brother-sammy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28664","title":"My Brother Sammy","author":"by Becky Armitage","description":"If only his brother was “normal”. Mum says that Sammy is “special” but the narrator doesn’t want a special brother. He describes a roller coaster of different feelings – loneliness and frustration, sadness and anger, embarrassment and guilt. With beautiful...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25239/giant-turnip-9781852697884.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25239","title":"The Giant Turnip","author":"by Henriette Barkow","description":"The children in Miss Honeywood's class decide to grow vegetables in their school garden. What a shock they get when they discover a huge turnip that they are unable to move.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28688/the-animal-boogie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28688","title":"The Animal Boogie","author":"by Stella Blackstone","description":"Boogie along with the jungle inhabitants who flap, shake, flap and slide their way through this colourful book","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33816/benjamin-spectacles-book-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33816","title":"Benjamin & the Super Spectacles","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33362/9781406322187-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33362","title":"The Black Book of Colours","author":"by Menena Cottin & Rosana Faria","description":"A visually impaired boy introduces us to colours as he experiences them – through his senses of hearing, touch, smell and taste.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30807/just-because.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30807","title":"Just Because","author":"by Rebecca Elliott","description":"This uplifting book focuses on a sibling relationship, as a little boy affectionately describes his older sister","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25693/seal_surfer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25693","title":"Seal Surfer","author":"by Michael Foreman","description":"A welcome re-publication of Foreman's timeless and evocative account of a boy's relationship with life and death.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28567.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28567","title":"Brian Has Dyslexia","author":"by Woody Fox","description":"Not knowing his left from his right, and his bad headaches are also adding to his problems. Then, with some help from Dr Spot and a specialist teacher, the cause is found to be dyslexia and a range of new...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33871/specs-for-rex.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33871","title":"Specs for Rex","author":"by Yasmeen Ismail","description":"A perfectly judged niche story that has general appeal due to a clean text and cute character; Specs for Rex is a visual treat that's really worth putting your glasses on for.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28652/this-little-piggy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28652","title":"This Little Piggy","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"Annie Kubler’s exuberant characters tell the well-known rhyme. One child uses a supported chair.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34630/wheels-on-the-bus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34630","title":"The Wheels on the Bus","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24863/elmer-s-friends.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24863","title":"Elmer's Friends","author":"by David McKee","description":"A colourful board book in which the ever-popular Elmer the Elephant praises each of his friends for their different strengths","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30652/lucys-picture.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30652","title":"Lucy's Picture","author":"by Nicola Moon & Alex Aycliffe","description":"It is art class at school and Lucy wants to make a picture for her grandfather when he comes to visit her.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28691/hamish.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28691","title":"Hamish: The Bear who Found his Child","author":"by Moira Munro","description":"Wheelchair-using teddies (quite rightly) blend effortlessly into the landscape,as the toys have fun while the humans aren't looking in this book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28694/the-ding-dong-bag.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28694","title":"The Ding-Dong Bag","author":"by Polly Peters","description":"The fast-moving and rhythmic text make this great book perfect for reading aloud, and a subtle arm splint on one of the boys is typical of Child’s Play’s inclusive approach to books.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28689/i-am-the-music-man.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28689","title":"I Am the Music Man","author":"by Debra Potter","description":"A large book featuring holes through which you can peek to spot which of the thoroughly inclusive band of musicians is playing each instrument.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33035/9781847803887-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33035","title":"Max the Champion","author":"by Sean Stockdale and Alexandra Strick","description":"This inclusive book is about a boy who loves sport, his friends, and school - and has a vivid imagination","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30569/winniewitch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30569","title":"Winnie the Witch","author":"by Valerie Thomas","description":"This is the first of many stories about Winnie and her cat, Wilber. Winnie is a well-loved character, and the excellent illustrations are wild and wacky."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33200/onetwothree.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33200","title":"One, two, three... Run!","author":"by Carol Thompson","description":"Even a simple book for babies and toddlers can include disabled children naturally and subtly in its images - and this delightful board book proves the point.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29982/susan-laughs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29982","title":"Susan Laughs","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Susan can do so many things - she can laugh, sing, fly, dance, swim and much more. The final page of this wonderful book reveals that Susan is in a wheelchair, showing that 'disabled' doesn't mean 'disadvantaged'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32734/9781846435010-mary-had-a-li.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32734","title":"Mary Had a Little Lamb - Classic Books with Holes","author":"by Marina Aizen","description":"One of Child's Play's delightful early years books which reflect the true diversity of society in a natural and uncontrived way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28686/peek-a-boo-nursery-games.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28686","title":"Peek-a-Boo!","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"The exuberant characters include children on supported mats, a child with a leg splint and a parent with a hearing aid.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28687/see-saw-nursery-songs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28687","title":"See-Saw!","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"This book offers nursery songs and among the many vibrant illustrations is a signing child with a hearing aid.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28690/the-mulberry-bush.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28690","title":"The Mulberry Bush","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"A large-format picture book with strong pages and peep-through holes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30571/pat-a-cake-nursery-rhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30571","title":"Pat-a-Cake!","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"Part of a series introducing well loved games and rhymes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30614/my-first-animal-signs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30614","title":"My First Animal Signs","author":"by Anthony Lewis","description":"One of the series of board books introducing useful words - delightful illustrations show children signing the words."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30654/theokaybook.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30654","title":"The Okay Book","author":"by Todd Parr","description":""}]}
{"id":33,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/33/","title":"Multicultural","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25239/giant-turnip-9781852697884.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25239","title":"The Giant Turnip","author":"by Henriette Barkow","description":"The children in Miss Honeywood's class decide to grow vegetables in their school garden. What a shock they get when they discover a huge turnip that they are unable to move.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28935/fruits.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28935","title":"Fruits: a Caribbean counting poem","author":"by Valerie Bloom","description":"From half a pawpaw to five jew-plums through to ten bananas, this girl’s love of Caribbean fruits is so infectious you can almost taste the juice dribbling down your chin.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30580/full-of-love.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30580","title":"Full, Full, Full of Love","author":"by Trish Cooke","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29128/9781406331264-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29128","title":"Ten Little Fingers and Ten Little Toes","author":"by Mem Fox & Helen Oxenbury","description":"This charming first book is perfect for new arrivals.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34381/black-and-white-club.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34381","title":"The Black and White Club","author":"by Alice Hemming","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34233/we-all-went-on-safari.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34233","title":"We All Went on Safari","author":"by Laurie Krebs and Julia Cairns","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25804/lulu-loves-library.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25804","title":"Lulu Loves the Library","author":"by Anna McQuinn","description":"Lulu has her library card, her rucksack full of borrowed books, and a big smile on her face, because it's Tuesday – and on Tuesdays Lulu and her mummy go to the library","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30506/lulu-loves-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30506","title":"LuLu Loves Stories","author":"by Anna McQuinn","description":"This lovely book introduces the magic of sharing stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28894/tickle-tickle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28894","title":"Tickle, Tickle","author":"by Helen Oxenbury","description":"Ideal for any time of the day, especially bathtime and bedtime, the language and repetition make this book good to read aloud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30556/one-two-tree-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30556","title":"One, Two, Tree!","author":"by Anushka Ravishankar","description":"This is an unusual and creative counting book. The pictures reflect the tribal traditions of central India, and the tree fills up with animals as the story progresses.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30517/making-friends-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30517","title":"Making Friends!","author":"by Jess Stockham","description":"This book is full of great animal pictures and lift-the-flap pages. It’s a friendly and colourful way to encourage children to enjoy sharing and have fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30528/lets-feed-the-ducks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30528","title":"Let's Feed the Ducks","author":"by Pamela Venus","description":"Feeding the ducks can be an adventure, as this story shows!"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30583/lets-go-to.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30583","title":"Let's go to Playgroup","author":"by Pamela Venus","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28587/lucy-loud-and-clear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28587","title":"Lucy: Loud and Clear","author":"by Laila Lavan","description":"Lucy is deaf and Omar is rather flippantly pretending he can't understand her request. Lucy has to be creative if she is to find a solution.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":35,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/35/","title":"Wildlife","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29500/wowsaidowl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29500","title":"WOW! Said the Owl","author":"by Tim Hopgood","description":"Everyone knows that owls are nocturnal but one curious little owl decides to take a long nap at night so she can stay awake during the day.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30544/baby-touch-farm.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30544","title":"Baby Touch, Farm","author":"by Fiona Land","description":"This is a great introduction to farm animals.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 1+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30554/oneisasnail.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30554","title":"One is a Snail, Ten is a Crab","author":"by April Pulley Sayre","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30528/lets-feed-the-ducks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30528","title":"Let's Feed the Ducks","author":"by Pamela Venus","description":"Feeding the ducks can be an adventure, as this story shows!"}]}
{"id":36,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/36/","title":"Transport","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28924/duck-in-the-truck.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28924","title":"Duck in the Truck","author":"by Jez Alborough","description":"As Duck is driving home his truck gets stuck in the mud. Frog and Sheep come to his aid, but it's only when Goat arrives that a solution is found.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33711/stanley-garage.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33711","title":"Stanley's Garage","author":"by William Bee","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31230/9780192763433-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31230","title":"Machine Poems","author":"by Jill Bennett","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31237/my-granny-hres.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31237","title":"My Granny Went to Market","author":"by Stella Blackstone","description":"Join Granny as she takes a magic carpet ride around the world","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33817/lildrivers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33817","title":"Little Drivers to the Rescue!","author":"by Dan Crisp","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30578/little-boat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30578","title":"Little Boat","author":"by Thomas Docherty","description":"Discover the world with Little Boat - this is a wonderfully illustrated sea adventure."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31234/driving-to-bed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31234","title":"Driving to Bed","author":"by Hallie Durand","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29507/toottootbeepbeep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29507","title":"Toot Toot Beep Beep","author":"by Emma Garcia","description":"n the eyes of a child traffic can be endlessly entertaining and varied","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30298/going-shopping.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30298","title":"Going Shopping","author":"by Sarah Garland","description":"This is all about a busy, muddy, funny and very realistic family day!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34630/wheels-on-the-bus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34630","title":"The Wheels on the Bus","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31232/beep-beep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31232","title":"Felt Fun Beep! Beep!","author":"by Jonathan Lambert","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31229/amazing-baby-move-it-jpg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31229","title":"Amazing Baby: Move It!","author":"by Bianca Lucas","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 1+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30604/flashing-fireengines.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30604","title":"Flashing Fire Engines","author":"by Tony Mitton","description":"This story’s full of big, bold fire engines ready to rescue or fight fires. There’s plenty of action, rhyme and rhythm."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30509/matty-takes-off.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30509","title":"Matty Takes Off","author":"by Miriam Moss","description":"Matty’s strong sibling relationship is a joy to read about, and there’s a great message in here about possessions not being everything."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31236/we-all.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31236","title":"We All Go Travelling By","author":"by Shena Roberts","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31235/rattle_and_rapv2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31235","title":"Rattle and Rap","author":"by Susan Steggall","description":"Young children will enjoy listening to the lovely rhyming text and looking at the detail in Steggall’s bold collaged illustrations."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30516/baby-s-very-first-outdoors-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30516","title":"Baby's Very First Outdoors Book","author":"by Jenny Tyler","description":"An ideal first book, with familiar, easily identifiable images offering plenty of opportunity for interaction between adult and child.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3 months +"}]}
{"id":37,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/37/","title":"Favourite books about love","list_description":"Children's books are the perfect place to explore and talk about the complexities of the heart. Here are some books to get you talking about your emotions.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28476/noughts-and-crosses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28476","title":"Noughts and Crosses","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Callum is a Nought but his best friend Sephy is a Cross - the daughter of one of the most influential politicians in the country.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30828/artichoke-hearts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30828","title":"Artichoke Hearts","author":"by Sita Brahmachari","description":"This empathetic account of the process of bereavement, a month’s diary, reassures readers that we grow from our experiences, however painful they are.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31994/love-monster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31994","title":"Love Monster","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"A funny and charming picture book illustrated with Rachel Bright’s engaging and expressive etchings with a feel good message","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24948/sugarrush.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24948","title":"Sugar Rush","author":"by Julie Burchill","description":"Shortlisted for the 2005 Booktrust Teenage Prize, this is a controversial and daring look at the gritty reality of teenage experience.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29741/romeo-and-juliet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29741","title":"Romeo and Juliet: Manga Shakespeare","author":"by Sonia Leong and William Shakespeare","description":"Set in modern Tokyo, with the Capulets and Montagues recast as organised-crime rivals, this racy retelling gets to the heart of the love story and the foolish rivalry that dooms it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25781/mr-puss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25781","title":"Mr Pusskins","author":"by Sam Lloyd","description":"Humorous, lively illustrations accompany the text in this unconventional love story, which is also a lesson in not taking people for granted.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29396/angus-thongs-and-full-frontal-snogging.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29396","title":"Angus, Thongs and Full-Frontal Snogging","author":"by Louise Rennison","description":"Welcome to the world of Georgia Nicolson - an angst-ridden teenage girl who keeps a diary to record the rollercoaster of emotions and experiences she faces every day","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26570/and-tango-makes-three.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26570","title":"And Tango Makes Three","author":"by Justin Richardson and Peter Parnell","description":"Roy and Silo are two boy penguins who live in the zoo in New York's Central Park. This is a really delightful story and the message behind it is subtle. It's a true story, and you can learn more about...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29550/shiver..jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29550","title":"Shiver","author":"by Maggie Stiefvater","description":"Set in small-town Minnesota, Stiefvater’s moving and poetic novel of human/wolf interaction and relationships is a werewolf story like no other.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28991/frog-is-in-love.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28991","title":"Frog in Love","author":"by Max Velthuijs","description":"Frog is not well. His heart is beating too fast and he feels hot and cold. A trip to the doctor reveals that he is in love. But who is he in love with?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"}]}
{"id":38,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/38/","title":"Ten fantasy books","list_description":"Winter is the perfect time to curl up with a good fantasy book. Here are some suggestions after you've exhausted Harry Potter, His Dark Materials, The Lord of the Rings trilogy, Earthsea et al.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30947/the-last-dragonslayer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30947","title":"The Last Dragonslayer","author":"by Jasper Fforde","description":"Times are tough for Jennifer Strange, manager of Kazam Mystical Arts - then predictions of a new Dragonslayer coming to slay the Last Dragon begin...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24536/inkheart-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24536","title":"Inkheart","author":"by Cornelia Funke","description":"12-year-old Meggie and her father, Mo, a bookbinder, both love reading, but since the disappearance of Meggie's mother, they no longer read together. One night a stranger knocks at their door, prompting Mo to reveal his awful secret.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25220/flybynight.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25220","title":"Fly By Night","author":"by Frances Hardinge","description":"Smugglers, thieves, murder, floating coffeehouses, river battles, highwaymen, suspense, political intrigue and excitement - this book has everything!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31738/9780552560221-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31738","title":"The Dragon Whisperer","author":"by Lucinda Hare","description":"Magic, treachery, bravery and sinister plots pepper the pages of this thrilling fantasy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25685/unlundun-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25685","title":"Un Lun Dun","author":"by China Miéville","description":"Zanna and Deeba inadvertently enter UnLondon, an alternative London which is threatened by Smog - a living poisonous cloud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28824/knifeofneverlettinggo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28824","title":"The Knife of Never Letting Go","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"The first in a series, this enthralling sci-fi/fantasy novel grips readers throughout, presenting them with tough questions about identity, ethics and the nature of truth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30378/fever-crumb-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30378","title":"Fever Crumb","author":"by Philip Reeve","description":"In a teasingly recognisable London threatened by northern invaders, orphan Engineer, Fever Crumb, is assigned to help renegade archaeologist Kit Solent.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30906/bartimaeus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30906","title":"Bartimaeus: The Ring of Solomon","author":"by Jonathan Stroud","description":"A fantastic, fast-paced adventure story set in a vividly-realised world of Arabian and Biblical myth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29332/tales-from-outer-suburbia-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29332","title":"Tales From Outer Suburbia","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"These often thought-provoking stories look at the reactions ordinary people have to the unusual situations they find themselves in and feature a host of different illustrative styles ranging from collage to painterly Edward Hopper-esque scenes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":39,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/39/","title":"Favourite scary books","list_description":"Haunted houses, wolves, other dimensions, dark secrets and terrifying mysteries - here are ten scary books to sink your teeth into.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25915/the-stuff-of-nightmares.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25915","title":"The Stuff of Nightmares","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Kyle is the only one conscious after an horrific train crash, but how long can he survive when death is stalking the carriages looking for him?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31737/9781849393218-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31737","title":"Haunted","author":"by Susan Cooper","description":"A scintillating selection of supremely scary tales from 11 well-known children’s authors","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24729/coraline-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24729","title":"Coraline","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"One day Coraline unlocks a mysterious door that opens onto another world, a twisted parody of Coraline's own dimension.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24991/the-wolves-in-the-walls.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24991","title":"The Wolves in the Walls","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"When Lucy hears noises in the walls of her home, she tries to warn her family that the wolves are coming. However, they do not heed her warnings – until it is too late.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25474/blackbookosecrets.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25474","title":"The Black Book of Secrets","author":"by F E Higgins","description":"An original and fascinating book by a talented new writer, which explores themes of trust, redemption, forgiveness and natural justice in the context of a dark and gripping mystery.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31857/9781406325614-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31857","title":"More Bloody Horowitz","author":"by Anthony Horowitz","description":"Entertaining and unsettling in equal measure!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29501/the-haunted-house.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29501","title":"The Haunted House","author":"by Kazuno Kohara","description":"When a young girl goes to live in a magnificent old house at the edge of town, she doesn't seem at all worried to find that it is haunted by not one, but many, floaty white ghosts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31745/forbidden.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31745","title":"The Demon Trappers: Forbidden","author":"by Jana Oliver","description":"A future where demons and the undead walk the streets"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30377/talesofterror.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30377","title":"Uncle Montague's Tales of Terror","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"These spine-tingling stories-within-a-story are the stuff of childhood nightmares, with a good smattering of ghosts, demons, blood and gore.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31774/9781408800041-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31774","title":"The Dead of Winter","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"A nail-biting story of hauntings and terror by the master of the genre, Chris Priestley","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31868/princeomist.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31868","title":"The Prince of Mist","author":"by Carlos Ruiz Zafon","description":"This is a chilling and haunting story of magic and mystery","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29206/flood-fang.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29206","title":"The Raven Mysteries: Flood and Fang","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"Strange things happen in Castle Otherhand, which isn't surprising given its eccentric inhabitants. Lord Valevine spends his time performing experiments on frogs, his wife Minty prizes her baking tins almost as highly as her children, ten-year-old Cudweed tears around the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31706/midwinterbloodd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31706","title":"Midwinterblood","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"In seven stories that take place on the strange island of Blessed, two souls seek each other over a period of a thousand years.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25331/lordloss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25331","title":"Lord Loss","author":"by Darren Shan","description":"Grubbs Grady thinks he's having a bad day when he's caught smoking and sent home from school. Very soon however, he learns that this is the least of his worries.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25815/frankenstein.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25815","title":"Pop-Up Frankenstein","author":"by Mary Shelley","description":"This remarkable new version blends the finest contemporary illustration, dramatic storytelling and superb paper engineering.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":40,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/40/","title":"Ten books about school","list_description":"Here are ten books about school, from entering the classroom for the very first time to teenage angst (and we couldn't resist including an Enid Blyton book too)!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24676/malorytowers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24676","title":"First Term at Malory Towers","author":"by Enid Blyton","description":"We're rooting for Darrell Rivers as she starts boarding school, and learns to cope with her fiery temper and decide for herself which friends are genuine.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24877/iam2small4school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24877","title":"I am Too Absolutely Small for School","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Lola is nearly big enough to go to school. But in her opinion she is still really quite small, and has far too many important things to keep her extremely busy at home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30066/song4summer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30066","title":"A Song for Summer","author":"by Eva Ibbotson","description":"A deliciously old-fashioned story, which encompasses love, adventure and a host of memorable characters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25337/once-upon-an-ordinary-school-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25337","title":"Once Upon an Ordinary School Day","author":"by Colin McNaughton","description":"An ordinary boy goes off to school and everything seems just as ordinary as ever, until a new teacher arrives in class.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28745/spud.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28745","title":"Spud","author":"by John van de Ruit","description":"Spud gets a scholarship to a smart boys’ school where he soon joins in with a mad bunch of boys – the Crazy Eight.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":41,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/41/","title":"Favourite books for teens","list_description":"Read our list of outstanding teenage books that have won or been shortlisted for the Book Trust Teenage Prize since it was founded in 2003.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24551/9781407138091-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24551","title":"Looking for JJ","author":"by Anne Cassidy","description":"When a 10-year-old girl kills her best friend, she is convicted of manslaughter and locked away. Seven years later she is released on licence with a new identity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32060/9780230762961-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32060","title":"After the Snow","author":"by S D Crocket","description":"Fifteen-year-old Willo has been left alone in the freezing and snow covered hills that have been his home for years.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25516/swiftpurecry.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25516","title":"A Swift Pure Cry","author":"by Siobhan Dowd","description":"Loosely based on the real life case of the Kerry babies, powerful imagery and lyrical prose is woven throughout this unforgettable, outstanding and ultimately hopeful novel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29125/the-graveyard-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29125","title":"The Graveyard Book","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"After his family are killed, Bod is brought up in a graveyard by ghosts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24568/curiousincident.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24568","title":"The Curious Incident of the Dog in the Night-time","author":"by Mark Haddon","description":"This funny, touching and compelling novel was the winner of the inaugural Booktrust Teenage Prize","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30467/unhooking-the-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30467","title":"Unhooking the Moon","author":"by Gregory Hughes","description":"Bob has a stubborn younger sister with disturbing fits and upsetting premonitions. She foretells her best friend's murder, their dog's disappearance and her father's death. Bob calls her the Rat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32383/9781408832332-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32383","title":"Throne of Glass","author":"by Sarah J Maas","description":"Infamous teenage assassin Celaena Sardothien has been condemned to a life sentence of hard labour in the salt mines of Endovier, until young Captain Westfall appears and offers her freedom, - but only if she'll compete in a deadly contest.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25663/henry-tumour.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25663","title":"Henry Tumour","author":"by Anthony McGowan","description":"Henry Tumour is certainly a memorable book: it's funny, shocking, and thought-provoking, too. Just be warned that the language is extreme throughout!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28824/knifeofneverlettinggo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28824","title":"The Knife of Never Letting Go","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"The first in a series, this enthralling sci-fi/fantasy novel grips readers throughout, presenting them with tough questions about identity, ethics and the nature of truth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24413/rani-and-sukh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24413","title":"Rani and Sukh","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"A vivid, fast-moving take on the Romeo and Juliet story, exploring the experience of young urban British Asians as they negotiate their way through two cultures","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25574/here-lies-arthur.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25574","title":"Here Lies Arthur","author":"by Philip Reeve","description":"The violence is darkly terrifying, the sense of landscape immediate and haunting and Gwyna/Gwyn's shifting gender permits Reeve to cast a unique, strikingly vivid glimpse into dark-age Britain.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24508/9780141318011-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24508","title":"How I Live Now","author":"by Meg Rosoff","description":"Fifteen-year-old New Yorker Daisy is sent to England to spend a summer with her unconventional cousins","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25821/my-swordhand-is-singing.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25821","title":"My Swordhand is Singing","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"Set in the seventeenth century amid the bleakness of winter in Eastern Europe, and inspired by vampire folklore, this is a superbly crafted, dark and menacing tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29795/out-of-shadows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29795","title":"Out of Shadows","author":"by Jason Wallace","description":"Back in the early 1980s, Robert Jacklin doesn't want to move to the newly independent Zimbabwe with his parents, nor does he want to be shipped off to boarding school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":42,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/42/","title":"Ten great adventure books for children","list_description":"From a fight with pirate dinosaurs, to a space voyage, to a world of ancient Mayan civilisations - here's a list of ten great adventure stories for all ages.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28473/captain-flinn-and-the-pirate-dinosaurs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28473","title":"Captain Flinn and the Pirate Dinosaurs: Missing Treasure!","author":"by Giles Andreae and Russell Ayto","description":"This latest Captain Flinn adventure finds Flinn and his friends fighting off pirate dinosaurs to recover Captain Rumblebelly's treasure and restore it to the museum.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30370/takeshita-demons-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30370","title":"Takeshita Demons","author":"by Cristy Burne","description":"When Miku moved to England from Japan, she never imagined that evil spirits would follow her. But one day an unusual looking supply teacher appears at school, and Miku suspects she may be a demon in disguise.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25929/the-london-eye-mystery.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25929","title":"The London Eye Mystery","author":"by Siobhan Dowd","description":"Ted likes the weather, he also likes statistics and routine but his life is thrown into disarray when his Aunt Gloria and cousin Salim arrive, like a hurricane, to stay in London en-route to a new life in New York.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24808/traction-man-is-here.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24808","title":"Traction Man is Here","author":"by Mini Grey","description":"Transformed in an instant from combat cool to sartorial nightmare, can Traction Man ever be a superhero again?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30375/invisiblecity.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30375","title":"The Joshua Files: Invisible City","author":"by M G Harris","description":"Josh Garcia is an ordinary teenager living in Oxford, until his archaeologist father's plane disappears in Mexico.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24769/journey2-the-river-sea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24769","title":"Journey to the River Sea","author":"by Eva Ibbotson","description":"Orphan Maia is thrilled to learn she is to live with relatives in South America and cannot wait to experience the sights, sounds and smells of the Amazon.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27139/the-way-backhome.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27139","title":"The Way Back Home","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"The boy from How to Catch a Star and Lost and Found returns for a third adventure, this time discovering an aeroplane in his cupboard.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25069/the-white-darkness.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25069","title":"The White Darkness","author":"by Geraldine McCaughrean","description":"Introspective 14-year-old Symone is obsessed with Antarctica but when her 'Uncle' Victor takes her to the land of ice, the journey soon turns into a nightmare of madness and death.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30306/we-re-going-bear-hunt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30306","title":"We're Going on a Bear Hunt","author":"by Michael Rosen & Helen Oxenbury","description":"Follow a father and his family as they go out in search of a bear.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"}]}
{"id":43,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/43/","title":"Favourite books from around the world","list_description":"Some of these books have been translated from other languages, while others use a different country as their setting - all will encourage readers to take a journey in their imagination.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31604/no1carspotter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31604","title":"No. 1 Car Spotter","author":"by Atinuke","description":"No. 1 comes to the rescue each and every time his family or the village are in trouble!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32711/9781742375731-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32711","title":"The Perfect Flower Girl","author":"by Taghred Chandab","description":"Sisters Mariam and Amani are very excited about being flower girls at the wedding feast of their Aunt Sarah and her new husband.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29013/jamela-s-dress.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29013","title":"Jamela's Dress","author":"by Niki Daly","description":"Jamela wraps herself up with the new material that her mother bought to make herself a dress for a wedding.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30946/two-good-thieves.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30946","title":"Two Good Thieves","author":"by Daniel Finn","description":"This nail-biting thriller is also a challenging story about the lives of the world's poorest children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28881/toby-alone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28881","title":"Toby Alone","author":"by Timothee de Fombelle","description":"Winner of the 2009 Marsh Award for Children's Literature in Translation, this exciting adventure has a serious message about the wisdom of using up the Earth’s resources","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24536/inkheart-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24536","title":"Inkheart","author":"by Cornelia Funke","description":"12-year-old Meggie and her father, Mo, a bookbinder, both love reading, but since the disappearance of Meggie's mother, they no longer read together. One night a stranger knocks at their door, prompting Mo to reveal his awful secret.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25611/just-like-tomorrow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25611","title":"Just Like Tomorrow","author":"by Faiza Guene","description":"Sarah Adams's deft translation foregrounds Faïza Guene's sharply creative use of language, highlighting cross-currents of urban and racial tensions, in this sad, funny and important book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+`"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30939/down-by-the-river.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30939","title":"Down by the River","author":"by Grace Hallworth","description":"Originally published in 1996, this is a welcome reappearance of a picture book brimming with Caribbean sunshine and culture.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33297/tintin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33297","title":"The Adventures of Tintin","author":"by Hergé","description":"Resourceful junior reporter Tintin embarks on a series of exciting international adventures, accompanied by his faithful dog Snowy, in this favourite series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34179/here-i-am.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34179","title":"Here I am","author":"by Patti Kim","description":"The word-less book deals with the challenges of leaving a beloved home; coming to terms with the big changes you face in your new world; and the emotions surrounding this journey.","reading_age":"Reading Age: wordless","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30963/a-beautiful-lie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30963","title":"A Beautiful Lie","author":"by Irfan Master","description":"Set in India during the summer of 1947, A Beautiful Lie follows the tumultuous events of the Partition of India through the eyes of Bilal who is looking after his ill father.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25508/sweets.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25508","title":"Sweets","author":"by Sylvia van Ommen","description":"This fantastically different picture book delivers a funny, touching and uplifting story about the nature of friendship.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35188/yokki.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35188","title":"Yokki and the Parno Gry","author":"by Richard O’Neill and Katharine Quarmby","description":"Yokki and his family are travellers. After a particularly poor harvest, Yokki raises people's spirits with his uplifting stories of a brighter future. This traditional Romani tale, with colourful illustrations, is full of hope and imagination.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34076/amina-through-my-eyes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34076","title":"Through My Eyes: Amina","author":"by J L Powers","description":"This moving story transports the reader to Somalia and allows them to experience the challenges faced by the Somalian families who chose to stay in their war torn country.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25571/pepperpotbaby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25571","title":"Mrs Pepperpot Minds the Baby","author":"by Alf Proysen","description":"Mrs Pepperpot has an unfortunate problem: she shrinks at the most unexpected moments. And one of those moments comes while she has agreed to look after Roger, the neighbour's baby.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31213/ramadan-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31213","title":"Ramadan Moon","author":"by Na'ima B Robert","description":"During Ramadan, Muslim families all over the world visit their mosques to listen to verses from the Koran. They will eat before dawn and will not eat again until after sunset.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34425/street-children.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34425","title":"Real Stories from Street Children Across the World","author":"by Anthony Robinson","description":"This moving book, illustrated by line drawings and the author's photographs, tells many such real life stories. Through them all, a spirit of optimism and resilience shines through. Despite violence, fear and sorrow, these children have hopes for the future.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32154/9781406337730-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32154","title":"Ladder to the Moon","author":"by Maya Soetoro-Ng","description":"In this picture book by US President Barack Obama's half sister, Maya Soetoro-Ng explores the themes of humanity, love, acceptance and reconcilliation through the story of a little girl whose grandmother takes her on a remarkable journey.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31519/9780340969939-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31519","title":"The Arrival","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"In this unusual book, we follow a young man as he packs his bags and leaves his family to go and start a new life in another country","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29837/my-village.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29837","title":"My Village: Rhymes from Around the World","author":"by Edited by Danielle Wright","description":"Printed beside each rhyme is its native language version. The illustrations are designed to attract even the youngest audience, lively, colourful and child-centred.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29226/j-is-for-jamaica.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29226","title":"J is for Jamaica","author":"by Benjamin Zephaniah","description":"Welcome to this whistle-stop tour of Jamaica - from A for Ackee to Z for Zinc.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":44,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/44/","title":"Ten books about the seaside","list_description":"We've chosen some of our favourite seaside-themed children’s books for all ages - which one is your favourite?","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25328/liltim.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25328","title":"Little Tim and the Brave Sea Captain","author":"by Edward Ardizzone","description":"This charming and ultimately reassuring story is a reissue of Edward Ardizzone's classic 1936 picture book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30389/alongfortheride.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30389","title":"Along for the Ride","author":"by Sarah Dessen","description":"Auden decides to go and spend the summer with her father, his new (much younger) wife and their newborn daughter, Thisbe, at their home in a seaside town.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25398/ingo-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25398","title":"Ingo","author":"by Helen Dunmore","description":"In Cornish legend, the Zenor mermaid fell in love with Mathew Trewhella and enticed him away to live in the sea with her forever...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25452/flush-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25452","title":"Flush","author":"by Carl Hiaasen","description":"This is an engaging and light-hearted thriller about issues that matter - justice, family and the environment.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25161/lost-found.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25161","title":"Lost and Found","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"Once there was a sad, lonely penguin who appeared at the door of a young boy. The boy decided he must be lost, so he set off to find his home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24957/tailofemilywindsnap.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24957","title":"The Tail of Emily Windsnap","author":"by Liz Kessler","description":"Emily Windsnap has lived on a boat her whole life but her mother has seemed strangely anxious to keep her away from the water itself. All is explained when Emily is finally allowed to have swimming lessons and she makes...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":45,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/45/","title":"Favourite Graphic Novels for Middle Grade Children","list_description":"These comics and graphic novels offer a different route into discovering the pleasure of reading.  Click here for a chance to win some of the graphic novels listed below.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35381/nightlights.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35381","title":"Nightlights","author":"by Lorena Alvarez","description":"A remarkable, haunting and beautiful graphic novel for younger readers, Nightlights is a magical fable about creativity and believing in yourself. With a 'Studio Ghibli' feel and some sumptuous artwork, this is a wonderful read and a visual treat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34126/el-deafo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34126","title":"El Deafo","author":"by Cece Bell","description":"Delivered in graphic-novel format, this story is based on the childhood of US author/illustrator Cece Bell who was diagnosed as deaf at the age of four.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34392/azzi-in-between.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34392","title":"Azzi in Between","author":"by Sarah Garland","description":"This is a moving tale of a refugee family told in graphic novel style and so appealing to a wide range of younger readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29691/calamity-jack.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29691","title":"Calamity Jack","author":"by Dean and Shannon Hale","description":"This graphic novel is full of fun action set pieces, comedic turns and well-drawn out characters and is a much-needed updating of the classic fairy tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31581/stormbreakergn.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31581","title":"Stormbreaker: The Graphic Novel","author":"by Anthony Horowitz","description":"The graphic novel adaptation of this well-written and action-packed story of a teenage spy works really well","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35341/9781909263741.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35341","title":"Hilda and the Stone Forest","author":"by Luke Pearson","description":"In her fifth adventure, the daring Hilda is back on form with plenty of strange magic, but this time with mum in tow. This allows Pearson to explore their mother-daughter relationship - as they battle two-headed trolls, of course.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34811/themarvels.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34811","title":"The Marvels","author":"by Brian Selznick","description":"More than just a mystery, The Marvels is a heart-warming story about growing up, identity and family, full of cinematic and captivating illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34714/9781447234425.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34714","title":"Scavenger: Chaos Zone","author":"by Paul Stewart, Chris Riddell","description":"The second in the Scavenger series, Chaos Zone finds York and his robot Zoid friend Belle exploding from a ventilation tube into a strange forest. A thousand years into space, the animals and plants aboard the city-sized Biosphere spaceship have...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35292/brownstone-s-mythical-collection.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35292","title":"Brownstone’s Mythical Collection: Arthur and the Golden Rope","author":"by Joe Todd-Stanton","description":"Arthur goes to the great hall to help Thor catch the wicked Fenrir. There, he is set the almost impossible task of making a magical Golden Rope. A fantastic version of a Norse myth that falls between a picture book...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7-10","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-10"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35431/hilo-the-boy-who-crashed-to-earth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35431","title":"Hilo: The Boy Who Crashed to Earth","author":"by Judd Winick","description":"Colourful, action-filled and laugh-out-loud funny, with plenty of burps, farts and catchphrases, HILO is the first in a bestselling US graphic novel series for younger readers. It's also a genuinely well-told, gripping sci-fi story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6-10","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30383/boffin-boy-ninja-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30383","title":"Boffin Boy and the Forest of the Ninja","author":"by David Orme","description":"This graphic novel style book is a quick read and perfect for those who don’t like too much text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":46,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/46/","title":"Christmas books to share","list_description":"Get into the festive spirit by sharing these children's books over the festive season.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29641/snow-queen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29641","title":"The Snow Queen","author":"by Hans Christian Andersen","description":"Lynch's vivid yet ethereal illustrations capture the balance between the wondrous and the recognisable in this powerful story about the redemptive nature of love and the passing of time.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29044/stickman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29044","title":"Stick Man","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"The award-winning creators of The Gruffalo now present us with a modern variation on a long-established folk tale theme, which details the perilous adventures of a stick.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29655/oxford-poems.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29655","title":"The Oxford Book of Christmas Poems","author":"by Michael Harrison and Christopher Stuart Clarke","description":"This magical anthology carries the reader from chilly December days, through the festive season to the New Year and then on to the first flowers of spring.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28233/the-night-before-christmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28233","title":"The Night Before Christmas","author":"by Clement C Moore","description":"There have been countless editions of Clement's poem but none has transcended this one illustrated by talented artist Christian Birmingham."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29631/the-best-of-times.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29631","title":"The Best of Times","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"The Prince invites entertainers to the palace to cheer up the Princess. The puppeteers come too and perform the greatest story – the Christmas Nativity story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29653/13daysxmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29653","title":"The Thirteen Days of Christmas","author":"by Jenny Overton","description":"Since their mother died, Annaple has frustrated her younger siblings with her over-zealous housekeeping, and terrible cooking. Overton creates a delightful tale of a close-knit family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25896/1stxmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25896","title":"The First Christmas","author":"by Jan Pienkowski","description":"Jan Pienkowski's silhouette illustrations lend an air of mystery and drama to this text, taken from the King James Bible.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29657/lionunicornme.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29657","title":"The Lion, the Unicorn and Me","author":"by Jeanette Winterson","description":"The donkey is chosen to carry Mary to Bethlehem by an angel who prizes the animal’s humility over the regal prowess of a lion and the mystery of a unicorn.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"}]}
{"id":47,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/47/","title":"Favourite funny books","list_description":"Warning: these books will make you laugh, snort, giggle, titter, chuckle and chortle. Some of the funniest books around are children's books, so you're in for a treat with these favourites below. Be careful, though - there's a danger of actual tears and serious stomach-hurt from doubling-over with laughter. Don't say we didn't warn you!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28465/themnawhoworeallhisclothes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28465","title":"The Man Who Wore All His Clothes","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"Mr Gaskitt works as Father Christmas in a department store, his wife is a taxi driver and Horace, their cat, loves spending much of his time watching sad old movies on TV.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25192/framed-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25192","title":"Framed","author":"by Frank Cottrell Boyce","description":"The story centres on Dylan Hughes, the only boy left in a small Welsh mountain town called Manod. This is an immensely entertaining book, about the power of art to bring about change and to redeem.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24569/utterlymer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24569","title":"Utterly Me, Clarice Bean","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Clarice Bean finds family life exhausting and exasperating, and school is no better; particularly when the teacher, Mrs Wilburton, sets an 'utterly dreary' book project.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29944/the-vicar-of-nibbleswicke.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29944","title":"The Vicar of Nibbleswicke","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This is the highly amusing tale of Reverend Lee, who does not realise that his dyslexia is affecting his sermons.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34858/superhero-street.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34858","title":"Superhero Street","author":"by Phil Earle","description":"Superhero Street is a heartwarming and laugh-out-loud read that celebrates mums as the everyday superheroes they are. Sara Ogilvie's illustrations add an even more warm, hilarious background to Earle's realistic family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30192/bumface.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30192","title":"Bumface","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"An extremely funny story, with a touch of poignancy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29291/diary-of-a-wimpy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29291","title":"Diary of a Wimpy Kid","author":"by Jeff Kinney","description":"Greg Heffley is a normal American kid, albeit one with a habit of getting into (and out of) trouble.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24958/9781408817261-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24958","title":"Girl 15 Charming But Insane","author":"by Sue Limb","description":"Laugh-out-loud funny, a riotous take on Jane Austen’s Emma that is both snazzy and very contemporary","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25663/henry-tumour.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25663","title":"Henry Tumour","author":"by Anthony McGowan","description":"Henry Tumour is certainly a memorable book: it's funny, shocking, and thought-provoking, too. Just be warned that the language is extreme throughout!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29396/angus-thongs-and-full-frontal-snogging.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29396","title":"Angus, Thongs and Full-Frontal Snogging","author":"by Louise Rennison","description":"Welcome to the world of Georgia Nicolson - an angst-ridden teenage girl who keeps a diary to record the rollercoaster of emotions and experiences she faces every day","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30903/alienography.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30903","title":"Alienography","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Have you ever feared a Martian attack? This book recommends creeping up close enough to plant a big wet slobbery kiss on their slimy skins – your germs will do the rest to defeat them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24649/dirty-bertie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24649","title":"Dirty Bertie","author":"by David Roberts","description":"This fun picture book about the not-so-nice side of a typical little boy will make children laugh out loud!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31572/9780230753136-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31572","title":"It’s a Book","author":"by Lane Smith","description":"Jackass, playing on his computer, wants to know what Monkey is up to. Monkey is reading a book","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29053/mrgum-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29053","title":"Mr Gum and the Dancing Bear","author":"by Andy Stanton","description":"Mr Gum is a very nasty man. He is mean, cruel, smelly and ruthless and has a dastardly plan to make money out of Padlock the bear.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29648/9780007279067-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29648","title":"Mr Stink","author":"by David Walliams","description":"Irreverant and charming, this is a hilarious and surprisingly touching story about secrets, love and life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":48,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/48/","title":"Ten books with words and pictures","list_description":"Here are ten books in which words and pictures work really well together. The list reflects the fact that books with pictures are not just for the very young; some will appeal most to teenagers and adults.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24866/handa-s-surprise.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24866","title":"Handa's Surprise","author":"by Eileen Browne","description":"Glorious images of an African village convey the sights, smells and colours of the landscape, its animals and its food in a story told as much through pictures as through words.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29317/box-of-tricks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29317","title":"Box of Tricks","author":"by Katie Cleminson","description":"Every child loves an empty box and here, with the help of some magic, it contains a fantasy birthday party.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26003/penguin-by-polly-dunbar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26003","title":"Penguin","author":"by Polly Dunbar","description":"Polly Dunbar's illustrations are gorgeous and her palette stylish - from the endearing Ben's rosy cheeks to the magnificent turquoise lion who eats him up.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29125/the-graveyard-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29125","title":"The Graveyard Book","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"After his family are killed, Bod is brought up in a graveyard by ghosts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25021/wolves-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25021","title":"Wolves","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"This is a humorous, highly imaginative and original picture book and even comes with an alternative vegetarian ending!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29291/diary-of-a-wimpy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29291","title":"Diary of a Wimpy Kid","author":"by Jeff Kinney","description":"Greg Heffley is a normal American kid, albeit one with a habit of getting into (and out of) trouble.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29442/outlaw-the-legend-of-robin-hood.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29442","title":"Outlaw: The Legend of Robin Hood","author":"by Tony Lee","description":"This is a captivating retelling of the Robin Hood story with punchy dialogue and suitably dark and atmospheric images.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29053/mrgum-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29053","title":"Mr Gum and the Dancing Bear","author":"by Andy Stanton","description":"Mr Gum is a very nasty man. He is mean, cruel, smelly and ruthless and has a dastardly plan to make money out of Padlock the bear.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29332/tales-from-outer-suburbia-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29332","title":"Tales From Outer Suburbia","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"These often thought-provoking stories look at the reactions ordinary people have to the unusual situations they find themselves in and feature a host of different illustrative styles ranging from collage to painterly Edward Hopper-esque scenes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25811/tracey-beaker.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25811","title":"The Story of Tracy Beaker","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Tracy lives in a children's home but constantly hopes that her absent, glamorous Mum will come and take her away.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":49,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/49/","title":"Children's books about summer","list_description":"Celebrate the sun with these children's books set during the summer holidays. The books below are some of our favourite children's titles about the summertime.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25547/penderwicks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25547","title":"The Penderwicks","author":"by Jeanne Birdsall","description":"Four eccentric sisters and their loving but distracted father take a holiday cottage in the beautiful Arundel estate.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25829/melrose-and-croc.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25829","title":"Melrose and Croc Beside the Sea","author":"by Emma Chichester Clark","description":"Little Green Croc is sulking and won't speak to his friend, Melrose the dog. Melrose decides to cheer up his pal. This is a delightful, heartwarming story about friendship.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25785/canuhearsea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25785","title":"Can You Hear the Sea?","author":"by Judy Cumberbatch","description":"This is a gentle, lovely story about taking time to notice what lies beyond the chaos of everyday life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33745/peas-book-of-holidays.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33745","title":"Pea's Book of Holidays","author":"by Susie Day","description":"Susie Day returns with another hugely fun installment of the delightful Pea's Book series. Whether or not they've read about Pea's previous adventures, young readers will enjoy the gentle humour of this entertaining contemporary spin on the classic family story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25693/seal_surfer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25693","title":"Seal Surfer","author":"by Michael Foreman","description":"A welcome re-publication of Foreman's timeless and evocative account of a boy's relationship with life and death.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29281/lightingthief.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29281","title":"Percy Jackson and the Lightning Thief","author":"by Rick Riordan","description":"In this leftfield comic fantasy novel, 12-year-old Percy Jackson discovers that the Greek gods of Olympus are alive and living in modern-day New York.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33624/rules-of-summer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33624","title":"Rules of Summer","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"An excellent book illustrating 'what I learned last summer' that would be an inspiring addition to any bookshelf.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5","interest_age":"Interest level: 7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25572/beepbeep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25572","title":"Beep, Beep, Let's Go!","author":"by Eleanor Taylor","description":"A family of dogs are setting off for the seaside in their car. Along the way they are joined by a menagerie of their friends.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29860/buried-alive.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29860","title":"Buried Alive!","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"This humorous tale sensitively highlights issues such as friendship and bullying.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":50,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/50/","title":"Our favourite poetry books","list_description":"From re-invented fairy tales to classics from Poet Laureate Carol Ann Duffy, here are some poetry books your child is sure to love and want to read out loud.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31796/goldilocks-on-cctv.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31796","title":"Goldilocks on CCTV","author":"by John Agard","description":"By turns funny, poignant and insightful Agard’s poems are told with a direct and distinctive voice","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32636/9781406317015.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32636","title":"Orange, Silver, Sausage: Poems without rhymes from Zephaniah to Agard","author":"by James Carter","description":"Orange Silver Sausage is a wholly unique anthology, lovingly compiled by James Carter and Graham Denton. It contains over 50 non–rhyming poems of every shape and size, in a wide array of voices from many of the UK’s top poets.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30413/allthewonders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30413","title":"All the Wild Wonders: Poems of the Earth","author":"by Edited by Wendy Cooling","description":"Celebrating the wonder and variety of the earth - and the need to protect it - this is an eclectic collection of poetry from across time and continents.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34443/hog-shrew-hullabaloo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34443","title":"The Hog, the Shrew and the Hullabaloo","author":"by Julia Copus","description":"Harry the Hog is fast asleep until a strange noise wakes him up."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24811/heartbeat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24811","title":"Heartbeat","author":"by Sharon Creech","description":"Annie loves drawing, running barefoot, her family, and possibly Max, her running partner. It’s an eventful time for the 12-year-old: as her mother is about to give birth, her beloved grandfather is sliding slowly into dementia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34554/oned.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34554","title":"One","author":"by Sarah Crossan","description":"This is a book that goes straight into your heart and once it is there, won't leave. One is a brilliant, beautiful, and heart-wrenching novel that is not to be missed.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31322/crazy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31322","title":"Crazy Mayonnaisy Mum","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"There is a poem to appeal to everyone in this thoughtful and fun collection","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29510/new-and-collected-poems-for-children.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29510","title":"New and Collected Poems for Children","author":"by Carol Ann Duffy","description":"Poet Laureate, Carol Ann Duffy, brings together the best of her poems for children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34767/mr-mistoffelees.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34767","title":"Mr Mistoffelees, The Conjuring Cat","author":"by TS Eliot and Arthur Robbins","description":"With magic tricks, incredible illusions and astonishing spectacles, both old and new fans will adore meeting the conjuring cat, Mr Mistoffelees, the second of the Old Possum's illustrated picture books. Arthur Robins brings this magical cat bursting to life. A..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25380/tedhughespoems.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25380","title":"Collected Poems for Children","author":"by Ted Hughes","description":"All Hughes readers might expect the crows, horses and sheep they encounter here, but the haggis/bagpipe hybrid might be more of a surprise!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28157/red-cherry-red.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28157","title":"Red, Cherry Red","author":"by Jackie Kay","description":"Truthful, soulful and witty poems in this collection explore a theme of identity. Who are we? What reveals us? Is our identity bound up in where we live or in the dreams we hold?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25381/sensational-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25381","title":"Sensational!","author":"by Roger McGough","description":"Every poem could inspire a child's writing, reading or thinking, and their teachers' too.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30379/michael-rosen-s-a-z-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30379","title":"Michael Rosen's A to Z","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":"Former Children’s Laureate, Michael Rosen, gathers together the best children’s poetry from Agard to Zephaniah in this collection. From Grace Nichol's poem about her Caribbean Gran visiting England to Rosen's own hilarious account of his Dad's intolerance to 'The Noise',...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34627/a-great-big-cuddle-front-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34627","title":"A Great Big Cuddle","author":"by Michael Rosen and Chris Riddell","description":"Beautifully illustrated poems for young children by two Children's Laureates","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31871/green-glass-beads.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31871","title":"Green Glass Beads","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"An eclectic collection of poetry that mixes old and contemporary, funny and deadly serious poems","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29226/j-is-for-jamaica.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29226","title":"J is for Jamaica","author":"by Benjamin Zephaniah","description":"Welcome to this whistle-stop tour of Jamaica - from A for Ackee to Z for Zinc.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35284/it-s-not-fine-to-sit-on-a-porcupine.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35284","title":"It’s Not Fine to Sit on a Porcupine","author":"by Neal Zetter","description":"An amusingly illustrated collection of humorous poems from an award-winning performance poet, which covers a wide range of funny and interesting subjects.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-11"}]}
{"id":52,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/52/","title":"Summer reads","list_description":"The sun's out, your holiday's planned - now all you need to do is decide which books you're going to take with you.  Here is a selection of books we've enjoyed over the last year. Whether you like short stories, fiction or non-fiction, we hope that you'll find something to enjoy among these titles. Happy holiday reading!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28996/i-was-told-there-d-be-cake.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28996","title":"I Was Told There'd Be Cake","author":"by Sloane Crosley","description":"Wittier than a convention of Woody Allen impersonators, and considerably more attractive, Sloane (I like to think of us on first-name terms) is a sassy, snappy New York girl with a good line in both withering condescension and touching uncertainty."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29423/grace-tamar-and-laszlo-the-beautiful.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29423","title":"Grace, Tamar and Laszlo the Beautiful","author":"by Deborah Kay Davies","description":"Spanning more than 30 years in the lives of Grace and Tamar and their family, Davies’s stories are short, sharp snapshots of childhood, adolescence, coming-of-age, marriage, divorce and the messiness of all the living that has to go on in..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28929/bloody-old-britain.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28929","title":"Bloody Old Britain","author":"by Kitty Hauser","description":"This grandiose manifesto was written by one of archaeology's lesser known heroes, a tactiturn man, who - as Kitty Hauser shows in this remarkable book - devoted most of his life both to his work and a twentieth-century political ideal,..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29416/unaccustomed-earth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29416","title":"Unaccustomed Earth","author":"by Jhumpa Lahiri","description":"In Jhumpa Lahiri's beautifully crafted stories about Bengali families in America, the sense of cultural and emotional dislocation is never far from the surface."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29261/it-s-beginning-to-hurt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29261","title":"It's Beginning to Hurt","author":"by James Lasdun","description":"There's something disarmingly low-key about James Lasdun's writing, a hard-to-define tone that nevertheless draws the reader deep into the specific moment of each story."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29274/in-other-rooms.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29274","title":"In Other Rooms, Other Wonders","author":"by Daniyal Mueenuddin","description":"In this beautiful and assured collection, Daniyal Mueenuddin works and reworks the eternal themes of life, love and death. His control never wavers - neither does his compassion."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28796/the-collector-of-worlds.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28796","title":"The Collector of Worlds","author":"by Iliya Troyanov","description":"There is something fitting about the fact that the author of a novel about Victorian soldier, explorer, linguist and polymath Richard Francis Burton is a Bulgarian whose family fled to West Germany to escape persecution before he emigrated to Kenya..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28789/breath.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28789","title":"Breath","author":"by Tim Winton","description":"REPRESENTING AUSTRALIA Tim Winton is one of the finest authors currently at work anywhere in the world, and Breath builds upon his reputation for writing novels that carefully pick away at relationships which exist in the context of almost overpowering..."}]}
{"id":53,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/53/","title":"Graphic Novels","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29473/fun-home.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29473","title":"Fun Home","author":"by Alison Bechdel","description":"Bechdel's moving 'graphic autobiography' beautifully tells the story of her strange childhood and adolescence in the funeral home run by her father.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29471/ghost-world.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29471","title":"Ghost World","author":"by Daniel Clowes","description":"This is an examination of the lives of two recent high school graduates from the advantaged perch of a constant and undetectable eavesdropper, with the shaky detachment of a scientist who has grown fond of the prize microbes in his...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30322/wilson.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30322","title":"Wilson","author":"by Daniel Clowes","description":"Once again Daniel Clowes proves himself to be the master of the graphic novel and the celebrator of the loveable loser."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31361/transmetropolitan.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31361","title":"Transmetropolitan","author":"by Warren Ellis","description":"After years of selfimposed exile from a civilization rife with degradation and indecency, cynical journalist Spider Jerusalem is forced to return to a job he hates and a city he loathes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31358/omega-the-unknown.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31358","title":"Omega the Unknown","author":"by Jonathan Lethem","description":"The story of a mute, reluctant super hero from another planet, and the earthly teenager with whom he shares a strange destiny.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31359/kick-ass.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31359","title":"Kick-Ass","author":"by Mark Millar","description":"Dave Lizewski is just an ordinary American teenager. He has a MySpace page, he loves comic books, and he is unable to find a girlfriend. Then an idea hits him: why not become a real life super hero?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31360/jamilti-and-other-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31360","title":"Jamilti and Other Stories","author":"by Rutu Modan","description":"Stories that range from darkly fantastical and unsettling to surprising discoveries that shape personal identity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29460/watchmens.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29460","title":"Watchmen","author":"by Alan Moore and Dave Gibbons","description":"This is the superlative post-modern superhero tale involving pulp noir, science, hubris, the Cold War, love, lust, craziness and pirates.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29475/the-league-of-extraodinary-gentleman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29475","title":"The League of Extraordinary Gentlemen","author":"by Alan Moore and Kevin ONeill","description":"The League of Extraordinary Gentlemen is comics scriptwriting supremo Alan Moore's incredible, reinvention of classic heroes and villains."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30862/the-night-bookmobile.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30862","title":"The Night Bookmobile","author":"by Audrey Niffenegger","description":"In the early hours of a summer morning, a young woman encounters a mysterious mobile library while walking down an empty suburban street.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29472/persepolis.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29472","title":"Persepolis","author":"by Marjane Satrapi","description":"Persepolis is Satrapi's history of Iran and her life in Iran and France as she tries to retain her Iranian culture but also grow up and become independent.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29463/maus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29463","title":"Maus","author":"by Art Spiegelman","description":"This is the complete story of Vladek Spiegelman and his wife, living and surviving in Hitler's Europe.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31362/alice-in-sunderland.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31362","title":"Alice in Sunderland","author":"by Bryan Talbot","description":"Alice in Sunderland is a graphic novel like no other. Bryan Talbot takes the city of Sunderland and the story of Lewis Carroll and Alice Liddell (the ‘real’ Alice) as the spine of his story and around them spins a...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29332/tales-from-outer-suburbia-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29332","title":"Tales From Outer Suburbia","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"These often thought-provoking stories look at the reactions ordinary people have to the unusual situations they find themselves in and feature a host of different illustrative styles ranging from collage to painterly Edward Hopper-esque scenes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30455/shortcomings.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30455","title":"Shortcomings","author":"by Adrian Tomine","description":"Faber reprints this gloriously arch and bittersweet graphic novel by Adrian Tomine, surely one of the biggest reasons to not dismiss graphic novels as worthy competitors in the sphere of literary fiction.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25942/jimmy-corrigan.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25942","title":"Jimmy Corrigan:","author":"by Chris Ware","description":"This extraordinary graphic novel is so obviously a labour of love that the reader can only marvel at the energy that has been expended in its creation.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25871/the-complete-calvin-and-hobbes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25871","title":"The Complete Calvin and Hobbes","author":"by Bill Watterson","description":"The comic-strip adventures of Calvin, a naughty boy with a philosophical bent, and his soft toy tiger companion Hobbes, delighted readers from 1985 to 1995.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":54,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/54/","title":"Carol Ann Duffy","list_description":"Five books by Carol Ann Duffy, the Poet Laureate.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26472/the-hat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26472","title":"The Hat","author":"by Carol Ann Duffy","description":"Bubbling over with humour and life, the poems in The Hat paint pictures, evoke smells, conjure sounds and encapsulate events both contemporary and historical.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29300/answering-back.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29300","title":"Answering Back","author":"by Carol Ann Duffy","description":"Carol Ann Duffy has invited 50 of her peers to choose and respond to a poem from the past."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29301/the-world-s-wife.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29301","title":"The World's Wife","author":"by Carol Ann Duffy","description":"This collection of poems about the women forgotten by history is witty, intelligent and funny, but it also tackles serious themes such as loneliness, jealousy, self-loathing, desire, and domestic tragedy."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29302/rapture.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29302","title":"Rapture","author":"by Carol Ann Duffy","description":"Rapture is a map of real love, in all its churning complexity; simultaneously direct and subtle, with poems that will find deep resonance in the experience of readers."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29303/feminine-gospels.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29303","title":"Feminine Gospels","author":"by Carol Ann Duffy","description":"With themes of beauty, identity and the body, the book tells tall stories as though they were the gospel truth, and presents new myths as strange and powerful as the old."}]}
{"id":55,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/55/","title":"American short story collections","list_description":"Ten American short story collections we love.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25888/the-dead-fish-museum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25888","title":"The Dead Fish Museum","author":"by Charles D'Ambrosio","description":"The range and depth of the stories in The Dead Fish Museum is matched only by the attention to detail which D'Ambrosio has invested in every line. Here are multi-layered tales of masculinity, botched relationships, psychological breakdown, sexual desire and..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29458/one-more-year.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29458","title":"One More Year","author":"by Sana Krasikov","description":"REPRESENTING GEORGIA A numbing, almost debilitating melancholia infects the exiled, as Sana Krasikov shows in this haunting debut collection."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29416/unaccustomed-earth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29416","title":"Unaccustomed Earth","author":"by Jhumpa Lahiri","description":"In Jhumpa Lahiri's beautifully crafted stories about Bengali families in America, the sense of cultural and emotional dislocation is never far from the surface."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25878/dead-girls.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25878","title":"Dead Girls","author":"by Nancy Lee","description":"Loosely linked by a man's conviction for the murder of a number of prostitutes, Lee's stories all have a dark undercurrent of despondency running through them: the fumblings of teenage sex; recreational drug use gone wrong; fractured relationships between parents..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33748/9780224099523.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33748","title":"Thunderstruck","author":"by Elizabeth McCracken","description":"A collection of nine stories from the author of Here's Your Hat, What's Your Hurry."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25884/gallatin-canyon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25884","title":"Gallatin Canyon","author":"by Thomas McGuane","description":"Thomas McGuane is a very funny writer, but the almost desperate humour in his stories is leavened by a sense of deep loneliness."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28024/the-secret-goldfish.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28024","title":"The Secret Goldfish","author":"by David Means","description":"This collection opens with a story about a man who has been repeatedly struck by lightning and is waiting for a final blast to finish him off for good."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33524/bark.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33524","title":"Bark","author":"by Lorrie Moore","description":"Lorrie Moore's short story collection features stories of people alone in new situations."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25939/how-to-breathe-underwater.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25939","title":"How to Breathe Underwater","author":"by Julie Orringer","description":"'Outstanding'; 'unbelievably good'; 'pitch perfect'; clear, cool and enticing'; 'subtle and multi-layered': these are just some of the justified reactions to Julie Orringer's first collection of short stories."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27851/last-night.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27851","title":"Last Night: Stories","author":"by James Salter","description":"In some ways the ten disturbing, compelling stories in Last Night are old-fashioned; men are manly, women are beautiful, and each one comes with a killer twist. Yet the stories' central themes - betrayal and the way it almost carelessly..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29461/everything-ravaged-everything-burned.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29461","title":"Everything Ravaged, Everything Burned","author":"by Wells Tower","description":"Tower has an uncanny and slightly alarming gift for bringing society's downbeats to our appalled attention. Also like Pollock, he roots these unfortunates in the small, tortured worlds of their relationships, from which, it seems, there is little chance of..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29457/the-maples.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29457","title":"The Maples Stories","author":"by John Updike","description":"Written over a period of more than twenty years, John Updike's stories about Richard and Joan Maple and their family sit handsomely together in this beautiful little volume."}]}
{"id":56,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/56/","title":"Funny Books","list_description":"Seven days without laughter makes one weak.  The nights have drawn in, it's cold, summer's a distant memory, there's a bitter chill in the wind - the best thing to do is laugh. And you can with these 10 novels that have made us laugh. From the curiously absurd to the classically wry to the best book set in Russia about penguins and the mafia, this list is guaranteed to warm your cockles with hearty laughs and paroxysms of guffaws.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29618/hgttg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29618","title":"Hitch-hikers Guide to the Galaxy","author":"by Douglas Adams","description":"The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy is officially one of the funniest books ever written.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29621/the-rotters-club.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29621","title":"The Rotters' Club","author":"by Jonathan Coe","description":"Jonathan Coe's warm and heartening look back at the 1970s and its fashions and tastes is a zesty comedy full of acute observations about growing up and being an awkward teenager at school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29623/bridget-jones.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29623","title":"Bridget Jones' Diary","author":"by Helen Fielding","description":"Bridget Jones wants to have it all - and once she's given up smoking and got down to 8st 7 she will."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29619/the-collector-collector.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29619","title":"The Collector Collector","author":"by Tibor Fischer","description":"Tibor Fischer's The Collector Collector is a bizarre anecdotal curio of laugh-out-loud absurdity and ridiculousness."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27086/high-fidelity.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27086","title":"High Fidelity","author":"by Nick Hornby","description":"Each character is drawn so lovingly and with enough one-liners to floor a novel-sized elephant, making the book a masterstroke of modern-day humour."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29616/blue-heaven.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29616","title":"Blue Heaven","author":"by Joe Keenan","description":"Written by one of the head writers of Frasier, this novel relocates Wodehouse/Evelyn Waugh-style hijinks to upper-class Manhattan homes, featuring an ebullient cast of loud and proud characters all scheming and scamming to get what they want."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25887/death-and-the-penguin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25887","title":"Death and the Penguin","author":"by Andrey Kurkov","description":"Set in post-Soviet Ukraine, this little gem of a novel follows the fortunes of Viktor, an aspiring short story writer, and his pet penguin Misha."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29615/a-confederacy-of-dunces.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29615","title":"A Confederacy of Dunces","author":"by John Kennedy Toole","description":"Ignatius is a testament to sloth, rage and contempt, a behemoth of fat, flatulence and furious suspicion of anything modern, a horrible man, a noble crusader against a world of dunces."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29622/sagharbor.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29622","title":"Sag Harbor","author":"by Colson Whitehead","description":"Sag Harbor is a warm and funny piece of literary comedy that is laidback like the summer it depicts and staunchly proud of its identity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":57,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/57/","title":"Biography and memoir","list_description":"'People write memoirs because they lack the imagination to make things up.' Tom Robbins The festive season is upon us. The supermarkets are heaving with novelty boxes of biscuits, tinsel and celebrity biographies. Lives of note and celebrity and creativity are inspiring to read. Whether we're writers and musicians ourselves, or in similar industries or have travelled or are interested in the geographic areas described, the biography and the memoir are both powerful mediums for telling stories, true and honest and funny and poignant. We've put together a new book list of ten biographies and memoirs that are engaging, honest and interesting.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34440/9781782112846.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34440","title":"Guantánamo Diary","author":"by (Editor) Larry Siems","description":"A biography about a man incarcerated in Guantánamo Diary - he has been tortured, trapped and as of yet not charged for a crime."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29661/we-can-t-all-be-astronauts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29661","title":"We Can't All Be Astronauts","author":"by Tim Clare","description":"Stand up poet Tim Clare's memoir of trying to write and publish the perfect book, mired by peer-jealousy and depression, is the best tool for any budding writer wanting an insight into the creative process."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29663/9780141015743.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29663","title":"What is the What","author":"by Dave Eggers","description":"This is the oral history of Valentino Achak Deng, a survivor of the Sudan genocide and now a political speaker and activist on the future of Sudan."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29664/dear-fatty.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29664","title":"Dear Fatty","author":"by Dawn French","description":"This book is entertaining, inspiring and a brilliant read. Dawn French has led a very interesting life; and it is a pleasure to read about personal events that have had such an impact on her."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34059/9781409142294.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34059","title":"The Best in the World - At What I Have No Idea","author":"by Chris Jericho with Peter Thomas Fornatale","description":"A look at WWE Wrestler and musician Chris Jericho's life in the ring and on tour"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29666/a-beginner-s-guide-to-acting-english.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29666","title":"A Beginner's Guide to Acting English","author":"by Shappi Khorsandi","description":"This breakout memoir by comedienne Shappi Khorsandi documents her arrival and early to teen years in the UK trying to fit in. More poignant than laugh-out-loud funny, more tragic and beautiful than punchline-fodder."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29659/long-walk-to-freedom.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29659","title":"Long Walk to Freedom","author":"by Nelson Mandela","description":"Long Walk to Freedom discloses a strong and generous spirit that refused to be broken under the most trying circumstances - a spirit in which just about everybody can find something to admire.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 16+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31529/supergodss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31529","title":"Supergods","author":"by Grant Morrison","description":"This is partly a potted history of superheroes, from the inception of Superman and everything he represented to the present day and partly a memoir of Morrison’s own work, from creating the gamechanging Arkham Asylum arc of Batman to his...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29658/dreams-from-my-father.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29658","title":"Dreams From My Father","author":"by Barack Obama","description":"Obama is an engaging writer, filled with wide-eyed optimism, struggling to reconcile his identity (being the son of a black father and a white mother) amidst the backdrop of American racial politics.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29660/seeing-things.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29660","title":"Seeing Things","author":"by Oliver Postgate","description":"This loving and beautifully constructed autobiography tells the story of the mind that created Bagpuss, The Clangers and Noggin the Nog."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29662/the-boy-with-the-topknot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29662","title":"The Boy with the Topknot","author":"by Sathnam Sanghera","description":"The book moves along quickly, never boring, always painting an interesting picture of a family dealing with mental illness and a family dealing with the cultural differences of old and new, East and West.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29472/persepolis.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29472","title":"Persepolis","author":"by Marjane Satrapi","description":"Persepolis is Satrapi's history of Iran and her life in Iran and France as she tries to retain her Iranian culture but also grow up and become independent.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34055/9780241971994.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34055","title":"Foxcatcher","author":"by Mark Schultz with Dave Thomas","description":"A biography about Olympic-medal winner Mark Schultz, whose brother was murdered by millionaire John Du Pont"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29463/maus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29463","title":"Maus","author":"by Art Spiegelman","description":"This is the complete story of Vladek Spiegelman and his wife, living and surviving in Hitler's Europe.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33502/bedsit-disco.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33502","title":"Bedsit Disco Queen: How I Grew Up and Tried to be a Pop Star","author":"by Tracey Thorn","description":"Tracy Thorn - lead singer of Everything But the Girl - writes about her 30-year career."}]}
{"id":58,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/58/","title":"Books about India","list_description":"'India is the cradle of the human race, the birthplace of human speech, the mother of history, the grandmother of legend, and the great grandmother of tradition.' Mark Twain To celebrate Channel 4's Indian Winter season, we thought we would put together a list of ten books about India. These are in no way prescriptive or 'the best.' So much is written about the country that we couldn't possibly cover everything. These books range between ones you will have heard of and ones you haven't, but the common strand between them is that the authors all present their own takes on aspects of modern India, almost unrecognisable from the India of the past, and this is why they were chosen.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29071/the-white-tiger.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29071","title":"The White Tiger","author":"by Aravind Adiga","description":"Over the course of seven nights, the White Tiger tells his story in Adiga's Man Booker Prize-winning debut novel. What we learn about India is the twin worlds of the bleak, soul-destroying poverty of village life and the glittering prizes..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29704/bunker-13.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29704","title":"Bunker 13","author":"by Aniruddha Bahal","description":"Bunker 13 is a visceral explosion of sex, drugs and war- unlike anything any Indian author has ever written, unlike any book that has ever been written."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29706/one-night-at-the-call-centre.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29706","title":"One Night at the Call Centre","author":"by Chetan Bhagat","description":"One Night At the Call Centre is a comedic look at modern India's interactions with the West, taking place in a call centre where we learn about the lives behind the voices on the end of the line when we..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29711/bollywood-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29711","title":"Bollywood Boy","author":"by Justine Hardy","description":"This amusing exploration of Bollywood and its twin extremes of extravagance and underworld by journalist Justine Hardy does justice to the high-concept day-glo filmi world of India."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29702/son-of-the-circus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29702","title":"Son of the Circus","author":"by John Irving","description":"No one could accuse John Irving of writing the same book twice. A Son of the Circus takes us out of the safety of his New England safe haven and relocates to India for a bizarre murder mystery involving twins..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29701/bombay-talkie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29701","title":"Bombay Talkie","author":"by Ameena Meer","description":"The book jolts into its relentless pace by starting at the end: main character Sabah's discovery of a dying boy in a temple; she knows him, she is connected to him."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29707/maximum-city.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29707","title":"Maximum City","author":"by Suketu Mehta","description":"Suketu Mehta's impressive and expansive non-fiction book about modern Mumbai is the definitive book about this massive city."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29705/shalimar-the-clown.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29705","title":"Shalimar the Clown","author":"by Salman Rushdie","description":"Maximilian Ophuls is knifed to death on the doorstep of his illegitimate daughter India, slaughtered by his Kashmiri driver, a mysterious figure who calls himself Shalimar, the Clown."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29703/are-you-experienced.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29703","title":"Are You Experienced","author":"by William Sutcliffe","description":"Are You Experienced? is a scathing satire of the enthusiastic gap year tradition of students heading to mystical climbs to 'find themselves.'"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29708/q-a.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29708","title":"Q and A","author":"by Vikas Swarup","description":"Before Slumdog Millionaire, there was Q&A, the book by Vikas Swarup. Ram Mohammed Thomas, a poor, 18-year old waiter from the wrong side of the tracks, becomes the biggest quiz-show winner in history, scooping a billion rupee prize"}]}
{"id":59,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/59/","title":"Love","list_description":"Love, love, love... love is all you need. If you're stuck for presents this Valentine's Day, look no further than our 'lovelist,' 15 books about love in all its epic, romantic, tragic, yearning glory. These books range from the classic to the contemporary, from the street-wise to the world-weary. Each one depicts love in its entirety, each one is love at its most true. So this Valentine's Day- forget the ubiquitous flowers and generic box of chocolates, go for the heart- give the gift of words.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29744/p-p.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29744","title":"Pride and Prejudice","author":"by Jane Austen","description":"Pride and Prejudice is an ironic novel of manners. In it the garrulous and empty-headed Mrs Bennet has only one aim - that of finding a good match for each of her five daughters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28476/noughts-and-crosses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28476","title":"Noughts and Crosses","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Callum is a Nought but his best friend Sephy is a Cross - the daughter of one of the most influential politicians in the country.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29748/wutheringheights.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29748","title":"Wuthering Heights","author":"by Emily Bronte","description":"Wuthering Heights is a wild, passionate story of the intense and almost demonic love between Catherine Earnshaw and Heathcliff.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29742/possession.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29742","title":"Possession","author":"by A S Byatt","description":"This Booker-winning novel is bound to set pulses racing and increase yearning and longing as its historical love affair affects the modern-day action."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29746/a-room-with-a-view.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29746","title":"A Room with a View","author":"by E M Forster","description":"A Room with a View is a sunny, brilliantly witty comedy of manners."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29740/far-from-the-madding.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29740","title":"Far from the Madding Crowd","author":"by Thomas Hardy","description":"Far from the Madding Crowd is perhaps the most pastoral of Hardy's Wessex novels. It tells the story of the young farmer Gabriel Oak and his love for and pursuit of the elusive Bathsheba Everdene, whose wayward nature leads her...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30066/song4summer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30066","title":"A Song for Summer","author":"by Eva Ibbotson","description":"A deliciously old-fashioned story, which encompasses love, adventure and a host of memorable characters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29741/romeo-and-juliet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29741","title":"Romeo and Juliet: Manga Shakespeare","author":"by Sonia Leong and William Shakespeare","description":"Set in modern Tokyo, with the Capulets and Montagues recast as organised-crime rivals, this racy retelling gets to the heart of the love story and the foolish rivalry that dooms it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26197/love-in-the-time-of.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26197","title":"Love in the Time of Cholera","author":"by Gabriel García Marquez","description":"Florentino Ariza has never forgotten his first love. He has waited nearly a lifetime in silence since his beloved Fermina married another man. No woman can replace her in his heart."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29736/frenchman-s-creek.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29736","title":"Frenchmans Creek","author":"by Daphne du Maurier","description":"Unhappy with her shallow existence and empty marriage in London, Lady Dona St Columb decides to leave Charles II's court and seek solace at her husband's remote Cornish estate, Navron, with her two young children."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29745/pursuitoflove.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29745","title":"The Pursuit of Love","author":"by Nancy Mitford","description":"This funny book is known for its portrayal of independent yet eccentric women and its depiction of love as being the ultimate goal despite its true course running far from smoothly.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29749/norwegian-wood.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29749","title":"Norwegian Wood","author":"by Haruki Murakami","description":"Like Proust's Madeleine cake, the Beatles song of the title sets off a wave of memories for the narrator, Toru Watanabe as his remembers his teenage relationships with fragile first love Naoko and impetuous and unpredictable Midori."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29737/the-english-patient.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29737","title":"English Patient","author":"by Michael Ondaatje","description":"The exhausted nurse, Hana; the maimed thief, Caravaggio; the wary bomb-defuser, Kip: each is haunted by the riddle of the English patient, the nameless burn victim who lies in an upstairs room."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27401/tipping-the-velvet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27401","title":"Tipping the Velvet","author":"by Sarah Waters","description":"Tipping the Velvet is as saucy, as tantalising, and as touching as the narrator's first encounter with the seductive but shame-ridden Miss Kitty Butler."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29738/love-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29738","title":"Love Me","author":"by Gemma Weekes","description":"Written in similes that drip with cultural relevance, rhythmical intelligence and poetical sibilance, she weaves textures into a simple tale where a punk rock girl falls in love with a hip-hop guy and obsesses over the perfect memory of a..."}]}
{"id":60,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/60/","title":"Cities in translation","list_description":"From Havana to Tokyo, from Oslo to Alexandria, from Lahore to Paris, these 10 books (8 in translation and 2 about far-off cities) are a good introduction to the world of international fiction and translated fiction, to different cities around the world and their offerings of danger, edge, vice and energy.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33523/hotel_brasil.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33523","title":"Hotel Brasil: The Mystery of the Severed Heads","author":"by Frei Betto","description":"A number of colourful characters are suspected of murder when a headless body turns up in the rundown hotel where they all live."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33421/almost_like_spring.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33421","title":"Almost Like Spring","author":"by Alex Capus","description":"An insight into the final weeks of Waldemar Velte and Kurt Sandweg - Switzerland's most notorious bank robbers."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26378/the-half-brother.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26378","title":"The Half Brother","author":"by Lars Saabye Christensen","description":"Winner of the Nordic Prize 2002, The Half Brother tells the story of an ordinary Norwegian family in the 1960s, set apart by extraordinary family members."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29803/burma-chronicles.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29803","title":"Burma Chronicles","author":"by Guy Delisle","description":"This graphic novel from Guy Delisle is a charming insight into a country notorious for its use of concealment and isolation as social control.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29802/the-alexandria-quartet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29802","title":"The Alexandria Quartet","author":"by Lawrence Durrell","description":"The Alexandria Quartet explores the sexual and political intrigues of a group of expatriates in Egypt before and after the Second World War."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34367/9781782270614.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34367","title":"Song for an Approaching Storm","author":"by Peter Fröberg Idling","description":"Set on the eve of an election in Cambodia in 1955 this is a thought-provoking book about a country on the cusp of change."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33428/the_spectre_of_alexander_wo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33428","title":"The Spectre of Alexander Wolf","author":"by Gaito Gazdanov","description":"Years after the Russian Revolution a man finds out that someone he thought he killed during battle didn't die - via a short story written by the victim."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29759/dreams-from-the-endz.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29759","title":"Dreams from the Endz","author":"by Faiza Guene","description":"A sharply observed, warm and witty exposé of life in the low-income outskirts of Paris."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26521/dirty-havana.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26521","title":"Dirty Havana Trilogy","author":"by Pedro Juan Gutirrez","description":"Pedro Juan is a reporter in Havana, but as existence in Cuba and his own life begin to collapse around him, he gives up the farce of a daily job, and begins to 'train himself to take nothing seriously.'"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29801/moth-smoke.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29801","title":"Moth Smoke","author":"by Mohsin Hamid","description":"This startling debut by Mohsin Hamid is a tightly packed exploration of Lahore's down and outers."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29805/978-1564785503.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29805","title":"The System of Vienna","author":"by Gert Jonke","description":"REPRESENTING AUSTRIA An astonishing and fantastical autobiographical novel, reminiscent of Italo Calvino and Laurence Sterne, The System of Vienna details Jonke's travels through Vienna by streetcar."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29800/city-of-god.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29800","title":"City of God","author":"by Paulo Lins","description":"Based on a true story, this is a sprawling, magnificently told epic about the history of gang life in Rio's favelas."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32948/9780857051769-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32948","title":"Brief Loves that Live Forever","author":"by Andrei Makine","description":"In a series of short, oblique episodes, essentially short stories, an unnamed narrator recalls his life as an orphan in the Soviet era, the brutality and stupidity of life under Communism, and the people that he encountered as he moved..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29749/norwegian-wood.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29749","title":"Norwegian Wood","author":"by Haruki Murakami","description":"Like Proust's Madeleine cake, the Beatles song of the title sets off a wave of memories for the narrator, Toru Watanabe as his remembers his teenage relationships with fragile first love Naoko and impetuous and unpredictable Midori."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33441/from_the_fatherland_with_lo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33441","title":"From the Fatherland, with Love","author":"by Ryu Murakami","description":"In a dystopian future Japan's last line of defence against a North Korean invasion comes in the form of a gang of social outcasts and misfits."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33452/barcelona_shadows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33452","title":"Barcelona Shadows","author":"by Marc Pastor","description":"Set in the early 1900s Barcelona, a brutal police Inspector tries to hunt down a sadistic, violent and cannibalistic child-killer."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29799/gomorrah.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29799","title":"Gomorrah: Italy's Other Mafia","author":"by Roberto Saviano","description":"Published to coincide with the eponymous blockbuster film, Roberto Saviano's groundbreaking and compelling book is a major international bestseller."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33882/9781908276384.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33882","title":"Nowhere People","author":"by Paulo Scott","description":"A young Brazillian student radical picks up a girl on the side of the motorway. From there the pair meet a range of people in an ever-changing Brazil."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33527/queens_necklace.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33527","title":"The Queen's Necklace","author":"by Antal Szerb","description":"A look at one of the remarkable and outrageous events that lead to the French Revolution."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33921/9781781722053.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33921","title":"Bilbao - New York - Bilbao","author":"by Kirmen Uribe","description":"The author muses about a varirty of topics whilst tarvelling to New York from Bilbao in order to research a book."}]}
{"id":61,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/61/","title":"Debuts","list_description":"Every year there are hundreds of debut novels published, and so many of them may pass us by unless they win prizes, or get picked up in the papers, or are adapted into films and on and on. We thought we'd put together a list of some of our favourite debut novels of recent times, from the sublime to the hilarious- from the mainstream to the literary, from short story collections to gritty urban tales.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33404/shadow-of-the-crescent-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33404","title":"The Shadow of the Crescent Moon","author":"by Fatima Bhutto","description":"Fatima Bhutto's debut novel tells the story of three brothers on the Pakistan-Afghan border whose lives take a devastating turn after they leave the house one morning. Normal 0 false false false EN-GB X-NONE X-NONE MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 /* Style Definitions */..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33653/9781843915157.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33653","title":"Spring Tide","author":"by Cilla & Rolf Börjlind","description":"A young police trainee looks into a 24-year-old cold-case her deceased father worked on before he dies."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33732/9781908968173.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33732","title":"Bonita Avenue","author":"by Peter Buwalda","description":"A very successful middle-class family implode when revelations of betrayal and guilt are revealed"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29843/a-heartbreaking-work-of-staggering-genius.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29843","title":"A Heartbreaking Work of Staggering Genius","author":"by Dave Eggers","description":"Balancing both anger and humour, this is a brilliant book, sparkling with a lightness of touch and full of warmth."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34617/414thufymtl._sx322_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34617","title":"Whispers Through a Megaphone","author":"by Rachel Elliott","description":"A look at what happens with relationships when people spend more time online than they do in the real world."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29620/then-we-came-to-an-end.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29620","title":"Then We Came to an End","author":"by Joshua Ferris","description":"Nothing, not even TV series The Office, comes close to this book in describing modern office life."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33505/terms-and-conditions.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33505","title":"Terms & Conditions","author":"by Robert Glancy","description":"The main protagonist in Robert Glancy's debut novel Terms & Conditions is Frank Shaw, a genius of a corporate lawyer renowned for his ability to create insurance contracts full of such unfathomable small print that insurance companies rarely have to..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34238/9781782270522.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34238","title":"One Night, Markovitch","author":"by Ayelet Gundar-Goshen","description":"Ayelet Gundar-Goshen's stunning debut novel expertly blends events of passion and upheaval, as well as the unrequited love and obsession of the title character for Bella."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29844/interpreter-of-maladies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29844","title":"Interpreter of Maladies","author":"by Jhumpa Lahiri","description":"With her experiences of three cultures - born in London of Bengali parents, and brought up on the east coast of America - Lahiri has been blessed with a selection of many narrative colours on her fictional palette."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27345/londonstani.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27345","title":"Londonstani","author":"by Gautam Malkani","description":"Set in Hounslow, Malkani's debut is about three tough Asian young men and the naive Jas, desperate to be in their gang and win the approval of Samira, a Muslim girl."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33697/9781908737670.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33697","title":"The Stillman","author":"by Tom McCulloch","description":"A curmudgeonly misanthrope whose life is passing him by meets a friend of his late mother in Cuba when he goes to settle her affairs."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33529/madness_of_july.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33529","title":"The Madness of July","author":"by James Naughtie","description":"Set in 1970s London during the height of the Cold War, a foreign minister with a secretaive past is drawn into a dangerous game when an America spy is found dead."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29700/tail-of-the-blue-bird.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29700","title":"Tail of the Blue Bird","author":"by Nii Ayikwei Parkes","description":"Nii Ayikwei Parkes' debut novel is a poetic, dreamy story about the influx of technology and modernity into rural Ghana, and the uneasy relationship between science and spirit.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33423/last_kings_of_sark.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33423","title":"The Last Kings of Sark","author":"by Rosa Rankin-Gee","description":"Three different people connect and experience life to the full one summer, but it's hard for them to adjust when that summer comes to an end."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27037/white-teeth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27037","title":"White Teeth","author":"by Zadie Smith","description":"Assured, audacious, good-hearted, impressive, raucous and funny: these are just some of the plaudits that greeted Zadie Smithís exuberant and incredibly successful debut novel."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29461/everything-ravaged-everything-burned.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29461","title":"Everything Ravaged, Everything Burned","author":"by Wells Tower","description":"Tower has an uncanny and slightly alarming gift for bringing society's downbeats to our appalled attention. Also like Pollock, he roots these unfortunates in the small, tortured worlds of their relationships, from which, it seems, there is little chance of..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29561/legend-of-a-suicide.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29561","title":"Legend of a Suicide","author":"by David Vann","description":"Five short short stories and one longer one about suicide might not be your idea of a relaxing fireside read but by approaching the same event from a number of angles Vann is able to successfully express the manifold effects..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29738/love-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29738","title":"Love Me","author":"by Gemma Weekes","description":"Written in similes that drip with cultural relevance, rhythmical intelligence and poetical sibilance, she weaves textures into a simple tale where a punk rock girl falls in love with a hip-hop guy and obsesses over the perfect memory of a..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29599/after-the-fire-a-still-small-voice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29599","title":"After the Fire, A Still Small Voice","author":"by Evie Wyld","description":"A sweet, sun-drenched, heart-felt love affair. Evie Wyld's debut novel slips across hard-edged themes of masculine expression, war, paternal relationships and grief with such beauty and ease that it feels like she is already an old hand."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33461/the_people_in_the_trees.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33461","title":"The People in the Trees","author":"by Hanya Yanagihara","description":"Hanya Yanagihara's debut novel tells the story about a pathologist whose memoirs have been edited by a colleague. The memoirs include his discovery of people who never age and his eventual imprisonment."}]}
{"id":62,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/62/","title":"Sport","list_description":"Here's a sports-themed booklist for you (ten fiction and five non-fiction), taking in football obsession, cricket in New York, the greatest boxing match ever and cycling as a way of life amongst others.  So, if you find yourself on the subs bench, you'll have plenty to read to pass the time.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31031/bicycle-diaries.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31031","title":"The Bicycle Diaries","author":"by David Byrne","description":"Filled with intimate photographs, incredible musical stories and a powerful ecological message, this is a enchanting celebration of bike riding."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31026/end-zone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31026","title":"End Zone","author":"by Don Delillo","description":"End Zone is a clever, playful and, above all, funny novel, which confirms DeLillo's status as one of the great American writers of the twentieth and twenty-first centuries.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27218/the-match.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27218","title":"The Match","author":"by Romesh Gunesekera","description":"As the sun goes down at the end of the match he realises that love, like cricket, is more than just a game. He sees one last chance to get his life into focus, if only there is time."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27035/fever-pitch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27035","title":"Fever Pitch","author":"by Nick Hornby","description":"The sport and one team in particular have crept into every aspect of Hornby's life- making him see the world through Arsenal-tinted spectacles."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31033/a-lot-of-hard-yakka.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31033","title":"Lot of Hard Yakka: Triumph and Torment: A County Cricketer's Life","author":"by Simon Hughes","description":"Packed with hilarious and embarrassing anecdotes about some of the greatest cricketers of the last 20 years."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31030/the-fight.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31030","title":"The Fight","author":"by Norman Mailer","description":"Norman Mailer's The Fight focuses on the 1975 World Heavyweight Boxing Championship in Kinshasa, Zaire, between Muhammad Ali and George Foreman.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31027/thenatural.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31027","title":"The Natural","author":"by Bernard Malamud","description":"This is a book about heroism, and it is a strange one. What makes Roy Hobbs potentially a hero is his immense natural gift for playing baseball.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31028/playing-days.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31028","title":"Playing Days","author":"by Benjamin Markovits","description":"Tinged with the melancholy and nostalgia of early steps into adulthood, it's the story of a young man's first experience of adult love, and of the discovery of his own limitations."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31023/netherland.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31023","title":"Netherland","author":"by Joseph O'Neill","description":"Netherland is a novel of belonging and not belonging, and the uneasy state in between."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31024/fight-club.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31024","title":"Fight Club","author":"by Chuck Palahniuk","description":"Every weekend, in basements and parking lots across the country, young men with good white-collar jobs and absent fathers take off their shoes and shirts and fight each other barehanded for as long as they have to."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25881/the-damned-united.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25881","title":"The Damned United","author":"by David Peace","description":"This is a brilliant portrait of a highly complex man; a feat of literary ventriloquism, and a powerful portrait of another era, when players warmed up with a couple of pints, a game of cards and a packet of fags,..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31029/double-fault.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31029","title":"Double Fault","author":"by Lionel Shriver","description":"Ever since she picked up a racquet at the age of four, tennis has been Willy's one love, until the day she meets Eric Oberdorf."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27867/the-loneliness-of-the-long-distance-runner.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27867","title":"The Loneliness of the Long distance Runner","author":"by Alan Sillitoe","description":"Sillitoe's depiction of petty crime and deep-seated anger in industrial and desperate cities remains as potent today as it was almost half a century ago.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"}]}
{"id":63,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/63/","title":"Travel memoirs","list_description":"For those with tickets to ride, we present our list of travel memoirs to help bring your holiday destinations to life.  Before you head off on summer holiday this year, check out our travel memoir booklist. You might even find something set in the countery you're visiting that may even point the way to adventure and new experiences. This list is far from definitive, but will hopefully whet your appetite for far-off lands and distant locations.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31039/in-patagonia.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31039","title":"In Patagonia","author":"by Bruce Chatwin","description":"In Patagonia is an account of Bruce Chatwin's travels to a remote country in search of a strange beast and his encounters with the people whose fascinating stories delay him on the road."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29803/burma-chronicles.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29803","title":"Burma Chronicles","author":"by Guy Delisle","description":"This graphic novel from Guy Delisle is a charming insight into a country notorious for its use of concealment and isolation as social control.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31038/mani.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31038","title":"Mani – Travels in the Southern Peloponnese","author":"by Patrick Leigh Fermor","description":"This is Patrick Leigh Fermor's spellbinding part-travelogue, part inspired evocation of a part of Greece's past."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31043/eat-pray-love.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31043","title":"Eat Pray Love","author":"by Elizabeth Gilbert","description":"It's 3 a.m. and Elizabeth Gilbert is sobbing on the bathroom floor. She's in her thirties, she has a husband, a house, they're trying for a baby - and she doesn't want any of it."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31042/assassinating-shakespeare.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31042","title":"Assassinating Shakespeare","author":"by Thomas Goltz","description":"In 1976, Thomas Goltz, then a naive twenty-one-year-old on the trail of his errant brother, worked his way around Africa putting on one-man Shakespeare performances.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31036/the-motorcycle-diaries.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31036","title":"The Motorcycle Diaries","author":"by Ernesto Guevara","description":"In January 1952, two young men from Buenos Aires set out to explore South America on 'La Poderosa', the Powerful One: a 500cc Norton motorcycle. One of them was the twenty-three-year-old Che Guevara."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31041/round-ireland-with-a-fridge.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31041","title":"Round Ireland with a Fridge","author":"by Tony Hawks","description":"I hereby bet Tony Hawks the sum of One Hundred Pounds that he cannot hitchhike round the circumference of Ireland, with a fridge, within one calendar month'."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31040/a-moveable-feast.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31040","title":"A Moveable Feast","author":"by Ernest Hemingway","description":"Hemingway's memories of his life as an unknown writer living in Paris in the 1920s are deeply personal, warmly affectionate and full of wit."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31037/on-the-road.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31037","title":"On the Road","author":"by Jack Kerouac","description":"On the Road swings to the rhythms of 1950s underground America, jazz, sex, generosity, chill dawns and drugs."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29601/six-months-in-sudan.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29601","title":"Six Months in Sudan","author":"by James Maskalyk","description":"With great hope and insight, Maskalyk illuminates a distant place - its heat, its people, its poverty, its war - to inspire possibilities for action."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29707/maximum-city.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29707","title":"Maximum City","author":"by Suketu Mehta","description":"Suketu Mehta's impressive and expansive non-fiction book about modern Mumbai is the definitive book about this massive city."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31034/9781407031323-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31034","title":"The Honey Gatherers","author":"by Mimlu Sen","description":"Mimlu Sen is living a bohemian life in Paris when she witnesses an electrifying performance by three wandering minstrels from rural India."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31035/surinam.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31035","title":"Surinam: Stumbling Through the Dark Heart of South America's Forgotten Jungle","author":"by Andrew Westoll","description":"Westoll explores Surinam's bloody past, the allure of its wild places, the legends and rituals of its extraordinary people. An honest and beautiful writer he conjures a place of golden light and impenetrable shadow, of long-held secrets and sacred stories."}]}
{"id":64,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/64/","title":"Science fiction/dystopian booklist","list_description":"Space... the final frontier. These are the booklists of the starship Book Trust. It's mission: to inspire a love of books; to seek out the best sci-fi and dystopia books and to boldly recommend titles that no one has done before!  Boldly going where no Book Trust booklist has gone before... discover dystopian worlds and intergalatic space in our sci-fi booklist.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29618/hgttg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29618","title":"Hitch-hikers Guide to the Galaxy","author":"by Douglas Adams","description":"The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy is officially one of the funniest books ever written.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31052/the-handmaid-s-tale.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31052","title":"The Handmaid’s Tale","author":"by Margaret Atwood","description":"The Republic of Gilead offers Offred only one function: to breed."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31048/oryx-and-cake.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31048","title":"Oryx and Crake","author":"by Margaret Atwood","description":"Pigs might not fly but they are strangely altered. So, for that matter, are wolves and racoons."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31051/feersum-endjinn.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31051","title":"Feersum Endjinn","author":"by Iain M Banks","description":"Count Sessine is about to die for the very last time.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31055/fahrenheit-451.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31055","title":"Fahrenheit 451","author":"by Ray Bradbury","description":"The hauntingly prophetic classic novel set in a not-too-distant future where books are burned by a special task force of firemen.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31044/do-androids-dream-of-electric.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31044","title":"Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?","author":"by Philip K Dick","description":"World War Terminus had left the Earth devastated. Through its ruins, bounty hunter Rick Deckard stalked, in search of the renegade replicants who were his prey.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31050/flowers4algernon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31050","title":"Flowers For Algernon","author":"by Daniel Keyes","description":"Charlie Gordon, IQ 68, is a floor sweeper, and the gentle butt of everyone's jokes, until an experiment in the enhancement of human intelligence turns him into a genius.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31047/gun-with-occasional-music.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31047","title":"Gun, with Occasional Music","author":"by Jonathan Lethem","description":"A science-fiction mystery, a dark and funny post-modern romp serving further evidence that Lethem is the distinctive voice of a new generation."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28824/knifeofneverlettinggo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28824","title":"The Knife of Never Letting Go","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"The first in a series, this enthralling sci-fi/fantasy novel grips readers throughout, presenting them with tough questions about identity, ethics and the nature of truth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27349/timetravelwife.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27349","title":"The Time Traveler's Wife","author":"by Audrey Niffenegger","description":"This extraordinary, magical novel is the story of Clare and Henry who have known each other since Clare was six and Henry was thirty-six, and were married when Clare was twenty-two and Henry thirty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31054/nineteen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31054","title":"Nineteen Eighty-Four","author":"by George Orwell","description":"Hidden away in the Record Department of the sprawling Ministry of Truth, Winston Smith skilfully rewrites the past to suit the needs of the Party.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31053/slaughterhouse-5.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31053","title":"Slaughterhouse 5","author":"by Kurt Vonnegut","description":"Prisoner of war, optometrist, time-traveller - these are the life roles of Billy Pilgrim, hero of this miraculously moving, bitter and funny story of innocence faced with apocalypse."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31049/waroworlds.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31049","title":"The War of the Worlds","author":"by H G Wells","description":"The whole of human civilisation is under threat, as powerful Martians build gigantic killing machines, destroy all in their path.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31046/ambient.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31046","title":"Ambient","author":"by Jack Womack","description":"In 21st century Manhattan, a good portion of the citizenry consists of freaks engendered by a nuclear accident on Long Island."}]}
{"id":65,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/65/","title":"International crime","list_description":"Mankell, Larsson, Nesbo may all be the current spearheads of the translated crime fiction revolution, but what about the macabre goings-on in Reykjavik, Paris, Havana, Breslau...?  Crime novels the world over have the universal appeal of macabre murders, grizzly policemen who won't play by the rules, clues and engaging readers in the problem-solving. With Henning Menkell, Stieg Larsson and Jo Nesbo all flying the flag for Scandanavian crime, we thought we would celebrate the expanse of novels available internationally... so here are ten of our favourite translated crime authors, and some of their books.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33703/9781843914983.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33703","title":"Death in Pont-Aven","author":"by Jean-Luc Bannalec","description":"In the small town of Pont-Aven on the Breton coast, a brutal murder takes place in the central hotel and the gruff Commissaire Dupin takes up the case, wading through lies, family secrets and the prejudices of the small town..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33523/hotel_brasil.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33523","title":"Hotel Brasil: The Mystery of the Severed Heads","author":"by Frei Betto","description":"A number of colourful characters are suspected of murder when a headless body turns up in the rundown hotel where they all live."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30737/the-baker-street-phantom.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30737","title":"The Baker Street Phantom","author":"by Fabrice Bourland","description":"London is in the grip of fear and a series of brutal, bloody murders. As the country cowers and looks for safety, of Messrs. Singleton and Trelawney quietly arrive from Boston to set up their own detective agency."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33421/almost_like_spring.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33421","title":"Almost Like Spring","author":"by Alex Capus","description":"An insight into the final weeks of Waldemar Velte and Kurt Sandweg - Switzerland's most notorious bank robbers."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30363/bad-intentions.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30363","title":"Bad Intentions","author":"by Karin Fossum","description":"In this, the seventh Sejer mystery to be translated into English, the detective is called upon to investigate a dead body floating in a lake by a remote cabin. The verdict is one of suicide, but Sejer is convinced there..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33420/closed_for_winter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33420","title":"Closed For Winter","author":"by Jorn Lier Horst","description":"Police Inspector William Wistig investigates a brutal murder at a holiday cottage. A murder that has consequences for his daughter"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31058/jar-city.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31058","title":"Jar City","author":"by Arnaldur Indridason","description":"A man is found murdered in his Reykjavik flat. There are no obvious clues apart from a cryptic note left on the body and a photograph of a young girl's grave."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31061/murder-on-the-eiffel-tower.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31061","title":"Murder on the Eiffel Tower","author":"by Claude Izner","description":"This is the first of a best-selling series of French murder mysteries now available in English for the first time. The series is a colourful evocation of late nineteenth-century Paris."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26965/death-in-breslau.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26965","title":"Death in Breslau","author":"by Marek Krajewski","description":"Marek Krajewski has written a quartet of novels which unfold the history of this exceptional city, standing on the faultline and crossroads of 20th century Europe."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31059/the-stonecutter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31059","title":"The Stonecutter","author":"by Camilla Lackberg","description":"The remote resort of Fjallbacka has seen its share of tragedy, though perhaps none worse than that of the little girl found in a fisherman's net. But the post-mortem reveals that this is no accidental drowning!"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33837/9781782066033.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33837","title":"Into a Raging Blaze","author":"by Andreas Norman","description":"The Swedish spy thriller that anticipated the Edward Snowden revelations."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26577/havana-red.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26577","title":"Havana Red","author":"by Leonardo Padura","description":"On 6 August 1989 the day on which the Catholic Church celebrates the Feast of the Transfiguration, the body of a strangled transvestite is discovered in the humid undergrowth of the Havana Woods."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33452/barcelona_shadows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33452","title":"Barcelona Shadows","author":"by Marc Pastor","description":"Set in the early 1900s Barcelona, a brutal police Inspector tries to hunt down a sadistic, violent and cannibalistic child-killer."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31056/the-chalk-circle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31056","title":"The Chalk Circle Man","author":"by Fred Vargas","description":"Jean-Baptiste Adamsberg is not like other policemen. His methods appear unorthodox in the extreme."}]}
{"id":66,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/66/","title":"Books set in Africa","list_description":"These books set in Africa carry a powerful tone, setting up the incredibly diverse talent in each country on the continent. From new debut authors to classic ones, from comedic takes on the student gap year to CSI-style investigations in rural Ghanaian villages, this booklist (something impossible to make definitive or exhaustive) showcases some of the best fiction from the African continent.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31063/things-fall-apart.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31063","title":"Things Fall Apart","author":"by Chinua Achebe","description":"Okonowo is the greatest warrior alive. His fame has spread like a bushfire in West Africa and he is one of the most powerful men of his clan. But he also has a fiery temper.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28107/half-of-a-yellow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28107","title":"Half of a Yellow Sun","author":"by Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie","description":"Half of a Yellow Sun is set in Nigeria during the 1960s, at the time of the vicious Nigeria- Biafra war in which more than a million people died and thousands were massacred in cold blood","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31065/the-sheltering-sky.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31065","title":"The Sheltering Sky","author":"by Paul Bowles","description":"The Sheltering Sky is a book about people on the edge of an alien space; somewhere where, curiously, 'they are never alone'."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31062/disgrace.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31062","title":"Disgrace","author":"by J M Coetzee","description":"This examination into the sexual and politcal lawlines of modern South Africa as it tries desperately to start a fresh page in its history is chilling, uncompromising and unforgettable."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31042/assassinating-shakespeare.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31042","title":"Assassinating Shakespeare","author":"by Thomas Goltz","description":"In 1976, Thomas Goltz, then a naive twenty-one-year-old on the trail of his errant brother, worked his way around Africa putting on one-man Shakespeare performances.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30404/broken-glass.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30404","title":"Broken Glass","author":"by Alain Mabanckou","description":"Alain Mabanckou's darkly glittering novel is an astringent portrait of post-colonial ennui and contemporary African social collapse, as well as a brilliantly witty homage to the written word."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31064/famishedroad.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31064","title":"The Famished Road","author":"by Ben Okri","description":"The Famished Road is the story of a spirit child Azaro. Azaro meaning 'born to die' has been born to his parents many a times only to die shortly after birth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29700/tail-of-the-blue-bird.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29700","title":"Tail of the Blue Bird","author":"by Nii Ayikwei Parkes","description":"Nii Ayikwei Parkes' debut novel is a poetic, dreamy story about the influx of technology and modernity into rural Ghana, and the uneasy relationship between science and spirit.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31066/ake.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31066","title":"Ake: The Years of Childhood","author":"by Wole Soyinka","description":"The first volume of Wole Soyinka's acclaimed series of autobiographical works. This vivid, exuberant book is the author's account of his childhood in colonial Nigeria.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33442/double_negative.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33442","title":"Double Negative","author":"by Ivan Vladislavić","description":"Set over several decades, Double Negative tells the story of a South Africa during and after the Apartheid."}]}
{"id":67,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/67/","title":"Books of the year 2010","list_description":"2010 saw the return of heavyweights like Peter Carey, David Mitchell and, after a long sabbatical, Jonathan Franzen. It was also the year that newcomers like Lee Rourke, Laura Dockrill and Anjali Joseph made a mark. It was the year of Tom McCarthy's astonishing C, and a sterling year for translated fiction, especially with the growth of new imprints like Pereine.  Here are Book Trust's books of the year, a mixture of literary fiction, graphic novels, short stories and translated fiction, hopefully showcasing the diversity not only of the books that we like here at Book House, but also, that have been commercially available this year.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30684/c.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30684","title":"C","author":"by Tom Mccarthy","description":"Set between the late nineteenth century and 1922, C traces the life of Serge Carrefax: a character born into the radio revolution. McCarthy's writing is exquisite, his sense of place and time beautifully rendered."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30322/wilson.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30322","title":"Wilson","author":"by Daniel Clowes","description":"Once again Daniel Clowes proves himself to be the master of the graphic novel and the celebrator of the loveable loser."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30718/echoes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30718","title":"Echoes","author":"by Laura Dockrill","description":"The new book from Laura Dockrill is a collection of modern-day fairytales, poems and retellings of classic stories, all with a slightly sinister edge. Reminiscent of Roald Dahl, Tim Burton and even Grimm, the stories take on a not-quite supernatural...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30679/freedom.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30679","title":"Freedom","author":"by Jonathan Franzen","description":"Freedom is about Patty and Walter Berglund and their precocious son and their perfect daughter. It's about how their pasts swirl around this seemingly perfect family into a series of repressions, depressions and obsessions."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30454/saraswati-park.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30454","title":"Saraswati Park","author":"by Anjali Joseph","description":"Saraswati Park is a book about loss and longing, love and regret. The prose sparkles like late afternoon sunshine and the characters hook you from their first introduction. This is a very special novel from a very special new talent."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30720/how-i-escaped-my-certain-fate.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30720","title":"How I Escaped My Certain Fate","author":"by Stewart Lee","description":"Stewart Lee is one of the country's most respected comedians, a tireless generator of new material and the inspiration for 'national treasure' Ricky Gervais, which is the cue for the start of this part-memoir/part-show transcript."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29715/even-the-dogs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29715","title":"Even the Dogs","author":"by Jon McGregor","description":"The new book from acclaimed author Jon McGregor is nothing short of intense. Filled with hope and fury, it is a poetic mediation on the lives and deaths of those who have fallen through the cracks."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30397/the-lost-world.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30397","title":"The Lost World","author":"by Patricia Melo","description":"This intelligent, fast-paced thriller takes us into the mind of a killer on a gripping road trip across Brazil."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30320/the-great-perhaps.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30320","title":"The Great Perhaps","author":"by Joe Meno","description":"The Caspars are falling apart as George W. Bush rushes towards reelection and the country towards paranoid door-closing. Joe Meno's book not only encapsulates a time in history, of paranoia and suspicion, of lack of faith in politics and maximised..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29720/skippy-dies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29720","title":"Skippy Dies","author":"by Paul Murray","description":"You probably won't read a funnier book than Skippy Dies this year. Told in three volumes, set in the grand Dublin institution of Seabrook School for Boys and featuring a cast of awkward teenagers looking for love and respect alike.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29819/beside-the-sea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29819","title":"Beside the Sea","author":"by Veronique Olmi","description":"On a rainy night, a mother sets out on a bus journey to the seaside with her two small sons, knowing that it will be the last trip they ever make. What she hopes will be a happy last memory..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30457/the-canal.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30457","title":"The Canal","author":"by Lee Rourke","description":"Part love story, part existential treatise, The Canal is brilliantly composed and utterly convincing. Also it is a book that takes on the modern world in all its contradictions with subtle strokes."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30719/death-of-an-unsigned-band.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30719","title":"Death of an Unsigned Band","author":"by Tim Thornton","description":"It's enjoyable, funny, bittersweet, and like the epic powerballad the band sometimes ends on, ultimately triumphant."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30459/the-financial-lives-of-the-poets.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30459","title":"The Financial Lives of the Poets","author":"by Jess Walter","description":"The Financial Lives of the Poets is very now, snappy, funny, filled with hilarious dialogue and brilliant representations of current zeitgeists."}]}
{"id":68,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/68/","title":"Heartbreaking Literature","list_description":"It's a well-worn cliche that the path of true love never runs smoothly.  It's also a well-worn cliche that the second week of February becomes a flutter of last minute bouquets of flowers and boxes of chocolates.  As an antidote to Valentine's Day we present ten books in this month's themed list, where the path of true love definitely DOES NOT run smoothly...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31408/9780297860099.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31408","title":"Lyrics Alley","author":"by Leila Aboulela","description":"Set in Sudan in the 1950s, Lyrics Alley tells the story of the wealthy and powerful Abuzeid dynasty"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29748/wutheringheights.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29748","title":"Wuthering Heights","author":"by Emily Bronte","description":"Wuthering Heights is a wild, passionate story of the intense and almost demonic love between Catherine Earnshaw and Heathcliff.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27541/what-we-talk-about.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27541","title":"What We Talk About When We Talk About Love","author":"by Raymond Carver","description":"With its spare, colloquial narration and razor-sharp sense of how people really communicate, this collection went on to become one of the most influential pieces of literary fiction."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29749/norwegian-wood.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29749","title":"Norwegian Wood","author":"by Haruki Murakami","description":"Like Proust's Madeleine cake, the Beatles song of the title sets off a wave of memories for the narrator, Toru Watanabe as his remembers his teenage relationships with fragile first love Naoko and impetuous and unpredictable Midori."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31068/9780099448426-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31068","title":"Doctor Zhivago","author":"by Boris Pasternak","description":"Doctor Zhivago is the epic novel of Russia in the throes of revolution and one of the greatest love stories ever told."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31029/double-fault.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31029","title":"Double Fault","author":"by Lionel Shriver","description":"Ever since she picked up a racquet at the age of four, tennis has been Willy's one love, until the day she meets Eric Oberdorf."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30787/super-sad-true-love-story.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30787","title":"Super Sad True Love Story","author":"by Gary Shteyngart","description":"A hilarious satire on digital consumerism and the death of the attention span, Shteyngart is masterful in never labouring a point and being constantly surprising, satirical and funny in this sign of the times book."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30719/death-of-an-unsigned-band.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30719","title":"Death of an Unsigned Band","author":"by Tim Thornton","description":"It's enjoyable, funny, bittersweet, and like the epic powerballad the band sometimes ends on, ultimately triumphant."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30952/caribou-island.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30952","title":"Caribou Island","author":"by David Vann","description":"Essentially the debut novel from literary powerhouse David Vann, Caribou Island is the tale of a crumbling marriage, blighted by disappointment, pretensions and a pounding headache. Caribou Island also features a lot of fish."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28873/revolutionary-road.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28873","title":"Revolutionary Road","author":"by Richard Yates","description":"Revolutionary Road ’s 1950s setting gives the book its context, but the timeless and universal faultlines that develop in the Wheelers’ relationship are as relevant today. In this way, Yates’ masterpiece is a microcosm of shattered dreams and wrong decisions..."}]}
{"id":69,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/69/","title":"Ten short story collections from British writers","list_description":"Ten collections to celebrate the strength of British short story writers...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34057/9781784750398.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34057","title":"A Christmas Feast","author":"by Katie Fforde","description":"Fans of Katie Fforde will no doubt enjoy this festive offering of Christmas stories; it's an amusing book of bite size stories to be enjoyed during the hectic holiday season."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31073/words-from-a-glass-bubble.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31073","title":"Words from a Glass Bubble","author":"by Vanessa Gebbie","description":"Words From a Glass Bubble is about coming to terms with the cards we are dealt. The stories pivot around the recognition that those who seem powerless can prove to be the strongest catalysts for change."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31071/the-white-road.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31071","title":"The White Road","author":"by Tania Hershman","description":"Tania Hershman allows her imagination free reign, as her characters navigate through love, death, friendship, spirituality, mental illness and the havoc wreaked by the weather."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31075/what-becomes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31075","title":"What Becomes","author":"by A L Kennedy","description":"Always attuned to the moment of epiphany, these twelve stories are profound, intimate observations of men and women whose lives ache with possibility"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29261/it-s-beginning-to-hurt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29261","title":"It's Beginning to Hurt","author":"by James Lasdun","description":"There's something disarmingly low-key about James Lasdun's writing, a hard-to-define tone that nevertheless draws the reader deep into the specific moment of each story."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33528/9781907773754.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33528","title":"The Rental Heart and Other Fairytales","author":"by Kirsty Logan","description":"The Rental Heart and Other Fairytales is a varied and exciting collection of short stories which bring together the mythical and magical in a fresh contemporary way."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31074/instruction-manual-for.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31074","title":"Instruction Manual for Swallowing","author":"by Adam Marek","description":"Robotic insects, in-growing cutlery, flesh-serving waiters in a zombie cafe... Welcome to the surreal, misshapen universe of Adam Marek's first collection."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31076/music-for-the-off-key.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31076","title":"Music for the Off-Key","author":"by Courttia Newland","description":"Drawing inspiration from everything from traditional horror movies to the contemporary sophistication of Japanese works in this genre, Newland brings together the literary and the popular in a uniquely Black British mix."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31072/don-t-tell-me-the-truth-about-love.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31072","title":"Don’t Tell Me The Truth about Love","author":"by Dan Rhodes","description":"With this new collection of short stories, Dan Rhodes keeps as his subject the intricacies and deficiencies of desire, but his methods have changed."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31070/everyday.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31070","title":"Everyday","author":"by Lee Rourke","description":"Everyday takes the reader for a dawdle into the moribund heart of London."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27682/hey-yeah-right-get-a-life.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27682","title":"Hey Yeah Right Get a Life","author":"by Helen Simpson","description":"Hey Yeah Right Get a Life, Helen Simpson's third collection of short stories, is about the hectic day-to-day whirlpool of women's lives- women who want to improve their lot, women who yearn to 'get a life' better than their own."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28954/the-loudest-sound-and-nothing.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28954","title":"The Loudest Sound and Nothing","author":"by Clare Wigfall","description":"Wigfall moves between territories effortlessly, creating her worlds with a wonderful economy, the perfectly weighted use of details and voice."}]}
{"id":70,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/70/","title":"Translated books of the year 2010","list_description":"Chosen by our translated fiction reviewers, Nikesh Shukla, Catherine Mansfield and Pete Mitchell, here are our five translated books of the year...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34440/9781782112846.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34440","title":"Guantánamo Diary","author":"by (Editor) Larry Siems","description":"A biography about a man incarcerated in Guantánamo Diary - he has been tortured, trapped and as of yet not charged for a crime."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30791/the-road.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30791","title":"The Road","author":"by Vasily Grossman","description":"It will soon be fifty years since Vasily Grossman died - worn out by a lifetime of witnessing horror and brutality, and by the unfriendly attentions of the Soviet state - and only now is he beginning to be acknowledged..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30397/the-lost-world.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30397","title":"The Lost World","author":"by Patricia Melo","description":"This intelligent, fast-paced thriller takes us into the mind of a killer on a gripping road trip across Brazil."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29819/beside-the-sea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29819","title":"Beside the Sea","author":"by Veronique Olmi","description":"On a rainy night, a mother sets out on a bus journey to the seaside with her two small sons, knowing that it will be the last trip they ever make. What she hopes will be a happy last memory..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30899/an-awkward-age.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30899","title":"An Awkward Age","author":"by Anna Starobinets","description":"Everything in Starobinets' stories smacks of the sinister and perverse. An unnamed narrator assuages loneliness with a companion grown from mould, until the horrific smell alerts the authorities"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30859/pereira-maintains.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30859","title":"Pereira Maintains","author":"by Antonio Tabucchi","description":"Pereira has never seen himself as a hero. He's a middle-aged, overweight culture editor for a second-rate newspaper in late 1930s Lisbon."}]}
{"id":72,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/72/","title":"Translated European novels","list_description":"Our choice of novels from mainland Europe.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33841/9781843915447.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33841","title":"Alphabet House","author":"by Jussi Adler-Olsen","description":"When two British Soldiers are shot down over Germany during WW2, they make their escape on a train carrying injured SS Officers. Little do they know they're destined for a mental hospital where their lives will be changed forever."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25910/gotz-and-meyer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25910","title":"Götz and Meyer","author":"by David Albahari","description":"In this disturbing novel, David Albahari takes one of the many infamous moments of Nazi history, and personalises it in the most extraordinary way."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33703/9781843914983.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33703","title":"Death in Pont-Aven","author":"by Jean-Luc Bannalec","description":"In the small town of Pont-Aven on the Breton coast, a brutal murder takes place in the central hotel and the gruff Commissaire Dupin takes up the case, wading through lies, family secrets and the prejudices of the small town..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33295/milly-molly-mandy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33295","title":"The Milly-Molly-Mandy Storybook","author":"by Joyce Lankester Brisley","description":"Milly-Molly-Mandy lives with her mother, father, uncle, aunt, grandmother and grandfather in a 'nice white cottage with a thatched roof'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33732/9781908968173.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33732","title":"Bonita Avenue","author":"by Peter Buwalda","description":"A very successful middle-class family implode when revelations of betrayal and guilt are revealed"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33421/almost_like_spring.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33421","title":"Almost Like Spring","author":"by Alex Capus","description":"An insight into the final weeks of Waldemar Velte and Kurt Sandweg - Switzerland's most notorious bank robbers."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28163/the-white-king.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28163","title":"The White King","author":"by Gyorgy Dragoman","description":"György Dragomán has succeeded in conjuring up not only a realsitic voice for his young protagonist Djata but also a sense of what it means to live in a country in which the state security services watch your every move..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33500/things-look-different-in-th.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33500","title":"Things Look Different in the Light","author":"by Medardo Fraile","description":"A collection portraying small moments in the lives of ordinary people, celebrating things that may initially seem unremarkable."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33428/the_spectre_of_alexander_wo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33428","title":"The Spectre of Alexander Wolf","author":"by Gaito Gazdanov","description":"Years after the Russian Revolution a man finds out that someone he thought he killed during battle didn't die - via a short story written by the victim."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33696/9780981955735.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33696","title":"Harlequin's Millions","author":"by Bohumil Hrabal","description":"In this moving, humorous and digressive novel, an old woman reflects upon age and memory within the surreal confines of a retirement home in post-Communist Czechoslovakia."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33456/rabbit_back_literature_soci.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33456","title":"Rabbit Back Literature Society","author":"by Pasi Ilmari Jääskeläinen","description":"A teacher in a small Finnish town starts to investigate when she notices that someone has been re-writing the storylines in classic books"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33497/the-little-old-lady.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33497","title":"The Little Old Lady Who Broke All the Rules","author":"by Catharina Ingelman-Sundberg","description":"REPRESENTING SWEDEN An oppressed elderly lady decides to break the mould before turning to crime."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29039/homage-to-czerny.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29039","title":"Homage to Czerny","author":"by Gert Jonke","description":"Playwright Gert Jonke's novel is a madcap exploration of perception and reality which circles round and round before landing somewhere equally odd. You won't find any answers to the big questions of life here, but you'll have a good time..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26136/agamemnon-s-daughter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26136","title":"Agamemnon's Daughter","author":"by Ismail Kadare","description":"This, a wonderful mix of fiction, mythology and politics in the form of what is more meditation than narrative, is frightening, beautiful, and utterly compelling."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33799/9781782390718.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33799","title":"Summer House with Swimming Pool","author":"by Herman Koch","description":"A group of people gather for a holiday at a rented villa, but things change after am unfortunate event at a beach party."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33651/the_beggar_and_the_hare.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33651","title":"The Beggar & The Hare","author":"by Tuomas Kyrö","description":"A Romanian construction worker is kidnapped and forced to beg in Finland, but his fortune's change when he's involved in an unexpected feast and a wounded rabbit."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33880/9781782270737.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33880","title":"The Things We Don't Do","author":"by Andres Neuman","description":"This is the first of Neuman's short story collections to be translated into English. A varied collection dealing with the break-down of relationships, the decision to end a life, and making friends with long held enemies, what powerfully strikes the..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33837/9781782066033.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33837","title":"Into a Raging Blaze","author":"by Andreas Norman","description":"The Swedish spy thriller that anticipated the Edward Snowden revelations."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33925/9781782270676.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33925","title":"A Childhood","author":"by Jona Oberski","description":"An evocative depiction of childhood blighted by war and prejudice. A child’s view of his family’s journey from Amsterdam to Belsen and back again."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33452/barcelona_shadows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33452","title":"Barcelona Shadows","author":"by Marc Pastor","description":"Set in the early 1900s Barcelona, a brutal police Inspector tries to hunt down a sadistic, violent and cannibalistic child-killer."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33457/victoria-system.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33457","title":"The Victoria System","author":"by Eric Reinhardt","description":"David starts a passionate affair with Victoria, but as their intensity and lust develops so does David's bitterness towards Victoria's capitalist career."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33638/9781844087372.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33638","title":"In Diamond Square","author":"by Mercè Rodoreda","description":"A love story set against the background of the Spanish Civil War."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33839/9781781253168.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33839","title":"Pedro Páramo","author":"by Juan Rulfo","description":"A man promises his dying mother that he will track down his father in the strange town of Comala."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33719/9781843915072.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33719","title":"Apocalypse Next Tuesday","author":"by David Safier","description":"A lonely woman in her mid-thirties falls in love with a man disguised as Jesus, who is trying to prevent the apocalypse."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25931/mrs-sartoris.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25931","title":"Mrs Sartoris","author":"by Elke Schmitter","description":"Mrs Sartoris is a controlled and moving novel which offers no happy conclusions or cheerful denouement, but is reconizably a true reflection of a very human malaise and all the more powerful for that."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33504/sicilian-uncles.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33504","title":"Sicilian Uncles","author":"by Leonardo Sciascia","description":"These four novellas each tell a story in which larger events have concrete impacts upon the inhabitants of rural Sicily."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25902/the-engineer-of-human-souls.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25902","title":"The Engineer of Human Souls","author":"by Josef Skvorecky","description":"'The engineer of human souls' is said to be Stalin’s definition of the writer (as an engineer constructs a machine, so must the writer construct the mind of the New Man) but this novel is much more than a critique..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33877/9781843914808.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33877","title":"The Best Book in the World","author":"by Peter Stjernström","description":"Two men become embroiled in a bid to write the best book in the world."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33883/9781843915362.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33883","title":"The Peculiar Life of a Lonely Postman","author":"by Denis Theriault","description":"An enchanting tale about the loneliness of a postal worker and his almost mystical involvement with a Japanese poetry form that transforms his life."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33460/erl_king.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33460","title":"The Erl-King","author":"by Michael Tournier","description":"Michael Tournier's seminal classic set during the Second World War tells the story of one man's journey through Nazi-occupied Eastern Europe."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33921/9781781722053.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33921","title":"Bilbao - New York - Bilbao","author":"by Kirmen Uribe","description":"The author muses about a varirty of topics whilst tarvelling to New York from Bilbao in order to research a book."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33724/9781846558047.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33724","title":"Never Any End to Paris","author":"by Enrique Vila-Matas","description":"A man becomes so obsessed with Ernest Hemingway that he fattenms himself up and travels to Florida to enter a Hemingway look-a-like competition."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26041/franziska.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26041","title":"Franziska","author":"by Ernst Weiss","description":"It poignantly describes a young female pianist's struggle, as artist, to reconcile the demands of her vocation with her need for human contact and love."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33721/9781908670151.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33721","title":"The Blue Room","author":"by Hanne Ørstavik","description":"Johanne's lover is leaving for America. Can she break free from the locked room and fly with him?"}]}
{"id":73,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/73/","title":"Tales from Scandinavia","list_description":"Norway, Sweden and Finland","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33841/9781843915447.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33841","title":"Alphabet House","author":"by Jussi Adler-Olsen","description":"When two British Soldiers are shot down over Germany during WW2, they make their escape on a train carrying injured SS Officers. Little do they know they're destined for a mental hospital where their lives will be changed forever."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33653/9781843915157.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33653","title":"Spring Tide","author":"by Cilla & Rolf Börjlind","description":"A young police trainee looks into a 24-year-old cold-case her deceased father worked on before he dies."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33420/closed_for_winter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33420","title":"Closed For Winter","author":"by Jorn Lier Horst","description":"Police Inspector William Wistig investigates a brutal murder at a holiday cottage. A murder that has consequences for his daughter"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33456/rabbit_back_literature_soci.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33456","title":"Rabbit Back Literature Society","author":"by Pasi Ilmari Jääskeläinen","description":"A teacher in a small Finnish town starts to investigate when she notices that someone has been re-writing the storylines in classic books"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33651/the_beggar_and_the_hare.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33651","title":"The Beggar & The Hare","author":"by Tuomas Kyrö","description":"A Romanian construction worker is kidnapped and forced to beg in Finland, but his fortune's change when he's involved in an unexpected feast and a wounded rabbit."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25935/the-savage-altar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25935","title":"The Savage Altar","author":"by Asa Larsson","description":"If Larsson keeps up the narrative pace of The Savage Altar in the other five Rebecka Martinsson mysteries still to be published in the UK, you – and Rebecka – will be shattered by the end of the final volume."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33729/9781908737632.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33729","title":"The Hunting Dogs","author":"by Jørn Lier Horst","description":"Lieutenant William Wisting returns in the third novel to be translated into English; this time he must confront accusations of planting evidence in a murder case from seventeen years ago. Out to prove his innocence, little does Wisting know that..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25933/out-stealing-horses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25933","title":"Out Stealing Horses","author":"by Per Petterson","description":"Petterson’s characters are embedded in the landscape and the seasons, the drifting snows of winter and the burning sunshine of high summer."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33923/9781846557811.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33923","title":"I Refuse","author":"by Per Petterson","description":"With quiet drama, Petterson tells the story of two young teenagers: Tommy and Jim. Despite their different backgrounds, they develop a friendship which is deeply sincere. However, as the two grow up together Jim’s struggles cause a separation which the..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25898/at-the-edge-of-light.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25898","title":"At the Edge of Light","author":"by Maria Peura","description":"Maria Peura's captivating novel, infused by the power of the seasons and the force of nature, is a primal story of adolescence set in a remote village in northern Finland."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28401/berlin-poplars.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28401","title":"Berlin Poplars","author":"by Anne B Ragde","description":"Neu-Drontheim: a projected city of 50,000 houses that was to be built on the Norwegian coast by the invading Germans during the Second World War. It was a grand scheme – the Reich’s architect Albert Speer had a 25-metre plaster..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25928/the-man-who-went-up-in-smoke.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25928","title":"The Man Who Went Up in Smoke","author":"by Maj Sjowall and Per Wahloo","description":"From 1965 to 1975, the husband and wife team of Maj Sjöwall and Per Wahlöö wrote ten crime novels about the lugubrious Swedish detective Martin Beck."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33877/9781843914808.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33877","title":"The Best Book in the World","author":"by Peter Stjernström","description":"Two men become embroiled in a bid to write the best book in the world."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33721/9781908670151.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33721","title":"The Blue Room","author":"by Hanne Ørstavik","description":"Johanne's lover is leaving for America. Can she break free from the locked room and fly with him?"}]}
{"id":74,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/74/","title":"Tales from the Dutch","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25857/beyond-sleep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25857","title":"Beyond Sleep","author":"by WF Hermans","description":"Summer in northern Norway: endless hours of light, clouds of mosquitoes, kilometre after kilometre of rocky terrain and stunted trees. Into this barren landscape trek four geology students, three of them Norwegian, one – Alfred Issendorf – Dutch. Each is..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25877/the-darkroom-of-damacles.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25877","title":"The Darkroom of Damocles","author":"by WF Hermans","description":"Fifty years since it was first published in Dutch, Hermans' tale of espionage in Holland during the Second World War has finally been translated into English. It has been worth the wait."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33799/9781782390718.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33799","title":"Summer House with Swimming Pool","author":"by Herman Koch","description":"A group of people gather for a holiday at a rented villa, but things change after am unfortunate event at a beach party."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28164/shutterspeed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28164","title":"Shutterspeed","author":"by Erwin Mortier","description":"Erwin Mortier’s deceptively simple tale of an adolescent boy growing up in a Flemish village with his aunt and uncle, is full of such beautiful, spare writing. Its inclusion on the 2008 Independent Foreign Fiction Prize longlist is no surprise."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33925/9781782270676.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33925","title":"A Childhood","author":"by Jona Oberski","description":"An evocative depiction of childhood blighted by war and prejudice. A child’s view of his family’s journey from Amsterdam to Belsen and back again."}]}
{"id":75,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/75/","title":"South American stories","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29557/a-chapter-of-hats.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29557","title":"A Chapter of Hats","author":"by Joachim Maria Machado de Assis","description":"The stories in this collection are beautiful vignettes of nineteenth-century Brazilian life. They sparkle with wit and a maudlin charm leavened by sly humour, but they also swipe at some less appealing aspects of Brazilian society - slavery and prostitution..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33523/hotel_brasil.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33523","title":"Hotel Brasil: The Mystery of the Severed Heads","author":"by Frei Betto","description":"A number of colourful characters are suspected of murder when a headless body turns up in the rundown hotel where they all live."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28452/the-past.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28452","title":"The Past","author":"by Alan Pauls","description":"The Past, by Argentine novelist Alan Pauls, is about obsessive love and self-destruction, and is a strange, unsettling read."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29079/the-armies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29079","title":"The Armies","author":"by Evelio Rosero","description":"'Every time I begin to write it is out of desperation’ The Armies, Evelio Rosero’s portrait of the effect of civil war on one rural Colombian village, has a gentle opening that belies the horror to come."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33882/9781908276384.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33882","title":"Nowhere People","author":"by Paulo Scott","description":"A young Brazillian student radical picks up a girl on the side of the motorway. From there the pair meet a range of people in an ever-changing Brazil."}]}
{"id":76,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/76/","title":"Short story collections of the year 2010","list_description":"There's been a resurgence of late in short stories, with a rising number of literature nights, new online portals and apps for the form and celebration from other writers. So we thought we'd give you our short story collections of the year...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30732/things-we-didn-t-see-coming.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30732","title":"Things We Didn't See Coming","author":"by Steven Amsterdam","description":"These apocalyptic stories make an oddly reassuring read. In the face of fire, flood, draught and plague, people remain basically the same they tell us. We are violent, tribal, insecure - yes - but creative, loving and cooperative too."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30718/echoes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30718","title":"Echoes","author":"by Laura Dockrill","description":"The new book from Laura Dockrill is a collection of modern-day fairytales, poems and retellings of classic stories, all with a slightly sinister edge. Reminiscent of Roald Dahl, Tim Burton and even Grimm, the stories take on a not-quite supernatural...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30851/the-spot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30851","title":"The Spot","author":"by David Means","description":"This short collection of short short stories all take place in a particular 'spot'. The singular sense of place in each story gives the eccentrics, hoboes, lowlifes and meanos a specific place to carve their loneliness and reflection."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29868/both-ways-is-the-way-i-want-it.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29868","title":"Both Ways is the Only Way I Want It","author":"by Maile Meloy","description":"The characters in these eleven stories include a love-struck young ranch hand, an aging Argentine lover, a self-involved grandmother who comes back from the dead, and two hitchhikers named Bonnie and Clyde. All of them are caught between opposing forces:..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29857/the-theory-of-light-and-matter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29857","title":"The Theory of Light and Matter","author":"by Andrew Porter","description":"This debut collection of stories introduces a new and distinctive voice in American fiction. Porter has a unique and quietly heartbreaking range, examining everyone from small children to the disappointed adults they become. This might sound depressing, but there are..."}]}
{"id":77,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/77/","title":"Booked Up 2011","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31324/pumpkin-grumpkin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31324","title":"Pumpkin Grumpkin","author":"by John Agard and Grace Nichols","description":"Amusing and bemusing poetry from around the globe. John Agard and Grace Nichols have assembled a bunch of silly poems in this new collection brought to life with quirky illustrations by Satoshi Kitamura. m From classics like The Jabberwocky to...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28939/namebooksecret.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28939","title":"The Name of this Book is SECRET","author":"by Pseudonymous Bosch","description":"Eleven-year-old Cass is a ‘survivalist’ and her school friend, Max Ernst, an expert at puzzles.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30828/artichoke-hearts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30828","title":"Artichoke Hearts","author":"by Sita Brahmachari","description":"This empathetic account of the process of bereavement, a month’s diary, reassures readers that we grow from our experiences, however painful they are.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30249/httyd_jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30249","title":"How to Train Your Dragon","author":"by Cressida Cowell","description":"Hiccup Horrendous Haddock III was an incredible sword-fighter, dragon-whisperer and the greatest Viking hero who ever lived.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31325/the-ghost-box-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31325","title":"The Ghost Box","author":"by Catherine Fisher","description":"This spooky thriller is a short and simple read ideal for reluctant and struggling readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31326/kickoff.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31326","title":"The Kick Off","author":"by Dan Freedman","description":"Packed full of footballing tips, fumbled free kicks and nail-biting penalties, every reader will be on Jamie's side.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30708/mortlock.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30708","title":"Mortlock","author":"by Jon Mayhew","description":"Orphaned twins Josie and Alfie, separated as babies, rediscover each other and set out on a quest for the truth of their past in this Victorian horror story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29068/snotgreen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29068","title":"Why is Snot Green?","author":"by Glenn Murphy","description":"Why is Snot Green? is a fresh and funny celebration of science and curiosity, and is perfect for young readers who prefer to dip in and out of a book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31327/big-nate.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31327","title":"Big Nate - The Boy with the Biggest Head in the World","author":"by Lincoln Peirce","description":"This hilarious take on American school life is sure to make readers laugh, cringe and turn the next page. Based on a comic strip by Lincoln Peirce, the inspiration behind Jeff Kinney, this is sure to appeal to any fans...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30900/laura-marlin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30900","title":"Dead Man's Cove","author":"by Lauren St John","description":"When mysterious uncle Calvin rescues Laura Marlin from her gloomy life in an orphanage, she can't believe her luck! But she soon realises that her Cornish paradise is full of mysteries...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31328/frankie-foster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31328","title":"Frankie Foster: Fizzy Pop","author":"by Jean Ure","description":"This fizzy book deals lightly with themes of adoption, family and friendship making for a bright and bubbly read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31338/little-bo-peep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31338","title":"Little Bo Peep has Knickers That Bleep","author":"by Laurence Anholt and Arthur Robins","description":"A fun collection of silly rhymes and snappy limericks which are ideal to read aloud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31337/edo_cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31337","title":"Boffin Boy and the Wizard of Edo","author":"by David Orme","description":"This graphic novel style book is a quick read and perfect for those who don’t like too much text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":78,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/78/","title":"Our booklist on... celebrity","list_description":"From models to musicians to movie stars... from reality shows to high society parties... from the depths of addiction and hubris to the heights of adoration and vanity... books exploring the myths behind celebrity give us glimpses into a world we live through vicariously, wish we had and probably know more than we should about... Here are our ten books on celebrity.  'Celebrity is the chastisement of merit and the punishment of talent.' Emily Dickinson","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29757/dazed-and-aroused.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29757","title":"Dazed and Aroused","author":"by Gavin James Bower","description":"Male model Alex exists in a bubble of slogans, consumerism, castings and never fully engaging in the world. A ghost in his own life, he allows a plethora of vacuous models and parties and drink and drugs invade his aura..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31176/great-jones-street.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31176","title":"Great Jones Street","author":"by Don DeLillo","description":"Bucky Wunderlick is a rock and roll star. Dissatisfied with a life that has brought fame and fortune, he suddenly decides he no longer wants to be a commodity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31178/glamorama.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31178","title":"Glamorama","author":"by Bret Easton Ellis","description":"The centre of the world: 1990s Manhattan. Victor Ward, a model with perfect abs and all the right friends, is seen and photographed everywhere, even in places he hasn’t been and with people he doesn’t know."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31181/the-great-gatsby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31181","title":"The Great Gatsby","author":"by F Scott Fitzgerald","description":"Jay Gatsby is the man who has everything. But one thing will always be out of his reach ...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31180/personality.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31180","title":"Personality","author":"by Andrew O'Hagan","description":"Maria Tambini is a thirteen-year-old girl with a great singing voice. Growing up on a small Scottish island, she is ready for the big time and keen to escape her ordinary life."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31179/angel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31179","title":"Angel","author":"by Elizabeth Taylor","description":"Writing stories that are extravagant and fanciful, fifteen-year-old Angel retreats to a world of romance, escaping the drabness of provincial life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31175/bonfireofthevanities.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31175","title":"The Bonfire of the Vanities","author":"by Tom Wolfe","description":"Sherman McCoy is a WASP, bond trader and self-appointed 'Master of the Universe'. He has a fashionable wife, a Park Avenue apartment and a Southern mistress.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"}]}
{"id":79,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/79/","title":"Lost in translation","list_description":"Five books in translation that made it on to our screens.  With the upcoming Independent Foreign Fiction Prize winner announcement, we thought it ample opportunity to draw your attention to other books in translation. So in the first of our themed booklists, here are five translated fiction novels that have been adapted for the screen.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31184/lettheright1in.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31184","title":"Let the Right One In","author":"by John Ajvide Lindqvist","description":"John Ajvide Lindqvist's novel is a unique and brilliant fusion of social novel and vampire legend, and a deeply moving fable about rejection, friendship and loyalty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29800/city-of-god.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29800","title":"City of God","author":"by Paulo Lins","description":"Based on a true story, this is a sprawling, magnificently told epic about the history of gang life in Rio's favelas."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29472/persepolis.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29472","title":"Persepolis","author":"by Marjane Satrapi","description":"Persepolis is Satrapi's history of Iran and her life in Iran and France as she tries to retain her Iranian culture but also grow up and become independent.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31182/the-reader.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31182","title":"The Reader","author":"by Bernhard Schlink","description":"For 15-year-old Michael Berg, a chance meeting with an older woman leads to far more than he ever imagined."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31183/perfume.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31183","title":"Perfume: The Story of a Murderer","author":"by Patrick Suskind","description":"Survivor, genius, perfumer, killer: this is Jean-Baptiste Grenouille. He is abandoned on the filthy streets of Paris as a child, but grows up to discover he has an extraordinary gift: a sense of smell more powerful than any other human's."}]}
{"id":80,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/80/","title":"Our booklist on... great film adaptations","list_description":"Books into films... this month, we look at the source material for some classic movies","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31191/the-big-sleep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31191","title":"The Big Sleep","author":"by Raymond Chandler","description":"Californian private eye Philip Marlowe's entanglement with the Sternwood family - and an attendant cast of colorful underworld figures - is the background to a story reflecting all the tarnished glitter of the great American Dream"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31044/do-androids-dream-of-electric.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31044","title":"Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?","author":"by Philip K Dick","description":"World War Terminus had left the Earth devastated. Through its ruins, bounty hunter Rick Deckard stalked, in search of the renegade replicants who were his prey.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31185/submarine-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31185","title":"Submarine","author":"by Joe Dunthorne","description":"Meet Oliver Tate, 15. Convinced that his father is depressed ('Depression comes in bouts. Like boxing. Dad is in the blue corner') and his mother is having an affair with her capoeira teacher.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31186/la-confidential.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31186","title":"LA Confidential","author":"by James Ellroy","description":"LA Confidential is set in 1950s Los Angeles is the seedy backdrop for this intricate noir-ish tale of police corruption and Hollywood sleaze."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31193/virginsuicides.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31193","title":"The Virgin Suicides","author":"by Jeffrey Eugenides","description":"The shocking thing about the girls was how nearly normal they seemed when their mother let them out for the one and only date of their lives.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31195/casino-royale.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31195","title":"Casino Royale","author":"by Ian Fleming","description":"James Bond: charming, sophisticated, handsome; chillingly ruthless and very deadly. Spymaster M has sent Bond on a mission to neutralize a lethal, high-rolling Russian operative called simply 'Le Chiffre'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31190/never-let-me-go.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31190","title":"Never Let Me Go","author":"by Kazuo Ishiguro","description":"In one of the most acclaimed and strange novels of recent years, Kazuo Ishiguro imagines the lives of a group of students growing up in a darkly skewered version of contemporary England.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31187/one-flew-over-the-cuckoo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31187","title":"One Flew Over the Cuckoo’s Nest","author":"by Ken Kesey","description":"Boisterous, ribald, and ultimately shattering, Ken Kesey's One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest is the seminal novel of the 1960s that has left an indelible mark on the literature of our time."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31188/the-constant-gardener.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31188","title":"The Constant Gardener","author":"by John le Carre","description":"Tessa Quayle has been horribly murdered on the shores of Lake Turkana in Northern Kenya, the birthplace of mankind."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28131/the-road.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28131","title":"The Road","author":"by Cormac McCarthy","description":"McCarthy’s pared-down prose describes the wholesale annihilation of a society and all that it holds dear, but it also celebrates ingenuity and the will to survive in the face of utter hopelessness."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31189/atonement.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31189","title":"Atonement","author":"by Ian McEwen","description":"On the hottest day of the summer of 1934, thirteen-year-old Briony Tallis sees her sister Cecilia strip off her clothes and plunge into the fountain in the garden of their country house.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31192/scott-pilgrim.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31192","title":"Scott Pilgrim series (vol. 1-6)","author":"by Bryan O’Malley","description":"Scott Pilgrim's life is totally sweet. He's 23 years old, he's in a rock band, he's 'between jobs', and he's dating a cute high school girl. Nothing could possibly go wrong...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31024/fight-club.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31024","title":"Fight Club","author":"by Chuck Palahniuk","description":"Every weekend, in basements and parking lots across the country, young men with good white-collar jobs and absent fathers take off their shoes and shirts and fight each other barehanded for as long as they have to."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29708/q-a.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29708","title":"Q and A","author":"by Vikas Swarup","description":"Before Slumdog Millionaire, there was Q&A, the book by Vikas Swarup. Ram Mohammed Thomas, a poor, 18-year old waiter from the wrong side of the tracks, becomes the biggest quiz-show winner in history, scooping a billion rupee prize"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31194/trainspotting.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31194","title":"Trainspotting","author":"by Irvine Welsh","description":"REPRESENTING UNITED KINGDOM This novel looks at life in the dark underside of Edinburgh, the AIDS capital of Europe, through the jaded eyes and harsh vernacular of heroin addict Mark Renton, who is sick of his friends, sick with the..."}]}
{"id":81,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/81/","title":"At the seaside","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31319/9780192763273-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31319","title":"Seaside Poems","author":"by Jill Bennett","description":"This is a delightful collection of seaside poems, beautifully illustrated by award-winning illustrator, Nick Sharratt.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31316/661416-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31316","title":"Miffy at the Seaside","author":"by Dick Bruna","description":"Toddlers will enjoy sharing this simple story about Miffy's day at the seaside","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25785/canuhearsea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25785","title":"Can You Hear the Sea?","author":"by Judy Cumberbatch","description":"This is a gentle, lovely story about taking time to notice what lies beyond the chaos of everyday life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33599/storm-whale.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33599","title":"The Storm Whale","author":"by Benji Davies","description":"Noi finds a baby whale washed up on the beach after a storm and decides to take it home to care for it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31318/9781840111545-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31318","title":"To the Beach","author":"by Thomas Docherty","description":"Lovely story of a boy using his imagination to go on a trip to the seaside","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4months+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33831/tip-tap-went-crab.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33831","title":"Tip Tap Went The Crab","author":"by Tim Hopgood","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31320/9780140544596-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31320","title":"Lucy and Tom at the Seaside","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Follow a happy family day out by the seaside as Tom and Lucy enjoy making sandcastles, looking in rock pools and going on a donkey ride","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33828/zoe-beans-pirate.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33828","title":"Zoe and Beans: Pirate Treasure!","author":"by Chloe and Mick Inkpen","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34232/out-of-the-blue-barefoot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34232","title":"Out of the Blue","author":"by Alison Jay","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: n/a","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34137/fish-food.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34137","title":"Fish Food","author":"by Andy Mansfield and Henning Löhlein","description":"A clever pop-up book about the underwater food chain.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30576/snap-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30576","title":"Snap","author":"by Margaret Mayo","description":"Watch out for the snapping sharks and dancing dolphins - a treat for all!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 1+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":82,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/82/","title":"Five of the Greatest Books about the Holocaust","list_description":"How do you define 'Holocaust literature'? The idea itself seems absurd, if not obscene; but the efforts of writers and philosophers to understand one of the most incomprehensible events in human history have produced mountains of books, some of them truly great, and it's an understandable instinct to lump them all together under a definable category. But categories are dangerous: some books are really about things they never explicitly mention, and some pretend to be about things that they're not; sometimes subsequent events give a book meanings it was never intended to have when it was written. With that in mind, here are five books, some well-known and some less so (and not all of them obvious choices), that concern or reflect upon or bear some meaningful relation to the Holocaust. Not all of them would sit comfortably on a shelf marked 'Holocaust Literature', and this is by no means a 'best-of' list; instead, we hope these books might open up new perspectives or introduce you to writers you hadn't yet encountered.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31239/babi-yar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31239","title":"Babi Yar","author":"by Anatoly Kuznetsov","description":"Babi Yar is the name of a ravine on the outskirts of Kiev, where between 1941 and 1943 the Nazis murdered untold numbers of Jews, Roma, the disabled, Ukrainian resisters and hostages."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31279/the-drowned-and-the-saved.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31279","title":"The Drowned and the Saved","author":"by Primo Levi","description":"The Drowned and the Saved was written towards the end of Primo Levi's life, and unlike his earlier memoirs If This is a Man and The Truce, it doesn't explicitly narrate his experiences in Auschwitz and after liberation."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31281/the-wandering-jews.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31281","title":"The Wandering Jews","author":"by Joseph Roth","description":"Finally, a book about what was lost. Written before the War - so, in fact, not a book 'about' the Holocaust at all - this slim volume records the great novelist and journalist Joseph Roth's journeys and observations amongst the..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31280/austerlitz.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31280","title":"Austerlitz","author":"by W G Sebald","description":"Austerlitz is about memory and forgetting, and the shadows of absence and guilt that the Holocaust cast forward into the future."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31238/night.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31238","title":"Night","author":"by Elie Wiesel","description":"One of the greatest Holocaust memoirs, Night records Elie Wiesel's childhood in Transylvania, his deportation, his separation from his family and his journey with his dying father through the inferno of the concentration camps."}]}
{"id":83,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/83/","title":"Classical Studies","list_description":"Five classic books that started life in another language. With the upcoming Independent Foreign Fiction Prize winner announcement next month, we thought it ample opportunity to draw your attention to other books in translation. Here are five classic books that started life in another language, you may have read them or you may have not... but chances are you will have heard of them...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26362/don-quixote.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26362","title":"Don Quixote","author":"by Miguel de Cervantes","description":"Addled by too many chivalric romances, the ageing Don Quixote resolves to become a knight errant. Setting out on his trusty steed, he employs Sancho Panza as his squire and determines to rescue damsels in distress, slay mighty giants, and..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26217/madame-bovary.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26217","title":"Madame Bovary","author":"by Gustave Flaubert","description":"Bored and beautiful, Emma Bovary is frustrated by the banality of provincial life in 19th Century France. Her marriage to a mediocre doctor cannot match the glittering, passion-filled romances of the sentimental novels she devours."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31299/the-tin-drum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31299","title":"The Tin Drum","author":"by Günter Grass","description":"Oskar Matzerath, inmate in a mental institution, narrates the extraordinary events of his life thus far."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31068/9780099448426-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31068","title":"Doctor Zhivago","author":"by Boris Pasternak","description":"Doctor Zhivago is the epic novel of Russia in the throes of revolution and one of the greatest love stories ever told."}]}
{"id":84,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/84/","title":"Five books about Russia","list_description":"With the upcoming Independent Foreign Fiction Prize winner announcement, we thought it ample opportunity to draw your attention to other books in translation. When we talk about 'State-of-the-nation' novels, we tend to mean books that are British or American, approximately the size of breezeblocks and terribly, terribly Serious – like Jonathan Franzen's Freedom or George Eliot's Middlemarch. What we tend to forget is that the Russians have been doing this for ever, and usually better - and far more entertainingly - than us Anglophones. Here is the Book Trust's list of 5 great State-of-Russia novels","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31300/petersburg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31300","title":"Petersburg","author":"by Andrei Bely","description":"A dizzy, impressionistic and occasionally downright demented portrait of a city on the edge of revolution, Petersburg takes its place among the great city-novels like Ulysses and Berlin Alexanderplatz."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26619/dead-souls.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26619","title":"Dead Souls","author":"by Nikolai Gogol","description":"The mummy and daddy of all Russian social novels, Gogol's masterpiece is equals parts rambling picaresque, Dickensian social tapestry, absurdist farce and caustic satire."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31330/life-and-fate.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31330","title":"Life and Fate","author":"by Vasily Grossman","description":"Grossman's epic panorama of the Second World War, the Holocaust and Stalin's postwar campaign of antisemitism is uncompromising in its realism and often harrowing in its depiction of the brutalities of battle and genocide."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31333/omon-ra.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31333","title":"Omon Ra","author":"by Victor Pelevin","description":"This slim book, mournfully consigns the Soviet Union to history's dustbin in a riot of paranoid psychedelia, wild satire and mordant wit."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31331/cancer-ward.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31331","title":"Cancer Ward","author":"by Alexander Solzhenistyn","description":"From the restricted environment of a hospital ward and an intensely personal portrait of disease, Solzhenitsyn spins a subtle, profound and intensely moving portrait of a pathological society and the suffering humanity that inhabits it."}]}
{"id":85,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/85/","title":"Stories from around the world","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25239/giant-turnip-9781852697884.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25239","title":"The Giant Turnip","author":"by Henriette Barkow","description":"The children in Miss Honeywood's class decide to grow vegetables in their school garden. What a shock they get when they discover a huge turnip that they are unable to move.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28688/the-animal-boogie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28688","title":"The Animal Boogie","author":"by Stella Blackstone","description":"Boogie along with the jungle inhabitants who flap, shake, flap and slide their way through this colourful book","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31237/my-granny-hres.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31237","title":"My Granny Went to Market","author":"by Stella Blackstone","description":"Join Granny as she takes a magic carpet ride around the world","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28935/fruits.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28935","title":"Fruits: a Caribbean counting poem","author":"by Valerie Bloom","description":"From half a pawpaw to five jew-plums through to ten bananas, this girl’s love of Caribbean fruits is so infectious you can almost taste the juice dribbling down your chin.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24866/handa-s-surprise.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24866","title":"Handa's Surprise","author":"by Eileen Browne","description":"Glorious images of an African village convey the sights, smells and colours of the landscape, its animals and its food in a story told as much through pictures as through words.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25785/canuhearsea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25785","title":"Can You Hear the Sea?","author":"by Judy Cumberbatch","description":"This is a gentle, lovely story about taking time to notice what lies beyond the chaos of everyday life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30556/one-two-tree-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30556","title":"One, Two, Tree!","author":"by Anushka Ravishankar","description":"This is an unusual and creative counting book. The pictures reflect the tribal traditions of central India, and the tree fills up with animals as the story progresses.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29226/j-is-for-jamaica.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29226","title":"J is for Jamaica","author":"by Benjamin Zephaniah","description":"Welcome to this whistle-stop tour of Jamaica - from A for Ackee to Z for Zinc.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":88,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/88/","title":"Ten Books by the Best New Illustrators 2008","list_description":"Having recently had the announcement of the Best New Illustrators Award 2011 we look back at those who came before. Here are the latest books from these illustrators.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31008/measuring-angels.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31008","title":"Measuring Angels","author":"by Lesley Ely","description":"A heartwarming tale with beautiful illustrations that reminds us how good it is to work together.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31009/the-nutcracker.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31009","title":"The Nutcracker","author":"by Emma Goldhawk","description":"This retelling of E.T.A. Hoffmann's surreal fairytale is illustrated by Lisa Evan's glowing, jewel-like colours, contrasted with soft pastels.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31010/wolf-won-t-bite.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31010","title":"Wolf Won't Bite!","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"Roll up, roll up! The Three Little Pigs capture the Wolf and have fun making him do circus tricks, each time claiming that 'Wolf Won't Bite'! But will the wolf have the last laugh?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30835/three-by-the-sea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30835","title":"Three by the Sea","author":"by Mini Grey","description":"Dog, Cat and Mouse are perfectly happy until a stranger arrives and begins to suggest to each that the others are boring and lazy, resulting in a dreadful row between the friends.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31011/up-and-down.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31011","title":"Up and Down","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"In this charming sequel to Lost and Found we rejoin Boy and Penguin who do everything together until one day Penguin decides he needs to try something on his own - fly.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31014/can-we-save-the-tiger.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31014","title":"Can We Save the Tiger?","author":"by Martin Jenkins","description":"A sequel to Ape, this beautifully illustrated book takes us through some of the extinct and endangered animals in the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31012/lost-in-the-toy-museum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31012","title":"Lost in the Toy Museum","author":"by David Lucas","description":"Set in the Museum of Childhood in Bethnal Green, East London, this magical book takes you through all of David Lucas' favourite toys in the collection.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31013/iris-and-isaac.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31013","title":"Iris and Isaac","author":"by Catherine Rayner","description":"This gorgeous story from an award-winning picture book- maker is a classic tale of friendship between two quarrelling polar bears. Rayner's illustrations are a delight and her animals are full of character.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30438/dexter-bexley-and-the-big.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30438","title":"Dexter Bexley and the Big Blue Beastie on the Road","author":"by Joel Stewart","description":"Dexter Bexley and the Big Blue Beastie simply love hooting. They hoot all day and all night until eventually they are thrown out of town.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":89,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/89/","title":"Ten books made into films","list_description":"It’s notoriously difficult to get it right when adapting books onto the screen. Here are some of our favourites:","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25343/the-wonderful-wizard-of-oz.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25343","title":"The Wonderful Wizard of Oz","author":"by L Frank Baum","description":"First published in 1900, this children's classic is still popular. Dorothy and her dog Toto find themselves in the strange land of Oz after a cyclone hits her Aunt and Uncle's house in Kansas.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30314/alice-s-adventures-in-wonderland.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30314","title":"Alice's Adventures in Wonderland","author":"by Lewis Carroll","description":"This lovely edition illustrated by Helen Oxenbury won the Kate Greenaway Medal in 1999."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31336/pinocchio.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31336","title":"The Adventures of Pinocchio","author":"by Carlo Collodi","description":"The story of the wooden puppet who learns goodness and becomes a real boy is famous the world over, and has been familiar in English for over a century.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24993/millions-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24993","title":"Millions","author":"by Frank Cottrell Boyce","description":"One night, a bag containing £229,370 falls from the sky and flattens the hermitage. Damian is convinced it is a gift from God.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24385/james-and-the-giant-peach.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24385","title":"James and the Giant Peach","author":"by Roald Dahl","description":"Through a series of peculiar and magical happenings, James finds himself on an adventure inside a giant peach with a bunch of friendly giant insects for travelling companions.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28969/gruffalo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28969","title":"The Gruffalo","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Axel Scheffler","description":"In this much-loved picture book, a little mouse walks through the woods and encounters a fox, an owl and a snake.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31372/howl-s-moving-castle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31372","title":"Howl's Moving Castle","author":"by Diana Wynne Jones","description":"Sophie Hatter is cursed with an old body by the Witch of the Waste and the spell can only be broken by the dreaded Wizard Howl who lives in his moving castle and likes to eat the souls of young...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31373/where-the-wild-things-are.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31373","title":"Where the Wild Things Are","author":"by Maurice Sendak","description":"First published in 1963, this classic picture book will fascinate both children and adults, evoking the fierce intensity of childhood"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30381/the-lost-thing-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30381","title":"The Lost Thing","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"A version of this unique book was the winner of Best Animated Short Film at the 2011 Oscars. A boy is out walking on the beach, when he spots a weird looking thing - it looks lost. The boy asks..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24574/mary-poppins.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24574","title":"Mary Poppins","author":"by P L Travers","description":"Mary Poppins arrives with the East wind to Number Seventeen Cherry Tree Lane to respond to the needs of Jane and Michael, whose parents are too busy to give them the attention they crave.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"}]}
{"id":90,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/90/","title":"Favourite books about time travel","list_description":"From The Time Machine to Dr Who, the ability to travel through time and change the course of history has long caught our imagination. Here are some of our favourite children's books about time travel both classic and recently published.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29598/time-quake.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29598","title":"Time Quake","author":"by Linda Buckley-Archer","description":"As in the two previous novels Buckley-Archer creates an exciting and thoughtful timeslip novel, offering a swiftly-paced adventure with a widely varied cast of characters from the eighteenth and twenty-first centuries.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31918/tempestt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31918","title":"Tempest","author":"by Julie Cross","description":"This gripping time-travel novel fuses the highs and lows of first love with the elements of a fast-paced thriller","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31158/a-roman-rescue.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31158","title":"A Roman Rescue","author":"by Kelly Gerard","description":"Charlie and his trusty dog Bandit fall down a sinkhole and are transported to ancient Rome where he meets Cosmo and goes on an adventure...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31246/a-year-without-autumn.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31246","title":"A Year Without Autumn","author":"by Liz Kessler","description":"Kessler combines a chatty tween novel with a serious dose of 'what if' in which a disused lift transports Jenni between the present and future years.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31376/a-wrinkle-in-time.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31376","title":"A Wrinkle in Time","author":"by Madeleine L'engle","description":"When Charles Wallace Murry goes searching through a 'wrinkle in time' for his lost father, he finds himself on an evil planet where all life is enslaved by a huge pulsating brain known as 'It'."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30832/day-of-deliverance.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30832","title":"Day of Deliverance","author":"by Johnny O'Brien","description":"The second adventure involving Jack Christie, son of scientists involved in an experiment to change the course of history through using the Taurus, a time machine.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31375/tomsmidnight-garden.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31375","title":"Tom's Midnight Garden","author":"by Philippa Pearce","description":"With no garden or children to play with Tom feels lonely and unhappy, until one night he hears the clock striking thirteen and discovers a secret garden."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30487/timeriders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30487","title":"TimeRiders","author":"by Alex Scarrow","description":"Maddy should have died in a plane crash. Liam should have died at sea when the Titanic sank. Sal should have died in a tragic fire. But a mysterious man whisked them away to safety.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31706/midwinterbloodd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31706","title":"Midwinterblood","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"In seven stories that take place on the strange island of Blessed, two souls seek each other over a period of a thousand years.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31020/when-you-reach-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31020","title":"When You Reach Me","author":"by Rebecca Stead","description":"Miranda's familiar world begins to unravel when her best friend is hit by a stranger and refuses to speak to her anymore. Then mysterious notes start to arrive with clues about the future.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31377/the-girl-who-leapt-through-time.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31377","title":"The Girl Who Leapt Through Time","author":"by Yasutaka Tsutsui","description":"The Girl Who Leapt Through Time is the story of 15-year-old schoolgirl Kazuko, who accidentally discovers that she can leap back and forth in time after a strange encounter with a shadowy figure at school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31374/travellerintime.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31374","title":"A Traveller in Time","author":"by Alison Uttley","description":"Penelope is sent to stay with her great-aunt in an old Derbyshire house where the Babingtons used to live where discovers she can slip in and out of time","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":91,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/91/","title":"Pirates","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34135/tenlittlepirates.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34135","title":"Ten Little Pirates","author":"by Mike Brownlow and Simon Rickerty","description":"A counting adventure with pirates... and a giant squid!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31321/9780230017948.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31321","title":"The Troll","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"This fun and unusual picture book brings together two classic tales with a modern twist","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31852/15-the-pirates-next-door.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31852","title":"The Pirates Next Door","author":"by Jonny Duddle","description":"Lots of humour and irrepressibly rakish pirates combine in this entertaining book about looking beyond appearances","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25457/9781405211611-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25457","title":"The Night Pirates","author":"by Peter Harris","description":"A band of rough, tough, girl pirates steal the front of Tom's house for disguise and agree to take him off on an adventure. The youthful pirates attack Captain Patch and his grown-up pirates, who have never seen a sailing...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31381/9781846860621-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31381","title":"Port Side Pirates!","author":"by Debbie Harter","description":"Fun rhyming text with a singalong CD","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33834/pirate-house.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33834","title":"The Pirate House","author":"by Rebecca Patterson","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24550/pirate-pete-a-changethestory-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24550","title":"Pirate Pete: A Change-the-Story Book","author":"by Nick Sharratt","description":"As Pirate Pete sails the sea in his pirate ship, he meets One-eyed Wanda and Captain Stubble, who guide him to a treasure chest containing... whatever the reader wants!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31383/9781409308416-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31383","title":"This Little Pirate","author":"by Lucy Lyes","description":"Toddlers and young children will love interacting with the friendly touch-and-feel pirates in this sturdy board book","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31382/9780746085240-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31382","title":"That's Not My Pirate...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"Lovely, colourful, stimulating book for very young children","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":92,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/92/","title":"Books about animals","list_description":"Lots of Julia Donaldson books feature animal characters - from whales to ladybirds, from monkeys to mice! Here are some of our favourite animal themed books.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24583/snailwhale.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24583","title":"The Snail and the Whale","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"This book by the award-winning Gruffalo partnership is about a tiny snail who longs to see the world, and the enormous grey-blue humpback whale who gives him a lift on his tail.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27003/tiddler-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27003","title":"Tiddler","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Although he looks small and ordinary, Tiddler is a fish who loves to tell tall tales. But one day he is swept up in a fisherman's net and then thrown back in to an unfamiliar part of the sea.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28969/gruffalo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28969","title":"The Gruffalo","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Axel Scheffler","description":"In this much-loved picture book, a little mouse walks through the woods and encounters a fox, an owl and a snake.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29586/tabbymctat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29586","title":"Tabby McTat","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"A poetic story of love, adventure and music that demands to be read aloud or possibly sung, depending on the power of the reader's purr.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30065/monkey-puzzle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30065","title":"Monkey Puzzle","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Monkey is lost in the jungle, so he asks Butterfly to help him find his mum. However, Butterfly cannot seem to understand that Monkey and his mum look alike!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31228/follow-the-swallow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31228","title":"Follow the Swallow","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Chack the blackbird is brown but claims he will turn black and that the berries in the tree where he lives will turn orange, but Apollo the swallow doesn't believe him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31899/9781407124377-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31899","title":"The Highway Rat","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"This rhyming tale of a villainous Highway Rat is the latest book from Children’s Laureate Julian Donaldson and her Gruffalo collaborator Axel Scheffler. The Highway Rat, gallops along the highway stealing food from other animals – clover from a rabbit,...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31227/night-monkey-day-monkey.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31227","title":"Night Monkey Day Monkey","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Lucy Richards","description":"Night Monkey and Day Monkey both live in the same jungle but their lives are worlds apart until one day Night Monkey wakes up in the day and Day Monkey wakes in the night.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31205/what-the-ladybird-heard.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31205","title":"What the Ladybird Heard","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Lydia Monks","description":"The animals on the farm are always noisy, all except for the ladybird who never says a word. But when burglars plot to steal the farmer's fine prize cow, the ladybird has a plan...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31208/sharing-a-shell.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31208","title":"Sharing a Shell","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Lydia Monks","description":"Poor crab has lost his shell, and nobody wants to share. But when he finally finds a shell of his own, he is surprised to find himself being asked to move over!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31212/chocmoussegreedygoose.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31212","title":"Chocolate Mousse for Greedy Goose","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Nick Sharratt","description":"Join in the fun as all the animals come together for a chaotic dinner party! Tasty treats are on the menu - but unfortunately not all of the animals have very good table manners.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31329/rhyming-rabbit.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31329","title":"The Rhyming Rabbit","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"The Rhyming Rabbit isn’t like the other rabbits, he likes to make up rhymes about the world around him but not everyone is interested in hearing them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":93,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/93/","title":"Booky's choice","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32472/topsy-and-tim.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32472","title":"Topsy and Tim Start School","author":"by Jean Adamson","description":"Find out what happens on the twins' first day at school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33125/9781847803832.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33125","title":"The Book of Dreams","author":"by Shirin Adl","description":"This unusual picture book may help some children to put into words their ideas about the strange and abstract concept of dreams.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29824/funnybones.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29824","title":"Funnybones","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"In the first book of this now classic series, we are taken down the dark, dark street to the dark, dark house and into the dark, dark cellar in which the skeletons live.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31536/the-jolly-postman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31536","title":"The Jolly Postman or Other People’s Letters","author":"by Janet & Allan Ahlberg","description":"Brilliantly designed with lots of little details to spot, this old favourite will be enjoyed time and time again","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32676/the-black-cat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32676","title":"Funnybones: The Black Cat","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"Another Funnybones adventure. This time, the skeleton friends go sledging - whee!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33782/mrs-wobble-the-waitress.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33782","title":"Mrs Wobble the Waitress","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"This cheery and funny tale is another winner in the Happy Families range of stories. Perfect for sharing, it is sure to raise lots of giggles!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30574/baby-s-catalogue.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30574","title":"The Baby's Catalogue","author":"by Janet and Allan Ahlberg","description":"This book's packed with lots of baby pictures and baby items. It's great for learning and making up stories - this fantastic book will lead to lots of talk with your child.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31926/9781847801890-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31926","title":"Little Lion","author":"by Lesley Beake","description":"A wonderful story based on a traditional tale from the Suthern African Bushmen","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33627/yes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33627","title":"The Yes","author":"by Sarah Bee","description":"Stunning illustrations complement this quirky story to encourage reluctant adventurers to overcome their anxieties and grasp life with both hands.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34605/51rb-nq5-vl._sx428_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34605","title":"Bunny Loves to Learn","author":"by Peter Bently","description":"Four friends are asked to dress up from someone from the past and create something to do with their respective character.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29326/what-does-daddy-do.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29326","title":"What Does Daddy Do?","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"One day at nursery, the children begin to discuss what their daddies do - which gets Daisy wondering about her own Daddy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30715/my-sister-is-an-alien.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30715","title":"My sister is an Alien","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"Alfie's new baby sister, Ruby, looks, sounds and smells like an alien. Alfie is convinced she often cries for home. He decides to take Ruby back to the moon where she belongs.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25020/jake-cake-the-robot-dinner-lady.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25020","title":"The Robot Dinner Lady","author":"by Michael Broad","description":"In these three short stories Jake tells his own incredible tales of the mayhem which follows when a normal boy investigates a variety of what seem to him to be unbelievable events.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24459/mister-seahorse.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24459","title":"Mister Seahorse","author":"by Eric Carle","description":"Mister Seahorse, like many other types of marine animal, is a 'male mother'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29869/slowly-slowly-slowly-said-the-sloth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29869","title":"\"Slowly, Slowly, Slowly,\" Said the Sloth","author":"by Eric Carle","description":"Sloth lives in the rainforest with pumas, bats, monkeys and many more animals. Sloth's fellow creatures can't understand why he is so quiet, so slow and so lazy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29884/do-you-want-to-be-my-friend.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29884","title":"Do You Want To Be My Friend?","author":"by Eric Carle","description":"'Do you want to be my friend?' Asked just once, this simple question starts a little mouse's journey through this almost wordless picture book, seeking the perfect companion.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24366/something-else.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24366","title":"Something Else","author":"by Kathryn Cave","description":"Something Else is a lonely creature, excluded from everything because he is different. This is the perfect book for reassuring any child that being different can be a very positive thing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32297/9780141502274-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32297","title":"This is Actually My Party","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Lauren Child's much-loved characters Charlie and little sister Lola are back in this fun birthday story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33272/2013-14-booktime-but-excuse-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33272","title":"But Excuse Me That is My Book","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Children will join Charlie, Lola and their friends on a trip to the library to look at all the different types of books that Lola might like to read. It is a warm and funny story about family, friends and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33927/new-small-person.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33927","title":"The New Small Person","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"An endearingly funny story, featuring Lauren Child's heart-warming illustrations, about the arrival of a new sibling and the havoc that ensues.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34547/grandads-island.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34547","title":"Grandad's Island","author":"by Benji Davies","description":"A subtle story about love and loss enhanced by delightful illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29823/hairy-maclary-s-bone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29823","title":"Hairy Maclary's Bone","author":"by Lynley Dodd","description":"Hairy Maclary is lucky enough to be given a big juicy bone by the butcher, Samuel Stone. This does not go unnoticed by all the other dogs who decide to follow him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33271/manual_9780141332888-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33271","title":"The Further Adventures of the Owl and the Pussy-Cat","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"At the end of Edward Lear's much loved poem, the happily married Owl and the Pussy-cat are dancing hand-in-hand on the edge of the sand... but what happened next?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33670/macavity.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33670","title":"Macavity","author":"by TS Eliot","description":"Escaped from Old Possum's Book of Practical Cats, Macavity is now the star of his own picture book. With new illustrations from Arthur Robins, this timeless rhyme will charm a new generation.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25740/here-we-go-round-the-mulberry-bush.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25740","title":"Here We Go Round the Mulberry Bush","author":"by Sophie Fatus and Fred Penner","description":"A multicultural take on a familiar old nursery rhyme, which transports each familiar activity into everyday life in Britain, West Africa, India and China.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33687/drummer-boy-of-john-john.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33687","title":"Drummer Boy of John John","author":"by Mark Greenwood","description":"The vibrant colours and swinging sounds of Trinidad resound through this story of musical invention and enjoyment","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33765/marshmallows-for-martians.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33765","title":"Marshmallows for Martians","author":"by Adam and Charlotte Guillain","description":"Bright, busy illustrations provide ample material for discussion, filled with a jumble of familiar objects and extraordinary aliens.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33863/wanda-and-alien-go-camping.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33863","title":"Wanda and the Alien Go Camping","author":"by Sue Hendra","description":"Vivid, exciting and imaginative illustrations complement a charming story celebrating difference, friendship, non-verbal communication and alternative views of the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33934/where-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33934","title":"Where Bear?","author":"by Sophie Henn","description":"When a little boy's pet polar bear grows up, he's too big for the house, and has to be found a new home. But where?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33747/mouse-who-ate-the-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33747","title":"The Mouse Who Ate the Moon","author":"by Petr Horáček","description":"This peep-through story book has beautiful illustrations which are brought to life with the peep-through hole on each page. An endearing and funny story with friendship at its heart.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34678/9781406358223.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34678","title":"The Mouse Who Reached the Sky","author":"by Petr Horáček","description":"A simple tale of friendship and cooperation between animals, beautifully illustrated in Horáček's distinctive style.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34515/the-little-gardener.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34515","title":"The Little Gardener","author":"by Emily Hughes","description":"With diverse illustrations, and a clear story to follow, this wonderful book is the perfect read - especially when your own garden is full in bloom.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34654/9781782300311.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34654","title":"Alfie Outdoors","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Shirley Hughes's iconic Alfie takes a trip into the garden and starts gardening and finding out more about the creepy crawlies.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.c