{"id":107,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/107/","title":"Poetry, Rhyme and Songs","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24857/eachpeach.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24857","title":"Each Peach Pear Plum","author":"by Janet & Allan Ahlberg","description":"This classic book from author and illustrator team Janet and Allan Ahlberg is a real favourite with families","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25148/friendly-matches.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25148","title":"Friendly Matches","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"Friendly Matches is an entertaining, and at times thought-provoking, collection of poetry about football.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29560/the-puffin-book-of-fantastic-first-poems.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29560","title":"The Puffin Book of Fantastic First Poems","author":"by June Crebbin","description":"Poets ranging from Robert Louis Stevenson to Eleanor Farjeon are featured in each of the themed sections devoted to subjects such as animals, night time, food and nonsense verse."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25325/revoltingrhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25325","title":"Revolting Rhymes","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This is an hilarious collection of some well-loved fairy tales, cleverly reinvented by Roald Dahl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29823/hairy-maclary-s-bone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29823","title":"Hairy Maclary's Bone","author":"by Lynley Dodd","description":"Hairy Maclary is lucky enough to be given a big juicy bone by the butcher, Samuel Stone. This does not go unnoticed by all the other dogs who decide to follow him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33271/manual_9780141332888-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33271","title":"The Further Adventures of the Owl and the Pussy-Cat","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"At the end of Edward Lear's much loved poem, the happily married Owl and the Pussy-cat are dancing hand-in-hand on the edge of the sand... but what happened next?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33670/macavity.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33670","title":"Macavity","author":"by TS Eliot","description":"Escaped from Old Possum's Book of Practical Cats, Macavity is now the star of his own picture book. With new illustrations from Arthur Robins, this timeless rhyme will charm a new generation.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25740/here-we-go-round-the-mulberry-bush.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25740","title":"Here We Go Round the Mulberry Bush","author":"by Sophie Fatus and Fred Penner","description":"A multicultural take on a familiar old nursery rhyme, which transports each familiar activity into everyday life in Britain, West Africa, India and China.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31484/9780140383911-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31484","title":"Bad, Bad Cats","author":"by Roger McGough","description":"Packed with witty wordplay, and quirky humour, this delightful collection will appeal to children of all ages","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29673/9780140384215-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29673","title":"The Puffin Book of Utterly Brilliant Poetry","author":"by Brian Patten","description":"Ten utterly individual poets contribute a selection of poems as varied as the colours of a rainbow to this glorious celebration of the power of verse","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30754/michael-rosen-s-book-of-bad-things.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30754","title":"Michael Rosen's Big Book of Bad Things","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":"Some poems are funny, some desperately sad. But in Rosen's hands, small, scruffy words you don't even notice gain extra weight and meaning...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31483/quick-lets-get-out-of-here.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31483","title":"Quick, Let’s Get Out of Here","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":"Two former Children’s Laureates join forces for this brilliantly entertaining poetry collection for children","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28993/yo-ho-ho.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28993","title":"Yo Ho Ho! A-Pirating We'll Go","author":"by Kaye Umansky","description":"Nick Sharratt's bold, colourful, funny illustrations filled with detail and movement bring added life to this collection of pirate-related short poems.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28640/ouch-pouch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28640","title":"There's an Ouch in My Pouch!","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Willaby Wallaby is throwing a wobbly...He’s quite determined he still needs a pouch to live in, but suddenly it’s just too knobbly, wodgy, wedgy and wriggly and so he jumps out.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
