{"id":116,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/116/","title":"Poetry books for the Poetry Friendly Classroom","list_description":"Take a look at some of our favourite children's poetry books - perfect for use in the poetry-friendly classroom.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31324/pumpkin-grumpkin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31324","title":"Pumpkin Grumpkin","author":"by John Agard and Grace Nichols","description":"Amusing and bemusing poetry from around the globe. John Agard and Grace Nichols have assembled a bunch of silly poems in this new collection brought to life with quirky illustrations by Satoshi Kitamura. m From classics like The Jabberwocky to...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24523/cloud-busting.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24523","title":"Cloud Busting","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Shortlisted for the 2004 Nestlé Smarties Book Prize (age 6-8 category), an exploration of an unlikely friendship between two very different boys.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24811/heartbeat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24811","title":"Heartbeat","author":"by Sharon Creech","description":"Annie loves drawing, running barefoot, her family, and possibly Max, her running partner. It’s an eventful time for the 12-year-old: as her mother is about to give birth, her beloved grandfather is sliding slowly into dementia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25325/revoltingrhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25325","title":"Revolting Rhymes","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This is an hilarious collection of some well-loved fairy tales, cleverly reinvented by Roald Dahl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31322/crazy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31322","title":"Crazy Mayonnaisy Mum","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"There is a poem to appeal to everyone in this thoughtful and fun collection","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26472/the-hat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26472","title":"The Hat","author":"by Carol Ann Duffy","description":"Bubbling over with humour and life, the poems in The Hat paint pictures, evoke smells, conjure sounds and encapsulate events both contemporary and historical.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29510/new-and-collected-poems-for-children.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29510","title":"New and Collected Poems for Children","author":"by Carol Ann Duffy","description":"Poet Laureate, Carol Ann Duffy, brings together the best of her poems for children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25380/tedhughespoems.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25380","title":"Collected Poems for Children","author":"by Ted Hughes","description":"All Hughes readers might expect the crows, horses and sheep they encounter here, but the haggis/bagpipe hybrid might be more of a surprise!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28157/red-cherry-red.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28157","title":"Red, Cherry Red","author":"by Jackie Kay","description":"Truthful, soulful and witty poems in this collection explore a theme of identity. Who are we? What reveals us? Is our identity bound up in where we live or in the dreams we hold?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25381/sensational-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25381","title":"Sensational!","author":"by Roger McGough","description":"Every poem could inspire a child's writing, reading or thinking, and their teachers' too.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31484/9780140383911-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31484","title":"Bad, Bad Cats","author":"by Roger McGough","description":"Packed with witty wordplay, and quirky humour, this delightful collection will appeal to children of all ages","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31481/9780590542913-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31481","title":"Plum","author":"by Tony Mitton","description":"This enjoyable collection from popular children’s poet Tony Mitton brings together a wide range of engaging poems for younger children","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28788/read-me-and-laugh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28788","title":"Read Me and Laugh","author":"by Gaby Morgan","description":"This is a collection of funny poems from a wide range of poets from Spike Milligan to Valarie Bloom, and Lewes Carroll to Michael Rosen.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30379/michael-rosen-s-a-z-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30379","title":"Michael Rosen's A to Z","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":"Former Children’s Laureate, Michael Rosen, gathers together the best children’s poetry from Agard to Zephaniah in this collection. From Grace Nichol's poem about her Caribbean Gran visiting England to Rosen's own hilarious account of his Dad's intolerance to 'The Noise',...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31483/quick-lets-get-out-of-here.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31483","title":"Quick, Let’s Get Out of Here","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":"Two former Children’s Laureates join forces for this brilliantly entertaining poetry collection for children","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29226/j-is-for-jamaica.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29226","title":"J is for Jamaica","author":"by Benjamin Zephaniah","description":"Welcome to this whistle-stop tour of Jamaica - from A for Ackee to Z for Zinc.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":117,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/117/","title":"Funny books","list_description":"From bottoms and pants to kung-fu pandas and monsters, there is a story for every child in this great list of funny books that will have you and your child rolling about with laughter.  For a selection of new funny reads, take a look at this year's Roald Dahl Funny Prize shortlisted books.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29824/funnybones.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29824","title":"Funnybones","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"In the first book of this now classic series, we are taken down the dark, dark street to the dark, dark house and into the dark, dark cellar in which the skeletons live.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33144/9780954737382.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33144","title":"I’m not cute!","author":"by Jonathan Allen","description":"Baby Owl is fed up. In fact, he’s furious. He sets off for a walk in the woods but kangaroo, fox and squirrel won’t leave him alone. They insist on picking him up, hugging him and telling him how cute...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24842/pants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24842","title":"Pants","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"From hairy pants, scary pants and fairy pants, to loose pants, tight pants and lighting up at night pants, this must-have picture book explores every possible variation on the theme.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31397/9781406323429-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31397","title":"A Visitor for Bear","author":"by Bonny Becker","description":"Bear likes to be on his own until a mouse turns up and teaches him that sharing experiences is far better than being on your own","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31498/9781849392075-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31498","title":"The Great Sheep Shenanigans","author":"by Peter Bently","description":"Lou Pine is one hungry wolf who cunjurs up a cunning plan to catch a sheep for his dinner. But the sheep are not as dumb as they first appear… This hilarious romp from the award-winning creators of The Great...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30715/my-sister-is-an-alien.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30715","title":"My sister is an Alien","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"Alfie's new baby sister, Ruby, looks, sounds and smells like an alien. Alfie is convinced she often cries for home. He decides to take Ruby back to the moon where she belongs.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33830/really-really-big-dinosaur.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33830","title":"The really, really, really big dinosaur","author":"by Richard Byrne","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33927/new-small-person.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33927","title":"The New Small Person","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"An endearingly funny story, featuring Lauren Child's heart-warming illustrations, about the arrival of a new sibling and the havoc that ensues.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33212/thedaythecrayonsquite.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33212","title":"The Day the Crayons Quit","author":"by Drew Daywalt & Oliver Jeffers","description":"Award-winning illustrator and artist Oliver Jeffers has teamed up with film writer and director Drew Daywalt to create this gorgeously colourful picture book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25568/wriggle-roar_fc.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25568","title":"Wriggle and Roar!","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"This super collection of 17 original rhymes for joining in with has appeal for the new toddler and well into the nursery years.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-4"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26003/penguin-by-polly-dunbar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26003","title":"Penguin","author":"by Polly Dunbar","description":"Polly Dunbar's illustrations are gorgeous and her palette stylish - from the endearing Ben's rosy cheeks to the magnificent turquoise lion who eats him up.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33713/never-ask-a-dinosaur-to-dinner.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33713","title":"Never Ask a Dinosaur to Dinner","author":"by Gareth Edwards","description":"This fabulously daft tale around a child's evening routine is the perfect bedtime book to share.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33869/winston-was-worried.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33869","title":"Winston Was Worried","author":"by Pamela Duncan Edwards and Benji Davies","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34223/yuck-said-the-yak.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34223","title":"Yuck said the Yak","author":"by Alex English","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31161/thank-you-for-looking-after-our-pets.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31161","title":"Thank You for Looking After Our Pets","author":"by Tim Hopgood","description":"Who can look after your pets if they are giraffes, or penguins or carnivorous plants? Hopgood's story and funny, bold, colourful illustrations will attract even the youngest child.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33076/9781408837016-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33076","title":"Time for Bed, Fred!","author":"by Yasmeen Ismail","description":"Fred is a very naughty dog - and he doesn't want to go to bed one bit!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30473/9781847384744-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30473","title":"Dogs Don't Do Ballet","author":"by Anna Kemp","description":"Everyone knows that dogs don’t do ballet, except for one little girl in Miss Polly’s ballet class.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32181/the-worst-princess-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32181","title":"The Worst Princess","author":"by Anna Kemp","description":"With a rhyming text by Anna Kemp and delightfully humorous illustrations by Sara Ogilvie, this entertaining picture book offers a refreshingly tongue-in-cheek spin on the conventional fairy tale princess.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32669/9781406343939-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32669","title":"This is Not My Hat","author":"by Jon Klassen","description":"A little fish has stolen an equally small bowler hat from a much bigger fish. Hiding himself in the weedsm, he is confident he won't be discovered - but the big fish is on his trail...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31394/wildwith-noises.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31394","title":"Go Wild with ... Noises","author":"by Neal Layton","description":"Growl like a bear and squawk like a parrot in this colourful and fun introduction to animal noises","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32399/9780192756794-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32399","title":"Chickens Can't See in the Dark","author":"by Kristyna Litten","description":"When Little Pippa Chicken is told by her teacher that chickens can't see in the dark, she sets out to prove him wrong, and soon becomes the talk of Sunnyside Farm.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34137/fish-food.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34137","title":"Fish Food","author":"by Andy Mansfield and Henning Löhlein","description":"A clever pop-up book about the underwater food chain.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33829/hugless-douglas-big-sleep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33829","title":"Hugless Douglas and the Big Sleep","author":"by David Melling","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33823/this-rabbit-that-rabbit.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33823","title":"this rabbit, that rabbit","author":"by Jane Porter","description":"Shiny pictures to touch and funny rhymes to make little ones laugh"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32479/9780857630193-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32479","title":"The Baby That Roared","author":"by Simon Puttock","description":"Mr and Mrs Deer don’t have any children, but they would love to have a baby of their own to look after. When a mysterious bundle arrives on their doorstep they are overjoyed.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30602/moo-cow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30602","title":"Moo-Cow, Kung-Fu-Cow","author":"by Nick Sharratt","description":"Pull the tabs and lift the flaps – who will be your favourite Moo-Cow?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31496/bedtime-for-monsters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31496","title":"Bedtime for Monsters","author":"by Ed Vere","description":"Do you ever wonder if somewhere, not too far away, there might be monsters?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30436/9780141328805-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30436","title":"Sing a Song of Bottoms!","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Young children will love the rhyming text which rejoices in the diversity of bottoms!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"}]}
{"id":118,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/118/","title":"Julia Donaldson","list_description":"Best known for The Gruffalo, Julia Donaldson has written over 120 books and plays for children and teenagers, including some of the UK's best-selling picture books. Julia was the Children's Laureate from 2011-13.  Download Julia Donaldson activity sheeets – includes crafts to make, songs to sing and a tasty Gruffalo cake to bake","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24472/gruffchild.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24472","title":"The Gruffalo's Child","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Five years after the publication of multi award-winning The Gruffalo, author Julia Donaldson and illustrator Axel Scheffler return with a much-awaited sequel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25568/wriggle-roar_fc.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25568","title":"Wriggle and Roar!","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"This super collection of 17 original rhymes for joining in with has appeal for the new toddler and well into the nursery years.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-4"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27003/tiddler-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27003","title":"Tiddler","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Although he looks small and ordinary, Tiddler is a fish who loves to tell tall tales. But one day he is swept up in a fisherman's net and then thrown back in to an unfamiliar part of the sea.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30357/toddlewoddle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30357","title":"Toddle Waddle","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"An ideal book for sharing - babies will love imitating the sounds in the text and pointing out details in the illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28969/gruffalo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28969","title":"The Gruffalo","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Axel Scheffler","description":"In this much-loved picture book, a little mouse walks through the woods and encounters a fox, an owl and a snake.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31207/cave-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31207","title":"Cave Baby","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Emily Gravett","description":"Cave Baby is restless and sets about amusing himself. But he is warned that being naughty will mean 'A mammoth's going to throw you to the big brown bear!'","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31205/what-the-ladybird-heard.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31205","title":"What the Ladybird Heard","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Lydia Monks","description":"The animals on the farm are always noisy, all except for the ladybird who never says a word. But when burglars plot to steal the farmer's fine prize cow, the ladybird has a plan...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":119,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/119/","title":"Best Book Guide 2011","list_description":"Booktrust's 2011 Best Book Guide brings together reviews of some of our favourite books published during the last year (July 2010 to July 2011). The selected books include picture books, graphic novels, poetry, short stories, fiction and non-fiction in the following age categories: 5 years and under; 5 to 8 years; 9 to 12 years; Teens and Young Adults.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29896/9781408309575-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29896","title":"I Love My Mummy","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"What is it about Mummies that makes them so lovable and so very special?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30828/artichoke-hearts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30828","title":"Artichoke Hearts","author":"by Sita Brahmachari","description":"This empathetic account of the process of bereavement, a month’s diary, reassures readers that we grow from our experiences, however painful they are.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31438/9781877467431-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31438","title":"Guji-Guji","author":"by Chih-Yaun Chen","description":"One day a rather unusual egg rolls into Mother Duck's nest and it hatches to reveal a baby crocodile. The little creature becomes a perfectly happy 'crocoduck', until one day he is asked to betray his duckling brothers and sisters…This...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31515/9781780080031-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31515","title":"Otto the Book Bear","author":"by Katie Cleminson","description":"A charming celebration of books and reading","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31308/a-place-to-call-home.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31308","title":"A Place to Call Home","author":"by Alexis Deacon","description":"A family of furry animals grow too big for their home in an old mattress and have to go out into the unknown world of the back yard to find a new one. This endearing and engaging picture book about...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31404/flumflum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31404","title":"Jack and the FlumFlum Tree","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"When Jack’s granny falls ill with the moozles, the doctor tells him that the only thing that will cure her is the fruit of the mysterious flumflum tree.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31485/9780857560087-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31485","title":"In The Sea There Are Crocodiles","author":"by Fabio Geda","description":"First published in Italian last year, the story of Enaiatollah Akbari's journey from Afghanistan to Italy has now been translated into English","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31158/a-roman-rescue.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31158","title":"A Roman Rescue","author":"by Kelly Gerard","description":"Charlie and his trusty dog Bandit fall down a sinkhole and are transported to ancient Rome where he meets Cosmo and goes on an adventure...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31573/9780141336039-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31573","title":"Grace","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"Grace's quest to find her father and reunite her family is moving and funny","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30425/losing-it.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30425","title":"Losing It","author":"by Edited by Keith Gray","description":"This is a collection of eight short stories about growing-up, virginity and sex for teenagers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31303/a-bit-lost.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31303","title":"A Bit Lost","author":"by Chris Haughton","description":"Little Owl falls asleep in his (rather precarious) nest, falls onto the ground with a 'bump' and becomes 'a bit lost'. But Squirrel comes to his rescue...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30467/unhooking-the-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30467","title":"Unhooking the Moon","author":"by Gregory Hughes","description":"Bob has a stubborn younger sister with disturbing fits and upsetting premonitions. She foretells her best friend's murder, their dog's disappearance and her father's death. Bob calls her the Rat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31305/one-dog-and-his-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31305","title":"One Dog and His Boy","author":"by Eva Ibbotson","description":"All Hal wants for his birthday is a dog and when he is given one he is overjoyed. But when Hal realises Fleck was only his for the weekend, he sets off on an adventure with the dog...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31570/9781847801852-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31570","title":"Actual Size","author":"by Steve Jenkins","description":"Have you ever looked a giant squid in the eye, shaken hands with a gorilla or been face to face with a tiger?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30821/the-parade.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30821","title":"The Parade","author":"by KP Kojo","description":"Why do hippos live under water, bees live in holes and spiders hide in dark places? Find out in this lively collection of Ananse stories from Ghana.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31241/taff-in-the-waaf.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31241","title":"Taff in the WAAF","author":"by Mick Manning and Brita Granstrom","description":"An account of the secret work carried out during WWII at Bletchley Park, based on the experience of Manning's own mother, Taff.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31245/9780385618519-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31245","title":"Moon Pie","author":"by Simon Mason","description":"A deceptively simple novel for older Key Stage 2 readers: easy to read but addressing serious and complex issues around bereavement, self-image, family relationships and loyalty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30963/a-beautiful-lie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30963","title":"A Beautiful Lie","author":"by Irfan Master","description":"Set in India during the summer of 1947, A Beautiful Lie follows the tumultuous events of the Partition of India through the eyes of Bilal who is looking after his ill father.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30440/counting-birds.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30440","title":"Counting Birds","author":"by Alice Melvin","description":"This stylishly illustrated counting book from a Best New Illustrator, opens with a vibrant cockerel crowing to welcome the day and ends with a solitary barn owl flying off the page and slipping into the night. Perfect for learning how...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31508/9781409526728-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31508","title":"Penny Dreadful is a Magnet for Disaster","author":"by Joanna Nadin","description":"Boys as well as girls will race through these stories giggling all the way!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31309/amonstercallsss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31309","title":"A Monster Calls","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"Connor's mum has cancer and life is changing. There is the nightmare, then there is school, where people avoid him, or persecute him. And then there is the immense, mythic Monster.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31282/life-an-exploded-diagram.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31282","title":"Life: An Exploded Diagram","author":"by Mal Peet","description":"In this intelligent young adult novel, Clem's coming-of-age story of first love and burgeoning sexuality is woven around a tense account of the mounting Cuban Missile Crisis","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30470/9781840111590-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30470","title":"The Django","author":"by Levi Pinfold","description":"This book, based on the story of legendary jazz musician Django Reinhardt, is illustrated in a detailed and painterly style.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31342/killing-honour.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31342","title":"Killing Honour","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"A blood-curdling murder story set in Leicester’s Asian community where family honour seems sometimes to count for more than family love","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30756/withering-tights.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30756","title":"Withering Tights","author":"by Louise Rennison","description":"When Tallulah’s parents pack her off to an am-dram college - Dother Hall, she hopes she will become a toppity-top-actress type without accidentally tripping over her knees or involuntarily doing Irish dancing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31224/the-language-of-cat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31224","title":"The Language of Cat","author":"by Rachel Rooney","description":"A wonderful testament to the scope and versatility of language which youngsters will enjoy reading and which is likely to inspire them to be creative in their own poetic endeavours.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30902/lunatics-and-luck.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30902","title":"The Raven Mysteries: Lunatics and Luck","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"When the body count mysteriously starts climbing, horrible new schoolteacher Mr Brandish’s suspicious-looking heavy wooden trunk starts to look, well, very suspicious indeed.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31569/9781780080017-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31569","title":"Good Little Wolf","author":"by Nadia Shireen","description":"Rolf is a good little wolf - he likes baking cakes, eating all his vegetables, and is always nice to his friends","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31572/9780230753136-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31572","title":"It’s a Book","author":"by Lane Smith","description":"Jackass, playing on his computer, wants to know what Monkey is up to. Monkey is reading a book","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30900/laura-marlin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30900","title":"Dead Man's Cove","author":"by Lauren St John","description":"When mysterious uncle Calvin rescues Laura Marlin from her gloomy life in an orphanage, she can't believe her luck! But she soon realises that her Cornish paradise is full of mysteries...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31020/when-you-reach-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31020","title":"When You Reach Me","author":"by Rebecca Stead","description":"Miranda's familiar world begins to unravel when her best friend is hit by a stranger and refuses to speak to her anymore. Then mysterious notes start to arrive with clues about the future.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31574/doesyourfacefit.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31574","title":"Does Your Face Fit?","author":"by Roger Stevens","description":"This thought-proving collection of poems explores everyday issues that affect young people today","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30904/do-igloos-have-loos.