hris Wormell","description":"A small silver fish has done everything he can possibly do in the ocean - he sings, dances and even performs plays, but has never walked upon the land.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29789/dog-loves-books.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29789","title":"Dog Loves Books","author":"by Louise Yates","description":"With an engaging hero and simple, understated text animated by witty, subtly coloured illustrations, this book about the sheer pleasure of books has a refreshing jaunty elegance.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":120,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/120/","title":"Favourite books about the environment","list_description":"From climate change to animal conservation, these picture books, poetry collections, novels and graphic novels will encourage children and young people to think about and discuss pressing issues about the environment.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30887/the-wombles.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30887","title":"The Wombles","author":"by Elizabeth Beresford","description":"A wayward umbrella, a life-like snowman and a landslide with a near-miss make young Womble Bungo’s first year out of the burrow a very exciting one indeed.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25143/9780330399081-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25143","title":"Exodus","author":"by Julie Bertagna","description":"Exodus is a disturbing and relevant epic that explores many contemporary themes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29639/under-the-weather.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29639","title":"Under the Weather","author":"by Tony Bradman","description":"A thought-provoking collection emphasising the importance of individual, as well as group initiatives.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31731/9781846434167-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31731","title":"The Lost Stars","author":"by Hannah Cumming","description":"A thought provoking tale of the beauty of the natural world and a reminder to value it in our increasingly busy lives","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31837/9781844287758-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31837","title":"North: The Greatest Animal Journey on Earth","author":"by Nick Dowson","description":"This exquisite picture book invites readers to accompany a host of animals from walruses to whales, as they migrate to the Arctic for the summer months","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28881/toby-alone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28881","title":"Toby Alone","author":"by Timothee de Fombelle","description":"Winner of the 2009 Marsh Award for Children's Literature in Translation, this exciting adventure has a serious message about the wisdom of using up the Earth’s resources","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31443/9781849393041-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31443","title":"One World","author":"by Michael Foreman","description":"A thought-provoking tale with a poignant environmental message","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31273/dear-greenpeace.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31273","title":"Dear Greenpeace","author":"by Simon James","description":"A simple, warm hearted and humorous book with charming illustrations. The correspondence could spark ideas for letter writing in the classroom setting.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29056/the-great-paper-caper.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29056","title":"The Great Paper Caper","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"This is an intelligent and entertaining picture book, with unique and fascinating illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31014/can-we-save-the-tiger.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31014","title":"Can We Save the Tiger?","author":"by Martin Jenkins","description":"A sequel to Ape, this beautifully illustrated book takes us through some of the extinct and endangered animals in the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31486/9781906427467-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31486","title":"Ravenwood","author":"by Andrew Peters","description":"Peters has dreamt up a surreal world which exists many centuries in the future, in the roots of the earth and many miles above it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35321/9781847807496.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35321","title":"Pandora","author":"by Victoria Turnbull","description":"Pandora the fox lives alone in a world of broken things. She fixes and mends them, giving new life to the forgotten. One day, an injured bird falls from the sky and she nurses it back to strength.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28532/varmints.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28532","title":"Varmints: Part One","author":"by Helen Ward","description":"In a world dehumanized by noisy industry and high-rise urbanisation, a lone thinker retains the ideal of living with nature, believing in its value for the future.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"}]}
{"id":121,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/121/","title":"Summer Reads 2011","list_description":"School's out for summer! We have picked some fun reads to enjoy over the summer holidays for every age, from thrilling adventures to holiday romances, there is something here for everyone.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31457/9781408312759-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31457","title":"Ultraviolet","author":"by RJ Anderson","description":"A remarkable, gripping and stunningly original new novel for teens","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31307/starcrossed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31307","title":"Starcrossed","author":"by Josephine Angelini","description":"When the beautiful and mysterious Delos family arrive on Nantucket Island, Helen Hamilton's teenaged life is turned upside down.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31399/9781406318333-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31399","title":"Anna Hibiscus' Song","author":"by Atinuke","description":"This delightful story about a happy girl learning to express her feelings is a wonderful celebration of the joy of life","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31221/too-much-trouble.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31221","title":"Too Much Trouble","author":"by Tom Avery","description":"An original interpretation of the Oliver Twist story reflecting a number of critical and significant contemporary issues.","re