{"id":127,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/127/","title":"Books about bullying for 8-12s","list_description":"Almost everyone gets bullied at some point in their life - so if this is happening to your child, they are not alone. Here are some books to help older primary school children who may be experiencing bullying or finding it tricky to make friends.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34162/7days.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34162","title":"7 Days","author":"by Eve Ainsworth","description":"This is the story of one week in Jess's life and that of her tormentor, popular girl Kez. A fresh approach to the school bully story, which is a short, punchy read with a strong and ever-relevant message.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24523/cloud-busting.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24523","title":"Cloud Busting","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Shortlisted for the 2004 Nestlé Smarties Book Prize (age 6-8 category), an exploration of an unlikely friendship between two very different boys.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31869/9781847802231-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31869","title":"Zero To Hero","author":"by Rob Childs","description":"An engaging tale of friendship, while at the same time raising the important issues of bullying and self confidence","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33986/blue-moon-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33986","title":"Blue Moon Day","author":"by Anne Fine","description":"Covering an interesting and varied mix of situations, these enjoyable school stories are a satisfying read, with particular appeal to more reluctant readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35331/9781408853368.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35331","title":"The Song from Somewhere Else","author":"by AF Harrold","description":"Frank is being bullied - for what, she's not sure. Being smart? Being different, perhaps. One day, after her bike is thrown in the middle of a huge patch of stinging nettles, Nick comes to her aid. A magical and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31309/amonstercallsss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31309","title":"A Monster Calls","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"Connor's mum has cancer and life is changing. There is the nightmare, then there is school, where people avoid him, or persecute him. And then there is the immense, mythic Monster.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25121/9780007332007-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25121","title":"Feather Boy","author":"by Nicky Singer","description":"Robert is having a tough time at school, being bullied by Nicker; he's also trying to deal with the break-up of his parents' marriage.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31805/9781848121645-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31805","title":"Don't Pick on Me!","author":"by Rosemary Stones","description":"This book explores why some people bully, why others are bullied and what you can do to change things","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29860/buried-alive.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29860","title":"Buried Alive!","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"This humorous tale sensitively highlights issues such as friendship and bullying.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30257/bad-girls.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30257","title":"Bad Girls","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Bitterly unhappy and fed up with being teased at school, Mandy White is in need of a friend.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":128,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/128/","title":"Favourite dystopian books","list_description":"Discover an array of dystopian worlds in our recommended booklist.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25143/9780330399081-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25143","title":"Exodus","author":"by Julie Bertagna","description":"Exodus is a disturbing and relevant epic that explores many contemporary themes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28476/noughts-and-crosses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28476","title":"Noughts and Crosses","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Callum is a Nought but his best friend Sephy is a Cross - the daughter of one of the most influential politicians in the country.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31517/9781408806487-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31517","title":"Gamerunner","author":"by B R Collins","description":"Collins’ fourth teen novel is dark, intense and disturbingly prophetic","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29230/hungergames.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29230","title":"The Hunger Games","author":"by Suzanne Collins","description":"Welcome to Panem: its Capitol repressively rules twelve satellite Districts, enslaving the populations as workers and controlling them through hunger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30948/matched.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30948","title":"Matched","author":"by Ally Condie","description":"Welcome to a Society that utterly controls its citizens; what they eat, what they do, who they marry - even when they die.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26036/9780340893609-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26036","title":"Incarceron","author":"by Catherine Fisher","description":"A rich complex fantasy about two very different worlds","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34669/9781781124048.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34669","title":"Jet Black Heart","author":"by Teresa Flavin","description":"A young girl named Dory is pulled back into the past after finding an old note in a letterbox.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31619/9780007326792-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31619","title":"The Pain Merchants","author":"by Janice Hardy","description":"The first in an epic dystopian fantasy adventure trilogy is an engaging story about family and friendship","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29567/theenemy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29567","title":"The Enemy","author":"by Charlie Higson","description":"When the sickness came, the adults became ill. The lucky ones died but many mutated into brainless, deformed monsters with a seemingly insatiable appetite - for children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27183/thedeclaration.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27183","title":"The Declaration","author":"by Gemma Malley","description":"A chilling story of a future where Longevity drugs have made sections of the population almost immortal. This is a thought-provoking read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28824/knifeofneverlettinggo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28824","title":"The Knife of Never Letting Go","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"The first in a series, this enthralling sci-fi/fantasy novel grips readers throughout, presenting them with tough questions about identity, ethics and the nature of truth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31022/across-the-universe.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31022","title":"Across the Universe","author":"by Beth Revis","description":"Amy and her family are cryogenically frozen and stored aboard the Godspeed to travel to a new planet - but Amy is wrongly unfrozen 50 years early, forcing her to experience life aboard the ship.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31455/9781906427627-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31455","title":"Six Days","author":"by Philip Webb","description":"In grim, post-apocalyptic London, the search is on for the ‘artefact’, an undefined and mysterious relic from the distant past which holds the key to the future of the earth and mankind.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32024/9781842999462-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32024","title":"Pale","author":"by Chris Wooding","description":"In an eerie futuristic world, society has figured out a way to bring people back from the dead...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31288/bloodredroadd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31288","title":"Blood Red Road","author":"by Moira Young","description":"A violent, desperate and compelling story about family, love and determination, which enthrals through its bold, powerful language","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":129,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/129/","title":"Favourite horror books","list_description":"Haunted houses, wolves, other dimensions, dark secrets and terrifying mysteries - here are ten scary books to sink your teeth into.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25915/the-stuff-of-nightmares.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25915","title":"The Stuff of Nightmares","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Kyle is the only one conscious after an horrific train crash, but how long can he survive when death is stalking the carriages looking for him?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31737/9781849393218-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31737","title":"Haunted","author":"by Susan Cooper","description":"A scintillating selection of supremely scary tales from 11 well-known children’s authors","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24729/coraline-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24729","title":"Coraline","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"One day Coraline unlocks a mysterious door that opens onto another world, a twisted parody of Coraline's own dimension.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29567/theenemy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29567","title":"The Enemy","author":"by Charlie Higson","description":"When the sickness came, the adults became ill. The lucky ones died but many mutated into brainless, deformed monsters with a seemingly insatiable appetite - for children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31745/forbidden.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31745","title":"The Demon Trappers: Forbidden","author":"by Jana Oliver","description":"A future where demons and the undead walk the streets"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31774/9781408800041-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31774","title":"The Dead of Winter","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"A nail-biting story of hauntings and terror by the master of the genre, Chris Priestley","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31868/princeomist.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31868","title":"The Prince of Mist","author":"by Carlos Ruiz Zafon","description":"This is a chilling and haunting story of magic and mystery","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31706/midwinterbloodd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31706","title":"Midwinterblood","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"In seven stories that take place on the strange island of Blessed, two souls seek each other over a period of a thousand years.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31114/birth-of-a-killer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31114","title":"Birth of a Killer","author":"by Darren Shan","description":"Birth of a Killer is the first book in a new series that form a prequel to the best-selling sequence The Saga of Darren Shan.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31455/9781906427627-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31455","title":"Six Days","author":"by Philip Webb","description":"In grim, post-apocalyptic London, the search is on for the ‘artefact’, an undefined and mysterious relic from the distant past which holds the key to the future of the earth and mankind.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":130,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/130/","title":"Historical fiction","list_description":"Older children and teenagers will enjoy these compelling stories set in times past - from exciting adventures to thought-provoking tales of troubled times.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29198/chains.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29198","title":"Chains","author":"by Laurie Halse Anderson","description":"A brilliantly told, exciting story, with a brave and dignified heroine, which reveals the complexities of this chapter of American history.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25439/strippedpjs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25439","title":"The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas","author":"by John Boyne","description":"Bruno is exploring his new home at 'Out-With' when he meets Shmuel, who lives on the other side of a fence which surrounds a large camp in the grounds.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31611/9780552560740-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31611","title":"Prisoner of the Inquisition","author":"by Theresa Breslin","description":"Zarita, only daughter of the town magistrate, lives a life of wealth and privilege","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33257/jadeboy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33257","title":"The Jade Boy","author":"by Cate Cain","description":"What is Count Cazalon's sinister plan - and can Jem and his friends stop him?","reading_