"description":"It is the day before Christmas and the four Mellops brothers all have the same idea - to surprise their family with a Christmas tree","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31854/9781840111880-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31854","title":"The Town Mouse and the Country Mouse","author":"by Helen Ward","description":"A visually stunning version of the classic tale","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31610/9781742373195-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31610","title":"FOX","author":"by Margaret Wild","description":"A story with a true moral behind it: that friendship can conquer anything. Now available in a beautiful 10th anniversary edition","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31708/9780385618922-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31708","title":"Sapphire Battersea","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Another fact-filled and exciting slice of working-class Victorian life, showing readers how young people used to live","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31871/green-glass-beads.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31871","title":"Green Glass Beads","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"An eclectic collection of poetry that mixes old and contemporary, funny and deadly serious poems","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31793/zeal-of-zebras.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31793","title":"A Zeal of Zebras","author":"by Woop Studios","description":"Vibrant design fills each page and the alphabetical listings create a clear, engaging read","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"}]}
{"id":132,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/132/","title":"Favourite books about love","list_description":"Books are the perfect place to explore and talk about the complexities of the heart. Here are some of our favourites to get you talking about your emotions.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31307/starcrossed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31307","title":"Starcrossed","author":"by Josephine Angelini","description":"When the beautiful and mysterious Delos family arrive on Nantucket Island, Helen Hamilton's teenaged life is turned upside down.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32617/9781595144355-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32617","title":"Chopsticks","author":"by Jessica Anthony and Rodrigo Corral","description":"This unusual story of star-crossed teenage love is told visually, through a series of photographs, collages and scrapbook pages","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28476/noughts-and-crosses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28476","title":"Noughts and Crosses","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Callum is a Nought but his best friend Sephy is a Cross - the daughter of one of the most influential politicians in the country.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31773/9780141326115-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31773","title":"Naked","author":"by Kevin Brooks","description":"London, 1976: a summer of chaos, punk, love ... and the boy they called Billy the Kid","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24948/sugarrush.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24948","title":"Sugar Rush","author":"by Julie Burchill","description":"Shortlisted for the 2005 Booktrust Teenage Prize, this is a controversial and daring look at the gritty reality of teenage experience.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31679/doingit.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31679","title":"Doing It","author":"by Melvin Burgess","description":"A much heralded, compelling sex story for teenage boys from this provocative writer","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31286/swimthefly.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31286","title":"Swim the Fly","author":"by Don Calame","description":"Matt, Coop and Sean have been friends forever. Each summer, they set themselves a goal, and this year tops the lot - they must see a real live naked girl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30425/losing-it.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30425","title":"Losing It","author":"by Edited by Keith Gray","description":"This is a collection of eight short stories about growing-up, virginity and sex for teenagers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32387/why-we-broke-upd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32387","title":"Why We Broke Up","author":"by Daniel Handler","description":"This beautifully presented and unusual young adult novel tells the story of Ed and Min's relationship, from their first meeting to their hearbreaking break-up.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24502/otorii.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24502","title":"Tales of the Otori: Across the Nightingale Floor","author":"by Lian Hearn","description":"A taut, compelling tale in the Samurai warrior tradition","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30066/song4summer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30066","title":"A Song for Summer","author":"by Eva Ibbotson","description":"A deliciously old-fashioned story, which encompasses love, adventure and a host of memorable characters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29741/romeo-and-juliet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29741","title":"Romeo and Juliet: Manga Shakespeare","author":"by Sonia Leong and William Shakespeare","description":"Set in modern Tokyo, with the Capulets and Montagues recast as organised-crime rivals, this racy retelling gets to the heart of the love story and the foolish rivalry that dooms it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30390/the-sky-is-everywhere.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30390","title":"The Sky is Everywhere","author":"by Jandy Nelson","description":"Grief has turned Lennie's world upside down - Bailey, her charismatic older sister, has died unexpectedly, forcing Lennie to step out from behind her shadow for the first time.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31681/9780330512855-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31681","title":"The Immortals: Evermore","author":"by Alyson Noel","description":"In the first book of The Immortals series, find out what Ever will do after discovering she can read auras and hear thoughts","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24413/rani-and-sukh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24413","title":"Rani and Sukh","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"A vivid, fast-moving take on the Romeo and Juliet story, exploring the experience of young urban British Asians as they negotiate their way through two cultures","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29396/angus-thongs-and-full-frontal-snogging.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29396","title":"Angus, Thongs and Full-Frontal Snogging","author":"by Louise Rennison","description":"Welcome to the world of Georgia Nicolson - an angst-ridden teenage girl who keeps a diary to record the rollercoaster of emotions and experiences she faces every day","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31788/there-is-no-dog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31788","title":"There Is No Dog","author":"by Meg Rosoff","description":"In the beginning there was Bob","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29550/shiver..jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29550","title":"Shiver","author":"by Maggie Stiefvater","description":"Set in small-town Minnesota, Stiefvater’s moving and poetic novel of human/wolf interaction and relationships is a werewolf story like no other.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31575/9780224090964-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31575","title":"A Taste of Chlorine","author":"by Bastien Vives","description":"This beautifully drawn book cleverly examines the intricacies and complications of friendship","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30964/angel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30964","title":"Angel","author":"by LA Weatherly","description":"A thriller with a difference, this riveting read explores the conflicting emotions felt by two young people who know that only by risking their lives can they save the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":134,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/134/","title":"Books of the year 2011","list_description":"Our books of the year 2011 reflect the wide range of literature being written today. While others might sniff and grumble about this year's Booker shortlist or the rise of the digital, we believe in celebrating good books for good books' sake. So, for what it's worth, here are the best books we've read all year.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31545/9780571279425.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31545","title":"Open City","author":"by Teju Cole","description":"Part psycho-geographic study of New York and its inhabitants, architecture and intellectual history, part study of the immigrant experience"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31080/a-visit-from-the-goon-squad.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31080","title":"A Visit from the Goon Squad","author":"by Jennifer Egan","description":"Told in an enigmatic way, flipping between narratives, characters and timeframes with ease, Egan paints portraits of some beautifully designed yet ultimately doomed to disappointment characters."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31532/9780241143117-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31532","title":"Gods Without Men","author":"by Hari Kunzru","description":"Hari Kunzru is now four books into a decade-long career and showing no signs of fatigue. Gods Without Men is as gloriously bizarre as his debut and as politically paradoxical as his last. After novels spanning India, the British Empire..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31847/9780241961506.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31847","title":"Home Boy","author":"by H M Naqvi","description":"Winner of the inaugural DSC Prize for South Asian Literature finally gets a UK release, courtesy of Penguin, and about time too."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31646/9781446485989.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31646","title":"Zone One","author":"by Colson Whitehead","description":"Always interesting, always brilliant, Colson Whitehead returns. Having done coming-of-age, surreal noir, history and corporate satire, his only option left was to write a literary zombie novel, an allegory for gentrification and the end of the world (the world here..."}]}
{"id":135,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/135/","title":"Our favourite children's book apps (2011)","list_description":"Find a poem for every occasion or learn French with the bilingual My House. Apps are a tactile and fun alternative to books - neither books nor games but in a happy space in between and perfect for entertainment for long journeys. This year we have another great crop of apps for young children to enjoy. Adaptations of popular classics and series such as Paddington Bear, Cinderella, Dear Zoo, Bizzy Bear, Elmer and Sir Charlie Stinky Socks are all brought to life on an iPad near you. See our Appy Christmas 2010 list","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31915/happybabies_1933768b-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31915","title":"Happy Babies","author":"by Fiona Land","description":"A gentle and simple way of introducing very young children to animals and their babies","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31908/sircharlie-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31908","title":"Sir Charlie Stinky Socks and the Really Big Adventure (app)","author":"by Kristina Stephenson","description":"This popular adventure has been brought to life in a simple app that uses the big, bright, lively pictures and fun, lively text to great effect","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"}]}
{"id":136,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/136/","title":"The Ant Club spring booklist","list_description":"Some of our favourite new books for sharing with your reception and Year 1 pupils this spring. There is something here for every child to enjoy.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35216/mira-forecasts-the-future.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35216","title":"Mira Forecasts the Future","author":"by Kell Andrews","description":"A deceptively simple picture book about understanding the weather that also explores ideas about success, failure and discovering individual talents.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35362/king-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35362","title":"King Baby","author":"by Kate Beaton","description":"King Baby bestows 'smiles and laughs and kisses' on everyone, for King Baby is generous. But he also has many demands: he must be fed. And changed! And burped! King Baby will have you in stitches. Buy it for every...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35246/ada-twist-scientist.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35246","title":"Ada Twist, Scientist","author":"by Andrea Beaty","description":"A brilliant and beautiful rhyming book about supporting your child's curiosity, and taking inspiration from Ada Lovelace (the pioneer mathematician and programmer), this is an inspirational and entertaining read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35227/return.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35227","title":"Return","author":"by Aaron Becker","description":"A lonely little girl can't distract her hardworking dad, so she takes her amazing red pen and draws herself into an adventure. This imaginative, fantastical escapade is wordless, but overflows with creativity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0 (as there are no words)","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35333/9780007594153.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35333","title":"Odd Dog Out","author":"by Rob Biddulph","description":"All the dogs at the beginning of this book look and act the same, but one is behaving differently. When they fly high, this dog flies low. When they say kick, this dog says throw!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35327/9781405283403.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35327","title":"Insect Emporium","author":"by Susie Brooks","description":"This stunning non-fiction picture book is a fabulous exploration of the insect world for young children. As well as looking at familiar creatures, such as bees, ladybirds and ants, it also features other more unusual specimens, including fireflies, stick insects...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35248/a-day-with-dogs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35248","title":"A Day With Dogs","author":"by Dorothee de Monfreid","description":"What do dogs do all day? A fantastically fun naming and classification-style book, A Day With Dogs will appeal to little ones that like to list and name different types of things - be it dogs, trains or elements of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35379/spinderella.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35379","title":"Spinderella","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Spinderella is a spider who lives with her spider mum and brothers and sisters on top of a ceiling light at a school. A story about numbers, football and family, Spinderella is an enjoyable read for young children just starting...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35359/hello-mr-dodo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35359","title":"Hello, Mr Dodo!","author":"by Nicholas John Frith","description":"Martha loves birds, but she can't believe her eyes when she discovers the rarest bird of them all in the woods behind her house. It's a real life Dodo! Retro illustration and technicolour splashes make this picture book a beautiful...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35290/the-star-tree.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35290","title":"The Star Tree","author":"by Catherine Hyde","description":"It is midnight at midsummer, and little Mia is awake. When the Great White Owl comes to the window and sings to her, it is the start of many magical journeys. A beautifully atmospheric book and a perfect bedtime read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35325/9781927271872.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35325","title":"Yours Sincerely, Giraffe","author":"by Megumi Iwasa","description":"Giraffe, who lives on the African savanna, is bored and lonely so decides to send a letter to an unknown animal on the other side of the horizon. The letter ends up with an inquisitive penguin who is studying at...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35328/9781847808905.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35328","title":"Little People, Big Dreams: Maya Angelou","author":"by Lisbeth Kaiser","description":"This inspiring biography for young readers focusses on writer, speaker and civil rights activist Maya Angelou.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35209/the-invincible-tony-spears.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35209","title":"The Invincible Tony Spears","author":"by Neal Layton","description":"After Tony moves house, the kitchen in his new place turns into a spaceship called The Invincible. Amid all the zaniness, there's an important message tucked in here about just trying your best.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35263/ludwig-the-space-dog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35263","title":"Ludwig the Space Dog","author":"by Henning Löhlein","description":"Perfect for young explorers, this endearing story features an adventurous dog who decides to visit the universe beyond the flat pages of his home - and 3D goggles will give the reader an even sharper focus on Ludwig's wonderful world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35206/don-t-cross-the-line2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35206","title":"Don’t Cross the Line","author":"by Isabel Minhos Martins and Bernardo P. Carvalho","description":"Little anarchists will love Don't Cross the Line, with its message that authority figures aren't always right. This colourful book is likely to make the whole family chortle.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3-6","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35383/by-the-light-of-the-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35383","title":"By the Light of the Moon","author":"by Tom Percival","description":"A reassuringly simple yet enchanting story, brought to life with appealing illustrations, to allay children's worries about moving house and creating a home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35380/there-s-a-snake-in-my-school-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35380","title":"There’s a Snake in my School!","author":"by David Walliams","description":"It's bring-your-pet-to-school-day and Miranda has brought her pet python, who is brilliant fun and entertains the children by turning herself into a climbing frame, a fireman's pole and the numbers one to nine. Riotous and with just enough yuckiness.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"}]}
{"id":137,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/137/","title":"Books inspired by the Holocaust","list_description":"We look at some of the best children's books inspired by the events of the Holocaust. Read an article from the archive.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25439/strippedpjs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25439","title":"The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas","author":"by John Boyne","description":"Bruno is exploring his new home at 'Out-With' when he meets Shmuel, who lives on the other side of a fence which surrounds a large camp in the grounds.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31944/deathmatchh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31944","title":"Death Match","author":"by Andy Croft","description":"During the occupation of Ukraine in World War II, players from what had been the Dynamo Kiev football team set themselves up as Start FC and competed in a Nazi-organised league","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30826/annexed..jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30826","title":"Annexed","author":"by Sharon Dogar","description":"This fictionalised account of Peter (a teenage Dutch Jew, hiding from the Nazis with his family and their friends, the Franks) is a meditation on the power of written testimony and the nature of evil.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25454/once.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25454","title":"Once","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"Morris Gleitzman brings heart and humour to the difficult subject of the Holocaust in this ground-breaking children's book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30066/song4summer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30066","title":"A Song for Summer","author":"by Eva Ibbotson","description":"A deliciously old-fashioned story, which encompasses love, adventure and a host of memorable characters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31956/9780007274772-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31956","title":"When Hitler Stole Pink Rabbit","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Partly autobiographical, this is first of the internationally acclaimed trilogy by Judith Kerr telling the unforgettable story of a Jewish family fleeing from Germany at the start of the World War II."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26527/anne-frank.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26527","title":"Anne Frank","author":"by Josephine Poole","description":"This account of the Nazi persecution of the Jews and Anne Frank's family's hiding in a secret annexe to escape them, is sensitively told.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25800/9780099572855-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25800","title":"The Silver Sword","author":"by Ian Serrailier","description":"In the chaos of World War II, Ruth, Edek and Bronia are separated from their parents, and left alone to fend for themselves, hiding from the Nazis in the ruins of their city.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29463/maus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29463","title":"Maus","author":"by Art Spiegelman","description":"This is the complete story of Vladek Spiegelman and his wife, living and surviving in Hitler's Europe.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24947/milkweed-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24947","title":"Milkweed","author":"by Jerry Spinelli","description":"This incredible book explores a horrific area of recent history in a totally unsentimental way. A masterpiece!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25136/hitler-s-canary.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25136","title":"Hitler's Canary","author":"by Sandi Toksvig","description":"Hitler's Canary, ultimately, is about the courage and heroism of ordinary citizens in a time of danger and strife.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31955/9780552773898-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31955","title":"The Book Thief","author":"by Markus Zusak","description":"A powerful story narrated by Death, about: a girl, an accordionist, some fanatical Germans, a Jewish fist fighter, and quite a lot of thievery","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":138,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/138/","title":"Dickens adaptations","list_description":"Charles Dickens is one of the most famous authors of all time. Here are some fun and accessible adaptations to introduce children and young people to the great writer.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27160/9780746077078-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27160","title":"Oliver Twist","author":"by Charles Dickens","description":"This classic is retold with simple text to delight and inspire any child who is just beginning to read","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31924/9781847801876-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31924","title":"Charles Dickens: Scenes from an Extraordinary Life","author":"by Mick Manning","description":"Celebrate the 2012 bi-centenary of Charles Dickens' life with this new, illustrated biography. Beginning with his birth it follows Dickens through his early years of hardship, career as a reporter and his family life, and then moves on to his...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32470/terry_pratchett_dodger_cover-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32470","title":"Dodger","author":"by Terry Pratchett","description":"Terry Pratchett once again proves himself a master storyteller in this tribute to one of Charles Dickens' best-known characters, the Artful Doger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31775/mister-creecher.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31775","title":"Mister Creecher","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"Friendship, trust and betrayal combine to form a dangerous liaison in this moving and frightening new book from Chris Priestley","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31988/oliver-twisted.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31988","title":"Oliver Twisted","author":"by J D Sharpe","description":"'Can I have some gore?' Oliver Twist is given a supernatural spin in this vivid reimagining of Dickens’ novel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31993/515997-l-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31993","title":"Charles Dickens and Friends","author":"by Marcia Williams","description":"A selection of the works of one of the world's greatest writers, retold in accessible comic-strip style.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":139,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/139/","title":"Beyond Booked Up spring term booklist","list_description":"These are some of our favourite new books from the last few months. We hope there's something here for everyone to enjoy in the spring term.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35381/nightlights.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35381","title":"Nightlights","author":"by Lorena Alvarez","description":"A remarkable, haunting and beautiful graphic novel for younger readers, Nightlights is a magical fable about creativity and believing in yourself. With a 'Studio Ghibli' feel and some sumptuous artwork, this is a wonderful read and a visual treat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35413/cogheart.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35413","title":"Cogheart","author":"by Peter Bunzl","description":"This ambitious debut is set in 1896, but in an alternative history - almost steampunk - with clockwork servants, silver airships and mechanical animals. Expect thrills and mystery, but also some deep messages about what it is to live and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35357/girl-with-no-nose.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35357","title":"The Girl with No Nose","author":"by Georgia Byng","description":"Life is tough in Victorian times, the world into which Alice Peasbody is born - and Alice is a girl with no nose. A wonderful, thoughtful book that teaches compassion, celebrates difference and tackles some weighty issues with a gentle...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35269/cats-and-curses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35269","title":"Cats and Curses","author":"by Elen Caldecott","description":"This is the fourth book in the Marsh Road Mysteries series, although there is no need to read them in order. Andrew, Piotr, Minnie, Flora and Sylvie are great characters and this is an exciting adventure that will be devoured...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35228/mind-writer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35228","title":"Mind Writer","author":"by Steve Cole","description":"Luke has a secret, a hidden skill: he can read minds. But when Luke meets Samira, he can't read her mind at all. A gripping thriller where fantasy meets horror - perfect for fearless older children or reluctant and dyslexic...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35208/the-new-teacher2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35208","title":"The New Teacher","author":"by Dominique Demers","description":"A delightful little story that welcomes a fabulously eccentric character in the form of Miss Charlotte. She's a bit Mary Poppins, a bit Nurse Matilda, and a whole lot of fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35278/spellchasers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35278","title":"Spellchasers: the beginner’s guide to curses","author":"by Lari Don","description":"Since coming to stay with Aunt Doreen in Speyside, something odd has happened to 11-year-old Molly: whenever she hears a dog bark, she transforms into a hare. This exciting page-turner will have readers gripped from the start.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35422/the-war-next-door.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35422","title":"The War Next Door","author":"by Phil Earle","description":"The War Next Door turns its focus to Masher, the bully of Storey Street. Part of the Storey Street series, Phil Earle's book has all the usual wit, pace, fun and silliness - but also gives a nicely rounded perspective...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35239/odd-and-the-frost-giants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35239","title":"Odd and the Frost Giants","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"Odd, a crippled orphan in a Viking village, isn't of much interest to his clan. When he leaves for adventure, he finds three talking animals that are actually gods - and they need his help. This is a wonderfully wintry,...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35331/9781408853368.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35331","title":"The Song from Somewhere Else","author":"by AF Harrold","description":"Frank is being bullied - for what, she's not sure. Being smart? Being different, perhaps. One day, after her bike is thrown in the middle of a huge patch of stinging nettles, Nick comes to her aid. A magical and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35370/repro_murderinmidwinter_cvr-300dpi-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35370","title":"Murder in Midwinter","author":"by Fleur Hitchcock","description":"On a cold, midwinter day, 13-year-old Maya spots a man holding a gun. She doesn't know exactly what's going on - but the man looked right at her, and she's been in danger ever since. A fast-paced story with nail-biting...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35382/the-liszts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35382","title":"The Liszts","author":"by Kyo Maclear","description":"Every member of the Liszt family makes lists - lists about ghastly illnesses, dreaded chores, cheeses, Bowie songs. But with all of their time spent categorising the world, what will they do when an unexpected visitor arrives?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35358/brian-moses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35358","title":"Lost Magic: The Very Best of Brian Moses","author":"by Brian Moses","description":"Brian Moses gathers 100 of his own favourite - and brilliant - poems from his prolific career, which spans nearly 30 years, into a beautiful hardback book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35360/black-light-express.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35360","title":"Black Light Express","author":"by Philip Reeve","description":"Philip Reeve is a master world-builder and the nuances of the Network Empire world are executed beautifully in this sequel to the stunning RailHead.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35218/the-secret-cooking-club.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35218","title":"The Secret Cooking Club","author":"by Laurel Remington","description":"Since Scarlett became the main subject of her mum's popular lifestyle blog, her confidence has plummeted - but a happy accident and an old recipe book open the door to new interests, friends and opportunities.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35214/missing-arabella.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35214","title":"Missing Arabella","author":"by Kathryn Siebel","description":"A warm and witty take on a traditional set-up of two sisters and some rather unpleasant parents. The style is fresh, fun and contemporary - less Grimm and more Disney.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35371/winter-magic.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35371","title":"Winter Magic","author":"by Various","description":"Winter Magic is a fabulous collection of atmospheric, sometimes sad, sometimes unnerving but mostly warming stories for cosy bedtimes or cold winter afternoons under a blanket - with a mug of hot chocolate handy, of course.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35264/clover-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35264","title":"Clover Moon","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Jacqueline Wilson has set her latest story in Victorian London. When Clover Moon receives one beating too many from her evil stepmother, she decides to set off on an adventure, which proves both funny and sad - hooking readers right...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35247/the-curiositree.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35247","title":"The Curiositree","author":"by Amanda Wood and Mike Jolley","description":"Natural World is an extremely beautiful reference book that explores the way that habitats, plants and animals are connected, and the way that all elements of nature work in harmony.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10-16"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35284/it-s-not-fine-to-sit-on-a-porcupine.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35284","title":"It’s Not Fine to Sit on a Porcupine","author":"by Neal Zetter","description":"An amusingly illustrated collection of humorous poems from an award-winning performance poet, which covers a wide range of funny and interesting subjects.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-11"}]}
{"id":140,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/140/","title":"Asperger’s Syndrome and autism","list_description":"This year, World Autism Awareness Week raises awareness for autism between 27 March to 2 April.  BookTrust believes that books are a great way to raise awareness and improve understanding of different experiences. This booklist aims to provide a range of children's and teens' books featuring characters who are on the autistic spectrum or have Asperger’s Syndrome.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34886/car-wash-wish.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34886","title":"Car Wash Wish","author":"by Sita Brahmachari","description":"Fourteen-year-old Hudson has Asperger's Syndrome, and knows his brain works differently. This entertaining and thought-provoking story reveals that there is more than one way of looking at life and its problems.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25929/the-london-eye-mystery.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25929","title":"The London Eye Mystery","author":"by Siobhan Dowd","description":"Ted likes the weather, he also likes statistics and routine but his life is thrown into disarray when his Aunt Gloria and cousin Salim arrive, like a hurricane, to stay in London en-route to a new life in New York.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31960/9781409538585-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31960","title":"Mockingbird","author":"by Kathryn Erskine","description":"A high school shooting has left a small American town devastated.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32016/somethingdifferentaboutdad.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32016","title":"Something Different About Dad","author":"by Kirstie Evans","description":"Sophie’s father Mark has Asperger’s Syndrome.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24568/curiousincident.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24568","title":"The Curious Incident of the Dog in the Night-time","author":"by Mark Haddon","description":"This funny, touching and compelling novel was the winner of the inaugural Booktrust Teenage Prize","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33791/reason-i-jump.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33791","title":"The Reason I Jump","author":"by Naoki Higashida","description":"An invaluable tool for family members trying to understand autistic behaviour but also a fascinating and powerful read in its own right.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32018/9781843100980-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32018","title":"Freaks, Geeks and Asperger Syndrome","author":"by Luke Jackson","description":"This is a guide to Asperger’s Syndrome by a young man who was just 13-years-old at the time of writing...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32015/51un3qri9gl._sl500_aa300_-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32015","title":"Ian's Walk: A Story about Autism","author":"by Laurie Lears","description":"This is a useful book for discussing autism, sibling relationships and responsibility.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31878/trueman-bradley.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31878","title":"Trueman Bradley - Aspie Detective","author":"by Alexei Maxim Russell","description":"It is the Aspergers mind which is Trueman’s most powerful asset as a detective and which enables him to develop ingenious crime-solving equation","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32017/d1cdb8b0-267c-45f6-b850-24a176c015ea-img100-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32017","title":"Anything But Typical","author":"by Nora Raleigh Baskin","description":"Jason is 12 and on the autistic spectrum...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31682/9781906427276-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31682","title":"The Pasta Detectives","author":"by Andreas Steinhafel","description":"The story of two misfit boys who find friendship as they set out to solve a very unusual mystery.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34008/9781908998460.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34008","title":"The Boy from Aleppo Who Painted the War","author":"by Sumia Sukkar","description":"This intensely moving story takes the reader to the heart of the war in Syria from the point of view of an extraordinary boy who lives through it."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33710/dandelion-clocks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33710","title":"Dandelion Clocks","author":"by Rebecca Westcott","description":"Powerful, memorable and accessible, the book also boasts a very positive depiction of a character with Asperger's Syndrome.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":141,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/141/","title":"Reading difficulties and dyslexia","list_description":"This list aims to provide a range of books that may appeal to young people of seven years plus with reading difficulties. The list includes books that:  Check out these other organisations for further resources: British Dyslexia Association; Dyslexia Action; Badger reading boxes for schools; Being Dyslexic website.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31613/9781848771260-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31613","title":"FArTHER","author":"by Grahame Baker-Smith","description":"Words and pictures combine beautifully to tell a moving story about fathers and sons","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33140/9781781120729.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33140","title":"Young Merlin","author":"by Tony Bradman","description":"Merlin has always felt different from the other boys, because of his dreadful nightmares full of fighting and death.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32023/9781408152690-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32023","title":"Petrify","author":"by Beth Chambers","description":"Ella’s new next-door neighbour is confident, verging on cocky. He’s keen to prove to Ella and her friends that he knows no fear, and when he learns that the local woods are supposed to be haunted, he persuades them to...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29942/9781408122341-1-.jpg","u