es.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31337/edo_cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31337","title":"Boffin Boy and the Wizard of Edo","author":"by David Orme","description":"This graphic novel style book is a quick read and perfect for those who don’t like too much text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33962/over-the-line2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33962","title":"Over the Line","author":"by Tom Palmer","description":"Set during World War I, this book tells the compelling true story of the professional footballers who signed up to fight. It's sure to enthral readers and pique their interest in the period.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34666/horace-burp.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34666","title":"Horace Burp, Lizard Boy","author":"by Christine Tennent","description":"Horace Burp is an eight year old boy with an unusual name and an even more unusual condition. His skin changes colour like a chameleon along with changes in mood. We join him on the day he first discovers his...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-9"}]}
{"id":142,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/142/","title":"Books to read out loud","list_description":"To celebrate World Book Day 2012, and the Storytelling Superstar competition, why not enjoy sharing some of our favourite books to read aloud?","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29645/a-necklace-of-raindrops.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29645","title":"A Necklace of Raindrops","author":"by Joan Aiken","description":"Filled with poetic repetitions, each story beautifully balances the prosaic with the wondrous.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29899/the-boy-who-climbed-into-the-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29899","title":"The Boy Who Climbed into the Moon","author":"by David Almond","description":"A child's imagination is a wonderful thing and Paul's is more wonderful and vivid than many. He has a theory - that the moon is not really the moon but a great big hole in the sky.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28935/fruits.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28935","title":"Fruits: a Caribbean counting poem","author":"by Valerie Bloom","description":"From half a pawpaw to five jew-plums through to ten bananas, this girl’s love of Caribbean fruits is so infectious you can almost taste the juice dribbling down your chin.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25192/framed-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25192","title":"Framed","author":"by Frank Cottrell Boyce","description":"The story centres on Dylan Hughes, the only boy left in a small Welsh mountain town called Manod. This is an immensely entertaining book, about the power of art to bring about change and to redeem.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27003/tiddler-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27003","title":"Tiddler","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Although he looks small and ordinary, Tiddler is a fish who loves to tell tall tales. But one day he is swept up in a fisherman's net and then thrown back in to an unfamiliar part of the sea.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34492/dinosaur-police.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34492","title":"Dinosaur Police","author":"by Sarah McIntyre","description":"Unashamedly silly and wonderfully mad, this will delight little dinosaur fans.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33276/the-cat-in-the-hat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33276","title":"The Cat in the Hat","author":"by Dr Seuss","description":"When Sally and her brother are left alone on a rainy day, they think they are in for a dull time - but then the Cat in the Hat appears.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31523/9781849392501-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31523","title":"Sticky Ends","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Jeanne Willis brings you 19 delightfully disgusting cautionary tales, from mishaps on the toilet to adventures with bubble gum in this collection. Hear the fate of a variety of feckless children, from The Tale of Icy Clare who ran off..."}]}
{"id":143,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/143/","title":"Books to get you talking","list_description":"For World Book Day 2012, we're recommending some books that are guaranteed to get you talking. Raising controversial issues and asking challenging questions, these books demand to be debated.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25439/strippedpjs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25439","title":"The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas","author":"by John Boyne","description":"Bruno is exploring his new home at 'Out-With' when he meets Shmuel, who lives on the other side of a fence which surrounds a large camp in the grounds.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30287/junk.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30287","title":"Junk","author":"by Melvin Burgess","description":"Tar loves Gemma, but Gemma doesn't want to be tied down to anyone or anything. Gemma wants to fly - but she can't fly forever...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24551/9781407138091-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24551","title":"Looking for JJ","author":"by Anne Cassidy","description":"When a 10-year-old girl kills her best friend, she is convicted of manslaughter and locked away. Seven years later she is released on licence with a new identity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31485/9780857560087-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31485","title":"In The Sea There Are Crocodiles","author":"by Fabio Geda","description":"First published in Italian last year, the story of Enaiatollah Akbari's journey from Afghanistan to Italy has now been translated into English","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24413/rani-and-sukh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24413","title":"Rani and Sukh","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"A vivid, fast-moving take on the Romeo and Juliet story, exploring the experience of young urban British Asians as they negotiate their way through two cultures","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29795/out-of-shadows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29795","title":"Out of Shadows","author":"by Jason Wallace","description":"Back in the early 1980s, Robert Jacklin doesn't want to move to the newly independent Zimbabwe with his parents, nor does he want to be shipped off to boarding school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":144,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/144/","title":"Books to cuddle up and share","list_description":"Cuddle up together to enjoy some of our favourite stories to share","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25027/there-s-a-house-inside-my-mummy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25027","title":"There's A House Inside My Mummy","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"This is just the book to explain to inquisitive children what going on inside mum during pregnancy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33786/dawn-chorus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33786","title":"The Dawn Chorus","author":"by Suzanne Barton","description":"A warm, reassuring tale about individual talents and about belonging, which will appeal to small children everywhere. Glorious illustrations swirl through the pages in a crescendo of appealing, harmonious images.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33978/blown-away.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33978","title":"Blown Away","author":"by Rob Biddulph","description":"Penguin Blue has got a new toy, and it's the right kind of day to try it out. But the wind is a little stronger than expected and along with the new kite, Penguin Blue is blown away.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34224/noodle-loves-to-cuddle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34224","title":"Noodle Loves to Cuddle","author":"by Marion Billet","description":"A touch-and-feel 