 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24997/monkey-me_300dpi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24997","title":"Monkey and Me","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"A small girl takes her toy monkey everywhere with her. Together they imitate and then imagine visiting a string of real animals, from penguins to kangaroos, whose glorious images fill the pages.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34044/spots-baby-sister.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34044","title":"Spot's Baby Sister","author":"by Eric Hill","description":"Spot and his friends play with his new sister, Susie.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30001/elmerand-the-lostteddy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30001","title":"Elmer and the Lost Teddy","author":"by David McKee","description":"In this republication of a 1999 title, McKee shows young readers that we each have special things which nobody else loves quite as we do.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34629/what-a-busy-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34629","title":"What a... Busy Baby!","author":"by Rebecca Patterson","description":"Great just before naptime!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33992/pip-posy-little-puddle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33992","title":"Pip and Posy: The Little Puddle","author":"by Axel Scheffler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31393/9781846433733-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31393","title":"Snug","author":"by Carol Thompson","description":"Delightful book celebrating the different ways to feel snug by comparing how animals and children stay cosy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34368/mockingbird-song.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34368","title":"Mockingbird Song","author":"by Carol Thompson","description":"A beautiful retelling of the classic lullaby.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34176/baby-touch-flip-flap.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34176","title":"Baby Touch Flip-Flap book","author":"by Ladybird","description":"Touch-and-feel book with colourful pictures to explore with your baby","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24828/twinkly-night.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24828","title":"Twinkly Night","author":"by Helen Stephens","description":"'Night has fallen all around. Lights are shining in the sleepy town'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24596/that-s-not-my-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24596","title":"That's Not My Bear...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"A different bear is introduced on each page of this colourful board book, but there is something not quite right about most of them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-4"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34180/thats-not-my-teddy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34180","title":"That's not my teddy...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"Touch-feely book with colourful illustrations and simply text","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":147,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/147/","title":"Princes and Princesses","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31147/prince-cinders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31147","title":"Prince Cinders","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"Prince Cinders leads a hard life, bullied by his three big hairy brothers - that is, until one Saturday night when Cinders' luck changes","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31296/the-princess-and-the-wizard.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31296","title":"The Princess and the Wizard","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Lydia Monks","description":"Princess Eliza is having a birthday party. But just as she blows out the seven candles on her cake, the wicked wizard arrives… uninvited.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30582/i-want-a-friend.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30582","title":"I Want a Friend!","author":"by Tony Ross","description":"Meet one of the great characters of children's books as Little Princess starts school."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32168/thats-not-my-princess-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32168","title":"That's Not My Princess...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"This sturdy and durable board book is perfect for the very youngest children, with touch and feel images full of interesting textures and shapes that are ideal for small fingers to explore.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":148,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/148/","title":"Shakespeare retold","list_description":"Take a look at some of our favourite re-tellings (or reimaginings) of Shakespeare's plays. They all bring these incredible stories to life for younger readers.  From picture book versions to teenage novels, the books provide the perfect introduction to Shakespeare.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32521/a-midsummer-night-s-dream.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32521","title":"A Midsummer Night's Dream - Manga Shakespeare","author":"by Kate Brown","description":"Shakespeare's enduring story set in present-day Athens, but a present with a massive difference.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30113/king-of-shadows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30113","title":"King of Shadows","author":"by Susan Cooper","description":"Nat Field, an orphaned American actor, is taken ill during a performance and slips back in time to the Tudor era.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29741/romeo-and-juliet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29741","title":"Romeo and Juliet: Manga Shakespeare","author":"by Sonia Leong and William Shakespeare","description":"Set in modern Tokyo, with the Capulets and Montagues recast as organised-crime rivals, this racy retelling gets to the heart of the love story and the foolish rivalry that dooms it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30703/the-merchant-of-venice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30703","title":"The Merchant of Venice: A Shakespeare Story","author":"by Andrew Matthews","description":"Shakespeare's dialogue is greatly abridged, but key passages are kept, and the well-known sayings remain.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29486/xposure.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29486","title":"Exposure","author":"by Mal Peet","description":"The third of Peet’s thrillers involving South American football journalist Paul Faustino.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24413/rani-and-sukh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24413","title":"Rani and Sukh","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"A vivid, fast-moving take on the Romeo and Juliet story, exploring the experience of young urban British Asians as they negotiate their way through two cultures","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29888/the-fool-s-girl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29888","title":"The Fool's Girl","author":"by Celia Rees","description":"After her father has been murdered and her lands and treasures taken, young Duchess Violetta seeks the help of Will Shakespeare to regain a treasure vital to her homeland.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25000/shakespeare-s-romeo-and-juliet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25000","title":"Shakespeare's Romeo and Juliet","author":"by retold by Michael Rosen and Jane Ray","description":"This beautifully designed book will really bring Shakespeare alive for a new generation of readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31446/shakespearesstorybook_pb_temp_w_1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31446","title":"Shakespeare's Storybook","author":"by Patrick Ryan","description":"These enjoyable traditional tales are an enticing introduction to Shakespeare for young readers","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31583/9780955816970-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31583","title":"Manga Shakespeare: King Lear","author":"by William Shakespeare","description":"Ilya's illustrations match the intensity of the play to bring this tragic classic vividly to life","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32180/9781406323351-2-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32180","title":"Bravo, Mr William Shakespeare!","author":"by Marcia Williams","description":"Illustrator Marcia Williams offers up lively illustrated retellings of some of Shakespeare's most famous plays in this entertaining picture book perfect for use in the classroom.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":149,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/149/","title":"Booktime Books 2012","list_description":"The Booktime books 2012","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32227/tims-din-medium.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32227","title":"Tim's Din","author":"by Monica Hughes","description":"Tim’s Din is a lively and entertaining story about the mischief that little monkeys can get up to when they’re bored."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32226/naughty-little-rabbit-mediu.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32226","title":"The Tale of a Naughty Little Rabbit","author":"by Frederick Warne","description":"The Tale of a Naughty Little Rabbit is a playful and funny retelling of Beatrix Potter’s original story The Tale of Peter Rabbit."}]}
{"id":151,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/151/","title":"The Ant Club summer booklist","list_description":"Take a look at our suggested summer term booklist for your Reception and Year 1 children. You can view it online or print out for your class. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35489/love-is.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35489","title":"Love is","author":"by Diane Adams","description":"A little girl cares for a duckling just as a parent would care for a baby. But also, as the duckling grows, the little girl comes to understand that part of love is letting things go. A gentle and inspiring...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35517/quiet2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35517","title":"Quiet!","author":"by Kate Alizadeh","description":"A small child takes us on an auditory tour of her home in this delightful picture of family life, ingeniously interpreted through its sounds. It's a book that radiates comfort, security, warmth and love.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35645/william-bee-s-wonderful-world-of-trucks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35645","title":"William Bee’s Wonderful World of Trucks","author":"by William Bee","description":"William Bee loves trucks. A lot. In fact, he loves them so much, he has written and illustrated this amazing guide to giant vehicles of all kinds. Children will return to this book again and again.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35586/the-night-gardener.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35586","title":"The Night Gardener","author":"by The Fan Brothers","description":"A sumptuously illustrated, heart-warming tale of a sad town and lonely orphan, given new life by the kindness of The Night Gardener. There is little text, leaving the emotional impact to the gorgeous pictures. This has the feel of an...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35537/if-i-had-a-dinosaur.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35537","title":"If I Had a Dinosaur","author":"by Gabby Dawnay","description":"A little girl wishes ever so desperately that she could have a pet, but she's unsure about what kind of pet she would like.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35584/last-stop-on-market-street.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35584","title":"Last Stop on Market Street","author":"by Matt de la Pena","description":"A New York Times Bestseller, this wonderful picture book about the riches that money can’t buy is a timely and timeless reminder for all of us, not just children, that caring, thoughtfulness and community are more important than material wealth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35497/horrible-bear-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35497","title":"Horrible Bear!","author":"by Ame Dyckman","description":"This sweet and simple story about friendship and saying sorry perfectly captures the frustration that children can feel when something doesn’t go right, and the relief we all feel at saying sorry and making things better again.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35638/grandad-s-secret-giant.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35638","title":"Grandad’s Secret Giant","author":"by David Litchfield","description":"Although the Secret Giant is rarely seen, grandad is convinced he exists. Maybe he's lonely, and just needs a friend? There's a mysterious luminosity to the illustrations of this magical story about accepting people who are different.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35496/i-can-only-draw-worms.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35496","title":"I Can Only Draw Worms","author":"by Will Mabbitt","description":"This genuinely hilarious book is brilliantly simple, based on the idea that the author-illustrator can only draw very childlike worms. Highly recommended.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35661/pigeon-pi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35661","title":"Pigeon P.I.","author":"by Meg McLaren","description":"Murray MacMurray, the Pigeon P.I., is enjoying some quiet time until a persistent yellow canary named Vee asks him to help find her missing friends. This story of mystery and friendship will delight both children and adults.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35512/piglet-called-truffle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35512","title":"A Piglet Called Truffle","author":"by Helen Peters","description":"When Jasmine discovers a helpless piglet, she takes it upon herself to make sure it has a chance. But will Truffle be allowed to stay with Jasmine for good? This short, sweet story of a little girl looking after the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35502/i-don-t-know-what-to-call-my-cat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35502","title":"I Don't Know What to Call My Cat","author":"by Simon Philip","description":"The girl in this book has got a new pet cat, but has absolutely no idea what to call it. This picture book provides some hearty chuckles and the illustrations have a lovely, big-eyed 'cartoony' feel to them, choc-a-bloc with...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35599/barefoot-book-of-children.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35599","title":"The Barefoot Book of Children","author":"by Tessa Strickland, Kate DePalma and David Dean","description":"This is a beautifully comprehensive and thought-provoking picture of the many different ways in which people live around the world. A book to dip into time and time again; a treasure trove of discussion topics, but also an aesthetic delight.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35650/how-to-be-a-tiger.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35650","title":"How To Be a Tiger","author":"by George Szirtes","description":"How To Be a Tiger is the first collection for younger children by multi-award-winning poet George Szirtes - and it's a treat that will make little ones laugh, think and wince.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35663/nanette-s-baguette.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35663","title":"Nanette’s Baguette","author":"by Mo Willems","description":"Nanette is excited to go to the bakery on her own to get the baguettes. Unfortunately, she cannot resist taking a bite - and then another... A story - told in giggle-inducing rhyme and quirky illustrations - all about responsibility...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"}]}
{"id":152,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/152/","title":"Animal stories for older readers","list_description":"Enjoy some of our favourite books about animals for older children, from Michael Morpurgo's War Horse to Eva Ibbotson's One Dog and His Boy.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32375/tiger-wars-new-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32375","title":"Tiger Wars","author":"by Steve Backshall","description":"Saker and Sinter live utterly different lives - until they find themselves unlikely companions on the run. A breathlessly exciting adventure set in India.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29761/the-great-hamster-massacre.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29761","title":"The Great Hamster Massacre","author":"by Katie Davies","description":"According to Anna's mum, hamsters are BAD NEWS. But that doesn't stop Anna and her friends from hatching a plan to persuade Mum to let them get a hamster.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28154/the-snow-goose.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28154","title":"The Snow Goose","author":"by Paul Gallico","description":"A lonely artist sets up home in an isolated lighthouse with only seabirds, boating and painting for distraction. Gradually he builds up a sanctuary where wild birds are safe from storms and hunters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32283/9780192757913-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32283","title":"Tilly's Moonlight Fox","author":"by Julia Green","description":"This sensitively-written story with a touch of time-travel magic has a flavour of classic children's books such as The Secret Garden and Tom's Midnight Garden.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31305/one-dog-and-his-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31305","title":"One Dog and His Boy","author":"by Eva Ibbotson","description":"All Hal wants for his birthday is a dog and when he is given one he is overjoyed. But when Hal realises Fleck was only his for the weekend, he sets off on an adventure with the dog...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26112/the-white-giraffe.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26112","title":"The White Giraffe","author":"by Lauren St John","description":"Devastated by her parents' death, Maxine is sent to South Africa and a grandmother she didn't know existed. When she glimpses the legendary white giraffe one night, the connection between them is instantaneous.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25341/the-sheeppig.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25341","title":"The Sheep-Pig","author":"by Dick King-Smith","description":"When Farmer Hogget wins a piglet at the fair, he is amazed that Fly, his sheep-dog, welcomes him as one of her own pups.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32217/white-dolphins.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32217","title":"White Dolphin","author":"by Gill Lewis","description":"A young dolphin, washed up on the beach, unexpectedly brings Kara and Felix together. But the new friends must take on new challenges - finding out the truth about Kara's missing mother, and protecting the bay when it falls under...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24556/war-horse.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24556","title":"War Horse","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Steven Spielberg enjoyed this story so much he has turned it into his latest film. Joey is a young farm horse, sold to the army at the beginning of the First World War. Through his eyes the reader experiences the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25091/the-last-wolf.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25091","title":"The Last Wolf","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Powerful illustrations underline this captivating tale of loyalty and bravery.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30091/the-cat-with-two-names.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30091","title":"Cat Tales: The Cat with Two Names","author":"by Linda Newbery","description":"Confusion arises when a homeless cat is simultaneously adopted by Rose and Wilfred, two neighbours living in separate flats.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32190/manual_9781444002690-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32190","title":"The One Dollar Horse","author":"by Lauren St John","description":"Casey Blue lives with her father in a tower block in Hackney, London , but despite her urban existence, she dreams of one day becoming an equestrian champion.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35317/9781782690993.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35317","title":"An Elephantasy","author":"by Maria Elena Walsh","description":"The fact that a girl is taking her geranium for a walk (the way she does every Thursday) is not the most unusual thing that happens on the first page of this book; there's an elephant on the doorstep. So...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"}]}
{"id":153,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/153/","title":"Beyond Booked Up summer term booklist","list_description":"Some of our favourite recommended reads for the summer term.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35655/see-you-in-the-cosmos.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35655","title":"See You in the Cosmos","author":"by Jack Cheng","description":"Alex has built his own rocket and he's going to launch it into space with a golden iPod full of Earth sounds. With themes of friendship and family, this is a highly engaging and heartwarming story - a true journey...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 10-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35589/fish-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35589","title":"Fish Boy","author":"by Chloe Daykin","description":"Billy is an odd boy: he's quiet, different from other children, and his skin's always wrinkled from swimming in the sea. At heart, this is a story about friendship in the face of adversity, and Chloe Daykin's writing is clear,...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35622/blue-john.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35622","title":"Blue John","author":"by Berlie Doherty","description":"Author Berlie Doherty has twice won the prestigious Carnegie medal. Beautiful illustrations and a fable-like story will appeal to children who enjoy myths and legends.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35582/the-jamie-drake-equation.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35582","title":"The Jamie Drake Equation","author":"by Christopher Edge","description":"Jamie’s dad is an astronaut on the International Space Station. One day, Jamie's phone picks up a up a weird signal. Could it be a message from his father? Filled with Christopher Edge's trademark combination of wit, pathos and hilarity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35626/the-night-spinner.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35626","title":"The Night Spinner","author":"by Abi Elphinstone","description":"The Dreamsnatcher Trilogy concludes with another epic journey for Moll Pecksniff and her band of loyal friends. Dangerous landscapes and dark magic threaten at every turn. Bravery triumphs, but fans will need tissues handy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35503/pharaoh-s-fate.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35503","title":"Pharaoh's Fate: Solve the Ancient Egyptian Mystery","author":"by Camille Gautier & Stéphanie Vernet","description":"You're in Ancient Egypt. Someone is plotting to murder the pharaoh - and it's up to you to stop them. This glorious whodunnit feeds you heaps of facts in a fun, interactive way - your child will barely notice they're...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35659/women-in-science.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35659","title":"Women in Science: 50 Fearless Pioneers Who Changed the World","author":"by Rachel Ignotofsky","description":"The 50 women profiled in this book are leaders in their fields of science, technology, engineering and mathematics. Thoroughly inspiring and informative, in a fun and stylish illustrated format: a must for every child.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35531/welcome-to-nowhere.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35531","title":"Welcome to Nowhere","author":"by Elizabeth Laird","description":"Omar doesn't know much about politics, nor does he care, however, when his older brother, Musa, throws his lot in with the student opposition to the government, everything changes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35621/beetle-queen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35621","title":"Beetle Queen","author":"by M G Leonard","description":"M G Leonard manages to subtly pack a swarm of scientific information into the adventure story. Fans of Beetle Boy will be thrilled at these further antics, and those who secretly loved the dastardly Lucretia will enjoy seeing her steal...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35672/the-young-magicians-and-the-thieves-almanac.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35672","title":"The Young Magicians and the Thieves’ Almanac","author":"by Nick Mohammed","description":"Comedian and real-life magician Nick Mohammed weaves together an action-packed and laugh-filled adventure, while at the same writing a heart-felt love letter to a childhood obsession with magic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35540/radio-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35540","title":"Radio Boy","author":"by Christian O’Connell","description":"Spike starts a radio show from his shed, under an anonymous identity: 'Radio Boy'. A very funny book that will have tweens and upper primary school children in stitches, with real heart and well-rounded characters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8-11","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35174/the-misadventures-of-max-crumbly.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35174","title":"The Misadventures of Max Crumbly: Locker Hero","author":"by Rachel Renée Russell","description":"Max is put in a locker by the school bully after everyone has left for the long weekend - and then three thieves break in to the school. Written in journal format and peppered with humorous illustrations, Max's (mis)adventures are...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35597/the-secret-keepers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35597","title":"The Secret Keepers","author":"by Trenton Lee Stewart","description":"When Rueben finds an unusual old pocket watch, he discovers it has a secret power: it makes the holder invisible for 15 minutes at a time. Unfortunately, the sinister ruler of the city will stop at nothing to possess it....","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35671/what-not-to-do-if-you-turn-invisible.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35671","title":"What Not to Do If You Turn Invisible","author":"by Ross Welford","description":"Thirteen-year-old Ethel absolutely hates having acne, and will go to some pretty drastic measures to cure it - but she didn't imagine she'd turn invisible. Full of pathos and moral dilemma, this book is a great parable for the emotional...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35527/a-gyal-called-owl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35527","title":"A Girl Called Owl","author":"by Amy Wilson","description":"This is a magical, wintery tale that explores the relationship between the human and fairy world, featuring well-known characters from folklore. Amy Wilson's debut novel is a perfect read for those who love wintery magic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":154,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/154/","title":"Bookbuzz 2012","list_description":"Take a look at the titles selected for the 2012 Bookbuzz programme.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30829/a-most-improper-magick.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30829","title":"A Most Improper Magick","author":"by Stephanie Burgis","description":"A 21st-century take on Jane Austen's world, entertainingly viewed through the eyes of a 12-year-old heroine who discovers she has inherited her mother's magical abilities.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32266/9780230751958-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32266","title":"Journey to the Centre of My Brain","author":"by James Carter","description":"Take a sneak peek into James Carter's weird and wonderful brain in this fun new poetry collection.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32267/9781445105550-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32267","title":"Rivets: Lifters","author":"by Joe Craig","description":"13-year-old Adaq and sister Maya make a slick team of 'lifters', stealing wallets from unsuspecting strangers in order to survive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32269/heroes-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32269","title":"True Stories of Heroes","author":"by Paul Dowswell","description":"From animals to astronauts, and captured spies in World War II, this collection of thirteen short stories celebrates some truly amazing, and amazingly true, heroic acts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32268/9781407124612-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32268","title":"The Messenger Bird","author":"by Ruth Eastham","description":"The Messenger Bird is an exciting adventure story with a twist, and will be particularly enjoyed by anyone who is interested in history and the Second World War.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32116/9780857630506-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32116","title":"Twelve Minutes to Midnight","author":"by Christopher Edge","description":"Every night at precisely 12 minutes to midnight, the inmates of Bedlam, London's notorious madhouse, all begin feverishly writing - incoherent ramblings that Penelope quickly realises are in fact terrifying visions of the new century to come.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31445/9780552561693-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31445","title":"Small Change for Stuart","author":"by Lissa Evans","description":"This humorous adventure is accompanied by atmospheric ink drawings, making this an attractive and compelling book for confident boy and girl readers","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26352/shadowforest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26352","title":"Shadow Forest","author":"by Matt Haig","description":"This fantasy story is both touching and humorous, and is sure to have wide appeal.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32271/9780141335223-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32271","title":"The Secrets Club: Alice in the Spotlight","author":"by Chris Higgins","description":"A lively, warm and entertaining story about friends, family and the ups and downs of school life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32278/9780330452090-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32278","title":"Lost Riders","author":"by Elizabeth Laird","description":"A powerful and challenging story, this title is ideal for children with an interest in social issues and the lives of others across the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31722/9781408313039-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31722","title":"The World of Norm","author":"by Jonathan Meres","description":"A funny illustrated book likely to find favour with fans of Wimpy Kid, Big Nate and Tom Gates.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34641/9781783443024.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34641","title":"Catherine Certitude","author":"by Patrick Modiano","description":"A woman in New York reminisces about growing up in Paris with her father.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32275/9781841676234-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32275","title":"Boffin Boy and the Temple of Mars","author":"by David Orme","description":"Boffin Boy discovers an ancient building on Mars containing mysterious creatures.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32270/9780385618663-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32270","title":"Don't Wipe Your Bum with a Hedgehog","author":"by Mitchell Symons","description":"Hilarious hints, tips and witty words of wisdom in a bumper book of words to live by from the ever popular Mitchell Symons","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32274/spooksquad_thebeastofhangmanshill_300.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32274","title":"Spook Squad: The Beast of Hangman's Hill","author":"by Roger Hurn","description":"The spook squad are Emma, Roxy, Nita and Leena; a team of four feisty girls who bust bogeymen and vanquish vampires.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32276/9781907152498-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32276","title":"Call Me Gorgeous","author":"by Giles Milton","description":"This stunning picture book intrigues and delights in equal measure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"}]}
{"id":157,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/157/","title":"Julia Donaldson's favourite picture books to share","list_description":"When Waterstones asked former Children's Laureate Julia Donaldson to choose her favourite picture books, these are the ones she selected. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32243/9781408309476-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32243","title":"Mad About Minibeasts!","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"These simple, cheerful and humorous rhymes about all the familiar insects you might encounter in your garden are great fun to read together","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24866/handa-s-surprise.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24866","title":"Handa's Surprise","author":"by Eileen Browne","description":"Glorious images of an African village convey the sights, smells and colours of the landscape, its animals and its food in a story told as much through pictures as through words.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32301/9781407116525-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32301","title":"The Snorgh and the Sailor","author":"by Will Buckingham","description":"This thought-provoking, poignant and humorous story about loneliness, friendship and the power of storytelling will delight young readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31515/9781780080031-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31515","title":"Otto the Book Bear","author":"by Katie Cleminson","description":"A charming celebration of books and reading","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31725/9781849390156-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31725","title":"The Day Louis Got Eaten","author":"by John Fardell","description":"Fardell creates a variation on the Old Woman who swallowed a fly in this hilarious adventure","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24861/9781862308053-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24861","title":"Dogger","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"When Dave loses his favourite toy, Dogger, he is desolate.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30473/9781847384744-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30473","title":"Dogs Don't Do Ballet","author":"by Anna Kemp","description":"Everyone knows that dogs don’t do ballet, except for one little girl in Miss Polly’s ballet class.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32300/9780007464388-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32300","title":"Frog and Toad Are Friends","author":"by Arnold Lobel","description":"Arnold Lobel's classic characters Frog and Toad return in this recently republished collection of five favourite stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29774/six-dinner-sid-a-highland-adventure.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29774","title":"Six Dinner Sid: A Highland Adventure","author":"by Inga Moore","description":"Readers are subtly reminded of the responsibilities of pet ownership, and then introduced to a variety of upland wildlife, from wildcat to golden eagle.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":158,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/158/","title":"Being active","list_description":"Hop, skip, dance and jump with these books guaranteed to get you up and moving","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33958/action-rhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33958","title":"Action Rhymes","author":"by Clare Beaton","description":"Simple rhymes with hand-sewn illustrations","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34628/peekaboo-park.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34628","title":"Peekaboo Park!","author":"by Emily Bolam","description":"A life-the-flaps adventure in the park!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24844/maisy-s-treasure-hunt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24844","title":"Maisy's Treasure Hunt","author":"by Lucy Cousins","description":"Maisy and her friends jump all aboard in search of treasure. They’ve got a ship and a map. All they need to find are three keys hidden beneath the flaps…","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34222/digby-dog-delivers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34222","title":"Digby Dog Delivers","author":"by Tor Freeman","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30577/can-you-move-like-and-eleph.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30577","title":"Can You Move Like an Elephant?","author":"by Judy Hindley","description":"This book is full of great pictures and good language to read together - you’ll have great fun trying to imitate the animals!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6months+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34370/surprise-for-tiny-mouse.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34370","title":"A Surprise for Tiny Mouse","author":"by Petr Horáček","description":"Expore different types of weather and turn the wheel for a surprise!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30475/9781846433412-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30475","title":"Hop a Little, Jump a Little!","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"This is a perfect book for sharing with lively toddlers, who will love to imitate the children’s actions, as they run, skip, stretch and nod.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34382/little-jungle-explorers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34382","title":"Little Jungle Explorers","author":"by Anthony Lewis","description":"Colourful board book with double-sided explorer figure!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34220/babys-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34220","title":"Baby's Day","author":"by Little Tiger Kids","description":"Colourful, rhyming board book with photos of happy babies.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfil