tle":"Doing the Animal Bop","author":"by Jan Ormerod","description":"Children will enjoy matching the rhythmic text to the animals actions, and joining in with the dancing themselves. A great book for sharing and one that children are sure to want to hear over and over again!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28585/bounce-and-jiggle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28585","title":"Bounce and Jiggle","author":"by Sanja Rescek","description":"Each Baby Gym book features a range of rhymes accompanied by simple descriptions of associated movements and advice for the parent/carer.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30306/we-re-going-bear-hunt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30306","title":"We're Going on a Bear Hunt","author":"by Michael Rosen & Helen Oxenbury","description":"Follow a father and his family as they go out in search of a bear.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33995/pip-posy-snowy-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33995","title":"Pip and Posy: The Snowy Day","author":"by Axel Scheffler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33827/clip-clop.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33827","title":"Clip-clop","author":"by Nicola Smee","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33035/9781847803887-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33035","title":"Max the Champion","author":"by Sean Stockdale and Alexandra Strick","description":"This inclusive book is about a boy who loves sport, his friends, and school - and has a vivid imagination","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33200/onetwothree.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33200","title":"One, two, three... Run!","author":"by Carol Thompson","description":"Even a simple book for babies and toddlers can include disabled children naturally and subtly in its images - and this delightful board book proves the point.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29981/giraffes-cant-dance.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29981","title":"Giraffes Can't Dance","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"Rhyming text and vibrant full-page illustrations make this marvellous picture book perfect for reading aloud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"}]}
{"id":159,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/159/","title":"Ten books for summer 2012","list_description":"Summer is approaching and you're probably wondering what books to take away with you.  Before you load up your e-reader or head on down to your local bookshop, here's a list of alternative choices for summer reads, books that have been released this year that would make for a great holiday companion, wherever you're going. A mixture of magical and literary fiction, of comedy, of non-fiction, of thriller, from prize winners and nominees to debuts and short story writers, this diverse list of books will help you wile away time on any beach.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32043/homesickd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32043","title":"Homesick","author":"by Roshi Fernando","description":"Thoughtful, melancholic, haunting, Homesick is a collection of interlinked stories which muse on growing up, fitting in and the ephemeral nature of human life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32178/absolution.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32178","title":"Absolution","author":"by Patrick Flanery","description":"This book seeks to lift the lid on modern South Africa and its relationship with its history of Apartheid and war. Part literary detective story and part treatise on socio-economic conditions, it is a strong debut."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32170/the-book-of-summers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32170","title":"The Book of Summers","author":"by Emylia Hall","description":"Hall's debut novel is being billed in most women's magazines as the perfect summer read. I can see why, and not just because of the title. The Book of Summers is an evocative, highly visual novel which conjures a picture..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31935/9780007374441.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31935","title":"The Art of Fielding","author":"by Chad Harbach","description":"The Art of Fielding is the newest heavyweight contender for Great American novel of the world. It arrives on a garlanded float of its own mythology (there’s a companion book detailing the struggles to get it published) and has garnered..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32179/snow-child.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32179","title":"The Snow Child","author":"by Eowyn Ivey","description":"The tough existence of frontier life is detailed without sentiment by Ivey, but with a bracing beauty in the tradition of the Russian fairytale it references."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32306/9780007462773.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32306","title":"Another Country","author":"by Anjali Joseph","description":"Anjali Joseph’s sophomore novel is another exercise in subtle, delicate beauty. Having been daubed one of the Telegraph’s 20 writers under 40, she has gone on from Saraswati Park to win a heap of awards. Another Country further confirms early..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31992/9780701186678.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31992","title":"Suddenly, A Knock At the Door","author":"by Etgar Keret","description":"Etgar Keret's latest collection of off-kilter short stories bring a welcome sense of playful oddness to a genre that is the perfect vehicle for this sort of nimble invention. With the short form a really interesting writer like Keret can..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32251/9781444737141.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32251","title":"Cuckoo In the Nest","author":"by Nat Luurtsema","description":"Comedian Nat Luurtsema is a very funny woman. As a stand-up and as part of sketch trio Jigsaw. This memoir of her 6 months living at home while looking for a flat started out as a collection of hilarious warts'n'all..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32055/this-is-life1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32055","title":"This Is Life","author":"by Dan Rhodes","description":"Dan Rhodes' new novel does that Dan Rhodes thing that Dan Rhodes does so well: talk about the extreme light and dark at the centre of the human condition in a wildly comedic way."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32303/9781444737837.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32303","title":"Snake Ropes","author":"by Jess Richards","description":"Beautifully paced and written with a distinct voice, Snake Ropes is a story of sisterhood, love and determination that builds to an emotional conclusion."}]}
{"id":160,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/160/","title":"Short story collections for young adults","list_description":"We love short stories! Whether you’re looking for an anthology you can dip in and out of, something to read in one sitting, or stories to kick-start the writing of your own, these are some of our favourite YA collections: inspiring, intriguing and surprising.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28582/countingstars.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28582","title":"Counting Stars","author":"by David Almond","description":"This evocative collection of short stories gives a clear insight into the experiences which lie behind David Almond's novels.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31169/the-kissing-game.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31169","title":"The Kissing Game","author":"by Aiden Chambers","description":"Each tale defines a particular moment in life, a revelation, usually for a teenage male protagonist.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30718/echoes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30718","title":"Echoes","author":"by Laura Dockrill","description":"The new book from Laura Dockrill is a collection of modern-day fairytales, poems and retellings of classic stories, all with a slightly sinister edge. Reminiscent of Roald Dahl, Tim Burton and even Grimm, the stories take on a not-quite supernatural...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32043/homesickd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32043","title":"Homesick","author":"by Roshi Fernando","description":"Thoughtful, melancholic, haunting, Homesick is a collection of interlinked stories which muse on growing up, fitting in and the ephemeral nature of human life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27885/smoke-and-mirrors.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27885","title":"Smoke and Mirrors","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"A collection of short stories: an elderly widow finds the Holy Grail beneath an old fur coat; a stray cat fights and refights a terrible nightly battle to protect his adoptive family from evil...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32370/9781849393003-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32370","title":"Next","author":"by Edited by Keith Gray","description":"Following on from the success of Losing It, Keith Gray has edited a new collection of eight short stories for young people exploring the complex question of what happens when we die.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30425/losing-it.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30425","title":"Losing It","author":"by Edited by Keith Gray","description":"This is a collection of eight short stories about growing-up, virginity and sex for teenagers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28085/no-one-belongs-here-more-than-you.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28085","title":"No One Belongs Here More Than You","author":"by Miranda July","description":"Miranda July’s debut collection is an engaging mix of the heartfelt and self-aware, with some very funny moments and sharp observations."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34095/9781405271356-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34095","title":"How They Met and Other Stories","author":"by David Levithan","description":"This collection of stories from bestselling YA author David Levithan shows the many sides of love - complicated, addictive, volatile, scary and wonderful.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30748/pretty-monsters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30748","title":"Pretty Monsters","author":"by Kelly Link","description":"It's a mistake anyone could make - digging up the body from the wrong grave. How could you possibly know the corpse would follow you home? And how can you explain it to your Mum?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31814/9781406336962-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31814","title":"Steampunk! An Anthology of Fantastically Rich and Strange Stories","author":"by Kelly Link","description":"A hugely varied anthology of thrilling and inventive short stories","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33988/my-true-love-gave-to-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33988","title":"My True Love Gave to Me","author":"by Stephanie Perkins","description":"A collection of Christmas-themed romantic short stories, one for each of the 'twelve days', by some of the best known American YA authors.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32553/9781471400131-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32553","title":"Under My Hat: Tales from the Cauldron","author":"by Jonathan Strahan","description":"What makes a witch? Despite the title, the stories in this imaginative collection suggest you might need more than just a pointy hat or a broomstick.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29332/tales-from-outer-suburbia-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29332","title":"Tales From Outer Suburbia","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"These often thought-provoking stories look at the reactions ordinary people have to the unusual situations they find themselves in and feature a host of different illustrative styles ranging from collage to painterly Edward Hopper-esque scenes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":161,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/161/","title":"Summer Reads 2012","list_description":"The summer holidays are here, and to celebrate we're sharing some of our favourite new holiday reads for children of all ages. Whether you'd prefer to set out for adventure in the wilds of India, undertake an epic sea voyage in the company of a bear, or even turn a hen house into a secret theatre, these fun, imaginative and adventurous stories will make perfect summer reading.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32375/tiger-wars-new-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32375","title":"Tiger Wars","author":"by Steve Backshall","description":"Saker and Sinter live utterly different lives - until they find themselves unlikely companions on the run. A breathlessly exciting adventure set in India.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32308/9781408820483-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32308","title":"The Mystery of Wickworth Manor","author":"by Elen Caldecott","description":"This lively story from Elen Caldecott is packed with humour and action, but also has a serious side, touching on the history of the slave trade.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32335/9781409538592-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32335","title":"Butterfly Summer","author":"by Anne-Marie Conway","description":"When Becky moves to the sleepy village of Oakbridge, she can’t imagine how she will fill the long empty days of the summer holidays. Then she discovers the beautiful Butterfly Garden, and befriends the mysterious Rosa May.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31404/flumflum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31404","title":"Jack and the FlumFlum Tree","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"When Jack’s granny falls ill with the moozles, the doctor tells him that the only thing that will cure her is the fruit of the mysterious flumflum tree.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32209/9781904442868-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32209","title":"The Summer Gang","author":"by Cornelia Funke","description":"Living on a remote farm, Charlie wants nothing more than sneak off with a gang of friends for adventure. This summer she's going to make it happen, no matter what.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32376/9780007263899-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32376","title":"Stuck","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"It started with Floyd's kite - but now there's all kinds of things stuck in the tree: a cat, a bucket of paint, the kitchen sink, and even a curious whale who happened to be in the wrong place at...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32217/white-dolphins.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32217","title":"White Dolphin","author":"by Gill Lewis","description":"A young dolphin, washed up on the beach, unexpectedly brings Kara and Felix together. But the new friends must take on new challenges - finding out the truth about Kara's missing mother, and protecting the bay when it falls under...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32059/9780857863249-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32059","title":"Wildwood","author":"by Colin Meloy","description":"When her baby brother is mysteriously kidnapped by crows, Prue McKeel knows she must rescue him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10 +","interest_age":"Interest level: 8 +"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32349/9781847802088-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32349","title":"Daisy's Big Dig","author":"by Angie Morgan","description":"Daisy loves talking to all her neighbours on Magnolia Street, but they never talk to each other. When Mr Hofmeister hurts his back, Daisy comes up with a plan to look after his garden and bring the neighbours together.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32374/9780857630650-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32374","title":"The Secret Hen House Theatre","author":"by Helen Peters","description":"Helen Peters has drawn on her own childhood on a farm, and her memories of writing and acting out her own plays, to create this lively story with a very convincing rural setting.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32213/9780230529229-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32213","title":"Solomon Crocodile","author":"by Catherine Rayner","description":"Everything is peaceful on the river, until Solomon Crocodile appears and disturbs everyone from the frogs to the dragonflies to the storks. When he takes on the hippos peacefully bathing in the river, they decide enough is enough.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32309/9781444004854-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32309","title":"Raven Boy and Elf Girl: Fright Forest","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"The first book in a magical new adventure series for younger readers from award-winning author Marcus Sedgwick, Fright Forest introduces us to dynamic duo Raven Boy and Elf Girl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31964/9780385618960-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31964","title":"A Boy and a Bear in a Boat","author":"by Dave Shelton","description":"Imagine travelling on a boat with a polar bear as your captain.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"}]}
{"id":162,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/162/","title":"Summers to remember","list_description":"The holidays are here and we're celebrating with this list of our favourite books about unforgettable summers. From love stories to dark comedy, these are all tales of memorable and life-changing summer adventures. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31286/swimthefly.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31286","title":"Swim the Fly","author":"by Don Calame","description":"Matt, Coop and Sean have been friends forever. Each summer, they set themselves a goal, and this year tops the lot - they must see a real live naked girl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32115/9781405260374-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32115","title":"Dear Dylan","author":"by Siobhan Curham","description":"A tender-hearted and funny teenage novel about the power of even the most unlikely friendships, with a wonderfully effervescent and likable heroine, Dear Dylan was a deserving winner of the 2010 Young Minds Book Award.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24436/a-gathering-light.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24436","title":"A Gathering Light","author":"by Jennifer Donnelly","description":"Mattie is entrusted by a female guest at the hotel where she works with some letters and instructed to burn them. The next day the woman is found drowned: murdered.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32319/9780440870043-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32319","title":"Dead End in Norvelt","author":"by Jack Gantos","description":"In a small town populated by larger-than-life characters, truth meets fantasy as this hilarious, semi-autobiographical novel charts the progress of Jack’s summer","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31018/everybody-jam.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31018","title":"Everybody Jam","author":"by Ali Lewis","description":"Set during a long, hot summer, this is an unflinching look at life on a cattle station in the Australian outback as a family tries to come to terms with the death of their oldest son in a horrific accident.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24508/9780141318011-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24508","title":"How I Live Now","author":"by Meg Rosoff","description":"Fifteen-year-old New Yorker Daisy is sent to England to spend a summer with her unconventional cousins","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30428/white-crow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30428","title":"White Crow","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"City girl Rebecca, spending the summer in a remote East Anglian seaside village, encounters Ferelith, a Goth who lives in a commune.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24572/icapturethecastle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24572","title":"I Capture the Castle","author":"by Dodie Smith","description":"17-year-old Cassandra lives an eccentric existence with her bohemian family in a crumbling castle in the English countryside, in this delightful classic coming-of-age story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32377/9780141340722-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32377","title":"The Probability of Miracles","author":"by Wendy Wunder","description":"Cyncial teenage cancer patient Campbell has a summer to remember in the magical town of Promise in this moving and bittersweet debut novel","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":163,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/163/","title":"Books about sport","list_description":"Here's a booklist that bursts through the finishing line. Whether you prefer football or cycling, ballet or basketball, there's something for everyone on our list, which is perfect for children aged 8-14 years-old.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25148/friendly-matches.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25148","title":"Friendly Matches","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"Friendly Matches is an entertaining, and at times thought-provoking, collection of poetry about football.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33753/story-of-the-world-cup.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33753","title":"The Story of the World Cup","author":"by Richard Brassey","description":"With its imaginative, graphic style and tongue in cheek humour, this bright, breezy, introduction packs in a lot of information, making it both accessible and entertaining - even to the non-football fan!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29827/willy-the-champ.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29827","title":"Willy the Champ","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"Another book about Willy the chimpanzee who doesn't conform to the macho stereotypes and so comes in for a lot of hard times and bullying.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24557/fat-boy-swims.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24557","title":"Fat Boy Swim","author":"by Catherine Forde","description":"This is a wonderful story, brilliantly told in the Glaswegian dialect, and despite containing distressing accounts of bullying, it also reveals the complexities of human nature","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29675/wonder-goal.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29675","title":"Wonder Goal","author":"by Michael Foreman","description":"Being the new boy on the football team is no fun, especially for one little boy who trips over the shoelaces his team-mates have tied together.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30348/tall-story.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30348","title":"Tall Story","author":"by Candy Gourlay","description":"Engagingly told in alternate chapters by four-foot, thirteen year-old Andi, in the UK, and her eight-foot, sixteen year-old half brother Bernardo, in the Philippines","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32292/9781406336108.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32292","title":"Hero on a Bicycle","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"The first novel from much-loved author and illustrator Shirley Hughes is a thrilling and moving story about a boy and his bicycle, set against a dramatic background of war-torn Italy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24505/keeper.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24505","title":"Keeper","author":"by Mal Peet","description":"In this excellent football story, set in modern-day South America, a hackneyed football reporter sits down with El Gato (the Cat), a World Cup-winning goalkeeper, to look back on his amazing life and career.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30497/dream-on.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30497","title":"Dream On","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"Much to the disapproval of his parents, Baljit is mad on football and when he is invited to trials at Leicester City, he has to lie about his whereabouts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32359/9781849394024-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32359","title":"I Want to Win!","author":"by Tony Ross","description":"The Little Princess is used to getting her own way, which means that when she plays games at home she always wins. But at school, the rules are different.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31112/dreamer-ballerina.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31112","title":"Dreamer Ballerina","author":"by Sarah Rubin","description":"A dance story with a difference, Dreamer Ballerina tells the story of small town girl Casey Quinn, who just can’t keep her toes from tapping.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34956/rugby-flyer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34956","title":"Rugby Flyer","author":"by Gerard Siggins","description":"Vividly drawn, engaging characters and short, sparky chapters keep the action fast-paced in this absorbing story set at a rugby school. It combines exciting sport tension, historical mystery and a ghost story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32190/manual_9781444002690-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32190","title":"The One Dollar Horse","author":"by Lauren St John","description":"Casey Blue lives with her father in a tower block in Hackney, London , but despite her urban existence, she dreams of one day becoming an equestrian champion.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33035/9781847803887-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33035","title":"Max the Champion","author":"by Sean Stockdale and Alexandra Strick","description":"This inclusive book is about a boy who loves sport, his friends, and school - and has a vivid imagination","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"}]}
{"id":164,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/164/","title":"Journeys to Other Lands","list_description":"Travel from the desert to the jungle, the beach to the snowy mountains with our list of books that will take you on journeys to many different lands. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30598/rumble-in-the-jungle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30598","title":"Rumble in the Jungle","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31399/9781406318333-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31399","title":"Anna Hibiscus' Song","author":"by Atinuke","description":"This delightful story about a happy girl learning to express her feelings is a wonderful celebration of the joy of life","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30715/my-sister-is-an-alien.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30715","title":"My sister is an Alien","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"Alfie's new baby sister, Ruby, looks, sounds and smells like an alien. Alfie is convinced she often cries for home. He decides to take Ruby back to the moon where she belongs.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24866/handa-s-surprise.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24866","title":"Handa's Surprise","author":"by Eileen Browne","description":"Glorious images of an African village convey the sights, smells and colours of the landscape, its animals and its food in a story told as much through pictures as through words.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34365/the-selfish-crocodile-faustin-charles.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34365","title":"The Selfish Crocodile","author":"by Faustin Charles and Mike Terry","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33707/tiny-the-invisible-world-of-microbes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33707","title":"Tiny: The Invisible World of Microbes","author":"by Nicola Davies","description":"This is an original, special and memorable book that sets the bar high for illustrated children's non-fiction.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31318/9781840111545-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31318","title":"To the Beach","author":"by Thomas Docherty","description":"Lovely story of a boy using his imagination to go on a trip to the seaside","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4months+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31295/the-magic-paintbrush.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31295","title":"The Magic Paintbrush","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"When Shen is given a magic paintbrush, she promises only to use it for the good of the poor. But how will she avoid painting for the greedy emperor?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25701/meerkatmail.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25701","title":"Meerkat Mail","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"Sunny lives on an arid plain with his extensive and loving meerkat family; they work together, play together and together do their best to stay away from jackals!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33831/tip-tap-went-crab.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33831","title":"Tip Tap Went The Crab","author":"by Tim Hopgood","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34232/out-of-the-blue-barefoot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34232","title":"Out of the Blue","author":"by Alison Jay","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: n/a","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25161/lost-found.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25161","title":"Lost and Found","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"Once there was a sad, lonely penguin who appeared at the door of a young boy. The boy decided he must be lost, so he set off to find his home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34233/we-all-went-on-safari.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34233","title":"We All Went on Safari","author":"by Laurie Krebs and Julia Cairns","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34382/little-jungle-explorers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34382","title":"Little Jungle Explorers","author":"by Anthony Lewis","description":"Colourful board book with double-sided explorer figure!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29177/9780340950654-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29177","title":"Miki","author":"by Stephen Mackey","description":"Shimmering like the northern lights, the illustrations' luminous blues and greens glow out of the darkness in this chilly yet elegantly magical wintry tale","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":165,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/165/","title":"Starting school or nursery","list_description":"These books are ideal for introducing children to the idea of starting school or nursery, and dealing with any fears or anxieties they may have.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24877/iam2small4school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24877","title":"I am Too Absolutely Small for School","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Lola is nearly big enough to go to school. But in her opinion she is still really quite small, and has far too many important things to keep her extremely busy at home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31505/9780007274680-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31505","title":"First Week at Cow School","author":"by Andy Cutbill","description":"This hilarious story celebrating difference and acceptance is told with charm and wonderfully illustrated with Russell Ayto's fun and wacky illustrations","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32407/9780330512282-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32407","title":"Goat Goes to Playgroup","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Julia Donaldson sets to work to reassure newcomers to playgroups everywhere in this picture book with a simple rhyming text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30532/going2playschool.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30532","title":"Going to Playschool","author":"by Sarah Garland","description":"This book is engaging, colourful and very real: the story captures perfectly the mood of playschool."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27339/alfie-and-the-big-boys.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27339","title":"Alfie and the Big Boys","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Children will relish this warm tale of everyday life with illustrations overflowing with colour and vitality.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3 - 8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32128/9781407108568-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32128","title":"Sidney Goes to School","author":"by Sharon Rentta","description":"Having just leant to ride a bicycle, Sidney, the little blue elephant can't wait to share his excitement with his friends at school, but new class member Alfie seems to be stealing the limelight.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31479/harry-and-the-dinosours-go-to-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31479","title":"Harry and the Dinosaurs go to School","author":"by Ian Whybrow","description":"It's Harry's first day at school. He and his dinosaurs are very excited and perhaps a little bit nervous.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":166,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/166/","title":"Olympic books","list_description":"I don't know if you knew but there are some Olympic Games currently taking place in London as we speak.  To celebrate, we thought, instead of giving you more sports books to read, how about a list of books inspired by the colours of the Olympic rings...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28107/half-of-a-yellow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28107","title":"Half of a Yellow Sun","author":"by Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie","description":"Half of a Yellow Sun is set in Nigeria during the 1960s, at the time of the vicious Nigeria- Biafra war in which more than a million people died and thousands were massacred in cold blood","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31638/9780955647611.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31638","title":"Girl in a Blue Dress","author":"by Gaynor Arnold","description":"In Alfred Gibson the fierce energy and brilliance of the most famous of the Victorian novelists is recreated, in a heart-warming story of first love--of a cocky young writer smitten by a pretty girl in a blue dress."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29877/black-water-rising.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29877","title":"Black Water Rising","author":"by Attica Locke","description":"On a dark night, out on the Houston bayou to celebrate his wife's birthday, Jay Porter hears a scream. Saving a distressed woman from drowning, he opens a Pandora's Box."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26068/9781843544234.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26068","title":"White and Red","author":"by Dorota Maslowska","description":"Andrzej 'Nails' Robakoski is a tracksuited slacker who spends most of his time doing nothing other than searching for his next line of speed and dreaming up conspiracy theories about the national economy. Dumped by his girlfriend Magda, a beautiful..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29880/the-white-woman-on-the-green-bicycle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29880","title":"The White Woman on the Green Bicycle","author":"by Monique Roffey","description":"When George and Sabine Harwood arrive in Trinidad from England George instantly takes to their new life, but Sabine feels isolated, heat-fatigued, and ill at ease with the racial segregation and the imminent dawning of a new era."}]}
{"id":167,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/167/","title":"Books about space","list_description":"If you've been inspired by Nasa's successful landing of the rover Curiosity on Mars, then why not take a look at our favourite children's books about space? These 10 great intergalactic adventures for all ages will take you on exciting interstellar journeys through the cosmos...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31891/man-on-the-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31891","title":"The Man on the Moon!","author":"by Simon Bartram","description":"Bob knows almost everything there is to know about the moon - but there's something going on behind his back that he hasn't spotted...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32427/6.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32427","title":"The Terrible Thing That Happened to Barnaby Brocket","author":"by John Boyne","description":"Barnaby Brocket has an unusual gift: he defies the law of gravity and floats. Embarassed by their child's 'abnormality', his parents set out to keep his feet on the ground.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31253/space-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31253","title":"Space School: Crash Course","author":"by Tony Bradman and Tom Bradman","description":"The first in the Space School series starring Luke Riley, whose mum is the captain of the Buzz Aldrin, a spaceship cruising the universe following a pollution-related disaster on Earth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30479/cosmic-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30479","title":"Cosmic","author":"by Frank Cottrell Boyce","description":"Long-legged Liam makes a giant leap for boy-kind by competing with a group of adults for the chance to go into space. Is Liam the best boy for the job?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26309/aliens-love-underpants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26309","title":"Aliens Love Underpants","author":"by Claire Freedman","description":"Underpants are a source of humour whatever your reading age, even, it appears, when it comes to aliens!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32416/9780857550217-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32416","title":"Toys in Space","author":"by Mini Grey","description":"The toys have been left outside in the garden one summer night. To help to pass the time till morning, Wonderdoll begins to tell a story about the arrival of a mysterious alien spaceship...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32339/9781849413855-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32339","title":"Wanda's Space Party","author":"by Sue Hendra","description":"For a birthday treat, Wanda the rabbit is invited to her friend’s house. But in fact, her friend is an alien and he’s taking Wanda home to his amazing planet.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31376/a-wrinkle-in-time.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31376","title":"A Wrinkle in Time","author":"by Madeleine L'engle","description":"When Charles Wallace Murry goes searching through a 'wrinkle in time' for his lost father, he finds himself on an evil planet where all life is enslaved by a huge pulsating brain known as 'It'."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25835/larklight.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25835","title":"Larklight","author":"by Philip Reeve","description":"Award-winning Reeve indulges his love of historical technology in a new novel for younger readers, which is as captivating as the Mortal Engines quartet was for an older audience.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":170,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/170/","title":"Five non-fiction books about contemporary youth","list_description":"A year on from the riots, as part of our youth focus season, we give you five books that explore the issues facing young people today - from the demonization of the working class to gang culture to the austerity cuts...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32445/chavs...jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32445","title":"Chavs","author":"by Owen Jones","description":"Chavs is a damning indictment of the media and political establishment and an illuminating, disturbing portrait of inequality and class hatred in modern Britain","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32446/9781844287789.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32446","title":"Politics - cutting through the crap","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"What is politics? How does Parliament work? Is the great British democracy even a true democracy?"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32448/among-the-hoodsm.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32448","title":"Among the hoods","author":"by Harriet Sergeant","description":"Harriet Sergeant's three year friendship with a teenage gang, and in particular the gang leader, Tuggy Tug began when she was researching a report on why so many black Caribbean and white working class boys are failing","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32447/9781448114757.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32447","title":"Summer of Unrest: Generation Vexed","author":"by Nikesh Shukla","description":"An antidote to the broadsheet commentariat, this street-level view of the defining moment of the Summer of Unrest finds much to inspire hope and confidence for our future.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32449/fe82097f-e28e-45e9-9cb0-3735b5194779-img100.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32449","title":"Gang Leader for a Day","author":"by Sudhir Venkatesh","description":"Sudhir Venkatesh the young sociologist who became famous in Freakonomics (Why do drug dealers still live with their moms?) describes his time living with the gangs on the Southside of Chicago","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"}]}
{"id":171,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/171/","title":"Contemporary teenage life","list_description":"What does it mean to be a young person today? These novels take a variety of approaches to exploring the reality of growing up in 21st century Britain","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30873/boys-dontcry.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30873","title":"Boys Don't Cry","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Dante is waiting for the postman. It's 'A' level results day and he has high hopes, but a knock on the door brings an old girlfriend and some news that will change his plans for good.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31521/9780141335643-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31521","title":"Kill All Enemies","author":"by Melvin Burgess","description":"There are always two sides to every story – who is making the rules, the young people or the adults?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26901/b4idie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26901","title":"Before I Die","author":"by Jenny Downham","description":"Stunning in its beauty and honesty, this is an exceptional and utterly compelling read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32395/9780370332345-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32395","title":"Turf","author":"by John Lucas","description":"15-year-old Jay is a member of the Blake Street Boyz gang. But when gang leader Shads decides it's time for him to step up and prove his loyalty, Jay realises he has a difficult choice to make.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31311/mysisterlivesonmatlepiece.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31311","title":"My Sister Lives on the Mantelpiece","author":"by Annabel Pitcher","description":"Told through the eyes of ten-year-old Jamie, My Sister Lives on the Mantelpiece sensitively tackles issues around grief, terrorism, racism and bullying.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31342/killing-honour.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31342","title":"Killing Honour","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"A blood-curdling murder story set in Leicester’s Asian community where family honour seems sometimes to count for more than family love","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31985/this-is-not-forgiveness.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31985","title":"This is Not Forgiveness","author":"by Celia Rees","description":"A hard-hitting, compelling novel about the effects of war","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29424/the-ant-colony.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29424","title":"The Ant Colony","author":"by Jenny Valentine","description":"Sam and Bo reveal their pasts in alternate chapters, each gradually facing the dysfunctional relationships and traumatic incidents which have triggered their current unlikely friendship.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":172,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/172/","title":"Reimagining children's classics","list_description":"Taking inspiration from some favourite stories and characters, these authors have all put a new spin on classic novels.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31435/9780571272389-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31435","title":"Tarzan: The Greystoke Legacy","author":"by Andy Briggs","description":"A classic with a 21st century twist, this riveting adventure overflows with suspense, danger, brutality and beauty","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35250/lydia.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35250","title":"Lydia: the wild girl of Pride and Prejudice","author":"by Natasha Farrant","description":"A spirited reimagining of Jane Austen's Pride and Prejudice, told from the perspective of Lydia, the youngest Bennet sister. It is great fun to see her thoughts on her older sisters Jane and Lizzy, plus Mr Darcy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31447/9780330512008-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31447","title":"Young Sherlock Holmes: Black Ice","author":"by Andrew Lane","description":"An exciting, fast-paced adventure, which paints a vivid picture of mid-nineteenth century Britain and Russia","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29640/wishing-for-tomorrow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29640","title":"Wishing for Tomorrow","author":"by Hilary McKay","description":"Evocatively illustrated, this is a warm and humorous sequel to Frances Hodgson Burnett's A Little Princess.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31709/this-dark-endeavourd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31709","title":"This Dark Endeavour","author":"by Kenneth Oppel","description":"Oppel paints a vivid, sometimes horrific, picture of medicine at the time, in a gripping, fast-moving and atmospheric narrative","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32470/terry_pratchett_dodger_cover-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32470","title":"Dodger","author":"by Terry Pratchett","description":"Terry Pratchett once again proves himself a master storyteller in this tribute to one of Charles Dickens' best-known characters, the Artful Doger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31775/mister-creecher.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31775","title":"Mister Creecher","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"Friendship, trust and betrayal combine to form a dangerous liaison in this moving and frightening new book from Chris Priestley","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31988/oliver-twisted.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31988","title":"Oliver Twisted","author":"by J D Sharpe","description":"'Can I have some gore?' Oliver Twist is given a supernatural spin in this vivid reimagining of Dickens’ novel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32468/the_further_tale_of_peter_rabbit_by_emma_thompson_home_banner-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32468","title":"The Further Tale of Peter Rabbit","author":"by Emma Thompson","description":"Oscar-winning actress and screenwriter Emma Thompson has turned her hand to children's books in this new continuation of Peter Rabbit's adventures.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32382/9780141341422-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32382","title":"Four Children and It","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Jacqueline Wilson pays tribute to her 'all-time favourite classic children's author' E. Nesbit in this contemporary reimagining of Five Children and It.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":173,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/173/","title":"All about starting school","list_description":"Some of our favourite books for children who are starting school.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32472/topsy-and-tim.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32472","title":"Topsy and Tim Start School","author":"by Jean Adamson","description":"Find out what happens on the twins' first day at school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32473/starting-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32473","title":"Starting School","author":"by Janet and Allan Ahlberg","description":"Starting School by Janet and Allan Ahlberg is an enchanting picture book for reassuring children who are about to start school for the very first time."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34605/51rb-nq5-vl._sx428_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34605","title":"Bunny Loves to Learn","author":"by Peter Bently","description":"Four friends are asked to dress up from someone from the past and create something to do with their respective character.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24877/iam2small4school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24877","title":"I am Too Absolutely Small for School","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Lola is nearly big enough to go to school. But in her opinion she is still really quite small, and has far too many important things to keep her extremely busy at home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33270/9780007258680-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33270","title":"Come to School Too, Blue Kangaroo","author":"by Emma Chichester Clark","description":"Lily thinks Blue Kangaroo might be nervous about starting school – but in fact he can’t wait to have fun and make some new friends.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31505/9780007274680-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31505","title":"First Week at Cow School","author":"by Andy Cutbill","description":"This hilarious story celebrating difference and acceptance is told with charm and wonderfully illustrated with Russell Ayto's fun and wacky illustrations","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34590/9781783441648.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34590","title":"A Big Day for Migs!","author":"by Jo Hodgkinson","description":"Migs is nervous on the first day of school, so he tries a number of things to calm his nerves.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27339/alfie-and-the-big-boys.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27339","title":"Alfie and the Big Boys","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Children will relish this warm tale of everyday life with illustrations overflowing with colour and vitality.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3 - 8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34597/51uli5pbwil._sx460_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34597","title":"Hugless Douglas Goes to School","author":"by David Melling","description":"Hugless Douglas has a great first day of school when he shows everyone his favourite activity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32474/meg-comes-to-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32474","title":"Meg Comes to School","author":"by Helen Nicoll","description":"When Meg attends Owl's school sports day in a very unusual hat, everyone is in for a big surprise!"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34613/51ntktevxpl._sx258_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34613","title":"Jellybean Goes to School","author":"by Margaret Roc","description":"Jellybean finds her first day of school a little scary, but she soon finds it easier when she makes a friend.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31479/harry-and-the-dinosours-go-to-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31479","title":"Harry and the Dinosaurs go to School","author":"by Ian Whybrow","description":"It's Harry's first day at school. He and his dinosaurs are very excited and perhaps a little bit nervous.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":174,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/174/","title":"Fun Facts","list_description":"Perfect for enquiring young minds, these engaging non-fiction books approach subjects from biography to nature and science to history in a variety of interesting ways.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32686/9781407116730-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32686","title":"Horrible Science: House of Horrors","author":"by Nick Arnold and Tony De Saulles","description":"Enter the house of horrors and get up close with fleas, dust-mites, rats and germs in this entertaining book from the popular Horrible Science series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33416/9781406323030-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33416","title":"See What a Seal Can Do","author":"by Chris Butterworth & Kate Nelms","description":"This stunning picture book follows a day in the life of a grey seal.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31900/9781846863325-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31900","title":"The Barefoot Books World Atlas","author":"by Nick Crane","description":"Full of fascinating facts and figures about the earth and beautifully illustrated with David Dean’s bright and colourful maps","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32288/9781406304916-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32288","title":"A First Book of Nature","author":"by Nicola Davies","description":"Hearld's nostalgic illustrations are the perfect accompaniment to this lovely chronicle of a child's first experiences of nature","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32906/9781406344776-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32906","title":"Just Ducks","author":"by Nicola Davies","description":"Every morning when she wakes up, a little girl hears the ducks quack down on the river that flows through the town.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31837/9781844287758-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31837","title":"North: The Greatest Animal Journey on Earth","author":"by Nick Dowson","description":"This exquisite picture book invites readers to accompany a host of animals from walruses to whales, as they migrate to the Arctic for the summer months","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32269/heroes-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32269","title":"True Stories of Heroes","author":"by Paul Dowswell","description":"From animals to astronauts, and captured spies in World War II, this collection of thirteen short stories celebrates some truly amazing, and amazingly true, heroic acts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31014/can-we-save-the-tiger.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31014","title":"Can We Save the Tiger?","author":"by Martin Jenkins","description":"A sequel to Ape, this beautifully illustrated book takes us through some of the extinct and endangered animals in the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31570/9781847801852-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31570","title":"Actual Size","author":"by Steve Jenkins","description":"Have you ever looked a giant squid in the eye, shaken hands with a gorilla or been face to face with a tiger?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31924/9781847801876-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31924","title":"Charles Dickens: Scenes from an Extraordinary Life","author":"by Mick Manning","description":"Celebrate the 2012 bi-centenary of Charles Dickens' life with this new, illustrated biography. Beginning with his birth it follows Dickens through his early years of hardship, career as a reporter and his family life, and then moves on to his...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32745/9781847802125-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32745","title":"Walter Tull's Scrapbook","author":"by Michaela Morgan","description":"Discover the fascinating true story of footballer and World War I officer Walter Tull in this highly visual scrapbook.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32425/9780330533874-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32425","title":"Tony Robinson's Weird World of Wonders: Egyptians","author":"by Tony Robinson","description":"If you have ever wondered why pyramids are pyramid-shaped or why Egyptian Gods looked so very strange, then this is the book for you!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32477/00a64982-6b10-4606-bcf6-1674952c092d-img100-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32477","title":"Fantastic Mr Dahl","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":"This new biography of Roald Dahl, written especially for children by former Children’s Laureate Michael Rosen, has been much anticipated - it's been ten years in the making!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30380/wombats-bum-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30380","title":"How to Avoid a Wombat's Bum","author":"by Mitchell Symons","description":"Have you ever wondered how long it would take to walk to the sun (about 2,000 years, if you didn’t burn to a crisp!)? And did you know that a snail has 25,000 teeth?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29696/insect-detective.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29696","title":"Insect Detective","author":"by Steve Voake","description":"A range of insects are introduced – wasps, solitary bees, ants, dragonflies – and their behaviour described.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33032/9781909263024-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33032","title":"One Night, Far From Here","author":"by Julia Wauters","description":"What animals are hiding in the woods at night, out on the African savannah, in the rainforest of South America, or at the bottom of the Pacific Ocean?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"}]}
{"id":175,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/175/","title":"Heroines","list_description":"To celebrate International Women's Day 2017, here's a list of some of our favourite stories with inspiring heroines for older girls and young teens.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29198/chains.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29198","title":"Chains","author":"by Laurie Halse Anderson","description":"A brilliantly told, exciting story, with a brave and dignified heroine, which reveals the complexities of this chapter of American history.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34805/am-i-normal-yet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34805","title":"Am I Normal Yet?","author":"by Holly Bourne","description":"This is a powerful and engrossing read that successfully informs, shocks, reassures and entertains in equal measures.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30829/a-most-improper-magick.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30829","title":"A Most Improper Magick","author":"by Stephanie Burgis","description":"A 21st-century take on Jane Austen's world, entertainingly viewed through the eyes of a 12-year-old heroine who discovers she has inherited her mother's magical abilities.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32846/9781907411588-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32846","title":"Etiquette and Espionage","author":"by Gail Carriger","description":"Sophronia is horrified when her mother decides to send her to an exclusive finishing school - but on arrival she realises it's not quite what her mother expected.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29230/hungergames.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29230","title":"The Hunger Games","author":"by Suzanne Collins","description":"Welcome to Panem: its Capitol repressively rules twelve satellite Districts, enslaving the populations as workers and controlling them through hunger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25342/matilda.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25342","title":"Matilda","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This modern fairy-tale with a brilliantly inspiring young heroine is one of Roald Dahl's best loved stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24706/bindi-babes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24706","title":"Bindi Babes","author":"by Narinder Dhami","description":"Narinder Dhami has a light touch which girls in particular will enjoy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32116/9780857630506-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32116","title":"Twelve Minutes to Midnight","author":"by Christopher Edge","description":"Every night at precisely 12 minutes to midnight, the inmates of Bedlam, London's notorious madhouse, all begin feverishly writing - incoherent ramblings that Penelope quickly realises are in fact terrifying visions of the new century to come.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24729/coraline-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24729","title":"Coraline","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"One day Coraline unlocks a mysterious door that opens onto another world, a twisted parody of Coraline's own dimension.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35366/front-lines.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35366","title":"Front Lines","author":"by Michael Grant","description":"It's an alternate history where girls are subject to the military draft in the US. Fast-paced, clever and with incredibly relatable characters, Front Lines is a fresh take on the second world war, while also letting females be kickass.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31372/howl-s-moving-castle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31372","title":"Howl's Moving Castle","author":"by Diana Wynne Jones","description":"Sophie Hatter is cursed with an old body by the Witch of the Waste and the spell can only be broken by the dreaded Wizard Howl who lives in his moving castle and likes to eat the souls of young...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24937/pirates.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24937","title":"Pirates!","author":"by Celia Rees","description":"Pirates! traces the adventures of Nancy Kington and Minerva Sharpe as they sail the high seas, often fighting for their lives, in the hope of gaining glory and riches.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25811/tracey-beaker.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25811","title":"The Story of Tracy Beaker","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Tracy lives in a children's home but constantly hopes that her absent, glamorous Mum will come and take her away.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":176,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/176/","title":"Booktime books, past and present","list_description":"Book suggestions for the autumn term to work with your Ant Club resources.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29824/funnybones.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29824","title":"Funnybones","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"In the first book of this now classic series, we are taken down the dark, dark street to the dark, dark house and into the dark, dark cellar in which the skeletons live.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29869/slowly-slowly-slowly-said-the-sloth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29869","title":"\"Slowly, Slowly, Slowly,\" Said the Sloth","author":"by Eric Carle","description":"Sloth lives in the rainforest with pumas, bats, monkeys and many more animals. Sloth's fellow creatures can't understand why he is so quiet, so slow and so lazy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29823/hairy-maclary-s-bone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29823","title":"Hairy Maclary's Bone","author":"by Lynley Dodd","description":"Hairy Maclary is lucky enough to be given a big juicy bone by the butcher, Samuel Stone. This does not go unnoticed by all the other dogs who decide to follow him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31495/facepainting-cover-high-res.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31495","title":"Face Painting","author":"by Monica Hughes","description":"'I am a clown, I am a pirate', there’s a face painting design every child will enjoy in this fun non-fiction book, from a beautiful butterfly to a fearsome pirate and a scary monster. Full of colourful photos of children...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32227/tims-din-medium.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32227","title":"Tim's Din","author":"by Monica Hughes","description":"Tim’s Din is a lively and entertaining story about the mischief that little monkeys can get up to when they’re bored."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29870/why-is-the-sky-blue.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29870","title":"Why is the Sky Blue?","author":"by Ladybird Books","description":"Why is the sky blue? Do fish drink? What are clouds made of? This book answers all these questions and many more.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31474/why-elephant-has-a-trunk.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31474","title":"Tinga Tinga Tales: Why Elephant has a Trunk","author":"by Claudia Lloyd","description":"There was a time when Elephant had no nose. He was big, clumsy and very, very smelly and always covered in flies because his nose was too small to wash himself with. This enteraining story about how elephant got his...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28966/mr-big.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28966","title":"Mr Big","author":"by Ed Vere","description":"With its gruff hero, vibrant, strong colours, bold design and spare text, this story about looking beyond appearances has a satisfying punchy simplicity and jazzy feel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32226/naughty-little-rabbit-mediu.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32226","title":"The Tale of a Naughty Little Rabbit","author":"by Frederick Warne","description":"The Tale of a Naughty Little Rabbit is a playful and funny retelling of Beatrix Potter’s original story The Tale of Peter Rabbit."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31479/harry-and-the-dinosours-go-to-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31479","title":"Harry and the Dinosaurs go to School","author":"by Ian Whybrow","description":"It's Harry's first day at school. He and his dinosaurs are very excited and perhaps a little bit nervous.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":177,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/177/","title":"Heroes","list_description":"This year's Children's Book Week theme is Heroes and Heroines - and here's a list of some of our favourite books with fantastic heroes.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33705/daddy-hero-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33705","title":"Daddy is My Hero","author":"by Dawn Richards and Jane Massey","description":"Fantasy, fun and fancy dress in this tender and touching tribute to heroic Dads!"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29551/9780141324302-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29551","title":"Young Samurai The Way of the Warrior","author":"by Chris Bradford","description":"This engaging historical adventure story will immerse young readers in the traditions and culture of Ancient Japan, including its complex codes of loyalty and honour.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28627/artemisfowl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28627","title":"Artemis Fowl","author":"by Eoin Colfer","description":"Twelve-year-old criminal mastermind Artemis Fowl hatches an ingenious plot to steal all the gold in fairy land.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30283/charlie-chocolatefactory.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30283","title":"Charlie and the Chocolate Factory","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"Roald Dahl's wicked sense of humour is perfectly in evidence in this marvellously imaginative classic story, which has been loved by generations of children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32456/moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32456","title":"Maggot Moon","author":"by Sally Gardner","description":"Combining conspiracy theory and dystopia, this hugely original novel is set in an alternate 1950s in which Britain is dominated by the ruthlessly oppressive forces of The Motherland.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25454/once.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25454","title":"Once","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"Morris Gleitzman brings heart and humour to the difficult subject of the Holocaust in this ground-breaking children's book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30118/stormbreakerz.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30118","title":"Stormbreaker","author":"by Anthony Horowitz","description":"Fourteen-year-old Alex Rider finds his life turned upside down on discovering that his late uncle wasn't a mild-mannered banker, but instead a field agent for MI6.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31305/one-dog-and-his-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31305","title":"One Dog and His Boy","author":"by Eva Ibbotson","description":"All Hal wants for his birthday is a dog and when he is given one he is overjoyed. But when Hal realises Fleck was only his for the weekend, he sets off on an adventure with the dog...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32186/9780552565974.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32186","title":"Wonder","author":"by R J Palacio","description":"August ('Auggie') Pullman can't help but stand out - he was born with a severe facial deformity. Written in the first person, Wonder follows Auggie as he experiences more than the usual ups-and-downs of friendships, family and school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32470/terry_pratchett_dodger_cover-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32470","title":"Dodger","author":"by Terry Pratchett","description":"Terry Pratchett once again proves himself a master storyteller in this tribute to one of Charles Dickens' best-known characters, the Artful Doger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29281/lightingthief.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29281","title":"Percy Jackson and the Lightning Thief","author":"by Rick Riordan","description":"In this leftfield comic fantasy novel, 12-year-old Percy Jackson discovers that the Greek gods of Olympus are alive and living in modern-day New York.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30267/9780747558194-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30267","title":"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone","author":"by J K Rowling","description":"After the misery of life with his ghastly aunt and uncle, Harry Potter is delighted to have the chance to embark on an exciting new life at the Hogwart's School of Wizardry and Witchcraft.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31807/horridhenry-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31807","title":"Horrid Henry","author":"by Francesca Simon & Tony Ross","description":"Stories about naughty characters have been told for centuries, and Horrid Henry is a modern-day rogue in the tradition of Dennis the Menace and Just William.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"}]}
{"id":179,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/179/","title":"Books by Nobel Laureates in Literature","list_description":"Celebrating the announcement of Mo Yan as 2012's Nobel Laureate in Literature, we thought we'd dig into our bookfinder archives and show you some books by previous Nobel Laureates.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31398/collected-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31398","title":"Collected Stories","author":"by Saul Bellow","description":"Bellow died in 2005; this collection of his shorter fiction is a worthy testament to his writing."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31062/disgrace.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31062","title":"Disgrace","author":"by J M Coetzee","description":"This examination into the sexual and politcal lawlines of modern South Africa as it tries desperately to start a fresh page in its history is chilling, uncompromising and unforgettable."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26708/hunger.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26708","title":"Hunger","author":"by Knut Hamsun","description":"Set in Oslo, Hunger is a compelling journey into the mind of a young writer who is driven by starvation to constantly fluctuating extremes of euphoria and despair."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31040/a-moveable-feast.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31040","title":"A Moveable Feast","author":"by Ernest Hemingway","description":"Hemingway's memories of his life as an unknown writer living in Paris in the 1920s are deeply personal, warmly affectionate and full of wit."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27772/plain-tales-from-the-hills.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27772","title":"Plain Tales from the Hills","author":"by Rudyard Kipling","description":"Kipling's early tales of the Raj were collected in this volume, his first published book, in 1888.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27542/collected-african-stories-volume-1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27542","title":"Collected African Stories Volume 1: This Was the Old Chief's Country","author":"by Doris Lessing","description":"Lessing explores the tensions between the white and black communities living side by side in early twentieth-century Africa in these 13 stories."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26197/love-in-the-time-of.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26197","title":"Love in the Time of Cholera","author":"by Gabriel García Marquez","description":"Florentino Ariza has never forgotten his first love. He has waited nearly a lifetime in silence since his beloved Fermina married another man. No woman can replace her in his heart."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30458/the-changeling.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30458","title":"The Changeling","author":"by Kenzaburo Oe","description":"The Changeling is the story of a famous novelist, Kogito, and how he keeps a connection alive with his film director friend, Goro, who has recently killed himself by jumping off a building in the city."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26457/snow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26457","title":"Snow","author":"by Orhan Pamuk","description":"Snow is a profoundly modern and universal novel, interested less in the real-life historical drama that forms the backdrop than in the emotional and moral dilemma of Jakob Torn"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31068/9780099448426-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31068","title":"Doctor Zhivago","author":"by Boris Pasternak","description":"Doctor Zhivago is the epic novel of Russia in the throes of revolution and one of the greatest love stories ever told."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30790/the-elephant-s-journey.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30790","title":"The Elephant's Journey","author":"by Jose Saramago","description":"In the 16th century, Soloman the elephant left his Indian homeland to become the resident pachyderm at King Dom João III's palace in Lisbon. However, two years later, the King decides to send Soloman as a wedding gift to his..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31066/ake.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31066","title":"Ake: The Years of Childhood","author":"by Wole Soyinka","description":"The first volume of Wole Soyinka's acclaimed series of autobiographical works. This vivid, exuberant book is the author's account of his childhood in colonial Nigeria.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27506/the-long-valley.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27506","title":"The Long Valley","author":"by John Steinbeck","description":"These stories are set in Steinbeck's birthplace, the rolling Salinas Valley in California. They explore the tensions between men and women, the individual and society, and humanity and the natural world."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31402/selected-short-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31402","title":"Selected Short Stories","author":"by Rabindranath Tagore","description":"Written during the 1890s, the stories in this selection brilliantly recreate vivid images of Bengali life and landscapes."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27575/9780413771193.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27575","title":"Shifu You'll Do Anything for a Laugh","author":"by Mo Yan","description":"Eight short stories, written over the past twenty years: surrealistic political fables, ghost stories, tales of failed and perverse love, and stories about the destructive effects of superstition and ignorance."}]}
{"id":180,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/180/","title":"Pori Drwy Stori autumn term booklist","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35094/erica-s-elephant.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35094","title":"Erica’s Elephant","author":"by Sylvia Bishop","description":"Erica is surprised to find an elephant on her doorstep. When she invites him in, a fantastic friendship begins. This short chapter book for young readers is a delight from start to finish.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35048/zim-zam-zoom-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35048","title":"Zim Zam Zoom!","author":"by James Carter","description":"An exciting, action-packed introduction to poetry for younger children. Perfect for reading out loud, at bedtime, playtime or at school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35187/vanilla-ice-cream.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35187","title":"Vanilla Ice Cream","author":"by Bob Graham","description":"A curious little sparrow travels from a dusty Indian truck stop to a vast southern city across the ocean. This endearing picture book about how lives are interconnected is accompanied by gentle pen, ink and watercolour illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35068/alphonse.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35068","title":"Alphonse, That Is Not OK To Do!","author":"by Daisy Hirst","description":"This charming and very funny book about the ups and downs of sibling relationships perfectly captures the affection and frustration experienced by an older sibling - and the monsters are wonderfully expressive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35041/footpath-flowers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35041","title":"Footpath Flowers","author":"by JonArno Lawson","description":"A little girl spreads joy and colour through the grey townscape, when she picks and presents flowers from the pavements to the people and animals she meets. This wordless picture book is a beauty to behold.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35170/the-colour-monster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35170","title":"The Colour Monster","author":"by Anna Llenas","description":"An original and entertaining picture book using colour, collage-effect illustrations and a delightfully cute monster to help youngsters identify and understand different emotions.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34999/this-is-not-a-bedtime-story.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34999","title":"This is Not a Bedtime Story","author":"by Will Mabbitt","description":"Bedtime stories go bonkers in this inventive, subversive version of a traditionally restful night-time tale. Funny illustrations accompany the witty text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35009/secret-railway.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35009","title":"The Secret Railway","author":"by Wendy Meddour","description":"A magical, thrilling and slightly scary ‘first chapter’ book featuring the adventures of a brother and sister who stumble into a hidden world. Tense, imaginative and highly recommended.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35151/a-guide-to-sisters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35151","title":"A Guide to Sisters","author":"by Paula Metcalf","description":"A big sister imparts her wisdom on all things to do with having a new little sister in this fun and playful picture book. Smart, funny text from Paula Metcalf is matched perfectly with cute line drawings from Suzanne Barton.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35166/under-earth-under-water.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35166","title":"Under Earth, Under Water","author":"by Aleksandra and David Mizielinski","description":"This gorgeous large hardback explores what happens under the earth and in our oceans and seas in fantastically colourful and accessible double-page spreads. This is a really excellent example of nonfiction that is both comprehensive and fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35070/can-i-eat-that.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35070","title":"Can I Eat That?","author":"by Joshua David Stein and Julia Rothman","description":"A quirky combination of fact and fun, this distinctive picture book about food poses questions that inquisitive children typically ask, such as: 'If I eat jelly and I eat fish, can I eat jellyfish?' Stylish, witty and informative.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35078/harold-s-hungry-eyes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35078","title":"Harold’s Hungry Eyes","author":"by Kevin Waldron","description":"Young readers will love this story of hungry Harold the dog, and have a great time spotting all the original places that food has replaced normal everyday items. Kevin Waldron's artwork is bright and colourful with a quirky, modern use...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35083/introducing-teddy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35083","title":"Introducing Teddy","author":"by Jessica Walton","description":"Errol starts to notice that his teddy bear Thomas seems sad - he has always known he is a girl teddy, but is worried that Errol will not want to play with him anymore. A rare but much-needed picture book...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"}]}
{"id":181,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/181/","title":"School Library Pack titles 2012","list_description":"Take a look at the titles in this year's school library pack. The free pack will provide secondary school libraries with books and resources to help staff create a reading culture that reaches all students, encouraging students to discuss what they are reading and join in activities such as reading groups.  Find out more about the School Library Pack.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27592/pigheart-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27592","title":"Pig Heart Boy","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Cameron desperately needs a new heart when he is offered the opportunity to take part in a radical and controversial experiment involving the transplant of a pig's heart.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25192/framed-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25192","title":"Framed","author":"by Frank Cottrell Boyce","description":"The story centres on Dylan Hughes, the only boy left in a small Welsh mountain town called Manod. This is an immensely entertaining book, about the power of art to bring about change and to redeem.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32521/a-midsummer-night-s-dream.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32521","title":"A Midsummer Night's Dream - Manga Shakespeare","author":"by Kate Brown","description":"Shakespeare's enduring story set in present-day Athens, but a present with a massive difference.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32665/9780857560490-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32665","title":"When it Snows","author":"by Richard Collingridge","description":"A little boy follows footprints in the snow until he finds a polar bear who leads him to the place where the snowmen live.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32518/how-to-make-a-universe.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32518","title":"How to Make a Universe from 92 Ingredients","author":"by Adrian Dingle","description":"A unique and imaginative take on chemistry, with 'experiments' that show how all things are made from just 92 chemical elements.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29125/the-graveyard-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29125","title":"The Graveyard Book","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"After his family are killed, Bod is brought up in a graveyard by ghosts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25813/orangesinnomansland.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25813","title":"Oranges in No Man's Land","author":"by Elizabeth Laird","description":"Ayesha and her young brothers find themselves refugees in a bombed out flat in Beirut with only an elderly grandmother to care for them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31514/9780230751934-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31514","title":"Phenomenal! The Small Book of Big Words","author":"by Jonathan Meres","description":"Improve your vocabulary and impress your friends with this entertaining introduction to big words","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27725/northernlights-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27725","title":"Northern Lights","author":"by Philip Pullman","description":"This extraordinary fantasy is the first book in Philip Pullman's multi-award-winning His Dark Materials trilogy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32517/the-worst-childrens-jobs-in-history.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32517","title":"The Worst Children's Jobs in History","author":"by Tony Robinson","description":"This book will tell you things you probably didn't want to know about the back-breaking realities of being a child in the past.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32520/super-animal-adventure-squad.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32520","title":"Super Animal Adventure Squad","author":"by James Turner","description":"Cutlasses, cookery and comedy capers abound in these two brilliantly funny stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30383/boffin-boy-ninja-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30383","title":"Boffin Boy and the Forest of the Ninja","author":"by David Orme","description":"This graphic novel style book is a quick read and perfect for those who don’t like too much text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":182,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/182/","title":"13 Halloween Reads","list_description":"Get into the mood for Halloween with 13 spooky, supernatural and spine-tingling stories. Both old favourites and new discoveries are included this list of some of our favourite scary books for dark and stormy nights.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31277/longlankin..jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31277","title":"Long Lankin","author":"by Lindsey Barraclough","description":"The isolated All Hallows church holds great terrors for Cora and Mimi and their new friends. Here the ghosts of children slain by Long Lankin appear. And now he's coming for Mimi...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30800/white-cat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30800","title":"White Cat","author":"by Holly Black","description":"Cassel Sharpe doesn't know who to trust - his mother is in prison; his grandfather is a black-fingered death-dealer and his brothers plan to use him to commit a murder.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12-16"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32458/the-divinersd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32458","title":"The Diviners","author":"by Libba Bray","description":"In this lively and atmospheric tale of 1920s New York, party girl Evie finds herself investigating a sinister string of occult murders.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30985/scarlett-dedd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30985","title":"Scarlett Dedd","author":"by Cathy Brett","description":"Scarlett is dead. Which sucks. She's stupidly gone and accidentally killed herself while trying to get out of a school trip.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32028/hollow-pike-juno-dawson.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32028","title":"Hollow Pike","author":"by Juno Dawson","description":"Lis London had hoped that a move to the country would allow her to escape not only the bullies but also her recurring nightmares","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32481/ghostknight.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32481","title":"Ghost Knight","author":"by Cornelia Funke","description":"At his new boarding school in Salisbury, Jon finds himself contronted by a terrifying and vengeful gang of ghosts that no one else can see.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29125/the-graveyard-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29125","title":"The Graveyard Book","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"After his family are killed, Bod is brought up in a graveyard by ghosts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32522/9781471400117-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32522","title":"Constable & Toop","author":"by Gareth P Jones","description":"A Victorian funeral parlour is the setting for this exciting mystery that blends comedy with the dark, spooky and supernatural.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30708/mortlock.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30708","title":"Mortlock","author":"by Jon Mayhew","description":"Orphaned twins Josie and Alfie, separated as babies, rediscover each other and set out on a quest for the truth of their past in this Victorian horror story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30377/talesofterror.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30377","title":"Uncle Montague's Tales of Terror","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"These spine-tingling stories-within-a-story are the stuff of childhood nightmares, with a good smattering of ghosts, demons, blood and gore.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32484/ravenboys.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32484","title":"The Raven Boys","author":"by Maggie Stiefvater","description":"Popular author Maggie Stiefvater is in top form in what is arguably her most complex and ambitious book to date, and the first in a magical new series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32553/9781471400131-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32553","title":"Under My Hat: Tales from the Cauldron","author":"by Jonathan Strahan","description":"What makes a witch? Despite the title, the stories in this imaginative collection suggest you might need more than just a pointy hat or a broomstick.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":183,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/183/","title":"Young adult crime","list_description":"With bestselling crime writers including John Grisham, Harlan Coben and James Patterson all turning to writing for a younger audience, young adult crime is being touted as 'the next big thing'. Here we share some of our favourite crime thrillers for teens and young adults.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32220/9780755393039-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32220","title":"Heart-Shaped Bruise","author":"by Tanya Byrne","description":"Lying forgotten on top of a wardrobe at the Archway Young Offenders institution is a notebook. Inside its pages, the notorious Emily Koll reveals the story she has refused to tell anyone, even her psychiatrist - the truth about the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24551/9781407138091-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24551","title":"Looking for JJ","author":"by Anne Cassidy","description":"When a 10-year-old girl kills her best friend, she is convicted of manslaughter and locked away. Seven years later she is released on licence with a new identity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32531/shelters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32531","title":"Shelter","author":"by Harlan Coben","description":"In the first young adult novel from bestselling crime author Harlan Coben, Mickey sets out to investigate the mysterious disappearence of his new girlfriend Ashley.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31982/theo-boone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31982","title":"Theodore Boone","author":"by John Grisham","description":"A cold-blooded killer is about to go free, and only Theo knows the truth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34675/long-halloween.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34675","title":"Batman: The Long Halloween","author":"by Loeb, Jeph","description":"Taking place during Batman's early days of crime fighting, The Long Halloween tells the story of a mysterious killer named Holiday, who murders people on holidays, one each month.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32523/crushers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32523","title":"Crusher","author":"by Niall Leonard","description":"When Finn Maguire finds his father brutally murdered, he sets out to discover who was behind the crime, taking him on a dangerous journey into London's criminal underworld.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32404/9780857072894-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32404","title":"Sister, Missing","author":"by Sophie McKenzie","description":"Sister, Missing is the second book in McKenzie’s projected trilogy about three siblings who share a common birth mother, but a complex extended family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":184,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/184/","title":"Tymor yr Hydref rhestr llyfrau'r","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32529/wedi-dy-weld-di.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32529","title":"Wedi dy Weld Di!","author":"by Hayley Acreman","description":"A Welsh and a bilingual version of a book about a rabbit and a duck as they prance around the country.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32528/y-tri-mochyn-bach.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32528","title":"Y Tri Mochyn Bach","author":"by Susanna Davidson","description":"The Three Little Pigs (Welsh language). The three little pigs have set off to build homes of their own. Little do they know, a big bad wolf is right behind them! Adapted into Welsh by Elinor Wyn Reynolds.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7-9","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32526/straeon-dau-funud.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32526","title":"Straeon Dau Funud","author":"by Gill Guile","description":"A treasury of 24 delightful short stories which are perfect for bed-time reading"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32525/deg-plentyn-bychan.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32525","title":"Deg Plentyn Bychan","author":"by Rose Impey","description":"A bilingual book - Ten Little Babies."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32527/hugan-fach-goch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32527","title":"Hugan Fach Goch a'r Blaidd Bach Annwyl!","author":"by Rachael Mortimer","description":"Red Riding Hood and the Sweet Little Wolf (Welsh)"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32655/hwyl-gyda-cyw.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32655","title":"Hwyl gyda Cyw a'i Ffrindiau","author":"by Cwmni Recordiau Sain","description":"The S4C children's character Cyw, is back with a book full of stories, quizzes, games, stickers and a DVD with some of Cyw's favourite songs."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32552/coblyn.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32552","title":"Pobl Pentre Bach: Coblyn o Broblem!","author":"by Ifana Savill","description":"A story based on the characters who live in Pentre Bach. Coblyn gets up early every morning and looks forward to his boiled egg. But one morning, there is no egg!"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32530/sali-mali.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32530","title":"Sali Mali a'r Hwdi Chwim","author":"by Dylan Williams","description":"A thief steals Sali Mali's iPod as she exercises in the park (Welsh).","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":185,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/185/","title":"Winter booklist","list_description":"Perfect books for cosy winter days...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32676/the-black-cat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32676","title":"Funnybones: The Black Cat","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"Another Funnybones adventure. This time, the skeleton friends go sledging - whee!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33399/joly-christmas-postman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33399","title":"The Jolly Christmas Postman","author":"by Janet & Allan Ahlberg","description":"Follow our favourite jolly postman as he delivers Christmas cards and gifts to fairytale folk","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34733/9781408859148.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34733","title":"Robin's Winter Song","author":"by Suzanne Barton","description":"A beautifully illustrated story about the changing seasons.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29103/the-snowman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29103","title":"The Snowman","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"James builds a snowman in the garden, then wakes up in the night to find that it has come to life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31881/9780140501872-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31881","title":"Father Christmas Goes on Holiday","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"Raymond Briggs' classic comic book has all of his trademark humour and an endearingly grumpy Father Christmas","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32656/9780141336251-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32656","title":"The Empty Stocking","author":"by Richard Curtis","description":"Award-winning writer and director Richard Curtis turns his hand to picture books in this magical festive story, beautifully illustrated by Rebecca Cobb","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28211/angelinasxmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28211","title":"Angelina's Christmas","author":"by Katharine Holabird","description":"Beautifully epitomises the real spirit of christmas","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34755/9781782955504.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34755","title":"Lucy and Tom At Christmas","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"A classic and heart-warming story about the excitement of Christmas, with many evocative illustrations to talk about.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34731/9781848691414.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34731","title":"Waiting for Santa","author":"by Steve Metzger","description":"On Christmas Eve, Bear is confident that Santa Claus will visit him and his forest friends. Santa just needs a little help to find them. This gentle picture book reminds readers that Christmas is a time for believing in all...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25896/1stxmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25896","title":"The First Christmas","author":"by Jan Pienkowski","description":"Jan Pienkowski's silhouette illustrations lend an air of mystery and drama to this text, taken from the King James Bible.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34746/9781408849491.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34746","title":"Santa Baby","author":"by Smitri Prasadam-Halls","description":"Having been told they're too young to join Santa on Christmas Eve, Santa Baby and Roo discover two presents left behind and decide to chase Santa round the globe. This exciting Christmas adventure story is jam-packed with colour and rhyme.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-8"}]}
{"id":186,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/186/","title":"The horror, the horror","list_description":"Quench your bloodthirst and get your teeth into these books for Halloween.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31719/9780141332048-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31719","title":"The True Tale of the Monster Billy Dean telt by hisself","author":"by David Almond","description":"Complex and difficult issues are reflected in both narrative style and content.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32461/9780224089081.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32461","title":"Adamtine","author":"by Hannah Berry","description":"Four strangers are on the last train home when it is mysteriously derailed. As they all try to find out what's going on, we find out the thing that connects them all, which may be lurking outside the train.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27566/9780192804471.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27566","title":"The Oxford Book of Victorian Ghost Stories","author":"by Michael Cox","description":"This anthology charts the development of the ghost story from 1850 to the early years of the twentieth century."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31121/visitation.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31121","title":"Visitation","author":"by Jenny Erpenbeck","description":"Visitation takes place in a chillingly spooky house. The stories that surround the house and Visitation build a history of horror, taking in the German population during the Jahrhundertwende, the turn-of-the-century shift, and over the following decades of war, National..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29125/the-graveyard-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29125","title":"The Graveyard Book","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"After his family are killed, Bod is brought up in a graveyard by ghosts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31184/lettheright1in.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31184","title":"Let the Right One In","author":"by John Ajvide Lindqvist","description":"John Ajvide Lindqvist's novel is a unique and brilliant fusion of social novel and vampire legend, and a deeply moving fable about rejection, friendship and loyalty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31309/amonstercallsss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31309","title":"A Monster Calls","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"Connor's mum has cancer and life is changing. There is the nightmare, then there is school, where people avoid him, or persecute him. And then there is the immense, mythic Monster.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34080/glass-children.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34080","title":"The Glass Children","author":"by Kristina Ohlsson","description":"After the death of her father, Billie and her mum are moving to a new town for a fresh start. But the house - or somebody in it - is trying to drive them out.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31603/cf1619cd-5338-4070-bf03-3592fc66617e-img100-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31603","title":"The Little Stranger","author":"by Sarah Waters","description":"After her award-winning trilogy of Victorian novels, Sarah Waters turned to the 1940s and wrote The Night Watch, a tender and tragic novel set against the backdrop of wartime Britain. Shortlisted for both the Orange and the Man Booker, it..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31126/villain.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31126","title":"Villain","author":"by Shuichi Yoshida","description":"Villain, the first novel by Shuichi Yoshida to be translated into English, is the story of a murder: a tale of desperation set in desolate seaside towns, online chat rooms and love hotels."}]}
{"id":187,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/187/","title":"Books about World War I","list_description":"These books about World War I will offer young readers a range of different perspectives on the conflict.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32421/9781447220053-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32421","title":"Soldier Dog","author":"by Sam Angus","description":"It's 1917 and Stanley Ryder is one of many young boys enlisting in the army, in spite of the fact he is underage. Assigned to working with messenger dogs, he is drafted to the Western Front.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33473/5.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33473","title":"Stay Where You Are and Then Leave","author":"by John Boyne","description":"This is a compelling story, beautifully observed, which covers difficult themes such as shellshock and loss in a sensitive and understanding way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33770/my-brothers-keeper.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33770","title":"My Brother's Keeper","author":"by Tom and Tony Bradman","description":"Alfie's story has obvious subject appeal for boys and the length is enticing for reluctant readers, but this neat little story manages to be both thought-provoking and moving, and in the barrage of solider stories coming out this year this...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33671/stories-of-ww1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33671","title":"Stories of WW1","author":"by Tony Bradman","description":"Poignantly bringing the First World War alive for teenagers, this anthology reminds us that many of those in the trenches were themselves no older.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31103/war-game.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31103","title":"War Game","author":"by Michael Foreman","description":"This simple yet haunting book tells the story of the First World War from the point of view of the writer’s uncles who lost their lives in the conflict.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25836/the-silver-donkey.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25836","title":"The Silver Donkey","author":"by Sonya Hartnett","description":"In French woodland, sisters Coco and Marcelle find and help a blind English deserter from the battlefront, trying to ensure he reaches home. In return, he tells them marvellous tales...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34671/9781781124260.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34671","title":"Respect","author":"by Michaela Morgan","description":"Find out about Walter Tull - a hero on the football pitch and during World War One.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24556/war-horse.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24556","title":"War Horse","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Steven Spielberg enjoyed this story so much he has turned it into his latest film. Joey is a young farm horse, sold to the army at the beginning of the First World War. Through his eyes the reader experiences the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24585/private-peaceful.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24585","title":"Private Peaceful","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Set during World War I, Private Peaceful charts eight hours in the life of Tommo, a young soldier at the Front.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25360/some-otherwar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25360","title":"Some Other War","author":"by Linda Newbery","description":"Seventeen-year-old twins Alice and Jack work at the mansion of the Morland family - but when the First World War breaks out, their lives are changed completely.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12-15"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33789/dear-jelly.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33789","title":"Dear Jelly: Family Letters from the First World War","author":"by Sarah Ridley","description":"Accompanied by historical notes on the progress of the war, this book is an accessible resource and an appealing read. It is also a moving story, as neither of the brothers returned home alive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25812/foreshadowing-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25812","title":"The Foreshadowing","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"17-year-old Sasha travels to France as a volunteer nurse in an attempt to rescue her beloved brother Tom from a terrible death. But can she really change the future?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33701/valentine-joe.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33701","title":"Valentine Joe","author":"by Rebecca Stevens","description":"Based on a true story, Valentine Joe offers an intriguing insight into the war, but at the same time provides a window into Rose's relationship with her family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33980/secret-message.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33980","title":"The Secret Message","author":"by John Townsend","description":"This short novel tells the story of Sam, who discovers the diary which his great-great-grandfather wrote during World War I. One of a new series of 'Cold Fusion' books suited to more able readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31151/archieswar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31151","title":"Archie's War","author":"by Marcia Williams","description":"In 1914, ten-year-old Archie is sent a scrapbook in the post by his Uncle Colin, and through the years that follow, we see the world through Archie's eyes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33787/tillys-promise.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33787","title":"Tilly's Promise","author":"by Linda Newbery","description":"A touching story by award-winning Linda Newbery about first love, loyalty and the horrors of war, written in dyslexia-friendly language.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":188,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/188/","title":"Books about World War II","list_description":"From classic favourites to more recent titles, these books for children and teenagers take a variety of different approaches to representing the events of World War II.  Read our list of children's books about the Holocaust ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33770/my-brothers-keeper.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33770","title":"My Brother's Keeper","author":"by Tom and Tony Bradman","description":"Alfie's story has obvious subject appeal for boys and the length is enticing for reluctant readers, but this neat little story manages to be both thought-provoking and moving, and in the barrage of solider stories coming out this year this...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29432/auslander.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29432","title":"Ausländer","author":"by Paul Dowswell","description":"Ausländer gives a fascinating insight into life in Berlin during WorldWar II – a perspective not frequently portrayed in young adult fiction.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32268/9781407124612-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32268","title":"The Messenger Bird","author":"by Ruth Eastham","description":"The Messenger Bird is an exciting adventure story with a twist, and will be particularly enjoyed by anyone who is interested in history and the Second World War.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25454/once.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25454","title":"Once","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"Morris Gleitzman brings heart and humour to the difficult subject of the Holocaust in this ground-breaking children's book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32144/9780141332192-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32144","title":"Duty Calls: Dunkirk","author":"by James Holland","description":"The exciting story of a teenage recruit who finds himself caught up in the evacuation of troops from Dunkirk in 1940.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32560/9780141332208-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32560","title":"Duty Calls: Battle of Britain","author":"by James Holland","description":"It's the Battle of Britain and 19-year-old pilot officer Archie Jackson is in control of the RAF's newest fighter aircraft, a Supermarine Spitfire.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32292/9781406336108.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32292","title":"Hero on a Bicycle","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"The first novel from much-loved author and illustrator Shirley Hughes is a thrilling and moving story about a boy and his bicycle, set against a dramatic background of war-torn Italy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31956/9780007274772-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31956","title":"When Hitler Stole Pink Rabbit","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Partly autobiographical, this is first of the internationally acclaimed trilogy by Judith Kerr telling the unforgettable story of a Jewish family fleeing from Germany at the start of the World War II."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30275/goodnight-mr-tom.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30275","title":"Goodnight Mister Tom","author":"by Michelle Magorian","description":"Willie Beech, a lonely and deprived child, is evacuated to a tiny English village just before the Second World War, and finds himself living with reclusive widower Thomas Oakley.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29042/9781847800756-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29042","title":"Tail-end Charlie","author":"by Mick Manning","description":"Mick Manning has carefully recreated the hair-raising tales his father told him about life as an RAF tail-gunner during the Second World War","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31241/taff-in-the-waaf.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31241","title":"Taff in the WAAF","author":"by Mick Manning and Brita Granstrom","description":"An account of the secret work carried out during WWII at Bletchley Park, based on the experience of Manning's own mother, Taff.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32330/9781908435088-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32330","title":"Hitler's Angel","author":"by William Osborne","description":"In the summer of 1941, two displaced teenagers, one German, one Austrian, are recruited by the British government for a secret mission.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26527/anne-frank.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26527","title":"Anne Frank","author":"by Josephine Poole","description":"This account of the Nazi persecution of the Jews and Anne Frank's family's hiding in a secret annexe to escape them, is sensitively told.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31987/betweenshadesofgrey.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31987","title":"Between Shades of Gray","author":"by Ruta Sepetys","description":"Set in 1941, Between Shades of Grey is an extraordinary and haunting story based on first-hand family accounts and memories from survivors.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25800/9780099572855-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25800","title":"The Silver Sword","author":"by Ian Serrailier","description":"In the chaos of World War II, Ruth, Edek and Bronia are separated from their parents, and left alone to fend for themselves, hiding from the Nazis in the ruins of their city.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25136/hitler-s-canary.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25136","title":"Hitler's Canary","author":"by Sandi Toksvig","description":"Hitler's Canary, ultimately, is about the courage and heroism of ordinary citizens in a time of danger and strife.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31986/code-name-verityv.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31986","title":"Code Name Verity","author":"by Elizabeth Wein","description":"Two young women become unlikely best friends during WWII, until one is captured by the Gestapo...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29157/secretwardiary.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29157","title":"My Secret War Diary, by Flossie Albright","author":"by Marcia Williams","description":"Following Archie's War, which recorded in diary form the First World War home-front experience of a ten year old, Williams now turns to Archie's daughter, Flossie Albright.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":189,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/189/","title":"Dark romance","list_description":"Seen the final Twilight film and feeling bereft? Fear not - the books on our list will help you fill the Twilight-shaped hole in your life. Taking a range of different approaches to the dark romance genre, these are all compelling novels combining love and passion with supernatural mystery.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31307/starcrossed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31307","title":"Starcrossed","author":"by Josephine Angelini","description":"When the beautiful and mysterious Delos family arrive on Nantucket Island, Helen Hamilton's teenaged life is turned upside down.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32286/shadow-and-bonev.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32286","title":"Shadow and Bone","author":"by Leigh Bardugo","description":"In this richly-imagined and beautifully-written novel, Leigh Bardugo has created a vivid fantasy world drawing on Russian traditions and folklore","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25216/9780689875359-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25216","title":"A Great And Terrible Beauty","author":"by Libba Bray","description":"Gemma Doyle struggles to deal with her strange supernatural powers in this first installment of Libba Bray's series set in Victorian England.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32458/the-divinersd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32458","title":"The Diviners","author":"by Libba Bray","description":"In this lively and atmospheric tale of 1920s New York, party girl Evie finds herself investigating a sinister string of occult murders.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26633/city-ofbones.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26633","title":"City of Bones","author":"by Cassandra Clare","description":"When Clary visits a nightclub, she discovers that she is one of the Shadowhunters - a group of demon-hunters living in a world of vampires, werewolves and warlocks.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29694/the-splendour-falls.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29694","title":"The Splendour Falls","author":"by Rosemary Clement-Moore","description":"Sylvie's future as a star ballet dancer is mapped out, but her dreams are shattered when she breaks her leg.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32357/9780552563772-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32357","title":"Blood Magic","author":"by Tessa Gratton","description":"Silla's father murdered her mother and then killed himself. She is convinced her father was not evil, but what could have led him to commit such an act? A mysterious spell book may provide the answers Silla seeks.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30874/fallen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30874","title":"Fallen","author":"by Lauren Kate","description":"Luce has been falsely implicated in the mysterious death of a school friend, and much to her despair, has been sent to reform school. But one student, Daniel, seems curiously familiar.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32378/9781471400025-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32378","title":"Angel Dust","author":"by Sarah Mussi","description":"Serafina is one of the brightest and most beloved of all God's angels - until she is sent down to earth to collect the soul of Marcus Montague, and deliver him to Hell.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31681/9780330512855-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31681","title":"The Immortals: Evermore","author":"by Alyson Noel","description":"In the first book of The Immortals series, find out what Ever will do after discovering she can read auras and hear thoughts","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32290/9781447206804-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32290","title":"The Soul Seekers: Fated","author":"by Alyson Noel","description":"Fans of The Immortals will not be disappointed by this, the first in a new series by Alyson Noel, which offers readers plenty of romance, excitement and mystery","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32291/9781408815229-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32291","title":"Burn Mark","author":"by Laura Powell","description":"This supernatural thriller is set in an alternate modern day London in which witchcraft exists, but those who have 'the fae' have become a mistrusted, persecuted underclass.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29550/shiver..jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29550","title":"Shiver","author":"by Maggie Stiefvater","description":"Set in small-town Minnesota, Stiefvater’s moving and poetic novel of human/wolf interaction and relationships is a werewolf story like no other.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30964/angel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30964","title":"Angel","author":"by LA Weatherly","description":"A thriller with a difference, this riveting read explores the conflicting emotions felt by two young people who know that only by risking their lives can they save the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":190,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/190/","title":"Cold weather, cold books","list_description":"Well, the weather outside IS frightful. And the nights are drawing in. Gone are the days of flip-flops and shorts. The scarves and gloves are out of storage. The big coat is on the back of your chair. If we're staying in and enjoying the warmth, what better way to curl up with these brrrrrrrr-illiantly cold books.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31351/half-blood-blues.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31351","title":"Half-Blood Blues","author":"by Esi Edugyan","description":"Enthralling, vividly written and entirely believable, this is a striking and accomplished novel from Canadian-based Edugyan. Her achievement is to have created a strong, unique voice in protagonist Sid, a bass player in a jazz band in 1930s Berlin."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25940/i-could-ride-all-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25940","title":"I Could Ride All Day in My Cool Blue Train","author":"by Peter Hobbs","description":"I Could Ride All Day … highlights the diversity and sheer excitement of Hobbs's writing. It also proves that well-written short stories are more than a match for their longer and flabbier cousin, the novel."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32179/snow-child.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32179","title":"The Snow Child","author":"by Eowyn Ivey","description":"The tough existence of frontier life is detailed without sentiment by Ivey, but with a bracing beauty in the tradition of the Russian fairytale it references."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29616/blue-heaven.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29616","title":"Blue Heaven","author":"by Joe Keenan","description":"Written by one of the head writers of Frasier, this novel relocates Wodehouse/Evelyn Waugh-style hijinks to upper-class Manhattan homes, featuring an ebullient cast of loud and proud characters all scheming and scamming to get what they want."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32087/9780224091404.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32087","title":"The Blue Book","author":"by A L Kennedy","description":"Elizabeth Barber is crossing the Atlantic by liner with her perfectly adequate boyfriend, Derek, who might be planning to propose. In fleeing the UK - temporarily - Elizabeth may also be in flight from her past and the charismatic Arthur,..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30916/snowdrops.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30916","title":"Snowdrops","author":"by A D Miller","description":"Snowdrops is a taut, lean, icily involving novel that is as sharp as an arctic blast. Full of palpable danger, moral ambiguity and with a tense, suspense plot, this is a debut novel of rare power and conviction."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26457/snow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26457","title":"Snow","author":"by Orhan Pamuk","description":"Snow is a profoundly modern and universal novel, interested less in the real-life historical drama that forms the backdrop than in the emotional and moral dilemma of Jakob Torn"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29700/tail-of-the-blue-bird.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29700","title":"Tail of the Blue Bird","author":"by Nii Ayikwei Parkes","description":"Nii Ayikwei Parkes' debut novel is a poetic, dreamy story about the influx of technology and modernity into rural Ghana, and the uneasy relationship between science and spirit.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31367/annabel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31367","title":"Annabel","author":"by Kathleen Winter","description":"In Annabel, Kathleen Winter has written a compelling and convincing debut novel that reads almost as a modern myth – a myth based on the taboo reality of intersexuality."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31124/dark-matter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31124","title":"Dark Matter","author":"by Juli Zeh","description":"Sebastian and Oskar have been friends since their days studying physics at university, when both were considered future Nobel Prize candidates. But their lives took divergent paths, as did their scientific views. Whenever Oskar comes to visit from his prestigious..."}]}
{"id":193,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/193/","title":"Festive Books for Children","list_description":"These festive, winter-themed books will make wonderful gifts for children this Christmas. Take a look at our list of great books to give to teens and young adults this year ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32677/9780857550484-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32677","title":"The Winter Sleepwalker and Other Stories","author":"by Joan Aiken","description":"This beautiful book brings together a selection of unusual and whimsical fairy-tales by classic children's author Joan Aiken, perfectly illustrated by Quentin Blake.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32667/9781408834244-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32667","title":"The Snow Womble","author":"by Elizabeth Beresford","description":"With a story taken from Elizabeth Beresford's first book, this picture book will bring favourite characters the Wombles to a new young audience.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33314/snowflakes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33314","title":"Snowflakes","author":"by Cerrie Burnell","description":"Mia has left the noisy city behind, and come to live with her Grandma in a land of forest and snow.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32665/9780857560490-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32665","title":"When it Snows","author":"by Richard Collingridge","description":"A little boy follows footprints in the snow until he finds a polar bear who leads him to the place where the snowmen live.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32485/wolfprincess.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32485","title":"The Wolf Princess","author":"by Cathryn Constable","description":"Lost on a school trip to Russia, Sophie and her friends are rescued by the beautiful Princess Anna Volonskaya, who whisks them away to her crumbling yet magnificent Winter Palace.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32659/9781406331042-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32659","title":"Happy Christmas Maisy","author":"by Lucy Cousins","description":"Christmas is coming and Maisy is enjoying all the preparations: buying presents for her friends, baking a Christmas cake, and decorating the tree.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32663/9780192793096-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32663","title":"The Christmas Unicorn","author":"by Anna Currey","description":"Milly is awakened in the night by a beautiful unicorn who helps to create a magical Christmas for her family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32656/9780141336251-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32656","title":"The Empty Stocking","author":"by Richard Curtis","description":"Award-winning writer and director Richard Curtis turns his hand to picture books in this magical festive story, beautifully illustrated by Rebecca Cobb","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33422/9781408196908-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33422","title":"Winter's Tales","author":"by Lari Don","description":"How did the boy known as the Prince of Wolves get his name? Where did tinsel come from? How did Lars and the snow bear get rid of Christmas trolls? Find out in this unusual collection.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32639/9781849417792-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32639","title":"The Dinosaur that Pooped Christmas","author":"by Tom Fletcher and Dougie Poynter","description":"Danny is greedy and spoilt - he already has so many toys there is no space in his room. When he sends Santa a long list for Christmas, St Nick decides to teach him a lesson.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32672/9781849393348-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32672","title":"The Snow Merchant","author":"by Sam Gayton","description":"Lettie Peppercorn hasn't left her house-on-stilts for ten years. Then a mysterious frozen man arrives at her door, and her life is changed forever.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32661/9781406337402-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32661","title":"Charley's First Night","author":"by Amy Hest","description":"On his first night at home, Charley the puppy is given a guided tour by his new owner, Henry.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32674/9781780878362-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32674","title":"Lost Christmas","author":"by David Logan","description":"Goose is lost until Anthony appears - a man who knows nothing about himself but sees and feels the secret pain of all those who shake his hand","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33411/9781909263130-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33411","title":"A Letter for Bear","author":"by David Lucas","description":"Bear works very hard, delivering post to all the animals in the wood - but he never receives any letters himself.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32687/9780857384287-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32687","title":"Winterling","author":"by Sarah Prineas","description":"Fer finds herself in a dangerous and enchanting new world in this magical adventure story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32657/9781407115894-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32657","title":"Fancy Dress Christmas","author":"by Nick Sharratt","description":"Today is the Christmas Party, and all the animals have come in fancy dress!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32668/9781408829059-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32668","title":"