/29356","title":"Mr Pusskins Colours","author":"by Sam Lloyd","description":"A great introduction to colours, simple stories and relationships – all in twelve pages!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24785/elmer-snake.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24785","title":"Elmer and Snake","author":"by David McKee","description":"A group of mischievous elephants decide to play a trick on Elmer, the famous multicolour patchwork elephant, so they ask Snake for help.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33824/elmers-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33824","title":"Elmer's Day","author":"by David McKee","description":"What does the world's favourite patchwork elephant do all day?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6months+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33843/mouse-is-small.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33843","title":"Mouse is Small","author":"by Mary Murphy","description":"A colourful picture book about animal sizes"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34227/quick-duck-mary-murphy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34227","title":"Quick Duck!","author":"by Mary Murphy","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24971/doing-the-animal-bop.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24971","title":"Doing the Animal Bop","author":"by Jan Ormerod","description":"Children will enjoy matching the rhythmic text to the animals actions, and joining in with the dancing themselves. A great book for sharing and one that children are sure to want to hear over and over again!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33923/9781846557811.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33923","title":"I Refuse","author":"by Per Petterson","description":"With quiet drama, Petterson tells the story of two young teenagers: Tommy and Jim. Despite their different backgrounds, they develop a friendship which is deeply sincere. However, as the two grow up together Jim’s struggles cause a separation which the..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33823/this-rabbit-that-rabbit.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33823","title":"this rabbit, that rabbit","author":"by Jane Porter","description":"Shiny pictures to touch and funny rhymes to make little ones laugh"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28470/harris-finds-his-feet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28470","title":"Harris Finds His Feet","author":"by Catherine Rayner","description":"Harris leaps joyfully across the pages, against vibrant washes of colour, as he learns to be independent for the first time.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29476/ernest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29476","title":"Ernest","author":"by Catherine Rayner","description":"Ernest’s huge, friendly face fills up the spreads of this gorgeously illustrated book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34366/axel-scheffler-rhyming-stories-part1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34366","title":"Axel Scheffler Rhyming Stories Book 1: Pip the Dog and Freddy the Frog","author":"by Axel Scheffler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34535/one-fluffy-baa-lamb.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34535","title":"One Fluffy Baa Lamb, Ten Hairy Caterpillars","author":"by Nick Sharratt","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33826/whose-nose-tail-toes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33826","title":"Whose Nose and Tail and Toes are Those?","author":"by Nick Sharratt and Sally Symes","description":"Lift the flaps to find a range of brightly illustrated animals."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34226/big-and-small.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34226","title":"Big and Small","author":"by Britta Teckentrup","description":"Explore the natural world with this brightly illustrated board book","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27294/banana.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27294","title":"Banana!","author":"by Ed Vere","description":"Follow the cartoon-style adventures of two monkeys. One of them has a banana and the other one wants it - but what is the magic word?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30469/9781409518990-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30469","title":"That's Not My Tiger...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"Small children will love touching the tiger’s fluffy ears, soft paws and bumpy teeth and will particularly like tracing his soft, stripy tail on the very last page.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29699/9781862306523-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29699","title":"One Smart Fish","author":"by Chris Wormell","description":"A small silver fish has done everything he can possibly do in the ocean - he sings, dances and even performs plays, but has never walked upon the land.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33216/crocodilewhodidnt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33216","title":"The Crocodile Who Didn't Like Water","author":"by Gemma Merino","description":"Little crocodile doesn't like water. It's cold. It's wet. It's embarrassing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34177/hello-animals.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34177","title":"Hello, Animals!","author":"by Smriti Prasadam and Emily Bolam","description":"Simple, friendly and engaging board book for babies","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":199,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/199/","title":"Pori Drwy Stori spring term booklist","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35216/mira-forecasts-the-future.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35216","title":"Mira Forecasts the Future","author":"by Kell Andrews","description":"A deceptively simple picture book about understanding the weather that also explores ideas about success, failure and discovering individual talents.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35362/king-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35362","title":"King Baby","author":"by Kate Beaton","description":"King Baby bestows 'smiles and laughs and kisses' on everyone, for King Baby is generous. But he also has many demands: he must be fed. And changed! And burped! King Baby will have you in stitches. Buy it for every...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35246/ada-twist-scientist.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35246","title":"Ada Twist, Scientist","author":"by Andrea Beaty","description":"A brilliant and beautiful rhyming book about supporting your child's curiosity, and taking inspiration from Ada Lovelace (the pioneer mathematician and programmer), this is an inspirational and entertaining read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35227/return.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35227","title":"Return","author":"by Aaron Becker","description":"A lonely little girl can't distract her hardworking dad, so she takes her amazing red pen and draws herself into an adventure. This imaginative, fantastical escapade is wordless, but overflows with creativity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0 (as there are no words)","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35333/9780007594153.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35333","title":"Odd Dog Out","author":"by Rob Biddulph","description":"All the dogs at the beginning of this book look and act the same, but one is behaving differently. When they fly high, this dog flies low. When they say kick, this dog says throw!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35327/9781405283403.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35327","title":"Insect Emporium","author":"by Susie Brooks","description":"This stunning non-fiction picture book is a fabulous exploration of the insect world for young children. As well as looking at familiar creatures, such as bees, ladybirds and ants, it also features other more unusual specimens, including fireflies, stick insects...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35248/a-day-with-dogs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35248","title":"A Day With Dogs","author":"by Dorothee de Monfreid","description":"What do dogs do all day? A fantastically fun naming and classification-style book, A Day With Dogs will appeal to little ones that like to list and name different types of things - be it dogs, trains or elements of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35379/spinderella.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35379","title":"Spinderella","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Spinderella is a spider who lives with her spider mum and brothers and sisters on top of a ceiling light at a school. A story about numbers, football and family, Spinderella is an enjoyable read for young children just starting...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35359/hello-mr-dodo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35359","title":"Hello, Mr Dodo!","author":"by Nicholas John Frith","description":"Martha loves birds, but she can't believe her eyes when she discovers the rarest bird of them all in the woods behind her house. It's a real life Dodo! Retro illustration and technicolour splashes make this picture book a beautiful...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35290/the-star-tree.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35290","title":"The Star Tree","author":"by Catherine Hyde","description":"It is midnight at midsummer, and little Mia is awake. When the Great White Owl comes to the window and sings to her, it is the start of many magical journeys. A beautifully atmospheric book and a perfect bedtime read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35325/9781927271872.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35325","title":"Yours Sincerely, Giraffe","author":"by Megumi Iwasa","description":"Giraffe, who lives on the African savanna, is bored and lonely so decides to send a letter to an unknown animal on the other side of the horizon. The letter ends up with an inquisitive penguin who is studying at...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35328/9781847808905.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35328","title":"Little People, Big Dreams: Maya Angelou","author":"by Lisbeth Kaiser","description":"This inspiring biography for young readers focusses on writer, speaker and civil rights activist Maya Angelou.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35209/the-invincible-tony-spears.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35209","title":"The Invincible Tony Spears","author":"by Neal Layton","description":"After Tony moves house, the kitchen in his new place turns into a spaceship called The Invincible. Amid all the zaniness, there's an important message tucked in here about just trying your best.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35263/ludwig-the-space-dog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35263","title":"Ludwig the Space Dog","author":"by Henning Löhlein","description":"Perfect for young explorers, this endearing story features an adventurous dog who decides to visit the universe beyond the flat pages of his home - and 3D goggles will give the reader an even sharper focus on Ludwig's wonderful world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35206/don-t-cross-the-line2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35206","title":"Don’t Cross the Line","author":"by Isabel Minhos Martins and Bernardo P. Carvalho","description":"Little anarchists will love Don't Cross the Line, with its message that authority figures aren't always right. This colourful book is likely to make the whole family chortle.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3-6","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35383/by-the-light-of-the-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35383","title":"By the Light of the Moon","author":"by Tom Percival","description":"A reassuringly simple yet enchanting story, brought to life with appealing illustrations, to allay children's worries about moving house and creating a home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35380/there-s-a-snake-in-my-school-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35380","title":"There’s a Snake in my School!","author":"by David Walliams","description":"It's bring-your-pet-to-school-day and Miranda has brought her pet python, who is brilliant fun and entertains the children by turning herself into a climbing frame, a fireman's pole and the numbers one to nine. Riotous and with just enough yuckiness.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"}]}
{"id":200,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/200/","title":"Tymor y Gwanwyn rhestr llyfrau'r","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30417/don-t-want-to-go.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30417","title":"Don't want to go!","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Lily's mum is in bed with flu and dad has to go to work, so Lily must spend the day at Melanie's house. She doesn't want to go, but she soon has fun playing with Ringo the dog.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28193/big-blue-train.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28193","title":"Big Blue Train","author":"by Julia Jarman","description":"After an earlier adventure with a Big Red Bath, Jarman and Reynolds send Ben and Bella on another imaginary adventure - a train journey to the seaside for a party.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32765/bethsydd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32765","title":"Beth sydd o dan y Gwely?","author":"by Mick Manning, Brita Granström","description":"A Welsh adaptation of What's Under the Bed?, a colourful story book presenting valuable information about the earth, by following the adventures of two children and their cat underground to examine hidden caves, fossils and even silver, gold and diamonds...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32764/paid-el.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32764","title":"Paid Eliffant Paid","author":"by Andrea Shavick","description":"A Welsh adaptation of Stop, Elephant, Stop!, a tropical story with bright colour illustrations and flip-flap pages depicting a crew of jungle animals as they try to keep themselves cool on a hot summer day.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31479/harry-and-the-dinosours-go-to-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31479","title":"Harry and the Dinosaurs go to School","author":"by Ian Whybrow","description":"It's Harry's first day at school. He and his dinosaurs are very excited and perhaps a little bit nervous.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29297/the-bog-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29297","title":"The Bog Baby","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Two little girls go walking in bluebell wood and rescue a Bog Baby.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"}]}
{"id":201,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/201/","title":"Our favourite children's book apps","list_description":"We take a look back over some of the best book apps and ebooks for children and teenagers released in 2012.  Find out about our favourite children's book apps from 2011","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32773/moomin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32773","title":"The Book about Moomin, Mymble and Little My (app)","author":"by Tove Jansson","description":"Tove Jansson’s original picture book from 1952 has been transformed into a beautiful interactive story in this iPad app.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":202,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/202/","title":"Debut novels","list_description":"New year, new books to read... but what of the new novelists, the debuts that come out every year? That's why we've put together a list of some of our favourite debut novels of the last few years. Enjoy these writers at the very start of their career because each one of them will be going on to bigger things. Some of them already have.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32049/9781447207658.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32049","title":"Hope: A Tragedy","author":"by Shalom Auslander","description":"Hilarious and gruesome by turns, Auslander's excursion into the mind of a dedicated paranoiac and self-obsessed neurotic fully merits an award for Book of the Year"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31185/submarine-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31185","title":"Submarine","author":"by Joe Dunthorne","description":"Meet Oliver Tate, 15. Convinced that his father is depressed ('Depression comes in bouts. Like boxing. Dad is in the blue corner') and his mother is having an affair with her capoeira teacher.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34617/414thufymtl._sx322_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34617","title":"Whispers Through a Megaphone","author":"by Rachel Elliott","description":"A look at what happens with relationships when people spend more time online than they do in the real world."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34238/9781782270522.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34238","title":"One Night, Markovitch","author":"by Ayelet Gundar-Goshen","description":"Ayelet Gundar-Goshen's stunning debut novel expertly blends events of passion and upheaval, as well as the unrequited love and obsession of the title character for Bella."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31935/9780007374441.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31935","title":"The Art of Fielding","author":"by Chad Harbach","description":"The Art of Fielding is the newest heavyweight contender for Great American novel of the world. It arrives on a garlanded float of its own mythology (there’s a companion book detailing the struggles to get it published) and has garnered..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30454/saraswati-park.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30454","title":"Saraswati Park","author":"by Anjali Joseph","description":"Saraswati Park is a book about loss and longing, love and regret. The prose sparkles like late afternoon sunshine and the characters hook you from their first introduction. This is a very special novel from a very special new talent."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34305/9781784630232.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34305","title":"The Good Son","author":"by Paul McVeigh","description":"Young Mickey Donnelly must try and escape his troublesome upbringing, if not via his local grammar school then via acting in America."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31647/9781446468265.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31647","title":"The Night Circus","author":"by Erin Morgenstern","description":"A magical whimsical intense rollercoaster journey through a turn of the century circus filled with mystery, intrigue and true love."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29074/god-s-own-country.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29074","title":"God's Own Country","author":"by Ross Raisin","description":"Replete with dialect (‘I glegged another look at my watch’), Raisin’s dark tale has an unhinged quality that never strays from its perfectly realised world. Nothing is superfluous in this tense, unsettling and at times very funny novel."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30818/the-still-point.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30818","title":"The Still Point","author":"by Amy Sackville","description":"Amy Sackville demonstrates that she is the mistress of narrative and structure in this stunningly crafted tale of icebergs and splintering marriages."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31978/9780571275762.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31978","title":"Narcopolis","author":"by Jeet Thayil","description":"Narcopolis is dark, set in dank rooms, embued with the stench of human sweat, vomit, and desperation. Narcopolis is narrated by an opium pipe. Narcopolis will hypnotise you."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31648/9780434019328.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31648","title":"The Submission","author":"by Amy Waldman","description":"The Submission walks a fine line between melodrama and emotional powerhouse and manages to succeed through the strength of its characters and what they represent. What emerges is a book that is about the human condition as much as it..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29599/after-the-fire-a-still-small-voice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29599","title":"After the Fire, A Still Small Voice","author":"by Evie Wyld","description":"A sweet, sun-drenched, heart-felt love affair. Evie Wyld's debut novel slips across hard-edged themes of masculine expression, war, paternal relationships and grief with such beauty and ease that it feels like she is already an old hand."}]}
{"id":203,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/203/","title":"Historical novels","list_description":"Following Hilary Mantel's historic win of the Booker and the Costa in the same year with a historic novel here are some more books that talk of the past and sing of days of yore.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32249/9781448130788.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32249","title":"HHhH","author":"by Laurence Binet","description":"HHhH, the debut novel from Laurent Binet, tells the story of Operation Anthropoid, two Czechoslovakian parachutists' mission to assassinate Nazi commander Reinhard Heydrich. With skill Binet guides us through Heydrich's cruel ascent to power, the Resistance fighters' preparations and the..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31082/jamrach-s-menagerie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31082","title":"Jamrach's Menagerie","author":"by Carol Birch","description":"Carol Birch's eleventh novel harnesses this same drive and commitment, producing a story of rich, vivid detail, brilliant characters and a satisfying and compelling narrative."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27024/slammerkin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27024","title":"Slammerkin","author":"by Emma Donoghue","description":"Set in the eighteen century, partly in London and partly in Wales, Slammerkin is the story of Mary Saunders - a clothes obsessed young woman, whose desire for fine dresses leads her into prostitution at the age of thirteen."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25861/the-blue-flower.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25861","title":"The Blue Flower","author":"by Penelope Fitzgerald","description":"The story is based upon the life of the romantic poet and philosopher Friedrich von Hardenberg, who wrote under the name Novalis, but Lively has written much more than a fictionalised biography of the man."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29878/wolf-hall.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29878","title":"Wolf Hall","author":"by Hilary Mantel","description":"England in the 1540s is a heartbeat from disaster. If the king dies without a male heir, the country could be destroyed by civil war. Henry VIII wants to annul his marriage of twenty years, and marry Anne Boleyn. The..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31280/austerlitz.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31280","title":"Austerlitz","author":"by W G Sebald","description":"Austerlitz is about memory and forgetting, and the shadows of absence and guilt that the Holocaust cast forward into the future."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33405/mouse-deer-kingdom.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33405","title":"The Mouse Deer Kingdom","author":"by Chiew-Siah Tei","description":"Following on from Little Hut of Leaping Fishes, Chiew-Siah Tei's The Mouse Deer Kingdom is a multi-narrative story that takes place in early 20th century Asia. Former mandarin Chai Mingzhi is caught in a huge sea storm as he escapes..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27122/restoration.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27122","title":"Restoration","author":"by Rose Tremain","description":"Tremain's exuberant tale of Robert Merivel, bumbling courtier to Charles II, who reluctantly leaves London but in the process achieves personal redemption."}]}
{"id":204,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/204/","title":"Rhyme","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24857/eachpeach.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24857","title":"Each Peach Pear Plum","author":"by Janet & Allan Ahlberg","description":"This classic book from author and illustrator team Janet and Allan Ahlberg is a real favourite with families","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30598/rumble-in-the-jungle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30598","title":"Rumble in the Jungle","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33958/action-rhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33958","title":"Action Rhymes","author":"by Clare Beaton","description":"Simple rhymes with hand-sewn illustrations","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33825/nursery-rhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33825","title":"Nursery Rhymes","author":"by Lucy Cousins","description":"Favourite nursery rhymes illustrated by the creator of Maisy!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30536/hairy-maclary.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30536","title":"Hairy Maclary from Donaldson's Dairy","author":"by Lynley Dodd","description":"This hilarious rhyming story follows Hairy Maclary from Donaldson's Dairy, as he sets off for a walk in town","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25568/wriggle-roar_fc.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25568","title":"Wriggle and Roar!","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"This super collection of 17 original rhymes for joining in with has appeal for the new toddler and well into the nursery years.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-4"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31205/what-the-ladybird-heard.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31205","title":"What the Ladybird Heard","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Lydia Monks","description":"The animals on the farm are always noisy, all except for the ladybird who never says a word. But when burglars plot to steal the farmer's fine prize cow, the ladybird has a plan...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24602/row-row-row-your-boat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24602","title":"Row, Row, Row Your Boat","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"Actions to accompany the verses are demonstrated in lively watercolour illustrations of bright and cheerful babies, bursting with energy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28652/this-little-piggy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28652","title":"This Little Piggy","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"Annie Kubler’s exuberant characters tell the well-known rhyme. One child uses a supported chair.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34630/wheels-on-the-bus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34630","title":"The Wheels on the Bus","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30604/flashing-fireengines.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30604","title":"Flashing Fire Engines","author":"by Tony Mitton","description":"This story’s full of big, bold fire engines ready to rescue or fight fires. There’s plenty of action, rhyme and rhythm."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34627/a-great-big-cuddle-front-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34627","title":"A Great Big Cuddle","author":"by Michael Rosen and Chris Riddell","description":"Beautifully illustrated poems for young children by two Children's Laureates","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34366/axel-scheffler-rhyming-stories-part1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34366","title":"Axel Scheffler Rhyming Stories Book 1: Pip the Dog and Freddy the Frog","author":"by Axel Scheffler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29514/octopus-socktopus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29514","title":"Octopus Socktopus","author":"by Nick Sharratt","description":"Brightly coloured octopuses appear throughout the pages of this fun pop-up book from Nick Sharratt.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34535/one-fluffy-baa-lamb.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34535","title":"One Fluffy Baa Lamb, Ten Hairy Caterpillars","author":"by Nick Sharratt","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34368/mockingbird-song.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34368","title":"Mockingbird Song","author":"by Carol Thompson","description":"A beautiful retelling of the classic lullaby.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34182/puffin-baby-and-toddler-treasury.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34182","title":"The Puffin Baby and Toddler Treasury","author":"by Various","description":"Favourite nursery rhymes, lullabies, poems and stories in one book","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30436/9780141328805-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30436","title":"Sing a Song of Bottoms!","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Young children will love the rhyming text which rejoices in the diversity of bottoms!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30647/bearhuntcd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30647","title":"We're Going on a Bear Hunt (book and CD)","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":""}]}
{"id":205,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/205/","title":"Eating Disorders Awareness Booklist","list_description":"These books all touch on the subject of eating disorders, and will help young readers to gain an understanding of eating issues.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31306/wintergirls..jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31306","title":"Wintergirls","author":"by Laurie Halse Anderson","description":"Wintergirls tells the story of Lia, a recovering anorexic whose recovery is sent spiralling out of control when her former best friend (and bulimic), Cassie, is found dead in a motel room.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32324/9780141341552-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32324","title":"Summer's Dream","author":"by Cathy Cassidy","description":"Thirteen year-old Summer has always been passionate about dancing, but when the chance to audition for a place at a prestigious ballet school comes her way, she feels sure her dreams are about to come true.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32651/a-perfect-10.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32651","title":"A Perfect 10","author":"by Chis Higgins","description":"Perfection. That's the key aim in Eva's life. She works hard to be the girl all the other girls wish they could be: pretty, popular, smart and the queen of her gymnastics clique, the 'Jimmies'. She seems to have it...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32851/9780571294404-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32851","title":"Butter","author":"by Erin Jade Lange","description":"Bullied at school, and weighing over 400 lbs, Butter feels he has nothing left to live for, and announces he will eat himself to death live on the internet.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32808/9780007424849-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32808","title":"Pumpkin Pie","author":"by Jean Ure","description":"Some unpleasant comments from girls at school and an embarrassing incident relating to her weight lead a girl to start worrying about her self-image.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32807/girls-under-pressure.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32807","title":"Girls Under Pressure","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Ellie feels like the ugly duckling beside her slim, gorgeous friends Magda and Nadine. She decides to go on a diet, but she soon gets carried away with her plan to lose weight.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":206,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/206/","title":"Ideas for presents for your mum","list_description":"It's Mother's Day this weekend. We hope you've bought a card and some flowers and are planning an elaborate lunch or breakfast for her! If you're looking for any book recommendations for your mum, here are some suggestions for you, including the painfully funny and honest graphic memoir about a summer a mother and her son spend together, Days of Bagnold Summer.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31409/fea008ca-13c2-44db-8e2d-d24866ff1251-img100-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31409","title":"The Pleasure Seekers","author":"by Tishani Doshi","description":"The dual heritages of India and Wales come together in this funny, bittersweet tale spanning four generations of Patels from dancer and poet, Tishani Doshi"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32085/9780571238309.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32085","title":"Gillespie & I","author":"by Jane Harris","description":"As she sits in her Bloomsbury home, with her two birds for company, elderly Harriet Baxter sets out to relate the story of her acquaintance, nearly four decades previously, with Ned Gillespie, a talented artist who never achieved the fame..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31190/never-let-me-go.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31190","title":"Never Let Me Go","author":"by Kazuo Ishiguro","description":"In one of the most acclaimed and strange novels of recent years, Kazuo Ishiguro imagines the lives of a group of students growing up in a darkly skewered version of contemporary England.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29876/the-lacuna.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29876","title":"The Lacuna","author":"by Barbara Kingsolver","description":"Born in the US and reared in a series of provincial households in Mexico, Harrison Shepherd is mostly a liability to his social-climbing mother, Salomé; his fortunes remaining insecure as Salomé finds her rich men-friends always on the losing side..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28204/beyond-black.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28204","title":"Beyond Black","author":"by Hilary Mantel","description":"Alison Hart, a medium by trade, tours the dormitory towns of London's orbital road with her flint-hearted sidekick Colette, passing on messages from dead ancestors."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27671/the-beggar-maid.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27671","title":"The Beggar Maid","author":"by Alice Munro","description":"This collection of stories reads like a novel following Rose's life as she moves away from her impoverished roots and forges her own path in the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28217/gilead.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28217","title":"Gilead","author":"by Marilynne Robinson","description":"Delighted to become a father so late in life, the Reverend John Ames is sad that there's no chance he'll live to see his son grown up. So he sets himself the task of writing a long letter for his..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32460/manual_9780241144145.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32460","title":"NW","author":"by Zadie Smith","description":"Leah, Felix and Keisha all grew up on the same estate in North West London. In different ways, they all work to escape where they've come from. They quickly realise that 'it's not where you're from, it's where you're at'..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27869/nothing-to-wear-and-nowhere-to-hide.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27869","title":"Nothing to Wear and Nowhere to Hide","author":"by Fay Weldon","description":"A spiky, feisty, hilarious collection of stories that expose women's clumsy, often doomed, attempts to negotiate a smooth path through life."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32751/9780224090841.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32751","title":"Days of the Bagnold Summer","author":"by Joff Winterhart","description":"There is something painfully familiar about this simple, funny and sad graphic novel about a mum trying to engage her awkward, moody teenage metalhead of a son over the 6 weeks of his summer holiday","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":207,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/207/","title":"Picture books about mums","list_description":"To celebrate Mother's Day, why not share one of these illustrated books featuring marvellous mums?  It's a good excuse to have some quiet time or talk through any issues. Together, you can celebrate all the different kinds of special mums in the world! ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35489/love-is.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35489","title":"Love is","author":"by Diane Adams","description":"A little girl cares for a duckling just as a parent would care for a baby. But also, as the duckling grows, the little girl comes to understand that part of love is letting things go. A gentle and inspiring...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29896/9781408309575-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29896","title":"I Love My Mummy","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"What is it about Mummies that makes them so lovable and so very special?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25557/my-mum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25557","title":"My Mum","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"All small children love their mums and in this colourful and entertaining picture book, Anthony Browne explains exactly why.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29825/piggybook.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29825","title":"Piggybook","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"Humour permeates this gentle exploration of gender stereotypes which will entertain families and mums in particular.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30585/sometimes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30585","title":"Sometimes","author":"by Emma Dodd","description":"This is a warm book about unconditional love. A perfect book for encouraging children to do what they want with reassuring support.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31303/a-bit-lost.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31303","title":"A Bit Lost","author":"by Chris Haughton","description":"Little Owl falls asleep in his (rather precarious) nest, falls onto the ground with a 'bump' and becomes 'a bit lost'. But Squirrel comes to his rescue...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30353/the-great-big-book-of-families.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30353","title":"The Great Big Book of Families","author":"by Mary Hoffman","description":"Hoffman and Asquith celebrate the diversity of family life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35559/mamasaurus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35559","title":"Mamasaurus","author":"by Stephan Lomp","description":"A striking book with brightly coloured, big eyed dinosaurs against a black background, Mamasaurus has the lovely message that all mums are different, but each mum is the perfect mama for their little babysaurus.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32855/9781407114927-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32855","title":"The Mummy Shop","author":"by Abie Longstaff","description":"One little boy is feeling very cross with his mummy, so when he sees an advert for ‘The Mummy Shop’ he decides to give them a ring.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29778/my-mum-has-x-ray-vision.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29778","title":"My Mum has X-ray Vision","author":"by Angela McAllister","description":"Milo’s mum looks ordinary, but he is convinced she has X-ray vision. She knows when he’s up to mischief, even if she’s in another room.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33626/dino-mummy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33626","title":"Dino-Mummy","author":"by Mark Sperring","description":"Dino-Mummy celebrates the multi-tasking super-dino who not only looks after two lively dino-babies and keeps their home in order, but also provides consistently delicious food and fun playtime.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":208,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/208/","title":"Counting","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28935/fruits.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28935","title":"Fruits: a Caribbean counting poem","author":"by Valerie Bloom","description":"From half a pawpaw to five jew-plums through to ten bananas, this girl’s love of Caribbean fruits is so infectious you can almost taste the juice dribbling down your chin.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32772/9781406325799-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32772","title":"One Gorilla","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"From one gorilla to ten lemurs, Anthony Browne's beautiful counting book will delight young children and their parents alike.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34135/tenlittlepirates.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34135","title":"Ten Little Pirates","author":"by Mike Brownlow and Simon Rickerty","description":"A counting adventure with pirates... and a giant squid!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29614/count-with-maisy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29614","title":"Count with Maisy","author":"by Lucy Cousins","description":"Young children will have fun counting from one to ten using familiar objects, such as pencils and fish.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31206/1moledighole.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31206","title":"One Mole Digging a Hole","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Nick Sharratt","description":"In this vibrant counting book, one mole digging a hole is soon joined by a troupe of gardening friends, including nine doves in gardening gloves and ten bees pruning trees.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33820/one-to-ten-animal-mayhem.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33820","title":"One to Ten Animal Mayhem","author":"by Thomas Flintham","description":"A colourful counting book full of animals."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29496/one-two-cockatoo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29496","title":"One, Two, Cockatoo!","author":"by Sarah Garson","description":"Here is a rhyming, counting book with cockatoos having fun on every page.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33831/tip-tap-went-crab.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33831","title":"Tip Tap Went The Crab","author":"by Tim Hopgood","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34233/we-all-went-on-safari.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34233","title":"We All Went on Safari","author":"by Laurie Krebs and Julia Cairns","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34175/baby-touch-one-two-three.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34175","title":"Baby Touch: One! Two! Three! bath book","author":"by Ladybird","description":"Padded, waterproof counting book for baby bath and meal times","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30440/counting-birds.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30440","title":"Counting Birds","author":"by Alice Melvin","description":"This stylishly illustrated counting book from a Best New Illustrator, opens with a vibrant cockerel crowing to welcome the day and ends with a solitary barn owl flying off the page and slipping into the night. Perfect for learning how...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30554/oneisasnail.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30554","title":"One is a Snail, Ten is a Crab","author":"by April Pulley Sayre","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30556/one-two-tree-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30556","title":"One, Two, Tree!","author":"by Anushka Ravishankar","description":"This is an unusual and creative counting book. The pictures reflect the tribal traditions of central India, and the tree fills up with animals as the story progresses.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34535/one-fluffy-baa-lamb.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34535","title":"One Fluffy Baa Lamb, Ten Hairy Caterpillars","author":"by Nick Sharratt","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32850/9780857550156-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32850","title":"Dog Loves Counting","author":"by Louise Yates","description":"Join Dog on a quest to discover creatures he can count - from a three-toed sloth to an eight-legged spider.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":209,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/209/","title":"A matter of life and death","list_description":"In the wake of debate and controversy in the media about books for teenagers exploring difficult topics such as terminal illness or suicide, we recommend some books that deal frankly with issues of life and death.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32796/9781408827116-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32796","title":"Anthem for Jackson Dawes","author":"by Celia Bryce","description":"Megan would never have met Jackson Dawes if she hadn't had cancer. But as the only teenagers on the children's ward, they soon form a powerful and unconventional bond.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32793/undoned.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32793","title":"Undone","author":"by Cat Clarke","description":"Jem and Kai have always been best friends - until Kai commits suicide and Jem's world collapses.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26901/b4idie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26901","title":"Before I Die","author":"by Jenny Downham","description":"Stunning in its beauty and honesty, this is an exceptional and utterly compelling read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28956/ostrich-boys.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28956","title":"Ostrich Boys","author":"by Keith Gray","description":"When teenager Ross Fell is killed, his closest friends are horrified by the sham and hypocrisy of his funeral.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32370/9781849393003-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32370","title":"Next","author":"by Edited by Keith Gray","description":"Following on from the success of Losing It, Keith Gray has edited a new collection of eight short stories for young people exploring the complex question of what happens when we die.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32863/9780141345659-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32863","title":"The Fault in Our Stars","author":"by John Green","description":"John Green tackles the subject of teenage cancer with sensitivity in this witty, life-affirming young adult romance.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32856/9781405256728-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32856","title":"Skin Deep","author":"by Laura Jarratt","description":"The car crash that left her best friend dead has left Jenna with scars both emotional and physical. She feels as though her life is over - but then Ryan turns up.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32851/9780571294404-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32851","title":"Butter","author":"by Erin Jade Lange","description":"Bullied at school, and weighing over 400 lbs, Butter feels he has nothing left to live for, and announces he will eat himself to death live on the internet.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32795/9781471400339-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32795","title":"Red Ink","author":"by Julie Mayhew","description":"This beautifully-written coming of age story interrogates family, identity, memory and the myths and superstitions we create for ourselves.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31309/amonstercallsss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31309","title":"A Monster Calls","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"Connor's mum has cancer and life is changing. There is the nightmare, then there is school, where people avoid him, or persecute him. And then there is the immense, mythic Monster.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31311/mysisterlivesonmatlepiece.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31311","title":"My Sister Lives on the Mantelpiece","author":"by Annabel Pitcher","description":"Told through the eyes of ten-year-old Jamie, My Sister Lives on the Mantelpiece sensitively tackles issues around grief, terrorism, racism and bullying.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25666/elsewheres.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25666","title":"Elsewhere","author":"by Gabrielle Zevin","description":"Life ends catastrophically suddenly for Elizabeth Hall, in a road accident. Not for her a future filled with love, marriage and children; instead, she awakes aboard a quiet, white cruise ship, steaming to Elsewhere.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":210,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/210/","title":"Books for bedtime","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33125/9781847803832.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33125","title":"The Book of Dreams","author":"by Shirin Adl","description":"This unusual picture book may help some children to put into words their ideas about the strange and abstract concept of dreams.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34514/zoom-trish-cooke.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34514","title":"Zoom!","author":"by Trish Cooke","description":"Hurricane Kieron and Rush Around Ria never stop. They run right through the day, rushing from breakfast to bedtime.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34636/9780008101343.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34636","title":"Goodnight Already!","author":"by Jory John","description":"Bear gets frustrated when Duck keeps waking him up because he isn't tired","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31143/meg-goes-to-bed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31143","title":"Meg Goes to Bed","author":"by Helen Nicoll","description":"Meg, Mog and Owl are a beloved addition to any picture book collection and this quirky fun tale is no exception.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32411/untitled.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32411","title":"Goodnight Digger","author":"by Michelle Robinson","description":"It’s time for bed. A little boy tidies away his toy vehicles and he says goodnight to each of them in turn - his train, plane, bus and of course his favourite - the big yellow digger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30750/harry-and-the-dinosaurs-first-sleepover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30750","title":"Harry and the Dinosaurs: First Sleepover","author":"by Ian Whybrow","description":"Mum and Nan are concerned about how Harry and his dinosaurs will handle a sleepover at Jack’s house – but their worries are unfounded.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":211,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/211/","title":"Books about family","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33803/mr-biff-the-boxer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33803","title":"Mr Biff the Boxer","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"The Ahlbergs' funny and classic Happy Families story is now available in a larger format and is ideal for newly independent readers","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30574/baby-s-catalogue.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30574","title":"The Baby's Catalogue","author":"by Janet and Allan Ahlberg","description":"This book's packed with lots of baby pictures and baby items. It's great for learning and making up stories - this fantastic book will lead to lots of talk with your child.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34657/9781406357509.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34657","title":"Albert and Little Henry","author":"by Jez Alborough","description":"Henry starts to feel left out and ignored when a new baby sibling arrives at home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29326/what-does-daddy-do.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29326","title":"What Does Daddy Do?","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"One day at nursery, the children begin to discuss what their daddies do - which gets Daisy wondering about her own Daddy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30715/my-sister-is-an-alien.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30715","title":"My sister is an Alien","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"Alfie's new baby sister, Ruby, looks, sounds and smells like an alien. Alfie is convinced she often cries for home. He decides to take Ruby back to the moon where she belongs.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31214/mine.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31214","title":"Mine!","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"One day Fifi and Frankie go to visit Grandma Flo and they both want to hold Funny Bunny. After some arguing they pull him in different directions and off come his ears.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33927/new-small-person.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33927","title":"The New Small Person","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"An endearingly funny story, featuring Lauren Child's heart-warming illustrations, about the arrival of a new sibling and the havoc that ensues.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25501/the-legend-of-captain-crow-s-teeth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25501","title":"The Legend of Captain Crow's Teeth","author":"by Eoin Colfer","description":"With characters last seen in Colfer's The Legend of Spud Murphy, this is another light-hearted adventure for younger readers, in which the issue of sibling rivalry is deftly and humorously handled.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31320/9780140544596-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31320","title":"Lucy and Tom at the Seaside","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Follow a happy family day out by the seaside as Tom and Lucy enjoy making sandcastles, looking in rock pools and going on a donkey ride","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28640/ouch-pouch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28640","title":"There's an Ouch in My Pouch!","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Willaby Wallaby is throwing a wobbly...He’s quite determined he still needs a pouch to live in, but suddenly it’s just too knobbly, wodgy, wedgy and wriggly and so he jumps out.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":212,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/212/","title":"Imagination","list_description":"Great books for stimulating young imaginations","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33705/daddy-hero-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33705","title":"Daddy is My Hero","author":"by Dawn Richards and Jane Massey","description":"Fantasy, fun and fancy dress in this tender and touching tribute to heroic Dads!"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29317/box-of-tricks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29317","title":"Box of Tricks","author":"by Katie Cleminson","description":"Every child loves an empty box and here, with the help of some magic, it contains a fantasy birthday party.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32790/9780230749535-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32790","title":"Lunchtime","author":"by Rebecca Cobb","description":"It's lunchtime for one little girl, but she's just not hungry. Then crocodile, wolf and bear appear - and they are starving!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24844/maisy-s-treasure-hunt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24844","title":"Maisy's Treasure Hunt","author":"by Lucy Cousins","description":"Maisy and her friends jump all aboard in search of treasure. They’ve got a ship and a map. All they need to find are three keys hidden beneath the flaps…","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31318/9781840111545-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31318","title":"To the Beach","author":"by Thomas Docherty","description":"Lovely story of a boy using his imagination to go on a trip to the seaside","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4months+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32033/arthurs-dream-boat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32033","title":"Arthur's Dream Boat","author":"by Polly Dunbar","description":"One night, Arthur has an amazing dream about a beautiful pink and green boat with a stripy mast...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32453/youchoose.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32453","title":"Just Imagine","author":"by Pippa Goodhart","description":"Just imagine if you were so big you could take a bath in a swimming pool...or so small that you could sleep in a matchbox! Imagine being a magical creature or even travelling through time...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32480/9781406332254-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32480","title":"Oh No, George!","author":"by Chris Haughton","description":"George is a dog with a big personality and he LOVES cake, rubbish bins and chasing Cat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29258/elephant_petr-horacek.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29258","title":"Elephant","author":"by Petr Horacek","description":"Horáček's illustrations vividly supplement this many-layered story of a lonely child who finds solace in an imaginary world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33828/zoe-beans-pirate.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33828","title":"Zoe and Beans: Pirate Treasure!","author":"by Chloe and Mick Inkpen","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34232/out-of-the-blue-barefoot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34232","title":"Out of the Blue","author":"by Alison Jay","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: n/a","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32399/9780192756794-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32399","title":"Chickens Can't See in the Dark","author":"by Kristyna Litten","description":"When Little Pippa Chicken is told by her teacher that chickens can't see in the dark, she sets out to prove him wrong, and soon becomes the talk of Sunnyside Farm.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33834/pirate-house.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33834","title":"The Pirate House","author":"by Rebecca Patterson","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31459/bruno.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31459","title":"Bruno's Box","author":"by Nicola Pontin","description":"The large, colourful illustrations make this ideal for classroom use where it could stimulate the imaginative use of a wide range of junk materials","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33035/9781847803887-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33035","title":"Max the Champion","author":"by Sean Stockdale and Alexandra Strick","description":"This inclusive book is about a boy who loves sport, his friends, and school - and has a vivid imagination","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31496/bedtime-for-monsters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31496","title":"Bedtime for Monsters","author":"by Ed Vere","description":"Do you ever wonder if somewhere, not too far away, there might be monsters?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29789/dog-loves-books.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29789","title":"Dog Loves Books","author":"by Louise Yates","description":"With an engaging hero and simple, understated text animated by witty, subtly coloured illustrations, this book about the sheer pleasure of books has a refreshing jaunty elegance.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":213,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/213/","title":"Detective stories","list_description":"Follow clues, unravel mysteries and uncover secrets with these engaging detective stories.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32218/9781444908657-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32218","title":"Five on a Treasure Island","author":"by Enid Blyton","description":"Meet Enid Blyton's most famous characters - Julian, Dick, Anne, George and of course the ever-loyal Timmy the dog - for the first time in this, the first book in the classic Famous Five series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31683/ruby-redfort-look-into-my-ey.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31683","title":"Ruby Redfort: Look Into My Eyes","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Blessed with an extraordinary talent for spotting things which others seldom notice, 13-year-old Ruby lands an undercover job as a code-breaker for secret-spy organisation, Spectrum.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32486/operationbunny.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32486","title":"Operation Bunny","author":"by Sally Gardner","description":"In the first case for the Fairy Detective Agency, Wings and Co, resourceful heroine Emily Vole must defeat the dastardly fairy-snatching villain Harpella.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30118/stormbreakerz.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30118","title":"Stormbreaker","author":"by Anthony Horowitz","description":"Fourteen-year-old Alex Rider finds his life turned upside down on discovering that his late uncle wasn't a mild-mannered banker, but instead a field agent for MI6.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32943/emil-and-the-detectives-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32943","title":"Emil and the Detectives","author":"by Erich Kästner","description":"Ten-year-old Emil is excited to be taking the train to Berlin on his own for the first time - but he doesn't like the look of his fellow passenger, the man in the bowler hat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25651/skullduggery-pleasant-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25651","title":"Skulduggery Pleasant","author":"by Derek Landy","description":"Meet Skulduggery Pleasant, skeleton detective, fighting to save the world from wizard-gone-to-the-dark-side, Nefarian Serpine.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32920/wild-boy-cover-web.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32920","title":"Wild Boy","author":"by Rob Lloyd-Jones","description":"In 1840s London, Wild Boy leads a miserable life in a travelling freak show. Treated as a monster and excluded from society, he develops an unusual talent for observation.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32914/9781444008883-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32914","title":"Mariella Mystery: The Ghostly Guinea Pig","author":"by Kate Pankhurst","description":"Mariella Mystery is a totally amazing girl detective, aged nine and a bit - and this is her top secret detective journal.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30900/laura-marlin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30900","title":"Dead Man's Cove","author":"by Lauren St John","description":"When mysterious uncle Calvin rescues Laura Marlin from her gloomy life in an orphanage, she can't believe her luck! But she soon realises that her Cornish paradise is full of mysteries...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24897/ottolineandtheyellowcat300dpi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24897","title":"Ottoline and the Yellow Cat","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Ottoline is good at solving mysteries, in part due to her eavesdropping habit and in part because of her qualification as a mistress of disguise.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"}]}
{"id":215,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/215/","title":"Pori Drwy Stori summer term Booklist","list_description":"Some of our favourite new books for the summer term...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35489/love-is.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35489","title":"Love is","author":"by Diane Adams","description":"A little girl cares for a duckling just as a parent would care for a baby. But also, as the duckling grows, the little girl comes to understand that part of love is letting things go. A gentle and inspiring...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35517/quiet2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35517","title":"Quiet!","author":"by Kate Alizadeh","description":"A small child takes us on an auditory tour of her home in this delightful picture of family life, ingeniously interpreted through its sounds. It's a book that radiates comfort, security, warmth and love.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35645/william-bee-s-wonderful-world-of-trucks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35645","title":"William Bee’s Wonderful World of Trucks","author":"by William Bee","description":"William Bee loves trucks. A lot. In fact, he loves them so much, he has written and illustrated this amazing guide to giant vehicles of all kinds. Children will return to this book again and again.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35586/the-night-gardener.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35586","title":"The Night Gardener","author":"by The Fan Brothers","description":"A sumptuously illustrated, heart-warming tale of a sad town and lonely orphan, given new life by the kindness of The Night Gardener. There is little text, leaving the emotional impact to the gorgeous pictures. This has the feel of an...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35537/if-i-had-a-dinosaur.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35537","title":"If I Had a Dinosaur","author":"by Gabby Dawnay","description":"A little girl wishes ever so desperately that she could have a pet, but she's unsure about what kind of pet she would like.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35584/last-stop-on-market-street.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35584","title":"Last Stop on Market Street","author":"by Matt de la Pena","description":"A New York Times Bestseller, this wonderful picture book about the riches that money can’t buy is a timely and timeless reminder for all of us, not just children, that caring, thoughtfulness and community are more important than material wealth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35497/horrible-bear-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35497","title":"Horrible Bear!","author":"by Ame Dyckman","description":"This sweet and simple story about friendship and saying sorry perfectly captures the frustration that children can feel when something doesn’t go right, and the relief we all feel at saying sorry and making things better again.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35638/grandad-s-secret-giant.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35638","title":"Grandad’s Secret Giant","author":"by David Litchfield","description":"Although the Secret Giant is rarely seen, grandad is convinced he exists. Maybe he's lonely, and just needs a friend? There's a mysterious luminosity to the illustrations of this magical story about accepting people who are different.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35496/i-can-only-draw-worms.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35496","title":"I Can Only Draw Worms","author":"by Will Mabbitt","description":"This genuinely hilarious book is brilliantly simple, based on the idea that the author-illustrator can only draw very childlike worms. Highly recommended.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35661/pigeon-pi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35661","title":"Pigeon P.I.","author":"by Meg McLaren","description":"Murray MacMurray, the Pigeon P.I., is enjoying some quiet time until a persistent yellow canary named Vee asks him to help find her missing friends. This story of mystery and friendship will delight both children and adults.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35512/piglet-called-truffle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35512","title":"A Piglet Called Truffle","author":"by Helen Peters","description":"When Jasmine discovers a helpless piglet, she takes it upon herself to make sure it has a chance. But will Truffle be allowed to stay with Jasmine for good? This short, sweet story of a little girl looking after the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35502/i-don-t-know-what-to-call-my-cat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35502","title":"I Don't Know What to Call My Cat","author":"by Simon Philip","description":"The girl in this book has got a new pet cat, but has absolutely no idea what to call it. This picture book provides some hearty chuckles and the illustrations have a lovely, big-eyed 'cartoony' feel to them, choc-a-bloc with...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35599/barefoot-book-of-children.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35599","title":"The Barefoot Book of Children","author":"by Tessa Strickland, Kate DePalma and David Dean","description":"This is a beautifully comprehensive and thought-provoking picture of the many different ways in which people live around the world. A book to dip into time and time again; a treasure trove of discussion topics, but also an aesthetic delight.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35650/how-to-be-a-tiger.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35650","title":"How To Be a Tiger","author":"by George Szirtes","description":"How To Be a Tiger is the first collection for younger children by multi-award-winning poet George Szirtes - and it's a treat that will make little ones laugh, think and wince.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35663/nanette-s-baguette.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35663","title":"Nanette’s Baguette","author":"by Mo Willems","description":"Nanette is excited to go to the bakery on her own to get the baguettes. Unfortunately, she cannot resist taking a bite - and then another... A story - told in giggle-inducing rhyme and quirky illustrations - all about responsibility...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"}]}
{"id":216,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/216/","title":"For fans of Arne Dahl","list_description":" If, like me, you've been addicted to Arne Dahl's BBC4 Intercrime adaptations, as well as The Killing and The Bridge, you've probably already torn through the books and you're hungry for more!  Never fear... I've had a look through the Book Trust archive of books and found these tasty crime thrillers in translation from all around the world to whet your appetite.  These books will take you deep into Scandinavia, to the heady heights of Havana, Cuba to Italy and beyond. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26269/a-walk-in-the-dark.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26269","title":"A Walk in the Dark","author":"by Gianrico Carofiglio","description":"Guido Guerreri is getting himself in trouble again: this time risking the wrath of all the vested interests and violent machismo of the southern Italian city in which he works, in order to help a woman battered by her well-connected..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32758/9781904738978.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32758","title":"No Sale","author":"by Patrick Conrad","description":"Set in Antwerp and translated from Flemish, No Sale is a nifty little thriller that manages to both capture the essence of classic crime fiction and be strikingly original."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29855/the-water-s-edge.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29855","title":"The Water's Edge","author":"by Karin Fossum","description":"The Water's Edge is a gripping psychological novel from a highly skilled crime writer, with an outstanding translation by Charlotte Barslund."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31058/jar-city.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31058","title":"Jar City","author":"by Arnaldur Indridason","description":"A man is found murdered in his Reykjavik flat. There are no obvious clues apart from a cryptic note left on the body and a photograph of a young girl's grave."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31059/the-stonecutter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31059","title":"The Stonecutter","author":"by Camilla Lackberg","description":"The remote resort of Fjallbacka has seen its share of tragedy, though perhaps none worse than that of the little girl found in a fisherman's net. But the post-mortem reveals that this is no accidental drowning!"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32946/9781846689123-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32946","title":"The Cutting Season","author":"by Attica Locke","description":"Contemporary Louisiana can't escape its slave trade past in Orange Prize-shortlisted author Attica Locke's second novel."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26577/havana-red.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26577","title":"Havana Red","author":"by Leonardo Padura","description":"On 6 August 1989 the day on which the Catholic Church celebrates the Feast of the Transfiguration, the body of a strangled transvestite is discovered in the humid undergrowth of the Havana Woods."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30918/a-shortcut-to-paradise.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30918","title":"A Shortcut to Paradise","author":"by Teresa Solana","description":"It’s perfect tabloid fodder right from the start in this wickedly funny and scathingly brilliant Catalonian crime novel."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31056/the-chalk-circle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31056","title":"The Chalk Circle Man","author":"by Fred Vargas","description":"Jean-Baptiste Adamsberg is not like other policemen. His methods appear unorthodox in the extreme."}]}
{"id":217,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/217/","title":"Bookbuzz 2013","list_description":"Take a look at the Bookbuzz titles for 2013.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32421/9781447220053-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32421","title":"Soldier Dog","author":"by Sam Angus","description":"It's 1917 and Stanley Ryder is one of many young boys enlisting in the army, in spite of the fact he is underage. Assigned to working with messenger dogs, he is drafted to the Western Front.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32335/9781409538592-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32335","title":"Butterfly Summer","author":"by Anne-Marie Conway","description":"When Becky moves to the sleepy village of Oakbridge, she can’t imagine how she will fill the long empty days of the summer holidays. Then she discovers the beautiful Butterfly Garden, and befriends the mysterious Rosa May.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32919/9780192756268-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32919","title":"After Tomorrow","author":"by Gillian Cross","description":"Matt's world changed forever on Armageddon Monday, when five banks crashed simultaneously. Now he's living in a refugee camp, struggling to survive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31852/15-the-pirates-next-door.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31852","title":"The Pirates Next Door","author":"by Jonny Duddle","description":"Lots of humour and irrepressibly rakish pirates combine in this entertaining book about looking beyond appearances","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32841/9780857631503-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32841","title":"Dear Scarlett","author":"by Fleur Hitchcock","description":"Was Scarlett’s dad really a master jewel thief? Was he a spy? A cardboard box full of clues might just provide the answers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32958/yshdeathcloud300dpi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32958","title":"Young Sherlock Holmes: Death Cloud","author":"by Andrew Lane","description":"14-year-old Sherlock is at boarding school, and like most of his fellow pupils, is looking forward to returning home for the summer holidays. He is dismayed then to find out that instead of going back to his parents in London...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31753/sky-hawk.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31753","title":"Sky Hawk","author":"by Gill Lewis","description":"Powerful, evocative writing about landscape and the natural world","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32963/giggle_giggle_cover_300.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32963","title":"Giggle Giggle What’s So Funny?","author":"by Ben Mantle","description":"Giggle, giggle, what's so funny? Is it two barmy ballet dancers jumping and jiggling? An exercising octopus all puffed out? Or perhaps there is a totally tickle-tastic answer?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32959/payback-web-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32959","title":"Payback","author":"by Graham Marks","description":"Greg is walking through the park when he sees a smooth, black oblong lying on a bench. Thinking it's a phone, he picks it up. But when he looks closer, he realises it's not a phone at all. The next...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32960/spacewhizzbangstory300.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32960","title":"Space: The Whole Whizz Bang Story","author":"by Glenn Murphy","description":"What is a black hole? What's it like on the Moon? And which planet is Earth's evil twin? Glenn Murphy, author of Why is Snot Green?, answers these questions and many more in this funny and informative book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32455/9-gods-and-warriors-the-outsiders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32455","title":"Gods and Warriors: The Outsiders","author":"by Michelle Paver","description":"In the first installment of a historical trilogy set during the Mycean Bronze Age, goatherd Hylas and High Priestess's daughter Pirra find themselves thrown together on a mysterious island.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30754/michael-rosen-s-book-of-bad-things.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30754","title":"Michael Rosen's Big Book of Bad Things","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":"Some poems are funny, some desperately sad. But in Rosen's hands, small, scruffy words you don't even notice gain extra weight and meaning...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32037/dark-lord.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32037","title":"Dark Lord: The Teenage Years","author":"by Jamie Thomson","description":"The Dark Lord falls to earth, crash-landing in a suburban car park in the body of a teenage boy, spitting out poisonous mucus","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32451/mybestfri.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32451","title":"My Best Friend and Other Enemies","author":"by Catherine Wilkins","description":"The first children's book from comedian Catherine Wilkins is told from the point of view of 11-year-old Jessica, whose best friend Natalie may have just become her worst enemy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32962/wimpsguid.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32962","title":"Killer Animals: The Wimp’s Guide","author":"by Tracey Turner","description":"Have you ever wrestled a crocodile? Or put your head in the mouth of a hippopotamus? Or let a tarantula walk on your hands? If you answered no, to all of the above, then this could be the book for...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31954/9780141330693-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31954","title":"Sir Scallywag and the Golden Underpants","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"When King Colin’s golden underpants go missing, he sends young Sir Scallywag on a quest to find them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32942/od-geoffrey-cov-uk.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32942","title":"Oh Dear, Geoffrey!","author":"by Gemma O'Neill","description":"Geoffrey the giraffe's height makes him clumsy - it's hard for him to make friends with the creatures on the ground.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"}]}
{"id":218,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/218/","title":"Fairy tales","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24857/eachpeach.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24857","title":"Each Peach Pear Plum","author":"by Janet & Allan Ahlberg","description":"This classic book from author and illustrator team Janet and Allan Ahlberg is a real favourite with families","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31147/prince-cinders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31147","title":"Prince Cinders","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"Prince Cinders leads a hard life, bullied by his three big hairy brothers - that is, until one Saturday night when Cinders' luck changes","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33038/9781904550198-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33038","title":"Goldilocks and the Three Bears","author":"by Estelle Corke","description":"The much-loved story of Goldilocks and the Three Bears is retold in this story from Child's Play's Flip-up Fairy Tale series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24891/mr-wolf-and-the-enormous-turnip.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24891","title":"Mr Wolf and the Enormous Turnip","author":"by Jan Fearnley","description":"Mr Wolf is about to dig up the enormous turnip in his garden for stew when a frog demands his assistance: the kiss of a princess is needed to restore his prince-hood.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32454/wolf.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32454","title":"What's the Time, Mr Wolf?","author":"by Debi Gliori","description":"Is Mr Wolf really as big and bad as his reputation suggests? Award-winning picture book creator Debi Gliori suggests otherwise in this delightful story inspired by traditional fairy tales.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25546/the-adventures-of-the-dish-and-the-spoon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25546","title":"The Adventures of the Dish and the Spoon","author":"by Mini Grey","description":"We all know that the dish ran away with the spoon but Mini Grey's new book explores what happened to the nursery rhyme characters next.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32997/9781444900675-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32997","title":"Red Riding Hood and the Sweet Little Wolf","author":"by Rachael Mortimer","description":"Sweet Little Wolf’s big, bad parents are at their wits’ end. When will their daughter start acting like a real wolf instead of loving all things pretty and pink?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30808/my-favourite-fairy-tales.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30808","title":"My Favourite Fairy Tales","author":"by Tony Ross","description":"Tony Ross retells seven fairy tales for a contemporary audience with wit and style.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30564/foggyfoggyforest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30564","title":"The Foggy Foggy Forest","author":"by Nick Sharratt","description":"Who's lurking in the foggy forest? Look through the trees and guess the shapes to find out.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33037/9781904550204-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33037","title":"Jack and the Beanstalk","author":"by Barbara Vagnozzi","description":"The classic story of Jack and the Beanstalk is retold in this colourful lift-the-flap book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"}]}
{"id":219,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/219/","title":"Top 10 books by Malorie Blackman","list_description":"To celebrate the appointment of Malorie Blackman as Waterstones Children's Laureate 2013-2015, here's a list of some of our favourite Malorie Blackman books.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24523/cloud-busting.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24523","title":"Cloud Busting","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Shortlisted for the 2004 Nestlé Smarties Book Prize (age 6-8 category), an exploration of an unlikely friendship between two very different boys.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24886/unheard-voices.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24886","title":"Unheard Voices","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"This collection of writing about slavery was published to coincide with the 200 year anniversary of the Abolition of the Slave Trade Act 1807.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27592/pigheart-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27592","title":"Pig Heart Boy","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Cameron desperately needs a new heart when he is offered the opportunity to take part in a radical and controversial experiment involving the transplant of a pig's heart.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27781/hacker-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27781","title":"Hacker","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"A thriller for the computer buffs. Vicky's father is arrested for the theft of millions from the bank where he works.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28476/noughts-and-crosses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28476","title":"Noughts and Crosses","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Callum is a Nought but his best friend Sephy is a Cross - the daughter of one of the most influential politicians in the country.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30873/boys-dontcry.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30873","title":"Boys Don't Cry","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Dante is waiting for the postman. It's 'A' level results day and he has high hopes, but a knock on the door brings an old girlfriend and some news that will change his plans for good.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32929/9781781121955-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32929","title":"Jon for Short","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Jon (or is it Joe?) lies alone and amnesiac in his hospital bed, plagued by a disturbing dream of a torch, a knife, and a murder in the dark.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32983/9780552568470-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32983","title":"Trust Me","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Seventeen-year-old Jayna can't wait to go on holiday with boyfriend Andrew - but their trip has unexpected and terrible consequences.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33018/9780552551687.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33018","title":"A.N.T.I.D.O.T.E","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Elliot wishes his Mum was more interesting: everyone else’s parents do exciting things like work for the BBC, but his is only a secretary. But is she?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33026/noble-conflicts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33026","title":"Noble Conflict","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Kaspar is proud to be one of the Guardians - an elite peacekeeping force who protect the Alliance against the rebel Insurgency. Then he encounters young rebel Rhea.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":220,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/220/","title":"School Library Pack titles 2013","list_description":"Take a look at the titles in this year's school library pack. The free pack will provide secondary school libraries with books and resources to help staff create a reading culture that reaches all students, encouraging students to discuss what they are reading and join in activities such as reading groups.  Find out more about the School Library Pack.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31917/9781408823002-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31917","title":"The Weight of Water","author":"by Sarah Crossan","description":"This beautiful book is written in verse and captures 13-year-old Kasienka’s emotions and experiences perfectly","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31960/9781409538585-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31960","title":"Mockingbird","author":"by Kathryn Erskine","description":"A high school shooting has left a small American town devastated.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31775/mister-creecher.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31775","title":"Mister Creecher","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"Friendship, trust and betrayal combine to form a dangerous liaison in this moving and frightening new book from Chris Priestley","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32241/9781407115276-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32241","title":"Goblins","author":"by Philip Reeve","description":"The dark towers of Clovenstone are home to several bands of goblins who spend their time squabbling and fighting each other. But Skarper is different: he is inquisitive and clever.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32405/9781848530836-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32405","title":"Now is the Time for Running","author":"by Michael Williams","description":"Deo's life is destroyed when government forces kill his family. Together with his brother Innocent, he flees his village in search of his father, encountering hardship and hostility along the way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":221,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/221/","title":"Twisted fairy tales","list_description":"Here's a list of some of our favourite twisted fairy tales - fun and anarchic new takes on traditional stories.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31796/goldilocks-on-cctv.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31796","title":"Goldilocks on CCTV","author":"by John Agard","description":"By turns funny, poignant and insightful Agard’s poems are told with a direct and distinctive voice","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32748/9781406330052-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32748","title":"Goldilocks","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"Favourite author Allan Ahlberg retells the favourite story of Goldilocks and the Three Bears in a host of different ways in this delightful book","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24575/into-the-forest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24575","title":"Into the Forest","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"One night a young boy is awoken by a terrible noise. The next day he finds his father has disappeared and his mother doesn't know when he's coming back.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31147/prince-cinders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31147","title":"Prince Cinders","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"Prince Cinders leads a hard life, bullied by his three big hairy brothers - that is, until one Saturday night when Cinders' luck changes","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25325/revoltingrhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25325","title":"Revolting Rhymes","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This is an hilarious collection of some well-loved fairy tales, cleverly reinvented by Roald Dahl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34145/cat-dog-little-red-exploding-wardrobe.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34145","title":"The Cat, the Dog, Little Red, the Exploding Eggs, the Wolf and Grandma's Wardrobe","author":"by Christyan and Diane Fox","description":"A comic retelling of Little Red Riding Hood."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31150/snow-white-in-new-york.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31150","title":"Snow White in New York","author":"by Fiona French","description":"A beautiful 1920s Art Deco treatment of the classic fairytale - now a beautiful socialite, Snow White falls foul of her celebrity-loving stepmother who the tabloids call 'the classiest dame in New York'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33984/sleeper-and-spindle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33984","title":"The Sleeper and the Spindle","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"This magnificent book combines two well-known fairy tales and challenges everything familiar about them. A spectacular book that deserves a spot on every bookcase.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24984/the-pea-and-the-princess.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24984","title":"The Pea and the Princess","author":"by Mini Grey","description":"This is the real story of the princess and the pea, which recounts events from the Pea’s perspective.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25546/the-adventures-of-the-dish-and-the-spoon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25546","title":"The Adventures of the Dish and the Spoon","author":"by Mini Grey","description":"We all know that the dish ran away with the spoon but Mini Grey's new book explores what happened to the nursery rhyme characters next.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31534/puss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31534","title":"Puss in Boots","author":"by Stella Gurney","description":"A lively tale of adventure in a fairytale kingdom that will delight fans of ogres, kings and well-dressed felines","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32493/9780857631077-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32493","title":"The Princess and the Peas","author":"by Caryl Hart","description":"In this light-hearted take on a favourite fairy-tale, Lily-Rose May is allergic to peas - so the doctor decides that she must be a princess!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33983/library-saved-rapunzel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33983","title":"How the Library (Not the Prince) Saved Rapunzel","author":"by Wendy Meddour","description":"This is how every fairy tale should be written, with the protagonist - regardless of gender - saving themselves from a life of solitude and boredom. A great read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32704/9781781120774-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32704","title":"Charming!","author":"by Michaela Morgan","description":"In this 21st century take on the Cinderella story, our heroine is shy, lonely and embarassed - until new girl Charmaine encourages her to join a hip-hop dance class.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32997/9781444900675-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32997","title":"Red Riding Hood and the Sweet Little Wolf","author":"by Rachael Mortimer","description":"Sweet Little Wolf’s big, bad parents are at their wits’ end. When will their daughter start acting like a real wolf instead of loving all things pretty and pink?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25327/the-true-story-of-the-three-little-pigs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25327","title":"The True Story of the Three Little Pigs","author":"by Jon Scieszka & Lane Smith","description":"What really happened to the three little pigs and the big bad wolf? Find out the truth in this hilarious picture book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31145/the-frog-prince-continued.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31145","title":"The Frog Prince Continued","author":"by Jon Scieszka","description":"After the Princess kissed the frog, he turned into a handsome prince, and they lived happily ever after… or did they?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31965/9781407109640-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31965","title":"Ella","author":"by Alex T Smith","description":"An original take on the Cinderella story featuring a specs-wearing ladybird","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32257/9781848772151-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32257","title":"Jack and the Baked Beanstalk","author":"by Colin Stimpson","description":"Stimpson sets his version of Jack and the Beanstalk in 1950s America, with skyscrapers surrounding the flyover under which Jack and his mother run a café","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32193/9781849394055-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32193","title":"The Three Little Pigs","author":"by David Wiesner","description":"How do the Three Little Pigs end up moving into a new brick house with a dragon?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"}]}
{"id":225,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/225/","title":"Best books for your preschool child","list_description":"Our panel of experts has chosen ten of the best picture books to read with your preschool child. All these titles are great fun to share and will help give your 3-4 year old child a flying start when they start school. Look out for forthcoming lists of the best books for babies and toddlers - coming soon!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24982/somedogsdo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24982","title":"Some Dogs Do","author":"by Jez Alborough","description":"One morning, Sid the dog is filled with an overwhelming feeling of happiness which – to his utter surprise – sends him floating into the sky and all the way to school!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24650/smartestgiant.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24650","title":"The Smartest Giant in Town","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"George is the scruffiest giant in town, so he buys a new outfit to smarten himself up. On the way home, however, he meets others who are in greater need of his clothes than he is...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26003/penguin-by-polly-dunbar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26003","title":"Penguin","author":"by Polly Dunbar","description":"Polly Dunbar's illustrations are gorgeous and her palette stylish - from the endearing Ben's rosy cheeks to the magnificent turquoise lion who eats him up.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30655/9780552560351-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30655","title":"You Choose!","author":"by Pippa Goodhart and Nick Sharratt","description":"Create your own story with this brilliant interactive book full of detailed, colourful illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29258/elephant_petr-horacek.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29258","title":"Elephant","author":"by Petr Horacek","description":"Horáček's illustrations vividly supplement this many-layered story of a lonely child who finds solace in an imaginary world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24582/halibutjackson.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24582","title":"Halibut Jackson","author":"by David Lucas","description":"One day Halibut Jackson receives an invitation from the Queen to a party at the palace and starts work on his most ambitious outfit yet, a bejewelled suit of silver and gold, which he thinks will go unnoticed amid the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30506/lulu-loves-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30506","title":"LuLu Loves Stories","author":"by Anna McQuinn","description":"This lovely book introduces the magic of sharing stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32132/ifyourehappy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32132","title":"If You're Happy and You Know It!","author":"by Anna McQuinn","description":"This lively and colourful retelling of a favourite action rhyme is accompanied by a fun watch and singalong CD."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24632/shark-in-the-park.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24632","title":"Shark in the Park!","author":"by Nick Sharratt","description":"But wait it's only a cat. He looks again and there's another shark! Phew, only a crow, and the next time, it's just his dad. But as he sets off for home, is he really sure it's a shark-free park?...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28640/ouch-pouch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28640","title":"There's an Ouch in My Pouch!","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Willaby Wallaby is throwing a wobbly...He’s quite determined he still needs a pouch to live in, but suddenly it’s just too knobbly, wodgy, wedgy and wriggly and so he jumps out.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":226,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/226/","title":"Summer Reads 2013","list_description":"Looking for summer holiday reading? Look no further than our list of great new holiday reads for children of all ages. There's something here for all tastes - from magical fantasy adventure to laugh-out-loud humour.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33086/9781849395601-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33086","title":"The Great Balloon Hullaballoo","author":"by Peter Bently","description":"Simon the squirrel and his friends head to outer space in a hot air balloon in this lively picture book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33025/9781408820506-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33025","title":"The Great Ice Cream Heist","author":"by Elen Caldecott","description":"Shy Eva lives a quiet life with her protective Dad - until the noisy McIntyre family move in next door.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33028/9781908435453-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33028","title":"The Extincts","author":"by Veronica Cossanteli","description":"George loves helping out at Wormestall Farm, a secret sanctuary for exinct and mythical beasts, where unlikely things are always happening.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32660/9781849390927-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32660","title":"The Great Unexpected","author":"by Sharon Creech","description":"In the little town of Blackbird Tree, friends and fellow orphans Naomi and Lizzie are startled when a strange boy, Finn, falls out of a tree.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33170/9781849394529.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33170","title":"Don’t Spill the Milk","author":"by Stephen Davies","description":"Penda is carrying a bowl of milk to Dad, minding sheep up in the grasslands - and whatever she does, she mustn't spill it!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32845/9780552566070-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32845","title":"Darcy Burdock","author":"by Laura Dockrill","description":"Ten-year-old Darcy Burdock is one of life's noticers, spotting the extraordinary in the everyday and coming up with ideas for wild and wonderful stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32908/9780857631992-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32908","title":"Weasels","author":"by Elys Dolan","description":"In this wonderfully humorous debut from an exciting new picture book talent, the weasels are plotting world domination.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32483/paperdolls.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32483","title":"The Paper Dolls","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"A little girl makes a string of paper dolls with her mother, and then takes them off to play in an imaginative world of her own - until a pair of scissors threaten.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33098/9781444003734.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33098","title":"Three Pickled Herrings","author":"by Sally Gardner","description":"A clever young girl called Emily, an 11-year-old fairy, and Fidget the talking cat run a detective agency, Wings & Co.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33201/f5334184-aaf3-47a3-84dc-1d525b0abd0b-img100-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33201","title":"Lilliput","author":"by Sam Gayton","description":"A memorable and magical spin on Gulliver's Travels.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33218/9780007263905-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33218","title":"This Moose Belongs to Me","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"Wilfred owned a moose. He hadn't always owned a moose. The moose came to him a while ago and he knew, just KNEW, that it was meant to be his.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33106/9781444008906.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33106","title":"Mariella Mystery Investigates A Cupcake Conundrum","author":"by Kate Pankhurst","description":"Mariella, Violet and Poppy are the Mystery Girls: there is no mystery too mysterious and no puzzle too puzzling for this team to take on.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33019/9781782690009-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33019","title":"Oksa Pollock: The Last Hope","author":"by Anne Plichota and Cendrine Wolf","description":"The Oksa Pollock series has legions of fans all over the world, and this first installment leaves us in no doubt why.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32842/rooftoppers-new-small.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32842","title":"Rooftoppers","author":"by Katherine Rundell","description":"Following an elusive cello melody over the rooftops of Paris, Sophie is determined to find her long lost mother, before it is too late.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32944/9781444903652-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32944","title":"Catch Us if You Can-Can!","author":"by Alex T Smith","description":"The stars of Alex T. Smith’s dinner-time crime Egg are back in a sparkly sequel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":227,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/227/","title":"Summer Reads 2013","list_description":"The summer holidays are here at last - and here's our pick of great books that are perfect for lazy afternoons and long summer evenings. From romance to dystopia to the books that have inspired this summer's biggest movies, there's something for everyone on our list.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33026/noble-conflicts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33026","title":"Noble Conflict","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Kaspar is proud to be one of the Guardians - an elite peacekeeping force who protect the Alliance against the rebel Insurgency. Then he encounters young rebel Rhea.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33217/ghostbride.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33217","title":"The Ghost Bride","author":"by Yangsze Choo","description":"Set in 1890s Malaysia, this is the story of seventeen-year-old Li Lan, whose quiet life with her father is dramatically altered when he returns one evening with a proposition for her.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33198/stolen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33198","title":"Stolen","author":"by Lucy Christopher","description":"Sixteen-year-old Gemma has no idea what is happening to her when she is kidnapped from Bangkok Airport and finds herself trapped in the Australian outback.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26633/city-ofbones.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26633","title":"City of Bones","author":"by Cassandra Clare","description":"When Clary visits a nightclub, she discovers that she is one of the Shadowhunters - a group of demon-hunters living in a world of vampires, werewolves and warlocks.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33199/cruel-summer-juno-dawson.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33199","title":"Cruel Summer","author":"by Juno Dawson","description":"A year after Janey's suicide, her friends come back together for a holiday at a luxurious Spanish villa. Then an unexpected guest arrives, claiming to have evidence that Janey was murdered.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33079/after-iriss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33079","title":"After Iris","author":"by Natasha Farrant","description":"Given a video camera on her thirteenth birthday, Bluebell Gadsby sets out to document her life and her quirky, bohemian family","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33228/9781780620381.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33228","title":"Half Lives","author":"by Sara Grant","description":"Separated by several hundred years, Icie and Beckett are linked by a deadly secret.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32738/hostage-threed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32738","title":"Hostage Three","author":"by Nick Lake","description":"Amy's voyage across the world in a luxury yacht takes a nightmarish turn when her family's boat is captured by Somali pirates.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32795/9781471400339-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32795","title":"Red Ink","author":"by Julie Mayhew","description":"This beautifully-written coming of age story interrogates family, identity, memory and the myths and superstitions we create for ourselves.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33021/9780857560674-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33021","title":"The Boy With Two Heads","author":"by Andy Mulligan","description":"Richard Westlake is an altogether ordinary boy, until he inexplicably grows another head.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32971/9781471400360-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32971","title":"Paper Aeroplanes","author":"by Dawn O'Porter","description":"Growing up in Guernsey in the 1990s, timid Flo struggles to deal with her dysfunctional family life - until rebellious extrovert Renee unexpectedly befriends her.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24508/9780141318011-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24508","title":"How I Live Now","author":"by Meg Rosoff","description":"Fifteen-year-old New Yorker Daisy is sent to England to spend a summer with her unconventional cousins","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33077/9781471401350-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33077","title":"Friday Brown","author":"by Vikki Wakefield","description":"Friday Brown is cursed. Warned of the terrible fates of the women in her family, each of whom has met a mysterious death, she carries the weight of her ancestors on her shoulders.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33029/9781405265119-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33029","title":"Rose Under Fire","author":"by Elizabeth Wein","description":"When flying an Allied fighter plane from Paris to England, young American pilot Rose is captured by the Nazis and sent to a women's concentration camp.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33023/9780141345833-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33023","title":"The 5th Wave","author":"by Rick Yancey","description":"A few months ago Cassie's biggest problem was that the boy she liked didn't know she was alive. Now she is alone, fighting for survival in a world ravaged by an alien invasion.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33072/9781409562689-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33072","title":"The Lucy Variations","author":"by Sara Zarr","description":"Lucy once had a promising future as a concert pianist, but the incessant pressure from her family made her give it all up. Can she learn to love music again - this time on her own terms?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":229,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/229/","title":"Baby's First Books","list_description":"It's never too soon to start enjoying books and reading - and these engaging baby books are the perfect places to start.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24857/eachpeach.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24857","title":"Each Peach Pear Plum","author":"by Janet & Allan Ahlberg","description":"This classic book from author and illustrator team Janet and Allan Ahlberg is a real favourite with families","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30574/baby-s-catalogue.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30574","title":"The Baby's Catalogue","author":"by Janet and Allan Ahlberg","description":"This book's packed with lots of baby pictures and baby items. It's great for learning and making up stories - this fantastic book will lead to lots of talk with your child.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34225/baby-s-very-first-black-and-white-book-of-babies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34225","title":"Baby's very first black and white book: Babies","author":"by Stella Baggott","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34138/babys-treasure-hunt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34138","title":"Baby's Treasure Hunt","author":"by Priddy Books","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29470/9780230747722-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29470","title":"Dear Zoo","author":"by Rod Campbell","description":"This appealing story, in lift-the-flap, board-book format has been a favourite with toddlers ever since it was first published in 1982.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24858/veryhungrycaterpillar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24858","title":"The Very Hungry Caterpillar","author":"by Eric Carle","description":"Eric Carle's The Very Hungry Caterpillar deserves its reputation as a much-loved classic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34134/baby-surprises.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34134","title":"Baby Surprises!","author":"by Sarah Davis","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30585/sometimes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30585","title":"Sometimes","author":"by Emma Dodd","description":"This is a warm book about unconditional love. A perfect book for encouraging children to do what they want with reassuring support.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29128/9781406331264-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29128","title":"Ten Little Fingers and Ten Little Toes","author":"by Mem Fox & Helen Oxenbury","description":"This charming first book is perfect for new arrivals.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24855/wheresspot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24855","title":"Where's Spot?","author":"by Eric Hill","description":"This adorable picture book about Spot the dog is the first in the Spot series","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34220/babys-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34220","title":"Baby's Day","author":"by Little Tiger Kids","description":"Colourful, rhyming board book with photos of happy babies.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33822/slow-snail.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33822","title":"Slow Snail","author":"by Mary Murphy","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34629/what-a-busy-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34629","title":"What a... Busy Baby!","author":"by Rebecca Patterson","description":"Great just before naptime!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24860/elephant-bad-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24860","title":"The Elephant and the Bad Baby","author":"by Elfrida Vipont & Raymond Briggs","description":"One day, an elephant offers a baby a ride through the town, and the set off on a great adventure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30645/maisy-s-panda.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30645","title":"Where is Maisy's Panda?","author":"by Lucy Cousins","description":"With bold, eye-catching primary colours (which are easy for the eye to focus on), simple rhymes and repetition, and a series of flaps to lift, this book should appeal to any or all of the senses."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25514/orangebear-applepear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25514","title":"Orange Pear Apple Bear","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"Emily Gravett's colourful yet sparse illustrations cleverly depict a bumbling bear interacting in many different and imaginative ways with the fruit mentioned in the title.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24596/that-s-not-my-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24596","title":"That's Not My Bear...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"A different bear is introduced on each page of this colourful board book, but there is something not quite right about most of them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-4"}]}
{"id":230,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/230/","title":"Holiday Reads 2013","list_description":"Before you all jet off on holiday, don't forget to pack a book. We have searched the archive and put together a list of ten summer sizzlers you won't be able to put down!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28303/blind-assassin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28303","title":"The Blind Assassin","author":"by Margaret Atwood","description":"A novel which not only won the Booker Prize, but, more importantly, deserved to win it. Unmissable."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30346/the-beach.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30346","title":"The Beach","author":"by Alex Garland","description":"Adapted into a film starring Leonardo de Caprio, this book is a brutal contemporary reimagining of Lord of the Flies, told in a frenetic style that captures the heady narcotic rush of the traveller experience."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32768/9781780220833.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32768","title":"The Notable Brain of Maximilian Ponder","author":"by J W Ironmonger","description":"Ironmonger's wit and intelligence coupled with engaging anecdotes and eccentric characters keep the reader enthralled right to the very end"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27523/don-t-look-now-and-other-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27523","title":"Don't Look Now and Other Stories","author":"by Daphne du Maurier","description":"Don't Look Now, Daphne du Maurier's terrifying tale set in Venice, was memorably filmed by Nicolas Roeg","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32887/9780755358786-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32887","title":"Instructions for a Heatwave","author":"by Maggie O'Farrell","description":"This, Maggie O'Farrell's sixth book, absorbs the reader with its sensory intensity, and shows her at the peak of her story weaving powers."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32815/9781846689215.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32815","title":"The Last Girlfriend on Earth","author":"by Simon Rich","description":"...break-ups, regret, apocalyptic women-less futures and cavemen called Oog with relationship drama, abound."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32870/9781780221243.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32870","title":"Where'd You Go, Bernadette","author":"by Maria Semple","description":"Bernadette Fox is notorious. To Elgie Branch, a Microsoft wunderkind, she's his hilarious, volatile, talented, troubled wife. To fellow mothers at the school gate, she's a menace. To design experts, she's a revolutionary architect. And to 15-year-old Bee, she is..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32783/andalucianfriend.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32783","title":"The Andalucian Friend","author":"by Alexander Söderberg","description":"Bullets are flying. A speeding car is swerving in and out of the fast lane and the man in the passenger seat has something to be sorry for"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29599/after-the-fire-a-still-small-voice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29599","title":"After the Fire, A Still Small Voice","author":"by Evie Wyld","description":"A sweet, sun-drenched, heart-felt love affair. Evie Wyld's debut novel slips across hard-edged themes of masculine expression, war, paternal relationships and grief with such beauty and ease that it feels like she is already an old hand."}]}
{"id":231,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/231/","title":"Tales from Italy","list_description":"Heading to Italy this summer? We've put together a list of six books from Italian authors in translation. This selection includes bestsellers turned movies, short stories and thrilling debuts; doppio espresso is optional!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32048/9780857861979.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32048","title":"Me & You","author":"by Niccolò Ammaniti","description":"Lorenzo Cuni hovers on the edge of adulthood. A child who is all too aware of his status as an oustider, more intelligent and persipcacious than most, Lorenzo adapts his character to conform to his parents' and peers' expectations. Taking..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26522/the-savage-detectives.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26522","title":"The Savage Detectives","author":"by Roberto Bolaño","description":"New Year's Eve 1975: Arturo Belano and Ulises Lima leave Mexico City in a hurry, in a borrowed white Chevrolet Impala. Their mission is one of poetry."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26933/the-natural-disorder-of-things.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26933","title":"The Natural Disorder of Things","author":"by Andrea Canobbio","description":"Claudio Fratta is a gentle man, a garden designer, naturally solitary. He is obsessed by the need to take revenge on the loan shark who bankrupted his father, and with the pursuit of an enigmatic, alluring woman , one of..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26546/involuntary-witness.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26546","title":"Involuntary Witness","author":"by Gianrico Carofiglio","description":"An innovative take on the traditional crime novel, Guanfrico Carofiglio's debut novel tells the story of Guido Gerrieri, a litigator who is defending a Senegalese peddler accused of murdering a nine-year-old boy."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29799/gomorrah.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29799","title":"Gomorrah: Italy's Other Mafia","author":"by Roberto Saviano","description":"Published to coincide with the eponymous blockbuster film, Roberto Saviano's groundbreaking and compelling book is a major international bestseller."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27527/cavalleria-rusticana-and-other-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27527","title":"Cavalleria Rusticana and Other Stories","author":"by Giovanni Verga","description":"Love, adultery and honour are recurring themes in stories grounded in the opportunism and hardship of peasant life, set against the scorched landscapes of the slopes of Mount Etna and the Plain of Catania."}]}
{"id":232,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/232/","title":"An Indian Summer?","list_description":"Before we all pack away our flip flops and suncream, we've put togther a list of ten books that might just inspire the sun to stay out a bit longer! Pimms optional...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31691/9781843918561.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31691","title":"My Kind of Girl","author":"by Buddhadeva Bose","description":"The story begins in the waiting room of a provincial station, where, on a cold winter night only a few years after Indian independence, four random strangers find themselves stuck until dawn as a result of a railway accident"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28089/katha.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28089","title":"Katha: Short Stories by Indian Women","author":"by Urvashi Butalia","description":"Whether it is in the kitchen or elsewhere, Indian women's stories have been handed down from generation to generation, enriched and embroidered along the way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31409/fea008ca-13c2-44db-8e2d-d24866ff1251-img100-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31409","title":"The Pleasure Seekers","author":"by Tishani Doshi","description":"The dual heritages of India and Wales come together in this funny, bittersweet tale spanning four generations of Patels from dancer and poet, Tishani Doshi"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27000/sea-of-poppies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27000","title":"Sea of Poppies","author":"by Amitav Ghosh","description":"It's a combustible combination and Ghosh makes the most of it. From the first page he plunges the reader into the lives of the rich and poor, black and white, high caste and low, natives and colonials. He is damning..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30454/saraswati-park.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30454","title":"Saraswati Park","author":"by Anjali Joseph","description":"Saraswati Park is a book about loss and longing, love and regret. The prose sparkles like late afternoon sunshine and the characters hook you from their first introduction. This is a very special novel from a very special new talent."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32612/9781847803573-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32612","title":"Om Shanti, Babe","author":"by Helen Limon","description":"Cass is excited to be flying to Kerala with her Mum, dreaming of Bollywood glamour, new friends and pop idol Johnny Gold. But when she arrives in India, nothing is quite as she had imagined...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29852/freed-from.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29852","title":"Freed From Disgrace","author":"by Phanishwar Nath Renu","description":"Freed From Disgrace centres around Bela Gupta, a social worker and acretaker of women's hostel in the booming city of Patna. Bela's struggle to help those dependent upon her brings her into conflict with the forces of corruption, moral compromise..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27676/east-west.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27676","title":"East, West","author":"by Salman Rushdie","description":"In these stories Salman Rushdie examines the consequences when external forces pull his characters first in one direction, then the other."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31684/9781843918509.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31684","title":"Boyhood Days","author":"by Rabindranath Tagore","description":"Boyhood Days is Tagore's memoir of childhood. It's a short, vivid, fragmentary work, which can be read in one sitting"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31978/9780571275762.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31978","title":"Narcopolis","author":"by Jeet Thayil","description":"Narcopolis is dark, set in dank rooms, embued with the stench of human sweat, vomit, and desperation. Narcopolis is narrated by an opium pipe. Narcopolis will hypnotise you."}]}
{"id":234,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/234/","title":"Summer Books","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33235/9781406339673-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33235","title":"Splash, Anna Hibiscus!","author":"by Atinuke","description":"Anna Hibiscus is at the beach with her family. She wants someone to go in the sea and splash in the waves with her but they are all busy doing other things.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33809/brambly-summer-story.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33809","title":"Brambly Hedge - Summer Story","author":"by Jill Barklem","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30559/skip-through-the-season.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30559","title":"Skip through the Seasons","author":"by Stella Blackstone","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30590/bear-in-sunshine.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30590","title":"Bear in Sunshine","author":"by Stella Blackstone","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33810/paddingtoninthegarden.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33810","title":"Paddington in the Garden","author":"by Michael Bond","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31318/9781840111545-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31318","title":"To the Beach","author":"by Thomas Docherty","description":"Lovely story of a boy using his imagination to go on a trip to the seaside","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4months+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30357/toddlewoddle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30357","title":"Toddle Waddle","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"An ideal book for sharing - babies will love imitating the sounds in the text and pointing out details in the illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33828/zoe-beans-pirate.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33828","title":"Zoe and Beans: Pirate Treasure!","author":"by Chloe and Mick Inkpen","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32410/9781408824375-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32410","title":"Florentine and Pig Have a Very Lovely Picnic","author":"by Eva Katzler","description":"One morning Florentine and Pig decide to cook food for a picnic. But first of all, they need some apples for their apple and carrot muffins.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32256/9780552565783-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32256","title":"Sometimes I Feel Sunny","author":"by Gillian Shields","description":"An introduction for the youngest readers to the different feelings they experience, from sad to funny, angry to sunny, and even lost and small.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33808/i-heart-holidays.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33808","title":"I Heart Holidays (Martha and the Bunny Brothers)","author":"by Clara Vulliamy","description":""}]}
{"id":235,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/235/","title":"We love books!","list_description":"These delightful picture books celebrate the joy of books and reading.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29895/babies-love-books.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29895","title":"Babies Love Books","author":"by Laurence Anholt","description":"Given the chance, babies certainly do love books and the familiar scenes depicted amidst these lively pages show how and where opportunities to share a book present themselves.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33245/9780857630902-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33245","title":"Books Always Everywhere","author":"by Jane Blatt","description":"Big and small, wide and tall, there are all kinds of books to enjoy in this charming celebration of reading for even the youngest children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32843/9780857630476-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32843","title":"Open Very Carefully","author":"by Nick Bromley and Nicola O'Byrne","description":"A crocodile has invaded the pages of this picture book, and is causing chaos by gobbling up words!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27958/bewarestorybook-wolves.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27958","title":"Beware of the Storybook Wolves","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Lauren Child has created a truly original and hilarious story, and her lively and unique collage-style illustrations are a joy. Ideal for reassuring children who are scared of the dark.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31515/9781780080031-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31515","title":"Otto the Book Bear","author":"by Katie Cleminson","description":"A charming celebration of books and reading","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31209/charliecooksfavbook.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31209","title":"Charlie Cook's Favourite Book","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Axel Scheffler","description":"From pirates to dragons, aliens and ghosts, this book serves as a celebration of all stories, and a reminder of how one story can lead to another!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25021/wolves-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25021","title":"Wolves","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"This is a humorous, highly imaginative and original picture book and even comes with an alternative vegetarian ending!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25757/bookeating-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25757","title":"The Incredible Book Eating Boy","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"Henry loves books. However, his pleasure isn't derived from reading them but from eating them instead, and the more he eats, the smarter he gets.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25804/lulu-loves-library.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25804","title":"Lulu Loves the Library","author":"by Anna McQuinn","description":"Lulu has her library card, her rucksack full of borrowed books, and a big smile on her face, because it's Tuesday – and on Tuesdays Lulu and her mummy go to the library","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31572/9780230753136-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31572","title":"It’s a Book","author":"by Lane Smith","description":"Jackass, playing on his computer, wants to know what Monkey is up to. Monkey is reading a book","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31148/how-to-live-forever.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31148","title":"How to Live Forever","author":"by Colin Thompson","description":"At night, the book shelves come to life and the library is transformed into a bustling miniature city. But Peter discovers there is one important book missing...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29789/dog-loves-books.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29789","title":"Dog Loves Books","author":"by Louise Yates","description":"With an engaging hero and simple, understated text animated by witty, subtly coloured illustrations, this book about the sheer pleasure of books has a refreshing jaunty elegance.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":236,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/236/","title":"Starting school or nursery","list_description":"These picture books are perfect for children starting school or nursery. Why not share them together, so you can talk through any fears and anxieties?","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32472/topsy-and-tim.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32472","title":"Topsy and Tim Start School","author":"by Jean Adamson","description":"Find out what happens on the twins' first day at school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32473/starting-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32473","title":"Starting School","author":"by Janet and Allan Ahlberg","description":"Starting School by Janet and Allan Ahlberg is an enchanting picture book for reassuring children who are about to start school for the very first time."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24877/iam2small4school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24877","title":"I am Too Absolutely Small for School","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Lola is nearly big enough to go to school. But in her opinion she is still really quite small, and has far too many important things to keep her extremely busy at home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33270/9780007258680-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33270","title":"Come to School Too, Blue Kangaroo","author":"by Emma Chichester Clark","description":"Lily thinks Blue Kangaroo might be nervous about starting school – but in fact he can’t wait to have fun and make some new friends.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31505/9780007274680-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31505","title":"First Week at Cow School","author":"by Andy Cutbill","description":"This hilarious story celebrating difference and acceptance is told with charm and wonderfully illustrated with Russell Ayto's fun and wacky illustrations","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32407/9780330512282-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32407","title":"Goat Goes to Playgroup","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Julia Donaldson sets to work to reassure newcomers to playgroups everywhere in this picture book with a simple rhyming text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35219/chus-first-day-at-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35219","title":"Chu’s First Day at School","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"Chu the panda has a very big sneeze for such a little panda. And sometimes, when he sneezes, funny things happen. A colourful, hilarious tale about starting school for the first time.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-6","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30532/going2playschool.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30532","title":"Going to Playschool","author":"by Sarah Garland","description":"This book is engaging, colourful and very real: the story captures perfectly the mood of playschool."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27339/alfie-and-the-big-boys.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27339","title":"Alfie and the Big Boys","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Children will relish this warm tale of everyday life with illustrations overflowing with colour and vitality.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3 - 8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35235/bug-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35235","title":"First Day at Bug School","author":"by Sam Lloyd","description":"With bright bustling illustrations fizzing with quirky details and insect jokes, this cheery, rhyming introduction to starting school from a unique bugs-eye point of view is reassuring and fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31507/9780007361427-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31507","title":"Marshall Armstrong is New to Our School","author":"by David Mackintosh","description":"A thoughtful book about tolerance, acceptance and celebrating difference","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32504/9781849415019-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32504","title":"Knight School","author":"by Marilyn Singer","description":"Little Knight and Little Dragon are the best of friends and they can't wait to start school. But when will they have time to play together?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31479/harry-and-the-dinosours-go-to-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31479","title":"Harry and the Dinosaurs go to School","author":"by Ian Whybrow","description":"It's Harry's first day at school. He and his dinosaurs are very excited and perhaps a little bit nervous.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":237,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/237/","title":"Booktime Books 2013","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33272/2013-14-booktime-but-excuse-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33272","title":"But Excuse Me That is My Book","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Children will join Charlie, Lola and their friends on a trip to the library to look at all the different types of books that Lola might like to read. It is a warm and funny story about family, friends and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33273/tom-s-mad-mop.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33273","title":"Tom's Mad Mop","author":"by Celia Warren","description":"A bright and familiar story about playing with friends, which parents and teachers can use to help children in their own reading.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-5"}]}
{"id":238,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/238/","title":"The Ant Club autumn booklist","list_description":"Some of our favourite new books for sharing with your reception and Year 1 pupils this autumn. We hope there's something here for every child to enjoy.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35094/erica-s-elephant.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35094","title":"Erica’s Elephant","author":"by Sylvia Bishop","description":"Erica is surprised to find an elephant on her doorstep. When she invites him in, a fantastic friendship begins. This short chapter book for young readers is a delight from start to finish.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35048/zim-zam-zoom-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35048","title":"Zim Zam Zoom!","author":"by James Carter","description":"An exciting, action-packed introduction to poetry for younger children. Perfect for reading out loud, at bedtime, playtime or at school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35187/vanilla-ice-cream.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35187","title":"Vanilla Ice Cream","author":"by Bob Graham","description":"A curious little sparrow travels from a dusty Indian truck stop to a vast southern city across the ocean. This endearing picture book about how lives are interconnected is accompanied by gentle pen, ink and watercolour illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35068/alphonse.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35068","title":"Alphonse, That Is Not OK To Do!","author":"by Daisy Hirst","description":"This charming and very funny book about the ups and downs of sibling relationships perfectly captures the affection and frustration experienced by an older sibling - and the monsters are wonderfully expressive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35041/footpath-flowers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35041","title":"Footpath Flowers","author":"by JonArno Lawson","description":"A little girl spreads joy and colour through the grey townscape, when she picks and presents flowers from the pavements to the people and animals she meets. This wordless picture book is a beauty to behold.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35170/the-colour-monster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35170","title":"The Colour Monster","author":"by Anna Llenas","description":"An original and entertaining picture book using colour, collage-effect illustrations and a delightfully cute monster to help youngsters identify and understand different emotions.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34999/this-is-not-a-bedtime-story.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34999","title":"This is Not a Bedtime Story","author":"by Will Mabbitt","description":"Bedtime stories go bonkers in this inventive, subversive version of a traditionally restful night-time tale. Funny illustrations accompany the witty text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35009/secret-railway.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35009","title":"The Secret Railway","author":"by Wendy Meddour","description":"A magical, thrilling and slightly scary ‘first chapter’ book featuring the adventures of a brother and sister who stumble into a hidden world. Tense, imaginative and highly recommended.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35151/a-guide-to-sisters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35151","title":"A Guide to Sisters","author":"by Paula Metcalf","description":"A big sister imparts her wisdom on all things to do with having a new little sister in this fun and playful picture book. Smart, funny text from Paula Metcalf is matched perfectly with cute line drawings from Suzanne Barton.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35166/under-earth-under-water.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35166","title":"Under Earth, Under Water","author":"by Aleksandra and David Mizielinski","description":"This gorgeous large hardback explores what happens under the earth and in our oceans and seas in fantastically colourful and accessible double-page spreads. This is a really excellent example of nonfiction that is both comprehensive and fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35070/can-i-eat-that.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35070","title":"Can I Eat That?","author":"by Joshua David Stein and Julia Rothman","description":"A quirky combination of fact and fun, this distinctive picture book about food poses questions that inquisitive children typically ask, such as: 'If I eat jelly and I eat fish, can I eat jellyfish?' Stylish, witty and informative.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35078/harold-s-hungry-eyes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35078","title":"Harold’s Hungry Eyes","author":"by Kevin Waldron","description":"Young readers will love this story of hungry Harold the dog, and have a great time spotting all the original places that food has replaced normal everyday items. Kevin Waldron's artwork is bright and colourful with a quirky, modern use...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35083/introducing-teddy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35083","title":"Introducing Teddy","author":"by Jessica Walton","description":"Errol starts to notice that his teddy bear Thomas seems sad - he has always known he is a girl teddy, but is worried that Errol will not want to play with him anymore. A rare but much-needed picture book...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"}]}
{"id":239,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/239/","title":"Books relevant to disability","list_description":"A selection of recommended books that feature disability, are useful for discussing disability, or simply include a disabled character naturally and without comment.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31211/freddie-and-the-fairy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31211","title":"Freddie and the Fairy","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Karen George","description":"Freddie rescues a fairy who offers to grant him his every wish. The only problem is that she can't hear very well, and so his wishes result in some unexpected surprises...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25929/the-london-eye-mystery.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25929","title":"The London Eye Mystery","author":"by Siobhan Dowd","description":"Ted likes the weather, he also likes statistics and routine but his life is thrown into disarray when his Aunt Gloria and cousin Salim arrive, like a hurricane, to stay in London en-route to a new life in New York.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25746/moonbird.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25746","title":"Moonbird","author":"by Joyce Dunbar","description":"Orla doesn't answer when his parents call his name, and seems to be shut away in his own world. When he meets the mysterious moonbird he learns how to speak with his hands and listen with his eyes, but now...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30807/just-because.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30807","title":"Just Because","author":"by Rebecca Elliott","description":"This uplifting book focuses on a sibling relationship, as a little boy affectionately describes his older sister","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31960/9781409538585-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31960","title":"Mockingbird","author":"by Kathryn Erskine","description":"A high school shooting has left a small American town devastated.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25693/seal_surfer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25693","title":"Seal Surfer","author":"by Michael Foreman","description":"A welcome re-publication of Foreman's timeless and evocative account of a boy's relationship with life and death.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32456/moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32456","title":"Maggot Moon","author":"by Sally Gardner","description":"Combining conspiracy theory and dystopia, this hugely original novel is set in an alternate 1950s in which Britain is dominated by the ruthlessly oppressive forces of The Motherland.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32334/9781848775466-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32334","title":"Whisper","author":"by Chrissie Keighery","description":"Fifteen year old Demi is starting a new school – always a nerve-racking experience. However, for Demi, it represents a time of far more dramatic change, as her new school is a college for deaf students, a recent case of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32217/white-dolphins.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32217","title":"White Dolphin","author":"by Gill Lewis","description":"A young dolphin, washed up on the beach, unexpectedly brings Kara and Felix together. But the new friends must take on new challenges - finding out the truth about Kara's missing mother, and protecting the bay when it falls under...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31938/9781406327069-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31938","title":"Mia’s Magic Uncle","author":"by Lindsay McLeod","description":"Mia's uncle is indeed magic - and in more ways than one","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33035/9781847803887-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33035","title":"Max the Champion","author":"by Sean Stockdale and Alexandra Strick","description":"This inclusive book is about a boy who loves sport, his friends, and school - and has a vivid imagination","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30569/winniewitch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30569","title":"Winnie the Witch","author":"by Valerie Thomas","description":"This is the first of many stories about Winnie and her cat, Wilber. Winnie is a well-loved character, and the excellent illustrations are wild and wacky."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33200/onetwothree.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33200","title":"One, two, three... Run!","author":"by Carol Thompson","description":"Even a simple book for babies and toddlers can include disabled children naturally and subtly in its images - and this delightful board book proves the point.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29982/susan-laughs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29982","title":"Susan Laughs","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Susan can do so many things - she can laugh, sing, fly, dance, swim and much more. The final page of this wonderful book reveals that Susan is in a wheelchair, showing that 'disabled' doesn't mean 'disadvantaged'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":240,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/240/","title":"Epic fantasy","list_description":"Swords and sorcerers, kings and queens, elves and dragons, myth and magic... If you like Game of Thrones and Lord of the Rings, then try one of these epic fantasies.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32286/shadow-and-bonev.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32286","title":"Shadow and Bone","author":"by Leigh Bardugo","description":"In this richly-imagined and beautifully-written novel, Leigh Bardugo has created a vivid fantasy world drawing on Russian traditions and folklore","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30811/reckless..jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30811","title":"Reckless: The Petrified Flesh","author":"by Cornelia Funke","description":"A dark and dangerous world peopled by dwarves, shape-shifting vixen, mythical beasts and stone Goyls lurks on the other side of the ornate mirror in Jacob's father's study.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11-15"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32289/a-face-like-glasss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32289","title":"A Face Like Glass","author":"by Frances Hardinge","description":"This unusual and highly imaginative fantasy from Frances Hardinge is spellbinding","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32670/seraphinas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32670","title":"Seraphina","author":"by Rachel Hartman","description":"In a world in which humans and dragons have come to an uneasy truce in order to live side-by-side, shy court musician Seraphina has a secret to hide.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32383/9781408832332-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32383","title":"Throne of Glass","author":"by Sarah J Maas","description":"Infamous teenage assassin Celaena Sardothien has been condemned to a life sentence of hard labour in the salt mines of Endovier, until young Captain Westfall appears and offers her freedom, - but only if she'll compete in a deadly contest.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32571/9781408814932-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32571","title":"Magyk","author":"by Angie Sage","description":"Enter the world of Septimus Heap, Wizard Apprentice, in this fast-paced fantastical tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33318/alliesandassassins.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33318","title":"Allies and Assassins","author":"by Justin Somper","description":"When Prince Anders is assassinated, his younger brother Jared's life is dramatically turned upside down.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30906/bartimaeus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30906","title":"Bartimaeus: The Ring of Solomon","author":"by Jonathan Stroud","description":"A fantastic, fast-paced adventure story set in a vividly-realised world of Arabian and Biblical myth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32654/9780007458424-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32654","title":"The Hobbit","author":"by J R R Tolkien","description":"This well-loved fantasy story has delighed readers ever since its first publication in 1937.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":241,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/241/","title":"100 Best Books for Children: 0-5","list_description":"Take a look at our pick of the best books for 0-5 year olds from the last 100 years.   Are you looking for the best books to read to your baby? Our Bookstart website has everything you need, from booklists to tips!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24857/eachpeach.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24857","title":"Each Peach Pear Plum","author":"by Janet & Allan Ahlberg","description":"This classic book from author and illustrator team Janet and Allan Ahlberg is a real favourite with families","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31536/the-jolly-postman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31536","title":"The Jolly Postman or Other People’s Letters","author":"by Janet & Allan Ahlberg","description":"Brilliantly designed with lots of little details to spot, this old favourite will be enjoyed time and time again","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29103/the-snowman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29103","title":"The Snowman","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"James builds a snowman in the garden, then wakes up in the night to find that it has come to life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29764/gorillaa.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29764","title":"Gorilla","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"Hannah's favourite animals in the whole world are