use's Big Book of Fears","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"Little Mouse is scared of most things, from creepy crawlies and loud noises, to getting lost.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24855/wheresspot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24855","title":"Where's Spot?","author":"by Eric Hill","description":"This adorable picture book about Spot the dog is the first in the Spot series","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24861/9781862308053-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24861","title":"Dogger","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"When Dave loses his favourite toy, Dogger, he is desolate.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25161/lost-found.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25161","title":"Lost and Found","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"Once there was a sad, lonely penguin who appeared at the door of a young boy. The boy decided he must be lost, so he set off to find his home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24800/the-tiger-who-came-to-tea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24800","title":"The Tiger Who Came to Tea","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Sophie and her Mummy are having tea in the kitchen when in walks a hungry tiger who asks to stay to tea.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31784/9781406336832-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31784","title":"I Want My Hat Back","author":"by Jon Klassen","description":"A bear sets out in search of his hat - he loves his hat and he wants it back","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31101/not-now-bernard.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31101","title":"Not now, Bernard","author":"by David McKee","description":"The classic tale of Bernard, whose distracted parents fail to notice that their son has been eaten and replaced by a monster.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33277/9780718194420-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33277","title":"Meg and Mog","author":"by Helen Nicholl & Jan Pienkowski","description":"In this the first story about much-loved characters Meg the witch and Mog her cat, the pair go off to a wild Hallowe'en party with all the other witches","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30306/we-re-going-bear-hunt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30306","title":"We're Going on a Bear Hunt","author":"by Michael Rosen & Helen Oxenbury","description":"Follow a father and his family as they go out in search of a bear.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33280/9781849394468-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33280","title":"I Want My Potty!","author":"by Tony Ross","description":"The Little Princess hates nappies, and thinks there must be something better.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31373/where-the-wild-things-are.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31373","title":"Where the Wild Things Are","author":"by Maurice Sendak","description":"First published in 1963, this classic picture book will fascinate both children and adults, evoking the fierce intensity of childhood"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33276/the-cat-in-the-hat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33276","title":"The Cat in the Hat","author":"by Dr Seuss","description":"When Sally and her brother are left alone on a rainy day, they think they are in for a dull time - but then the Cat in the Hat appears.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24860/elephant-bad-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24860","title":"The Elephant and the Bad Baby","author":"by Elfrida Vipont & Raymond Briggs","description":"One day, an elephant offers a baby a ride through the town, and the set off on a great adventure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":242,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/242/","title":"100 Best Books: 6-8 years","list_description":"Take a look at our pick of the best books for 6-8 year olds from the last 100 years. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33287/the-enchanted-wood.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33287","title":"The Enchanted Wood","author":"by Enid Blyton","description":"When Joe, Beth and Frannie move into a new home, they discover a mysterious wood on their very doorstep.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30154/9780007261963-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30154","title":"A Bear Called Paddington","author":"by Michael Bond","description":"Paddington, the brown bear from darkest Peru, is found by the Brown family on Paddington Station with his hat, duffel coat and marmalade sandwiches.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33295/milly-molly-mandy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33295","title":"The Milly-Molly-Mandy Storybook","author":"by Joyce Lankester Brisley","description":"Milly-Molly-Mandy lives with her mother, father, uncle, aunt, grandmother and grandfather in a 'nice white cottage with a thatched roof'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33292/flat-stanley.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33292","title":"Flat Stanley","author":"by Jeff Brown","description":"Stanley Lambchop wakes up one morning to find he is only half an inch thick","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29113/cb-that-s-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29113","title":"Clarice Bean, That's Me","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Clarice Bean gives us a snapshot of her life and family in the book that launched a bestselling series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28946/rabbit-emily-brown.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28946","title":"That Rabbit Belongs to Emily Brown","author":"by Cressida Cowell","description":"Emily and her toy rabbit, Stanley, love to go on adventures together.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33296/bfg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33296","title":"The BFG","author":"by Roald Dahl","description":"The BFG stands for Big Friendly Giant, who unexpectedly spirits a little girl named Sophie out of bed, and into the land of the child-eating giants.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33285/9781405238182-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33285","title":"The Story of Babar","author":"by Jean De Brunhoff","description":"' In the great forest, a litle elephant was born. His name was Babar...'","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33289/9781405253345-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33289","title":"My Naughty Little Sister","author":"by Dorothy Edwards","description":"This affectionate portrait of family life is the story of a naughty three-year-old sister who is obstinate, inquisitive and full of mischief.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33291/asterix.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33291","title":"Asterix the Gaul","author":"by René Goscinny","description":"In a tiny corner of Brittany, one small village of indomitable Gauls hold out against the almighty, all-conquering Romans.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29181/9781845077495-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29181","title":"Amazing Grace","author":"by Mary Hoffman & Caroline Binch","description":"This classic story clearly communicates an inspiring message that anything is possible","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31343/moomin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31343","title":"Finn Family Moomintroll","author":"by Tove Jansson","description":"Moomintroll is cheerful and chubby and lives in the magical Moominvalley with his mother, Moominmamma, his father, Moominpappa and all of their friends.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33294/9780141318233-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33294","title":"The Queen's Nose","author":"by Dick King-Smith","description":"Harmony's Uncle Ginger sends her on a treasure trail - which ends in finding a 50p piece.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Inte