rust.org.uk/books/view/30118","title":"Stormbreaker","author":"by Anthony Horowitz","description":"Fourteen-year-old Alex Rider finds his life turned upside down on discovering that his late uncle wasn't a mild-mannered banker, but instead a field agent for MI6.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30036/the-kite-rider.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30036","title":"The Kite Rider","author":"by Geraldine McCaughrean","description":"Haoyou feels powerless when the man responsible for his father's death demands to marry his mother. Determined to support her himself, the young boy joins a travelling circus.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28824/knifeofneverlettinggo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28824","title":"The Knife of Never Letting Go","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"The first in a series, this enthralling sci-fi/fantasy novel grips readers throughout, presenting them with tough questions about identity, ethics and the nature of truth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31282/life-an-exploded-diagram.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31282","title":"Life: An Exploded Diagram","author":"by Mal Peet","description":"In this intelligent young adult novel, Clem's coming-of-age story of first love and burgeoning sexuality is woven around a tense account of the mounting Cuban Missile Crisis","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27725/northernlights-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27725","title":"Northern Lights","author":"by Philip Pullman","description":"This extraordinary fantasy is the first book in Philip Pullman's multi-award-winning His Dark Materials trilogy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33350/the-ruby-in-the-smoked.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33350","title":"The Ruby in the Smoke","author":"by Philip Pullman","description":"Determined to discover the truth about her father's tragic death, Sally Lockhart is plunged into a dangerous and terrifying adventure that takes her to the dark heart of Victorian London.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24773/mortalengines-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24773","title":"Mortal Engines","author":"by Philip Reeve","description":"London is on the move again: the traction city trawls the world on wheels, capturing and eating smaller towns.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29396/angus-thongs-and-full-frontal-snogging.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29396","title":"Angus, Thongs and Full-Frontal Snogging","author":"by Louise Rennison","description":"Welcome to the world of Georgia Nicolson - an angst-ridden teenage girl who keeps a diary to record the rollercoaster of emotions and experiences she faces every day","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24508/9780141318011-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24508","title":"How I Live Now","author":"by Meg Rosoff","description":"Fifteen-year-old New Yorker Daisy is sent to England to spend a summer with her unconventional cousins","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29268/revolver.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29268","title":"Revolver","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"'They say dead men tell no tales, but they're wrong. Even the dead tell stories.'","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24572/icapturethecastle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24572","title":"I Capture the Castle","author":"by Dodie Smith","description":"17-year-old Cassandra lives an eccentric existence with her bohemian family in a crumbling castle in the English countryside, in this delightful classic coming-of-age story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33346/9780261103573-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33346","title":"The Fellowship of The Ring","author":"by J R R Tolkien","description":"The first part of J R R Tolkien's epic masterpiece The Lord of the Rings, this is the story of young hobbit Frodo Baggins, who finds himself faced with an immense and terrible duty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":246,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/246/","title":"Black History Month Books","list_description":"To celebrate Black History Month we have put together ten of the best books by writers of African origin.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31063/things-fall-apart.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31063","title":"Things Fall Apart","author":"by Chinua Achebe","description":"Okonowo is the greatest warrior alive. His fame has spread like a bushfire in West Africa and he is one of the most powerful men of his clan. But he also has a fiery temper.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28108/purple-hibiscus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28108","title":"Purple Hibiscus","author":"by Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie","description":"Kambili, the 15-year-old protagonist, her brother Jaja, and their mother Beatrice would seem, from the outside, to have an ideal life under care of her father – the self-made businessman, newspaper proprietor and humble servant of the Catholic Church.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33338/we-need-new.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33338","title":"We Need New Names","author":"by NoViolet Bulawayo","description":"Through the eyes of a young girl, Darling, we are given a startling insight into events in Zimbabwe during a time of great change."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30404/broken-glass.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30404","title":"Broken Glass","author":"by Alain Mabanckou","description":"Alain Mabanckou's darkly glittering novel is an astringent portrait of post-colonial ennui and contemporary African social collapse, as well as a brilliantly witty homage to the written word."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30954/how-to-read-the-air.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30954","title":"How to Read the Air","author":"by Dinaw Mengestu","description":"Dinaw Mengestu's second novel is a thing of beauty, delicate fractured beauty, but beauty all the same. Weaving together two road trips tracing the same ground, Mengestu injects life into the old 'tracing your past to understand your present/change your..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30816/black-mamba-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30816","title":"Black Mamba Boy","author":"by Nadifa Mohamed","description":"Black Mamba Boy is a sumptuous and bittersweet journey book that starts in Aden in 1935 in war-torn Eritrea and Sudan, to Egypt, Palestine and to Britain."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32898/9780670919864-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32898","title":"Ghana Must Go","author":"by Taiye Selasi","description":"This is one of the year's best debuts and an accomplished masterstroke from the future voice of a generation."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27037/white-teeth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27037","title":"White Teeth","author":"by Zadie Smith","description":"Assured, audacious, good-hearted, impressive, raucous and funny: these are just some of the plaudits that greeted Zadie Smithís exuberant and incredibly successful debut novel."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31066/ake.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31066","title":"Ake: The Years of Childhood","author":"by Wole Soyinka","description":"The first volume of Wole Soyinka's acclaimed series of autobiographical works. This vivid, exuberant book is the author's account of his childhood in colonial Nigeria.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26524/wizard-of-the-crow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26524","title":"Wizard of the Crow","author":"by Ngugi Wa Thiongo","description":"Ngugi's most recent novel is a sprawling, fierce, scalding epic that turns a pitiless gaze on a postcolonial African dictatorship in the fictional country of Aburiria."}]}
{"id":247,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/247/","title":"Spooky tales for Halloween","list_description":"Prepare to be scared! Halloween is fast apporaching and we thought we'd get you in the mood with ten of the best scary stories. With classical tales of hauntings to modern psychological thrillers, these books are bound to have you checking under your bed at night!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32917/9780141326122-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32917","title":"Bunker Diary","author":"by Kevin Brooks","description":"Linus wakes up in a cold, dark, underground bunker with no recollection of how he got there.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27817/gothic-tales.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27817","title":"Gothic Tales","author":"by Elizabeth Gaskell","description":"Gaskell's chilling Gothic tales blend the real and the supernatural to eerie, compelling effect, and form a stark contrast to the social realism of Gaskell's novels."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33353/tales-from-dead.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33353","title":"Tales from the Dead of Night","author":"by Cecily Gayford","description":"Prepare to be scared! Collecting the best of classic ghost stories from E.Nesbit to Ruth Rendell, this anthology is the perfect match to any Halloween party.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28891/dark-paradise.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28891","title":"Dark Paradise","author":"by Rosa Liksom","description":"Liksom presents us with a naked world, a bare expose of everyday horror and love in a cold land."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27476/the-fall-of-the-house-of-usher-and-other-writings.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27476","title":"The Fall of the House of Usher and Other Writings","author":"by Edgar Allan Poe","description":"This selection of Poe's short fiction demonstrates his intense interest in aesthetic issues and the astonishing power and imagination with which he probed the darkest corners of the human mind.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33352/bellman-black.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33352","title":"Bellman and Black","author":"by Diane Setterfield","description":"When ten year-old William Bellman, known by his neighbours as someone who ‘could go to the good or the bad’, kills a rook with catapult, little does he know the action will impact his life forever."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27843/transformation.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27843","title":"Transformation","author":"by Mary Shelley","description":"Having squandered his wealth, Guido returns to claim the hand of the celestial Juliet, but finds himself censured by her father.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30899/an-awkward-age.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30899","title":"An Awkward Age","author":"by Anna Starobinets","description":"Everything in Starobinets' stories smacks of the sinister and perverse. An unnamed narrator assuages loneliness with a companion grown from mould, until the horrific smell alerts the authorities"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31198/roll-up-for-the-arabian-derby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31198","title":"Roll Up for the Arabian Derby","author":"by Susan Wicks","description":"Roll up for the Arabian Derby, a sinister fairground booth where children are tempted, become addicted and can never escape."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29808/cross-country-murder-song.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29808","title":"Cross Country Murder Song","author":"by Philip Wilding","description":"This work of contemporary noir is dark as they come and brilliantly executed within its non-linear skewed dissection of America."}]}
{"id":248,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/248/","title":"Visual impairment","list_description":"This list comprises books featuring characters who are blind as well as books which include characters with glasses and/or eye patches in a natural and positive way.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33362/9781406322187-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33362","title":"The Black Book of Colours","author":"by Menena Cottin & Rosana Faria","description":"A visually impaired boy introduces us to colours as he experiences them – through his senses of hearing, touch, smell and taste.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30353/the-great-big-book-of-families.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30353","title":"The Great Big Book of Families","author":"by Mary Hoffman","description":"Hoffman and Asquith celebrate the diversity of family life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32012/humpty-dumpty.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32012","title":"Humpty Dumpty","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"A simple board book featuring a well-known nursery rhyme with interactive text","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30652/lucys-picture.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30652","title":"Lucy's Picture","author":"by Nicola Moon & Alex Aycliffe","description":"It is art class at school and Lucy wants to make a picture for her grandfather when he comes to visit her.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33361/fliprapunzel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33361","title":"Rapunzel: Flip-up Fairy Tales","author":"by Simona Sanfilippo","description":"One of a series of ‘Flip-Up Fairy Tales’ which retell traditional stories with beautiful artwork and flaps to lift.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33035/9781847803887-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33035","title":"Max the Champion","author":"by Sean Stockdale and Alexandra Strick","description":"This inclusive book is about a boy who loves sport, his friends, and school - and has a vivid imagination","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30998/roger-gets-carried-away.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30998","title":"Roger Gets Carried Away","author":"by Barbara Todd and Rogé","description":"Roger is a little boy with a big imagination.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32123/9781406337785-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32123","title":"Mole's Sunrise","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Mole can't see the sunrise with his eyes because he is blind, but his friends help him to see it in his mind, and it is more beautiful than he had ever imagined. This simple story is a touching tale...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":249,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/249/","title":"Ghost stories","list_description":"The days are getting shorter, the nights are getting longer - what better time to curl up with a ghost story? Some of these stories are funny, others are scary, but all are certain to entertain young readers with a taste for all things spooky and spectral.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31737/9781849393218-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31737","title":"Haunted","author":"by Susan Cooper","description":"A scintillating selection of supremely scary tales from 11 well-known children’s authors","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32481/ghostknight.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32481","title":"Ghost Knight","author":"by Cornelia Funke","description":"At his new boarding school in Salisbury, Jon finds himself contronted by a terrifying and vengeful gang of ghosts that no one else can see.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29125/the-graveyard-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29125","title":"The Graveyard Book","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"After his family are killed, Bod is brought up in a graveyard by ghosts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33371/dialaghost.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33371","title":"Dial A Ghost","author":"by Eva Ibbotson","description":"Fulton Snodde-Brittle has gone to the Dial A Ghost agency with a fiendish plan - he wants to hire some terrifying ghosts to scare his 10-year-old nephew Oliver to death.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32522/9781471400117-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32522","title":"Constable & Toop","author":"by Gareth P Jones","description":"A Victorian funeral parlour is the setting for this exciting mystery that blends comedy with the dark, spooky and supernatural.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29793/frightfully-friendly-ghosties.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29793","title":"Frightfully Friendly Ghosties","author":"by Daren King","description":"When Pamela Fraidy gets locked in the attic with a big, leggy spider by a mean still-alive, her ghostie friends have to call on all their ingenuity to set her free.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-10"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28194/dust-n-bones-ten-ghost-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28194","title":"Dust 'n' Bones","author":"by Chris Mould","description":"Mould has adapted five classic short ghost stories and added five of his own invention in a similar vein.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31375/tomsmidnight-garden.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31375","title":"Tom's Midnight Garden","author":"by Philippa Pearce","description":"With no garden or children to play with Tom feels lonely and unhappy, until one night he hears the clock striking thirteen and discovers a secret garden."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33263/gothgirl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33263","title":"Goth Girl and the Ghost of a Mouse","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Fans of Chris Riddell's Ottoline books will love this quirky story about young heroine Ada Goth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33261/lockwood-co-the-screaming-staircased.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33261","title":"Lockwood & Co: The Screaming Staircase","author":"by Jonathan Stroud","description":"Best known for his sarcastic djinni creation Bartimaeus, Stroud returns with an equally engaging new series, this time following a young set of ghost hunters","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":250,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/250/","title":"Favourite translated children's books","list_description":"If you're interested in exploring children's books in translation, these well-loved favourites and award-winning titles offer the perfect places to start.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32195/9781907912085-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32195","title":"Mr Leon's Paris","author":"by Barroux","description":"Paris is beautifully rendered in moody beige, blue and orange in this retro-styled tale of French taxi driver Mr Leon and his multifarious taxi journeys around the city.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33285/9781405238182-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33285","title":"The Story of Babar","author":"by Jean De Brunhoff","description":"' In the great forest, a litle elephant was born. His name was Babar...'","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28881/toby-alone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28881","title":"Toby Alone","author":"by Timothee de Fombelle","description":"Winner of the 2009 Marsh Award for Children's Literature in Translation, this exciting adventure has a serious message about the wisdom of using up the Earth’s resources","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31485/9780857560087-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31485","title":"In The Sea There Are Crocodiles","author":"by Fabio Geda","description":"First published in Italian last year, the story of Enaiatollah Akbari's journey from Afghanistan to Italy has now been translated into English","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33291/asterix.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33291","title":"Asterix the Gaul","author":"by René Goscinny","description":"In a tiny corner of Brittany, one small village of indomitable Gauls hold out against the almighty, all-conquering Romans.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33297/tintin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33297","title":"The Adventures of Tintin","author":"by Hergé","description":"Resourceful junior reporter Tintin embarks on a series of exciting international adventures, accompanied by his faithful dog Snowy, in this favourite series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31343/moomin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31343","title":"Finn Family Moomintroll","author":"by Tove Jansson","description":"Moomintroll is cheerful and chubby and lives in the magical Moominvalley with his mother, Moominmamma, his father, Moominpappa and all of their friends.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32943/emil-and-the-detectives-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32943","title":"Emil and the Detectives","author":"by Erich Kästner","description":"Ten-year-old Emil is excited to be taking the train to Berlin on his own for the first time - but he doesn't like the look of his fellow passenger, the man in the bowler hat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31538/pippi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31538","title":"Pippi Longstocking","author":"by Astrid Lindgren","description":"Follow Pippi Longstocking on her amazing adventures as she moves into Villa Villekulla with a horse, a monkey, and a big suitcase of gold coins.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33019/9781782690009-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33019","title":"Oksa Pollock: The Last Hope","author":"by Anne Plichota and Cendrine Wolf","description":"The Oksa Pollock series has legions of fans all over the world, and this first installment leaves us in no doubt why.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31713/9781849415279-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31713","title":"Mrs Pepperpot’s Christmas","author":"by Alf Prøysen","description":"Mrs Pepperpot’s shrinking habit can be very inconvenient, especially when she wants to go shopping for Christmas presents","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33303/9780749707231-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33303","title":"The Little Prince","author":"by Antoine de Saint-Exupery","description":"An air pilot makes a forced landing deep in the Sahara Desert. There, he makes a mysterious Little Prince, who tells him a series of wise and enchanting stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31219/9781444001679-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31219","title":"The Midnight Palace","author":"by Carlos Ruiz Zafon","description":"In Calcutta in 1916, after the deaths of both their parents in bizarre circumstances, two babies are separated at birth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":251,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/251/","title":"Classics","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31536/the-jolly-postman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31536","title":"The Jolly Postman or Other People’s Letters","author":"by Janet & Allan Ahlberg","description":"Brilliantly designed with lots of little details to spot, this old favourite will be enjoyed time and time again","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34181/peepo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34181","title":"Peepo!","author":"by Janet & Allan Ahlberg","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29470/9780230747722-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29470","title":"Dear Zoo","author":"by Rod Campbell","description":"This appealing story, in lift-the-flap, board-book format has been a favourite with toddlers ever since it was first published in 1982.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24858/veryhungrycaterpillar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24858","title":"The Very Hungry Caterpillar","author":"by Eric Carle","description":"Eric Carle's The Very Hungry Caterpillar deserves its reputation as a much-loved classic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28376/cl-tomato.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28376","title":"I Will Not Ever Never Eat a Tomato","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Charlie tricks his younger sister, Lola - an extremely fussy eater - into eating all her least favourite foods.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24855/wheresspot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24855","title":"Where's Spot?","author":"by Eric Hill","description":"This adorable picture book about Spot the dog is the first in the Spot series","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30306/we-re-going-bear-hunt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30306","title":"We're Going on a Bear Hunt","author":"by Michael Rosen & Helen Oxenbury","description":"Follow a father and his family as they go out in search of a bear.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33276/the-cat-in-the-hat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33276","title":"The Cat in the Hat","author":"by Dr Seuss","description":"When Sally and her brother are left alone on a rainy day, they think they are in for a dull time - but then the Cat in the Hat appears.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24860/elephant-bad-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24860","title":"The Elephant and the Bad Baby","author":"by Elfrida Vipont & Raymond Briggs","description":"One day, an elephant offers a baby a ride through the town, and the set off on a great adventure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":252,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/252/","title":"Ten True Tales","list_description":"Fiction not for you? We have put together a list of ten fantastic non-fiction titles to suit all tastes!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29661/we-can-t-all-be-astronauts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29661","title":"We Can't All Be Astronauts","author":"by Tim Clare","description":"Stand up poet Tim Clare's memoir of trying to write and publish the perfect book, mired by peer-jealousy and depression, is the best tool for any budding writer wanting an insight into the creative process."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32312/9780224096690.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32312","title":"Jerusalem","author":"by Guy Delisle","description":"...a dazzling brilliant book that is subtly political, never heavy-handed and always cast with a fair eye.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33320/georgian-london.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33320","title":"Georgian London","author":"by Lucy Inglis","description":"Lucy Inglis's cracking debut is about London and the Georgians who inhabited it. Taking geographic areas in turn, Lucy brings to life the people and places with a dash of humour and real primary research."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29659/long-walk-to-freedom.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29659","title":"Long Walk to Freedom","author":"by Nelson Mandela","description":"Long Walk to Freedom discloses a strong and generous spirit that refused to be broken under the most trying circumstances - a spirit in which just about everybody can find something to admire.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 16+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28932/stuart-a-life-backwards.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28932","title":"Stuart","author":"by Alexander Masters","description":"Masters salutes the painful, schizophrenic life of Stuart Shorter, but this is also an angry book about the way society treats those who have been horribly abused and abandoned. It was a long time in the writing, but A Life..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25886/do-not-pass-go.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25886","title":"Do Not Pass Go","author":"by Tim Moore","description":"A nice idea, this: a jaunt around the streets of London immortalised on the Monopoly board, looking back to their hectic heydays as well as at the present state of them, with a little bit of Monopoly history and folklore..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31958/9781847082534.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31958","title":"Londoners","author":"by Craig Taylor","description":"So much has been written about London, from Dickens to Ackroyd to Monica Ali to Patrick Hamilton and on and on and more and more. Craig Taylor, the brilliantly funny author of A Million Tiny Plays About Britain has taken..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28122/the-partly-cloudy-patriot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28122","title":"The Partly Cloudy Patriot","author":"by Sarah Vowell","description":"Vowell’s secret is that she never gets bogged down in her numerous and varied subjects. She is particularly adept at including personal anecdotes that somehow always appear to be relevant. In one 14-page chapter, she manages to write about President..."}]}
{"id":253,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/253/","title":"Your favourite children's books","list_description":"After much debate and discussion, we put together our list of our 100 best children's fiction books from the last 100 years - but what did you think?  We invited you to let us know which titles you thought were missing. Here's our list of some of the great books that didn't make our final cut, but that you told us were your favourites.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33400/9781849411110-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33400","title":"Over Sea, Under Stone","author":"by Susan Cooper","description":"On holiday in Cornwall, Simon, Jane and Barney discover an ancient map in the attic of the Grey House, where they are staying with their much-loved but mysterious Great Uncle Merry.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30249/httyd_jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30249","title":"How to Train Your Dragon","author":"by Cressida Cowell","description":"Hiccup Horrendous Haddock III was an incredible sword-fighter, dragon-whisperer and the greatest Viking hero who ever lived.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30283/charlie-chocolatefactory.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30283","title":"Charlie and the Chocolate Factory","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"Roald Dahl's wicked sense of humour is perfectly in evidence in this marvellously imaginative classic story, which has been loved by generations of children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28969/gruffalo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28969","title":"The Gruffalo","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Axel Scheffler","description":"In this much-loved picture book, a little mouse walks through the woods and encounters a fox, an owl and a snake.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33401/9780571302246-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33401","title":"The Iron Man","author":"by Ted Hughes","description":"Subtitled 'a children's story in five nights' this powerful, moving and beautifully-written fable from poet Ted Hughes is a true modern classic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28983/the-knife-that-killed-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28983","title":"The Knife That Killed Me","author":"by Anthony McGowan","description":"Paul isn't one of the tough kids, but when he ends up delivering a message from Roth, the terrifying school bully, he finds himself drawn into a dangerous rivalry.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24935/cherub.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24935","title":"CHERUB: The Recruit","author":"by Robert Muchamore","description":"In the first book in Robert Muchamore's spectacular series, James is recruited into the ranks of CHERUB - a secret organisation which trains children as spies.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30573/peace-at-last2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30573","title":"Peace At Last","author":"by Jill Murphy","description":"The hour is late and Mr Bear is tired. But he just can't sleep - however hard he tries, all he can hear are the noises in the house.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32186/9780552565974.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32186","title":"Wonder","author":"by R J Palacio","description":"August ('Auggie') Pullman can't help but stand out - he was born with a severe facial deformity. Written in the first person, Wonder follows Auggie as he experiences more than the usual ups-and-downs of friendships, family and school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33402/wolfbrother.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33402","title":"Wolf Brother","author":"by Michelle Paver","description":"Twelve-year-old Torak sees his father murdered by a terrible demon in the form of a bear. With his dying breath, Torak's father tells his son that he is the only one who can stop it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31375/tomsmidnight-garden.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31375","title":"Tom's Midnight Garden","author":"by Philippa Pearce","description":"With no garden or children to play with Tom feels lonely and unhappy, until one night he hears the clock striking thirteen and discovers a secret garden."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25800/9780099572855-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25800","title":"The Silver Sword","author":"by Ian Serrailier","description":"In the chaos of World War II, Ruth, Edek and Bronia are separated from their parents, and left alone to fend for themselves, hiding from the Nazis in the ruins of their city.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33403/9780192753922-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33403","title":"Eagle of the Ninth","author":"by Rosemary Sutcliff","description":"In AD 117AD, the Ninth Legion marched into the mists of northern Britain... and were never seen again.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":254,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/254/","title":"Top 10 Children's Books","list_description":"You voted in your thousands to tell us your favourite books on our list of the top 100 best children's books from the last century. This is your top 10 of the best children's books from the past 100 years.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24858/veryhungrycaterpillar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24858","title":"The Very Hungry Caterpillar","author":"by Eric Carle","description":"Eric Carle's The Very Hungry Caterpillar deserves its reputation as a much-loved classic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29230/hungergames.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29230","title":"The Hunger Games","author":"by Suzanne Collins","description":"Welcome to Panem: its Capitol repressively rules twelve satellite Districts, enslaving the populations as workers and controlling them through hunger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33296/bfg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33296","title":"The BFG","author":"by Roald Dahl","description":"The BFG stands for Big Friendly Giant, who unexpectedly spirits a little girl named Sophie out of bed, and into the land of the child-eating giants.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33305/the-lion-the-witch-the-wardrobe.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33305","title":"The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe","author":"by C S Lewis","description":"When Peter, Susan, Edmund and Lucy - step through a wardrobe door in the strange country house where they are staying, they find themselves in the land of Narnia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33284/winnie-the-pooh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33284","title":"Winnie-the-Pooh","author":"by A A Milne","description":"No child's library could be complete without A A Milne's stories about Pooh, Christopher Robin and their friends in the Hundred Acre Wood.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27725/northernlights-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27725","title":"Northern Lights","author":"by Philip Pullman","description":"This extraordinary fantasy is the first book in Philip Pullman's multi-award-winning His Dark Materials trilogy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30267/9780747558194-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30267","title":"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone","author":"by J K Rowling","description":"After the misery of life with his ghastly aunt and uncle, Harry Potter is delighted to have the chance to embark on an exciting new life at the Hogwart's School of Wizardry and Witchcraft.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33276/the-cat-in-the-hat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33276","title":"The Cat in the Hat","author":"by Dr Seuss","description":"When Sally and her brother are left alone on a rainy day, they think they are in for a dull time - but then the Cat in the Hat appears.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33346/9780261103573-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33346","title":"The Fellowship of The Ring","author":"by J R R Tolkien","description":"The first part of J R R Tolkien's epic masterpiece The Lord of the Rings, this is the story of young hobbit Frodo Baggins, who finds himself faced with an immense and terrible duty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33290/charlottes-web.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33290","title":"Charlotte's Web","author":"by E B White","description":"This is the tale of how a little girl named Fern - with the help of a friendly talking spider called Charlotte - saved her pig, Wilbur, from the usual fate of nice fat little pigs.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"}]}
{"id":256,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/256/","title":"A Winter's Tale","list_description":"  A list of winter books that feature dysfunctional families, alternative Christmas yarns and tales of the fantastic.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27403/sleep-with-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27403","title":"Sleep With Me","author":"by Joanna Briscoe","description":"This sensual and psychologically disturbing novel is compulsively readable."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32816/9781448134380.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32816","title":"Byron Easy","author":"by Jude Cook","description":"Byron Easy, failed poet, failed philanderer, dropout and cuckold, shares little with his literary namesake."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28420/9780141033587.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28420","title":"A Spell of Winter","author":"by Helen Dunmore","description":"As the world outside moves towards war, Catherine and Rob are deeply involved in their own conflict. But gradually the spell of winter starts to weaken, and Catherine begins to free herself from the past in this haunting, involving tale."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25879/the-corrections.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25879","title":"The Corrections","author":"by Jonathan Franzen","description":"If you look beyond the hyperbole that surrounded The Corrections upon its publication, you will find a marvellously entertaining, thought-provoking, moving and laugh-out-loud hilarious book. Even if you never see the metaphor of 'family-as-America-in-microcosm, state-of-the-nation, terminal-decline etc etc' supposedly contained..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32179/snow-child.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32179","title":"The Snow Child","author":"by Eowyn Ivey","description":"The tough existence of frontier life is detailed without sentiment by Ivey, but with a bracing beauty in the tradition of the Russian fairytale it references."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29715/even-the-dogs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29715","title":"Even the Dogs","author":"by Jon McGregor","description":"The new book from acclaimed author Jon McGregor is nothing short of intense. Filled with hope and fury, it is a poetic mediation on the lives and deaths of those who have fallen through the cracks."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30324/he-good-man-jesus-and-the-scoundrel-christ.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30324","title":"The Good Man Jesus and the Scoundrel Christ","author":"by Philip Pullman","description":"Jesus is a passionate, charismatic preacher, while Christ is his cynical and introspective twin, with an eye for posterity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32437/9780977857616.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32437","title":"A Dream in Polar Fog","author":"by Yuri Rytkheu","description":"A Dream in Polar Fog is one of these stories: a gorgeous symphony in arctic colours that's by turns tender, funny, tragic and grim"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32754/5fb3904a-2a22-43c7-99f0-aeec34eba5f3-img100.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32754","title":"Tenth of December","author":"by George Saunders","description":"A new short story collection from George Saunders and the birds are singing, the internet isn't buffering, the sun is out. This master of the form isn't the most prolific of short story writers so this new collection is cause..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29629/the-atheist-s-guide-to-christmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29629","title":"The Atheist's Guide to Christmas","author":"by Ariane Sherine","description":"42 atheist celebrities, comedians, scientists and writers give their funny and serious tips for enjoying the Christmas season."}]}
{"id":257,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/257/","title":"Christmas Gifts for Children 2013","list_description":"Looking for the perfect gifts this Christmas? Check out our list of great books that children will love finding under the tree or in their Christmas stocking this year","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33407/9780857532671-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33407","title":"Doll Bones","author":"by Holly Black","description":"Zach, Poppy and Alice have been friends for as long as they can remember - but now they are twelve, things are beginning to change.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33262/iremonger-heap-housed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33262","title":"Iremonger: Heap House","author":"by Edward Carey","description":"At the heart of Heap House, amongst the piles of rubbish that cover the London borough of Filching, Clod Iremonger can hear his bath-plug speaking to him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33406/9780230764811-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33406","title":"Aunt Amelia","author":"by Rebecca Cobb","description":"'We were in a bad mood. Aunt Amelia was coming to look after us. We didn't know who Aunt Amelia was and we didn't want looking after.'","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33212/thedaythecrayonsquite.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33212","title":"The Day the Crayons Quit","author":"by Drew Daywalt & Oliver Jeffers","description":"Award-winning illustrator and artist Oliver Jeffers has teamed up with film writer and director Drew Daywalt to create this gorgeously colourful picture book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33341/9780230769885-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33341","title":"Sugarlump and the Unicorn","author":"by Julia Donaldson & Lydia Monks","description":"Julia Donaldson and Lydia Monks have teamed up to create another delightful picture book, complete with sparkly glitter on each page.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33317/gaiman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33317","title":"Fortunately the Milk","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"When Dad goes out to get some milk from the corner shop, a host of completely unexpected adventures befall him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33384/9781780621494-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33384","title":"Tinder","author":"by Sally Gardner & David Roberts","description":"Award-winning author Sally Gardner teams up with David Roberts to put a new spin on Hans Christian Andersen’s classic fairy-tale The Tinder Box in this dark and gripping tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33084/9781909263086-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33084","title":"Wild","author":"by Emily Hughes","description":"A little girl grows up in the wild woods, taught to talk by the birds, eat by the bears, and to play by the foxes. Then some very strange animals arrive and take her away.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33225/9780857078414.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33225","title":"Eleanor's Eyebrows","author":"by Timothy Knapman & David Tazzyman","description":"Eleanor declares her eyebrows are two silly, scruffy, hairy, little bits of fluff - but they are deeply offended","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33408/9781844089888-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33408","title":"Emily of New Moon","author":"by L M Montgomery","description":"When Emily's beloved father dies, she is sent to live at New Moon with her strict Aunt Elizabeth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33419/9780007395354-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33419","title":"Of Lions and Unicorns","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"A variety of short stories and extracts from Michael Morpurgo, 'The Nation’s Favourite Storyteller’ are collected in this lovely gift edition.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33434/9781843914747-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33434","title":"The Story of the Treasure Seekers","author":"by E Nesbit","description":"The first book from classic children's author E Nesbit, this is the much-loved story of the Bastable family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33438/9781848778245-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33438","title":"Walk This World","author":"by Lotta Nieminen","description":"This gorgeously-produced book from illustrator and graphic designer Lotta Nieminen will take young readers on a tour of the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33237/9781909263147-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33237","title":"Hilda and the Troll","author":"by Luke Pearson","description":"Blue-haired explorer Hilda has an uncanny ability to find weird and wonderful adventures and befriend peculiar creatures.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33269/9780192734556-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33269","title":"Oliver and the Seawigs","author":"by Philip Reeve and Sarah McIntyre","description":"Philip Reeve and Sarah McInytre have joined forces to create a wonderfully wacky nautical tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33263/gothgirl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33263","title":"Goth Girl and the Ghost of a Mouse","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Fans of Chris Riddell's Ottoline books will love this quirky story about young heroine Ada Goth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33387/9781780080147-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33387","title":"Yeti and the Bird","author":"by Nadia Shireen","description":"Yeti is all alone in the forest: he is so big and scary that all the animals leave him alone. Then one day a funny little orange bird turns up","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33261/lockwood-co-the-screaming-staircased.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33261","title":"Lockwood & Co: The Screaming Staircase","author":"by Jonathan Stroud","description":"Best known for his sarcastic djinni creation Bartimaeus, Stroud returns with an equally engaging new series, this time following a young set of ghost hunters","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33432/9780007453566-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33432","title":"The Demon Dentist","author":"by David Walliams","description":"Strange things are happening in the dead of night. Children who put a tooth under the pillow for the tooth fairy wake to find... a dead slug; a live spider; or hundreds of earwigs...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33392/9780552571524-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33392","title":"Dot.","author":"by Randi Zuckerberg and Joe Berger","description":"Dot is an expert in electronic devices - she knows how to tap, to swipe, to share and to talk. But when she gets tired of being online, it's time to go outside and reboot, recharge and restart!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":258,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/258/","title":"Christmas Gifts for Teenagers 2013","list_description":"Looking for the perfect book to give a teenager to read this Christmas? Look no further than our list of some of the must-read titles that teens and young adults will want to find under the tree this year.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33316/coldest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33316","title":"The Coldest Girl in Coldtown","author":"by Holly Black","description":"Welcome to Coldtown. Once you enter, you can never leave. Delightfully dark and gorgeously gothic, it is certain to enchant fans of all things chilling and supernatural.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33430/9780141348940-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33430","title":"Doctor Who: 11 Doctors, 11 Stories","author":"by Eoin Colfer et al","description":"This anthology brings together 11 new Doctor Who stories, one for each of the 11 Doctors, written by some of the biggest names in writing for children and teenagers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33264/vivianversus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33264","title":"Vivian Versus the Apocalypse","author":"by Katie Coyle","description":"Sixteen-year-old Vivian Apple is awaiting the predicted 'Rapture' with a healthy degree of scepticism.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33385/9781471402272-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33385","title":"The Isobel Journal","author":"by Isobel Harrop","description":"Subtitled ‘Just a Northern Girl from Where Nothing Really Happens’, this beautifully-presented book from 18-year-old debut author Isobel Harrop is a vivid scrapbook of teenage life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33319/russian-rouletted.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33319","title":"Russian Roulette","author":"by Anthony Horowitz","description":"An international contract killer has been given his orders. His next target is a fourteen-year-old spy by the name of Alex Rider.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33333/teardrops.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33333","title":"Teardrop","author":"by Lauren Kate","description":"Ever since her beloved mother died in an astonishing freak accident, Eureka has had little to live for - but then she meets Anders, a strange boy who insists she too is in terrible danger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33256/everyday.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33256","title":"Every Day","author":"by David Levithan","description":"Every day, A wakes up in a different body.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33266/ness.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33266","title":"More Than This","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"'Haven't you ever felt like there has to be more? Like there's more out there somewhere, just beyond your grasp, and if you could only get to it?'","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33267/picture-me-goned.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33267","title":"Picture Me Gone","author":"by Meg Rosoff","description":"Twelve-year-old Mila has a talent for noticing things that other people don't.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33433/eleanor-parks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33433","title":"Eleanor & Park","author":"by Rainbow Rowell","description":"Set over the course of one school year in 1986, this is a beautifully-written love story about two high school outsiders","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33418/9780552571340.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33418","title":"Phoenix","author":"by S F Said","description":"Lucky is on the run and joins up with a group of aliens - refugees from the ongoing war between aliens and humans - who agree to help Lucky find his father. A thrilling space adventure, full of suspense, action,...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33440/song.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33440","title":"This Song Will Save Your Life","author":"by Leila Sales","description":"When high school misfit Elise stumbles upon an underground indie club night, Start, she unexpectedly finds a place she belongs","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33431/9781406329889-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33431","title":"Dark Satanic Mills","author":"by Marcus & Julian Sedgwick","description":"In a Britain laid to waste by catastrophic global warming, a motorcycle courier, Christy, and an atheist campaigner are on the run.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33298/the-bone-seasond.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33298","title":"The Bone Season","author":"by Samantha Shannon","description":"The year is 2059 and Paige Mahoney is breaking the law just by being alive. Her psychic powers, which allow her to enter the minds of others and read their thoughts, make her public enemy number one in the new...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"}]}
