{"id":270,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/270/","title":"Award-winning adaptations","list_description":"It seems to be Awards season - BAFTAs, Costa Book Awards, The Oscars - not to mention the constant activity around our very own Kim Scott Walwyn Prize and the BBC National Short Story Award in partnership with Book Trust.  So this month's booklist is dedicated to award-winning book adaptations, from the fantasic to the gritty - there's something for everyone.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29623/bridget-jones.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29623","title":"Bridget Jones' Diary","author":"by Helen Fielding","description":"Bridget Jones wants to have it all - and once she's given up smoking and got down to 8st 7 she will."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31181/the-great-gatsby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31181","title":"The Great Gatsby","author":"by F Scott Fitzgerald","description":"Jay Gatsby is the man who has everything. But one thing will always be out of his reach ...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31187/one-flew-over-the-cuckoo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31187","title":"One Flew Over the Cuckoo’s Nest","author":"by Ken Kesey","description":"Boisterous, ribald, and ultimately shattering, Ken Kesey's One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest is the seminal novel of the 1960s that has left an indelible mark on the literature of our time."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31188/the-constant-gardener.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31188","title":"The Constant Gardener","author":"by John le Carre","description":"Tessa Quayle has been horribly murdered on the shores of Lake Turkana in Northern Kenya, the birthplace of mankind."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29800/city-of-god.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29800","title":"City of God","author":"by Paulo Lins","description":"Based on a true story, this is a sprawling, magnificently told epic about the history of gang life in Rio's favelas."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29799/gomorrah.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29799","title":"Gomorrah: Italy's Other Mafia","author":"by Roberto Saviano","description":"Published to coincide with the eponymous blockbuster film, Roberto Saviano's groundbreaking and compelling book is a major international bestseller."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32654/9780007458424-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32654","title":"The Hobbit","author":"by J R R Tolkien","description":"This well-loved fantasy story has delighed readers ever since its first publication in 1937.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31194/trainspotting.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31194","title":"Trainspotting","author":"by Irvine Welsh","description":"REPRESENTING UNITED KINGDOM This novel looks at life in the dark underside of Edinburgh, the AIDS capital of Europe, through the jaded eyes and harsh vernacular of heroin addict Mark Renton, who is sick of his friends, sick with the..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31955/9780552773898-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31955","title":"The Book Thief","author":"by Markus Zusak","description":"A powerful story narrated by Death, about: a girl, an accordionist, some fanatical Germans, a Jewish fist fighter, and quite a lot of thievery","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":271,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/271/","title":"Bears","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31397/9781406323429-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31397","title":"A Visitor for Bear","author":"by Bonny Becker","description":"Bear likes to be on his own until a mouse turns up and teaches him that sharing experiences is far better than being on your own","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30590/bear-in-sunshine.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30590","title":"Bear in Sunshine","author":"by Stella Blackstone","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33038/9781904550198-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33038","title":"Goldilocks and the Three Bears","author":"by Estelle Corke","description":"The much-loved story of Goldilocks and the Three Bears is retold in this story from Child's Play's Flip-up Fairy Tale series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31392/9780857630025-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31392","title":"Bizzy Bear: Fun on the Farm","author":"by Benji Davies","description":"Babies and toddlers will enjoy this sturdy board book with lots of sliders and tabs to push and pull","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33829/hugless-douglas-big-sleep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33829","title":"Hugless Douglas and the Big Sleep","author":"by David Melling","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30306/we-re-going-bear-hunt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30306","title":"We're Going on a Bear Hunt","author":"by Michael Rosen & Helen Oxenbury","description":"Follow a father and his family as they go out in search of a bear.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32809/9781848950337-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32809","title":"Don't Wake the Bear, Hare!","author":"by Steve Smallman","description":"It's the day of the spring party, but all the woodland animals are nervous when they see a big brown bear sleeping in the old hollow tree","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25526/cantusleeplilbear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25526","title":"Can't You Sleep, Little Bear?","author":"by Martin Waddell","description":"Little Bear just can't get to sleep because he is afraid of the dark. Big Bear is patient and brings bigger and bigger lanterns to keep away the darkness. Still Little Bear is afraid, so Big Bear takes him outside...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25514/orangebear-applepear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25514","title":"Orange Pear Apple Bear","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"Emily Gravett's colourful yet sparse illustrations cleverly depict a bumbling bear interacting in many different and imaginative ways with the fruit mentioned in the title.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24596/that-s-not-my-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24596","title":"That's Not My Bear...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"A different bear is introduced on each page of this colourful board book, but there is something not quite right about most of them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-4"}]}
{"id":272,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/272/","title":"Family","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33705/daddy-hero-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33705","title":"Daddy is My Hero","author":"by Dawn Richards and Jane Massey","description":"Fantasy, fun and fancy dress in this tender and touching tribute to heroic Dads!"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33144/9780954737382.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33144","title":"I’m not cute!","author":"by Jonathan Allen","description":"Baby Owl is fed up. In fact, he’s furious. He sets off for a walk in the woods but kangaroo, fox and squirrel won’t leave him alone. They insist on picking him up, hugging him and telling him how cute...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25027/there-s-a-house-inside-my-mummy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25027","title":"There's A House Inside My Mummy","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"This is just the book to explain to inquisitive children what going on inside mum during pregnancy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29896/9781408309575-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29896","title":"I Love My Mummy","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"What is it about Mummies that makes them so lovable and so very special?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34841/i-love-you-more-and-more.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34841","title":"I Love You More And More","author":"by Nicky Benson","description":"Bear and Cub love roaming through their world. And as they roam, Bear explains how much she loves Cub. The deceptively simple rhyming text celebrates the solidity of this parent and child bond, with stylish double-page illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29326/what-does-daddy-do.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29326","title":"What Does Daddy Do?","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"One day at nursery, the children begin to discuss what their daddies do - which gets Daisy wondering about her own Daddy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24365/my-dad.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24365","title":"My Dad","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"A young boy proudly describes his father (a big, friendly, unshaven dad, sporting an old dressing gown).","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25557/my-mum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25557","title":"My Mum","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"All small children love their mums and in this colourful and entertaining picture book, Anthony Browne explains exactly why.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33971/miffy-and-the-new-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33971","title":"Miffy and the New Baby","author":"by Dick Bruna","description":"Miffy's mummy and daddy have some very exciting news, Miffy is going to be a big sister!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33406/9780230764811-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33406","title":"Aunt Amelia","author":"by Rebecca Cobb","description":"'We were in a bad mood. Aunt Amelia was coming to look after us. We didn't know who Aunt Amelia was and we didn't want looking after.'","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30580/full-of-love.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30580","title":"Full, Full, Full of Love","author":"by Trish Cooke","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30585/sometimes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30585","title":"Sometimes","author":"by Emma Dodd","description":"This is a warm book about unconditional love. A perfect book for encouraging children to do what they want with reassuring support.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30552/my-brother_jj.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30552","title":"My Big Brother JJ","author":"by Odette Elliott and Patrice Aggs","description":"This book features a great relationship between a young girl and her much older sibling."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34037/whats-in-tummy-mummy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34037","title":"What's in your Tummy, Mummy?","author":"by Sam Llloyd","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30573/peace-at-last2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30573","title":"Peace At Last","author":"by Jill Murphy","description":"The hour is late and Mr Bear is tired. But he just can't sleep - however hard he tries, all he can hear are the noises in the house.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30204/likewhen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30204","title":"I Like It When","author":"by Mary Murphy","description":"A touching and heart-warming book, illustrated in dramatic primary colours.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1-4"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34847/kiss-it-better.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34847","title":"Kiss it Better","author":"by Smriti Prasadam-Halls","description":"Mummy bear shares plenty of kisses with her cubs, each one carrying a special message of love, in this heart-warming tale with delightful illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34216/grandma-jessica-shepherd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34216","title":"Grandma","author":"by Jessica Shepherd","description":"This is a sensitive and touching picture book that helps young children understand dementia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30822/share.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30822","title":"Share!","author":"by Anthea Simmons","description":"Georgie Birkett beautifully captures the expressions of both big sister and baby brother in this funny and endearing picture book about learning to share.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24362/owl-babies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24362","title":"Owl Babies","author":"by Martin Waddell","description":"his reassuring and stunningly illustrated book tackles the subject of temporary separation - a situation which all children are likely to experience, be it Mum going to work or first day at Nursery.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30514/thats-not-my-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30514","title":"That's Not My Baby...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"This book is full of bright pictures with touch-and feel patches.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":273,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/273/","title":"World Book Day","list_description":"Inspired by World Book Day on 6 March, this month's list brings together nine novels from different countries around the globe. Japan, India, Russia and other countries are the backdrop to stories about murder, lust, sorrow and redemption.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32833/bundu.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32833","title":"Bundu","author":"by Chris Barnard","description":"Bundu is both a love story and a poetic tale of loneliness and loss."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31136/2666.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31136","title":"2666","author":"by Roberto Bolaño","description":"The fictional city of Santa Teresa on the Mexico-US border draws in lost souls: convicts and academics, an American sportswriter, a teenage student with her widowed father, and a reclusive, 'missing' writer. But there is a darker side still."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29802/the-alexandria-quartet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29802","title":"The Alexandria Quartet","author":"by Lawrence Durrell","description":"The Alexandria Quartet explores the sexual and political intrigues of a group of expatriates in Egypt before and after the Second World War."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32836/murder-of-halland.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32836","title":"The Murder of Halland","author":"by Pia Juul","description":"Let's get one thing out of the way before we begin: The Murder of Halland is a Scandinavian crime novel."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25847/9780571215676.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25847","title":"A Married Woman","author":"by Manju Kapur","description":"In this unsparing but moving novel, Manju Kapur explores the institution of the modern Indian marriage."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31018/everybody-jam.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31018","title":"Everybody Jam","author":"by Ali Lewis","description":"Set during a long, hot summer, this is an unflinching look at life on a cattle station in the Australian outback as a family tries to come to terms with the death of their oldest son in a horrific accident.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33243/exquisite-sense-of-what-is-beautiful.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33243","title":"An Exquisite Sense of What is Beautiful","author":"by J David Simons","description":"An admired British writer, Edward Strathairn returns to the hotel in Japan in which he wrote his first novel and began an intense love affair with a Japanese woman."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29851/confession.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29851","title":"A Confession","author":"by Leo Tolstoy","description":"A Confession is essential reading for anyone interested in Tolstoy as a man. The book's publication, years after he wrote it, marked his transformation from worldly man of letters into the mystic bearded sage of his latter years"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32252/9781408830284.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32252","title":"Once You Break A Knuckle","author":"by D W Wilson","description":"The best evidence of Wilson's writing prowess is in the BBC National Short Story Award-winning 'The Dead Roads', which describes a friendship group and road trip with a mixture of tenderness and intensity, and that is where Wilson carves out..."}]}
{"id":275,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/275/","title":"Down's Syndrome Awareness","list_description":"Around 750 babies in the UK every year are born with Down's syndrome. This equates to one in every thousand.  This year (2017), Tuesday 21 March is World Down Syndrome Day and 20-26 March is Down's Syndrome Awareness Week, with the theme of 'My voice, my community’.  To mark the week, here are children's and young teen books that feature characters who have Down's syndrome. The following list includes UK titles where characters with Down's syndrome either appear as protagonists or are simply included naturally in the images.  Go to the Down's Syndrome Association website for plenty of wonderful myth-busting information and advice - including a free information pack that can be downloaded or ordered.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33573/big-ben.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33573","title":"Big Ben","author":"by Rachel Anderson","description":"Matthew wants to write about his older brother Ben who has Down syndrome for a school project on individuals who the students admire.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34940/winter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34940","title":"Winter","author":"by Ailie Busby","description":"One of a lively series of board books featuring a highly inclusive cast. In this title, there is a child with Down Syndrome and an adapted sledge.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 1+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29117/victoria-s-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29117","title":"Victoria's Day","author":"by Maria De Fatima Campos","description":"A photographic diary documenting a day in the life of a four year old girl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33790/dead-ends.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33790","title":"Dead Ends","author":"by Erin Lange","description":"Dane Washington is the quick-tempered local bully, Billy D his new neighbour who has Down Syndrome.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33035/9781847803887-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33035","title":"Max the Champion","author":"by Sean Stockdale and Alexandra Strick","description":"This inclusive book is about a boy who loves sport, his friends, and school - and has a vivid imagination","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30517/making-friends-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30517","title":"Making Friends!","author":"by Jess Stockham","description":"This book is full of great animal pictures and lift-the-flap pages. It’s a friendly and colourful way to encourage children to enjoy sharing and have fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33200/onetwothree.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33200","title":"One, two, three... Run!","author":"by Carol Thompson","description":"Even a simple book for babies and toddlers can include disabled children naturally and subtly in its images - and this delightful board book proves the point.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34939/wind-carol-thompson.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34939","title":"Wind","author":"by Carol Thompson","description":"Sumptuous illustrations celebrate children's responses to the weather, in this series of board books. This title features a child with a hearing aid and a child with Down Syndrome.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35618/sun-carol-thompson.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35618","title":"Sun","author":"by Carol Thompson","description":"It’s the perfect day to slap on the sunscreen and sunhats and explore the great outdoors. Sumptuous illustrations celebrate children's responses to the weather, in this series of board books.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35619/naked-without-a-hat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35619","title":"Naked Without a Hat","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"A touching and humorous coming-of-age story, which acknowledges societal prejudice and raises some uncomfortable truths. A secret about the protagonist is only revealed to the reader towards the end.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":276,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/276/","title":"Environmental books for Earth Day","list_description":"As it's Earth Day on 22 April, this month's booklist is dedicated to books about the environment.  An investigation into the global food crisis and post-apocalyptic worlds feature in a list that includes novels and short stories. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30732/things-we-didn-t-see-coming.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30732","title":"Things We Didn't See Coming","author":"by Steven Amsterdam","description":"These apocalyptic stories make an oddly reassuring read. In the face of fire, flood, draught and plague, people remain basically the same they tell us. We are violent, tribal, insecure - yes - but creative, loving and cooperative too."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31031/bicycle-diaries.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31031","title":"The Bicycle Diaries","author":"by David Byrne","description":"Filled with intimate photographs, incredible musical stories and a powerful ecological message, this is a enchanting celebration of bike riding."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28128/the-pesthouse.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28128","title":"The Pesthouse","author":"by Jim Crace","description":"Jim Crace, has written a page-turning novel full of detail, description and – surprisingly – love. His post-apocalyptic America has reverted to an almost medieval way of life, in which horse-drawn carts are the most advanced mode of transport and..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31044/do-androids-dream-of-electric.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31044","title":"Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?","author":"by Philip K Dick","description":"World War Terminus had left the Earth devastated. Through its ruins, bounty hunter Rick Deckard stalked, in search of the renegade replicants who were his prey.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29756/eating-animals.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29756","title":"Eating Animals","author":"by Jonathan Sarfran Froer","description":"Eating Animals takes the Fast Food Nation/Waste premise of exploring where our food comes from and beats you over the head with it. You may emerge from this vegan."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31071/the-white-road.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31071","title":"The White Road","author":"by Tania Hershman","description":"Tania Hershman allows her imagination free reign, as her characters navigate through love, death, friendship, spirituality, mental illness and the havoc wreaked by the weather."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28131/the-road.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28131","title":"The Road","author":"by Cormac McCarthy","description":"McCarthy’s pared-down prose describes the wholesale annihilation of a society and all that it holds dear, but it also celebrates ingenuity and the will to survive in the face of utter hopelessness."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33239/man-with-compound.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33239","title":"The Man with the Compound Eyes","author":"by Wu Ming-Yi","description":"This is Wu Ming-Yi’s fourth novel, though the first that has been translated into English; hopefully more will follow."}]}
{"id":277,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/277/","title":"Short story collections for children","list_description":"These collections of bitesize short stories are perfect for dipping in and out of - great for classroom use, or simply for enjoying at home.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29645/a-necklace-of-raindrops.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29645","title":"A Necklace of Raindrops","author":"by Joan Aiken","description":"Filled with poetic repetitions, each story beautifully balances the prosaic with the wondrous.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28582/countingstars.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28582","title":"Counting Stars","author":"by David Almond","description":"This evocative collection of short stories gives a clear insight into the experiences which lie behind David Almond's novels.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34670/half-a-creature-from-the-seas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34670","title":"Half a Creature from the Sea","author":"by David Almond","description":"A collection of eight spooky tales of the fantastic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29639/under-the-weather.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29639","title":"Under the Weather","author":"by Tony Bradman","description":"A thought-provoking collection emphasising the importance of individual, as well as group initiatives.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31737/9781849393218-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31737","title":"Haunted","author":"by Susan Cooper","description":"A scintillating selection of supremely scary tales from 11 well-known children’s authors","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32269/heroes-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32269","title":"True Stories of Heroes","author":"by Paul Dowswell","description":"From animals to astronauts, and captured spies in World War II, this collection of thirteen short stories celebrates some truly amazing, and amazingly true, heroic acts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29022/give-peas-a-chance.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29022","title":"Give Peas A Chance","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"Fifteen funny stories, at times comic, wry, whimsical, moving, off-the-wall and downright hilarious, make up this brilliant book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30499/unbelievable-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30499","title":"Unbelievable!","author":"by Paul Jennings","description":"A brilliant collection of funny, weird and whacky short stories in which, believe it or not, a kid can grow younger; birds can bury you; ghosts have exams; there are eyes in the milk.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33419/9780007395354-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33419","title":"Of Lions and Unicorns","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"A variety of short stories and extracts from Michael Morpurgo, 'The Nation’s Favourite Storyteller’ are collected in this lovely gift edition.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30377/talesofterror.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30377","title":"Uncle Montague's Tales of Terror","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"These spine-tingling stories-within-a-story are the stuff of childhood nightmares, with a good smattering of ghosts, demons, blood and gore.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29332/tales-from-outer-suburbia-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29332","title":"Tales From Outer Suburbia","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"These often thought-provoking stories look at the reactions ordinary people have to the unusual situations they find themselves in and feature a host of different illustrative styles ranging from collage to painterly Edward Hopper-esque scenes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32035/magic-beans.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32035","title":"Magic Beans: A Handful of Fairy Tales from the Storybag","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"14 fairy tales are plucked from the Storybag and given new life by acclaimed writers from Michael Morpurgo to Jacqueline Wilson","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"}]}
{"id":278,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/278/","title":"Historical Books","list_description":"Here are some ideas to help you get a History Badge.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31259/aftershock.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31259","title":"Aftershock","author":"by Bernard Ashley","description":"After a major earthquake in 1951 devastates their lives, Makis and his mother are re-homed in North London, but they face antagonism from both the British and Greek communities.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30829/a-most-improper-magick.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30829","title":"A Most Improper Magick","author":"by Stephanie Burgis","description":"A 21st-century take on Jane Austen's world, entertainingly viewed through the eyes of a 12-year-old heroine who discovers she has inherited her mother's magical abilities.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32432/after.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32432","title":"After","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"The fourth installment in Morris Gleitzman's unforgettable series beginning with Once, tells the story of what happened to Felix in the final, agonising stages of the Second World War.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33291/asterix.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33291","title":"Asterix the Gaul","author":"by René Goscinny","description":"In a tiny corner of Brittany, one small village of indomitable Gauls hold out against the almighty, all-conquering Romans.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28759.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28759","title":"A Nest Of Vipers","author":"by Catherine Johnson","description":"We meet Cato Hopkins in Newgate Prison in September 1712, on the morning of the day he is due to be hanged for fraud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29904/spoonfulofjam.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29904","title":"A Spoonful of Jam","author":"by Michelle Magorian","description":"To avoid a gang of bullies during the summer holidays, 12-year-old Elsie eagerly accepts a role in a play at the local theatre.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33172/9781781121962.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33172","title":"A Lily, A Rose","author":"by Sally Nicholls","description":"Lady Elinor of Hardford Castle might have a grand title, but in fact she is a lonely 14-year-old girl. Then fledgling knight, cousin Dan arrives.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32424/9781406338324-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32424","title":"Ancient Egypt: Tales of Gods and Pharaohs","author":"by Marcia Williams","description":"Marcia Williams explores the rich culture and traditions of Ancient Egypt in this attractive large-format picture book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"}]}
{"id":279,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/279/","title":"Myths and Legends","list_description":"Read enough of these and you might find the mythical Myth Badge!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31890/9780340844106-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31890","title":"A Pilgrim's Progress","author":"by John Bunyan","description":"This retelling of John Bunyan's classic story is filled with drama, excitement and adventure","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32646/9781847802279-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32646","title":"Greek Myths: Stories of Sun, Stone and Sea","author":"by Sally Pomme Clayton","description":"Written to be read aloud, this collection of ten iconic Greek myths brings an ancient magical world vividly to life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24770/arthur-at-the-crossing-places.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24770","title":"Arthur At the Crossing Places","author":"by Kevin Crossley-Holland","description":"Crossley-Holland's trilogy continues with Arthur leaving Caldicot and his childhood behind and taking up a position as squire to Lord Stephen.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33658/breaking-the-spell.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33658","title":"Breaking the Spell","author":"by Lari Don","description":"A wonderful collection of myths, legends and fairy tales from Scotland.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33446/9781848531062-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33446","title":"Blackberry Blue","author":"by Jamila Gavin & Richard Collingridge","description":"A stunning collection of mystical fairy tales that are at once exotic and fresh, and traditionally heartening.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29691/calamity-jack.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29691","title":"Calamity Jack","author":"by Dean and Shannon Hale","description":"This graphic novel is full of fun action set pieces, comedic turns and well-drawn out characters and is a much-needed updating of the classic fairy tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32337/9781907411465-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32337","title":"Goddess Girls: Athena the Brain","author":"by Joan Holub and Suzanne Morgan Williams","description":"One morning a mystery scroll arrives for Athena, revealing that she is not a mere mortal, but is in fact the goddess daughter of Zeus, and has been summoned to enrol in Mount Olympus Academy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25173/casting-the-godsadrfit.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25173","title":"Casting the Gods Adrift","author":"by Geraldine McCaughrean","description":"This is a journey back in time to the era of the ancient Egyptians, when religion and ritual were central to people's lives.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32455/9-gods-and-warriors-the-outsiders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32455","title":"Gods and Warriors: The Outsiders","author":"by Michelle Paver","description":"In the first installment of a historical trilogy set during the Mycean Bronze Age, goatherd Hylas and High Priestess's daughter Pirra find themselves thrown together on a mysterious island.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25574/here-lies-arthur.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25574","title":"Here Lies Arthur","author":"by Philip Reeve","description":"The violence is darkly terrifying, the sense of landscape immediate and haunting and Gwyna/Gwyn's shifting gender permits Reeve to cast a unique, strikingly vivid glimpse into dark-age Britain.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":280,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/280/","title":"Pirates","list_description":"Are you looking for the Pirate Badge? Read some of these books to dig it up!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33022/productimage-7558367-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33022","title":"Go Saddle the Sea","author":"by Joan Aiken","description":"In this historical novel, young hero Felix travels from Spain to England, encountering all manner of adventures along the way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33660/magic-marks-the-spot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33660","title":"Magic Marks the Spot","author":"by Caroline Carlson","description":"The first of an exciting new trilogy, this is an action packed and fast paced story appealing to girls and boys.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32141/9781842996324-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32141","title":"Pirate Attack","author":"by Paul Dowswell","description":"Joe is on a dream holiday with his best friend Dan's family, who have won a two week sailing holiday off the African coast. Their captain, Nathan, teases the teenagers with tales of pirates and sharks, but when a mysterious...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30192/bumface.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30192","title":"Bumface","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"An extremely funny story, with a touch of poignancy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25441/bloodfever.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25441","title":"Blood Fever","author":"by Charlie Higson","description":"A sinister and secret society seems to be operating at Eton, while in the Mediterranean a young girl and her tutor are taken captive by a Hungarian pirate - but are the two linked?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32798/9781407129884-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32798","title":"Midnight Pirates","author":"by Ally Kennen","description":"Three children take on the running of a secluded Cornish guest-house and soon find themselves in danger in this contemporary adventure story bursting with exuberance and energy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30934/the-mourning-emporium.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30934","title":"The Mourning Emporium","author":"by Michelle Lovric","description":"The sequel to Lovric's The Undrowned Child moves from Venice to the dark, narrow backstreets of Victorian London, and evil plot to supplant the Royal succession.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33062/9781405258760-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33062","title":"The Magnificent Moon Hare and the Foul Treasure","author":"by Sue Monroe","description":"The pirates have Uncle Julian’s treasure map and plan to steal the Petulant Diamond","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24937/pirates.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24937","title":"Pirates!","author":"by Celia Rees","description":"Pirates! traces the adventures of Nancy Kington and Minerva Sharpe as they sail the high seas, often fighting for their lives, in the hope of gaining glory and riches.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32652/aptimized-jpg-339f36b540a19c218c308de69aa2f901-mzu0utyym6wwmtdg0q3qvdyvtyzrz8xnte8t1s9lsthp0bc0tza0mdc3ndgamoesa0mlm72sgnqa-41e2017e-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32652","title":"The Cloud Hunters","author":"by Alex Shearer","description":"Many years after an unspecified cataclysm, the Earth has been shattered into a myriad of tiny planetoids floating in a vast ocean of air.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":281,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/281/","title":"Around the World","list_description":"Take a trip around the world with these books - there might be a badge in it for you...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32943/emil-and-the-detectives-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32943","title":"Emil and the Detectives","author":"by Erich Kästner","description":"Ten-year-old Emil is excited to be taking the train to Berlin on his own for the first time - but he doesn't like the look of his fellow passenger, the man in the bowler hat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32794/9781405266437-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32794","title":"Into That Forest","author":"by Louis Nowra","description":"Two girls find themselves lost in the Tasmanian bush in this powerful and memorable novel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32143/9781847800060-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32143","title":"Far From Home","author":"by Na'ima B Robert","description":"This moving tale describes the violent history of Zimbabwe as seen through the eyes of two very different young girls.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":283,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/283/","title":"Bookbuzz 2014","list_description":"The Bookbuzz titles for 2014 have been announced! This autumn, students in Bookbuzz schools will be able to choose their own book to keep from this list, suitable for 11 - 13-year-olds and selected by a panel of experts. Find out more about Bookbuzz, a Book Trust reading programme, on the Bookbuzz website.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32375/tiger-wars-new-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32375","title":"Tiger Wars","author":"by Steve Backshall","description":"Saker and Sinter live utterly different lives - until they find themselves unlikely companions on the run. A breathlessly exciting adventure set in India.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33671/stories-of-ww1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33671","title":"Stories of WW1","author":"by Tony Bradman","description":"Poignantly bringing the First World War alive for teenagers, this anthology reminds us that many of those in the trenches were themselves no older.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33025/9781408820506-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33025","title":"The Great Ice Cream Heist","author":"by Elen Caldecott","description":"Shy Eva lives a quiet life with her protective Dad - until the noisy McIntyre family move in next door.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31683/ruby-redfort-look-into-my-ey.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31683","title":"Ruby Redfort: Look Into My Eyes","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Blessed with an extraordinary talent for spotting things which others seldom notice, 13-year-old Ruby lands an undercover job as a code-breaker for secret-spy organisation, Spectrum.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33126/9780440870159.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33126","title":"Whale Boy","author":"by Nicola Davies","description":"In this short novel, Nicola Davies paints a rich and vibrant picture of island life, which feels as fresh as the sea air.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32649/a-laureate-s-choice-cover-w.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32649","title":"A Laureate's Choice: 101 Poems for Children chosen by Carol Ann Duffy","author":"by Carol Ann Duffy","description":"Poet Laureate Carol Ann Duffy has created a spirited, enriching and exquisite anthology of poems for children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33679/extra-time.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33679","title":"Extra Time","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"Imagine being filmed using your football skills to avoid being trampled by a herd of stampeding cattle. That's what happens to 14 year old Matt and it changes his life forever."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32920/wild-boy-cover-web.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32920","title":"Wild Boy","author":"by Rob Lloyd-Jones","description":"In 1840s London, Wild Boy leads a miserable life in a travelling freak show. Treated as a monster and excluded from society, he develops an unusual talent for observation.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33683/boffin-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33683","title":"Boffin Boy Goes to Hollywood","author":"by David Orme","description":"Rick Shaw might seem like an ordinary teenager, but when danger strikes Ricky becomes... Boffin Boy!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33673/ghost-stadium.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33673","title":"Ghost Stadium","author":"by Tom Palmer","description":"Tom Palmer's Ghost Stadium is a fast-paced and properly spooky ghost story. The book suits reluctant readers and is also dyslexia friendly.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33685/super-animals-cover-web.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33685","title":"Super Animals","author":"by Anne Rooney","description":"Have you ever wondered how a clever crow can crack a hard nut, or how a wild cat can trap a baby monkey? Super Animals can tell you!"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33370/9780007489442-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33370","title":"Geek Girl","author":"by Holly Smale","description":"Everyone at school knows Harriet Manners is a geek.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33602/operation-ouch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33602","title":"Operation Ouch!","author":"by Dr Chris and Dr Xand van Tulleken","description":"Have you ever wondered how long you'll spend on the toilet in your lifetime, or how many skin cells you shed in one day? Operation Ouch! Your Brilliant Body explains everything you've ever wanted to know about your body, including...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33674/a-boy-called-hopes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33674","title":"A Boy Called Hope","author":"by Lara Williamson","description":"A Boy Called Hope is a moving story about a boy's search for his dad. Dan Hope is a funny and likeable boy who tackles the questions he has in his life head on. His determination to find answers is...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32992/9780192794031-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32992","title":"Winnie's Dinosaur Day","author":"by Valerie Thomas","description":"When Winne the Witch discovers that the local museum is holding a competition, she comes up with a good idea.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32188/9780091893323-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32188","title":"Croc and Bird","author":"by Alexis Deacon","description":"Two eggs lie side-by-side on a sandy beach: one hatches to reveal a crocodile and the other a bird.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33686/off-to-the-park-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33686","title":"Off to the Park!","author":"by Stephen Cheetham","description":"We're off to the park - what will we find? Which way shall we go? The swings or the slide? Take a look inside!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"}]}
{"id":284,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/284/","title":"Books on dementia","list_description":"Dementia is a difficult thing to deal with and it can be hard to talk about with your loved ones.  If you're looking for some books for children and young teens to help start a difficult conversation, check out these books, which look at dementia and its impact on families in different ways.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26090/sundaegirl...jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26090","title":"Sundae Girl","author":"by Cathy Cassidy","description":"All teenagers are embarrassed by their parents but Jude feels she has more reason than most to cringe when hers are around her in public.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29113/cb-that-s-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29113","title":"Clarice Bean, That's Me","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Clarice Bean gives us a snapshot of her life and family in the book that launched a bestselling series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24811/heartbeat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24811","title":"Heartbeat","author":"by Sharon Creech","description":"Annie loves drawing, running barefoot, her family, and possibly Max, her running partner. It’s an eventful time for the 12-year-old: as her mother is about to give birth, her beloved grandfather is sliding slowly into dementia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35670/the-lotterys-plus-one.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35670","title":"The Lotterys Plus One","author":"by Emma Donoghue","description":"Sumac lives with her huge and diverse family. All is chaotic, offbeat brilliance until the 82-year-old grandfather the kids have never met moves in. Told with utter charm and a lightness of touch, ultimately The Lotterys Plus One is about...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35630/unbecoming.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35630","title":"Unbecoming","author":"by Jenny Downham","description":"Unbecoming is an intriguing mystery, with the idea of 'living bravely' at its heart. Vividly drawn characters and a complex story keeps readers turning the page as three generations of secrets are gradually unravelled and released in the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31618/9781407120522-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31618","title":"The Memory Cage","author":"by Ruth Eastham","description":"Alex needs to act fast or his family will be torn apart","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32799/back-to-blackbricks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32799","title":"Back to Blackbrick","author":"by Sarah Moore Fitzgerald","description":"When Cosmo steps through the crumbling gates of the mysterious Blackbrick Abbey, he comes face to face with his Grandad as a young man.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34169/stonebird.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34169","title":"Stonebird","author":"by Mike Revell","description":"An accessible and engaging story about the sadness and joy of family life and the power of memory, magic and storytelling.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9","interest_age":"Interest level: 11-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34216/grandma-jessica-shepherd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34216","title":"Grandma","author":"by Jessica Shepherd","description":"This is a sensitive and touching picture book that helps young children understand dementia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":285,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/285/","title":"Female authors","list_description":"This month sees a new Kim Scott Walwyn-winner crowned ahead of the Baileys Women's Prize for Fiction-winner announcement a few weeks later, so this month's booklist is dedicated to female authors.  Peruse the booklist for memoirs, translated fiction, horror stories and more.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28704/love-in-a-fallen-city.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28704","title":"Love in a Fallen City","author":"by Eileen Chang","description":"Expanding their Modern Classics series, Penguin have now published two collections of novellas and short stories by the celebrated Chinese writer Eileen Chang, containing several perfectly-formed examples of her writing about 30s and 40s Hong Kong and Shanghai."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31907/9780224089043.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31907","title":"The Forgotten Waltz","author":"by Anne Enright","description":"A deceptively simple story, beautifully crafted, Anne Enright's The Forgotten Waltz is a welcome return for the author of the Booker-winning The Gathering"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29664/dear-fatty.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29664","title":"Dear Fatty","author":"by Dawn French","description":"This book is entertaining, inspiring and a brilliant read. Dawn French has led a very interesting life; and it is a pleasure to read about personal events that have had such an impact on her."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28204/beyond-black.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28204","title":"Beyond Black","author":"by Hilary Mantel","description":"Alison Hart, a medium by trade, tours the dormitory towns of London's orbital road with her flint-hearted sidekick Colette, passing on messages from dead ancestors."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29853/thursday-night-widows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29853","title":"Thursday Night Widows","author":"by Claudia Pineiro","description":"Claudia Piñeiro’s Thursday Night Widows is a whodunnit, a black comedy, a social portrait and a prophecy, a timely dissection of the disintegration of a privileged class and an important addition to 21st Century Latin American fiction."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29472/persepolis.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29472","title":"Persepolis","author":"by Marjane Satrapi","description":"Persepolis is Satrapi's history of Iran and her life in Iran and France as she tries to retain her Iranian culture but also grow up and become independent.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33563/9781471127380.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33563","title":"The Burgess Boys","author":"by Elizabeth Strout","description":"The Burgess brothers return to the landscape of their childhood, where the long-buried tensions that have shaped and shadowed their relationship begin to surface in unexpected ways that will change them forever."}]}
{"id":286,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/286/","title":"Deaf Awareness Week booklist","list_description":"Deaf Awareness Week runs from 15-21 May 2017. Relevant organisations will use the week to flag up the need for greater understanding of the vast spectrum of deafness and their work in and around this area.  The following booklist features a range of books relevant to the subject. The selection includes books that feature deafness as a key theme, books with a deaf protagonist, and books that happen to include children with hearing aids and cochlear implants, in a subtle and natural way.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35033/river-of-ink-jacket-image.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35033","title":"River of Ink: Genesis","author":"by Helen Dennis","description":"River Boy is washed up on the banks of the River Thames, unable to find his voice or memory. The only things he can draw on are his visions and mysterious symbols. An exciting first book in a trilogy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31211/freddie-and-the-fairy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31211","title":"Freddie and the Fairy","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Karen George","description":"Freddie rescues a fairy who offers to grant him his every wish. The only problem is that she can't hear very well, and so his wishes result in some unexpected surprises...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25746/moonbird.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25746","title":"Moonbird","author":"by Joyce Dunbar","description":"Orla doesn't answer when his parents call his name, and seems to be shut away in his own world. When he meets the mysterious moonbird he learns how to speak with his hands and listen with his eyes, but now...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29119/the-deaf-musicians.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29119","title":"The Deaf Musicians","author":"by Pete Seeger and Paul Dubois Jacobs","description":"Stylish artwork accompanies the story of a pianist who loses his hearing and his job, only to start a popular new band of deaf musicians.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34643/9781908446336.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34643","title":"The Silent Striker","author":"by Pete Kalu","description":"Marcus lives and breathes football. He might even have the makings of a professional player. But Marcus' life is about to change. Neither a book 'about' deafness or disability, nor another stock football story, this is an uplifting and accessible...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32334/9781848775466-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32334","title":"Whisper","author":"by Chrissie Keighery","description":"Fifteen year old Demi is starting a new school – always a nerve-racking experience. However, for Demi, it represents a time of far more dramatic change, as her new school is a college for deaf students, a recent case of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32739/ketchup-cloudsd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32739","title":"Ketchup Clouds","author":"by Annabel Pitcher","description":"Fifteen-year-old Zoe attempts to come to terms with a dark secret by writing letters to a murderer awaiting execution on Death Row.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33035/9781847803887-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33035","title":"Max the Champion","author":"by Sean Stockdale and Alexandra Strick","description":"This inclusive book is about a boy who loves sport, his friends, and school - and has a vivid imagination","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32007/noo-noos.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32007","title":"Noo-Noos","author":"by Carol Thompson","description":"Every young child has a noo-noo. It’s that scruffy piece of well-loved fabric, fur, plastic or rubber, that goes everywhere with you...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34380/what-the-jackdaw-saw.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34380","title":"What the Jackdaw Saw","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Nick Sharratt","description":"A highly entertaining book with an inclusive cast of characters, providing an introduction to sign language to all children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28587/lucy-loud-and-clear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28587","title":"Lucy: Loud and Clear","author":"by Laila Lavan","description":"Lucy is deaf and Omar is rather flippantly pretending he can't understand her request. Lucy has to be creative if she is to find a solution.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
