o?","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"One day at nursery, the children begin to discuss what their daddies do - which gets Daisy wondering about her own Daddy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25557/my-mum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25557","title":"My Mum","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"All small children love their mums and in this colourful and entertaining picture book, Anthony Browne explains exactly why.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33599/storm-whale.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33599","title":"The Storm Whale","author":"by Benji Davies","description":"Noi finds a baby whale washed up on the beach after a storm and decides to take it home to care for it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30807/just-because.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30807","title":"Just Because","author":"by Rebecca Elliott","description":"This uplifting book focuses on a sibling relationship, as a little boy affectionately describes his older sister","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34222/digby-dog-delivers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34222","title":"Digby Dog Delivers","author":"by Tor Freeman","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30532/going2playschool.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30532","title":"Going to Playschool","author":"by Sarah Garland","description":"This book is engaging, colourful and very real: the story captures perfectly the mood of playschool."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32260/9781862307858-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32260","title":"Alfie Gives a Hand","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Shirley Hughes' much-loved Alfie goes to his first birthday party in this lovely picture book for pre-school children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33871/specs-for-rex.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33871","title":"Specs for Rex","author":"by Yasmeen Ismail","description":"A perfectly judged niche story that has general appeal due to a clean text and cute character; Specs for Rex is a visual treat that's really worth putting your glasses on for.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34382/little-jungle-explorers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34382","title":"Little Jungle Explorers","author":"by Anthony Lewis","description":"Colourful board book with double-sided explorer figure!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30001/elmerand-the-lostteddy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30001","title":"Elmer and the Lost Teddy","author":"by David McKee","description":"In this republication of a 1999 title, McKee shows young readers that we each have special things which nobody else loves quite as we do.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25804/lulu-loves-library.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25804","title":"Lulu Loves the Library","author":"by Anna McQuinn","description":"Lulu has her library card, her rucksack full of borrowed books, and a big smile on her face, because it's Tuesday – and on Tuesdays Lulu and her mummy go to the library","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30422/christopher-nibble.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30422","title":"Christopher Nibble","author":"by Charlotte Middleton","description":"Christopher Nibble loves to eat dandelion leaves. But so does every other guinea pig in Dandeville – and that’s the problem!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30604/flashing-fireengines.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30604","title":"Flashing Fire Engines","author":"by Tony Mitton","description":"This story’s full of big, bold fire engines ready to rescue or fight fires. There’s plenty of action, rhyme and rhythm."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30204/likewhen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30204","title":"I Like It When","author":"by Mary Murphy","description":"A touching and heart-warming book, illustrated in dramatic primary colours.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1-4"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28470/harris-finds-his-feet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28470","title":"Harris Finds His Feet","author":"by Catherine Rayner","description":"Harris leaps joyfully across the pages, against vibrant washes of colour, as he learns to be independent for the first time.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32062/9781407116440-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32062","title":"A Day with the Animal Doctors","author":"by Sharon Rentta","description":"Terence the Tapir accompanies his doctor mum to the animal hospital for the day.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7 +","interest_age":"Interest level: 3 +"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33989/pip-posy-bedtime-frog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33989","title":"Pip and Posy: The Bedtime Frog","author":"by Axel Scheffler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33992/pip-posy-little-puddle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33992","title":"Pip and Posy: The Little Puddle","author":"by Axel Scheffler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34216/grandma-jessica-shepherd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34216","title":"Grandma","author":"by Jessica Shepherd","description":"This is a sensitive and touching picture book that helps young children understand dementia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32916/9781408330029-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32916","title":"The Dark","author":"by Lemony Snicket","description":"One night, the night-light goes out, and the dark calls Laszlo down into the basement to meet it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29699/9781862306523-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29699","title":"One Smart Fish","author":"by Chris Wormell","description":"A small silver fish has done everything he can possibly do in the ocean - he sings, dances and even performs plays, but has never walked upon the land.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33216/crocodilewhodidnt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33216","title":"The Crocodile Who Didn't Like Water","author":"by Gemma Merino","description":"Little crocodile doesn't like water. It's cold. It's wet. It's embarrassing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"}]}
{"id":294,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/294/","title":"World War One anniversary","list_description":"To mark the 100 year anniversary of the start of World War One, this month's booklist pays tribute to books about the First World War.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29084/the-forbidden-zone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29084","title":"The Forbidden Zone","author":"by Mary Borden","description":"This, then, was daily life on the Western Front: boredom, routine, fear, shock, death. It was Mary Borden's supreme achievement not only to save as many men as she did - and nurse the others gently to the end -..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28929/bloody-old-britain.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28929","title":"Bloody Old Britain","author":"by Kitty Hauser","description":"This grandiose manifesto was written by one of archaeology's lesser known heroes, a tactiturn man, who - as Kitty Hauser shows in this remarkable book - devoted most of his life both to his work and a twentieth-century political ideal,..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27664/ashenden.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27664","title":"Ashenden","author":"by W Somerset Maugham","description":"The stories in Ashenden are rooted in Maugham's own experiences as an agent in Switzerland during the First World War."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32868/9780857521002.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32868","title":"The Light Between Oceans","author":"by M L Stedman","description":"Tom Sherbourne, released from the horrors of the First World War, is now a lighthouse keeper, cocooned on a remote island with his young wife Izzy, who is content in everything but her failure to have a child. One April..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31858/f32df743-4093-4509-8e40-0ca6a67a70cb-img100.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31858","title":"Blow On A Dead Man's Embers","author":"by Mari Strachan","description":"The title of this book lends it a darker tone than the story warrants. This is no thriller or murder mystery, rather it is the touching story of one woman's attempts to find out what happened to her emotionally bruised..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28790/in-the-blue-light-of-african-dreams.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28790","title":"In the Blue Light of African Dreams","author":"by Paul Watkins","description":"Flying with the Lafayette squadron over France in 1918, Charlie Halifax is shot down and wounded. When he is well enough, he attempts to escape to America but is captured and forced to join the Foreign Legion."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30337/fighting-france.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30337","title":"Fighting France","author":"by Edith Wharton","description":"Wharton brings empathy, passion and a novelist's eye for detail to this series of essays on France at the outbreak of World War I."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31973/9780857386540.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31973","title":"Bereft","author":"by Chris Womersley","description":"Chris Womersley captures the end of World War I in Bereft. The rapid onset of a plague that will turn out to be Spanish Influenza might seem biblical in its apocalyptic proportions, but, after the chaos of the war, faith..."}]}
{"id":295,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/295/","title":"School Library Pack 2014 - future classics","list_description":"These are the future classics selected for the School Library Pack 2014. The pack is free to all schools in England that have Year 7 students.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32427/6.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32427","title":"The Terrible Thing That Happened to Barnaby Brocket","author":"by John Boyne","description":"Barnaby Brocket has an unusual gift: he defies the law of gravity and floats. Embarassed by their child's 'abnormality', his parents set out to keep his feet on the ground.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33766/the-company-of-ghosts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33766","title":"The Company of Ghosts","author":"by Berlie Doherty","description":"Over the past year many things have changed in Ellie’s life. When she is told she must go away with her mum and her stepfather on their honeymoon, it’s the last straw and she decides to run away. Fortunately she...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33767/runners.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33767","title":"Runners","author":"by Ann Kelley","description":"In a not too distant future in which the oceans have risen and resources are scarce, 14 year-old Sid is trying to keep himself and his five year-old sister Lo safe from harm.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32803/binny-for-short.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32803","title":"Binny for Short","author":"by Hilary McKay","description":"Since her father died, Binny's family have struggled. Then old Aunt Violet dies, leaving them her house by the sea.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32794/9781405266437-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32794","title":"Into That Forest","author":"by Louis Nowra","description":"Two girls find themselves lost in the Tasmanian bush in this powerful and memorable novel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":296,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/296/","title":"Books to develop understanding of disability","list_description":"The following list represents just a few examples of titles which feature disability as a theme and might be valuable in helping children and young people to consider their perceptions and understanding of disability.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33362/9781406322187-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33362","title":"The Black Book of Colours","author":"by Menena Cottin & Rosana Faria","description":"A visually impaired boy introduces us to colours as he experiences them – through his senses of hearing, touch, smell and taste.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32010/sometimes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32010","title":"Sometimes","author":"by Rebecca Elliott","description":"When Toby’s sister Clemmie is unwell, she has to go and stay in hospital...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33791/reason-i-jump.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33791","title":"The Reason I Jump","author":"by Naoki Higashida","description":"An invaluable tool for family members trying to understand autistic behaviour but also a fascinating and powerful read in its own right.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31002/hudson-hates-school.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31002","title":"Hudson Hates School","author":"by Ella Hudson","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28580/accidents-of-nature.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28580","title":"Accidents of Nature","author":"by Harriet McBride Johnson","description":"Jean, who has Cerebral Palsy, is about to spend ten days at Camp Courage (or ‘Crip Camp’ as her cabinmate Sara calls it), which is to prove an eye-opening experience.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32334/9781848775466-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32334","title":"Whisper","author":"by Chrissie Keighery","description":"Fifteen year old Demi is starting a new school – always a nerve-racking experience. However, for Demi, it represents a time of far more dramatic change, as her new school is a college for deaf students, a recent case of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32186/9780552565974.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32186","title":"Wonder","author":"by R J Palacio","description":"August ('Auggie') Pullman can't help but stand out - he was born with a severe facial deformity. Written in the first person, Wonder follows Auggie as he experiences more than the usual ups-and-downs of friendships, family and school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32017/d1cdb8b0-267c-45f6-b850-24a176c015ea-img100-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32017","title":"Anything But Typical","author":"by Nora Raleigh Baskin","description":"Jason is 12 and on the autistic spectrum...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":297,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/297/","title":"All in the Family","list_description":"It's a family affair as Cousin's Day (24 July), Aunt & Uncle Day (26 July) & Father-in-law Day all occur in July.  So, celebrate with your nearest and dearest by perusing this month's booklist, which is dedicated to books, works and novels about family. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33404/shadow-of-the-crescent-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33404","title":"The Shadow of the Crescent Moon","author":"by Fatima Bhutto","description":"Fatima Bhutto's debut novel tells the story of three brothers on the Pakistan-Afghan border whose lives take a devastating turn after they leave the house one morning. Normal 0 false false false EN-GB X-NONE X-NONE MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 /* Style Definitions */..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33554/9781846557194.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33554","title":"The Bear","author":"by Claire Cameron","description":"A young girl must protect her brother on a family camping trip."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28053/family-connections.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28053","title":"Family Connections","author":"by Chrissie Gittins","description":"These stories trace the fragile and enduring connections between those related by blood, and those not."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31997/9781846554674.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31997","title":"A Death In the Family","author":"by Karl Ove Knausgaard","description":"REPRESENTING NORWAY Karl Ove Knausgaard's A Death In The Family is an experiment that has paid off handsomely in his native Norway, where the author has emerged as one of the leaders of his country's new generation of literary talent."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27673/a-lazy-eye.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27673","title":"A Lazy Eye Stories","author":"by Mary Morrissy","description":"A woman confesses her guilty secret to an obscene caller; a daughter trades with God for her father's life; a family re-enacts an unholy nativity."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28164/shutterspeed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28164","title":"Shutterspeed","author":"by Erwin Mortier","description":"Erwin Mortier’s deceptively simple tale of an adolescent boy growing up in a Flemish village with his aunt and uncle, is full of such beautiful, spare writing. Its inclusion on the 2008 Independent Foreign Fiction Prize longlist is no surprise."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29658/dreams-from-my-father.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29658","title":"Dreams From My Father","author":"by Barack Obama","description":"Obama is an engaging writer, filled with wide-eyed optimism, struggling to reconcile his identity (being the son of a black father and a white mother) amidst the backdrop of American racial politics.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33359/quesadillas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33359","title":"Quesadillas","author":"by Juan Pablo Villalobos","description":"Here’s a rambunctious, energetic piece of writing. Madcap and effervescent, this story of a teenager’s desire to escape his dull, supposedly middle class family home is an education and entertainment."}]}
{"id":298,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/298/","title":"Summer reads 2014","list_description":"Dive into these young adult books this summer - a collection of our favourites from the past year, ones you're bound to get lost in.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33316/coldest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33316","title":"The Coldest Girl in Coldtown","author":"by Holly Black","description":"Welcome to Coldtown. Once you enter, you can never leave. Delightfully dark and gorgeously gothic, it is certain to enchant fans of all things chilling and supernatural.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33338/we-need-new.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33338","title":"We Need New Names","author":"by NoViolet Bulawayo","description":"Through the eyes of a young girl, Darling, we are given a startling insight into events in Zimbabwe during a time of great change."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33264/vivianversus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33264","title":"Vivian Versus the Apocalypse","author":"by Katie Coyle","description":"Sixteen-year-old Vivian Apple is awaiting the predicted 'Rapture' with a healthy degree of scepticism.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33451/untitled-1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33451","title":"Boys Don't Knit","author":"by T S Easton","description":"'I'm aware that keeping a diary is considered part of the female domain, but in my life, with the family and friends I'm stuck with, it is the only reason I haven't run away and gone to live in the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33708/lobsters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33708","title":"Lobsters","author":"by Tom Ellen and Lucy Ivison","description":"The first novel from friends and collaborators Tom Ellen and Lucy Ivison, Lobsters is a frank and very funny young adult romance.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33448/9781447241713-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33448","title":"Stella","author":"by Helen Eve","description":"Stella is the Queen Bee of Temperley, whilst quiet new girl Caitlin feels out of place at an English boarding school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33681/we-were-liars.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33681","title":"We Were Liars","author":"by E Lockhart","description":"E Lockhart paints a vivid portrait of the Sinclair family, spinning an addictive tale of first love, friendship and family that teens will find impossible to put down.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33587/amy-and-matthew.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33587","title":"Amy and Matthew: A Love Story","author":"by Cammie McGovern","description":"Amy, who has cerebral palsy, is in her final year of high school and she wants this year to be different: she wants to replace the adult aides who help her, with her fellow students, so she can get to...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33636/grasshopper-jungles.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33636","title":"Grasshopper Jungle","author":"by Andrew Smith","description":"Grasshopper Jungle is both an exciting edge-of-your-seat young adult dystopia, and a bold and thoughtful novel about history and identity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33540/avalavender.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33540","title":"The Strange and Beautiful Sorrows of Ava Lavender","author":"by Leslye Walton","description":"This is the story of Ava Lavender, a girl born with the wings of a bird.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":299,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/299/","title":"Be a daily reading hero!","list_description":"We chose a hero-themed book for every day of National Bookstart Week 2014 and you can see the seven books below, as well as downloading a PDF of the booklist.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33705/daddy-hero-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33705","title":"Daddy is My Hero","author":"by Dawn Richards and Jane Massey","description":"Fantasy, fun and fancy dress in this tender and touching tribute to heroic Dads!"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33815/superduck-book-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33815","title":"Super Duck","author":"by Jez Alborough","description":"Bright illustrations and rhyming text in a fun adventure with kites!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29896/9781408309575-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29896","title":"I Love My Mummy","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"What is it about Mummies that makes them so lovable and so very special?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33818/daleyb-book-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33818","title":"You're a Hero, Daley B!","author":"by Jon Blake and Axel Scheffler","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33816/benjamin-spectacles-book-jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33816","title":"Benjamin & the Super Spectacles","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29917/granpa.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29917","title":"Granpa","author":"by John Burningham","description":"A sensitive and moving exploration of the relationship between a young girl and her grandfather.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33817/lildrivers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33817","title":"Little Drivers to the Rescue!","author":"by Dan Crisp","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"}]}
{"id":300,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/300/","title":"Bringing World War I to life in the classroom","list_description":"A selection of books about World War I that are particularly suited to the classroom - because they provide a good overview, or offer a new angle, or are suited to reluctant readers, or come with excellent resources.  ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33773/shadow-of-the-zeppelin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33773","title":"Shadow of the Zeppelin","author":"by Bernard Ashley","description":"Set around Woolwich, in Flanders and in Germany, Ashley's latest powerful novel for KS3+ readers shows World War One from the viewpoint of British and German combatants, but concentrates on the little-known Home Front experience.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33473/5.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33473","title":"Stay Where You Are and Then Leave","author":"by John Boyne","description":"This is a compelling story, beautifully observed, which covers difficult themes such as shellshock and loss in a sensitive and understanding way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33770/my-brothers-keeper.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33770","title":"My Brother's Keeper","author":"by Tom and Tony Bradman","description":"Alfie's story has obvious subject appeal for boys and the length is enticing for reluctant readers, but this neat little story manages to be both thought-provoking and moving, and in the barrage of solider stories coming out this year this...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32610/9781408826232-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32610","title":"Eleven Eleven","author":"by Paul Dowswell","description":"In the early hours of 11 November 1918, the agreement to end World War I is finally sealed, and the lives of three young men collide as they fight to survive the final hours of the conflict.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33772/charlies-war.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33772","title":"Charlie’s War Illustrated - Remembering World War One","author":"by Mick Manning and Brita Granstrom","description":"A collage approach makes this picture flat a brilliant book to support school study of World War One.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32745/9781847802125-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32745","title":"Walter Tull's Scrapbook","author":"by Michaela Morgan","description":"Discover the fascinating true story of footballer and World War I officer Walter Tull in this highly visual scrapbook.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33789/dear-jelly.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33789","title":"Dear Jelly: Family Letters from the First World War","author":"by Sarah Ridley","description":"Accompanied by historical notes on the progress of the war, this book is an accessible resource and an appealing read. It is also a moving story, as neither of the brothers returned home alive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33980/secret-message.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33980","title":"The Secret Message","author":"by John Townsend","description":"This short novel tells the story of Sam, who discovers the diary which his great-great-grandfather wrote during World War I. One of a new series of 'Cold Fusion' books suited to more able readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33759/ghost-of-the-trenches.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33759","title":"The Ghost of the Trenches","author":"by Helen Watts and Taffy Thomas","description":"This slim volume includes 14 'war stories' made up of poems, songs and re-tellings of ghostly sightings and mysterious coincidences, themed around World War One.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31151/archieswar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31151","title":"Archie's War","author":"by Marcia Williams","description":"In 1914, ten-year-old Archie is sent a scrapbook in the post by his Uncle Colin, and through the years that follow, we see the world through Archie's eyes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"}]}
{"id":301,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/301/","title":"Long Hot Summer","list_description":"Try to cool off and relax during this long hot summer by viewing our booklist featuring books set in during the heatwave of July and August.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32759/hajicek_rustic_baroque.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32759","title":"Rustic Baroque","author":"by Jiří Hájíček","description":"Rustic Baroque is a gorgeous and lyrical mystery about trust, about the past, and about the secret pain that can lie beneath the sunniest summer idyll."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25857/beyond-sleep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25857","title":"Beyond Sleep","author":"by WF Hermans","description":"Summer in northern Norway: endless hours of light, clouds of mosquitoes, kilometre after kilometre of rocky terrain and stunted trees. Into this barren landscape trek four geology students, three of them Norwegian, one – Alfred Issendorf – Dutch. Each is..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31028/playing-days.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31028","title":"Playing Days","author":"by Benjamin Markovits","description":"Tinged with the melancholy and nostalgia of early steps into adulthood, it's the story of a young man's first experience of adult love, and of the discovery of his own limitations."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30963/a-beautiful-lie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30963","title":"A Beautiful Lie","author":"by Irfan Master","description":"Set in India during the summer of 1947, A Beautiful Lie follows the tumultuous events of the Partition of India through the eyes of Bilal who is looking after his ill father.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33501/labor-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33501","title":"Labor Day","author":"by Joyce Maynard","description":"Over a long summer a boy's life changes after a man befriends his reclusive mother."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33203/birds-in-a-cage.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33203","title":"Birds in a Cage","author":"by Derek Niemann","description":"Countless attempts were made at escaping the bleak surroundings but, for Peter Conder, Edward Buxton, George Waterston and John Barrett, escape came in the form of a bird watching society, and the meticulous daily observation and recording of the antics..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26577/havana-red.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26577","title":"Havana Red","author":"by Leonardo Padura","description":"On 6 August 1989 the day on which the Catholic Church celebrates the Feast of the Transfiguration, the body of a strangled transvestite is discovered in the humid undergrowth of the Havana Woods."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29625/giraffes-in-my-hair.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29625","title":"Giraffes in My Hair","author":"by Bruce Paley","description":"This graphic novel by Bruce Paley illustrated with gorgeous charcoal-y drawings by Carole Swain tells short stories and anecdotes from Bruce's life as a teenager and drifter who turns 18 in the Summer of Love and hits the road to..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25933/out-stealing-horses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25933","title":"Out Stealing Horses","author":"by Per Petterson","description":"Petterson’s characters are embedded in the landscape and the seasons, the drifting snows of winter and the burning sunshine of high summer."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30818/the-still-point.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30818","title":"The Still Point","author":"by Amy Sackville","description":"Amy Sackville demonstrates that she is the mistress of narrative and structure in this stunningly crafted tale of icebergs and splintering marriages."}]}
{"id":302,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/302/","title":"Best books 2014","list_description":"Below are the dozen books for readers ages 0-5 that were selected to appear in the Book Trust Best Book Guide 2014. We hope you like them as much as we do!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33406/9780230764811-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33406","title":"Aunt Amelia","author":"by Rebecca Cobb","description":"'We were in a bad mood. Aunt Amelia was coming to look after us. We didn't know who Aunt Amelia was and we didn't want looking after.'","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33598/peck-peck-peck.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33598","title":"Peck Peck Peck","author":"by Lucy Cousins","description":"The new picture book from Lucy Cousins introduces readers to an enthusiastic and eager woodpecker who is being taught to peck by its dad.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33599/storm-whale.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33599","title":"The Storm Whale","author":"by Benji Davies","description":"Noi finds a baby whale washed up on the beach after a storm and decides to take it home to care for it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33707/tiny-the-invisible-world-of-microbes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33707","title":"Tiny: The Invisible World of Microbes","author":"by Nicola Davies","description":"This is an original, special and memorable book that sets the bar high for illustrated children's non-fiction.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33212/thedaythecrayonsquite.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33212","title":"The Day the Crayons Quit","author":"by Drew Daywalt & Oliver Jeffers","description":"Award-winning illustrator and artist Oliver Jeffers has teamed up with film writer and director Drew Daywalt to create this gorgeously colourful picture book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33340/9781407116549-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33340","title":"The Snatchabook","author":"by Helen and Thomas Docherty","description":"This delightful picture book from husband-and-wife team Helen and Thomas Docherty is a real treat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33670/macavity.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33670","title":"Macavity","author":"by TS Eliot","description":"Escaped from Old Possum's Book of Practical Cats, Macavity is now the star of his own picture book. With new illustrations from Arthur Robins, this timeless rhyme will charm a new generation.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32669/9781406343939-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32669","title":"This is Not My Hat","author":"by Jon Klassen","description":"A little fish has stolen an equally small bowler hat from a much bigger fish. Hiding himself in the weedsm, he is confident he won't be discovered - but the big fish is on his trail...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33843/mouse-is-small.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33843","title":"Mouse is Small","author":"by Mary Murphy","description":"A colourful picture book about animal sizes"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33368/9780857075765-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33368","title":"Monkey Nut","author":"by Simon Rickerty","description":"Two little spiders find a monkey nut, and shouting 'it's mine!', each tries to snatch it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32916/9781408330029-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32916","title":"The Dark","author":"by Lemony Snicket","description":"One night, the night-light goes out, and the dark calls Laszlo down into the basement to meet it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33213/monsterzoo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33213","title":"Do Not Enter the Monster Zoo!","author":"by Amy Sparkes and Sara Ogilvie","description":"Can our young hero take on a Monster Zoo full of naughty creatures - and survive to tell the tale?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":304,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/304/","title":"Books set in a dystopia","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32919/9780192756268-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32919","title":"After Tomorrow","author":"by Gillian Cross","description":"Matt's world changed forever on Armageddon Monday, when five banks crashed simultaneously. Now he's living in a refugee camp, struggling to survive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33071/648707d7-f3ef-4fc3-a53e-3fe7c750b6c1-img100.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33071","title":"Hav3n","author":"by Tom Easton","description":"When the world is struck down by a fast-spreading, deadly plague, only the small, isolated village of Great Sheen in the English countryside manages to escape the ravages of death","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32456/moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32456","title":"Maggot Moon","author":"by Sally Gardner","description":"Combining conspiracy theory and dystopia, this hugely original novel is set in an alternate 1950s in which Britain is dominated by the ruthlessly oppressive forces of The Motherland.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33801/boy-in-the-tower.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33801","title":"The Boy in the Tower","author":"by Polly Ho-Yen","description":"Taking place in a believable urban, multicultural environment that will be familiar to many young readers, Polly Ho-Yen's debut is an impressively moving and thought-provoking story that will touch children and adults alike.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33646/interrogation-of-ashala-wolf.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33646","title":"The Interrogation of Ashala Wolf","author":"by Ambelin Kwaymullina","description":"The first in a four part series, this imaginative and engrossing story is a clever spin on the dystopian genre. The author expertly creates a believable, alternative world featuring a strong, moral heroine.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32737/9781849416177-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32737","title":"The Lost Girl","author":"by Sangu Mandanna","description":"Eva is an echo, created by the mysterious Weavers as an exact copy of someone else. When her 'other', Amarra is killed in a car accident, Eva must take over her life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32797/boonies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32797","title":"Boonie","author":"by Richard Masson","description":"In a post-apocalyptic world, JD is growing up far from civilisation, out in the Dry Marsh. When the Silver Men kill his father and burn down his shack, JD heads for the City to find out why.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33174/9780552566148.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33174","title":"ACID","author":"by Emma Pass","description":"Jenna Strong used to be pretty, popular and rich - now she is a violent, battle-scarred skinhead in an all-male maximum security prison.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32457/firecity.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32457","title":"Fire City","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"In this terrifying dystopia from Bali Rai, the young, the old and the sick have become the prey of horrifying demons that Fire City's wealthy employ to police the city.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":305,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/305/","title":"Colours","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33362/9781406322187-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33362","title":"The Black Book of Colours","author":"by Menena Cottin & Rosana Faria","description":"A visually impaired boy introduces us to colours as he experiences them – through his senses of hearing, touch, smell and taste.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29356/mr-pusskins-colours.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29356","title":"Mr Pusskins Colours","author":"by Sam Lloyd","description":"A great introduction to colours, simple stories and relationships – all in twelve pages!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32051/9781419703294-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32051","title":"Colours","author":"by Pantone Inc","description":"This fun book illustrates all the colours of the rainbow with simple, bright pictures.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"}]}
{"id":306,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/306/","title":"Casual inclusion of disabled characters","list_description":"This list comprises books which include disabled characters within their images and/or story naturally, subtly and often without comment.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25239/giant-turnip-9781852697884.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25239","title":"The Giant Turnip","author":"by Henriette Barkow","description":"The children in Miss Honeywood's class decide to grow vegetables in their school garden. What a shock they get when they discover a huge turnip that they are unable to move.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34622/my-big-barefoot-book-of-wonderful-words.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34622","title":"My Big Barefoot Book of Wonderful Words","author":"by Sophie Fatus","description":"A simple concept but a hugely satisfying wealth of material is offered up in this vibrant catalogue of words and pictures. The reader is first introduced to a diverse cast of characters before joining them in a jubilant celebration of..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30353/the-great-big-book-of-families.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30353","title":"The Great Big Book of Families","author":"by Mary Hoffman","description":"Hoffman and Asquith celebrate the diversity of family life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32217/white-dolphins.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32217","title":"White Dolphin","author":"by Gill Lewis","description":"A young dolphin, washed up on the beach, unexpectedly brings Kara and Felix together. But the new friends must take on new challenges - finding out the truth about Kara's missing mother, and protecting the bay when it falls under...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28694/the-ding-dong-bag.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28694","title":"The Ding-Dong Bag","author":"by Polly Peters","description":"The fast-moving and rhythmic text make this great book perfect for reading aloud, and a subtle arm splint on one of the boys is typical of Child’s Play’s inclusive approach to books.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33868/made-by-raffi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33868","title":"Made By Raffi","author":"by Craig Pomranz","description":"A delightful and gently revolutionary picture book that challenges our absurd notions about what constitutes 'normal' or 'appropriate'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25510/small-steps.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25510","title":"Small Steps","author":"by Louis Sachar","description":"Small Steps is the indirect sequel to Holes and follows the fortunes of its protagonist, Armpit, once he leaves Camp Green Lake and returns home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33035/9781847803887-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33035","title":"Max the Champion","author":"by Sean Stockdale and Alexandra Strick","description":"This inclusive book is about a boy who loves sport, his friends, and school - and has a vivid imagination","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28595/it-s-raining-it-s-pouring.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28595","title":"It's Raining! It's Pouring! We're Exploring!","author":"by Polly Peters and Jess Stockham","description":"Three children are stuck inside while it's raining. Luckily they have plenty of imaginative ideas to turn a potentially dull and dreary day into a series of exhilarating adventures.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":307,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/307/","title":"Booktime Books 2014-15","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30536/hairy-maclary.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30536","title":"Hairy Maclary from Donaldson's Dairy","author":"by Lynley Dodd","description":"This hilarious rhyming story follows Hairy Maclary from Donaldson's Dairy, as he sets off for a walk in town","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33873/go-to-bed-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33873","title":"Go To Bed","author":"by Emma Lynch","description":"Go to Bed explores a variety of beds, nests and homes around the world, allowing parents and teachers to support children as they develop their own reading skills.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":308,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/308/","title":"Back to school","list_description":"Some funny, exciting, mysterious, thrilling stories about school, friends and everyday life to get back into the swing of things.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24523/cloud-busting.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24523","title":"Cloud Busting","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Shortlisted for the 2004 Nestlé Smarties Book Prize (age 6-8 category), an exploration of an unlikely friendship between two very different boys.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25738/sunita-s-secret.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25738","title":"Sunita's Secret","author":"by Narinder Dhami","description":"Sunita's perfect world collapses when her father is accused of stealing money from his clients, and he disappears.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32735/9781408827789-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32735","title":"Shiverton Hall","author":"by Emerald Fennell","description":"Arriving at his new school, Shiverton Hall, Arthur discovers its has a strange and spine-chilling history of ancient curses and sinister secrets.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24688/ghost-writer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24688","title":"Ghost Writer","author":"by Julia Jarman","description":"Frankie Ruggles has just moved to a new school. Not only does he have to cope with explaining his dyslexia, but he's also visited by the ghost of a Victorian boy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33678/glass-bird-girl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33678","title":"The Glass Bird Girl","author":"by Esme Kerr","description":"There's an old-fashioned quality to this boarding school mystery; yet there is more tension, suspense and sinister atmosphere here than you might expect from a traditional Blytonesque tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31722/9781408313039-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31722","title":"The World of Norm","author":"by Jonathan Meres","description":"A funny illustrated book likely to find favour with fans of Wimpy Kid, Big Nate and Tom Gates.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29545/9781847382306-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29545","title":"Ribblestrop","author":"by Andy Mulligan","description":"There’s a wonderful, anarchic energy to this funny, pacey, action-packed novel","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33019/9781782690009-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33019","title":"Oksa Pollock: The Last Hope","author":"by Anne Plichota and Cendrine Wolf","description":"The Oksa Pollock series has legions of fans all over the world, and this first installment leaves us in no doubt why.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33631/dream-on-amber.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33631","title":"Dream On, Amber","author":"by Emma Shevah","description":"Dream On, Amber is fast and funny with wonderful little illustrations. Emma Shevah has created a wonderfully modern voice that manages to perfectly balance a sensitive subject with light and laughter.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33706/murder-most-unladylike.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33706","title":"Murder Most Unladylike","author":"by Robin Stevens","description":"There's been a rather shocking murder at Deepdean School for Girls - but luckily, young detectives Daisy Wells and Hazel Wong are on the case!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":309,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/309/","title":"Cancer Awareness Month","list_description":"September is both Childhood Cancer Awareness Month and Ovarian Cancer Awareness month, so our latest booklist features a myriad of books featuring characters who have been afflicted by cancer.    ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33429/the_quarry.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33429","title":"The Quarry","author":"by Iain Banks","description":"Iain Banks's final novel tells the story of a group of old university friends who visit their old friend Guy, a misanthropic 40-year-old who is dying of cancer."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32043/homesickd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32043","title":"Homesick","author":"by Roshi Fernando","description":"Thoughtful, melancholic, haunting, Homesick is a collection of interlinked stories which muse on growing up, fitting in and the ephemeral nature of human life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25900/electric-michaelangelo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25900","title":"The Electric Michelangelo","author":"by Sarah Hall","description":"The Electric Michelangelo is a gutsy and exuberant fairground sideshow of a novel, an homage to the tattooist's art and to the seaside resorts of the early twentieth century."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32622/9781848879218.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32622","title":"Mortality","author":"by Christopher Hitchens","description":"Whatever your opinion of the late Christopher Hitchens, you can't deny he had a way with words. There was a real weight and intensity to what he said. He may not have always said the right thing but he had..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25939/how-to-breathe-underwater.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25939","title":"How to Breathe Underwater","author":"by Julie Orringer","description":"'Outstanding'; 'unbelievably good'; 'pitch perfect'; clear, cool and enticing'; 'subtle and multi-layered': these are just some of the justified reactions to Julie Orringer's first collection of short stories."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33010/9781906994464.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33010","title":"Unhappy-Go-Lucky","author":"by Ian Pattison","description":"Unhappy-Go-Lucky explores the life of Ivan Moss, a struggling writer who must put his selfishness aside to care for his ailing mother as she battles against lung cancer."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31125/i-curse-the-river-of-time.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31125","title":"I Curse the River of Time","author":"by Per Petterson","description":"Everything goes wrong for thirtysomething Arvid Jansen in one autumnal weekend in 1989. With a backdrop of the crumbling of Eastern communism, he is divorcing, watching his mother die from cancer and feels lost."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31417/9780701186029.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31417","title":"Swamplandia!","author":"by Karen Russell","description":"This exuberant fantastical romp about alligator wrestlers in the Florida Everglades by acclaimed author Karen Russell is, simply put, fun"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30325/the-sickness.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30325","title":"The Sickness","author":"by Alberto Barrera Tyszka","description":"In this strange, understated yet compelling debut novel, Venezuelan writer Alberto Barrera Tyszka explores the meaning of sickness: physical, mental and social."}]}
{"id":310,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/310/","title":"Back to School","list_description":"The holidays are over, but here are some books to get you back into the school spirit...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28940/parttimeindian.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28940","title":"The Absolutely True Diary of a Part-time Indian","author":"by Sherman Alexie","description":"In his first book for young adults, Sherman Alexie tells the story of budding artist Junior, a 14-year-old Native American","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25216/9780689875359-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25216","title":"A Great And Terrible Beauty","author":"by Libba Bray","description":"Gemma Doyle struggles to deal with her strange supernatural powers in this first installment of Libba Bray's series set in Victorian England.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33518/9781406353044.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33518","title":"Jane, the Fox & Me","author":"by Fanny Britt & Isabelle Arsenault","description":"This thought-provoking graphic novel by Fanny Britt, exquisitely illustrated by Isabelle Arsenault, is a real visual delight","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32859/9781471400292-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32859","title":"A Month with April-May","author":"by Edyth Bulbring","description":"Follow bored, angry yet irresistible teen April-May as she negotiates a new school and a new family situation in her own unique way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33385/9781471402272-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33385","title":"The Isobel Journal","author":"by Isobel Harrop","description":"Subtitled ‘Just a Northern Girl from Where Nothing Really Happens’, this beautifully-presented book from 18-year-old debut author Isobel Harrop is a vivid scrapbook of teenage life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32334/9781848775466-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32334","title":"Whisper","author":"by Chrissie Keighery","description":"Fifteen year old Demi is starting a new school – always a nerve-racking experience. However, for Demi, it represents a time of far more dramatic change, as her new school is a college for deaf students, a recent case of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32379/9781471400001-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32379","title":"Insignia","author":"by S J Kinkaid","description":"What if playing computer games could help you save the world?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33274/d340f618-ed9b-48fc-8aff-6b32b6502aba-img100-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33274","title":"Hello Darkness","author":"by Anthony McGowan","description":"Johnny Middleton is hiding in the boys toilets to avoid double maths when a shower of dead stick insects hit the floor.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25678/sea-of-monsters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25678","title":"Percy Jackson and the Sea of Monsters","author":"by Rick Riordan","description":"After monsters infiltrate Percy Jackson's school and try to kill him, Percy, Annabeth and new schoolmate Tyson, who is not all he seems, rush to Camp Half-Blood which is under attack.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33433/eleanor-parks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33433","title":"Eleanor & Park","author":"by Rainbow Rowell","description":"Set over the course of one school year in 1986, this is a beautifully-written love story about two high school outsiders","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33370/9780007489442-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33370","title":"Geek Girl","author":"by Holly Smale","description":"Everyone at school knows Harriet Manners is a geek.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32037/dark-lord.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32037","title":"Dark Lord: The Teenage Years","author":"by Jamie Thomson","description":"The Dark Lord falls to earth, crash-landing in a suburban car park in the body of a teenage boy, spitting out poisonous mucus","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":312,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/312/","title":"World Teachers' Day","list_description":"Sunday 5 October is World Teachers' Day. So, let's throw our mortar boards in the air for teachers all over the globe. The following A+ list contains books that feature a range of different teachers. Enjoy! ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33394/madonna-and-the-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33394","title":"The Madonna on the Moon","author":"by Rolf Bauerdick","description":"An enthralling story that is populated with brilliant characters, it definitely deserves to be on every Christmas reading list."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28052/sunstroke.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28052","title":"Sunstroke","author":"by Tessa Hadley","description":"This is a deftly assembled collection of short stories about the everyday flow of human lives, and unexpected moments that can shift those lives off (or back on) course."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27127/notes-on-a-scandal.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27127","title":"Notes on a Scandal","author":"by Zoe Heller","description":"It is not hard to see why Zoë Heller's second novel was shortlisted for the Man Booker Prize 2003: it is a precise and in parts hilarious account of a relationship between Sheba, a pottery teacher at a north London..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33456/rabbit_back_literature_soci.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33456","title":"Rabbit Back Literature Society","author":"by Pasi Ilmari Jääskeläinen","description":"A teacher in a small Finnish town starts to investigate when she notices that someone has been re-writing the storylines in classic books"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33548/the-dark-road-high-res-jacket-image.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33548","title":"The Dark Road","author":"by Ma Jian","description":"Meili, a young peasant woman born in the remote heart of China, is married to Kongzi, a village school teacher, and a distant descendant of Confucius. They have a daughter, but desperate for a son to carry on his illustrious..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30819/a-light-song-of-light.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30819","title":"A Light Song of Light","author":"by Kei Miller","description":"A Light Song of Light is full of beautiful, graceful poems ruminating on Miller’s various identities: teacher, immigrant, gay man and, of course, poet.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25019/be-near-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25019","title":"Be Near Me","author":"by Andrew O'Hagan","description":"Every word in this profound, and wonderful novel is there for a reason. Sentence by careful sentence, O'Hagan develops his characters and builds his devastating story with a 'capturing eye' for the truth."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33321/swing-low.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33321","title":"Swing Low","author":"by Miriam Toews","description":"Swing Low by Miriam Toews is a brave and interesting novel. Based on her imaginings of her father’s life long battle with manic depression, the book explores what it means to suffer in silence."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33379/stoner.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33379","title":"Stoner","author":"by John Williams","description":"Perhaps what marks Stoner out is its sheer simplicity, everything that needs to be said is said – and not a word more."}]}
{"id":313,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/313/","title":"Books to support understanding of mental health","list_description":"The lives of a huge proportion of children and young people will be touched by mental health issues, whether directly or indirectly. As many as one in ten children and young people aged five to 16 have a diagnosable mental health disorder - that is three in any one classroom.  By adulthood, the figure rises to one in four, meaning many children will come into contact with relatives or other adults who are affected.  Books that acknowledge and explore mental health problems can help to increase awareness, encourage dialogue, reduce stigma and develop real understanding. Such books are still fairly rare, but the following teen/young adult reads offer a range of different perspectives and are well worth seeking out.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34805/am-i-normal-yet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34805","title":"Am I Normal Yet?","author":"by Holly Bourne","description":"This is a powerful and engrossing read that successfully informs, shocks, reassures and entertains in equal measures.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34897/aubrey-and-the-terrible-yoot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34897","title":"Aubrey and the Terrible Yoot","author":"by Horatio Clare","description":"This fabulously illustrated book addresses the difficult subject of parental depression, at once describing the horror of Aubrey’s dad’s experience but also remaining upbeat and full of surreal humour.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29391/bang-bang-you-re-dead.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29391","title":"Bang, Bang, You're Dead!","author":"by Narinder Dhami","description":"Dhami's thriller takes us from a dysfunctional home, where twins Mia and Jamie live with their divorced mother, to a school siege in which a pupil holds a class hostage.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29216/runningoncracks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29216","title":"Running on the Cracks","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Donaldson's style engages immediately and through her characters she raises many questions about our attitudes to those perceived as ‘different'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33906/finding-a-voice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33906","title":"Finding a Voice","author":"by Kim Hood","description":"This is an engaging story about the two-way nature of friendship and the risks of making assumptions. The overriding message is uplifting, whilst also leaving the reader with a powerful reminder that good intentions aren't always enough.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12-16"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33738/scarlet-ibisd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33738","title":"Scarlet Ibis","author":"by Gill Lewis","description":"At times heart-rending, this is a powerful story which skilfully gains our sympathy for those who are often misjudged, feared and derided by society.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33266/ness.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33266","title":"More Than This","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"'Haven't you ever felt like there has to be more? Like there's more out there somewhere, just beyond your grasp, and if you could only get to it?'","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33947/the-ghosts-of-heavend.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33947","title":"The Ghosts of Heaven","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"The Ghosts of Heaven is an excellent book that will open up new avenues of thought and future reading and introduces teenage readers to a more inventive understanding of storytelling.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30105/illustratedmum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30105","title":"The Illustrated Mum","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"This is a moving yet unsentimental account of two children coming to terms with their mother’s depression, mental instability and alcohol problem.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":315,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/315/","title":"Occult of Personality","list_description":"Seeing as we didn't have a scary Halloween-related booklist in October, we thought we'd make it up to you in November by featuring a booklist all about the occult, as it's Occult Day on 18 November.  So enjoy our booklist dedicated to witches, black magic and the paranormal.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33339/harvest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33339","title":"Harvest","author":"by Jim Crace","description":"Harvest is not a piece of historical fiction, rather a snapshot of one persons struggle to come to terms with political upheaval, violence, dispossession and change beyond his control."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27817/gothic-tales.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27817","title":"Gothic Tales","author":"by Elizabeth Gaskell","description":"Gaskell's chilling Gothic tales blend the real and the supernatural to eerie, compelling effect, and form a stark contrast to the social realism of Gaskell's novels."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26965/death-in-breslau.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26965","title":"Death in Breslau","author":"by Marek Krajewski","description":"Marek Krajewski has written a quartet of novels which unfold the history of this exceptional city, standing on the faultline and crossroads of 20th century Europe."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28204/beyond-black.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28204","title":"Beyond Black","author":"by Hilary Mantel","description":"Alison Hart, a medium by trade, tours the dormitory towns of London's orbital road with her flint-hearted sidekick Colette, passing on messages from dead ancestors."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27967/the-migration-of-ghosts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27967","title":"The Migration of Ghosts","author":"by Pauline Melville","description":"In this collection of short stories, the author dabbles in and out of the occult."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32514/9780571284030.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32514","title":"Kimberley's Capital Punishment","author":"by Richard Milward","description":"This is a shocking, laugh-out-loud, nightmare-and-nausea-inducing book; a wild narrative experiment that recalls taboo-busting writers from William Burroughs to Irvine Welsh to Chuck Palahniuk."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32814/9780571286751.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32814","title":"Shall We Gather at the River?","author":"by Peter Murphy","description":"The central event of this novel takes place on the 1 November 1984, when the river Rua bursts its banks, flooding the small Irish town of Murn and the surrounding areas."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29853/thursday-night-widows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29853","title":"Thursday Night Widows","author":"by Claudia Pineiro","description":"Claudia Piñeiro’s Thursday Night Widows is a whodunnit, a black comedy, a social portrait and a prophecy, a timely dissection of the disintegration of a privileged class and an important addition to 21st Century Latin American fiction."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31034/9781407031323-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31034","title":"The Honey Gatherers","author":"by Mimlu Sen","description":"Mimlu Sen is living a bohemian life in Paris when she witnesses an electrifying performance by three wandering minstrels from rural India."}]}
{"id":316,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/316/","title":"Magical reads","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33661/jinx-wizards-apprentice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33661","title":"Jinx: the Wizard's Apprentice","author":"by Sage Blackwood","description":"This is an exciting adventure that also references social, ethical, and environmental issues on the way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33287/the-enchanted-wood.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33287","title":"The Enchanted Wood","author":"by Enid Blyton","description":"When Joe, Beth and Frannie move into a new home, they discover a mysterious wood on their very doorstep.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33293/worst-witch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33293","title":"The Worst Witch","author":"by Jill Murphy","description":"Long before Harry Potter first went to Hogwarts, trainee witch Mildred Hubble embarked on life at Miss Cackle's Academy for Witches...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32258/9780007430017-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32258","title":"The Peppers and the International Magic Guys","author":"by Sian Pattenden","description":"Monty and Esmé's parents have left them for a week in the care of their magician uncle, Potty. Monty has been happily drawn in to be Uncle Potty's assistant in his magic tricks, but unfortunately, his routine keeps going disastrously...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33111/9781405262705.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33111","title":"Agatha Parrot and the Zombie Bird","author":"by Kjartan Poskitt","description":"Agatha Parrot suspects Misto the Mysterious is up to no good!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32125/9781849393553-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32125","title":"A Fairy-Tale","author":"by Tony Ross","description":"In a dreary town, between the two world wars, young Bessie is lonely and bored. She meets the elderly Mrs Leaf who lives next door and they talk about whether fairies really exist.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":317,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/317/","title":"Magical stories","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30829/a-most-improper-magick.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30829","title":"A Most Improper Magick","author":"by Stephanie Burgis","description":"A 21st-century take on Jane Austen's world, entertainingly viewed through the eyes of a 12-year-old heroine who discovers she has inherited her mother's magical abilities.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34016/archie-green-magicians-secret.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34016","title":"Archie Green and the Magician's Secret","author":"by D D Everest","description":"If you love books that show you where the magical could be hiding in your everyday world then this is the book for you.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30947/the-last-dragonslayer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30947","title":"The Last Dragonslayer","author":"by Jasper Fforde","description":"Times are tough for Jennifer Strange, manager of Kazam Mystical Arts - then predictions of a new Dragonslayer coming to slay the Last Dragon begin...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24536/inkheart-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24536","title":"Inkheart","author":"by Cornelia Funke","description":"12-year-old Meggie and her father, Mo, a bookbinder, both love reading, but since the disappearance of Meggie's mother, they no longer read together. One night a stranger knocks at their door, prompting Mo to reveal his awful secret.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33446/9781848531062-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33446","title":"Blackberry Blue","author":"by Jamila Gavin & Richard Collingridge","description":"A stunning collection of mystical fairy tales that are at once exotic and fresh, and traditionally heartening.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33305/the-lion-the-witch-the-wardrobe.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33305","title":"The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe","author":"by C S Lewis","description":"When Peter, Susan, Edmund and Lucy - step through a wardrobe door in the strange country house where they are staying, they find themselves in the land of Narnia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25103/midnight-for-charlie-bone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25103","title":"Midnight For Charlie Bone","author":"by Jenny Nimmo","description":"Charlie is unnerved to discover that he can hear people in photographs talking. His aunts take an unhealthy interest in his gift and send him to the notorious Bloor's Academy...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31462/troubletwisters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31462","title":"Troubletwisters","author":"by Garth Nix","description":"The first of a five part fantasy series","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33019/9781782690009-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33019","title":"Oksa Pollock: The Last Hope","author":"by Anne Plichota and Cendrine Wolf","description":"The Oksa Pollock series has legions of fans all over the world, and this first installment leaves us in no doubt why.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30267/9780747558194-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30267","title":"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone","author":"by J K Rowling","description":"After the misery of life with his ghastly aunt and uncle, Harry Potter is delighted to have the chance to embark on an exciting new life at the Hogwart's School of Wizardry and Witchcraft.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-13"}]}
{"id":318,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/318/","title":"Penguin books for Penguin Awareness Day","list_description":"It's Penguin Awareness Day, so, we've put together a booklist full of books about penguins, so you can get to know more about the flightless birds and love everything they're about.  There's also our Penguin Huddle game and cool penguin facts and our audio book Pengin goes on holiday/ Pengwin ar ei Wyliau in Welsh on offer as well.   ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30416/me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30416","title":"Me","author":"by Emma Dodd","description":"A baby penguin realises how small he is and on each page he compares himself to the world around him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26003/penguin-by-polly-dunbar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26003","title":"Penguin","author":"by Polly Dunbar","description":"Polly Dunbar's illustrations are gorgeous and her palette stylish - from the endearing Ben's rosy cheeks to the magnificent turquoise lion who eats him up.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33569/penguin-in-peril.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33569","title":"Penguin in Peril","author":"by Helen Hancocks","description":"Penguin hatches an escape plan to avoid becoming dinner for a group of cats, who have kidnapped him from the zoo.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30433/monday.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30433","title":"Monday","author":"by Anne Herbauts","description":"Monday is a penguin who likes to stay warm. When winter comes, Monday's house is blown away in a snowstorm, and his friends go in search of him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33169/9780857077509.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33169","title":"Ping and Pong Are Best Friends (Mostly)","author":"by Tim Hopgood","description":"Penguins, Ping and Pong, are best friends. But whatever they do – skating, painting, fishing – Pong always does it better. Ping starts to feel a little downcast.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25161/lost-found.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25161","title":"Lost and Found","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"Once there was a sad, lonely penguin who appeared at the door of a young boy. The boy decided he must be lost, so he set off to find his home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35433/penguin-problems.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35433","title":"Penguin Problems","author":"by Jory John","description":"A little penguin is out in the cold, and he doesn’t like it: the sun is too bright, the ocean is too salty, and he’s tired of whales and orcas trying to hunt him. A sweet and tongue-in-cheek story about...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26570/and-tango-makes-three.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26570","title":"And Tango Makes Three","author":"by Justin Richardson and Peter Parnell","description":"Roy and Silo are two boy penguins who live in the zoo in New York's Central Park. This is a really delightful story and the message behind it is subtle. It's a true story, and you can learn more about...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33735/not-so-perfect-penguin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33735","title":"The Not-So-Perfect-Penguin","author":"by Steve Smallman","description":"Big, lively illustrations and a simple message make this book ideal for classroom circle times. Points for discussion are included at the back.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32668/9781408829059-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32668","title":"Penguin and Pinecone","author":"by Salina Yoon","description":"Penguin would like to keep the pinecone he finds, but soon realises that it was lost and isn’t happy in the snowy land in which he lives.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"}]}
{"id":319,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/319/","title":"New brother or sister","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30574/baby-s-catalogue.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30574","title":"The Baby's Catalogue","author":"by Janet and Allan Ahlberg","description":"This book's packed with lots of baby pictures and baby items. It's great for learning and making up stories - this fantastic book will lead to lots of talk with your child.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25027/there-s-a-house-inside-my-mummy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25027","title":"There's A House Inside My Mummy","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"This is just the book to explain to inquisitive children what going on inside mum during pregnancy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34035/sophie-new-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34035","title":"Sophie and the New Baby","author":"by Laurence and Catherine Anholt","description":"A comforting book about sharing parents' love...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30715/my-sister-is-an-alien.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30715","title":"My sister is an Alien","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"Alfie's new baby sister, Ruby, looks, sounds and smells like an alien. Alfie is convinced she often cries for home. He decides to take Ruby back to the moon where she belongs.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33971/miffy-and-the-new-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33971","title":"Miffy and the New Baby","author":"by Dick Bruna","description":"Miffy's mummy and daddy have some very exciting news, Miffy is going to be a big sister!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30794/there-s-going-to-be-a-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30794","title":"There's Going to be a Baby","author":"by John Burningham","description":"A mother tells her little boy that ‘there’s going to be a baby’, but the little boy doesn’t like the sound of this – he doesn’t think they really need the new baby…","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33927/new-small-person.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33927","title":"The New Small Person","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"An endearingly funny story, featuring Lauren Child's heart-warming illustrations, about the arrival of a new sibling and the havoc that ensues.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34047/usborne-new-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34047","title":"Usborne First Experiences: The New Baby","author":"by Anna Civardi and Stephen Cartwright","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30807/just-because.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30807","title":"Just Because","author":"by Rebecca Elliott","description":"This uplifting book focuses on a sibling relationship, as a little boy affectionately describes his older sister","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34048/you-and-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34048","title":"You and Me","author":"by Rachel Fuller","description":"Explore and talk about what will change when a new baby arrives","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34044/spots-baby-sister.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34044","title":"Spot's Baby Sister","author":"by Eric Hill","description":"Spot and his friends play with his new sister, Susie.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34037/whats-in-tummy-mummy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34037","title":"What's in your Tummy, Mummy?","author":"by Sam Llloyd","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28640/ouch-pouch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28640","title":"There's an Ouch in My Pouch!","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"Willaby Wallaby is throwing a wobbly...He’s quite determined he still needs a pouch to live in, but suddenly it’s just too knobbly, wodgy, wedgy and wriggly and so he jumps out.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
