iew/34175","title":"Baby Touch: One! Two! Three! bath book","author":"by Ladybird","description":"Padded, waterproof counting book for baby bath and meal times","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34182/puffin-baby-and-toddler-treasury.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34182","title":"The Puffin Baby and Toddler Treasury","author":"by Various","description":"Favourite nursery rhymes, lullabies, poems and stories in one book","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34176/baby-touch-flip-flap.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34176","title":"Baby Touch Flip-Flap book","author":"by Ladybird","description":"Touch-and-feel book with colourful pictures to explore with your baby","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34177/hello-animals.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34177","title":"Hello, Animals!","author":"by Smriti Prasadam and Emily Bolam","description":"Simple, friendly and engaging board book for babies","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30632/nursery-rhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30632","title":"Nursery Rhymes","author":"by Priddy Books","description":"A large board book of over 20 nursery rhymes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34180/thats-not-my-teddy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34180","title":"That's not my teddy...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"Touch-feely book with colourful illustrations and simply text","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":321,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/321/","title":"Great Christmas gifts for 9-12 year olds","list_description":"Looking for the perfect gifts this Christmas? Check out our list of great books from the past year that children aged 9-12 will love finding under the tree or in their Christmas stocking.  For more children's book recommendations, discover a book every day with our advent calendar!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33930/mynameisbook.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33930","title":"My Name is Book","author":"by John Agard","description":"If you are intrigued as to how sheep and birds have played important roles in the recording of the written word then this is the definitely the book for you!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34670/half-a-creature-from-the-seas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34670","title":"Half a Creature from the Sea","author":"by David Almond","description":"A collection of eight spooky tales of the fantastic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33518/9781406353044.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33518","title":"Jane, the Fox & Me","author":"by Fanny Britt & Isabelle Arsenault","description":"This thought-provoking graphic novel by Fanny Britt, exquisitely illustrated by Isabelle Arsenault, is a real visual delight","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34083/animalium.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34083","title":"Animalium","author":"by Jenny Broom","description":"Quirky yet authoritative, this book is bursting with information to engage young naturalists, whilst the spectacular illustrations in a rich colour palette give it real 'wow' factor.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33850/compton-valance.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33850","title":"Compton Valance: The Most Powerful Boy in the Universe","author":"by Matt Brown","description":"TV presenter Matt Brown's bonkers debut plays with form and timelines almost to the brink of confusion. It will take a fairly sophisticated reader to keep up!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34089/spy-who-loved-school-dinners.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34089","title":"The Spy Who Loved School Dinners","author":"by Pamela Butchart","description":"Izzy is really excited to be picked to look after the new girl, Mathilde, but the new girl isn't quite what Izzy and her friends were expecting...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33982/creeps.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33982","title":"The Creeps: A Samuel Johnson Adventure","author":"by John Connolly","description":"This is the third book in the Samuel Johnson trilogy, although it reads perfectly well as a stand-alone nove. The fantastic detail makes this book stand out from the crowd.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33872/witchworld.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33872","title":"Witchworld","author":"by Emma Fischel","description":"Witchworld is a thoroughly bewitching tale that brings witches into the 21st century and touches upon environmental issues as well as family relationships.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33508/9781471402388.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33508","title":"Ophelia and the Marvellous Boy","author":"by Karen Foxlee","description":"On her first day exploring the strange museum in the foreign city where it always snows, Ophelia stumbles across something impossible: a boy, locked away in a forgotten room.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33984/sleeper-and-spindle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33984","title":"The Sleeper and the Spindle","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"This magnificent book combines two well-known fairy tales and challenges everything familiar about them. A spectacular book that deserves a spot on every bookcase.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33446/9781848531062-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33446","title":"Blackberry Blue","author":"by Jamila Gavin & Richard Collingridge","description":"A stunning collection of mystical fairy tales that are at once exotic and fresh, and traditionally heartening.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34046/the-imaginary.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34046","title":"The Imaginary","author":"by A F Harrold","description":"This is young fiction of the very best quality, showcasing inspiration, inventiveness and an intoxicating passion for storytelling. The Imaginary has the potential to be a family favourite and a future classic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33801/boy-in-the-tower.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33801","title":"The Boy in the Tower","author":"by Polly Ho-Yen","description":"Taking place in a believable urban, multicultural environment that will be familiar to many young readers, Polly Ho-Yen's debut is an impressively moving and thought-provoking story that will touch children and adults alike.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33678/glass-bird-girl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33678","title":"The Glass Bird Girl","author":"by Esme Kerr","description":"There's an old-fashioned quality to this boarding school mystery; yet there is more tension, suspense and sinister atmosphere here than you might expect from a traditional Blytonesque tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33898/has-anyone-seen-jessica-jenkins.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33898","title":"Has Anyone Seen Jessica Jenkins?","author":"by Liz Kessler","description":"One Friday afternoon in Geography Jessica's friend, Izzy, notices Jessica turning invisible...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33738/scarlet-ibisd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33738","title":"Scarlet Ibis","author":"by Gill Lewis","description":"At times heart-rending, this is a powerful story which skilfully gains our sympathy for those who are often misjudged, feared and derided by society.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33755/secret-of-the-tombs-the-phoenix-code.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33755","title":"Secrets of the Tombs; The Phoenix Code","author":"by Helen Moss","description":"There's a fast-moving plot, plenty of cliff-hangers and unexpected bad-guys, with humour provided by interplay between happy-go-lucky Ryan and nerdy Chloe in this engaging, informative ancient historical mystery.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34090/corpse-talk-season-1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34090","title":"Corpse Talk: Season 1","author":"by Adam Murphy","description":"Corpse Talk, the 'show that brings the dead famous to life' is a highly amusing and clever comic style history book that introduces the reader to historical figures in a fresh and funny way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34065/brockenspectre.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34065","title":"The Brockenspectre","author":"by Linda Newbery","description":"Tomas sets out to find his father, terrified that the Brockenspectre - a mountain monster which his father had told him about - has got him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34071/moone-boythe-blunder-years.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34071","title":"Moone Boy: The Blunder Years","author":"by Chris O'Dowd and Nick V Murphy","description":"Genuinely bizarre and ridiculously funny, this is one of the maddest books of the year.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34080/glass-children.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34080","title":"The Glass Children","author":"by Kristina Ohlsson","description":"After the death of her father, Billie and her mum are moving to a new town for a fresh start. But the house - or somebody in it - is trying to drive them out.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34078/lost-children-mysteries-ravenstorm-island.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34078","title":"Mysteries of Ravenstorm Island: The Lost Children","author":"by Gillian Philip","description":"Thrown together during a summer holiday on a remote island, Molly and Arthur seem unlikely friends who must solve a mystery together.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34072/last-of-the-spirits.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34072","title":"The Last of the Spirits","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"This book is the perfect Christmas gift for anyone who has watched and loved a film adaptation of A Christmas Carol but who isn't quite ready for Dickens himself just yet!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34087/goth-girl-and-the-fete-worse-than-deaths.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34087","title":"Goth Girl and the Fete Worse than Death","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Chris Riddell's third book in the Goth Girl series intrigues and delights with a cakey combination of adventure, love and webbed footnotes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33804/cat-who-came-in-through-the-roof.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33804","title":"The Cat Who Came in Off the Roof","author":"by Annie M G Schmidt","description":"This is a humorous, surreal and satisfying story with an old fashioned feel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34088/silly-book-side-splitting-stuff.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34088","title":"The Silly Book of Side-Splitting Stuff","author":"by Andy Seed","description":"Ever wanted to know what kind of animal an aye-aye is? Or how much gravy the boot of a Mini Cooper Convertible can hold? What about which country's residents dine on maggot cheese?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33706/murder-most-unladylike.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33706","title":"Murder Most Unladylike","author":"by Robin Stevens","description":"There's been a rather shocking murder at Deepdean School for Girls - but luckily, young detectives Daisy Wells and Hazel Wong are on the case!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33979/opal-plumstead.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33979","title":"Opal Plumstead","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Fourteen-year-old Opal's family falls on hard times when her accountant father foolishly forges a cheque to support his family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":322,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/322/","title":"Great Christmas gifts for 5-8 year olds","list_description":"Looking for the perfect gifts this Christmas? Check out our list of great books that children aged 5-8 will love finding under the tree or in their Christmas stocking this year","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34063/im-a-little-alien.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34063","title":"I'm a Little Alien","author":"by James Carter","description":"Through rhyme smaller children can be introduced to new words and concepts while older children can try reading the poems aloud themselves. An absolute delight."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33707/tiny-the-invisible-world-of-microbes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33707","title":"Tiny: The Invisible World of Microbes","author":"by Nicola Davies","description":"This is an original, special and memorable book that sets the bar high for illustrated children's non-fiction.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33650/nuts-in-space.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33650","title":"Nuts in Space","author":"by Elys Dolan","description":"Fans of Elys Dolan's first book, Weasels, will love this second offering: a fun intergalactic caper packed with similarly silly humour.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33520/9780571302505.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33520","title":"Squishy McFluff: the Invisible Cat!","author":"by Pip Jones & Ella Okstad","description":"Squishy McFluff is Ava's best friend. He may be invisible, but that doesn't stop them having all kinds of fun together - and you won't believe just how much trouble one invisible kitten can cause!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33907/what-i-think-about-when-i-think-about-swimming.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33907","title":"What I Think About When I Think About … Swimming","author":"by Eleanor Levenson","description":"An introduction to philosophy and thoughts on the meaning of life as seen from the perspective of a goldfish.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34041/something-about-a-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34041","title":"Something About a Bear","author":"by Jackie Morris","description":"A beautiful gift for bear and book lovers alike, this is a showpiece for Morris's paintings which are as awe-inspiring as their subjects.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33851/9780141354156.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33851","title":"Danger is Everywhere","author":"by David O'Doherty","description":"Just like this book says, danger is everywhere. Don't worry, though, because Docter Noel Zone (yes, Docter) is an experienced Dangerologist and is here to help you in this fun and very funny book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33990/dragons-at-crumbling-castle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33990","title":"Dragons at Crumbling Castle (and Other Stories)","author":"by Terry Pratchett","description":"Despite the book's large size, the format is ideal for reluctant or newly confidant readers, the print large, well-spaced and liberally aided by the illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33909/cakes-in-space.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33909","title":"Cakes in Space","author":"by Philip Reeve and Sarah McIntyre","description":"This lively and exciting space story from the duo behind Oliver and the Seawigs is packed with fun, adventure and plenty of surreal humour.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33740/wild-moose-chase.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33740","title":"Wild Moose Chase","author":"by Siobhan Rowden","description":"Fascinating but perilous adventures through Asia drive the twins to work together. Humour, excitement and word-play abound, but don't obscure the underlying messages of friendship, co-operation and loyalty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34088/silly-book-side-splitting-stuff.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34088","title":"The Silly Book of Side-Splitting Stuff","author":"by Andy Seed","description":"Ever wanted to know what kind of animal an aye-aye is? Or how much gravy the boot of a Mini Cooper Convertible can hold? What about which country's residents dine on maggot cheese?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34075/treasury-of-animal-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34075","title":"A Treasury of Animal Stories","author":"by Holly webb","description":"There are puppies and kittens as well as ducks, a hedgehog and penguins too in these 11 stories about animals.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"}]}
{"id":323,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/323/","title":"Great Christmas gifts: Picture books","list_description":"Looking for the perfect gifts this Christmas? Check out our list of great picture books that children will love finding under the tree or in their Christmas stocking this year.  For inclusive titles, take a look at The Five of Us, Off to the Park, Over the Hills and Far Away, or Made by Raffi.  For parents who are unconfident readers, Freddy and the Pig, Itch Scritch Scratch, Wolfman and All I Said Was are picture books that will support your reading with your child.  For beautiful books, have a look at Have You Seen My Dragon?, Mr Tweed's Good Deeds, and The Memory of an Elephant.  And have a look to see what else is there!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33908/colour-thief.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33908","title":"The Colour Thief","author":"by Gabriel Alborozo","description":"Zot lives in a grey world. Everyone around him is sad because there are no beautiful blues or happy yellows...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33627/yes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33627","title":"The Yes","author":"by Sarah Bee","description":"Stunning illustrations complement this quirky story to encourage reluctant adventurers to overcome their anxieties and grasp life with both hands.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33914/the-five-of-us.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33914","title":"The Five of Us","author":"by Quentin Blake","description":"This book is testament to Blake's belief that all children need to be able find themselves in books.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33700/little-lou-and-woolly-mammoth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33700","title":"Little Lou and the Woolly Mammoth","author":"by Paula Bowles","description":"This rhyming picture book tells an entertaining and engaging story with funny twists, which is great to read out loud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33946/this-book-just-ate-my-dog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33946","title":"This Book Just Ate My Dog!","author":"by Richard Byrne","description":"Bella decides to take her dog for a walk but as she crosses from one page to the next her dog disappears between the pages! Many people come to investigate including Bella's friend Ben, a dog rescue van and the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33951/bears-don-t-read.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33951","title":"Bears Don't Read","author":"by Emma Chichester Clark","description":"Bears Don't Read is a wonderfully engaging picture book about the joy of reading and how much fun it can be to help others.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34040/its-snow-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34040","title":"It's Snow Day","author":"by Richard Curtis","description":"This must-read winter picture book is crammed with fabulously joyful and expressive illustrations and will be loved by young and old alike.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33533/hermelin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33533","title":"Hermelin: The Detective Mouse","author":"by Mini Grey","description":"Hermelin the Detective Mouse lives in the attic at the top of Number 33 Offley Street. From here, with the help of his trusty typewriter and binoculars, he solves all kinds of mysteries","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34014/over-the-hills-far-away.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34014","title":"Over the Hills and Far Away","author":"by Elizabeth Hammill","description":"With rhymes from African, Native American, First Nation, Inuit, Latino and Maori cultures set alongside more well-known ones from the United Kingdom, this is truly a treasure trove of nursery rhymes that belongs on every bookshelf.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33530/shh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33530","title":"Shh! We Have a Plan","author":"by Chris Haughton","description":"Deep in the dark of a moonlit forest, four shady hunters are out to catch themselves a bird. Or at least they’re trying...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33771/have-you-seen-my-dragon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33771","title":"Have You Seen My Dragon?","author":"by Steve Light","description":"A counting book that is a cut above the rest in terms of its beautiful design and style. New Yorker Steve Light brings all the shapes and sights of the city to these stunning spreads.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33983/library-saved-rapunzel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33983","title":"How the Library (Not the Prince) Saved Rapunzel","author":"by Wendy Meddour","description":"This is how every fairy tale should be written, with the protagonist - regardless of gender - saving themselves from a life of solitude and boredom. A great read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33860/dinosaur-rhyme-time.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33860","title":"Dinosaur Rhyme Time","author":"by Valentina Mendicino","description":"All your favourite nursery rhymes... but all the characters in this version are dinosaurs!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33868/made-by-raffi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33868","title":"Made By Raffi","author":"by Craig Pomranz","description":"A delightful and gently revolutionary picture book that challenges our absurd notions about what constitutes 'normal' or 'appropriate'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33864/mr-tweeds-good-deeds.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33864","title":"Mr Tweed's Good Deeds","author":"by Jim Stoten","description":"Children will love playing along and discerning adults cannot fail to be impressed by Flying Eye's beautiful production. Mr Tweed's Good Deeds is very good indeed.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34042/memory-of-an-elephant.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34042","title":"The Memory of an Elephant","author":"by Sophie Strady","description":"The Memory of an Elephant is one of the most unusual picture books of the year. Marcel's marvellous book will be a real conversation piece.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33686/off-to-the-park-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33686","title":"Off to the Park!","author":"by Stephen Cheetham","description":"We're off to the park - what will we find? Which way shall we go? The swings or the slide? Take a look inside!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34026/freddy-and-the-pig.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34026","title":"Freddy and the Pig","author":"by Charlie Higson and Mark Chambers","description":"Freddy hates school and thinks that it is boring, but he comes up with clever plan. The dyslexia-friendly features make this book highly accessible."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33709/all-i-said-was.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33709","title":"All I Said Was","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"One of an innovative series of dyslexia-friendly picture books which feature accessible fonts, strong contrast, good spacing and uncluttered layout to ensure accessibility for all, including parents with reading difficulties."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34028/wolfman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34028","title":"Wolfman","author":"by Michael Rosen and Chris Mould","description":"Wolf Man has escaped from his cage and is wrecking the town. All of the people in the town are scared and are rushing to hide indoors. The dyslexia-friendly features make this book highly accessible."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34027/itch-scritch-scratch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34027","title":"Itch Scritch Scratch","author":"by Eleanor Updale and Sarah Horne","description":"Head lice are the focus of this fun and engaging picture book. The dyslexia-friendly features make this book highly accessible."}]}
{"id":324,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/324/","title":"Christmas Reads 2014","list_description":"Welcome in the festive period by checking out our Christmas booklist.  We've got heart-warming books that will put you in the mood for Christmas as well as unorthodox stories about affairs and murder! There's definitely something for everyone on our list. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27403/sleep-with-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27403","title":"Sleep With Me","author":"by Joanna Briscoe","description":"This sensual and psychologically disturbing novel is compulsively readable."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33499/harbour-street.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33499","title":"Harbour Street","author":"by Ann Cleeves","description":"DI Vera Stanhope investigates the murder of a woman whose life is shrouded in secrecy."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34057/9781784750398.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34057","title":"A Christmas Feast","author":"by Katie Fforde","description":"Fans of Katie Fforde will no doubt enjoy this festive offering of Christmas stories; it's an amusing book of bite size stories to be enjoyed during the hectic holiday season."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34058/elf.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34058","title":"The Reluctant Elf","author":"by Michele Gorman","description":"A delightful festive read in which a young woman must become a B&B Hostess over Christmas to achieve the rating her hospitalised Aunt needs to keep her livelihood"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32895/9781447210900-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32895","title":"The Book of My Lives","author":"by Aleksandar Hemon","description":"Shakespeare and genocide, football and third-world exile, joke Nazis and real Nazis, the most unimaginable fears of a parent and David Bowie in the tropical clouds. It's all here."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29274/in-other-rooms.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29274","title":"In Other Rooms, Other Wonders","author":"by Daniyal Mueenuddin","description":"In this beautiful and assured collection, Daniyal Mueenuddin works and reworks the eternal themes of life, love and death. His control never wavers - neither does his compassion."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33988/my-true-love-gave-to-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33988","title":"My True Love Gave to Me","author":"by Stephanie Perkins","description":"A collection of Christmas-themed romantic short stories, one for each of the 'twelve days', by some of the best known American YA authors.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32785/9781846555879.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32785","title":"The Healer","author":"by Antti Tuomainen","description":"Winner of the Best Finnish Crime Novel of the Year Award in 2010, The Healer is a fantastic introduction to a promising new name in Scandinavian Crime."}]}
{"id":325,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/325/","title":"Christmas gifts for teenagers 2014","list_description":"Looking for the perfect gifts this Christmas? Check out our list of great books that teenagers will love finding under the tree or in their Christmas stocking this year","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33805/half-a-kings.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33805","title":"Half a King","author":"by Joe Abercrombie","description":"From the first page, Yarvi's story, set in a vividly imagined fantasy world, is gripping, fast-paced and hard to put down. Explores complex questions of morality, loyalty and obligation.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33987/afterwalkers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33987","title":"Afterwalkers","author":"by Tom Becker","description":"This disturbing tale in the supernatural, zombie/horror genre has a refreshingly inventive storyline and credible and likeable protagonists the reader can really root for. A very rewarding and exciting page turner.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33518/9781406353044.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33518","title":"Jane, the Fox & Me","author":"by Fanny Britt & Isabelle Arsenault","description":"This thought-provoking graphic novel by Fanny Britt, exquisitely illustrated by Isabelle Arsenault, is a real visual delight","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33677/love-lies-lemon-pies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33677","title":"Love, Lies and Lemon Pies","author":"by Katy Cannon","description":"This heart-warming teen love story is as sweet and light as the lemon pie of the title. Katy Cannon manages to delicately touch on some difficult issues, without compromising the lightness of the tone.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33901/boy-with-the-tigers-heart.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33901","title":"The Boy with the Tiger's Heart","author":"by Linda Coggin","description":"Written, unusually, in the present tense, this dystopian fable expresses an idea about the way the relationship between nature and society could develop.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33866/speed-of-light.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33866","title":"Speed of Light","author":"by Joy Cowley","description":"Cowley's writing is a delight to read and this family drama is engrossing and endearing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33844/apple-and-rains.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33844","title":"Apple and Rain","author":"by Sarah Crossan","description":"Engrossing and uplifting, challenging and charming, Apple and Rain brings fiction and poetry together in a well-crafted story about growing up and learning to love.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33451/untitled-1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33451","title":"Boys Don't Knit","author":"by T S Easton","description":"'I'm aware that keeping a diary is considered part of the female domain, but in my life, with the family and friends I'm stuck with, it is the only reason I haven't run away and gone to live in the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33746/flora-in-loves.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33746","title":"Flora in Love","author":"by Natasha Farrant","description":"This lovely family story from Natasha Farrant is the second in the Diaries of Bluebell Gadsby series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33699/the-year-of-the-rats.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33699","title":"The Year of the Rat","author":"by Clare Furniss","description":"This unflinching portrait of a teenage girl dealing with the death of a parent is an enormously compelling read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33892/skink-no-surrender.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33892","title":"Skink No Surrender","author":"by Carl Hiaasen","description":"This is a brilliant and utterly gripping adventure, featuring an unusual, endearing and very funny hero in Skink. A tense thriller full of plot twists and laugh out loud humour.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33906/finding-a-voice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33906","title":"Finding a Voice","author":"by Kim Hood","description":"This is an engaging story about the two-way nature of friendship and the risks of making assumptions. The overriding message is uplifting, whilst also leaving the reader with a powerful reminder that good intentions aren't always enough.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12-16"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33778/haunt-dead-scared.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33778","title":"Haunt: Dead Scared","author":"by Curtis Jobling","description":"This ghost story is funny, touching and exciting all in one go. This is the first in a series of adventures for Will and Dougie and it is sure to gather a horde of fans.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33464/running-girls.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33464","title":"Running Girl","author":"by Simon Mason","description":"Simon Mason turns his hand to crime writing in this fast-paced, action-packed and wonderfully engaging whodunnit.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33587/amy-and-matthew.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33587","title":"Amy and Matthew: A Love Story","author":"by Cammie McGovern","description":"Amy, who has cerebral palsy, is in her final year of high school and she wants this year to be different: she wants to replace the adult aides who help her, with her fellow students, so she can get to...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33586/tribute.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33586","title":"Tribute","author":"by Ellen Renner","description":"Zara lives in a world where magic means power and those without are forced to work as slaves - but Zara fights against this.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34087/goth-girl-and-the-fete-worse-than-deaths.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34087","title":"Goth Girl and the Fete Worse than Death","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Chris Riddell's third book in the Goth Girl series intrigues and delights with a cakey combination of adventure, love and webbed footnotes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33511/9781447263227.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33511","title":"Fangirl","author":"by Rainbow Rowell","description":"Wren is excited about starting a new life at college, but twin sister Cath is much more comfortable in the world of the fan fiction she writes, preferring to write about romance than to experience it for herself.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33645/where-the-rock-splits-the-sky.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33645","title":"Where the Rock Splits the Sky","author":"by Philip Webb","description":"This highly original and creative story cleverly combines dystopian sci-fi thriller with a western adventure. It has a strong heroine, faithful companions, a worthy quest, and very creepy aliens!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33887/noggin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33887","title":"Noggin","author":"by John Corey Whaley","description":"Sixteen-year-old Travis died from leukaemia five years ago. But he's alive again (and still sixteen) as the result of pioneering transplant surgery to attach his cryogenically saved head to another body.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33935/fiendish.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33935","title":"Fiendish","author":"by Brenna Yovanoff","description":"This is an exceptionally well-paced thriller, packed with fantastic characters and an explosive climax. Highly recommended.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":326,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/326/","title":"Best young adult books from 2014","list_description":"Catch up on the best 2014 had to offer!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33800/the-rain.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33800","title":"The Rain","author":"by Virginia Bergin","description":"A funny, smart and wonderfully British take on dystopia that will leave readers eager for the next installment of Ruby's story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33931/frozen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33931","title":"Frozen: Heart of Dread","author":"by Melissa de la Cruz and Michael Johnston","description":"This is the promising start to a new series of magic and adventure amid a post-apocalyptic setting. Fantasy and science fiction meet love and romance in a thrilling and engrossing page turner.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33708/lobsters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33708","title":"Lobsters","author":"by Tom Ellen and Lucy Ivison","description":"The first novel from friends and collaborators Tom Ellen and Lucy Ivison, Lobsters is a frank and very funny young adult romance.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33588/echo-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33588","title":"Echo Boy","author":"by Matt Haig","description":"Audrey lives in a future world where technology has changed everything and where families are served by cyborgs who unquestioningly obey their orders. But when her parents are killed by their cyborg, Audrey is in terrible danger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33865/replica.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33865","title":"Replica","author":"by Jack Heath","description":"This is a great, high octane, YA thriller with a strong-willed female protagonist.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33910/isla-and-the-happily-ever-after.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33910","title":"Isla and the Happily Ever After","author":"by Stephanie Perkins","description":"This delightful romance from bestselling US author Stephanie Perkins is set against the background of Paris, New York and Barcelona.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33511/9781447263227.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33511","title":"Fangirl","author":"by Rainbow Rowell","description":"Wren is excited about starting a new life at college, but twin sister Cath is much more comfortable in the world of the fan fiction she writes, preferring to write about romance than to experience it for herself.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33728/take-back-the-skies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33728","title":"Take Back the Skies","author":"by Lucy Saxon","description":"As an introduction to other-world fantasy fiction this is engaging and accessible but it will appeal most to younger teens.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33845/between-the-lives.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33845","title":"Between the Lives","author":"by Jessica Shirvington","description":"This is one of the most original YA books in a long time. It is gripping and exceptionally well-written with fantastic characters and an exciting plot. One of the best of 2014.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33636/grasshopper-jungles.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33636","title":"Grasshopper Jungle","author":"by Andrew Smith","description":"Grasshopper Jungle is both an exciting edge-of-your-seat young adult dystopia, and a bold and thoughtful novel about history and identity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33944/lies-we-tell-ourselves.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33944","title":"The Lies We Tell Ourselves","author":"by Robin Talley","description":"This exceptional novel of first love and sexual awakenings is set against a backdrop of shocking racism and prejudice.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33540/avalavender.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33540","title":"The Strange and Beautiful Sorrows of Ava Lavender","author":"by Leslye Walton","description":"This is the story of Ava Lavender, a girl born with the wings of a bird.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33776/the-young-worlds.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33776","title":"The Young World","author":"by Chris Weitz","description":"Although this may not be the first time a post-apocalyptic, teenage-run world has been written about, it is one of the best in the genre.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 15+","interest_age":"Interest level: 16+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33981/afterworlds.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33981","title":"Afterworlds","author":"by Scott Westerfeld","description":"Afterworlds is very well written with an exciting double plot that keeps the reader engrossed. An all-round great read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":327,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/327/","title":"Dyslexia-friendly picture books","list_description":"Red Squirrel picture books were developed by Barrington Stoke, a publisher specialising in dyslexia-friendly books. These picture books can be enjoyed by all members of the family. They support parents who are unconfident readers in passing on a love of reading to their child by reading with them. The font, lay-out and wording all help support the reader through the pages.  Find out more about these picture books on our blog","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33050/9781781120088.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33050","title":"The Snake who Came to Stay","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Polly’s holiday home for pets is much in demand. There are guinea pigs, a noisy mynah bird - and now Doris the snake."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34944/we-are-not-frogs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34944","title":"We Are Not Frogs!","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Alice and Jago are playing in granny's garden one day when they find lots of toads in the long grass. Michael Morpurgo's lovely nature tale and Sam Usher's sensitive and funny illustrations bring this story hoppingly alive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34736/9781781125090.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34736","title":"Mad in the Back","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":"How can Mum possibly drive when her two children are going mad in the back?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34026/freddy-and-the-pig.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34026","title":"Freddy and the Pig","author":"by Charlie Higson and Mark Chambers","description":"Freddy hates school and thinks that it is boring, but he comes up with clever plan. The dyslexia-friendly features make this book highly accessible."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33709/all-i-said-was.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33709","title":"All I Said Was","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"One of an innovative series of dyslexia-friendly picture books which feature accessible fonts, strong contrast, good spacing and uncluttered layout to ensure accessibility for all, including parents with reading difficulties."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34028/wolfman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34028","title":"Wolfman","author":"by Michael Rosen and Chris Mould","description":"Wolf Man has escaped from his cage and is wrecking the town. All of the people in the town are scared and are rushing to hide indoors. The dyslexia-friendly features make this book highly accessible."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34027/itch-scritch-scratch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34027","title":"Itch Scritch Scratch","author":"by Eleanor Updale and Sarah Horne","description":"Head lice are the focus of this fun and engaging picture book. The dyslexia-friendly features make this book highly accessible."}]}
{"id":328,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/328/","title":"Winter in picturebooks","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33314/snowflakes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33314","title":"Snowflakes","author":"by Cerrie Burnell","description":"Mia has left the noisy city behind, and come to live with her Grandma in a land of forest and snow.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30555/one-snowy-night.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30555","title":"One Snowy Night","author":"by Nick Butterworth","description":"This is a heartwarming story of animals in winter - the story teaches children to look and think about the world around them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33048/9781849395182.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33048","title":"Bear Has a Story to Tell","author":"by Philip C. Stead","description":"It is almost winter, and Bear is getting sleepy. Before he finds somewhere to hibernate he has a story to tell but all the animals are too busy getting ready for winter to listen.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25654/maisy-s-wonderful-weather-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25654","title":"Maisy's Wonderful Weather Book","author":"by Lucy Cousins","description":"Maisy returns, this time leaping out of bed and investigating weather with characteristic mouse-like joie de vivre.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34040/its-snow-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34040","title":"It's Snow Day","author":"by Richard Curtis","description":"This must-read winter picture book is crammed with fabulously joyful and expressive illustrations and will be loved by young and old alike.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32288/9781406304916-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32288","title":"A First Book of Nature","author":"by Nicola Davies","description":"Hearld's nostalgic illustrations are the perfect accompaniment to this lovely chronicle of a child's first experiences of nature","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30433/monday.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30433","title":"Monday","author":"by Anne Herbauts","description":"Monday is a penguin who likes to stay warm. When winter comes, Monday's house is blown away in a snowstorm, and his friends go in search of him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25792/one-year-with-kipper.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25792","title":"One Year With Kipper","author":"by Mick Inkpen","description":"Kipper has a new camera and starts the year as he means to go on, by taking photographs during each month so he doesn't forget what he and his best friend Tiger got up to.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30643/9780230705418-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30643","title":"Jack Frost","author":"by Kazuno Kohara","description":"A little boy sits by the fire, miserable because it is winter and all his friends are hibernating.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29177/9780340950654-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29177","title":"Miki","author":"by Stephen Mackey","description":"Shimmering like the northern lights, the illustrations' luminous blues and greens glow out of the darkness in this chilly yet elegantly magical wintry tale","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30926/brrrr-a-book-of-winter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30926","title":"Brrrr: A Book of Winter","author":"by Il Sung Na","description":"When snow falls on the ground, and all the trees are bare, everything changes ... including the white rabbit!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":330,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/330/","title":"Books to read if you love Frozen","list_description":"If you love Disney's Frozen, here are some books you might enjoy! (Ranging from ages 5-12.)","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29641/snow-queen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29641","title":"The Snow Queen","author":"by Hans Christian Andersen","description":"Lynch's vivid yet ethereal illustrations capture the balance between the wondrous and the recognisable in this powerful story about the redemptive nature of love and the passing of time.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33422/9781408196908-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33422","title":"Winter's Tales","author":"by Lari Don","description":"How did the boy known as the Prince of Wolves get his name? Where did tinsel come from? How did Lars and the snow bear get rid of Christmas trolls? Find out in this unusual collection.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32181/the-worst-princess-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32181","title":"The Worst Princess","author":"by Anna Kemp","description":"With a rhyming text by Anna Kemp and delightfully humorous illustrations by Sara Ogilvie, this entertaining picture book offers a refreshingly tongue-in-cheek spin on the conventional fairy tale princess.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31538/pippi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31538","title":"Pippi Longstocking","author":"by Astrid Lindgren","description":"Follow Pippi Longstocking on her amazing adventures as she moves into Villa Villekulla with a horse, a monkey, and a big suitcase of gold coins.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33983/library-saved-rapunzel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33983","title":"How the Library (Not the Prince) Saved Rapunzel","author":"by Wendy Meddour","description":"This is how every fairy tale should be written, with the protagonist - regardless of gender - saving themselves from a life of solitude and boredom. A great read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29992/princessaasta.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29992","title":"Princess Aasta","author":"by Stina Langlo Ordal","description":"Lonely Princess Aasta wants a bear to play with, so she places an advertisement in the newspaper.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32687/9780857384287-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32687","title":"Winterling","author":"by Sarah Prineas","description":"Fer finds herself in a dangerous and enchanting new world in this magical adventure story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32452/supersister.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32452","title":"My Super Sister","author":"by Gwyneth Rees","description":"Sensible Emma and her naughty little sister Saffie love having superpowers. The only problem is that Mum and Dad don't want anyone to find out about their very unusual gifts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25269/snow-white-rose-red.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25269","title":"Snow White and Rose Red","author":"by Bernadette Watts","description":"Snow White and Rose Red live in an isolated cottage in the middle of the forest with their widowed mother. One wintry night there is a knock at the door...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25688/tanglewreck.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25688","title":"Tanglewreck","author":"by Jeanette Winterson","description":"This complex but utterly readable book, encompasses chaos theory and time travel but is also filled with humorous asides and a cast of memorable characters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":331,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/331/","title":"Fairy Tales","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27217/previously.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27217","title":"Previously","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"Using just the word 'previously' various fairytales are retold – starting with their endings and working back to their beginnings.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30369/me-and-you.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30369","title":"Me and You","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"The resolution of this story about a girl and three bears will challenge perceptions and provoke much thought in those who read it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24662/bigbadbook.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24662","title":"Who's Afraid of the Big Bad Book?","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Lauren Child uses a classic fairy-tale formula for this ingenious and original tale. The quirky, hilarious, collage illustrations are what make this picture book special.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25325/revoltingrhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25325","title":"Revolting Rhymes","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This is an hilarious collection of some well-loved fairy tales, cleverly reinvented by Roald Dahl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30430/cloud-tea-monkeys.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30430","title":"Cloud Tea Monkeys","author":"by Mal Peet and Elspeth Graham","description":"Tashi's mother is an impoverished tea-picker, and when she becomes ill, the little girl tries to continue her mother's job.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34677/9780552572729.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34677","title":"The Fairytale Hairdresser and the Sugar Plum Fairy","author":"by Abie Longstaff","description":"A retelling of The Nutcracker in an ever-growing series of picturebooks for KS1 girls.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33983/library-saved-rapunzel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33983","title":"How the Library (Not the Prince) Saved Rapunzel","author":"by Wendy Meddour","description":"This is how every fairy tale should be written, with the protagonist - regardless of gender - saving themselves from a life of solitude and boredom. A great read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33093/9781847804594.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33093","title":"Spellbound","author":"by Siobhán Parkinson","description":"A fascinating selection of folk and fairy tales.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25327/the-true-story-of-the-three-little-pigs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25327","title":"The True Story of the Three Little Pigs","author":"by Jon Scieszka & Lane Smith","description":"What really happened to the three little pigs and the big bad wolf? Find out the truth in this hilarious picture book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32257/9781848772151-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32257","title":"Jack and the Baked Beanstalk","author":"by Colin Stimpson","description":"Stimpson sets his version of Jack and the Beanstalk in 1950s America, with skyscrapers surrounding the flyover under which Jack and his mother run a café","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"}]}
{"id":332,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/332/","title":"Fairy Tales","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31796/goldilocks-on-cctv.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31796","title":"Goldilocks on CCTV","author":"by John Agard","description":"By turns funny, poignant and insightful Agard’s poems are told with a direct and distinctive voice","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30965/tom-trueheart-and-the-land-of-myths-and-legends.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30965","title":"Tom Trueheart and the Land of Myths and Legends","author":"by Ian Beck","description":"Tom Trueheart leaves the Land of Stories to free his father, Big Jack the Giant Killer, from the clutches of treacherous King Ormestone.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32521/a-midsummer-night-s-dream.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32521","title":"A Midsummer Night's Dream - Manga Shakespeare","author":"by Kate Brown","description":"Shakespeare's enduring story set in present-day Athens, but a present with a massive difference.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33658/breaking-the-spell.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33658","title":"Breaking the Spell","author":"by Lari Don","description":"A wonderful collection of myths, legends and fairy tales from Scotland.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30430/cloud-tea-monkeys.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30430","title":"Cloud Tea Monkeys","author":"by Mal Peet and Elspeth Graham","description":"Tashi's mother is an impoverished tea-picker, and when she becomes ill, the little girl tries to continue her mother's job.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32240/9781847802538-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32240","title":"Shahnameh: The Persian Book of Kings","author":"by Elizabeth Laird","description":"Shahnameh is an ancient Persian poem comprising a collection of stories, myths and legends which have been retold for over a thousand years.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31873/liesel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31873","title":"Liesl & Po","author":"by Lauren Oliver","description":"Death and danger are balanced against friendship and love in this intoxicating blend of adventure, fairy tale and fantasy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29169/talesofbeedle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29169","title":"The Tales of Beedle the Bard","author":"by J K Rowling","description":"Each of these five tales contains a life lesson for children and parents alike, from the importance of trusted friendships to the redemptive power of love.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32699/9781780338330-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32699","title":"The Girl Who Circumnavigated Fairyland in a Ship of Her Own Making","author":"by Catherynne M Valente","description":"When the Green Wind turns up and carries September away to Fairyland, she soon finds herself battling to stop the evil Marquess.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24624/george-and-the-dragon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24624","title":"George and the Dragon","author":"by Chris Wormell","description":"The dragon in this tale is a fire-breathing beast, but there's one thing that makes him cower in fear.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"}]}
{"id":335,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/335/","title":"National Storytelling Week","list_description":"The end of this month sees the start of National Storytelling Week, so we've hand-picked a number of great stories that either won or were shortlisted for one of last year's Book Trust-run prizes.  From foreign fiction to short stories, we've got it all.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33553/9780007356348.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33553","title":"Americanah","author":"by Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie","description":"As teenagers in a Lagos secondary school, Ifemelu and Obinze fall in love. Their Nigeria is under military dictatorship, and people are leaving the country if they can."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33426/dogs_of_littlefield.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33426","title":"The Dogs of Littlefield","author":"by Suzanne Berne","description":"A visiting scholar travels to the town of Littlefield to study 'one of the top 20 places to live in America', although all isn't as it seems as someone is poisoning all the town's dogs."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33550/iraqi-christ-2-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33550","title":"The Iraqi Christ","author":"by Hassan Blasim","description":"From hostage-video makers in Baghdad, to human trafficking in the forests of Serbia, institutionalised paranoia in the Saddam years, to the nightmares of an exile trying to embrace a new life in Amsterdam... Blasim's stories present an uncompromising view of..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33545/strangeweatherintokyo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33545","title":"Strange Weather in Tokyo","author":"by Hiromi Kawakami","description":"A woman in her late 30s starts a relationship with a former teacher 30 years older than herself."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33252/burial.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33252","title":"Burial Rites","author":"by Hannah Kent","description":"Iceland, 1829, Anges Magnúsdóttir has been sentenced to death for the brutal murder of her employer Natan Ketilsson."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33561/9780957185326.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33561","title":"A Girl is a Half-Formed Thing","author":"by Eimear McBride","description":"Eimear McBride's debut tells the story of a young woman's relationship with her brother and the long shadow cast by his childhood brain tumour."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33542/mealinwinter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33542","title":"A Meal in Winter","author":"by Hubert Mingarelli","description":"One morning, in the dead of winter, three German soldiers head out into the frozen Polish countryside. They have been charged by their commanders to track down and bring back for execution 'one of them' - a Jew."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33544/cover-image.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33544","title":"Revenge","author":"by Yoko Ogawa","description":"A woman goes into a bakery to buy a strawberry cream tart. Another customer comes in. The woman tells the new arrival that she is buying her son a treat for his birthday. Every year she buys him his favourite..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33564/9780349139630.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33564","title":"The Goldfinch","author":"by Donna Tartt","description":"After surviving an accident, a young boy clings to the thing that most reminds him of his mother: a small, strangely captivating painting that ultimately draws him into the criminal underworld."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33551/mussels_fullsize_hires.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33551","title":"The Mussel Feast","author":"by Birgit Vanderbeke","description":"A mother and her two teenage children sit at the dinner table. In the middle stands a large pot of cooked mussels. Why has the father not returned home?"}]}
{"id":339,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/339/","title":"Read for My School recommended reads: Non-fiction","list_description":"We asked publishers to put forward some of their best non-fiction books, and an independent panel of experts - including teachers, librarians, booksellers and children's book reviewers - read through them and selected their favourites for you to read in 2015.  Go back to the Read for My School booklists","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34144/discover-the-mega-world.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34144","title":"Discover the Mega World","author":"by Belinda Gallagher","description":"Discover the Mega World is a mega book about enormous things."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34151/boy-on-the-wooden-box.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34151","title":"The Boy on the Wooden Box","author":"by Leon Leyson","description":"The harrowing story of Leon Leyson, a Jewish boy who was saved by Oskar Schindler is hard to read at times but it’s wonderfully written and sure to move readers to the core.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34150/big-city-explorer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34150","title":"Big City Explorer","author":"by Maggie Li","description":"This fantastic book is a perfect introduction into some of the world’s largest cities. It’s full of fun, facts and great illustrations that will appeal to young readers."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34142/story-of-first-world-war-for-children.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34142","title":"The Story of the First World War for Children","author":"by John Malam","description":"This is an ideal introduction to World War I."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34159/our-amazing-planet.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34159","title":"Our Amazing Planet: The World in Infographics","author":"by Jon Richards and Ed Simkins","description":"Bold images, glorious graphics and oodles of information about our wonderful planet guarantee that children will love learning about our awesome world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34143/daydreams-and-diaries.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34143","title":"Daydreams and Diaries","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Jacqueline Wilson is one of our best loved children’s authors and this volume contains everything you need to know about her childhood and her journey to becoming a writer.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":340,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/340/","title":"Read for My School recommended reads: Humour","list_description":"We asked publishers to put forward some of their best funny books, and an independent panel of experts - including teachers, librarians, booksellers and children's book reviewers - read through them and selected their favourites for 2015.  Go back to the Read for My School booklists","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34089/spy-who-loved-school-dinners.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34089","title":"The Spy Who Loved School Dinners","author":"by Pamela Butchart","description":"Izzy is really excited to be picked to look after the new girl, Mathilde, but the new girl isn't quite what Izzy and her friends were expecting...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34145/cat-dog-little-red-exploding-wardrobe.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34145","title":"The Cat, the Dog, Little Red, the Exploding Eggs, the Wolf and Grandma's Wardrobe","author":"by Christyan and Diane Fox","description":"A comic retelling of Little Red Riding Hood."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34141/tom-gates-tiny-bit-lucky.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34141","title":"Tom Gates: A Tiny Bit Lucky","author":"by Liz Pichon","description":"Another in the series of the Tom Gates series and it doesn't disappoint.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33990/dragons-at-crumbling-castle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33990","title":"Dragons at Crumbling Castle (and Other Stories)","author":"by Terry Pratchett","description":"Despite the book's large size, the format is ideal for reluctant or newly confidant readers, the print large, well-spaced and liberally aided by the illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33631/dream-on-amber.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33631","title":"Dream On, Amber","author":"by Emma Shevah","description":"Dream On, Amber is fast and funny with wonderful little illustrations. Emma Shevah has created a wonderfully modern voice that manages to perfectly balance a sensitive subject with light and laughter.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34146/story-of-matthew-buzzington.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34146","title":"The Story of Matthew Buzzington","author":"by Andy Stanton","description":"Matthew Buzzington is a boy who is desperate to turn himself into a fly!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+"}]}
{"id":342,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/342/","title":"Read for My School recommended reads: Film and TV","list_description":"To give you a hand in finding something fantastic to read, we asked publishers to put forward some of their best books that have been adapted for TV and film, and an independent panel of experts - including teachers, librarians, booksellers and children's book reviewers - read through them and selected their favourites for 2015.  Go back to the Read for My School booklists","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34149/strange-case-of-origami-yoda.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34149","title":"The Strange Case of Origami Yoda","author":"by Tom Angleberger","description":"A hilarious account of an advice-giving origami figure and its eccentric owner who manage to save many pupils from embarrassing situations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30154/9780007261963-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30154","title":"A Bear Called Paddington","author":"by Michael Bond","description":"Paddington, the brown bear from darkest Peru, is found by the Brown family on Paddington Station with his hat, duffel coat and marmalade sandwiches.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34154/counting-by-7s.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34154","title":"Counting by 7s","author":"by Holly Goldberg Sloan","description":"Willow is a very gifted child that everyone finds a little disconcerting, when her parents are killed in a car accident those around her take care of her and their lives are changed forever.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34155/the-true-meaning-of-smekday.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34155","title":"The True Meaning of Smekday","author":"by Adam Rex","description":"When aliens arrive on Earth on Christmas Day everyone has to move to Florida, Gratuity Tucci decides to drive herself there and makes friend with a boov called J Lo, there follows a funny and exciting journey.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29281/lightingthief.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29281","title":"Percy Jackson and the Lightning Thief","author":"by Rick Riordan","description":"In this leftfield comic fantasy novel, 12-year-old Percy Jackson discovers that the Greek gods of Olympus are alive and living in modern-day New York.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34161/hank-zipzer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34161","title":"Hank Zipzer: The Curtain Went Up, My Trousers Fell Down","author":"by Henry Winkler and Lin Oliver","description":"The title pretty much says it all. Hank, a twelve-year-old boy who has dyslexia has a unique way of dealing with any problems he faces, to the dismay of those around him! But Hank always has a plan to save...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":344,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/344/","title":"Great stories to read out loud","list_description":"As it's National Story Telling Week this February, here are some of the best stories and poems to read out loud.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27217/previously.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27217","title":"Previously","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"Using just the word 'previously' various fairytales are retold – starting with their endings and working back to their beginnings.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25325/revoltingrhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25325","title":"Revolting Rhymes","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This is an hilarious collection of some well-loved fairy tales, cleverly reinvented by Roald Dahl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33658/breaking-the-spell.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33658","title":"Breaking the Spell","author":"by Lari Don","description":"A wonderful collection of myths, legends and fairy tales from Scotland.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30936/mr-aesop-s-story-shop.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30936","title":"Mr. Aesop's Story Shop","author":"by Bob Hartman","description":"Ten of Aesop's fables are here retold within the framework of a storyteller who tells and sells his stories for a living.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29404/the-storytellers-secrets.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29404","title":"The Storyteller's Secrets","author":"by Tony Mitton","description":"Toby and Tess meet an old man in an old fashioned robe carrying a staff. He gives his name as Teller and he tells the children five traditional tales in rhyming verse.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34211/book-with-no-pictures.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34211","title":"The Book with No Pictures","author":"by B J Novak","description":"Demanding to be shared, this is a fresh and enormously funny book that children will want to hear time and time again."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33716/ahmed-and-the-feather-girl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33716","title":"Ahmed and the Feather Girl","author":"by Jane Ray","description":"This beautiful fairy tale story of hope and dreams is enchanting. Jane Ray's illustrations are truly magical. A wonderful book to keep and treasure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30808/my-favourite-fairy-tales.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30808","title":"My Favourite Fairy Tales","author":"by Tony Ross","description":"Tony Ross retells seven fairy tales for a contemporary audience with wit and style.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-9"}]}
{"id":345,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/345/","title":"Epic couples","list_description":"Here are the teen and YA read with the most epic of couples. Read them all already? Take our Epic Teen Romance Couples quiz!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26633/city-ofbones.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26633","title":"City of Bones","author":"by Cassandra Clare","description":"When Clary visits a nightclub, she discovers that she is one of the Shadowhunters - a group of demon-hunters living in a world of vampires, werewolves and warlocks.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29230/hungergames.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29230","title":"The Hunger Games","author":"by Suzanne Collins","description":"Welcome to Panem: its Capitol repressively rules twelve satellite Districts, enslaving the populations as workers and controlling them through hunger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32863/9780141345659-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32863","title":"The Fault in Our Stars","author":"by John Green","description":"John Green tackles the subject of teenage cancer with sensitivity in this witty, life-affirming young adult romance.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33282/9780007533039-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33282","title":"Boy Meets Boy","author":"by David Levithan","description":"This delightful high-school story is set in a town in which being a gay teenager is no more fraught with difficulty than being straight.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25470/twilight.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25470","title":"Twilight","author":"by Stephanie Meyer","description":"Edward seems to hate Bella, but it turns out that he is in love with her and he is afraid of what he might do to her.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29396/angus-thongs-and-full-frontal-snogging.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29396","title":"Angus, Thongs and Full-Frontal Snogging","author":"by Louise Rennison","description":"Welcome to the world of Georgia Nicolson - an angst-ridden teenage girl who keeps a diary to record the rollercoaster of emotions and experiences she faces every day","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24508/9780141318011-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24508","title":"How I Live Now","author":"by Meg Rosoff","description":"Fifteen-year-old New Yorker Daisy is sent to England to spend a summer with her unconventional cousins","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33433/eleanor-parks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33433","title":"Eleanor & Park","author":"by Rainbow Rowell","description":"Set over the course of one school year in 1986, this is a beautifully-written love story about two high school outsiders","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29550/shiver..jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29550","title":"Shiver","author":"by Maggie Stiefvater","description":"Set in small-town Minnesota, Stiefvater’s moving and poetic novel of human/wolf interaction and relationships is a werewolf story like no other.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31288/bloodredroadd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31288","title":"Blood Red Road","author":"by Moira Young","description":"A violent, desperate and compelling story about family, love and determination, which enthrals through its bold, powerful language","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":346,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/346/","title":"Holocaust Memorial Day","list_description":"To mark Holocaust Memorial Day and the 70th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz, we have assembled a poignant booklist that should hopefully help explain and inform younger readers about the events surrounding the Holocaust.  Books by Morris Gleitzman, John Boyne and Anne Booth make up some of the titles appropriate for readers aged 10-14-years-old.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33535/girlwithawhitedog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33535","title":"Girl with a White Dog","author":"by Anne Booth","description":"Jessie is delighted when she finds a beautiful white puppy at Gran's house. But then Gran starts becoming confused, and saying strange things about their new pet.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25439/strippedpjs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25439","title":"The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas","author":"by John Boyne","description":"Bruno is exploring his new home at 'Out-With' when he meets Shmuel, who lives on the other side of a fence which surrounds a large camp in the grounds.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30826/annexed..jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30826","title":"Annexed","author":"by Sharon Dogar","description":"This fictionalised account of Peter (a teenage Dutch Jew, hiding from the Nazis with his family and their friends, the Franks) is a meditation on the power of written testimony and the nature of evil.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25454/once.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25454","title":"Once","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"Morris Gleitzman brings heart and humour to the difficult subject of the Holocaust in this ground-breaking children's book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30339/now.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30339","title":"Now","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"A beautifully written book, full of hope, love and sorrow; it provides an apt ending to the unforgettable trilogy that also includes Once and Then.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29178/then.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29178","title":"Then","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"Then opens with Felix and Zelda running for their lives from a train taking them to a concentration camp.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32432/after.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32432","title":"After","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"The fourth installment in Morris Gleitzman's unforgettable series beginning with Once, tells the story of what happened to Felix in the final, agonising stages of the Second World War.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29463/maus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29463","title":"Maus","author":"by Art Spiegelman","description":"This is the complete story of Vladek Spiegelman and his wife, living and surviving in Hitler's Europe.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":348,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/348/","title":"Picture books that love libraries","list_description":"We love libraries, and we love picture books. So here's our list of picture books that love libraries too!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33951/bears-don-t-read.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33951","title":"Bears Don't Read","author":"by Emma Chichester Clark","description":"Bears Don't Read is a wonderfully engaging picture book about the joy of reading and how much fun it can be to help others.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33272/2013-14-booktime-but-excuse-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33272","title":"But Excuse Me That is My Book","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"Children will join Charlie, Lola and their friends on a trip to the library to look at all the different types of books that Lola might like to read. It is a warm and funny story about family, friends and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31515/9781780080031-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31515","title":"Otto the Book Bear","author":"by Katie Cleminson","description":"A charming celebration of books and reading","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34193/wanted-ralfy-rabbitt-book-burglar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34193","title":"Wanted! Ralfy Rabbit, Book Burglar","author":"by Emily MacKenzie","description":"Little book lovers will adore this silly story of naughty Ralfy. The illustrations are fun and modern, with some bunny puns to keep adults entertained too.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31728/9781406322880-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31728","title":"Have You Ever Ever Ever?","author":"by Colin McNaughton","description":"An essential book for everyone, which expounds the importance of libraries, books and the wonders which lie within them!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25804/lulu-loves-library.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25804","title":"Lulu Loves the Library","author":"by Anna McQuinn","description":"Lulu has her library card, her rucksack full of borrowed books, and a big smile on her face, because it's Tuesday – and on Tuesdays Lulu and her mummy go to the library","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33983/library-saved-rapunzel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33983","title":"How the Library (Not the Prince) Saved Rapunzel","author":"by Wendy Meddour","description":"This is how every fairy tale should be written, with the protagonist - regardless of gender - saving themselves from a life of solitude and boredom. A great read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"}]}
{"id":349,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/349/","title":"World Cancer Day 2017","list_description":"4 February is World Cancer Day, which aims to raise awareness, urge governments to take action, and educate us all about the disease and its impact.  We've put together a booklist for readers aged 9+ full of novels that explore the effects of cancer, so if you and your family want to do some wider reading, take a look at our recommendations below.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32026/the-lookd.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32026","title":"The Look","author":"by Sophia Bennett","description":"Ted is an awkward, gangly teenager constantly following in her older sister Ava’s confident footsteps...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30828/artichoke-hearts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30828","title":"Artichoke Hearts","author":"by Sita Brahmachari","description":"This empathetic account of the process of bereavement, a month’s diary, reassures readers that we grow from our experiences, however painful they are.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32796/9781408827116-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32796","title":"Anthem for Jackson Dawes","author":"by Celia Bryce","description":"Megan would never have met Jackson Dawes if she hadn't had cancer. But as the only teenagers on the children's ward, they soon form a powerful and unconventional bond.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29929/two-weeks-with-the-queen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29929","title":"Two Weeks with the Queen","author":"by Morris Gleitzman","description":"When his brother becomes seriously ill with leukaemia, Colin is sent to stay with relatives in England. Determined to get the best help possible, he decides to approach the Queen.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32863/9780141345659-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32863","title":"The Fault in Our Stars","author":"by John Green","description":"John Green tackles the subject of teenage cancer with sensitivity in this witty, life-affirming young adult romance.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35130/best-medicine.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35130","title":"The Best Medicine","author":"by Christine Hamill","description":"Twelve-year old Philip Wright is a comedian in the making. Then one day, he tells his mother a joke, and she breaks down in tears. It's a brave challenge to unite the themes of cancer and comedy - but this...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32650/32c-that-s-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32650","title":"32C, That’s Me","author":"by Chris Higgins","description":"Jess seems to have it all. She has a gorgeous boyfriend, Muggs, landed the lead in the school play and her best friend Ali will always stick by her. She even gets on well with her older sister! Then her...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31309/amonstercallsss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31309","title":"A Monster Calls","author":"by Patrick Ness","description":"Connor's mum has cancer and life is changing. There is the nightmare, then there is school, where people avoid him, or persecute him. And then there is the immense, mythic Monster.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25372/lolarose.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25372","title":"Lola Rose","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Jacqueline Wilson demonstrates her skill by capturing the experiences of a young carer, fearful about what the cancer will do to her mother.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32377/9780141340722-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32377","title":"The Probability of Miracles","author":"by Wendy Wunder","description":"Cyncial teenage cancer patient Campbell has a summer to remember in the magical town of Promise in this moving and bittersweet debut novel","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":350,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/350/","title":"Books with positive images of disability","list_description":"These are 12 books that we think show positive images of disability, as well as titles that may prove useful in discussing disability and diversity.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33914/the-five-of-us.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33914","title":"The Five of Us","author":"by Quentin Blake","description":"This book is testament to Blake's belief that all children need to be able find themselves in books.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33535/girlwithawhitedog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33535","title":"Girl with a White Dog","author":"by Anne Booth","description":"Jessie is delighted when she finds a beautiful white puppy at Gran's house. But then Gran starts becoming confused, and saying strange things about their new pet.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32796/9781408827116-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32796","title":"Anthem for Jackson Dawes","author":"by Celia Bryce","description":"Megan would never have met Jackson Dawes if she hadn't had cancer. But as the only teenagers on the children's ward, they soon form a powerful and unconventional bond.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34024/baking-life-amelie-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34024","title":"The Baking Life of Amelie Day","author":"by Vanessa Curtis","description":"In some ways Amelie Day is a teenager like any other, much of her day-to-day life revolving around her best friend, school, loyal boyfriend and fretful mother. However, in other ways, she is rather less typical...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33655/young-knights-of-the-round-table.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33655","title":"Young Knights of the Round Table","author":"by Julia Golding","description":"Together with plenty of humour, mystery, twists and turns, Young Knights of the Round Table is a fast-paced time-travelling fantasy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33906/finding-a-voice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33906","title":"Finding a Voice","author":"by Kim Hood","description":"This is an engaging story about the two-way nature of friendship and the risks of making assumptions. The overriding message is uplifting, whilst also leaving the reader with a powerful reminder that good intentions aren't always enough.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12-16"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33871/specs-for-rex.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33871","title":"Specs for Rex","author":"by Yasmeen Ismail","description":"A perfectly judged niche story that has general appeal due to a clean text and cute character; Specs for Rex is a visual treat that's really worth putting your glasses on for.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33790/dead-ends.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33790","title":"Dead Ends","author":"by Erin Lange","description":"Dane Washington is the quick-tempered local bully, Billy D his new neighbour who has Down Syndrome.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33587/amy-and-matthew.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33587","title":"Amy and Matthew: A Love Story","author":"by Cammie McGovern","description":"Amy, who has cerebral palsy, is in her final year of high school and she wants this year to be different: she wants to replace the adult aides who help her, with her fellow students, so she can get to...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33868/made-by-raffi.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33868","title":"Made By Raffi","author":"by Craig Pomranz","description":"A delightful and gently revolutionary picture book that challenges our absurd notions about what constitutes 'normal' or 'appropriate'.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33465/tim-tron.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33465","title":"Heads Up, Tim-Tron","author":"by Ian Ray & Garry Parsons","description":"This is the engaging story of a little robot. His day-to-day activities are much the same as that of any other young robot. Then he has an accident, injuring his head playing football.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33710/dandelion-clocks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33710","title":"Dandelion Clocks","author":"by Rebecca Westcott","description":"Powerful, memorable and accessible, the book also boasts a very positive depiction of a character with Asperger's Syndrome.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":351,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/351/","title":"Books about grief and loss","list_description":"Books can help children to understand sad feelings – from losing a cherished toy to the death of a family member. We've suggested a few books to help them cope, prepare for future tough times, or just enjoy a good book together now.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29917/granpa.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29917","title":"Granpa","author":"by John Burningham","description":"A sensitive and moving exploration of the relationship between a young girl and her grandfather.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34547/grandads-island.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34547","title":"Grandad's Island","author":"by Benji Davies","description":"A subtle story about love and loss enhanced by delightful illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33996/rabbityness.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33996","title":"Rabbityness","author":"by Jo Empson","description":"This beautifully illustrated, simple book will engage young readers, and address the sorrow of any bereavement they experience.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25693/seal_surfer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25693","title":"Seal Surfer","author":"by Michael Foreman","description":"A welcome re-publication of Foreman's timeless and evocative account of a boy's relationship with life and death.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29831/heart-and-the-bottle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29831","title":"The Heart and the Bottle","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"An inquisitive little girl, who is enchanted by the world around her, is badly shaken when she loses someone she loves.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31556/9780007388110-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31556","title":"My Henry","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Unconventional subject matter for the very young is presented with gentle humour and a sense of great joy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35323/9781781125342.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35323","title":"Grandpa Was an Astronaut","author":"by Jonathan Meres","description":"Sherman is fascinated by the moon - all the more so because he knows someone who has actually been there, his Grandpa!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35320/9780571314102.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35320","title":"The Building Boy","author":"by Ross Montgomery","description":"The boy loves his grandmother dearly. Best of all, he loves the stories about her life as a prize-winning architect. One day, she promises she'll build him an extraordinary house. Now his grandmother's gone, and he's heartbroken. But in her...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30349/9781849920490-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30349","title":"Lob","author":"by Linda Newbery","description":"Lucy and her beloved grandfather enjoy gardening together, and Lucy becomes aware that she, like him, can sense-see a small figure who helps with the gardening.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25190/michael-rosen-s-sad-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25190","title":"Michael Rosen's Sad Book","author":"by Michael Rosen","description":"The subject of bereavement is treated in an unusual way in Michael Rosen's Sad Book, which deals with the death of the author's own son.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31015/milo-and-the-restart-button.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31015","title":"Milo and the Restart Button","author":"by Alan Silberberg","description":"Silberberg's novel is funny, sad, and empowering for young readers who have suffered bereavement. His comical illustrations and lists both lighten and extend the text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28571/the-cat-mummy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28571","title":"The Cat Mummy","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"A deceptively simple tale which explores the issue of bereavement for younger readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30024/vickyangel.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30024","title":"Vicky Angel","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"A moving novel about guilt and bereavement, written with humour and sensitivity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":352,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/352/","title":"International Women's Day","list_description":"Peruse our list of excellent books that have been written by the best female authors.  Authors include winners of the David Cohen Prize and the Baileys Women's Prize for literature","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26933/the-natural-disorder-of-things.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26933","title":"The Natural Disorder of Things","author":"by Andrea Canobbio","description":"Claudio Fratta is a gentle man, a garden designer, naturally solitary. He is obsessed by the need to take revenge on the loan shark who bankrupted his father, and with the pursuit of an enigmatic, alluring woman , one of..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33323/nothing-holds-back.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33323","title":"Nothing holds back the night","author":"by Delphine de Vigan","description":"REPRESENTING FRANCE This is an exceptional book. Reading it is like being in a room with mirrors on opposite walls."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31356/bossypants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31356","title":"Bossypants","author":"by Tina Fey","description":"Tina Fey, the creator of 30 Rock, one of Saturday Night Live’s best stalwarts and she of the uncanny Sarah Palin impressions in the run-up to the 2008 USA elections, may not be as widely known here as she should..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29878/wolf-hall.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29878","title":"Wolf Hall","author":"by Hilary Mantel","description":"England in the 1540s is a heartbeat from disaster. If the king dies without a male heir, the country could be destroyed by civil war. Henry VIII wants to annul his marriage of twenty years, and marry Anne Boleyn. The..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33561/9780957185326.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33561","title":"A Girl is a Half-Formed Thing","author":"by Eimear McBride","description":"Eimear McBride's debut tells the story of a young woman's relationship with her brother and the long shadow cast by his childhood brain tumour."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33748/9780224099523.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33748","title":"Thunderstruck","author":"by Elizabeth McCracken","description":"A collection of nine stories from the author of Here's Your Hat, What's Your Hurry."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31029/double-fault.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31029","title":"Double Fault","author":"by Lionel Shriver","description":"Ever since she picked up a racquet at the age of four, tennis has been Willy's one love, until the day she meets Eric Oberdorf."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33502/bedsit-disco.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33502","title":"Bedsit Disco Queen: How I Grew Up and Tried to be a Pop Star","author":"by Tracey Thorn","description":"Tracy Thorn - lead singer of Everything But the Girl - writes about her 30-year career."}]}
{"id":353,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/353/","title":"Spring explorer booklist","list_description":"Spring is a great time to start exploring the world around you - whether that's learning more about animals, going for a picnic or simply visiting your local park. Here are some books to spark children's curiosity for the world around them.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33665/walk-in-the-park.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33665","title":"A Walk in the Park","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"A welcome republication for an Anthony Browne classic from 1977. Two children from very different backgrounds (and their dogs) make friends where their parents cannot.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30352/i-love-bugs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30352","title":"I Love Bugs","author":"by Emma Dodd","description":"A large, bright, creepy-crawly bug safari through a little boy’s garden, with a final spread which shows how we often react to them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31228/follow-the-swallow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31228","title":"Follow the Swallow","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Chack the blackbird is brown but claims he will turn black and that the berries in the tree where he lives will turn orange, but Apollo the swallow doesn't believe him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35150/9781783702398.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35150","title":"The Perfect Picnic","author":"by Ciara Flood","description":"Squirrel and Mole do everything together, including going on picnics. Squirrel is determined that the picnic will be perfect, and that means trying out quite a few different places! Unfortunately, the picnic gets lost on the way, but the other...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30698/who-s-in-the-garden-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30698","title":"Who's in the Garden?","author":"by Phillis Gershator","description":"The inviting patchwork of colours used throughout this celebration of a British garden, will immediately draw young readers into its pages.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35001/tidy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35001","title":"Tidy","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"Pete the badger likes to keep everything neat and tidy, but his over-zealous cleaning begins to have a damaging impact on the forest. This entertaining picture book, with its rich illustrations, carries an important environmental message.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35521/norton-and-alpha.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35521","title":"Norton and Alpha","author":"by Kristyna Litten","description":"This charming tale about appreciating the wonder of nature is accompanied by gorgeous atmospheric illustrations, which bring the endearing characters to life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35523/lots.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35523","title":"Lots","author":"by Marc Martin","description":"This beautiful book celebrates the world we live in: there are LOTS of people, places, landscapes and cultures to see. Marc Martin's illustrations capture the spirit of every place and culture, igniting the travelling bug for young explorers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3-6","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34944/we-are-not-frogs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34944","title":"We Are Not Frogs!","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Alice and Jago are playing in granny's garden one day when they find lots of toads in the long grass. Michael Morpurgo's lovely nature tale and Sam Usher's sensitive and funny illustrations bring this story hoppingly alive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34898/guide-to-bear-spotting.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34898","title":"A Beginner’s Guide to Bear Spotting","author":"by Michelle Robinson and David Roberts","description":"This amusing guide book contains an array of information about how to spot and behave around bears. The result is a stylish, highly entertaining picture book, perfect for reading aloud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34033/tony-robinson-weird-world-pets.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34033","title":"Sir Tony Robinson's Weird World of Wonders: Pets","author":"by Tony Robinson and Jessica Cobb","description":"Bursting with amazing tales, fantastic facts and practical tips on how best to look after your pets, Tony Robinson's compendium of stories, statistics and advice will delight animal lovers of any age.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29775/birdsong.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29775","title":"Birdsong","author":"by Ellie Sandall","description":"Delicate representations of meadow and tree, and quirky, colourful birds amusingly illustrate a gentle fable.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"}]}
{"id":355,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/355/","title":"Politics, freedom of choice, and the big issues","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31221/too-much-trouble.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31221","title":"Too Much Trouble","author":"by Tom Avery","description":"An original interpretation of the Oliver Twist story reflecting a number of critical and significant contemporary issues.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11-16"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28476/noughts-and-crosses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28476","title":"Noughts and Crosses","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Callum is a Nought but his best friend Sephy is a Cross - the daughter of one of the most influential politicians in the country.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31917/9781408823002-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31917","title":"The Weight of Water","author":"by Sarah Crossan","description":"This beautiful book is written in verse and captures 13-year-old Kasienka’s emotions and experiences perfectly","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25608/roadobones.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25608","title":"The Road of Bones","author":"by Anne Fine","description":"Anne Fine subtly but accessibly explores the nature of state repression, personal freedom and responsibility in this thrilling, darkly chilling adventure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34165/captive.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34165","title":"Captive","author":"by A J Grainger","description":"Robyn, the daughter of the British Prime Minister, is kidnapped at gunpoint, incarcerated in a tiny cell. A gripping read and a moving exploration of identity, celebrity, loyalty, politics and power.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25371/lines-in-the-sand.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25371","title":"Lines in the Sand","author":"by Mary Hoffman and Rhiannon Lassiter","description":"This anthology about war and peace contains poems, short stories and illustrations from 135 contributors from around the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32446/9781844287789.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32446","title":"Politics - cutting through the crap","author":"by Bali Rai","description":"What is politics? How does Parliament work? Is the great British democracy even a true democracy?"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29463/maus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29463","title":"Maus","author":"by Art Spiegelman","description":"This is the complete story of Vladek Spiegelman and his wife, living and surviving in Hitler's Europe.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34045/terror-kid.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34045","title":"Terror Kid","author":"by Benjamin Zephaniah","description":"A powerful, accessible and revelatory novel with its finger firmly on the pulse of contemporary social and political issues.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33806/klaus-vogel-and-the-bad-lads.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33806","title":"Klaus Vogel and the Bad Lads","author":"by David Almond","description":"Thought-provoking, dyslexia-friendly morality tale with black and white illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11-16"}]}
{"id":356,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/356/","title":"Moment of Laughter Day - April 2015","list_description":"14 April is World Moment of Laughter Day, a day where you can just take a moment, or several, to laugh at your own convenience.  And, although you probably don't need a reason to chuckle, we've assembled a list of the best funny and homorous adult books.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33948/9780007501762.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33948","title":"The Year I Met You","author":"by Cecelia Ahern","description":"A career-driven woman strikes up an unlikely friendship with her neighbour after she's given gardening leave for a year."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28100/mere-anarchy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28100","title":"Mere Anarchy","author":"by Woody Allen","description":"Woody Allen's collection of stories is surreal, absurd, rich in verbal play, bitingly satirical and just plain daft."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32311/9780007484652.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32311","title":"Driving Jarvis Ham","author":"by Jim Bob","description":"Part Withnail & I, part Gonzo, all comedy, this bizarre, quirky road-trip tale from ex-Carter USM member Jim Bob is an exercise in wrenching comedy out of a simple premise."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29666/a-beginner-s-guide-to-acting-english.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29666","title":"A Beginner's Guide to Acting English","author":"by Shappi Khorsandi","description":"This breakout memoir by comedienne Shappi Khorsandi documents her arrival and early to teen years in the UK trying to fit in. More poignant than laugh-out-loud funny, more tragic and beautiful than punchline-fodder."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31656/9781846553981.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31656","title":"The Milkman in the Night","author":"by Andrey Kurkov","description":"The Milkman in the Night is a black comedy telling the story of a handful of residents of post-Orange Revolution Kiev drawn together into a surreal murder mystery."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28375/beaufort.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28375","title":"Beaufort","author":"by Ron Leshem","description":"Fast-paced and brutally honest, unflinching and uproariously funny, Beaufort has been hailed – not only by critics but by the generation of soldiers who served in Lebanon during Israeli occupation – as the true voice of that sobering period."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27473/the-quantity-theory-of-insanity.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27473","title":"The Quantity Theory of Insanity","author":"by Will Self","description":"Among the curious and disturbing subjects Self's debut deals with are the Ur-Bororo, a superhumanly dull tribe of Amazonian bores; the terrible, seductive secret of Ward 9; and the revolutionary possibilities of waiting."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30913/the-thing-about-life-is-that-one-day-you-ll-be-dead.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30913","title":"The Thing About Life is that one day you'll be dead","author":"by David Shields","description":"Shields draws together his own experiences, his observations of his ageing father, the wisdom of great thinkers, and the bulging research of medical science to trace a narrative of life, from painful birth, through the extraordinary vigour and potential of..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33794/9780007565061.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33794","title":"Meatspace","author":"by Nikesh Shukla","description":"A fast-paced and funny satire of life in the internet age, Meatspace is about a writer losing his grip on the modern world. When his namesake appears at a book reading and tries to steal his identity, he begins to..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30918/a-shortcut-to-paradise.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30918","title":"A Shortcut to Paradise","author":"by Teresa Solana","description":"It’s perfect tabloid fodder right from the start in this wickedly funny and scathingly brilliant Catalonian crime novel."}]}
{"id":358,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/358/","title":"Bookbuzz 2015","list_description":"These are the Bookbuzz titles for 2015! This autumn, students in Bookbuzz schools will be able to choose their own book to keep from this list, suitable for 11 - 13-year-olds and selected by a panel of experts. Find out more about Bookbuzz, a Book Trust reading programme, on the Bookbuzz website.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33661/jinx-wizards-apprentice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33661","title":"Jinx: the Wizard's Apprentice","author":"by Sage Blackwood","description":"This is an exciting adventure that also references social, ethical, and environmental issues on the way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33675/cuchoo-song.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33675","title":"Cuckoo Song","author":"by Frances Hardinge","description":"This dark fairy-story from critically acclaimed author Frances Hardinge puts a richly imaginative spin on the old tales of changelings. Sensitive readers beware: there are some genuinely chilling and disturbing scenes here.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34338/children-of-the-king.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34338","title":"The Children of the King","author":"by Sonya Hartnett","description":"Brilliantly written, this is an original and exciting story set in England and London during the Blitz."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33781/flirty-dancing.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33781","title":"Flirty Dancing","author":"by Jenny McLachlan","description":"First of four books, this is smart, funny writing, engagingly balancing the serious stuff - bullying, first love, friendship - with the joy of lindy hop and aerial moves.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34335/sons-of-scarlatti.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34335","title":"Sons of Scarlatti - Infinity Drake","author":"by John McNally","description":"This is a real page turner with lots of twists and turns! An action-packed sci-fi adventure with killer wasps, and the first of a three book series."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33861/tornado-chasers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33861","title":"The Tornado Chasers","author":"by Ross Montgomery","description":"While this is an engaging, humorous story, with lively characters; it is also substantial in its reflection on what is more frightening: risking our lives or wasting them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33641/what-are-we-fighting-for.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33641","title":"What Are We Fighting For?","author":"by Brian Moses and Roger Stevens","description":"In the one hundredth year since the outbreak of World War I, this outstanding collection captures the humanity, horror and even humour of events and experiences generated by conflict and will appeal to both young readers and adults.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30987/doctor-proctors-fart-powder-bb.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30987","title":"Doctor Proctor's Fart Powder","author":"by Jo Nesbø","description":"Doctor Proctor's Fart Powder is a laugh-out-loud funny title for everyone who finds fart jokes funny.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34336/astronauts-handbook.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34336","title":"The Usborne Official Astronaut's Handbook","author":"by Louie Stowell","description":"This is a fun, fact-packed and practical guide to launching your interstellar career!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33482/5.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33482","title":"The Last Wild","author":"by Piers Torday","description":"In a world where animals no longer exist, twelve-year-old Kester Jaynes sometimes feels like he hardly exists either. Locked away in a home for troubled children, he's told there's something wrong with him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33710/dandelion-clocks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33710","title":"Dandelion Clocks","author":"by Rebecca Westcott","description":"Powerful, memorable and accessible, the book also boasts a very positive depiction of a character with Asperger's Syndrome.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32024/9781842999462-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32024","title":"Pale","author":"by Chris Wooding","description":"In an eerie futuristic world, society has figured out a way to bring people back from the dead...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33965/my-name-is-bob.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33965","title":"My Name is Bob","author":"by James Bowen and Garry Jenkins","description":"An uplifting, true story, a prequel to the adult bestseller.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33216/crocodilewhodidnt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33216","title":"The Crocodile Who Didn't Like Water","author":"by Gemma Merino","description":"Little crocodile doesn't like water. It's cold. It's wet. It's embarrassing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34339/see-you-later-alligator-jacket-for-web.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34339","title":"See You Later, Alligator","author":"by Annie Kubler","description":"A fabulous interactive story which encourages the reader to join in and encourages good discussion.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34340/boffin-boy-and-the-emperor-s-tomb.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34340","title":"Boffin Boy and the Emperor's Tomb","author":"by David Orme","description":"This particular quest sees the schoolboy-turned-superhero, his equally brave friend Chika and a new sidekick (Kat the dog) teaming up to battle evil ancient warriors in a secret tomb."}]}
{"id":360,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/360/","title":"Super books for Superhero Day","list_description":"15 May is Superhero Day! Dust off your cape and wear your underpants on the outside of your trousers in celebration of the day dedicated to heroes - in whatever form.  To mark the day, we've assembled a team of super books to make a super booklist for readers aged 10+. These books feature a range of heroes - from everyday people at school to cats in outer space!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32102/9781407111216-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32102","title":"Atomic! The Vengeance of Vinister Vile","author":"by Guy Bass","description":"Ten year old twins Tommy and Jonny Atomic have a very weird family. Dad is a superhero, Mum's in prison for super-villainy, Aunt Sandwich is a hamster and Uncle Dogday - yes, he's a dog. And a chess grandmaster.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9 +","interest_age":"Interest level: 7 +"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33081/507e563f-e9d1-4410-b0c3-037d36410569-img100-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33081","title":"The School for Good and Evil","author":"by Soman Chainani","description":"Every four years, two children are chosen from Sophie's village to join the fabled School for Good and Evil and become fairy tale heroes or villains.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34029/young-bond-shoot2kill.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34029","title":"Shoot to Kill","author":"by Steve Cole","description":"Young Bond: Shoot to Kill is a real page turner with heroes and villains, adventure, action and humour. The book works well as a stand-alone novel, but once you've read it you'll be glad there is a whole catalogue of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28706/9781407105284-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28706","title":"Eliot Jones, Midnight Superhero","author":"by Anne Cottringer","description":"This laugh-out-loud picture book is a delight.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24536/inkheart-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24536","title":"Inkheart","author":"by Cornelia Funke","description":"12-year-old Meggie and her father, Mo, a bookbinder, both love reading, but since the disappearance of Meggie's mother, they no longer read together. One night a stranger knocks at their door, prompting Mo to reveal his awful secret.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32979/9781447227991-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32979","title":"Lost Worlds","author":"by Andrew Lane","description":"Calum Challenger is a boy on a mission to track down legendary creatures and capture their DNA in this fast-paced, hi-tech adventure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31254/boy-zero.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31254","title":"Boy Zero Wannabe Hero: The Curse of the Catastrophic Cupcakes","author":"by Peter Millett","description":"The third in the Boy Zero series, this is a short chapter book which continues the story of Charlie Applejack, the world's newest and youngest superhero.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33683/boffin-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33683","title":"Boffin Boy Goes to Hollywood","author":"by David Orme","description":"Rick Shaw might seem like an ordinary teenager, but when danger strikes Ricky becomes... Boffin Boy!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34096/star-cat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34096","title":"Star Cat","author":"by James Turner","description":"n the deepest depths of space, there is only one crew brave enough to take on the universe's most dangerous villains...Unfortunately, they weren't available for this book, so you'll have to make do with the crew of the...STAR CAT!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":361,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/361/","title":"Eurovision 2015 booklist","list_description":"We wanted to get into the Eurovision spirit, so we've devised a booklist that features books from/about the countries participating in this year's competition.  From Albania to Australia (yes, Australia) we've got literary translations, personal and historical memoirs, crime and romance. There should be something for everyone on the list, so hopefully there's no need to award 'nul points'.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33323/nothing-holds-back.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33323","title":"Nothing holds back the night","author":"by Delphine de Vigan","description":"REPRESENTING FRANCE This is an exceptional book. Reading it is like being in a room with mirrors on opposite walls."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30957/granta-issue-113.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30957","title":"Granta issue 113","author":"by John Freeman","description":"REPRESENTING SPAIN Granta is offering us a sneak preview of the future of Spanish language writers - included in this eye-catching collection of short stories and extracts may be tomorrow's García Márquez, Allende, Vargas Llosa, or Borges."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33207/an-armenian-sketchbook.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33207","title":"An Armenian Sketchbook","author":"by Vasily Grossman","description":"REPRESENTING ARMENIA For two months in late autumn 1961, Ukrainian born author Vasily Grossman visited Armenia to apply literary polish to an Armenian novel which had already been translated into Russian. Grossman was highly acclaimed as a novelist. Why, then,..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33497/the-little-old-lady.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33497","title":"The Little Old Lady Who Broke All the Rules","author":"by Catharina Ingelman-Sundberg","description":"REPRESENTING SWEDEN An oppressed elderly lady decides to break the mould before turning to crime."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30330/small-wars.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30330","title":"Small Wars","author":"by Sadie Jones","description":"REPRESENTING CYPRUS Sadie Jones's second novel follows in the footsteps of her phenomenally successful debut, The Outsider, in exploring the darker side of 1950s society."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29805/978-1564785503.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29805","title":"The System of Vienna","author":"by Gert Jonke","description":"REPRESENTING AUSTRIA An astonishing and fantastical autobiographical novel, reminiscent of Italo Calvino and Laurence Sterne, The System of Vienna details Jonke's travels through Vienna by streetcar."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30788/the-accident.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30788","title":"The Accident","author":"by Ismail Kadare","description":"REPRESENTING ALBANIA The Accident is probably the essential mystery/thriller of the New Europe. Poised somewhere between Conrad and Le Carre, it's epic, comfortless and absolutely gripping."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33209/journey-to-nowhere.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33209","title":"A Journey to Nowhere","author":"by Jean-Paul Kauffmann","description":"REPRESENTING LATVIA What might journalist and travel writer Jean-Paul Kauffmann hope to find on an expedition to a country that no longer exists?"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26616/the-marquise-of-o.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26616","title":"The Marquise of O","author":"by Heinrich von Kleist","description":"REPRESENTING GERMANY An ingenious 'whodunnit', The Marquise of O subverts the eighteenth-century notion of the infallibility of man, and reveals the true ambiguity and caprice of humanity."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31997/9781846554674.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31997","title":"A Death In the Family","author":"by Karl Ove Knausgaard","description":"REPRESENTING NORWAY Karl Ove Knausgaard's A Death In The Family is an experiment that has paid off handsomely in his native Norway, where the author has emerged as one of the leaders of his country's new generation of literary talent."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29458/one-more-year.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29458","title":"One More Year","author":"by Sana Krasikov","description":"REPRESENTING GEORGIA A numbing, almost debilitating melancholia infects the exiled, as Sana Krasikov shows in this haunting debut collection."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34307/9781846558559.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34307","title":"I Am Radar","author":"by Reif Larsen","description":"REPRESENTING SERBIA A born to a Serbian father and American mother has a very rare weird skin pigmentation afflication that leaves him with completely black skin."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32089/9781408816035.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32089","title":"The Song of Achilles","author":"by Madeline Miller","description":"REPRESENTING GREECE Greece in the age of Heroes. Patroclus, an awkward young prince, has been exiled to the kingdom of Phthia."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30783/purge.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30783","title":"Purge","author":"by Sofi Oksanen","description":"REPRESENTING ESTONIA When Aliide Truu, an elderly woman living in rural Estonia, finds a tattered young woman lying bruised and exhausted in her front yard, her immediate reaction is suspicion - after all, her long life during a violent period..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32057/9780701185503.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32057","title":"Scenes from Village Life","author":"by Amos Oz","description":"REPRESENTING ISRAEL Amos Oz's new fiction presents a surreal and unsettling portrait of a village in Israel. A picture of the community takes shape across seven stories, in which a group of characters appear and return."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31086/lumen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31086","title":"Lumen","author":"by Ben Pastor","description":"REPRESENTING POLAND With Nazi-occupied Cracow as its backdrop, this crime novel incorporates the murder of a Polish mystic, the suspicious suicide of a Nazi officer, the violent treatment of Polish dissidents."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33842/9781846552656.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33842","title":"Iza's Ballad","author":"by Magda Szabó","description":"REPRESENTING HUNGARY Iza's Ballad discusses family relationships and estrangement, told in a narrative dominated by domestic routine, which slowly and eloquently builds to a dramatic climax."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29719/our-circus-presents.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29719","title":"Our Circus Presents","author":"by Lucian Dan Teodorovici","description":"REPRESENTING ROMANIA The Birdman, our narrator, climbs out on to his window ledge every single day to test himself, to see if he can manage to kill himself, and yet he never does."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26664/the-death-of-ivan-ilyich-and-other-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26664","title":"The Death of Ivan Ilyich and Other Stories","author":"by Leo Tolstoy","description":"REPRESENTING RUSSIA Three of Tolstoy’s most powerful and moving shorter works are brought together in this volume."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30785/river-of-shadows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30785","title":"River of Shadows","author":"by Valerio Varesi","description":"REPRESENTING ITALY This tense, intriguing crime novel draws the reader into the mystery of a small town with a dark, secret at its heart."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31194/trainspotting.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31194","title":"Trainspotting","author":"by Irvine Welsh","description":"REPRESENTING UNITED KINGDOM This novel looks at life in the dark underside of Edinburgh, the AIDS capital of Europe, through the jaded eyes and harsh vernacular of heroin addict Mark Renton, who is sick of his friends, sick with the..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28789/breath.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28789","title":"Breath","author":"by Tim Winton","description":"REPRESENTING AUSTRALIA Tim Winton is one of the finest authors currently at work anywhere in the world, and Breath builds upon his reputation for writing novels that carefully pick away at relationships which exist in the context of almost overpowering..."}]}
{"id":362,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/362/","title":"Superheroes","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32102/9781407111216-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32102","title":"Atomic! The Vengeance of Vinister Vile","author":"by Guy Bass","description":"Ten year old twins Tommy and Jonny Atomic have a very weird family. Dad is a superhero, Mum's in prison for super-villainy, Aunt Sandwich is a hamster and Uncle Dogday - yes, he's a dog. And a chess grandmaster.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9 +","interest_age":"Interest level: 7 +"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32973/9781406324235-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32973","title":"How to Be Invisible","author":"by Tim Lott","description":"A strange encounter with a moustachioed man in a dusty bookshop offers a cryptic answer to Strato Nyman's troubles","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32275/9781841676234-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32275","title":"Boffin Boy and the Temple of Mars","author":"by David Orme","description":"Boffin Boy discovers an ancient building on Mars containing mysterious creatures.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34403/kenny-wright-superhero.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34403","title":"Kenny Wright: Superhero","author":"by James Patterson and Chris Tebbetts","description":"This entertaining book tackles the serious issues of bullying, poverty and difficult family circumstances with a light-hearted touch. Short chapters and the use of comic strip drawings to illustrate Stainlezz Steel's imaginary escapades make this is an accessible and amusing...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32224/9780385618939-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32224","title":"The Worst Thing About My Sister","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Sisters Marty and Melissa just about manage to get along until they are forced to share a bedroom. Soon they are fighting every day, and to make things worse, Marty finds herself in trouble at school too.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"}]}
{"id":363,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/363/","title":"Superheroes","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33167/9781907912221.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33167","title":"Captain Valiant and Me: Revenge of the Black Phantom","author":"by Adam Britten","description":"Mark looks like an ordinary schoolboy, but the truth is he is really Dynamic Boy, one of a family of Astral Guardians sent to protect planet Earth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28706/9781407105284-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28706","title":"Eliot Jones, Midnight Superhero","author":"by Anne Cottringer","description":"This laugh-out-loud picture book is a delight.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32969/9781407124063-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32969","title":"Superkid","author":"by Claire Freedman","description":"When his X-ray eyes spot someone in trouble, Superkid is always ready to save the other children from all kinds of horrors - from playground bullies to grandma's broccoli","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34454/mighty-small.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34454","title":"Mighty Small","author":"by Timothy Knapman","description":"Max Small has the perfect name, because he's a tiny mouse. But Max is convinced that actually he is a superhero.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31254/boy-zero.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31254","title":"Boy Zero Wannabe Hero: The Curse of the Catastrophic Cupcakes","author":"by Peter Millett","description":"The third in the Boy Zero series, this is a short chapter book which continues the story of Charlie Applejack, the world's newest and youngest superhero.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"}]}
{"id":364,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/364/","title":"Great picture books for dads to read out loud","list_description":"These are great books for dads to read out loud to their children.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27217/previously.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27217","title":"Previously","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"Using just the word 'previously' various fairytales are retold – starting with their endings and working back to their beginnings.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32843/9780857630476-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32843","title":"Open Very Carefully","author":"by Nick Bromley and Nicola O'Byrne","description":"A crocodile has invaded the pages of this picture book, and is causing chaos by gobbling up words!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33970/my-amazing-dad.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33970","title":"My Amazing Dad","author":"by Ross Collins","description":"An appealing story with amusing illustrations for children and dads to share together.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25325/revoltingrhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25325","title":"Revolting Rhymes","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This is an hilarious collection of some well-loved fairy tales, cleverly reinvented by Roald Dahl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34301/oi-frog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34301","title":"Oi Frog!","author":"by Kes Gray","description":"Bright, bold, expressive illustrations add to the fun in this hilarious picture book with a knockout ending. A must for the under 5s.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34492/dinosaur-police.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34492","title":"Dinosaur Police","author":"by Sarah McIntyre","description":"Unashamedly silly and wonderfully mad, this will delight little dinosaur fans.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34211/book-with-no-pictures.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34211","title":"The Book with No Pictures","author":"by B J Novak","description":"Demanding to be shared, this is a fresh and enormously funny book that children will want to hear time and time again."}]}
{"id":365,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/365/","title":"Independent Bookshop Week booklist","list_description":"To celebrate this year's Independent Bookshop Week we've put together a great children's booklist made up of the Independent Bookshop Week Award shortlist.  Enjoy! ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33978/blown-away.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33978","title":"Blown Away","author":"by Rob Biddulph","description":"Penguin Blue has got a new toy, and it's the right kind of day to try it out. But the wind is a little stronger than expected and along with the new kite, Penguin Blue is blown away.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34463/never-tickle-a-tiger.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34463","title":"Never Tickle a Tiger","author":"by Pamela Butchart","description":"For fidgety children everywhere, especially those who don't heed good advice, this cautionary tale shows what the unconsidered consequences can be when we can't understand just why we're told never to do something.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33951/bears-don-t-read.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33951","title":"Bears Don't Read","author":"by Emma Chichester Clark","description":"Bears Don't Read is a wonderfully engaging picture book about the joy of reading and how much fun it can be to help others.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33844/apple-and-rains.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33844","title":"Apple and Rain","author":"by Sarah Crossan","description":"Engrossing and uplifting, challenging and charming, Apple and Rain brings fiction and poetry together in a well-crafted story about growing up and learning to love.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34171/13-storey-treehouse.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34171","title":"The 13-Storey Treehouse","author":"by Andy Griffiths and Terry Denton","description":"Griffiths and Denton create a triumph to engage even the most determined hater of books, which includes hilarious cartoon drawings.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34357/9781447264101.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34357","title":"The Lie Tree","author":"by Frances Hardinge","description":"This dark, exciting novel delves into the world of religion versus science in the late 1800s, and twists towards a thrilling climax.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33530/shh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33530","title":"Shh! We Have a Plan","author":"by Chris Haughton","description":"Deep in the dark of a moonlit forest, four shady hunters are out to catch themselves a bird. Or at least they’re trying...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33747/mouse-who-ate-the-moon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33747","title":"The Mouse Who Ate the Moon","author":"by Petr Horáček","description":"This peep-through story book has beautiful illustrations which are brought to life with the peep-through hole on each page. An endearing and funny story with friendship at its heart.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34193/wanted-ralfy-rabbitt-book-burglar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34193","title":"Wanted! Ralfy Rabbit, Book Burglar","author":"by Emily MacKenzie","description":"Little book lovers will adore this silly story of naughty Ralfy. The illustrations are fun and modern, with some bunny puns to keep adults entertained too.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33464/running-girls.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33464","title":"Running Girl","author":"by Simon Mason","description":"Simon Mason turns his hand to crime writing in this fast-paced, action-packed and wonderfully engaging whodunnit.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33742/apple-tart-of-hope.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33742","title":"The Apple Tart of Hope","author":"by Sarah Moore Fitzgerald","description":"Oscar's apple tarts bring hope to the sad or desperate. He is loved and appreciated for this special gift. Meg is his best friend, but just as their friendship is about to blossom into love she has to go to...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33979/opal-plumstead.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33979","title":"Opal Plumstead","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Fourteen-year-old Opal's family falls on hard times when her accountant father foolishly forges a cheque to support his family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":369,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/369/","title":"Shirley Hughes","list_description":"Author and illustrator Shirley Hughes OBE is the first ever Book Trust Lifetime Achievement Award winner. She has written and illustrated over 200 cherished children’s books, including the celebrated Alfie stories. Shirley is currently collaborating with her daughter, Clara Vulliamy, on the Dixie O’Day series, one of which is included in the Book Trust Best Book Guide 2015. Take a look at just a snapshot of some of Shirley's most amazing and celebrated work below.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24861/9781862308053-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24861","title":"Dogger","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"When Dave loses his favourite toy, Dogger, he is desolate.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25684/alfie-wins-a-prize.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25684","title":"Alfie Wins a Prize","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Alfie's painting at the Big School's Harvest Fair is judged worthy of one of the main prizes. But Alfie is more taken with the consolation prize...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27339/alfie-and-the-big-boys.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27339","title":"Alfie and the Big Boys","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Children will relish this warm tale of everyday life with illustrations overflowing with colour and vitality.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3 - 8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29030/jonadab-and-rita.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29030","title":"Jonadab and Rita","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Jonadab is an old, neglected donkey made of worn grey velvet. He has one good friend in the shy toy mouse, Rita. Jonadab also has a secret - he can fly.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30095/the-lion-and-the-unicorn.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30095","title":"The Lion and the Unicorn","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Lenny is bullied by the children at his new school, but draws courage from a badge his father gave him, and comes to terms with his fear and loneliness when he befriends Mick.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30417/don-t-want-to-go.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30417","title":"Don't want to go!","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Lily's mum is in bed with flu and dad has to go to work, so Lily must spend the day at Melanie's house. She doesn't want to go, but she soon has fun playing with Ringo the dog.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30875/the-christmas-eve-ghost.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30875","title":"The Christmas Eve Ghost","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"In 1930s Liverpool, young Bronwen and Dylan find kindness from an unexpected source when they are frightened by what they think is a ghost on Christmas Eve.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31320/9780140544596-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31320","title":"Lucy and Tom at the Seaside","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Follow a happy family day out by the seaside as Tom and Lucy enjoy making sandcastles, looking in rock pools and going on a donkey ride","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32260/9781862307858-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32260","title":"Alfie Gives a Hand","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Shirley Hughes' much-loved Alfie goes to his first birthday party in this lovely picture book for pre-school children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32292/9781406336108.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32292","title":"Hero on a Bicycle","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"The first novel from much-loved author and illustrator Shirley Hughes is a thrilling and moving story about a boy and his bicycle, set against a dramatic background of war-torn Italy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32540/9780370332079-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32540","title":"Bobbo Goes to School","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Lily and mum are worried when Bobbo the toy dog goes missing - but he soon turns up in a school playground.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32607/9781849412889-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32607","title":"All About Alfie","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"In a brand new collection of stories and poems, Alfie has a spooky late-night adventure with an owl and introduces us to his secret den in the garden.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33224/dixieoday.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33224","title":"Dixie O'Day: In the Fast Lane","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"Mother and daughter Shirley Hughes and Clara Vulliamy have teamed up for the first time for this sweet story, the first in a series about canine driver Dixie O'Day and his friend, Percy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"}]}
{"id":370,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/370/","title":"If you like the Diary of a Wimpy Kid try...","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34149/strange-case-of-origami-yoda.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34149","title":"The Strange Case of Origami Yoda","author":"by Tom Angleberger","description":"A hilarious account of an advice-giving origami figure and its eccentric owner who manage to save many pupils from embarrassing situations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29290/joeypigza.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29290","title":"Joey Pigza Swallowed The Key","author":"by Jack Gantos","description":"This is a sensitive portrayal of a young ADHD sufferer, but is also a thoroughly entertaining insight into the life of the immensely likeable Joey Pigza, whose escapades are certain to amuse any reader.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31722/9781408313039-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31722","title":"The World of Norm","author":"by Jonathan Meres","description":"A funny illustrated book likely to find favour with fans of Wimpy Kid, Big Nate and Tom Gates.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29545/9781847382306-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29545","title":"Ribblestrop","author":"by Andy Mulligan","description":"There’s a wonderful, anarchic energy to this funny, pacey, action-packed novel","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34129/i-funny.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34129","title":"I Funny: A Middle School Story","author":"by James Patterson and Chris Grabenstein","description":"Jamie Grimm loves to tell jokes. His friends and his Uncle think he's so funny that he should enter the 'Planet's Funniest Kid Comic' contest. But Jamie knows that his mind might go blank when faced with an audience.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31327/big-nate.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31327","title":"Big Nate - The Boy with the Biggest Head in the World","author":"by Lincoln Peirce","description":"This hilarious take on American school life is sure to make readers laugh, cringe and turn the next page. Based on a comic strip by Lincoln Peirce, the inspiration behind Jeff Kinney, this is sure to appeal to any fans...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":377,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/377/","title":"Great teachers in children's books","list_description":"This booklist celebrates books with characters who are great teachers.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24676/malorytowers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24676","title":"First Term at Malory Towers","author":"by Enid Blyton","description":"We're rooting for Darrell Rivers as she starts boarding school, and learns to cope with her fiery temper and decide for herself which friends are genuine.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34040/its-snow-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34040","title":"It's Snow Day","author":"by Richard Curtis","description":"This must-read winter picture book is crammed with fabulously joyful and expressive illustrations and will be loved by young and old alike.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25342/matilda.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25342","title":"Matilda","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This modern fairy-tale with a brilliantly inspiring young heroine is one of Roald Dahl's best loved stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29125/the-graveyard-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29125","title":"The Graveyard Book","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"After his family are killed, Bod is brought up in a graveyard by ghosts.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25337/once-upon-an-ordinary-school-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25337","title":"Once Upon an Ordinary School Day","author":"by Colin McNaughton","description":"An ordinary boy goes off to school and everything seems just as ordinary as ever, until a new teacher arrives in class.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33293/worst-witch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33293","title":"The Worst Witch","author":"by Jill Murphy","description":"Long before Harry Potter first went to Hogwarts, trainee witch Mildred Hubble embarked on life at Miss Cackle's Academy for Witches...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29281/lightingthief.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29281","title":"Percy Jackson and the Lightning Thief","author":"by Rick Riordan","description":"In this leftfield comic fantasy novel, 12-year-old Percy Jackson discovers that the Greek gods of Olympus are alive and living in modern-day New York.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30267/9780747558194-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30267","title":"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone","author":"by J K Rowling","description":"After the misery of life with his ghastly aunt and uncle, Harry Potter is delighted to have the chance to embark on an exciting new life at the Hogwart's School of Wizardry and Witchcraft.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-13"}]}
{"id":378,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/378/","title":"Jungle","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30598/rumble-in-the-jungle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30598","title":"Rumble in the Jungle","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34532/peekaboo-jungle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34532","title":"Peekabooks: In the Jungle","author":"by Emily Bolam","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33820/one-to-ten-animal-mayhem.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33820","title":"One to Ten Animal Mayhem","author":"by Thomas Flintham","description":"A colourful counting book full of animals."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34381/black-and-white-club.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34381","title":"The Black and White Club","author":"by Alice Hemming","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34382/little-jungle-explorers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34382","title":"Little Jungle Explorers","author":"by Anthony Lewis","description":"Colourful board book with double-sided explorer figure!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32233/9781407108230-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32233","title":"Jungle Jive","author":"by Tony Mitton","description":"It's Monkey's birthday and he's organising a party tonight for all the animals in the jungle. Everyone is putting their best clothes on and getting ready to dance","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24971/doing-the-animal-bop.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24971","title":"Doing the Animal Bop","author":"by Jan Ormerod","description":"Children will enjoy matching the rhythmic text to the animals actions, and joining in with the dancing themselves. A great book for sharing and one that children are sure to want to hear over and over again!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27294/banana.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27294","title":"Banana!","author":"by Ed Vere","description":"Follow the cartoon-style adventures of two monkeys. One of them has a banana and the other one wants it - but what is the magic word?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29981/giraffes-cant-dance.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29981","title":"Giraffes Can't Dance","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"Rhyming text and vibrant full-page illustrations make this marvellous picture book perfect for reading aloud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"}]}
{"id":379,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/379/","title":"Summer Reads","list_description":"Here are our suggestions for summer reads - and there's something for everyone. New books; old books; books about summer; books to get lost in; and books that come in series so you won't have to stop reading this summer!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25547/penderwicks.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25547","title":"The Penderwicks","author":"by Jeanne Birdsall","description":"Four eccentric sisters and their loving but distracted father take a holiday cottage in the beautiful Arundel estate.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33025/9781408820506-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33025","title":"The Great Ice Cream Heist","author":"by Elen Caldecott","description":"Shy Eva lives a quiet life with her protective Dad - until the noisy McIntyre family move in next door.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34397/charlie-merrick2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34397","title":"Charlie Merrick’s Misfits: I’m a Nobody, Get Me Out of Here!","author":"by Dave Cousins","description":"The second Charlie Merrick book takes our hero and his football-mad friends on a Soccer Camp holiday, but the plan misfires when they discover that the booking got confused, and they end up at a Survival Camp instead.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33745/peas-book-of-holidays.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33745","title":"Pea's Book of Holidays","author":"by Susie Day","description":"Susie Day returns with another hugely fun installment of the delightful Pea's Book series. Whether or not they've read about Pea's previous adventures, young readers will enjoy the gentle humour of this entertaining contemporary spin on the classic family story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31138/olivia-goes-to-venice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31138","title":"Olivia goes to Venice","author":"by Ian Falconer","description":"This story follows Olivia as she gets ready for her holiday, flies on a plane, gets searched at the airport and explores Venice.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29728/diary-of-a-wimpy-kid-dog-days.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29728","title":"Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Dog Days","author":"by Jeff Kinney","description":"Greg's idea of a perfect summer holiday is to sit indoors and play computer games but for some reason his Mum thinks fresh air and 'family togetherness' are a much better plan.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31705/9781444003284-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31705","title":"Adventure Island: The Mystery of the Whistling Caves","author":"by Helen Moss","description":"An action-packed beginning to a new series and a good old-fashioned mystery.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34078/lost-children-mysteries-ravenstorm-island.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34078","title":"Mysteries of Ravenstorm Island: The Lost Children","author":"by Gillian Philip","description":"Thrown together during a summer holiday on a remote island, Molly and Arthur seem unlikely friends who must solve a mystery together.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33299/swallows-and-amazons.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33299","title":"Swallows and Amazons","author":"by Arthur Ransome","description":"It's the summer holidays, and the Walker children are excited to set sail on their boat Swallow and camp on Wild Cat Island.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31867/9781444000214-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31867","title":"Kidnap in the Caribbean","author":"by Lauren St John","description":"The second Laura Marling mystery has all the elements of an old fashioned adventure story, action packed with friends rallying to fight an evil enemy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33624/rules-of-summer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33624","title":"Rules of Summer","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"An excellent book illustrating 'what I learned last summer' that would be an inspiring addition to any bookshelf.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5","interest_age":"Interest level: 7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31272/lily-alone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31272","title":"Lily Alone","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Lily's self-centred young mother jets off to a holiday in Spain with her new boyfriend. Lily and her three younger siblings are carelessly left behind.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":380,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/380/","title":"Summer Reads","list_description":"This summer try out some of these books, there's something for everyone - whether you're after a funny book, an emotional book, a thriller, or a road trip.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32119/9781447205180-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32119","title":"Jasmine Skies","author":"by Sita Brahmachari","description":"Following from Brahmachari's debut novel, Artichoke Hearts, this a thoughtful, tender and uplifting novel, which continues the story of Mira, now two years older, as she negotiates challenging new experiences, the complexities of family and friendship, and the uncertainty of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32864/9780857078025-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32864","title":"Infinite Sky","author":"by C J Flood","description":"Iris's mum has gone, leaving her to look after her older brother and dad. When a family of Irish Travellers park up on the farm, the summer becomes even more eventful.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33589/why-we-took-the-car.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33589","title":"Why We Took the Car","author":"by Wolfgang Herrndorf","description":"Mike and Tschik take off in a 'borrowed' Lada for a summer road trip.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30963/a-beautiful-lie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30963","title":"A Beautiful Lie","author":"by Irfan Master","description":"Set in India during the summer of 1947, A Beautiful Lie follows the tumultuous events of the Partition of India through the eyes of Bilal who is looking after his ill father.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34537/all-my-secrets.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34537","title":"All My Secrets","author":"by Sophie McKenzie","description":"Fast paced and easy to read, this exciting mystery with unexpected plot twists, new friendships and a touch of teenage romance is a great summer teen read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24508/9780141318011-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24508","title":"How I Live Now","author":"by Meg Rosoff","description":"Fifteen-year-old New Yorker Daisy is sent to England to spend a summer with her unconventional cousins","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30347/the-cardturner.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30347","title":"The Cardturner","author":"by Louis Sachar","description":"Alton has been unwillingly forced by his parents into being his irrascible, blind, bridge-mad uncle’s cardturner, in the hope that the family will be beneficiaries of the old man’s will.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"}]}
{"id":381,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/381/","title":"Summer Reads","list_description":"Try these YA summer reads to get lost in this summer... and if you get started on The Rain or Take Back the Skies, you can go straight to the sequels when you're done!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33800/the-rain.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33800","title":"The Rain","author":"by Virginia Bergin","description":"A funny, smart and wonderfully British take on dystopia that will leave readers eager for the next installment of Ruby's story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32983/9780552568470-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32983","title":"Trust Me","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Seventeen-year-old Jayna can't wait to go on holiday with boyfriend Andrew - but their trip has unexpected and terrible consequences.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33199/cruel-summer-juno-dawson.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33199","title":"Cruel Summer","author":"by Juno Dawson","description":"A year after Janey's suicide, her friends come back together for a holiday at a luxurious Spanish villa. Then an unexpected guest arrives, claiming to have evidence that Janey was murdered.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32548/9781407120843-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32548","title":"The Twice-Lived Summer of Bluebell Jones","author":"by Susie Day","description":"Bluebell Jones is about to turn 13 and all she really wants for her birthday is to blossom into someone cool.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33708/lobsters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33708","title":"Lobsters","author":"by Tom Ellen and Lucy Ivison","description":"The first novel from friends and collaborators Tom Ellen and Lucy Ivison, Lobsters is a frank and very funny young adult romance.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34347/last-summer-of-us.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34347","title":"The Last Summer of Us","author":"by Maggie Harcourt","description":"After her mother’s funeral, Limpet is only too glad to get away for a few days and join her best friends Steffan and Jared on a summer road trip.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33855/since-youve-been-gone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33855","title":"Since You've Been Gone","author":"by Morgan Matson","description":"This is the perfect summer read about friendship, romance and self-discovery, written with real understanding and humour.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34132/all-the-bright-places.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34132","title":"All the Bright Places","author":"by Jennifer Niven","description":"All the Bright Places will pull you in and won’t let you go again, even long after you turned the final page – a must-read","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33440/song.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33440","title":"This Song Will Save Your Life","author":"by Leila Sales","description":"When high school misfit Elise stumbles upon an underground indie club night, Start, she unexpectedly finds a place she belongs","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33728/take-back-the-skies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33728","title":"Take Back the Skies","author":"by Lucy Saxon","description":"As an introduction to other-world fantasy fiction this is engaging and accessible but it will appeal most to younger teens.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32377/9780141340722-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32377","title":"The Probability of Miracles","author":"by Wendy Wunder","description":"Cyncial teenage cancer patient Campbell has a summer to remember in the magical town of Promise in this moving and bittersweet debut novel","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":382,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/382/","title":"Summer Reads 2015","list_description":"It may not be the highest priority on your holiday packing list, but we strongly recommend you invest in a couple of great holiday reads for the beach/swimming pool/park/back garden this summer.  This Summer Reads 2015 list features great crime thrillers, funny biographies and stories of holiday romances. So, have a look through our summer booklist and rush out and buy a book or two - along with suntan lotion and travel sweets - or just look out for these books at the airport.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34580/9781509801657.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34580","title":"In the Unlikely Event","author":"by Judy Blume","description":"A story woven around the events of 1952 in Elizabeth, New Jersey, this semi-autobiographical novel tells of the horror of a town shattered by disaster and the amazing courage of its people as they seek to rebuild their lives."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31191/the-big-sleep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31191","title":"The Big Sleep","author":"by Raymond Chandler","description":"Californian private eye Philip Marlowe's entanglement with the Sternwood family - and an attendant cast of colorful underworld figures - is the background to a story reflecting all the tarnished glitter of the great American Dream"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31356/bossypants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31356","title":"Bossypants","author":"by Tina Fey","description":"Tina Fey, the creator of 30 Rock, one of Saturday Night Live’s best stalwarts and she of the uncanny Sarah Palin impressions in the run-up to the 2008 USA elections, may not be as widely known here as she should..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32787/49390cda-43cb-4fc2-ae32-6452283c4828-img100.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32787","title":"Clay","author":"by Melissa Harrison","description":"Clay, by first time novelist Melissa Harrison, is a story of how nature in one city unites four very different people through their love, and almost deep connection to a nondescript inner-city park and the natural wonders it holds within..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33799/9781782390718.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33799","title":"Summer House with Swimming Pool","author":"by Herman Koch","description":"A group of people gather for a holiday at a rented villa, but things change after am unfortunate event at a beach party."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33832/9780007441761.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33832","title":"A Girl Called Summer","author":"by Lucy Lord","description":"Bella's hope of a quiet life is disrupted when her A-list Hollywood friends descend to her new home in Ibiza."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32251/9781444737141.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32251","title":"Cuckoo In the Nest","author":"by Nat Luurtsema","description":"Comedian Nat Luurtsema is a very funny woman. As a stand-up and as part of sketch trio Jigsaw. This memoir of her 6 months living at home while looking for a flat started out as a collection of hilarious warts'n'all..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33522/panic.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33522","title":"Panic","author":"by Lauren Oliver","description":"Three people with different agendas take part in an illegal and dangerous game called 'Panic' in order secure a cash prize."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30854/nerd-do-well.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30854","title":"Nerd Do Well","author":"by Simon Pegg","description":"I don't mean to frame this like an advert but, simply, the book is a breezy, funny read, filled with anecdotes and humility. And that's the type of 'celebrity' I want to read about."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31406/collected-stories.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31406","title":"Collected Stories","author":"by Ruth Rendell","description":"Well kown for her Inspector Wexford mysteries, Ruth Rendell is also a prolific short story writer."}]}
{"id":383,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/383/","title":"Booktime books 2015-16","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32843/9780857630476-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32843","title":"Open Very Carefully","author":"by Nick Bromley and Nicola O'Byrne","description":"A crocodile has invaded the pages of this picture book, and is causing chaos by gobbling up words!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":384,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/384/","title":"Chris Riddell books","list_description":" We're thrilled to announce that Children's Laureate Chris Riddell will be releasing a fun picture/activity book. Chris's Doodle-a-Day diary will be great for doodlers and features step-by-step guides, colouring in and story starters.  The book's publisher, Macmillan Children's Books, are kindly donating 20p from every copy sold in the UK to Book Trust, which will be available from 22 October.  Since being announced as Children's Laureate back in June, Chris has been doodling every day, and these pictures can be seen on the Children's Laureate site. Chris also kindly made Illustrations in Search of a Story - a fun activity for children and teens - for the Book Trust website.  So, before his Doodle-a-Day diary is released, relive or discover some of Chris's previous books and illustrations.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29057/absurdia.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29057","title":"The Emperor of Absurdia","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"The Emperor of Absurdia awakes one morning and can't find his snuggly scarf, so after checking with The Wardrobe Monster, begins to search for it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29563/mr-underbed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29563","title":"Mr Underbed","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"One night, as Jim is just about to drop off to sleep, a large, blue, shaggy head pops out from under the mattress and complains about how uncomfortable it is to always sleep on the floor.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30903/alienography.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30903","title":"Alienography","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Have you ever feared a Martian attack? This book recommends creeping up close enough to plant a big wet slobbery kiss on their slimy skins – your germs will do the rest to defeat them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32685/9780230741041-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32685","title":"Alienography 2: Tips for Tiny Tyrants","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Find out how to take over the universe in this funny and engaging book from Chris Riddell (and Colin the Alien)","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33263/gothgirl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33263","title":"Goth Girl and the Ghost of a Mouse","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Fans of Chris Riddell's Ottoline books will love this quirky story about young heroine Ada Goth.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34087/goth-girl-and-the-fete-worse-than-deaths.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34087","title":"Goth Girl and the Fete Worse than Death","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Chris Riddell's third book in the Goth Girl series intrigues and delights with a cakey combination of adventure, love and webbed footnotes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24668/blobheds.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24668","title":"Blobheads","author":"by Paul Stewart and Chris Riddell","description":"Ever wondered what might rise out of the toilet when you lift the lid? In Billy Barnes' case it's the Blobheads, three incompetent aliens...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"}]}
{"id":385,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/385/","title":"Halloween","list_description":"These picture books featuring witches, wizards and monsters are perfect to share with little ones at Halloween.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29824/funnybones.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29824","title":"Funnybones","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"In the first book of this now classic series, we are taken down the dark, dark street to the dark, dark house and into the dark, dark cellar in which the skeletons live.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31994/love-monster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31994","title":"Love Monster","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"A funny and charming picture book illustrated with Rachel Bright’s engaging and expressive etchings with a feel good message","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28735/room-on-the-broom.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28735","title":"Room on the Broom","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Axel Scheffler","description":"From former Children's Laureate Julia Donaldson and longtime collaborator Axel Scheffler comes this much-loved tale about a witch and her gang of friends.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31296/the-princess-and-the-wizard.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31296","title":"The Princess and the Wizard","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Lydia Monks","description":"Princess Eliza is having a birthday party. But just as she blows out the seven candles on her cake, the wicked wizard arrives… uninvited.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31883/9780140568707-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31883","title":"Angelina's Halloween","author":"by Katharine Holabird","description":"Helen Craig's delicate and intricate illustrations beautifully conjur up the Halloween atmosphere and are full of detail children will love to explore","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31476/9780230736085-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31476","title":"Little Wizard","author":"by Kazuno Kohara","description":"A touching story about the power of friendship and self-belief from the CILIP Kate Greenaway-nominated creator of The Haunted House and Jack Frost","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33277/9780718194420-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33277","title":"Meg and Mog","author":"by Helen Nicholl & Jan Pienkowski","description":"In this the first story about much-loved characters Meg the witch and Mog her cat, the pair go off to a wild Hallowe'en party with all the other witches","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33213/monsterzoo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33213","title":"Do Not Enter the Monster Zoo!","author":"by Amy Sparkes and Sara Ogilvie","description":"Can our young hero take on a Monster Zoo full of naughty creatures - and survive to tell the tale?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35274/four-silly-skeletons.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35274","title":"Four Silly Skeletons","author":"by Mark Sperring","description":"This bold rhyming picture book features four accident-prone skeletons. Children will giggle at their various mishaps, making this an ideal book to share with little ones at Halloween.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30569/winniewitch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30569","title":"Winnie the Witch","author":"by Valerie Thomas","description":"This is the first of many stories about Winnie and her cat, Wilber. Winnie is a well-loved character, and the excellent illustrations are wild and wacky."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31496/bedtime-for-monsters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31496","title":"Bedtime for Monsters","author":"by Ed Vere","description":"Do you ever wonder if somewhere, not too far away, there might be monsters?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33351/9781409520986-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33351","title":"That's Not My Monster...","author":"by Fiona Watt and Rachel Wells","description":"This monster-themed book is an entertaining addition to the much-loved That's Not My... series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34960/nibbles-the-book-monster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34960","title":"Nibbles: The Book Monster","author":"by Emma Yarlett","description":"This is a story about a little monster called… Nibbles. And with that, he nibbles his way right out of the book! This really exciting reading experience is sure to be a hit with the whole family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6","interest_age":"Interest level: 3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29872/the-very-busy-spider.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29872","title":"The Very Busy Spider","author":"by Eric Carle","description":"One morning in a farmyard a spider begins to spin a web. All the animals try to persuade her to stop but she doesn't answer any of them; she is too busy spinning her web.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":386,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/386/","title":"11 children's books about bees and dragons","list_description":"Inspired by BBC One's The Apprentice, we've compiled a list of classic and amazing children's books that are better than the books created on the TV show.  Viewers would have seen how the two competing teams had to create, design and sell a children's book for 3-5 year-olds in two days. Creating a children's book from start to finish is no easy job and both teams fell a little short when trying to put a children's book together in just 48 hours. One team created Bizzy Bee's First Adventure, a book about a bee who's trying to make honey, and the other team created Snottydink, a tale about a dragon that's a bit like an elephant.  So, we thought we'd show the teams what they're up against as we highlight some of the more celebrated books about bees and dragons.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32288/9781406304916-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32288","title":"A First Book of Nature","author":"by Nicola Davies","description":"Hearld's nostalgic illustrations are the perfect accompaniment to this lovely chronicle of a child's first experiences of nature","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30838/zog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30838","title":"Zog","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Zog is a keen dragon at Dragon School who aims to be the best in his class and win a golden star.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33966/dragon-loves-penguin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33966","title":"Dragon Loves Penguin","author":"by Debi Gliori","description":"The dragons have settled in the land of ice and snow, and their eggs are waiting to hatch, but one dragon doesn't have an egg to care for.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32907/9780330544030-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32907","title":"Again!","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"It's Cedric's the little dragon's bedtime, but before he goes to sleep, there's just enough time for mum to read him a bedtime story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25585/9780141500577-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25585","title":"Guess What I Found in Dragon Wood","author":"by Timothy Knapman","description":"Dragon is excited – and just a little scared – when he finds the Benjamin","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29137/winnie-the-pooh-and-ten-busy-bees.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29137","title":"Winnie-the-Pooh and Ten Busy Bees","author":"by A A Milne","description":"Winnie-the-Pooh counts the reader down from ten to zero, ably assisted by the appropriate number of elevated plastic bees.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31589/cat-in-the-hat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31589","title":"The Cat in the Hat Knows a Lot About That: Show Me The Honey","author":"by Tish Rabe","description":"Includes easy and funny rhymes which children will love to read again and again","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29278/sylvia-and-bird.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29278","title":"Sylvia and Bird","author":"by Catherine Rayner","description":"A story that gently explores themes of expectation, loneliness, friendship and valuing others.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32504/9781849415019-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32504","title":"Knight School","author":"by Marilyn Singer","description":"Little Knight and Little Dragon are the best of friends and they can't wait to start school. But when will they have time to play together?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29696/insect-detective.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29696","title":"Insect Detective","author":"by Steve Voake","description":"A range of insects are introduced – wasps, solitary bees, ants, dragonflies – and their behaviour described.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31275/bumblebee.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31275","title":"Bumblebee","author":"by J. V. Wilson and Adrienne Kennaway","description":"The life cycle of a queen bumblebee starts on a sunny spring day when she sleepily leaves her winter home...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-9"}]}
{"id":387,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/387/","title":"Books about cats","list_description":"We all love Mog the cat. But she isn’t the only kitty to get up to mischief in a children’s book.  Here are a few other cat stories to lay your paws on and enjoy with the little ones.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32676/the-black-cat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32676","title":"Funnybones: The Black Cat","author":"by Allan Ahlberg","description":"Another Funnybones adventure. This time, the skeleton friends go sledging - whee!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31506/9780230714021-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31506","title":"Cats Ahoy!","author":"by Peter Bently","description":"Cats’ favourite thing in the world is fish. So when Alfonso the cat overhears a two old men discussing the imminent arrival of a boat, carrying its largest ever catch, he hatches a plan. This book is very funny –...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29586/tabbymctat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29586","title":"Tabby McTat","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"A poetic story of love, adventure and music that demands to be read aloud or possibly sung, depending on the power of the reader's purr.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33670/macavity.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33670","title":"Macavity","author":"by TS Eliot","description":"Escaped from Old Possum's Book of Practical Cats, Macavity is now the star of his own picture book. With new illustrations from Arthur Robins, this timeless rhyme will charm a new generation.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33938/pete-cat-four-groovy-buttons.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33938","title":"Pete the Cat and his Four Groovy Buttons","author":"by Eric Litwin","description":"This book is fun! It's got counting, singing, rhyming and repetition. Pete's 'don't sweat the small stuff' life philosophy is engaging and the vibrant, almost perspective-less illustrations are strangely beautiful.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25781/mr-puss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25781","title":"Mr Pusskins","author":"by Sam Lloyd","description":"Humorous, lively illustrations accompany the text in this unconventional love story, which is also a lesson in not taking people for granted.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33277/9780718194420-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33277","title":"Meg and Mog","author":"by Helen Nicholl & Jan Pienkowski","description":"In this the first story about much-loved characters Meg the witch and Mog her cat, the pair go off to a wild Hallowe'en party with all the other witches","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33276/the-cat-in-the-hat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33276","title":"The Cat in the Hat","author":"by Dr Seuss","description":"When Sally and her brother are left alone on a rainy day, they think they are in for a dull time - but then the Cat in the Hat appears.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32708/9781905417704-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32708","title":"Grumpy Cat","author":"by Britta Teckentrup","description":"Cat eats, sleeps and spends his days alone. The other cats think he is grumpy, but really he is just lonely. But then Kitten turns up and everything changes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":388,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/388/","title":"Battle of the Santas","list_description":"Usually jolly, sometimes grumpy, young and old - we've all got a favourite Father Christmas in fiction. Which book has the Santa that you love the most?  To get you started, here are just a few of Mr Claus' best moments: ho, ho, hooray!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31864/polarxpress.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31864","title":"The Polar Express","author":"by Chris Van Allsburg","description":"An enchanting Christmas story, beautifully written and illustrated with pictures full of warmth and light","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33412/i-love-you-father-christmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33412","title":"I Love You, Father Christmas","author":"by Giles Andreae & Emma Dodd","description":"A sweet picture book, full of engaging rhyme about one child's love for Father Christmas.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29103/the-snowman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29103","title":"The Snowman","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"James builds a snowman in the garden, then wakes up in the night to find that it has come to life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34759/9780723277972.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34759","title":"Father Christmas","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"For poor Father Christmas, December 24th is the hardest night of work in the year. Raymond Briggs follows him on his wonderfully grumpy and funny journey, revealing some beautifully illustrated moments of joy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29044/stickman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29044","title":"Stick Man","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"The award-winning creators of The Gruffalo now present us with a modern variation on a long-established folk tale theme, which details the perilous adventures of a stick.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25403/fatherchristmass.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25403","title":"Dear Father Christmas","author":"by Alan Durant","description":"Christmas is fast approaching and Holly writes to Father Christmas. To her surprise, he replies and the pair begin to exchange letters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34718/a-boy-called-christmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34718","title":"A Boy Called Christmas","author":"by Matt Haig","description":"A Boy Called Christmas is a tale of adventure, snow, kidnapping, elves, more snow, and a boy called Nikolas, who isn't afraid to believe in magic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33305/the-lion-the-witch-the-wardrobe.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33305","title":"The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe","author":"by C S Lewis","description":"When Peter, Susan, Edmund and Lucy - step through a wardrobe door in the strange country house where they are staying, they find themselves in the land of Narnia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28233/the-night-before-christmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28233","title":"The Night Before Christmas","author":"by Clement C Moore","description":"There have been countless editions of Clement's poem but none has transcended this one illustrated by talented artist Christian Birmingham.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"}]}
{"id":389,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/389/","title":"Christmas books for teenagers","list_description":"Looking for some wintry or festive page-turners? Here's our selection of teenage books to keep you warm in the holidays. Some are the perfect cosy read. Others have storylines to get the blood pumping!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33936/winterkills.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33936","title":"Winterkill","author":"by Kate A Boorman","description":"This is the first in a series and is sure to gather many fans. A great read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33487/darkisrising.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33487","title":"The Dark is Rising","author":"by Susan Cooper","description":"This is probably one of the greatest fantasy sequences ever written. Darkly magical and intense Cooper weaves her storytelling wonder over fully realised characters and worlds, drawing in the reader and leading them on a journey that will leave them...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33194/one-crow-aloned.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33194","title":"One Crow Alone","author":"by Sophie Crockett","description":"In the midst of a seemingly never-ending winter, Magda gradually loses all the things that give her life direction and meaning.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32674/9781780878362-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32674","title":"Lost Christmas","author":"by David Logan","description":"Goose is lost until Anthony appears - a man who knows nothing about himself but sees and feels the secret pain of all those who shake his hand","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33988/my-true-love-gave-to-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33988","title":"My True Love Gave to Me","author":"by Stephanie Perkins","description":"A collection of Christmas-themed romantic short stories, one for each of the 'twelve days', by some of the best known American YA authors.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31774/9781408800041-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31774","title":"The Dead of Winter","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"A nail-biting story of hauntings and terror by the master of the genre, Chris Priestley","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33572/when-the-guns-fall-silent.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33572","title":"When the Guns Fall Silent","author":"by James Riordan","description":"A boy's understanding of the First World War changes as he visits Flanders Fields with his grandfather and hears his stories of being a soldier in the war.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34726/the-wolf-wilders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34726","title":"The Wolf Wilder","author":"by Katherine Rundell","description":"When the murderous hostility of the Russian Army threatens her very existence, Feo is left with no option but to go on the run. What follows is a story of revolution and adventure, about standing up for the things you...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25821/my-swordhand-is-singing.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25821","title":"My Swordhand is Singing","author":"by Marcus Sedgwick","description":"Set in the seventeenth century amid the bleakness of winter in Eastern Europe, and inspired by vampire folklore, this is a superbly crafted, dark and menacing tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30900/laura-marlin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30900","title":"Dead Man's Cove","author":"by Lauren St John","description":"When mysterious uncle Calvin rescues Laura Marlin from her gloomy life in an orphanage, she can't believe her luck! But she soon realises that her Cornish paradise is full of mysteries...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31762/wuthering-hearts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31762","title":"Wuthering Hearts","author":"by Kay Woodward","description":"A teen romance which is well-written and suffused with humour and a touch of pathos","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34758/9781471123832.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34758","title":"The Winter Place","author":"by Alexander Yates","description":"The line between family drama and folklore fantasy is blurred in this unique story of two orphaned siblings. Each is trying to get back some sense of a family after they are forced to move to Finland.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":390,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/390/","title":"Best of 2015: Children's books","list_description":"We've assembled a definitive booklist of the best children's books of 2015: Grandads - one escaping in a fighter plane and one with his own island, crayons returning home, a vegetable-eating dinosaur and a boy made of broccoli. These are just some of the fun and amazing stories that have made our best of 2015 list.  We're highlighting our favourite 12 books from the last 12 months, and many of the stories listed featured on our Best Book Guide earlier this year.  Look through our list of adventure stories, picture books and fun tales and see if any of these books will make your child's reading list      ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34657/9781406357509.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34657","title":"Albert and Little Henry","author":"by Jez Alborough","description":"Henry starts to feel left out and ignored when a new baby sibling arrives at home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34520/please-mr-panda.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34520","title":"Please Mr Panda","author":"by Steve Antony","description":"Children will love looking through the pages time and time again - and will also pick up on the story's simple but all-important message: good manners will get you anything, including doughnuts!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34514/zoom-trish-cooke.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34514","title":"Zoom!","author":"by Trish Cooke","description":"Hurricane Kieron and Rush Around Ria never stop. They run right through the day, rushing from breakfast to bedtime.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34525/astounding-broccoli-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34525","title":"The Astounding Broccoli Boy","author":"by Frank Cottrell Boyce","description":"Rory Rooney is unremarkable in almost everything, apart from his capacity to attract the attention of the school bully. But when he suddenly and spectacularly turns green, he becomes a superhero!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34547/grandads-island.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34547","title":"Grandad's Island","author":"by Benji Davies","description":"A subtle story about love and loss enhanced by delightful illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33934/where-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33934","title":"Where Bear?","author":"by Sophie Henn","description":"When a little boy's pet polar bear grows up, he's too big for the house, and has to be found a new home. But where?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34571/im-a-girl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34571","title":"I'm a Girl!","author":"by Yasmeen Ismail","description":"Like all good children's writers, Ismail has managed to bind the message in a picture book that is a delight in every aspect.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34689/9781847806840.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34689","title":"T-Veg: the story of a carrot-crunching dinosaur","author":"by Smriti Prasadam-Halls","description":"Reg dares to be different - he is a vegetarian T-Rex.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34724/chris-riddell-s-doodle-a-day.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34724","title":"Chris Riddell's Doodle-a-Day","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Chris Riddell's Doodle-A-Day features 366 illustration prompts, tips and artwork from award-winning illustrator Riddell, which will have you doodling every day for a year."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34526/dixie-oday-diamond-robbery.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34526","title":"Dixie O'Day and the Great Diamond Robbery","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"This gentle illustrated storybook is full of fun: with a short chapter for each day of the week, and lots of added extras, it makes perfect reading for newly-independent readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34734/9780007494019.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34734","title":"Grandpa's Great Escape","author":"by David Walliams","description":"Jack and his World War II flying-ace Grandpa hatch a daring plan for Grandpa to escape from his dreadful old-age home, Twilight Towers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34477/mystery-of-the-clockwork-sparrow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34477","title":"Mystery of the Clockwork Sparrow","author":"by Katherine Woodfine","description":"Mystery of the Clockwork Sparrow is a wonderful adventure full of friendship and heart, danger and mystery, and is not to be missed.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":393,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/393/","title":"10 top recent teen/YA romance books","list_description":"Love is a classic theme in teen and Young Adult fiction, so here are our top 10 romances from the last year or so.  CAUTION: MAY INCLUDE hot graffiti artists, sexy surfers, reincarnation, gangster families, hilarious, three-dimensional characters and a truckload of simmering chemistry… ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34855/9780141356099.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34855","title":"Simon vs. the Homo Sapiens Agenda","author":"by Becky Abertalli","description":"Simon finds himself in trouble when an email he sent ends up in the wrong hands; will his secret about his sexuality be revealed?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34644/9781471125300.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34644","title":"Night Owls","author":"by Jenn Bennett","description":"A promising artist meets a secretive and charming boy on the night bus, and her life takes a very different direction.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34539/its-about-love.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34539","title":"It's About Love","author":"by Steven Camden","description":"This gripping and thought provoking story slowly unfolds to reveal credible characters and events.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34854/9781848663428.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34854","title":"Air","author":"by Lisa Glass","description":"Iris travels far away to a surfing competition with her boyfriend, Zeke, but when they are both far away from what they know, Iris sees a different side to her boyfriend.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34606/23266378.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34606","title":"The Next Together","author":"by Lauren James","description":"A couple keep coming together time after time in order to change world events.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34484/read-me-like-a-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34484","title":"Read Me Like a Book","author":"by Liz Kessler","description":"Written 15 years ago, Kessler's novel is about 17-year-old Ash, discovering her sexuality and eventually coming out.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34567/darkmere.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34567","title":"Darkmere","author":"by Helen Maslin","description":"This dual-narrative romantic thriller links Kate's contemporary story with events from 200 years ago and the terrible fate of the castle's first mistress. For fans of Point Horror.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14-17"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34475/ill-give-you-the-sun.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34475","title":"I'll Give You the Sun","author":"by Jandy Nelson","description":"I'll Give You the Sun is a beautiful book about family, about choices, about art, and about growing up.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34258/sin-eaters-daughter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34258","title":"The Sin Eater's Daughter","author":"by Melinda Salisbury","description":"The Sin Eater's Daughter is a truly original fantasy set in a richly imagined world full of complex and complicated characters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":394,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/394/","title":"Galaxy Quick Reads 2016","list_description":"One in six adults of working age in the UK find reading difficult and may never pick up a book. People's reasons for not reading are varied: some people say they find books intimidating, that they struggle to find the time or that books are difficult or boring.  Quick Reads sets out to challenge these beliefs and to show that books and reading can be for everyone. Big name authors have written shorter, abridged versions of their books that are not as long as the originals so that they are easier to raed for less confident adults.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34818/y450-283.png","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34818","title":"The Double Club and Other Hercule Poirot Stories (Quick Reads)","author":"by Agatha Christie","description":"A man is found shot dead in a locked room; a wealthy banker disappears after posting a letter; a thief disappears with a haul of rubies and emeralds, and the men who discovered an ancient Eqyptian tomb are dying one..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34817/51dzlp4keql._sx327_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34817","title":"Too Good to be True (Quick Reads)","author":"by Ann Cleeves","description":"When his ex-wife Sarah asks him to look into the apparent suicide of local teacher, Detective Jimmy Perez is reluctant to get involved. But rumours are circulating that Sarah's husband was having an affair with the teacher."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34816/516peuiqhal._sx329_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34816","title":"A Baby at the Beach Cafe (Quick Reads)","author":"by Lucy Diamond","description":"Feisty Evie loves running her Cornish beach café and doesn't want to let go of the reins, even with a baby on the way. Helen, having moved to Cornwall to start a new life, is finding village life a little..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34819/6a010536b33b69970b01bb086ee8ba970d-250wi.png","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34819","title":"The Anniversary (Quick Reads)","author":"by Veronica Henry","description":"A collection of short stories about everything from an agoraphobic man who helps a woman who has been mugged, to a child that has survived her house being bombed in the war, there is a story for everyone to enjoy..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34820/516upxryf3l._sx323_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34820","title":"On the Rock (Quick Reads)","author":"by Andy McNab","description":"A secret operative paid in cash by the UK government to do the jobs they don't want to is commissioned to go to Gibraltar to stop a terrorist attack with other ex-SAS operatives."}]}
{"id":398,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/398/","title":"Easter bunnies, eggs and chicks","list_description":"Always on the lookout for pictures of bunny rabbits and baby chicks, we've dug out the best Easter and springtime-themed books - and a couple about chocolate, too. Take a look, but be warned... you'll want them all.  They're an ideal bundle of books for entertaining children over the bank holiday weekend, once they've calmed down from all the egg hunting (and eating).","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34931/lullaby-for-little-one.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34931","title":"A Lullaby for Little One","author":"by Dawn Casey","description":"This heartwarming rhyming story is beautifully illustrated by Charles Fuge - with the huggiest and loveliest bunnies imaginable.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-4"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34930/farewell-floppy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34930","title":"Farewell Floppy","author":"by Benjamin Chaud","description":"This funny and bittersweet story about growing up and friendship is a thoughtful and mature read for any child that loves animals - reassuring us all that we don't have to be too grown-up too soon.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35647/mr-bunny-s-chocolate-factory.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35647","title":"Mr Bunny's Chocolate Factory","author":"by Elys Dolan","description":"Mr Bunny gets taught a big lesson about how he should treat his employees when his chickens go on strike in this funny and sophisticated Easter egg tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6-8","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34934/small-bunny-s-blue.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34934","title":"Small Bunny’s Blue Blanket","author":"by Tatyana Feeney","description":"Small Bunny loves his blue blanket; it's perfect in every way. But one day, mummy insists on giving Blue Blanket a wash - and Small Bunny is worried that it will never be the same.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34937/hooray-for-hoppy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34937","title":"Hooray for Hoppy!","author":"by Tim Hopgood","description":"Tim Hopgood delights again with his signature heartwarming and thoughtful approach to concept books for young children. This one, a book about the senses, joins his equally fantastic previous books about colours, counting and shapes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34933/too-many-carrots.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34933","title":"Too Many Carrots","author":"by Katy Hudson","description":"Rabbit loves carrots so much that his whole burrow is full of them, and there's no room for him to sleep! Katy Hudson explores the themes of friendship and sharing in this charming and beautifully illustrated picture book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34932/going-on-an-egg-hunt.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34932","title":"We’re Going on an Egg Hunt","author":"by Laura Hughes","description":"This Easter-themed lift-the-flap book will delight little ones who are already excited about the big day - or discovering the joy of an egg hunt for the first time.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35648/the-chocolate-monster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35648","title":"WANTED: The Chocolate Monster","author":"by Pip Jones","description":"Guard your treats: the Chunk is on the loose and he's coming after your chocolate stash! This hilarious and chaotic picture book will delight anyone who loves biscuits, truffles, cakes, pudding... well, just about anything to do with chocolate, really.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34929/rabbits-don-t-lay-eggs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34929","title":"Rabbits Don’t Lay Eggs","author":"by Paula Metcalf and Cally Johnson-Isaacs","description":"Rupert the rabbit is lonely - but when he burrows under the wall, and bursts out of the ground next to Dora the duck, nobody seems that impressed with his attempts to fit in. A charming board book about recognising...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34936/hello-little-egg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34936","title":"Hello little Egg!","author":"by Puffin","description":"The first in a new series of picture books from the phenomenally successful children's TV series Puffin Rock is as cute and appealing as you would expect - and a great bedtime choice for any young fan of the show.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34928/higgly-hen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34928","title":"Higgly Hen","author":"by Axel Scheffler","description":"Oh dear - Higgly Hen has lost her chicks! This friendly farmyard board book is a must for Scheffler fans. The addition of a fun sound button will amuse toddlers and adds an extra element of play.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34935/warning-this-book-may-contain-rabbits.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34935","title":"Warning! This Book Contains Rabbits!","author":"by Tim Warnes","description":"Mole and The Lumpy-Bumpy Thing (which looks suspiciously like a crocodile) discover a magic hat. Even more surprisingly, the magic hat keeps producing bunnies - so many, in fact, that it starts to become a bit of a problem.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-6"}]}
{"id":399,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/399/","title":"St Patrick’s Day books for 9+","list_description":"Why not ring in St Patrick's Day this year by adding these books to your reading list?  Our St Patrick's Day booklist featuring titles about or set in the Emerald Isle features a range of books - from tales of time travel, magic, witches, natural disasters and mythical worlds to funny books about contemporary Ireland and short stories too.  We've picked out 11 titles for slightly older readers which could make you see Ireland in a whole new light... so which one will you be sampling first on 17 March?","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35444/the-making-of-mollie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35444","title":"The Making of Mollie","author":"by Anna Carey","description":"When Mollie discovers big sister Phyllis is part of the suffragette movement, she’s determined to do something to help. A sweet epistolary novel that makes the historical context accessible to modern audiences.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25630/scralett-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25630","title":"Scarlett","author":"by Cathy Cassidy","description":"Twelve-year-old Scarlett is a rebel: outrageous clothes, tongue stud, total contempt for authority and thinks she is totally cool.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32660/9781849390927-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32660","title":"The Great Unexpected","author":"by Sharon Creech","description":"In the little town of Blackbird Tree, friends and fellow orphans Naomi and Lizzie are startled when a strange boy, Finn, falls out of a tree.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28199/bogchild.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28199","title":"Bog Child","author":"by Siobhan Dowd","description":"This is a beautifully written coming-of-age tale, which deals with themes of mortality, peace and sacrifice.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33788/brilliants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33788","title":"Brilliant","author":"by Roddy Doyle","description":"A high-speed, high-adrenaline and highly surreal adventure which deals with the difficult topic of depression with a sensitive, humorous touch.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34465/cage-of-root.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34465","title":"Cage of Roots","author":"by Matt Green","description":"A gripping read with a feisty heroine, about time travel, loyalty, magic, betrayal and bravery which convincingly captures both contemporary and ancient Ireland.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34782/a-hollow-in-the-hills.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34782","title":"A Hollow in the Hills","author":"by Ruth Frances Long","description":"Izzy, who is only just getting used to her new powers, must try to stop a war breaking out. Hunted into the hills, she encounters an angel of death. This is a magical fantasy, brimming with suspense and adventure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34071/moone-boythe-blunder-years.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34071","title":"Moone Boy: The Blunder Years","author":"by Chris O'Dowd and Nick V Murphy","description":"Genuinely bizarre and ridiculously funny, this is one of the maddest books of the year.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34431/maloneys-magical-weather-box.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34431","title":"The Maloneys' Magical Weatherbox","author":"by Nigel Quinlan","description":"Mr Maloney is a Weatherman, an important and powerful man. It is his task to open the door of a magical telephone box that allows one season to leave and another to begin.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25195/the-new-policeman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25195","title":"The New Policeman","author":"by Kate Thompson","description":"JJ Byrne’s mum never has enough time and JJ decides to buy some for her birthday. This unusual quest leads him to Tir na n’Og, land of eternal youth, where time stands still.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34019/beyond-the-stars.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34019","title":"Beyond the Stars","author":"by Sarah Webb","description":"Twelve brand new stories from the cream of Irish writers and illustrators who jostle for space in this collection of inspirational writing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"}]}
{"id":400,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/400/","title":"Laugh Out Loud Book Awards shortlist","list_description":"We thought we'd use April's Funny Books month to have a laugh at the Lollies shortlisted books.  A bear in need of the toilet, a shy viking and a lonely slug make up the laughs on our Lollies list. So, chuckle, belly laugh and even RAOFL (roll around on the floor laughing) at our books perfect for ages 5-13.  You can even win all of the books","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34988/61dkzjkch0l._sx326_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34988","title":"The Parent Agency","author":"by David Baddiel","description":"Barry Bennett has a long list of things he dislikes about his parents, but what if the tables were turned and children could choose their parents? What would Barry do?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34990/petuniaperry_cvr_hr_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34990","title":"Petunia Perry and the Curse of the Ugly Pigeon","author":"by Pamela Butchart","description":"Petunia Perry is writing her memoir to fully explain why she's no longer friends with Cammy - and why, therefore, she and Cammy's band are unlikely to be the Next Big Thing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34987/9781848772410.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34987","title":"The Jolley-Rogers and the Cave of Doom","author":"by Jonny Duddle","description":"Nugget and her big brother Jim Lad Jolley-Rogers are off on an expedition with their pirate parents when they happen on the enchantingly dangerous Cave of Doom, and find themselves in a bit of a pickle.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34981/9781471120879.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34981","title":"I Need a Wee!","author":"by Sue Hendra and Paul Linnet","description":"Alan the bear is having a fantastic time at the funfair until he starts dancing in that unmistakeable way and his friends have to help him find somewhere he can have a wee. But unfortunately there's nowhere to go, until...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34799/badly-drawn-beth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34799","title":"Badly Drawn Beth","author":"by Knife & Packer","description":"A comic/storybook crossover where hilarious heroine, Beth, charts her survival of school, friends (best and worst), the dreaded family barbecue and other natural disasters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34985/61ufqceygel._sx258_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34985","title":"Thorfinn and the Awful Invasion","author":"by David MacPhail","description":"Thorfinn is possibly the nicest and politest Viking that ever lived, which is absolutely no good at all from the point of view of his dad, Chief Harald the Skull-Splitter, who wants him to Viking-up a bit more. So Harald...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34989/9780141359205.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34989","title":"Danger is Still Everywhere - Beware of the Dog","author":"by David O'Doherty and Chris Judge","description":"Docter Noel Zone is a Dangerologist, and he's here to tell you all about the dangers that exist in everyday life and how to avoid them - or, at least, recognise them, bubble wrap them and possibly most importantly of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34986/9781848668614.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34986","title":"Wilf The Mighty Worrier Saves the World","author":"by Georgia Pritchett","description":"Lots of things worry Wilf: peanut butter getting stuck to the roof of his mouth, stuffed animals, rollnecks and creepy crawlies with lots of legs. But one day, something worse than any of those things changes Wilf's life forever:","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34982/9781407158044.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34982","title":"Gracie Grabbit and the Tiger","author":"by Helen Stephens","description":"Gracie's daddy, Bobby Grabbit is very naughty, because he steals things from other people. When they go to the zoo, he even steals from the people and the animals there! Fortunately, Gracie's there to put things right and make sure...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34984/9781783441198.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34984","title":"Slug Needs a Hug","author":"by Jeanne Willis and Tony Ross","description":"Poor little slug never gets a hug from his mummy and he's starting to feel a bit sad about it, so he goes and asks all the other animals what he should do to be more appealing. They have plenty...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"}]}
{"id":401,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/401/","title":"Bookbuzz 2016","list_description":"Here are the Bookbuzz titles for 2016! This autumn, Year 7 and 8 students in Bookbuzz schools will be able to choose their own book to keep from this list - with something for every reader.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34990/petuniaperry_cvr_hr_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34990","title":"Petunia Perry and the Curse of the Ugly Pigeon","author":"by Pamela Butchart","description":"Petunia Perry is writing her memoir to fully explain why she's no longer friends with Cammy - and why, therefore, she and Cammy's band are unlikely to be the Next Big Thing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35033/river-of-ink-jacket-image.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35033","title":"River of Ink: Genesis","author":"by Helen Dennis","description":"River Boy is washed up on the banks of the River Thames, unable to find his voice or memory. The only things he can draw on are his visions and mysterious symbols. An exciting first book in a trilogy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35032/13-hours-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35032","title":"13 Hours","author":"by Narinder Dhami","description":"Twelve-year-old Anni never really questions why her frightened, ill mother won't leave their once grand but now dilapidated house - until, one day, her mum's worst fears are realised. An exciting, page-turning story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-13","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33754/cover-image.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33754","title":"Arrowhead","author":"by Ruth Eastham","description":"With its complex, well-defined characters and vivid setting, Arrowhead's narrative shares much of the same dark driving power that drives Viking mythology, in this thrilling time-slip novel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34831/repro_themanyworlds_cvr_001.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34831","title":"The Many Worlds of Albie Bright","author":"by Christopher Edge","description":"A son of two scientists, it's only natural that Albie uses quantum theory when his mum dies, to find a parallel universe where she's still alive. Considering the topics covered, it's a light read that even reluctant readers might be...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25230/cover-high-res.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25230","title":"The Day I Swapped My Dad For Two Goldfish","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"When Mike swaps his dad for his friend Nathan’s two goldfish his mum is not pleased. But when Mike tries to get his dad back, he finds he's already been traded for an electric guitar.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35031/9781781121887.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35031","title":"You Killed Me!","author":"by Keith Gray","description":"Toby wakes in the middle of the night and there's a ghost at the end of his bed. It's the ghost of a man with a hole in his head - a ghost claiming that Toby killed him.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34357/9781447264101.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34357","title":"The Lie Tree","author":"by Frances Hardinge","description":"This dark, exciting novel delves into the world of religion versus science in the late 1800s, and twists towards a thrilling climax.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34600/gorilla-dawn.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34600","title":"Gorilla Dawn","author":"by Gill Lewis","description":"This book tells the story of Imara, taken as a small child from her village when rebels raid it, and brainwashed into thinking that she has magical powers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34696/cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34696","title":"An Eagle in the Snow","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Stuck on a train, a boy listens to a stranger’s story about one moment that could have stopped World War II. A thought-provoking story that young history enthusiasts will especially welcome.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35028/cover-boffin-boy-and-the-poison-garden.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35028","title":"Boffin Boy and the Poison Garden","author":"by David Orme","description":"Both loyal Boffin Boy fans, and those discovering the series for the first time, will enjoy this outlandish adventure about a famous female scientist who is planting trees that look disturbingly like people and animals.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34543/mybrotherisasuperhero_cvr_hr_001.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34543","title":"My Brother is a Superhero","author":"by David Solomons","description":"Fast-moving, very funny, and gleefully mining the comic potential of the superhero genre, this is an inventive story about Luke: superhero expert and comic-lover.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34692/the-boy-who-sailed-the-ocean-in-an-armchair.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34692","title":"The Boy Who Sailed the Ocean in an Armchair","author":"by Lara Williamson","description":"Becket Rumsey decides to investigate the reasons behind the strange actions of some of the adults in his life. With the help of his brother Billy and his pet snail Brian, he uncovers some difficult truths - and some beautiful...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35034/i-am-malala-jacket-image.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35034","title":"I am Malala","author":"by Malala Yousafzai and Patricia McCormick","description":"This is the real life story of one of the most incredible and inspirational young people in the world. Reading this book might just change the way you think and feel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33733/gigantosaurus-front-cover-smaller-for-web.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33733","title":"Gigantosaurus","author":"by Jonny Duddle","description":"Wonderfully characterised and atmospheric illustrations complement humorous rhyming text in a story that will appeal to young dinosaur-lovers. Ideal for reading to groups as plenty of repetition will encourage youngsters to join in.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34927/bear-and-piano_pb_cvr.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34927","title":"The Bear and the Piano","author":"by David Litchfield","description":"A bear's piano playing makes him a huge star, but he misses the friends and family he has left behind. A moving tale of exploration and belonging from an exciting debut author-illustrator.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35027/leopards-snore-2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35027","title":"Leopard's Snore!","author":"by Emma Trithart","description":"A sturdy book with an appealing puppet that pokes her head through a hole in each page of the book, this is one of a series featuring different puppet characters, based loosely on the natural and spontaneous noises our bodies...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":402,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/402/","title":"14 of the best queens in fiction","list_description":"It's the Queen's 90th birthday, which is pretty impressive - and she is already our longest-serving monarch.  Children's books are full of varied and colourful portrayals of queens: some wield Evil Powers, while others save the day in interesting ways. Nearly all are characters you'll find hard to forget. So whether you want to celebrate Queen Elizabeth II's reign, powerful female role models, or just simply age and wisdom, take a look at our top fictional queens below. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35087/queens-knickers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35087","title":"The Queen’s Knickers","author":"by Nicholas Allan","description":"Let's face it: knickers are funny, and in The Queen's Knickers, Nicholas Allan makes them even funnier with this cheeky look inside the Queen's wardrobe.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4-6","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29641/snow-queen.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29641","title":"The Snow Queen","author":"by Hans Christian Andersen","description":"Lynch's vivid yet ethereal illustrations capture the balance between the wondrous and the recognisable in this powerful story about the redemptive nature of love and the passing of time.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32307/9781408320051-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32307","title":"Me, the Queen and Christopher","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"A warm, touching and funny tale of an unusual meeting with the Queen","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32521/a-midsummer-night-s-dream.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32521","title":"A Midsummer Night's Dream - Manga Shakespeare","author":"by Kate Brown","description":"Shakespeare's enduring story set in present-day Athens, but a present with a massive difference.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31274/cloudland.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31274","title":"Cloudland","author":"by John Burningham","description":"On the way home from a day spent high in the mountains, Albert trips and falls off into the clouds. His parents are very sad. Fortunately the Cloud Children come to his rescue...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30043/princess-diaries.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30043","title":"The Princess Diaries","author":"by Meg Cabot","description":"Mia hides her real feelings as she takes care of her disastrously disorganised mother, until her absent father drops a bombshell: She is actually Princess Amelia of Genovia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30314/alice-s-adventures-in-wonderland.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30314","title":"Alice's Adventures in Wonderland","author":"by Lewis Carroll","description":"This lovely edition illustrated by Helen Oxenbury won the Kate Greenaway Medal in 1999."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33296/bfg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33296","title":"The BFG","author":"by Roald Dahl","description":"The BFG stands for Big Friendly Giant, who unexpectedly spirits a little girl named Sophie out of bed, and into the land of the child-eating giants.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27394/at-the-house-of-the-magician.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27394","title":"At the House of the Magician","author":"by Mary Hooper","description":"Lucy discovers that she has second sight. This enables her to warn the Queen of danger, and leads to her covert employment as a spy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33305/the-lion-the-witch-the-wardrobe.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33305","title":"The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe","author":"by C S Lewis","description":"When Peter, Susan, Edmund and Lucy - step through a wardrobe door in the strange country house where they are staying, they find themselves in the land of Narnia.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34722/9781782952695.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34722","title":"Ellie's Magical Bakery: A Royal Tea for Royalty","author":"by Ellie Simmonds","description":"This is the fourth in the Ellie's Magical Bakery series. Ellie tries to win a trip to London by magically helping her relatives to succeed in a baking competition in order to swim in the Olympic Park Pool.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33484/2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33484","title":"The Queen & Mr Brown: A Day for Dinosaurs","author":"by James Francis Wilkins","description":"This picture book will make younger readers chuckle as the Queen and her corgi take a trip to London's Natural History Museum and ponder about what really made the dinosaurs die out."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31275/bumblebee.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31275","title":"Bumblebee","author":"by J. V. Wilson and Adrienne Kennaway","description":"The life cycle of a queen bumblebee starts on a sunny spring day when she sleepily leaves her winter home...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-9"}]}
{"id":403,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/403/","title":"Best bedtime books for newborns (0-2 months)","list_description":"We know that reading with your newborn baby at bedtime can be lots of fun. It's also a special time for snuggling up and sharing a story: it's important bonding time. However, we think the bedtime story's role in getting your little one to sleep can be the best part of a successful sleepy time routine. If you want to get your little one off to sleep, a soothing, sleepy, soporific story or poem will be a big help. Here are some of our top recommendations for sleepy time reads. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33957/teddy-bedtime.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33957","title":"Teddy Bedtime","author":"by Georgie Birkett","description":"Colourful, rhyming board book for bedtime.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35036/guess-how-much-i-love-you-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35036","title":"Guess How Much I Love You","author":"by Sam McBratney","description":"This modern classic is a wonderful story about love between a child and a parent, which is never too early to share with your baby. The repetitive text lends itself perfectly to a soothing bedtime read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0-3","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33623/april-2014-comp-bunny-brothers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33623","title":"I Heart Bedtime (Martha and the Bunny Brothers)","author":"by Clara Vulliamy","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35037/goodnight-moon-cover.png","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35037","title":"Goodnight Moon","author":"by Margaret Wise Brown & Clement Herd","description":"Margaret Wise Brown's comforting, rhythmical text makes Goodnight Moon a timeless picture book, which is known and loved around the world. This gentle bedtime story, which has lulled generations of children to sleep, is the perfect first book to share...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0-3","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"}]}
{"id":404,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/404/","title":"Best bedtime books for babies (2-12 months)","list_description":"We know that reading with your baby at bedtime can be lots of fun. And it's an opportunity for parents and carers to give outlandish accents and voices a try. Bedtime stories are the last part of an effective and good bedtime routine for your baby. A story to your child can send your little one off to sleep for longer. Here are some top recommendations for sleepy time reads. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30526/sweet-dreams-maisy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30526","title":"Sweet Dreams, Maisy","author":"by Lucy Cousins","description":"A favourite with so many babies, Maisy the mouse and her friends admire the beautiful sunset before Maisy goes home to settle down for bed. She reads Panda a story and then snuggles up in bed with her bear. Sweet...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4months+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29128/9781406331264-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29128","title":"Ten Little Fingers and Ten Little Toes","author":"by Mem Fox & Helen Oxenbury","description":"This charming first book is perfect for new arrivals.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35038/good-night-like-this-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35038","title":"Good Night Like This","author":"by Mary Murphy","description":"Beautifully illustrated and with special sparkly purple glitter for extra sleepy time loveliness, this calm and cuddly bedtime read is a must for any bedtime routine.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0-3","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24913/no-bed-without-ted.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24913","title":"No Bed without Ted","author":"by Nicola Smee","description":"Simple rhyming text and bright, colourful, endearing images of a little girl with her pets and toys make this familiar domestic tale of a missing ted into an appealing bedtime tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6 months+"}]}
{"id":405,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/405/","title":"Best bedtime books for toddlers (12-36 months)","list_description":"We know that reading with your toddler at bedtime can be lots of fun. It's also a time to help your child and relax into bedtime Books are an important part of a bedtime routine. So, If you want to get your little one off to sleep, a soothing, sleepy, soporific story or poem will be a big help. Here are some of our top recommendations for sleepy time reads. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35039/dozy-bear-and-the-secret-of-sleep-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35039","title":"Dozy Bear and the Secret of Sleep","author":"by Katie Blackburn","description":"This beautifully illustrated tale of Dozy Bear combines proven sleep and relaxation techniques with a lovely story, perfect for any parent who wants to turn nap time or bedtime into a calming experience.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0-3","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30573/peace-at-last2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30573","title":"Peace At Last","author":"by Jill Murphy","description":"The hour is late and Mr Bear is tired. But he just can't sleep - however hard he tries, all he can hear are the noises in the house.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31373/where-the-wild-things-are.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31373","title":"Where the Wild Things Are","author":"by Maurice Sendak","description":"First published in 1963, this classic picture book will fascinate both children and adults, evoking the fierce intensity of childhood"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34946/before-i-wake-up-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34946","title":"Before I Wake Up…","author":"by Britta Teckentrup","description":"Asleep and dreaming, the little girl in this book floats through a shadowy and beautiful blue-black world with her friend, a watchful lion, at her side. Britta Teckentrup is a gifted illustrator-writer, and this is a wonderful, poetic and stylish...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25526/cantusleeplilbear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25526","title":"Can't You Sleep, Little Bear?","author":"by Martin Waddell","description":"Little Bear just can't get to sleep because he is afraid of the dark. Big Bear is patient and brings bigger and bigger lanterns to keep away the darkness. Still Little Bear is afraid, so Big Bear takes him outside...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":406,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/406/","title":"Under the sea: watery reads for 8-12s","list_description":"It's National Bookstart Week (6-12 June)! Our theme is 'under the sea', and we want everyone to get into the habit of sharing stories, books and rhymes with young children every day.  But older children can join in with the fun, too. Below are our favourite sea-based books - so get ready to dive into an exciting world of mermaids, pirates, selkies and shipwrecks. Fin-tastic! ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34252/not-as-we-know-it.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34252","title":"Not As We Know It","author":"by Tom Avery","description":"Younger middle-grade readers desperate to get their teeth into something a little more serious will enjoy this sensitive story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35086/tamsin-and-the-deep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35086","title":"Tamsin and the Deep","author":"by Neill Cameron and Kate Brown","description":"A fantastic graphic novel from the team at children's comic The Phoenix, this is a page-turning adventure with a great main character in brave, athletic and reckless Tamsin.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33676/deep-blue-waterfire-saga-1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33676","title":"Deep Blue","author":"by Jennifer Donnelly","description":"The first book in the Waterfire saga, this magical undersea adventure takes its inspiration from the myth of Atlantis. The courageous teen mermaid heroines will especially appeal to girl readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25398/ingo-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25398","title":"Ingo","author":"by Helen Dunmore","description":"In Cornish legend, the Zenor mermaid fell in love with Mathew Trewhella and enticed him away to live in the sea with her forever...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34896/deep-water.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34896","title":"Deep Water","author":"by Lu Hersey","description":"Hugely evocative of the romantic and wild Cornish landscape, this modern retelling of the selkie myth is a magical and beautiful story about coming of age, transformation and belonging.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34814/adventures-steampunk-slippery-sea-monster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34814","title":"Adventures of the Steampunk Pirates: rise of the slippery sea monster","author":"by Gareth P Jones","description":"The Steampunk Pirates' treasure has been stolen by what they think is a sea monster. They make a plan to get their treasure back and uncover more mysteries than they bargained for in this rip-roaring tale of daring-do on the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29584/sirenssecret.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29584","title":"Emily Windsnap and the Siren's Secret","author":"by Liz Kessler","description":"If anyone can single-handedly bring peace, solve the mystery of the lost sirens, find her estranged grandparents and persuade Neptune to lift his banishment curse, it's Emily...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33269/9780192734556-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33269","title":"Oliver and the Seawigs","author":"by Philip Reeve and Sarah McIntyre","description":"Philip Reeve and Sarah McInytre have joined forces to create a wonderfully wacky nautical tale.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34706/9780330472012.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34706","title":"Ottoline at Sea","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"When Mr Munroe starts wearing the Bog Goggles he is led on an unexpected journey. On her quest to find her friend, Ottoline meets a host of different people and creatures, goes deep sea diving, and even flies in a...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":407,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/407/","title":"Best picture books about dads","list_description":"Father's Day 2017 is on Sunday, 18 June and we've got all the books you need - whether you're looking for some good present inspiration, or you're a dad who wants your child to realise just how great you are! ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33075/9781847388742-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33075","title":"Dustbin Dad","author":"by Peter Bently","description":"Dad eats everything - from half-eaten pies and unwanted sandwiches to soggy old bits of tomato and manky spaghetti. Then one day he bites off more than he can chew...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35092/amazing-daddy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35092","title":"Amazing Daddy","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"Unabashedly going straight for the heartstrings, this picture book looks at the father-child love between two every-day, house-dwelling pandas. It's full of lovely, funny details that never tips into schmaltziness.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35088/my-dad-is-brilliantr.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35088","title":"My Dad is Brilliant","author":"by Nick Butterworth","description":"This dad does everything well: from running like a cheetah to singing like a pop star. Quite simply, he's brilliant. This board book version of a much-loved story brims over with an adorable, young enthusiasm for dads everywhere.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35717/superdad-s-day-off.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35717","title":"Superdad’s Day Off","author":"by Phil Earle","description":"Stanley is an ordinary boy from an ordinary family, with one notable exception: his father is a superhero. With lively, colourful illustrations, short chapters and clear, well-spaced text, this very funny tale is ideal for reluctant readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35749/just-like-daddy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35749","title":"Just Like Daddy","author":"by Lucy Freegard","description":"A baby raccoon dreams of growing up to be just like Daddy in this cute, heart-warming book that's perfect for fathers to share with their little ones.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33041/9781406347302-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33041","title":"My Dad Thinks He's Funny","author":"by Katrina Germein","description":"What do you do when your Dad has a terrible sense of humour? And he repeats the same jokes over and over again?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35750/9781910959138.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35750","title":"My Daddy is a Silly Monkey","author":"by Dianne Hofmeyr and Carol Thompson","description":"A little girl imagines her busy Daddy as all sorts of animals during their packed day in a playful, warm story about a single father and his daughter.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35751/alfie-and-dad.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35751","title":"Alfie and Dad","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"This collection of three classic Alfie stories is a charming reminder of just how perfectly Shirley Hughes understands little ones.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26906/just-like-my-dad.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26906","title":"Just Like My Dad","author":"by David Melling","description":"A little lion cub loves and respects his dad. He wants to grow up to be just like him, with sharp teeth, long nails and a swishy tail.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35089/dad-used-to-be-so-cool.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35089","title":"My Dad Used To Be So Cool","author":"by Keith Negley","description":"Unfolding like a detective story, the son in this story sets out to discover if his dad was ever cooler than he seems right now. After all - the evidence is stacked against him!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35457/daddy-do-my-hair.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35457","title":"Daddy Do My Hair: Beth’s Twists","author":"by Tola Okogwu","description":"Softly rhyming text and glowing, illustrations in this calm, gentle book celebrate an apparently insignificant domestic ritual, which means everything to this father and daughter as they make time for each other.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34998/goodnight-spaceman.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34998","title":"Goodnight Spaceman","author":"by Michelle Robinson","description":"Opening with a special letter from the first British ESA astronaut Tim Peake, this rhyming picture book will inspire any child who gazes at the night sky, longing to explore space. Informative, exciting and beautifully illustrated.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"}]}
{"id":408,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/408/","title":"Books about refugees and asylum seekers","list_description":"Refugee Week takes place 15-25 June 2017.  Since asylum can be a confusing issue for children (and even adults), here are some books that explore what it really means to flee your home and have to start your life over.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29033/jackdawsumer.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29033","title":"Jackdaw Summer","author":"by David Almond","description":"Fate leads Liam to find an abandoned baby and as a result his life becomes entwined with that of Oliver, an African boy seeking asylum and Crystal, an emotionally damaged girl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35378/abidjan-to-gare-du-nord.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35378","title":"Alpha: Abidjan to Gare du Nord","author":"by Bessora & Barroux","description":"A powerful, terrible and essential story, Alpha should be required reading for everyone. The graphic novel highlights the terror and hopelessness experienced by someone forced to leave their own country in search of a future.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34774/refuge.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34774","title":"Refuge","author":"by Anne Booth","description":"This beautiful book follows Mary, Joseph and baby Jesus as they flee into Egypt as refugees. The gorgeous drawings and Booth's sparse, poetic words make this a Christmas book to treasure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24753/give-me-shelter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24753","title":"Give Me Shelter","author":"by Edited by Tony Bradman","description":"Told through the eyes of children, this moving collection of short stories focuses on the experiences of asylum seekers from all over the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35096/the-bone-sparrows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35096","title":"The Bone Sparrow","author":"by Zana Fraillon","description":"Focusing on a friendship between two young refugees, The Bone Sparrow is one of those rare, special books that will break your heart with its honesty and beauty - but is ultimately hopeful and uplifting.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34392/azzi-in-between.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34392","title":"Azzi in Between","author":"by Sarah Garland","description":"This is a moving tale of a refugee family told in graphic novel style and so appealing to a wide range of younger readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31485/9780857560087-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31485","title":"In The Sea There Are Crocodiles","author":"by Fabio Geda","description":"First published in Italian last year, the story of Enaiatollah Akbari's journey from Afghanistan to Italy has now been translated into English","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28743/the-island.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28743","title":"The Island","author":"by Armin Greder","description":"This chilling picture book about prejudice, intolerance and the plight of refugees will spark classroom discussions with older readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25813/orangesinnomansland.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25813","title":"Oranges in No Man's Land","author":"by Elizabeth Laird","description":"Ayesha and her young brothers find themselves refugees in a bombed out flat in Beirut with only an elderly grandmother to care for them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35531/welcome-to-nowhere.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35531","title":"Welcome to Nowhere","author":"by Elizabeth Laird","description":"Omar doesn't know much about politics, nor does he care, however, when his older brother, Musa, throws his lot in with the student opposition to the government, everything changes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35758/story-like-the-wind.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35758","title":"A Story Like The Wind","author":"by Gill Lewis","description":"Gill Lewis’s brief but beautiful story is rich in wonder, as well as being a timely reminder of the refugee crisis. Mixed with an exotic story of wild horses and a Dark Lord that rules a kingdom in peril, this...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35831/my-name-is-not-refugee.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35831","title":"My Name is not Refugee","author":"by Kate Milner","description":"When they reach a safe place, a little boy must remember that although children call him Refugee, that is not his real name. Clear, moving illustrations complement this simple, touching book that explains the refugee crisis in an accessible way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35701/a-dangerous-crossing.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35701","title":"A Dangerous Crossing","author":"by Jane Mitchell","description":"This heartbreaking story depicts the reality of fleeing war, as told by a 13-year-old boy. Not only is her story told with compassion and understanding, it is also a timely and vital read. Deserving of a place on every school...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29733/the-silence-seeker.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29733","title":"The Silence Seeker","author":"by Ben Morley","description":"This story explores the vibrancy and diversity of city life through gritty, yet child-friendly illustrations that are beautifully atmospheric and evocative.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30888/shadow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30888","title":"Shadow","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"This is a candid exploration of the injustices of war, at home and away, and an unflinching account of the treatment of asylum seekers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31519/9780340969939-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31519","title":"The Arrival","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"In this unusual book, we follow a young man as he packs his bags and leaves his family to go and start a new life in another country","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32405/9781848530836-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32405","title":"Now is the Time for Running","author":"by Michael Williams","description":"Deo's life is destroyed when government forces kill his family. Together with his brother Innocent, he flees his village in search of his father, encountering hardship and hostility along the way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":409,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/409/","title":"Judith Kerr booklist","list_description":" To honour the BookTrust Lifetime Achievement Award winner we've highlighted some of Judith's best tales.  As well as the classic Mog books and The Tiger That Came to Tea, Judith has had several books published in the last few years.  Reminisce over this list and share these books with your children. There's something for everyone, and usually there's an animal involved somewhere. See how Mister Cleghorn deals with a new pet seal and discover how an elderly woman goes on adventures with her husband after he passes away.  ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24799/mog-the-forgetful-cat.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24799","title":"Mog the Forgetful Cat","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Reformatted and reissued, Mog the Forgetful Cat has lost none of its gentle charm.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24800/the-tiger-who-came-to-tea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24800","title":"The Tiger Who Came to Tea","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Sophie and her Mummy are having tea in the kitchen when in walks a hungry tiger who asks to stay to tea.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29559/one-night-in-the-zoo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29559","title":"One Night in the Zoo","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"This rhyming counting book is set in a zoo and follows the antics of the various animal inhabitants once night falls.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31556/9780007388110-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31556","title":"My Henry","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Unconventional subject matter for the very young is presented with gentle humour and a sense of great joy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31956/9780007274772-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31956","title":"When Hitler Stole Pink Rabbit","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Partly autobiographical, this is first of the internationally acclaimed trilogy by Judith Kerr telling the unforgettable story of a Jewish family fleeing from Germany at the start of the World War II."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34725/mogs_christmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34725","title":"Mog's Christmas","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"The house is full of strange bustling, there are new noises and new smells, and where is that tree going? Disconcerted by all the unusual activities, Mog escapes to the roof, and there she stays…until, unexpectedly, she returns with a..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35135/9780007149698.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35135","title":"Goodbye Mog","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Mog helps a new kitten settle into life with the Thomas family afer she passes away.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35136/9780007171323.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35136","title":"Mog and the Baby","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Mog's peaceful day is shattered when a baby comes to visit.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35137/9780008171179.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35137","title":"Mog and Me","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Follow Mog and a little boy through their busy day. From when they wake up in the morning with a big stretch until when they fall fast asleep curled up together","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35138/9780007586776.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35138","title":"The Crocodile Under the Bed","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Matty is sick, and very sad because he's too sick to go to the Queen's birthday party! But when he gets an unexpected visitor, it seems that Matty might not miss out after all...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35139/9780008157302.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35139","title":"Mister Cleghorn's Seal","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"What do you do if you find an abandoned seal pup on a rock in the middle of the sea? Well, take it home with you to your flat, of course","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"}]}
{"id":410,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/410/","title":"If you love Roald Dahl books...","list_description":"...why not try one of these hilarious books from some of our favourite funny authors?","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32845/9780552566070-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32845","title":"Darcy Burdock","author":"by Laura Dockrill","description":"Ten-year-old Darcy Burdock is one of life's noticers, spotting the extraordinary in the everyday and coming up with ideas for wild and wonderful stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34858/superhero-street.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34858","title":"Superhero Street","author":"by Phil Earle","description":"Superhero Street is a heartwarming and laugh-out-loud read that celebrates mums as the everyday superheroes they are. Sara Ogilvie's illustrations add an even more warm, hilarious background to Earle's realistic family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35108/beaky-malone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35108","title":"World’s Greatest Liar: Beaky Malone","author":"by Barry Hutchison","description":"What happens when a compulsive liar is suddenly unable to tell anything but the truth? Misunderstanding and mayhem, certainly - but also plenty of laugh-out-loud moments and some unexpected consequences.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31784/9781406336832-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31784","title":"I Want My Hat Back","author":"by Jon Klassen","description":"A bear sets out in search of his hat - he loves his hat and he wants it back","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34989/9780141359205.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34989","title":"Danger is Still Everywhere - Beware of the Dog","author":"by David O'Doherty and Chris Judge","description":"Docter Noel Zone is a Dangerologist, and he's here to tell you all about the dangers that exist in everyday life and how to avoid them - or, at least, recognise them, bubble wrap them and possibly most importantly of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34986/9781848668614.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34986","title":"Wilf The Mighty Worrier Saves the World","author":"by Georgia Pritchett","description":"Lots of things worry Wilf: peanut butter getting stuck to the roof of his mouth, stuffed animals, rollnecks and creepy crawlies with lots of legs. But one day, something worse than any of those things changes Wilf's life forever:","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34732/pugs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34732","title":"Pugs of the Frozen North","author":"by Philip Reeve and Sarah McIntyre","description":"A race to the far north among some very unconventional competitors and their vehicles. A winning combination of text, image, humour and sadness.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35112/king-flashypants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35112","title":"King Flashypants and the Evil Emperor","author":"by Andy Riley","description":"When nine-year-old King Edwin runs out of pocket money, he can no longer buy his subjects Friday chocolate. The peasants revolt and elect a new leader, Evil Emperor Nurbison. This slapstick tale will appeal to those who love something a...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35118/gym-teacher-is-alien-overlord.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35118","title":"My Gym Teacher is an Alien Overlord","author":"by David Solomons","description":"Ever had that funny feeling your gym teacher is an alien hell-bent on destruction? Well, so has 11-year-old Luke. This is a funny, sweet, surreal and madcap adventure, full of laughs and thrills.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34964/awful-auntie.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34964","title":"Awful Auntie","author":"by David Walliams","description":"A rude, witty and irreverent illustrated story in which an orphaned girl tries to escape from her murderous auntie and solve the mystery of her parents’ death. It's just a bit scary and fantastic fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-13"}]}
{"id":411,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/411/","title":"Books about depression","list_description":"Reading can be a wonderful way to explore emotions or tricky situations. If you're a parent or carer with depression, the fiction books below may help your child talk about their feelings and understand what's going on a bit better. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34806/spooks-and-scooters.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34806","title":"Spooks and Scooters","author":"by Elen Caldecott","description":"When Flora and Sylvie's holiday with dad is cancelled, they are determined to discover who or what is responsible. Amid the excitement of unravelling the mystery, Caldecott sympathetically shows us families coming to terms with change.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-10"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34897/aubrey-and-the-terrible-yoot.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34897","title":"Aubrey and the Terrible Yoot","author":"by Horatio Clare","description":"This fabulously illustrated book addresses the difficult subject of parental depression, at once describing the horror of Aubrey’s dad’s experience but also remaining upbeat and full of surreal humour.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35093/library-of-lemons.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35093","title":"A Library of Lemons","author":"by Jo Cotterill","description":"Believable, memorable, charming and moving, fans of Jacqueline Wilson's domestic dramas will enjoy this bittersweet story of a family finding their feet in the next chapter of their lives.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31957/9781849393966-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31957","title":"Lolly Luck","author":"by Ellie Daines","description":"Lolly has always been lucky but a series of catastrophes at home threaten both her family life and her experience at school","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33788/brilliants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33788","title":"Brilliant","author":"by Roddy Doyle","description":"A high-speed, high-adrenaline and highly surreal adventure which deals with the difficult topic of depression with a sensitive, humorous touch.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33801/boy-in-the-tower.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33801","title":"The Boy in the Tower","author":"by Polly Ho-Yen","description":"Taking place in a believable urban, multicultural environment that will be familiar to many young readers, Polly Ho-Yen's debut is an impressively moving and thought-provoking story that will touch children and adults alike.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34079/colourthief.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34079","title":"The Colour Thief","author":"by Andrew Fusek Peters and Polly Peters","description":"Drawing on personal experiences of living in a family blighted by depression, this unusual, yet important, book may help youngsters to make sense of an illness they cannot see.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31520/9780734411372-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31520","title":"The Red Tree","author":"by Shaun Tan","description":"The perfect blend of words and pictures, this is a wonderful book to share with anyone suffering from depression or uncertainty","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30105/illustratedmum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30105","title":"The Illustrated Mum","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"This is a moving yet unsentimental account of two children coming to terms with their mother’s depression, mental instability and alcohol problem.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"}]}
{"id":412,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/412/","title":"Great children's books for the summer holidays","list_description":"The summer holidays are here, which means picnics in the park, getaways to the beach and lazing in the back garden (weather permitting). So we've put together a list of great summer books for your young children.  If you want to soak up the sun with your little one then take one or two of these books out with you. You can have a read in between having lunch and playing on the swings.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35148/9781909263918.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35148","title":"Smart About Sharks","author":"by Owen Davey","description":"Presenting an ever-popular topic, this fantastic, high quality illustrated book is fascinating and attractive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35150/9781783702398.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35150","title":"The Perfect Picnic","author":"by Ciara Flood","description":"Squirrel and Mole do everything together, including going on picnics. Squirrel is determined that the picnic will be perfect, and that means trying out quite a few different places! Unfortunately, the picnic gets lost on the way, but the other...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34923/hector-and-hummingbird.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34923","title":"Hector and Hummingbird","author":"by Nicholas John Frith","description":"The story of Hector and Hummingbird is a lovely one for children with - sometimes irritating but always lovable - little brothers and sisters. The 1950s style and colouring of this fantastic picture book is very appealing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34981/9781471120879.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34981","title":"I Need a Wee!","author":"by Sue Hendra and Paul Linnet","description":"Alan the bear is having a fantastic time at the funfair until he starts dancing in that unmistakeable way and his friends have to help him find somewhere he can have a wee. But unfortunately there's nowhere to go, until...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35146/9780723299868.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35146","title":"Pass It On","author":"by Sophy Henn","description":"The little girl in this bright, happy book embraces the simple act of passing on smiles, laughs, chuckles and whoops to others.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34873/the-cloudspotter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34873","title":"The Cloudspotter","author":"by Tom McLaughlin","description":"Franklin was called 'The Cloudspotter' - and he didn't want to share his clouds with anyone. That's why he pops the infuriating Scruffy Dog into a hot-air balloon and lets her fly away. A charming story about a lonely little...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34944/we-are-not-frogs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34944","title":"We Are Not Frogs!","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Alice and Jago are playing in granny's garden one day when they find lots of toads in the long grass. Michael Morpurgo's lovely nature tale and Sam Usher's sensitive and funny illustrations bring this story hoppingly alive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35147/9781848692886.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35147","title":"Bee","author":"by Britta Teckentrup","description":"This bee-autiful and special book takes children on a poetic journey through the bee's day.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35078/harold-s-hungry-eyes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35078","title":"Harold’s Hungry Eyes","author":"by Kevin Waldron","description":"Young readers will love this story of hungry Harold the dog, and have a great time spotting all the original places that food has replaced normal everyday items. Kevin Waldron's artwork is bright and colourful with a quirky, modern use...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"}]}
{"id":413,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/413/","title":"Foody booklist for World Baking Day","list_description":"To celebrate World Baking Day, we've sieved together some great baking book recommendations to get you in the foody mood.  With the zest of dragons, a hint of Chris Riddell and garnished with a bit royalty, this booklist is perfect for children aged 4-10 years old.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35152/bear-cub-bakers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35152","title":"The Bear Cub Bakers","author":"by Caroline Baxter","description":"A group of young bear cubs go to Miss Betsy Bear's baking school for a week of fun in the kitchen - but who will take home the golden trophy for best baker at the end of the week?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35202/9781444919882.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35202","title":"Hugless Douglas and the Great Cake Bake","author":"by David Melling","description":"Douglas wakes up to find sticky honey footprints leading from his cupboard to the tree outside, where the sheep are collecting everything they need to bake honey cakes. Problem is, Douglas needs to put honey on everything he eats, otherwise...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35141/caramel-hearts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35141","title":"Caramel Hearts","author":"by E R Murray","description":"One day, 14-year-old Liv discovers recipes written in her mother's handwriting, and this sets her off on a journey towards self-discovery and reconciliation. A beautifully told story about what it takes to get through hard times.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35203/9781408839560.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35203","title":"The Great Dragon Bake Off","author":"by Nicola O'Byrne","description":"Flamie Oliver is a terrifying dragon with a secret: he's passionate about pastry! But he must kidnap a princess and eat her in order to pass Ferocious Dragon Academy!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34087/goth-girl-and-the-fete-worse-than-deaths.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34087","title":"Goth Girl and the Fete Worse than Death","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Chris Riddell's third book in the Goth Girl series intrigues and delights with a cakey combination of adventure, love and webbed footnotes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34722/9781782952695.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34722","title":"Ellie's Magical Bakery: A Royal Tea for Royalty","author":"by Ellie Simmonds","description":"This is the fourth in the Ellie's Magical Bakery series. Ellie tries to win a trip to London by magically helping her relatives to succeed in a baking competition in order to swim in the Olympic Park Pool.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35070/can-i-eat-that.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35070","title":"Can I Eat That?","author":"by Joshua David Stein and Julia Rothman","description":"A quirky combination of fact and fun, this distinctive picture book about food poses questions that inquisitive children typically ask, such as: 'If I eat jelly and I eat fish, can I eat jellyfish?' Stylish, witty and informative.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34849/bakers-magic.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34849","title":"Baker’s Magic","author":"by Diane Zahler","description":"An orphaned girl with a talent for baking must use courage, intelligence and just a little bit of magic to save her country from a wicked mage in this fantasy adventure for younger readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"}]}
{"id":414,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/414/","title":"Books to share with older children","list_description":"Reading together doesn’t have to stop once your children can read for themselves – it’s still fun to read aloud to older children!   Here are a selection of great stories to share with 8-12s that you’re going to love, too...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34988/61dkzjkch0l._sx326_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34988","title":"The Parent Agency","author":"by David Baddiel","description":"Barry Bennett has a long list of things he dislikes about his parents, but what if the tables were turned and children could choose their parents? What would Barry do?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30249/httyd_jacket.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30249","title":"How to Train Your Dragon","author":"by Cressida Cowell","description":"Hiccup Horrendous Haddock III was an incredible sword-fighter, dragon-whisperer and the greatest Viking hero who ever lived.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35173/malkin-moonlight.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35173","title":"Malkin Moonlight","author":"by Emma Cox","description":"Malkin Moonlight is given his wonderful name by the Moon, who also tells the tiny black kitten that he is destined for great things. This charming, magical story is beautifully written and reads like a classic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34348/demolition-dad.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34348","title":"Demolition Dad","author":"by Phil Earle","description":"Demolition Dad is sure to delight children, and adults, of all ages and is perfect for fans of David Walliams and Roald Dahl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35105/sweet-pizza.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35105","title":"Sweet Pizza","author":"by G R Gemin","description":"In a small Welsh town, a young man gets to reconnect to his Italian roots and explore his entrepreneurial streak, as he exchanges the joys of fried chicken and chips for fresh espresso and pasta puttanesca.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11-15"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35109/the-emergency-zoo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35109","title":"The Emergency Zoo","author":"by Miriam Halahmy","description":"An unusual and atmospheric story set in the run-up to World War II. As London's children prepare for evacuation to the countryside, they are horrified to discover that their beloved pets are due to be put down.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35030/girl-of-ink-and-stars.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35030","title":"The Girl of Ink and Stars","author":"by Kiran Millwood Hargrave","description":"When her closest friend disappears into the island's Forgotten Territories, Isabella Riosse volunteers to guide the search. A stunning debut, full of myth, magic and mapmaking.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34989/9780141359205.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34989","title":"Danger is Still Everywhere - Beware of the Dog","author":"by David O'Doherty and Chris Judge","description":"Docter Noel Zone is a Dangerologist, and he's here to tell you all about the dangers that exist in everyday life and how to avoid them - or, at least, recognise them, bubble wrap them and possibly most importantly of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34726/the-wolf-wilders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34726","title":"The Wolf Wilder","author":"by Katherine Rundell","description":"When the murderous hostility of the Russian Army threatens her very existence, Feo is left with no option but to go on the run. What follows is a story of revolution and adventure, about standing up for the things you...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32037/dark-lord.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32037","title":"Dark Lord: The Teenage Years","author":"by Jamie Thomson","description":"The Dark Lord falls to earth, crash-landing in a suburban car park in the body of a teenage boy, spitting out poisonous mucus","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":415,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/415/","title":"Children's books about dogs","list_description":"They're man's best friend, so we had to dedicate a booklist to them. This booklist features classic reads as well as newer books, all about different dogs and canines. Although there may be a couple of cats thrown into the mix too.  Have a look at our great collection of books featuring dogs for children aged three and older.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33665/walk-in-the-park.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33665","title":"A Walk in the Park","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"A welcome republication for an Anthony Browne classic from 1977. Two children from very different backgrounds (and their dogs) make friends where their parents cannot.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30536/hairy-maclary.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30536","title":"Hairy Maclary from Donaldson's Dairy","author":"by Lynley Dodd","description":"This hilarious rhyming story follows Hairy Maclary from Donaldson's Dairy, as he sets off for a walk in town","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34330/dog-called-flow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34330","title":"A Dog Called Flow","author":"by Pippa Goodhart","description":"This is a powerful story that clearly leads its reader through the struggles of dyslexia. But it is also an adventurous tale of a boy and his dog and the powerful friendship between them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34401/space-dog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34401","title":"Space Dog","author":"by Mini Grey","description":"Visually and graphically inventive, packed with tongue-in-cheek humour and witty details, this comic-style picture book delights in subverting the conventions of epic space adventure!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32480/9781406332254-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32480","title":"Oh No, George!","author":"by Chris Haughton","description":"George is a dog with a big personality and he LOVES cake, rubbish bins and chasing Cat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33297/tintin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33297","title":"The Adventures of Tintin","author":"by Hergé","description":"Resourceful junior reporter Tintin embarks on a series of exciting international adventures, accompanied by his faithful dog Snowy, in this favourite series.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24861/9781862308053-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24861","title":"Dogger","author":"by Shirley Hughes","description":"When Dave loses his favourite toy, Dogger, he is desolate.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28889/kipperbday.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28889","title":"Kipper's Birthday","author":"by Mick Inkpen","description":"Kipper is working hard preparing for his birthday. He bakes a very interesting cake to share with his friends and makes beautiful invitations but is too tired to deliver them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32348/9781407108629-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32348","title":"Dogs Go Shopping","author":"by Sharon Rentta","description":"Max and Mummy are shopping for a birthday present for Daddy, and where do dogs go shopping? In the ‘Just for Dogs’ shopping centre of course!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30986/claude-in-the-city.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30986","title":"Claude in the City","author":"by Alex T Smith","description":"Claude is no ordinary dog - he leads an extraordinary life! When Mr and Mrs Shinyshoes set off for work, Claude heads for the city, where pigeons, beret shops and robberies await.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29100/fleabg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29100","title":"Fleabag","author":"by Helen Stephens","description":"A small, scruffy dog visits the park every day and looks longingly at the other dogs who all have people to take for walks.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35084/philomena-jessie-hall.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35084","title":"Philomena - The Cat Who Thinks She’s a Dog","author":"by Jessie Wall","description":"Philomena is a cat with an identity crisis. Having been brought up with a puppy, she is now convinced she is actually a dog herself. The plot is simple but fun, and carries a gentle message about being yourself.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"}]}
{"id":417,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/417/","title":"Books about books and reading","list_description":"To celebrate the release of Oliver Jeffers and Sam Winston's wonderful new book about the power of reading, A Child of Books, on 1 September, we put together this booklist of other fabulous picture books that celebrate the joy of reading and the wonderful places books can take you.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35241/51oc6x2cbfl._sx258_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35241","title":"Library Lion","author":"by Michelle Knudsen","description":"One day, a lion turns up at the library and no-one knows quite what to do - not even Miss Merriweather, the head librarian, who has rules for most things. However, the lion turns out to be rather a nice...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29895/babies-love-books.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29895","title":"Babies Love Books","author":"by Laurence Anholt","description":"Given the chance, babies certainly do love books and the familiar scenes depicted amidst these lively pages show how and where opportunities to share a book present themselves.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34947/wrong-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34947","title":"We’re In The Wrong Book!","author":"by Richard Byrne","description":"A picture book that thinks outside the box in the most literal of ways, this funny story about a boy and a girl interacting directly with different genres of childrens' books is a lovely one to talk about with little...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33951/bears-don-t-read.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33951","title":"Bears Don't Read","author":"by Emma Chichester Clark","description":"Bears Don't Read is a wonderfully engaging picture book about the joy of reading and how much fun it can be to help others.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35177/the-detective-dog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35177","title":"The Detective Dog","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Detective Dog Nell is famed for her sleuthing skills in this witty detail-packed book, full of exuberant rhyming couplets - perfect for sharing and reading aloud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34945/are-you-sitting-comfortably.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34945","title":"Are You Sitting Comfortably?","author":"by Leigh Hodgkinson","description":"The little boy in this book is looking for the perfect place to read his book - but nothing he finds is quite right. Hodgkinson's recognisably quirky and appealing rhyming text and illustration celebrates the enduring importance of reading together.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25757/bookeating-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25757","title":"The Incredible Book Eating Boy","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"Henry loves books. However, his pleasure isn't derived from reading them but from eating them instead, and the more he eats, the smarter he gets.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35240/3035.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35240","title":"A Child of Books","author":"by Oliver Jeffers and Sam Winston","description":"A little girl sails across the sea of her imagination to ask a little boy to come away with her to find stories again, worried that some people in the world have forgotten them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25804/lulu-loves-library.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25804","title":"Lulu Loves the Library","author":"by Anna McQuinn","description":"Lulu has her library card, her rucksack full of borrowed books, and a big smile on her face, because it's Tuesday – and on Tuesdays Lulu and her mummy go to the library","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34960/nibbles-the-book-monster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34960","title":"Nibbles: The Book Monster","author":"by Emma Yarlett","description":"This is a story about a little monster called… Nibbles. And with that, he nibbles his way right out of the book! This really exciting reading experience is sure to be a hit with the whole family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6","interest_age":"Interest level: 3"}]}
{"id":419,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/419/","title":"Roald Dahl books","list_description":"We wanted to celebrate the Roald Dahl centenary by putting a selection of 'wondercrump' books Roald Dahl has written into one perfect list.  Go on an adventure and get caught up in the nostalgia of The Witches ('It doesn't matter who you are or what you look like, so long as somebody loves you'), James and the Giant Peach ('Come right up close to me and I will show you something wonderful') and Matilda ('If you are good life is good').  You've probably read all these books several times already, but you can never get tired of these individual pieces of magic.  Win a Matilda DVD and tote bag  Discover 10 things you didn't know about Roald Dahl  View our Roald Dahl booklist  Learn words from the Roald Dahl dictionary","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24385/james-and-the-giant-peach.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24385","title":"James and the Giant Peach","author":"by Roald Dahl","description":"Through a series of peculiar and magical happenings, James finds himself on an adventure inside a giant peach with a bunch of friendly giant insects for travelling companions.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33296/bfg.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33296","title":"The BFG","author":"by Roald Dahl","description":"The BFG stands for Big Friendly Giant, who unexpectedly spirits a little girl named Sophie out of bed, and into the land of the child-eating giants.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30283/charlie-chocolatefactory.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30283","title":"Charlie and the Chocolate Factory","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"Roald Dahl's wicked sense of humour is perfectly in evidence in this marvellously imaginative classic story, which has been loved by generations of children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33343/the-witches.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33343","title":"The Witches","author":"by Roald Dahl","description":"Real witches disguise themselves as lovely ladies, when secretly they want to squish and squelch all the wretched children they despise.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34099/the-twits.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34099","title":"The Twits","author":"by Roald Dahl","description":"Mr and Mrs Twit are extremely nasty, so the Muggle-Wump monkeys and the Roly-Poly bird hatch an ingenious plan to give them just the ghastly surprise they deserve!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25325/revoltingrhymes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25325","title":"Revolting Rhymes","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This is an hilarious collection of some well-loved fairy tales, cleverly reinvented by Roald Dahl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25342/matilda.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25342","title":"Matilda","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This modern fairy-tale with a brilliantly inspiring young heroine is one of Roald Dahl's best loved stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29944/the-vicar-of-nibbleswicke.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29944","title":"The Vicar of Nibbleswicke","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This is the highly amusing tale of Reverend Lee, who does not realise that his dyslexia is affecting his sermons.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"}]}
{"id":420,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/420/","title":"Books about friendship","list_description":"'We'll be Friends Forever, won't we, Pooh?' asked Piglet. 'Even longer,' Pooh answered.  Can you imagine Pooh without Piglet? Or Frodo without Sam?  Here are some children's books that celebrate the power, fun and wonder of friendship.  After all, we can all do a bit more when we're supported by our friends. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27570/9780340944950-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27570","title":"Skellig","author":"by David Almond","description":"Exploring a ramshackle garage with his new-found friend, Mina, Michael discovers a strange, magical creature.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28476/noughts-and-crosses.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28476","title":"Noughts and Crosses","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"Callum is a Nought but his best friend Sephy is a Cross - the daughter of one of the most influential politicians in the country.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24389/secretgarden.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24389","title":"The Secret Garden","author":"by Frances Hodgson Burnett","description":"When the spoilt and bad-tempered Mary is orphaned at the age of ten, she is sent from India to live with her hunchback uncle on the Yorkshire Moors.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25342/matilda.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25342","title":"Matilda","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This modern fairy-tale with a brilliantly inspiring young heroine is one of Roald Dahl's best loved stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35258/colin-and-lee-carrot-and-pea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35258","title":"Colin and Lee: Carrot and Pea","author":"by Morag Hood","description":"Colin is a carrot, and Lee is a pea. An amusing and deceptively simple look at friendship and difference, this is a lovely book for young readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4-5","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25161/lost-found.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25161","title":"Lost and Found","author":"by Oliver Jeffers","description":"Once there was a sad, lonely penguin who appeared at the door of a young boy. The boy decided he must be lost, so he set off to find his home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29291/diary-of-a-wimpy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29291","title":"Diary of a Wimpy Kid","author":"by Jeff Kinney","description":"Greg Heffley is a normal American kid, albeit one with a habit of getting into (and out of) trouble.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33284/winnie-the-pooh.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33284","title":"Winnie-the-Pooh","author":"by A A Milne","description":"No child's library could be complete without A A Milne's stories about Pooh, Christopher Robin and their friends in the Hundred Acre Wood.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30267/9780747558194-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30267","title":"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone","author":"by J K Rowling","description":"After the misery of life with his ghastly aunt and uncle, Harry Potter is delighted to have the chance to embark on an exciting new life at the Hogwart's School of Wizardry and Witchcraft.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33346/9780261103573-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33346","title":"The Fellowship of The Ring","author":"by J R R Tolkien","description":"The first part of J R R Tolkien's epic masterpiece The Lord of the Rings, this is the story of young hobbit Frodo Baggins, who finds himself faced with an immense and terrible duty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33290/charlottes-web.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33290","title":"Charlotte's Web","author":"by E B White","description":"This is the tale of how a little girl named Fern - with the help of a friendly talking spider called Charlotte - saved her pig, Wilbur, from the usual fate of nice fat little pigs.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"}]}
{"id":421,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/421/","title":"Books by Michael Morpurgo","list_description":"Some might say that Michael Morpurgo is the nation's storyteller. A titan of literature, children all over the planet love and devour his books.  The BookTrust President and former Children's Laureate has written quite a few stories - so here are just a few to start reading first. Trust us - you'll end up wanting to read them all...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24556/war-horse.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24556","title":"War Horse","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Steven Spielberg enjoyed this story so much he has turned it into his latest film. Joey is a young farm horse, sold to the army at the beginning of the First World War. Through his eyes the reader experiences the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24585/private-peaceful.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24585","title":"Private Peaceful","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Set during World War I, Private Peaceful charts eight hours in the life of Tommo, a young soldier at the Front.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24814/the-amazing-story-of-adolphus-tips.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24814","title":"The Amazing Story of Adolphus Tips","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Moving from the present day to wartime diary and back again, this ultimately uplifting novel illuminates the effects of the fateful events on the lives of those involved and the generations that followed.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25091/the-last-wolf.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25091","title":"The Last Wolf","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Powerful illustrations underline this captivating tale of loyalty and bravery.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26762/alone-on-a-wide-wide-sea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26762","title":"Alone on a Wide Wide Sea","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Filled with vividly beautiful descriptions of land and seascapes, this roller-coaster novel quietly maps the changing nature of childhood through time.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30104/kensuke-s-kingdom.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30104","title":"Kensuke's Kingdom","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"This is a beautifully written tale of an exceptional friendship which survives beyond the boundaries of culture and language.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30168/farm-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30168","title":"Farm Boy","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Rich with historical detail and beautifully illustrated, this is a touching and inspirational portrayal of farming life and familial ties.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30888/shadow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30888","title":"Shadow","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"This is a candid exploration of the injustices of war, at home and away, and an unflinching account of the treatment of asylum seekers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32692/9780007487516-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32692","title":"A Medal for Leroy","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"A moving story of love, loss and discovering your identity, inspired by the true story of Walter Tull, the first black officer in the British army","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34696/cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34696","title":"An Eagle in the Snow","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Stuck on a train, a boy listens to a stranger’s story about one moment that could have stopped World War II. A thought-provoking story that young history enthusiasts will especially welcome.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":422,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/422/","title":"BookTrust Great Books Guide 2016: age 4-5","list_description":"We've just published the Great Books Guide 2016 for Children's Book Week: a round-up of 60 books from over the last year, which we think your child will love.   These are our favourite books for 4-5-year-olds:","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34925/have-you-seen-elephant.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34925","title":"Have You Seen Elephant?","author":"by David Barrow","description":"This hilarious book - about an elephant who wants to play hide and seek - will delight children and adults with its offbeat humour and beautiful illustration.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35261/hungry-lion.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35261","title":"A Hungry Lion: or a dwindling assortment of animals","author":"by Lucy Ruth Cummins","description":"The author keeps the surprises coming in this hilarious and quirkily illustrated picture book. It proves that, while you can never trust a hungry lion, there’s always a bigger eater waiting in the wings…","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4-5","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35259/home.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35259","title":"Home","author":"by Carson Ellis","description":"Where is your home? Where are you? Carson Ellis explores wild and wonderful, familiar and extraordinary places that people – real and imaginary – might live.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4-5","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34531/kitchen-disco.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34531","title":"Kitchen Disco","author":"by Clare Foges and Al Murphy","description":"Did you know when you go to sleep all the fruit in the bowl comes to life and has a fun-filled, night long party?"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34923/hector-and-hummingbird.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34923","title":"Hector and Hummingbird","author":"by Nicholas John Frith","description":"The story of Hector and Hummingbird is a lovely one for children with - sometimes irritating but always lovable - little brothers and sisters. The 1950s style and colouring of this fantastic picture book is very appealing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35001/tidy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35001","title":"Tidy","author":"by Emily Gravett","description":"Pete the badger likes to keep everything neat and tidy, but his over-zealous cleaning begins to have a damaging impact on the forest. This entertaining picture book, with its rich illustrations, carries an important environmental message.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34860/quick-quack-quentin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34860","title":"Quick Quack Quentin","author":"by Kes Gray and Jim Field","description":"This beautifully illustrated, colourful picture book explores spelling and letter sounds in the context of great characters and a clever quest story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35146/9780723299868.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35146","title":"Pass It On","author":"by Sophy Henn","description":"The little girl in this bright, happy book embraces the simple act of passing on smiles, laughs, chuckles and whoops to others.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35258/colin-and-lee-carrot-and-pea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35258","title":"Colin and Lee: Carrot and Pea","author":"by Morag Hood","description":"Colin is a carrot, and Lee is a pea. An amusing and deceptively simple look at friendship and difference, this is a lovely book for young readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4-5","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35260/nothing.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35260","title":"Nothing!","author":"by Yasmeen Ismail","description":"Lila has a fabulous imaginary world: if she’s not wrestling an octopus or soaring over a jungle, she’s racing in a winged chariot. Visiting grandpa might not seem as fascinating, but he’s just as keen to join her fantasy world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4-5","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34873/the-cloudspotter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34873","title":"The Cloudspotter","author":"by Tom McLaughlin","description":"Franklin was called 'The Cloudspotter' - and he didn't want to share his clouds with anyone. That's why he pops the infuriating Scruffy Dog into a hot-air balloon and lets her fly away. A charming story about a lonely little...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34898/guide-to-bear-spotting.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34898","title":"A Beginner’s Guide to Bear Spotting","author":"by Michelle Robinson and David Roberts","description":"This amusing guide book contains an array of information about how to spot and behave around bears. The result is a stylish, highly entertaining picture book, perfect for reading aloud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34627/a-great-big-cuddle-front-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34627","title":"A Great Big Cuddle","author":"by Michael Rosen and Chris Riddell","description":"Beautifully illustrated poems for young children by two Children's Laureates","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35066/i-have-an-orange-juicy-drink.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35066","title":"I Have an Orange Juicy Drink","author":"by Andrew Sanders","description":"Porker has an orange juicy drink, but there's no chance he's going to get to drink it in peace. This book is wonderfully vibrant - and the story is funny enough to make parents chuckle, as well as kids.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0-3","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35069/the-bumblebear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35069","title":"The Bumblebear","author":"by Nadia Shireen","description":"Norman the bear loves honey, so he thinks up an ingenious plan to get his paws on as much as he can eat - by enrolling at Bee School! An endearing tale about friendship and loyalty.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34862/i-am-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34862","title":"I am Bear","author":"by Ben Bailey Smith and Sav Akyüz","description":"Meet Bear: the rebel hero of the forest. This charming and anarchic picture book celebrates a mischievious and loveable character.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35070/can-i-eat-that.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35070","title":"Can I Eat That?","author":"by Joshua David Stein and Julia Rothman","description":"A quirky combination of fact and fun, this distinctive picture book about food poses questions that inquisitive children typically ask, such as: 'If I eat jelly and I eat fish, can I eat jellyfish?' Stylish, witty and informative.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34846/hoot-owl-master-of-disguise.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34846","title":"Hoot Owl: master of disguise","author":"by Sean Taylor and Jean Jullien","description":"Hoot Owl wears a selection of ingenious disguises when hunting for food, but his prey always manages to escape. Vibrant illustrations and repetitive text combine to create a comical tale of perseverance. Very silly and the illustrations are great!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35147/9781848692886.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35147","title":"Bee","author":"by Britta Teckentrup","description":"This bee-autiful and special book takes children on a poetic journey through the bee's day.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34960/nibbles-the-book-monster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34960","title":"Nibbles: The Book Monster","author":"by Emma Yarlett","description":"This is a story about a little monster called… Nibbles. And with that, he nibbles his way right out of the book! This really exciting reading experience is sure to be a hit with the whole family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6","interest_age":"Interest level: 3"}]}
{"id":423,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/423/","title":"BookTrust Great Books Guide 2016: age 6-7","list_description":"We've just published the Great Books Guide 2016 for Children's Book Week: a round-up of 60 books from over the last year, which we think your child will love.  These are our favourite books for 6-7-year-olds:","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34737/evil_emperor-penguin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34737","title":"Evil Emperor Penguin: Book 1","author":"by Laura Ellen Anderson","description":"Far away in the icy wastes of Antarctica lives a warm and cuddly, kind-hearted penguin who only wants to do good in the world...NOT! This is no ordinary penguin! This is...EVIL EMPEROR PENGUIN! And he wants to take over the..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35019/wild-animals-of-the-north.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35019","title":"Wild Animals of the North","author":"by Dieter Braun","description":"This special book takes us on an animal journey through North America, Europe and Asia. It is ideal for an animal-loving child, young person interested in animal conservation, or anyone who would appreciate the book's enchanting artwork.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35025/harper-and-the-circus-of-dreams.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35025","title":"Harper and the Circus of Dreams","author":"by Cerrie Burnell","description":"When a magical girl arrives, bringing with her a storm and The Circus of Dreams, Harper and her friends set off on a journey to find out more about the strange world in the sky. A great read with tonnes...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7-9","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35255/wigglesbottom-primary-magic-hamster.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35255","title":"Wigglesbottom Primary: the magic hamster","author":"by Pamela Butchart","description":"This instalment of the greatly loved Wigglesbottom Primary series sees class 2F puzzling over the great mysteries of their school existence - including the makeup of the school mashed potato and what happens when you eat a fly by accident.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34545/i-dont-like-snakes.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34545","title":"I (Don't) Like Snakes","author":"by Nicola Davies and Luciano Lozano","description":"This is an unusual and amusing tale about a girl who doesn't share her family's enthusiasm for snakes. However, as they tell her more about the incredible reptiles, she has a change of heart.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35254/the-jolley-rogers-and-the-monster-s-gold.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35254","title":"The Jolley Rogers and the Monster's Gold","author":"by Jonny Duddle","description":"The Jolley-Rogers are just your everyday pirate family, doing everyday pirate family things. This clever series serves up lots of nautical giggles, and will be enjoyed by all children.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35300/rabbit-and-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35300","title":"Rabbit's Bad Habits","author":"by Julian Gough and Jim Field","description":"Gentle Bear wakes up early from hibernation one day and decides to build a snowman. Grumpy, know-it-all Rabbit comes along, and then Wolf, too. A beautiful modern classic about friends and sharing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35253/dave-pigeon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35253","title":"Dave Pigeon","author":"by Swapna Haddow","description":"Dave Pigeon, the brilliant pigeon mastermind, is determined to find and eat all of your biscuits. The expressive illustrations complete a perfect funny book for younger readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34661/9780763678883.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34661","title":"The Princess in Black","author":"by Shannon and Dean Hale","description":"A prim and proper princess leads a double life as a superhero ninja","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34958/louie-lets-loose.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34958","title":"Louie Lets Loose!","author":"by Rachel Hamilton","description":"Louie the unicorn lives a quiet life with his parents in Story Land, until his invite to the New York School of Performing Arts arrives. This book is a fantastically funny tale of friendship and adapting to a new school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7-9","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35252/above-and-below.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35252","title":"Above and Below","author":"by Patricia Hegarty and Hanako Clulow","description":"This fascinating and stylish picture book explores habitats both above and below the surface. The half-page flaps add another level of interactivity to this wonderful information book that young nature fans will love.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34799/badly-drawn-beth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34799","title":"Badly Drawn Beth","author":"by Knife & Packer","description":"A comic/storybook crossover where hilarious heroine, Beth, charts her survival of school, friends (best and worst), the dreaded family barbecue and other natural disasters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35041/footpath-flowers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35041","title":"Footpath Flowers","author":"by JonArno Lawson","description":"A little girl spreads joy and colour through the grey townscape, when she picks and presents flowers from the pavements to the people and animals she meets. This wordless picture book is a beauty to behold.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34550/toby-and-the-ice-giants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34550","title":"Toby and the Ice Giants","author":"by Joe Lillington","description":"A charming story with lively illustrations to learn more about the last Ice Age.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35257/jack-dash-and-the-magic-feather.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35257","title":"Jack Dash and the Magic Feather","author":"by Sophie Plowden","description":"On the day that Jack’s family moves to a new house, he finds a magic feather in the attic that makes whatever he draws real. Surreal humour and a page-turning plot will keep boys and girls hooked.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34732/pugs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34732","title":"Pugs of the Frozen North","author":"by Philip Reeve and Sarah McIntyre","description":"A race to the far north among some very unconventional competitors and their vehicles. A winning combination of text, image, humour and sadness.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35112/king-flashypants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35112","title":"King Flashypants and the Evil Emperor","author":"by Andy Riley","description":"When nine-year-old King Edwin runs out of pocket money, he can no longer buy his subjects Friday chocolate. The peasants revolt and elect a new leader, Evil Emperor Nurbison. This slapstick tale will appeal to those who love something a...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35029/claude-going-for-gold.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35029","title":"Claude: Going For Gold","author":"by Alex T Smith","description":"It's The Stonking Great Big Sports Day, and returning hero Claude is itching to take part! Hilarious and beautifully illustrated, Claude: Going For Gold is great fun and will carry you off in a gleeful adventure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7-9","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35256/future-ratboy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35256","title":"Future Ratboy and the Invasion of the Nom-Noms","author":"by Jim Smith","description":"Future Ratboy (A.K.A Colin Lamppost) has been zapped millions of years into the future by a bolt of lightning. As if that’s not bad enough, horrible little insects are turning everyone into zombies. A brilliantly hilarious superhero comedy adventure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34927/bear-and-piano_pb_cvr.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34927","title":"The Bear and the Piano","author":"by David Litchfield","description":"A bear's piano playing makes him a huge star, but he misses the friends and family he has left behind. A moving tale of exploration and belonging from an exciting debut author-illustrator.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-8"}]}
{"id":424,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/424/","title":"BookTrust Great Books Guide 2016: age 8+","list_description":"We've just published the Great Books Guide 2016 for Children's Book Week: a round-up of 60 books from over the last year, which we think your child will love.  These are our favourite books for children aged 8 and above:","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35161/the-sword-of-herobrine.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35161","title":"The Sword of Herobrine","author":"by Jim Anotsu","description":"Arthur's sister Mallu is obsessed with Minecraft. When a mysterious code sucks her into the Overworld, he has no choice but to follow her. This unofficial fan story has all the thrills and spills of an accessible adventure story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35095/mega-robo-bros.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35095","title":"Mega Robo Bros","author":"by Neill Cameron","description":"Brothers always find something to fight about. Alex and Freddy are no different - even though they're also the most powerful robots in the universe.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34889/scarlet-files-cat-burglar.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34889","title":"The Scarlet Files: Cat Burglar","author":"by Tamsin Cooke","description":"Scarlet McCall is schoolgirl by day and a cat burglar by night. Her father has taught her to help him burgle houses and return artefacts to their rightful owners. When her father vanishes she must use all the skills he...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-10"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35121/how-to-fight-a-dragon-s-fury.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35121","title":"How to Fight a Dragon’s Fury","author":"by Cressida Cowell","description":"This is the final instalment in the How to Train Your Dragon series and it packs an emotional punch. It brings together every adventure Hiccup and his friends have had, as well as reintroducing old characters and tying up loose...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35148/9781909263918.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35148","title":"Smart About Sharks","author":"by Owen Davey","description":"Presenting an ever-popular topic, this fantastic, high quality illustrated book is fascinating and attractive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34858/superhero-street.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34858","title":"Superhero Street","author":"by Phil Earle","description":"Superhero Street is a heartwarming and laugh-out-loud read that celebrates mums as the everyday superheroes they are. Sara Ogilvie's illustrations add an even more warm, hilarious background to Earle's realistic family.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34831/repro_themanyworlds_cvr_001.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34831","title":"The Many Worlds of Albie Bright","author":"by Christopher Edge","description":"A son of two scientists, it's only natural that Albie uses quantum theory when his mum dies, to find a parallel universe where she's still alive. Considering the topics covered, it's a light read that even reluctant readers might be...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34994/bubble-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34994","title":"The Bubble Boy","author":"by Stewart Foster","description":"Joe has always lived in a sterile room in a hospital. He's the 'bubble boy': documented on TV because of a rare condition, affecting his immune system, that keeps him vacuum-packed from the rest of society.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35096/the-bone-sparrows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35096","title":"The Bone Sparrow","author":"by Zana Fraillon","description":"Focusing on a friendship between two young refugees, The Bone Sparrow is one of those rare, special books that will break your heart with its honesty and beauty - but is ultimately hopeful and uplifting.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34763/the-epic-book-of-epicness.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34763","title":"The Epic Book of Epicness: The world’s most epic facts in pictures","author":"by Adam Frost","description":"In full colour throughout with great, modern design, this book is extremely well written and fun. Every page is full of genuinely fascinating and unusual facts."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35030/girl-of-ink-and-stars.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35030","title":"The Girl of Ink and Stars","author":"by Kiran Millwood Hargrave","description":"When her closest friend disappears into the island's Forgotten Territories, Isabella Riosse volunteers to guide the search. A stunning debut, full of myth, magic and mapmaking.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34902/perijee-and-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34902","title":"Perijee and Me","author":"by Ross Montgomery","description":"When 11-year-old Caitlin discovers a shrimp-like alien creature on the shores of her island home, she takes responsibility for teaching it about the world. Perfect for fans of Roald Dahl and Studio Ghibli films.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34696/cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34696","title":"An Eagle in the Snow","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"Stuck on a train, a boy listens to a stranger’s story about one moment that could have stopped World War II. A thought-provoking story that young history enthusiasts will especially welcome.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35080/wings-flyboy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35080","title":"Wings: Flyboy","author":"by Tom Palmer","description":"On the football field and off it, Jatinder always wants to excel, but he always takes the easy option instead of the risky one. Then Jatinder reads a book by a World War 1 pilot - and finds himself transported...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-14"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35026/pax.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35026","title":"Pax","author":"by Sara Pennypacker","description":"Peter's dad is joining the war, and Peter must leave his pet fox Pax behind. This is a touching story of the bond between a child and his pet, as well as the devastating and often unseen consequences of war.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34726/the-wolf-wilders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34726","title":"The Wolf Wilder","author":"by Katherine Rundell","description":"When the murderous hostility of the Russian Army threatens her very existence, Feo is left with no option but to go on the run. What follows is a story of revolution and adventure, about standing up for the things you...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35023/astro-cat-atomic-adventure.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35023","title":"Professor Astro Cat’s Atomic Adventure","author":"by Dr Dominic Walliman and Ben Newman","description":"Laid out beautifully, covering a science topic on each double-page spread, with information in bite-size chunks, this book will give you activities and brain teasers to keep you occupied for hours.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 10-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34692/the-boy-who-sailed-the-ocean-in-an-armchair.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34692","title":"The Boy Who Sailed the Ocean in an Armchair","author":"by Lara Williamson","description":"Becket Rumsey decides to investigate the reasons behind the strange actions of some of the adults in his life. With the help of his brother Billy and his pet snail Brian, he uncovers some difficult truths - and some beautiful...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35055/rent-a-bridesmaid.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35055","title":"Rent a Bridesmaid","author":"by Jacqueline Wilson","description":"Tilly's dream is to be a bridesmaid at her mum and dad's wedding, but until mum comes back, Tilly decides to offer to be a bridesmaid for hire. Jacqueline Wilson weaves a magical, tale of love, loss, diversity and friendship.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34892/mystery-of-jewelled-moth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34892","title":"The Mystery of the Jewelled Moth","author":"by Katherine Woodfine","description":"In the follow up to The Mystery of the Clockwork Sparrow, we are reunited with Sophie, Lil and the rest of the gang, and Woodfine introduces some fantastic new characters. Perfect for fans of Chris Riddell, Enid Blyton and Robin...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"}]}
{"id":425,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/425/","title":"Best diary books for how it feels to be a teenager","list_description":"There's something about the diary or journal format in a book that really helps you get under a character's skin. After all, you're privy to their first-person, most innermost thoughts. The relationship between the reader and this character feels so close that it can almost feel like a friendship.  This must be why diary books are at their most powerful when you are a pre-teen or a young teenager: battling through puberty, everyday life, and trying to figure out who you are and want to be.  Below are some of our favourites for capturing the highs, the lows, and the very, very funny bits. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32631/manual_9781471116148-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32631","title":"The Perks of Being a Wallflower","author":"by Stephen Chbosky","description":"High school student Charlie prefers to look on life from the sidelines, but he can't be a 'wallflower' for ever, and soon finds himself grappling with the challenges of adolescence.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32862/9781406340013-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32862","title":"OMG! Is This Actually My Life?","author":"by Rae Earl","description":"When Hattie is sent to her room for being sick in her step-father's fish tank, she decides to start writing a diary and sort her life out.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33451/untitled-1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33451","title":"Boys Don't Knit","author":"by T S Easton","description":"'I'm aware that keeping a diary is considered part of the female domain, but in my life, with the family and friends I'm stuck with, it is the only reason I haven't run away and gone to live in the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33385/9781471402272-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33385","title":"The Isobel Journal","author":"by Isobel Harrop","description":"Subtitled ‘Just a Northern Girl from Where Nothing Really Happens’, this beautifully-presented book from 18-year-old debut author Isobel Harrop is a vivid scrapbook of teenage life.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32273/frenchkiss.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32273","title":"Diary of a Crush: French Kiss","author":"by Sarra Manning","description":"First published as a hugely popular serial story in Just 17 magazine, French Kiss is the first in a trilogy following the tumultuous relationship between Edie and her on-off boyfriend Dylan.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33610/rachelrileydiaries.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33610","title":"My So-Called Life","author":"by Joanna Nadin","description":"'Why is life never like it is in books? Nothing interesting ever happens to me...Even my name sucks. In other words, my life is earth-shatteringly normal.'","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29396/angus-thongs-and-full-frontal-snogging.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29396","title":"Angus, Thongs and Full-Frontal Snogging","author":"by Louise Rennison","description":"Welcome to the world of Georgia Nicolson - an angst-ridden teenage girl who keeps a diary to record the rollercoaster of emotions and experiences she faces every day","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28745/spud.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28745","title":"Spud","author":"by John van de Ruit","description":"Spud gets a scholarship to a smart boys’ school where he soon joins in with a mad bunch of boys – the Crazy Eight.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24572/icapturethecastle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24572","title":"I Capture the Castle","author":"by Dodie Smith","description":"17-year-old Cassandra lives an eccentric existence with her bohemian family in a crumbling castle in the English countryside, in this delightful classic coming-of-age story.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35316/secretdiary-of-adrianmole.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35316","title":"The Secret Diary of Adrian Mole Aged 13 3/4","author":"by Sue Townsend","description":"The first book in the Adrian Mole series, this was a publishing sensation back in the 1980s, but still has the power to entertain pre-teen, teen and even adult readers, and make them double up with laughter.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":426,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/426/","title":"Spooky reads for autumn and winter nights","list_description":"Now the nights are dark and long, there's a definite chill in the air. But is that shiver down your spine caused by the cold weather or something else?  If you like to spook yourself silly, prepare to be scared with these enjoyably eerie books about ghosts, gods, nightmares and monsters. Don't say we didn't warn you...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35249/three-dark-crowns.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35249","title":"Three Dark Crowns","author":"by Kendare Blake","description":"Three queens, all equal heirs to the crown and possessor of a coveted magic - and when they are 16, they must battle to the death to become Queen of the island. This story is feminist, fierce and unforgettable -...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35046/the-hawkweed-prophecys.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35046","title":"The Hawkweed Prophecy","author":"by Irena Brignull","description":"Strong characters, complex relationships, and important themes of family, belonging, identity, love and loneliness, drive this absorbing story of magic and painful family secrets.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35282/the-wrong-train.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35282","title":"The Wrong Train","author":"by Jeremy de Quidt","description":"Getting on the wrong train is usually just a minor inconvenience but, as this masterful piece of horror writing confirms, it can sometimes become one of your worst nightmares. Utterly chilling and haunting.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35304/the-graces.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35304","title":"The Graces","author":"by Laure Eve","description":"Like everyone else in town, River is obsessed with the Graces: attracted by their glamour and apparent ability to weave magic. But are they really what they seem? A beautifully written, deliciously dark YA fantasy with a fresh take on...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35293/the-otherlife.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35293","title":"The Otherlife","author":"by Julia Gray","description":"An intelligent and insightful read, this YA novel manages to merge Norse myth, competitive parenting, bullying, class issues and exam pressures into a taut and chilling thriller. Perfect for fans of Sarah Govett and Neil Gaiman.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35294/haunt-me.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35294","title":"Haunt Me","author":"by Liz Kessler","description":"Introverted Erin has just moved to a new house and school - and finds her new bedroom is haunted by teenager Joe. With a mature and sensitive approach to bereavement, loss and teen relationships, this proves a thought-provoking read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12-16"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35295/the-creeper-man.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35295","title":"The Creeper Man","author":"by Dawn Kurtagich","description":"Kurtagich has created an incredibly assured, claustrophobic horror with a fractured and troubled teen narrator that will have you gripped to the very last page.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35273/barefoot-on-the-wind.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35273","title":"Barefoot on the Wind","author":"by Zoe Marriott","description":"This stylish reworking of Beauty and the Beast unfolds in mythical Japan. Beautiful visual imagery, viscerally brutal action and desperate passions make this retelling feel fresh.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35016/book-of-lies.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35016","title":"Book of Lies","author":"by Terri Terry","description":"Piper and Quinn find out they're identical twins when their mother dies. Written with alternating viewpoint chapters between the twins, there is a genuinely spooky feel to this excellent psychological and supernatural thriller.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35199/and-i-darkend.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35199","title":"And I Darken","author":"by Kiersten White","description":"And I Darken is a fictional retelling of the rise of Vlad the Impaler - except, in White's thrilling take on it, Vlad isn't Vlad but Lady Lada. The political intrigue and character relationships are wonderfully done, and Lada is...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":427,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/427/","title":"Books for reluctant readers","list_description":"There's a book out there for every child, even the most reluctant of readers. Try a few of the books below to see if they click with your child and help them love reading. There's fiction, non-fiction, rhyme and laugh-out-loud moments! Let us know which one works for your family... ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35011/going-batty.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35011","title":"Going Batty","author":"by John Agard","description":"Dyslexia-friendly, super-readable, illustrated story about a girl whose school project (and a hidden colony in the attic) makes her face up to her greatest fear.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34737/evil_emperor-penguin.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34737","title":"Evil Emperor Penguin: Book 1","author":"by Laura Ellen Anderson","description":"Far away in the icy wastes of Antarctica lives a warm and cuddly, kind-hearted penguin who only wants to do good in the world...NOT! This is no ordinary penguin! This is...EVIL EMPEROR PENGUIN! And he wants to take over the..."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29551/9780141324302-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29551","title":"Young Samurai The Way of the Warrior","author":"by Chris Bradford","description":"This engaging historical adventure story will immerse young readers in the traditions and culture of Ancient Japan, including its complex codes of loyalty and honour.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34990/petuniaperry_cvr_hr_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34990","title":"Petunia Perry and the Curse of the Ugly Pigeon","author":"by Pamela Butchart","description":"Petunia Perry is writing her memoir to fully explain why she's no longer friends with Cammy - and why, therefore, she and Cammy's band are unlikely to be the Next Big Thing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35148/9781909263918.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35148","title":"Smart About Sharks","author":"by Owen Davey","description":"Presenting an ever-popular topic, this fantastic, high quality illustrated book is fascinating and attractive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34531/kitchen-disco.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34531","title":"Kitchen Disco","author":"by Clare Foges and Al Murphy","description":"Did you know when you go to sleep all the fruit in the bowl comes to life and has a fun-filled, night long party?"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24991/the-wolves-in-the-walls.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24991","title":"The Wolves in the Walls","author":"by Neil Gaiman","description":"When Lucy hears noises in the walls of her home, she tries to warn her family that the wolves are coming. However, they do not heed her warnings – until it is too late.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34922/super-happy-magic-forest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34922","title":"Super Happy Magic Forest","author":"by Matty Long","description":"This anarchic and amusing picture book deserves much praise for taking commonplace story elements - pixies, goblins, unicorns and magical locations - and giving them an original twist. It's a hilarious read, with rich and vibrant illustrations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33851/9780141354156.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33851","title":"Danger is Everywhere","author":"by David O'Doherty","description":"Just like this book says, danger is everywhere. Don't worry, though, because Docter Noel Zone (yes, Docter) is an experienced Dangerologist and is here to help you in this fun and very funny book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32685/9780230741041-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32685","title":"Alienography 2: Tips for Tiny Tyrants","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"Find out how to take over the universe in this funny and engaging book from Chris Riddell (and Colin the Alien)","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34862/i-am-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34862","title":"I am Bear","author":"by Ben Bailey Smith and Sav Akyüz","description":"Meet Bear: the rebel hero of the forest. This charming and anarchic picture book celebrates a mischievious and loveable character.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-5"}]}
{"id":428,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/428/","title":"Non-fiction and fact books your child will love","list_description":"Getting children to love reading isn't necessarily about fiction and fairy tales. There are loads of brilliant non-fiction books that can teach your child about the world, as well as being entertaining, funny and gorgeous to look at. Sometimes non-fiction is also a fantastic way to tempt a reluctant reader into sitting down with a book.  Here are just a few of our favourites to get your family ready and excited to read.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35148/9781909263918.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35148","title":"Smart About Sharks","author":"by Owen Davey","description":"Presenting an ever-popular topic, this fantastic, high quality illustrated book is fascinating and attractive.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35020/outside-guide-to-discovering-nature.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35020","title":"Outside: A Guide to Discovering Nature","author":"by Maria Ana Peixe Dias and Ines Teixeira do Rosario","description":"Amphibians, birds, rocks, oceans and clouds: they're all explored in this large and stylish hardcover guide to nature for children in cities and the countryside alike.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35265/199-things-that-go.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35265","title":"199 Things that Go","author":"by Jessica Greenwell","description":"Usborne have put together a very comprehensive list of things that go, from the everyday to the not-so-common. A lovely way to teach children about various modes of transport from the road to outer space."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35242/the-great-big-body-book.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35242","title":"The Great Big Body Book","author":"by Mary Hoffman","description":"How does the human body develop and change in a lifetime? Hoffman and Asquith explore these questions and more in this honest, entertaining and fact-filled celebration of the human body, which also reflects the diversity of the world we live...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35166/under-earth-under-water.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35166","title":"Under Earth, Under Water","author":"by Aleksandra and David Mizielinski","description":"This gorgeous large hardback explores what happens under the earth and in our oceans and seas in fantastically colourful and accessible double-page spreads. This is a really excellent example of nonfiction that is both comprehensive and fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35244/fantastically-great-women-who-changed-the-world.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35244","title":"Fantastically Great Women Who Changed The World","author":"by Kate Pankhurst","description":"Written and illustrated by a direct descendant of suffragette Emmeline Pankhurst, this colourful picture book is full of facts about 13 inspirational women from history, showcasing their achievements in a fun and accessible way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35286/the-book-of-bees.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35286","title":"The Book of Bees","author":"by Piotr Socha and Wojciech Grajkowski","description":"This glorious book will introduce you to the bee world. It is fantastically illustrated in a cartoonish style that is big, bold and great fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7-9","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-9"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35070/can-i-eat-that.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35070","title":"Can I Eat That?","author":"by Joshua David Stein and Julia Rothman","description":"A quirky combination of fact and fun, this distinctive picture book about food poses questions that inquisitive children typically ask, such as: 'If I eat jelly and I eat fish, can I eat jellyfish?' Stylish, witty and informative.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34885/frida-kahlo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34885","title":"Frida Kahlo","author":"by Ma Isabel Sanchez Vegara","description":"Frida Kahlo's life story is adapted for younger readers - with bold and colourful illustrations, and an inspiring facts and photos section at the back.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35023/astro-cat-atomic-adventure.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35023","title":"Professor Astro Cat’s Atomic Adventure","author":"by Dr Dominic Walliman and Ben Newman","description":"Laid out beautifully, covering a science topic on each double-page spread, with information in bite-size chunks, this book will give you activities and brain teasers to keep you occupied for hours.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 10-12"}]}
{"id":429,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/429/","title":"We love tigers","list_description":"There's a long history of tigers cropping up in children's books - and they don't only pop round for tea...  Here are some of our favourite 'tiger' books for you to share with your little one, full of fantastic drawings of this iconic creature.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30525/tigers-story2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30525","title":"Tiger's Story","author":"by Harriet Blackford","description":"","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34463/never-tickle-a-tiger.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34463","title":"Never Tickle a Tiger","author":"by Pamela Butchart","description":"For fidgety children everywhere, especially those who don't heed good advice, this cautionary tale shows what the unconsidered consequences can be when we can't understand just why we're told never to do something.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33068/9780745963495.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33068","title":"The Last Tiger","author":"by Rebecca Elliott","description":"Luka lives in a drab, grey world where there are no more trees, flowers or animals - or so Luka thinks, until he meets the last tiger.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24800/the-tiger-who-came-to-tea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24800","title":"The Tiger Who Came to Tea","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"Sophie and her Mummy are having tea in the kitchen when in walks a hungry tiger who asks to stay to tea.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29147/tigerontree.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29147","title":"Tiger on a Tree","author":"by Anushka Ravishankar","description":"A highly original picture book from India, this is the story of a tiger who ventures onto human territory.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25657/augustus-and-his-smile.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25657","title":"Augustus and his Smile","author":"by Catherine Rayner","description":"Augustus is a tiger, who though large and fearless, is sad, because he has lost his smile. He goes on a journey to find it.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35002/tiger-in-a-tutu.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35002","title":"Tiger in a Tutu","author":"by Fabi Santiago","description":"Max the tiger longs to be a ballet dancer, but when he twirls majestically through the streets of Paris, people flee in terror. It takes a very special friend to help Max realise his dream.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34982/9781407158044.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34982","title":"Gracie Grabbit and the Tiger","author":"by Helen Stephens","description":"Gracie's daddy, Bobby Grabbit is very naughty, because he steals things from other people. When they go to the zoo, he even steals from the people and the animals there! Fortunately, Gracie's there to put things right and make sure...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34996/tiger-in-the-garden.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34996","title":"There’s a Tiger in the Garden","author":"by Lizzy Stewart","description":"A sweet and surreal story with lush painterly illustrations and a high quality production. Nora's tiger is sure to delight little ones who dream of tigers coming to tea, and then staying to play in the garden!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35144/don-t-wake-up-tiger.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35144","title":"Don’t Wake Up Tiger!","author":"by Britta Teckentrup","description":"Tiger has fallen asleep in the middle of the floor – much to the annoyance of all her friends, who now have to try not to wake Tiger up. This fun and interactive picture book is full of colourful illustrations...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0-3","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30469/9781409518990-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30469","title":"That's Not My Tiger...","author":"by Fiona Watt","description":"Small children will love touching the tiger’s fluffy ears, soft paws and bumpy teeth and will particularly like tracing his soft, stripy tail on the very last page.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30761/the-nanny-goat-s-kid.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30761","title":"The Nanny Goat's Kid","author":"by Jeanne Willis","description":"The tiger cub is different to the other Kids and the sisters criticise the way Nanny Goat is bringing him up.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"}]}
{"id":430,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/430/","title":"Top 10 new picture books for winter","list_description":"The festive season might be over... but winter is still in full flow.  Here are some of our favourite new seasonal picture books to snuggle up and read with the little ones.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35394/dotinthesnow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35394","title":"A Dot in the Snow","author":"by Corrinne Averiss","description":"Miki the polar bear cub is bored: mum is fishing on the ice, but he wants to play. He sees a red dot, far in the distance: what could it be?","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35401/stormwhale-in-winter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35401","title":"The Storm Whale in Winter","author":"by Benji Davies","description":"The follow up to Benji Davies' The Storm Whale, this atmospheric story about friendship and family is perfect for cosy winter bedtimes.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35395/nuddynedxmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35395","title":"Nuddy Ned's Christmas","author":"by Kes Gray","description":"This hilarious rhyming book by Kes Gray and illustrated by Garry Parsons is a brilliantly silly one to share, especially at bedtime in the run up to Christmas.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35399/princess-xmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35399","title":"The Princess and the Christmas Rescue","author":"by Caryl Hart","description":"Princess Eliza lives in a beautiful palace amid a forest - but living in a palace is about the only bit of being a traditional princess she really does. Eliza is in fact a brilliant, brainy inventor, and she can...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35403/walking-in-a-winter-wonderland.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35403","title":"Walking in a Winter Wonderland","author":"by Tim Hopgood","description":"The words to the famous Christmas song by Peggy Lee are given new life in this beautiful new picture book by Tim Hopgood - and children (and grown ups) can sing along with the singalong CD included in the book,...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35398/sproutzilla.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35398","title":"Sproutzilla vs Christmas","author":"by Tom Jamieson","description":"Anarchic and brilliantly funny (with a whole page dedicated to a fart), Sproutzilla vs Christmas is also a great book to encourage children to eat their greens.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35397/snowbeast.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35397","title":"The Snow Beast","author":"by Chris Judge","description":"Somebody has been stealing the friendly snow beast's tools, just when he's about to help the local village put on a snow festival.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35396/olliexmas.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35396","title":"Ollie’s Christmas Reindeer","author":"by Nicola Killen","description":"Nicola Killen's black, white and red picture book with silver detailing is a stylish take on the magic of Christmas Eve, a simple, lovely story about friendship at Christmas.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35400/ravenchild-snowwitch.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35400","title":"Raven Child and the Snow Witch","author":"by Linda Sunderland","description":"A stunningly illustrated story, reminiscent of Hand Christian Andersen's The Snow Queen, Anya's quest to find her mother and her befriending of animal friends along the way is a mythic tale you'll want to return to every winter.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35402/winnie-wilbur-meet-santa.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35402","title":"Winnie and Wilbur Meet Santa","author":"by Valerie Thomas and Korky Paul","description":"A lovely festive addition of the Winnie series, this is as full of colourful detail and crazy antics as the rest, and children will love the fold-out letter to Santa at the end, and the final pop-up page.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":431,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/431/","title":"Kindness, compassion and empathy","list_description":"Help put your child in another person’s shoes with these books that inspire compassion: whether that’s towards animals, friends, or people in very different situations to your own.  Not only will you end up caring about about them all, but you’ll also feel grateful for the simple things you have and the people you love.  So share these books as a family, and let’s spread a little kindness in the world…","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34259/we-are-all-born-free.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34259","title":"We Are All Born Free","author":"by Amnesty International","description":"The variety of illustrations is a delight, while the content is essential knowledge for children to learn. An unmissable book to read cover to cover or dip into as you please.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33535/girlwithawhitedog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33535","title":"Girl with a White Dog","author":"by Anne Booth","description":"Jessie is delighted when she finds a beautiful white puppy at Gran's house. But then Gran starts becoming confused, and saying strange things about their new pet.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34774/refuge.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34774","title":"Refuge","author":"by Anne Booth","description":"This beautiful book follows Mary, Joseph and baby Jesus as they flee into Egypt as refugees. The gorgeous drawings and Booth's sparse, poetic words make this a Christmas book to treasure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24753/give-me-shelter.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24753","title":"Give Me Shelter","author":"by Edited by Tony Bradman","description":"Told through the eyes of children, this moving collection of short stories focuses on the experiences of asylum seekers from all over the world.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34015/red-leaves.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34015","title":"Red Leaves","author":"by Sita Brahmachari","description":"Sita Brahmachari has created a beautiful tale of modern multicultural Britain. Her characters come from diverse backgrounds but are brought together by the common theme - they all feel they have been abandoned by someone they love.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35357/girl-with-no-nose.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35357","title":"The Girl with No Nose","author":"by Georgia Byng","description":"Life is tough in Victorian times, the world into which Alice Peasbody is born - and Alice is a girl with no nose. A wonderful, thoughtful book that teaches compassion, celebrates difference and tackles some weighty issues with a gentle...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35093/library-of-lemons.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35093","title":"A Library of Lemons","author":"by Jo Cotterill","description":"Believable, memorable, charming and moving, fans of Jacqueline Wilson's domestic dramas will enjoy this bittersweet story of a family finding their feet in the next chapter of their lives.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35041/footpath-flowers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35041","title":"Footpath Flowers","author":"by JonArno Lawson","description":"A little girl spreads joy and colour through the grey townscape, when she picks and presents flowers from the pavements to the people and animals she meets. This wordless picture book is a beauty to behold.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34600/gorilla-dawn.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34600","title":"Gorilla Dawn","author":"by Gill Lewis","description":"This book tells the story of Imara, taken as a small child from her village when rebels raid it, and brainwashed into thinking that she has magical powers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30888/shadow.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30888","title":"Shadow","author":"by Michael Morpurgo","description":"This is a candid exploration of the injustices of war, at home and away, and an unflinching account of the treatment of asylum seekers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34778/acts-of-kindness-for-kids.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34778","title":"Do Nice, Be Kind, Spread Happy","author":"by Bernadette Russell","description":"This gives children 80 ways to make the world a better place – and have some fun at the same time. Most will long to join the Kindness Club and dish out ‘ninja niceness’ after flicking through the ideas in...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35034/i-am-malala-jacket-image.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35034","title":"I am Malala","author":"by Malala Yousafzai and Patricia McCormick","description":"This is the real life story of one of the most incredible and inspirational young people in the world. Reading this book might just change the way you think and feel.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"}]}
{"id":432,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/432/","title":"Books to inspire your imagination","list_description":"These picture books are all about the power of imagination: be inspired to imagine new worlds and new words with your children!","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35473/her-idea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35473","title":"Her Idea","author":"by Rilla Alexander","description":"Inspired by Rilla Alexander's own experiences of working with children who can get frustrated about finishing a story or a picture, this is a how-to book about Rilla's own practice of keeping an ideas journal.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35381/nightlights.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35381","title":"Nightlights","author":"by Lorena Alvarez","description":"A remarkable, haunting and beautiful graphic novel for younger readers, Nightlights is a magical fable about creativity and believing in yourself. With a 'Studio Ghibli' feel and some sumptuous artwork, this is a wonderful read and a visual treat.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35227/return.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35227","title":"Return","author":"by Aaron Becker","description":"A lonely little girl can't distract her hardworking dad, so she takes her amazing red pen and draws herself into an adventure. This imaginative, fantastical escapade is wordless, but overflows with creativity.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0 (as there are no words)","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30465/play-the-shape-game.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30465","title":"Play the Shape Game","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"Celebrities, authors and illustrators join the Children's Laureate Anthony Browne in this fun novelty book encouraging children to be creative and use their imaginations.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35240/3035.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35240","title":"A Child of Books","author":"by Oliver Jeffers and Sam Winston","description":"A little girl sails across the sea of her imagination to ask a little boy to come away with her to find stories again, worried that some people in the world have forgotten them.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35041/footpath-flowers.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35041","title":"Footpath Flowers","author":"by JonArno Lawson","description":"A little girl spreads joy and colour through the grey townscape, when she picks and presents flowers from the pavements to the people and animals she meets. This wordless picture book is a beauty to behold.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35474/use-your-imagination.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35474","title":"Use Your Imagination","author":"by Nicola O'Byrne","description":"Rabbit is bored, so librarian Wolf suggests that he writes a story. Rabbit is delighted - what a brilliant idea! Wolf is full of great ideas - some of them less friendly than others.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34955/beekle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34955","title":"The Adventures of Beekle; The Unimaginary Friend","author":"by Dan Santat","description":"Seeing the world from the imaginary friend's viewpoint, rather than the child's, sheds fresh light on this familiar yet magical friendship. The stylish, striking, images emphasise its vibrancy against everyday drabness.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35340/9781783444670.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35340","title":"Are We There Yet?","author":"by Dan Santat","description":"A little boy is on the way to his Grandma's birthday party in the car with mum and dad, but after the first hour, the journey gets more and more boring. But as the little boy feels the hours ahead...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35472/also-an-octopus.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35472","title":"Also an Octopus","author":"by Maggie Tokuda-Hall","description":"This is a lovely story about storytelling which extends the invitation to the reader to continue the tale after the last page has been turned.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"}]}
{"id":434,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/434/","title":"Best Fictional Libraries (12+)","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35059/peace-maker.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35059","title":"Peace Maker","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"In Michela's world, aggression is forbidden - but sometimes fighting is the only way to keep the peace. This is a well-paced and interesting story, designed to appeal to reluctant or hesitant readers, as well as dyslexia-friendly.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25342/matilda.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25342","title":"Matilda","author":"by Roald Dahl and Quentin Blake","description":"This modern fairy-tale with a brilliantly inspiring young heroine is one of Roald Dahl's best loved stories.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34016/archie-green-magicians-secret.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34016","title":"Archie Green and the Magician's Secret","author":"by D D Everest","description":"If you love books that show you where the magical could be hiding in your everyday world then this is the book for you.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24536/inkheart-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24536","title":"Inkheart","author":"by Cornelia Funke","description":"12-year-old Meggie and her father, Mo, a bookbinder, both love reading, but since the disappearance of Meggie's mother, they no longer read together. One night a stranger knocks at their door, prompting Mo to reveal his awful secret.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35160/the-other-alice.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35160","title":"The Other Alice","author":"by Michelle Harrison","description":"Michelle Harrison's dark take on middle-grade fairytale fantasy will appeal to those readers with a leaning towards the Grimm. Murder and mystery are afoot - and it's fabulously good fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34046/the-imaginary.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34046","title":"The Imaginary","author":"by A F Harrold","description":"This is young fiction of the very best quality, showcasing inspiration, inventiveness and an intoxicating passion for storytelling. The Imaginary has the potential to be a family favourite and a future classic.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30862/the-night-bookmobile.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30862","title":"The Night Bookmobile","author":"by Audrey Niffenegger","description":"In the early hours of a summer morning, a young woman encounters a mysterious mobile library while walking down an empty suburban street.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 14+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/27725/northernlights-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/27725","title":"Northern Lights","author":"by Philip Pullman","description":"This extraordinary fantasy is the first book in Philip Pullman's multi-award-winning His Dark Materials trilogy","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30267/9780747558194-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30267","title":"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone","author":"by J K Rowling","description":"After the misery of life with his ghastly aunt and uncle, Harry Potter is delighted to have the chance to embark on an exciting new life at the Hogwart's School of Wizardry and Witchcraft.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-13"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35438/the-road-to-ever-after.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35438","title":"The Road to Ever After","author":"by Moira Young","description":"This beautifully written, sad and bittersweet story about family, bereavement and having faith in your own abilities has a truly timeless feel. Readers will root for Davy and the indomitable Miss Flint.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-14"}]}
{"id":435,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/435/","title":"National Cheese Lovers Day","list_description":"","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33095/9781406339666.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33095","title":"Cheese Belongs To You","author":"by Alexis Deacon","description":"‘RAT LAW’ states that ‘Cheese Belongs To You’ – at least until someone bigger, stronger, faster, or scarier decides otherwise.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34837/great-cheese-robbery.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34837","title":"The Great Cheese Robbery","author":"by Chris Mould","description":"When the skirting board mice kidnap the ship's cat for a cheese ransom, the pirates are ready for action. An easy-to-read and exciting adventure story, which is perfect for readers starting to read alone.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34100/the_stinky_cheese_man_book_cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34100","title":"The Stinky Cheese Man and other Fairly Stupid Tales","author":"by Jon Scieszka and Lane Smith","description":"Jon Scieszka introduces some really stupid off-the-wall fairy tales including: Chicken Licken, The Princess and the Bowling Ball; The Really Ugly Duckling, and Jack's Bean Problem. Chosen by children as the Book of the Year for the Federation of Children's...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35117/the-world-famous-cheese-shop-break-in.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35117","title":"The World-Famous Cheese Shop Break-in","author":"by Sean Taylor","description":"When Daddypops and his two baby rats discover a cheese shop even stinkier than ancient socks, there is only one thing for it…they have to break in! A comical story, with hilarious illustrations, that's perfect for reading out loud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34460/great-cheese-robbery.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34460","title":"The Great Cheese Robbery","author":"by Tim Warnes","description":"Patrick thinks Daddy Elephant is not scared of anything until a mouse comes to call.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-7"}]}
{"id":436,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/436/","title":"Books to read during LGBT History Month","list_description":"Help teenagers to explore diversity, identity and love with this selection of some favourite books below. They include lesbian, gay, bisexual or transgender characters and relationships.  These are the perfect reads for LGBT History Month, which takes place every February: a month-long celebration of LGBT rights and role models.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34209/love-hurts.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34209","title":"Love Hurts","author":"by Malorie Blackman","description":"This anthology depicts a very wide range of romantic relationships, and a diverse set of characters, showing love in all its forms.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33912/this-book-is-gay-juno-dawson.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33912","title":"This Book is Gay","author":"by Juno Dawson","description":"A fantastic book for classrooms and school libraries, This Book is Gay is a must-read for teachers and parents, as well as teens themselves.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34751/georgea.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34751","title":"George","author":"by Alex Gino","description":"This short, sweet story of embracing your true self and trusting those around you is a light read for such a heavy topic, which tackles transgender identification. Gino keeps the story simple and the voice friendly.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35198/you-know-me-well.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35198","title":"You Know Me Well","author":"by Nina LaCour and David Levithan","description":"Mark and Kate have never spoken outside class - and little do they know how important they will become to each other. As well as being a wonderful book for LGBT representation, this honestly and hilariously celebrates first love and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33282/9780007533039-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33282","title":"Boy Meets Boy","author":"by David Levithan","description":"This delightful high-school story is set in a town in which being a gay teenager is no more fraught with difficulty than being straight.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32442/9780340988374-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32442","title":"Ash","author":"by Malinda Lo","description":"In this bewitching and sophisticated re-interpretation of the Cinderella story, lonely orphan Ash falls in love not with a handsome prince, but with Kaisa, the King's Huntress.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32272/9780340883723-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32272","title":"Pretty Things","author":"by Sarra Manning","description":"Sarra Manning cleverly conveys the confusion and uncertainty of adolescence, revealing that sexuality is not always as straightforward as we are sometimes led to believe","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 15+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31070/everyday.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31070","title":"Everyday","author":"by Lee Rourke","description":"Everyday takes the reader for a dawdle into the moribund heart of London."},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35243/girl-hearts-girl.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35243","title":"Girl Hearts Girl","author":"by Lucy Sutcliffe","description":"A real-life memoir about a young person coming to terms with her sexuality and her 'coming out', as well as her first relationship, this is a positive and upbeat read about being comfortable in your own skin that will inspire...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33944/lies-we-tell-ourselves.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33944","title":"The Lies We Tell Ourselves","author":"by Robin Talley","description":"This exceptional novel of first love and sexual awakenings is set against a backdrop of shocking racism and prejudice.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35167/here-i-stand.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35167","title":"Here I Stand","author":"by Various","description":"These short stories by writers such as Sita Brahmachari, Matt Haig and Frances Harding, with illustration by Chris Riddell, put current and continuing political situations in context for young people. Not an easy read, but a necessary one.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34128/art-of-being-normal.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34128","title":"The Art of Being Normal","author":"by Lisa Williamson","description":"David Piper has always been an outsider, labelled a freak by the school bully. Only his two best friends know the real truth – David wants to be a girl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 13+","interest_age":"Interest level: 14+"}]}
{"id":438,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/438/","title":"Our favourite picture books about love","list_description":"Valentine's Day doesn't just have to be about couples - it's also an excellent excuse to snuggle up with your family and share some time together.  There's nothing quite like the bond between a carer and their child, and these picture books beautifully explore that unconditional love.  So whether you're cuddling with your child before bed or just want to relax with an adorable tale, we've chosen some books that are bound to make your storytime even more heartwarming than normal.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35489/love-is.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35489","title":"Love is","author":"by Diane Adams","description":"A little girl cares for a duckling just as a parent would care for a baby. But also, as the duckling grows, the little girl comes to understand that part of love is letting things go. A gentle and inspiring...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35511/love-you-hoo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35511","title":"Love You Hoo","author":"by Rachel Bright","description":"Big Owl snuggles up for a bedtime cuddle with Little Hoo in this heartwarming story about the unconditional love and support between a carer and child.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35490/when-an-elephant-falls-in-love.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35490","title":"When an Elephant Falls in Love","author":"by Davide Cali and Alice Notti","description":"Adults will recognise all the symptoms of the first flush of love in this tongue-in-cheek picture book, and children will delight in the funny illustrations and the happy ending.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32555/9781848777828-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32555","title":"Cinderelephant","author":"by Emma Dodd","description":"Prince Trunky is looking for a bride and all the girls in the neighbourhood are invited to his ball - but poor Cinderelephant is stuck at home cooking and cleaning for the Warty Sisters.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35510/love....jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35510","title":"Love...","author":"by Emma Dodd","description":"Perfect for sharing at bedtime, this beautifully illustrated story about love follows a baby bunny and parent rabbit as they spend the day enjoying each other's company.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35508/i-love-you-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35508","title":"I Love You, Baby","author":"by Claire Freedman and Judi Abbot","description":"This celebration of the love a parent has for their child is perfect for cuddles, as all sorts of baby animals learn that they will always be loved - no matter what.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35509/i-love-you.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35509","title":"I Love You","author":"by Clemency Pearce and Rosalind Beardshaw","description":"This beautifully illustrated book about forest animals shares a very important lesson: that those three little words can make a huge difference to someone feeling blue.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1-4"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34627/a-great-big-cuddle-front-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34627","title":"A Great Big Cuddle","author":"by Michael Rosen and Chris Riddell","description":"Beautifully illustrated poems for young children by two Children's Laureates","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35507/i-ll-love-you-always.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35507","title":"I'll Love You Always","author":"by Mark Sperring and Alison Brown","description":"This is a perfect bedtime book about the everlasting bond of love between a little mouse and her mummy or daddy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34991/sean-taylor.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34991","title":"A Brave Bear","author":"by Sean Taylor","description":"A book for families, for dads and for illustration fans, this is in the same territory as the phenomenally successful Guess How Much I Love You, but with a subtler sentimentality that might appeal to a new generation of parents.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5","interest_age":"Interest level: 3"}]}
{"id":439,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/439/","title":"Becoming a big sibling","list_description":"It can be a confusing time for children when they find out there's going to be a new addition to the family - from understanding what pregnancy is right through to trying to work out what will happen when their baby sibling arrives.  These books explore all those issues, from what takes place when someone finds out that they're expecting to the thorny issue of sibling rivalry.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34657/9781406357509.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34657","title":"Albert and Little Henry","author":"by Jez Alborough","description":"Henry starts to feel left out and ignored when a new baby sibling arrives at home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25027/there-s-a-house-inside-my-mummy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25027","title":"There's A House Inside My Mummy","author":"by Giles Andreae","description":"This is just the book to explain to inquisitive children what going on inside mum during pregnancy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35123/a-welcome-song-for-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35123","title":"A Welcome Song for Baby","author":"by Marsha Diane Arnold","description":"This reassuring, sensitively illustrated story celebrates the milestones of pregnancy as the seasons pass, foregrounding the naturalness of the process as Emma excitedly awaits her new brother or sister.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30794/there-s-going-to-be-a-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30794","title":"There's Going to be a Baby","author":"by John Burningham","description":"A mother tells her little boy that ‘there’s going to be a baby’, but the little boy doesn’t like the sound of this – he doesn’t think they really need the new baby…","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34635/9781447257431.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34635","title":"Lion Practice","author":"by Emma Carlisle","description":"Laura goes to long and noisry lengths to remind her mum and dad she's still there after a new sibling arrives on the scene.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 0-5","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33927/new-small-person.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33927","title":"The New Small Person","author":"by Lauren Child","description":"An endearingly funny story, featuring Lauren Child's heart-warming illustrations, about the arrival of a new sibling and the havoc that ensues.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33751/little-frogs-tadpole-trouble.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33751","title":"Little Frog's Tadpole Trouble","author":"by Tatyana Feeney","description":"Simple, but wonderfully expressive, d­­etailed line drawings, and a green froggy font add additional layers of humour to this funny yet reassuring story of new sibling anxiety.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30579/waiting-for-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30579","title":"Waiting for Baby","author":"by Rachel Fuller","description":"This gentle book deals with the anticipation of waiting for a new baby.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6 months+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34037/whats-in-tummy-mummy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34037","title":"What's in your Tummy, Mummy?","author":"by Sam Llloyd","description":""},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34170/15-things-not-to-do-with-a-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34170","title":"15 Things Not to Do With a Baby","author":"by Margaret McAllister and Holly Sterling","description":"A simple and sweet little idea that will make tots who have new baby siblings really giggle.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35226/lulu-and-the-noisy-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35226","title":"Lulu and the Noisy Baby","author":"by Camilla Reid","description":"Mummy and daddy have some great news for Lulu - she is going to be a big sister! This is an absolutely adorable book about adapting to change. Each page is bursting with detail and endless flaps to lift and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35538/im-big-now.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35538","title":"I'm Big Now","author":"by Anthea Simmons","description":"When her little brother is born, a little girl realises she is no longer the baby!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"}]}
{"id":440,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/440/","title":"Raymond Briggs: a lifetime in books","list_description":"Raymond Briggs has just won our Lifetime Achievement Award 2017 - and with very good reason.  He's been writing and illustrating for decades and has won over legions of fans with his ability to be outrageously funny but also moving and reflective. He's unafraid to steer children and adults through some of life's big themes, but always in a way that's completely engaging. His stories and drawings live long in the mind. Below are some of our favourites, covering a wide range of reading ages - from teeny tots to reluctant grown-ups. If you only know a couple of Raymond Briggs' works, you're in for a treat... ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30504/ug.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30504","title":"Ug","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"Ug and his parents live in the Stone Age. This means stone blankets, stone-cold food, an even colder cave and, worst of all, hard stone trousers!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31881/9780140501872-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31881","title":"Father Christmas Goes on Holiday","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"Raymond Briggs' classic comic book has all of his trademark humour and an endearingly grumpy Father Christmas","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34759/9780723277972.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34759","title":"Father Christmas","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"For poor Father Christmas, December 24th is the hardest night of work in the year. Raymond Briggs follows him on his wonderfully grumpy and funny journey, revealing some beautifully illustrated moments of joy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35544/fungus-the-bogeyman-book-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35544","title":"Fungus the Bogeyman","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"This sophisticated cartoon-strip picture book for older children follows one day in the life of Fungus, a morose bogeyman who scares humans - but starts wondering what it's really all for? This is Briggs at his subversive and entertaining finest.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35545/the-man.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35545","title":"The Man","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"The Man is a dialogue between a boy, John, and a tiny naked man who appears in the middle of the night, demanding clothes. The book perfectly captures an enchanting friendship with its message of kindness and intolerance of prejudice.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35546/gentleman-jim.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35546","title":"Gentleman Jim","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"The life of toilet attendant Jim Bloggs is pretty dreary and his great wish is to escape. Will he manage to do so? Briggs' story is funny and uplifting, with beautiful, delicate illustrations - a charming story for dreamers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35547/jim-and-the-beanstalk.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35547","title":"Jim and the Beanstalk","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"This is a fun, engaging re-telling of the original folklore story of Jack and the Beanstalk, which also doubles as a clever sequel - an excellent picture book for early readers.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35548/the-bear.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35548","title":"The Bear","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"Young Tilly is delighted when a polar bear clambers through her bedroom window one night - but are mischievous polar bears really ideal domestic pets? The Bear is a warm story about kindness, caring, and letting go.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35556/ethel-and-ernest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35556","title":"Ethel & Ernest","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"Ethel & Ernest tells the story of Raymond Briggs' parents, from 1928 to their deaths in the 70s - spanning a period of great social change for the country. Although your eyes will mist up by the end, you'll also...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35557/when-the-wind-blows.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35557","title":"When the Wind Blows","author":"by Raymond Briggs","description":"Jim and Hilda are your typical couple, living in rural England. When warned of a nuclear strike, they resurrect a 'wartime spirit' - surely everything will be all right in the end? This graphic novel is powerful, heartbreaking and educational.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 13+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24860/elephant-bad-baby.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24860","title":"The Elephant and the Bad Baby","author":"by Elfrida Vipont & Raymond Briggs","description":"One day, an elephant offers a baby a ride through the town, and the set off on a great adventure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0+"}]}
{"id":441,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/441/","title":"Babette Cole: some favourites","list_description":"When Babette Cole died at the beginning of this year (2017), many authors and fans went into mourning - she was a unique and joyful voice in children's books. Unafraid to tackle big and tricky issues with a light, hilarious touch, Babette was also prolific - creating over 70 books throughout her career. Her fantastically detailed illustrations have been just as big a part of that achievement as her words.  Unfortunately, we don't have space to list all of Babette's books, so below are just a few that we love to bits - whether that's because they broke ground at the time, had something to say, or just made us laugh really, really hard.  Make a donation in memory of Babette Cole","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31147/prince-cinders.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31147","title":"Prince Cinders","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"Prince Cinders leads a hard life, bullied by his three big hairy brothers - that is, until one Saturday night when Cinders' luck changes","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/28148/a-dose-of-dr-dog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/28148","title":"A Dose of Dr Dog","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"The focus on tropical diseases means A Dose of Doctor Dog is not as educational in its focus as the first in the series, Doctor Dog, but it also means that Babette Cole’s anarchic sense of humour can be fully...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31576/9780747599340-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31576","title":"The Enchanted Pony","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"The story cleverly combines every young girl’s favourite themes, magic and ponies, to create an exciting adventure","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33279/9780140555264-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33279","title":"Princess Smartypants","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"Princess Smartypants does not want to get married. She enjoys being a Ms. But being a rich and pretty princess means that all the princes want her to become their wife.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35462/princess-smartypants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35462","title":"Princess Smartypants and the Missing Princes","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"A stroppy, independent-minded princess sets out to solve the mysterious disappearance of the prospective husbands of her three best friends.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35549/dr-dog.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35549","title":"Dr Dog","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"Cole's funny illustrations demonstrate serious but easy-to-understand facts about personal hygiene, such as washing your hands, wearing a coat and not picking your nose.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35550/trouble-with-mum.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35550","title":"The Trouble with Mum","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"The trouble with mum is that she just isn't like other mums: she's a witch. Cole's colourful pictures teem with detail and inventiveness, and the raucous humour couches a moving sentiment: difference is not deficit.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35551/mummy-laid-an-egg-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35551","title":"Mummy Laid an Egg!","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"This facts-of-life book has become a classic, despite its controversial subject matter. Cole firmly believed in children's right to knowledge about their own bodies and the accompanying pictures are never vulgar.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35552/two-of-everything.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35552","title":"Two of Everything","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"Demetrius and Paula find out that they're not the only children at school with 'problem parents'. Cole is characteristically forthright and witty about the potential benefits of unsuited parents separating, but never in a way that trivialises.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35553/drop-dead.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35553","title":"Drop Dead","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"This comic take on the life cycle is balanced by the calm acceptance on the part of the narrative voice that death is simply part of a natural process. A wickedly funny and tender exploration of ageing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35554/princess-smartypants-breaks-the-rules.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35554","title":"Princess Smartypants Breaks the Rules","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"As with other books in the Princess Smartypants series, Cole has a lot to say here about gender stereotyping, but the book is more than a conveyor belt for politically correct messaging. The book is beguiling, compelling and droll.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35555/hair-in-funny-places.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35555","title":"Hair in Funny Places","author":"by Babette Cole","description":"Who else but Babette Cole would have the audacity to tackle puberty in a picture book - and the comic genius to make it work? This hilarious book is a conversation between a girl and her teddy bear about 'Mr...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"}]}
{"id":442,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/442/","title":"Books about pigs","list_description":"Pigs are often described as one of the most intelligent animals, so maybe that's why they've inspired countless children's books. From their curly tails to their oink oink sounds and their love of rolling in mud, they're perfect for picture books. But slightly older readers have also warmed to the brave exploits of swine in classics like Charlotte's Web and The Sheep-Pig.  So in celebration of this magnificent animal - and National Pig Day, of course - we've collected together just some of our favourite stories about hogs.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33085/9781780080260-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33085","title":"You're a Rude Pig, Bertie!","author":"by Claudia Boldt","description":"Bertie is a rude pig. He insults all the other animals, whilst all the time thinking what a magnificent and beautiful piglet he is. Then he meets cute rabbit Ruby.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/24511/mercy-watson-to-the-rescue.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/24511","title":"Mercy Watson to the Rescue","author":"by Kate DiCamillo","description":"Mercy the pig loves the buttery-toasty feeling she gets when the Watsons sing to her at bedtime, but she doesn't like sleeping alone.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29468/don-t-lose-pigley-wibbly-pig.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29468","title":"Don't Lose Pigley, Wibbly Pig!","author":"by Mick Inkpen","description":"Wibbly Pig and Pigley have just left a party and Wibbly's desperate to discover what's inside the mysterious parcel in his party bag.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/25341/the-sheeppig.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/25341","title":"The Sheep-Pig","author":"by Dick King-Smith","description":"When Farmer Hogget wins a piglet at the fair, he is amazed that Fly, his sheep-dog, welcomes him as one of her own pups.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30013/ladylollipop.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30013","title":"Lady Lollipop","author":"by Dick King-Smith","description":"A spoilt princess demands to have Lollipop the pig as her eighth birthday present. Lollipop and his trainer, Johnny Skinner, then have to teach the princess how to behave.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35512/piglet-called-truffle.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35512","title":"A Piglet Called Truffle","author":"by Helen Peters","description":"When Jasmine discovers a helpless piglet, she takes it upon herself to make sure it has a chance. But will Truffle be allowed to stay with Jasmine for good? This short, sweet story of a little girl looking after the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31792/bumble-ardy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31792","title":"Bumble-Ardy","author":"by Maurice Sendak","description":"Sendak explores the joyfulness and anarchic spirit of young children","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33396/9781407136370-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33396","title":"The Unbelievable Top Secret Diary of Pig","author":"by Emer Stamp","description":"Pig is quite happy on the farm - until Duck reveals the terrible truth that Farmer doesn't love him at all and is simply fattening him up to become his dinner.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33290/charlottes-web.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33290","title":"Charlotte's Web","author":"by E B White","description":"This is the tale of how a little girl named Fern - with the help of a friendly talking spider called Charlotte - saved her pig, Wilbur, from the usual fate of nice fat little pigs.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31332/9780333966259-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31332","title":"Hide-and-Seek Pig","author":"by Julia Donaldson","description":"Help Pig find Hen by lifting the flaps on each page in this fun game of hide and seek.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34026/freddy-and-the-pig.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34026","title":"Freddy and the Pig","author":"by Charlie Higson and Mark Chambers","description":"Freddy hates school and thinks that it is boring, but he comes up with clever plan. The dyslexia-friendly features make this book highly accessible."}]}
{"id":443,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/443/","title":"Counting books","list_description":"1, 2, 3... it's time to get counting! It's never too early to start learning about numbers, and books are a great way to make that fun.  We've put together a list of some of our favourite counting books to help your little ones get to grips with maths - and whether they're totting up gorillas, fruits, or even legs, they'll be enjoying themselves so much that they'll be memorising pi before you know it.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29624/cockatoos.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29624","title":"Cockatoos","author":"by Quentin Blake","description":"The eccentric and absent-minded Professor Dupont is the proud but worried owner of ten cockatoos.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 2+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32772/9781406325799-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32772","title":"One Gorilla","author":"by Anthony Browne","description":"From one gorilla to ten lemurs, Anthony Browne's beautiful counting book will delight young children and their parents alike.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30443/one-two-three-to-the-zoo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30443","title":"1, 2, 3 to the Zoo","author":"by Eric Carle","description":"Glorious two-dimensional illustrations in soft sponge-prints bring the animals to life and encourage counting without the need for words. This is a book to treasure.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 1+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34595/51wzy-1bg5l._sx411_bo1-204-203-200_.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34595","title":"Counting Lions","author":"by Katie Cotton","description":"Counting lions is a beautifully illustrated counting book with a strong conservation message. Beginning with one lion and ending with ten zebras, the text is used to carefully describe the behaviour of the animal. Stephen Walton's full page black and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/31206/1moledighole.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/31206","title":"One Mole Digging a Hole","author":"by Julia Donaldson and Nick Sharratt","description":"In this vibrant counting book, one mole digging a hole is soon joined by a troupe of gardening friends, including nine doves in gardening gloves and ten bees pruning trees.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-5"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34455/how-many-legs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34455","title":"How Many Legs?","author":"by Kes Gray","description":"How many legs are coming to my party? This is what's puzzling a little boy who has invited all sorts of weird and wonderful creatures to share his celebratory feast.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/29559/one-night-in-the-zoo.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/29559","title":"One Night in the Zoo","author":"by Judith Kerr","description":"This rhyming counting book is set in a zoo and follows the antics of the various animal inhabitants once night falls.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33771/have-you-seen-my-dragon.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33771","title":"Have You Seen My Dragon?","author":"by Steve Light","description":"A counting book that is a cut above the rest in terms of its beautiful design and style. New Yorker Steve Light brings all the shapes and sights of the city to these stunning spreads.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 3+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35334/9781909263871.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35334","title":"Dogs in Cars","author":"by Felix Massie & Emmanuelle Walker","description":"Five fluffy Eurasiers riding round in force; Six French bulldogs graceful as a prancing horse! If you can't think of many dog breeds before reading this book, you certainly will by the time you've finished it!","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34032/ten-terrible-dinosaurs.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34032","title":"Ten Terrible Dinosaurs","author":"by Paul Strickland","description":"A fun rhyming counting book which small children will love. They can learn the words, point at the pictures, count the dinosaurs and copy their comical jigging and jiving. Exuberant and amusing illustrations complement the text in this welcome reprint...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-8"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32136/9781849393089-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32136","title":"Sixes and Sevens","author":"by John Yeoman","description":"A comic counting book follows Barnaby and his raft on a ten-stop journey to Limber Lea. At each village Barnaby has to collect something and his mother advises him that if he has any difficulties, he should look in his...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"}]}
{"id":444,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/444/","title":"Bath, Book, Bed 2017: Best Bedtime Books","list_description":"But if you need some advice about which stories will send your little ones happily off into the land of nod, you've come to the right place - we've picked out ten brilliant books that will have you cuddling up and dreaming big.  So choose a book, get all snuggly under the covers, and enjoy spending that all-important time together as you say goodnight.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35517/quiet2.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35517","title":"Quiet!","author":"by Kate Alizadeh","description":"A small child takes us on an auditory tour of her home in this delightful picture of family life, ingeniously interpreted through its sounds. It's a book that radiates comfort, security, warmth and love.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35613/silver.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35613","title":"Silver","author":"by Walter de la Mare","description":"This beautifully illustrated version of Walter de la Mare's classic poem about the moon's night-time adventures is sure to help your little ones nod off, thanks to its gorgeous colours and soft rhythm.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35616/beep-beep-beep-time-for-sleep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35616","title":"Beep Beep Beep Time For Sleep!","author":"by Claire Freedman and Richard Smythe","description":"This bedtime book with a difference will appeal to digger-mad little ones as it follows the busy vehicles working on a motorway - at least, that is, until night falls and they can get some much-needed rest.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35245/goodnight-everyone.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35245","title":"Goodnight Everyone","author":"by Chris Haughton","description":"The visuals are the main appeal of this beautiful bedtime book, which explodes with a fantastic pink-and-purple starry colour palette, as well as having a simple and lulling bedtime story that will help little ones yawn along.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35612/bedtime-with-ted.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35612","title":"Bedtime with Ted","author":"by Sophy Henn","description":"Little ones will love following the story of Ted's night-time routine - from splashing in the bath with penguins to having some milk with a tiger - in this colourful board book with flaps.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2-3"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35610/baby-sparkle-bedtime.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35610","title":"Baby Sparkle: Bedtime","author":"by Dorling Kindersley","description":"This simple board book about settling down for the night is a perfect accompaniment to a regular bedtime routine for babies, especially as they can follow along with the glittery detailing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-2"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35614/dave-s-cave.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35614","title":"Dave's Cave","author":"by Frann Preston-Gannon","description":"Dave the caveman has a great cave... but could he find an even better one? This amusing picture book conveys the simple message that there's no place like home in a witty new way.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-6","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34627/a-great-big-cuddle-front-cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34627","title":"A Great Big Cuddle","author":"by Michael Rosen and Chris Riddell","description":"Beautifully illustrated poems for young children by two Children's Laureates","reading_age":"Reading Age: 4+","interest_age":"Interest level: 2+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35611/hush-little-bear-is-sleeping.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35611","title":"Hush... Little Bear is Sleeping","author":"by Surya Sajnani","description":"Baby Bear is trying to get to sleep, but will the other animals stop making so much noise? Hush... Little Bear Is Sleeping is a simple board book with soothing sounds that will help your own little cub drift off.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 0-2"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35615/hush-a-bye-bunny.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35615","title":"Hush-a-bye Bunny","author":"by Holly Surplice","description":"Full of affection and snuggles, this simple rhyme about Bunny's bedtime is just the thing for a relaxing good-night read.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5-7","interest_age":"Interest level: 3-6"}]}
{"id":445,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/445/","title":"Nature non-fiction booklist","list_description":"From flora- and fauna-themed early learning books to detailed studies of species and habitats, these non-fiction nature books are perfect for any young inquisitive minds.","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35685/deepinforest.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35685","title":"Deep in the Forest: A Seek and Find Adventure","author":"by Josef Anton and Lucie Brunelliere","description":"Each double page spread of this large nonfiction seek-and-find book features a new high colour graphic spread young readers can explore to find the missing animal.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35682/colourswalkincountry.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35682","title":"COLOURS: A Walk in the Countryside","author":"by Rosalind Beardshaw","description":"A young girl and boy play in the countryside, finding ladybirds and butterflies, birds and flowers, before sitting down for a nice picnic. Finally, after a lovely day spotting animals, they sit down beside the river and gaze up at...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 1+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35468/cool-nature.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35468","title":"Cool Nature","author":"by Amy-Jane Beer","description":"This captivating reference guide to the natural world contains just the right amount of material to inform and educate, but not overwhelm the reader. Each double-page spread focusses on a single topic and there are plenty of experiments to try...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35680/wildanimalsofthesouth.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35680","title":"Wild Animals of the South","author":"by Dieter Braun","description":"Dedicated to the animals in the southern hemisphere, this large, beautiful hardback takes us on a journey from tropical regions to the Antarctic, learning about the many wonderful animals that make the southern half of the world their home.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6-10","interest_age":"Interest level: 5-11"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35683/alphamals.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35683","title":"Alphamals A-Z","author":"by Graham Carter","description":"From A for Armadillo to N for Newt and X for X-ray Tetra (it's a fish), Alphamals combines alphabet book with poetry and sophisticated printmaking.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32288/9781406304916-1-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32288","title":"A First Book of Nature","author":"by Nicola Davies","description":"Hearld's nostalgic illustrations are the perfect accompaniment to this lovely chronicle of a child's first experiences of nature","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35185/animals-are-delicious.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35185","title":"Animals are Delicious","author":"by Sarah Hutt","description":"This box set of attractive concertina-style board books explores food chains in three different environments: the sky, the forest and the ocean. Crisp, stylish illustrations create a dynamic visual accompaniment to the simple yet informative text.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4-7"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35681/itstartswithaseed.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35681","title":"It Starts with a Seed","author":"by Laura Knowles","description":"A seed becomes a sapling, then a young tree, until, after many years, it grows into a large tree with roots and branches filling the page.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 5+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35679/earthbook.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35679","title":"The Earth Book","author":"by Jonathan Litton","description":"Learn about the inner workings of our earth, including earthquakes, volcanoes, thunderstorms and tsunamis; animal life on earth; the earth regions and the impact of humans on the planet, including information on migration, population and sustainability in this comprehensive hardback...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35684/over-and-under-the-pond.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35684","title":"Over and Under the Pond","author":"by Kate Messner","description":"A boy and his mother take their canoe out to explore the mountain pond, paddling past painted turtles, red-winged blackbirds and a moose eating lunch. Under the water, a beaver is diving for roots from the mud at the bottom...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 5+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35166/under-earth-under-water.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35166","title":"Under Earth, Under Water","author":"by Aleksandra and David Mizielinski","description":"This gorgeous large hardback explores what happens under the earth and in our oceans and seas in fantastically colourful and accessible double-page spreads. This is a really excellent example of nonfiction that is both comprehensive and fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 4+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35286/the-book-of-bees.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35286","title":"The Book of Bees","author":"by Piotr Socha and Wojciech Grajkowski","description":"This glorious book will introduce you to the bee world. It is fantastically illustrated in a cartoonish style that is big, bold and great fun.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7-9","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-9"}]}
{"id":446,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/446/","title":"Bookbuzz 2017","list_description":"Here are the amazing Bookbuzz titles for 2017! This autumn, students in Bookbuzz schools can choose their own book to keep from this list - and all schools who sign up get two sets of the Bookbuzz books for their library. There really is something for everyone, even the most reluctant of readers, with funny books, fact books, fast-paced action and mystery - and much, much more.  Click on the books below for a review and sneak preview. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35687/fiction_scream_mummysrevenge.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35687","title":"S.C.R.E.A.M.: The Mummy’s Revenge","author":"by Andrew Beasley","description":"This terrifically exciting book has it all – mystery, creepy paranormal baddies and lashings of sharp humour. You’ll be right there with Charley and Billy as they outwit the grown-ups and use their wits in their battle to beat the...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35688/the-it-girl-superstar-geek.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35688","title":"The It Girl: Superstar Geek","author":"by Katy Birchall","description":"Anna Huntley just moved to London and isn’t the most popular girl at school. But when her dad gets engaged to one of the most famous actresses in the world, Anna is thrust into the spotlight. A funny book about...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35689/cover-image.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35689","title":"The Croc and the Sock","author":"by Claire Evans","description":"Croc wakes up and there’s a sock left on his floor: a smelly, wet, dirty sock. Who has left it, and where is its matching pair? An engaging story with a rhyming text and a fun Croc puppet attached to...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35690/the-awesome-book-of-awesomeness-hi-res.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35690","title":"The Awesome Book of Awesomeness","author":"by Adam Frost","description":"This is a super cool non-fiction book, a little bit like a small version of the Guinness Book of Records. It’s packed full of strange and fascinating facts – after reading this book, you will be able to wow everyone...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35370/repro_murderinmidwinter_cvr-300dpi-.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35370","title":"Murder in Midwinter","author":"by Fleur Hitchcock","description":"On a cold, midwinter day, 13-year-old Maya spots a man holding a gun. She doesn't know exactly what's going on - but the man looked right at her, and she's been in danger ever since. A fast-paced story with nail-biting...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35742/9780552569170.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35742","title":"Where Monsters Lie","author":"by Polly Ho-Yen","description":"It all began when Effie's rabbit Buster escaped from his hutch. It was on the night of the offering - a tradition in Mivtown to keep the monsters of the loch away from the tiny village. A spooky and compelling...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35677/girlonaplane-with-black-keyline.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35677","title":"Girl on a Plane","author":"by Miriam Moss","description":"Anna has spent the summer with her family in Jordan and is on her way back to boarding school in England. Minutes into her flight, the plane is hijacked. A tense psychological thriller based on true events.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33851/9780141354156.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33851","title":"Danger is Everywhere","author":"by David O'Doherty","description":"Just like this book says, danger is everywhere. Don't worry, though, because Docter Noel Zone (yes, Docter) is an experienced Dangerologist and is here to help you in this fun and very funny book.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35686/boundless-paperback-front.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35686","title":"The Boundless","author":"by Kenneth Oppel","description":"Travelling on a gigantic train, The Boundless, Will witnesses a brutal murder - and it is up to Will to save the train. A rollercoaster of a read, with thrilling turns, dazzling characters and non-stop action.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/32186/9780552565974.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/32186","title":"Wonder","author":"by R J Palacio","description":"August ('Auggie') Pullman can't help but stand out - he was born with a severe facial deformity. Written in the first person, Wonder follows Auggie as he experiences more than the usual ups-and-downs of friendships, family and school.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35741/wickford-doom.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35741","title":"The Wickford Doom","author":"by Chris Priestley","description":"Harry and his mum have just inherited Wickford Hall from his father's family. They know it's a grand house by the sea, but when they arrive, what they find is not what they were expecting. This is an atmospheric and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 8+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33580/the-blood-guard.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33580","title":"The Blood Guard","author":"by Carter Roy","description":"Ronan discovers why his mother has filled all his spare time with classes of every kind, from martial arts to fencing. Think Anthony Horowitz meets Dan Brown and be prepared for a fast and spectacular ride in this first book...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34570/fuzzy-mud-hi-res.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34570","title":"Fuzzy Mud","author":"by Louis Sachar","description":"Marshall and Tamaya take a short cut home from school one day to avoid the school bully – through the forbidden, completely out-of-bounds woods. This is a fast-paced and exciting story of bravery, friendships, and science gone wacky.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33418/9780552571340.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33418","title":"Phoenix","author":"by S F Said","description":"Lucky is on the run and joins up with a group of aliens - refugees from the ongoing war between aliens and humans - who agree to help Lucky find his father. A thrilling space adventure, full of suspense, action,...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35739/cover.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35739","title":"Is There a Dog In This Book?","author":"by Viviane Schwarz","description":"Join the cats on this fun, interactive story as they hide from and search for the (spoiler alert) dog that is in this book. Told entirely through speech bubbles and with lots of flaps to lift, this is a book...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 6+","interest_age":"Interest level: 3+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35052/bad-guys-1.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35052","title":"The Bad Guys: Episode 1","author":"by Aaron Blabey","description":"Written like a comic book, this is a very funny story full of action and crazy characters. Reading this book is a bit like reading a cartoon - it's lots of fun and will probably make you laugh out loud.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35740/ocean-animals_cvr_final.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35740","title":"Ocean Animals","author":"by Johnna Rizzo","description":"Get close-up with ocean animals - from sharks and manatees to turtles and blobfish. This book, full of amazing underwater photography, is perfect for any animal lover or aspiring oceanographer.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 6+"}]}
{"id":447,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/447/","title":"Branford Boase Award 2017","list_description":"It's always worth keeping an eye on the Branford Boase Award. It's an excellent talent spotter, highlighting some of the best novels for young people by first-time writers.  In fact, the Branford Boase shortlist has just been announced, and a winner will be picked this summer. In the meantime, take a look at our reviews of the seven brilliant books - and let us know if you've got a favourite...","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35413/cogheart.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35413","title":"Cogheart","author":"by Peter Bunzl","description":"This ambitious debut is set in 1896, but in an alternative history - almost steampunk - with clockwork servants, silver airships and mechanical animals. Expect thrills and mystery, but also some deep messages about what it is to live and...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34975/we-are-giants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34975","title":"We Are Giants","author":"by Amber Lee Dodd","description":"Sydney's mother Amy is 124cm tall - and in her heart, Sydney longs to be a 'little person' too. She feels like she's growing too fast, and she's scared to outgrow her mum and lose their special connection. Perfect for...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35143/little-bits-of-sky.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35143","title":"Little Bits of Sky","author":"by S E Durrant","description":"Ira and Jack arrive at Skilly House, a home for foster children, and realise that life is about to get very interesting. Set against the backdrop of the 1990 poll tax strikes, this is a personal and heartfelt tale of...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9+","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34994/bubble-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34994","title":"The Bubble Boy","author":"by Stewart Foster","description":"Joe has always lived in a sterile room in a hospital. He's the 'bubble boy': documented on TV because of a rare condition, affecting his immune system, that keeps him vacuum-packed from the rest of society.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34948/beetle-boy.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34948","title":"Beetle Boy","author":"by MG Leonard","description":"When Darkus' father mysteriously disappears from London’s Natural History Museum, Darkus has to move in with his rather odd Uncle Max AND change schools. A wonderfully funny and engaging book, perfect for fans of Roald Dahl.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 9-12","interest_age":"Interest level: 9-12"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35030/girl-of-ink-and-stars.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35030","title":"The Girl of Ink and Stars","author":"by Kiran Millwood Hargrave","description":"When her closest friend disappears into the island's Forgotten Territories, Isabella Riosse volunteers to guide the search. A stunning debut, full of myth, magic and mapmaking.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35082/riverkeep.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35082","title":"Riverkeep","author":"by Martin Stewart","description":"An utterly compelling and masterful young adult fantasy, Riverkeep swallows the reader whole from the first page, immersing them in its atmospheric, watery, ghostly world and keeping them gripped to the end.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"}]}
{"id":448,"url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/children/booklists/448/","title":"Jane Austen with a twist - for children","list_description":"It's no wonder that Jane Austen's books have stood the test of time: they're funny, romantic and full of crisply perfect observations about people and they ways we all get along.  Pride and Prejudice is of course a much-loved route into Austen's works - and it's perfect for older teens. But here are other books by other authors that may appeal to children a little bit younger. ","books":[{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34481/boywatching.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34481","title":"Boywatching","author":"by Chloe Bennet","description":"This hilarious story of Chloe and her friends navigating their way through the highs and lows of teenage life is a highly entertaining read for younger teenagers","reading_age":"Reading Age: 7+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35688/the-it-girl-superstar-geek.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35688","title":"The It Girl: Superstar Geek","author":"by Katy Birchall","description":"Anna Huntley just moved to London and isn’t the most popular girl at school. But when her dad gets engaged to one of the most famous actresses in the world, Anna is thrust into the spotlight. A funny book about...","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/26833/sisterhoodoftravellingpants.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/26833","title":"The Sisterhood of the Travelling Pants","author":"by Ann Brashares","description":"Bridget, Carmen, Tibby and Lena have been inseparable all their lives and are about to embark on their first summer apart.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30829/a-most-improper-magick.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30829","title":"A Most Improper Magick","author":"by Stephanie Burgis","description":"A 21st-century take on Jane Austen's world, entertainingly viewed through the eyes of a 12-year-old heroine who discovers she has inherited her mother's magical abilities.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 10+","interest_age":"Interest level: 10+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/35250/lydia.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/35250","title":"Lydia: the wild girl of Pride and Prejudice","author":"by Natasha Farrant","description":"A spirited reimagining of Jane Austen's Pride and Prejudice, told from the perspective of Lydia, the youngest Bennet sister. It is great fun to see her thoughts on her older sisters Jane and Lizzy, plus Mr Darcy.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 11+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/33781/flirty-dancing.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/33781","title":"Flirty Dancing","author":"by Jenny McLachlan","description":"First of four books, this is smart, funny writing, engagingly balancing the serious stuff - bullying, first love, friendship - with the joy of lindy hop and aerial moves.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 12+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/30756/withering-tights.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/30756","title":"Withering Tights","author":"by Louise Rennison","description":"When Tallulah’s parents pack her off to an am-dram college - Dother Hall, she hopes she will become a toppity-top-actress type without accidentally tripping over her knees or involuntarily doing Irish dancing.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 11+","interest_age":"Interest level: 12+"},{"img":"https://artlogic-res.cloudinary.com/w_120,c_limit/ws-booktrustfileserver/usr/images/books/main_image/34792/goth-girl-wuthering-fright.jpg","url":"http://www.booktrust.org.uk/books/view/34792","title":"Goth Girl and the Wuthering Fright","author":"by Chris Riddell","description":"While famous writers and their pampered pets gather for a literary dog show at Ghastly-Gorm Hall, Goth Girl Ada has a mystery to solve. This high-speed adventure is penned and illustrated by the children's laureate, Chris Riddell.","reading_age":"Reading Age: 8+","interest_age":"Interest level: 7-12"}]}
